
#bookname=indian-epigraphical-glossary (sa-en)
#stripmethod=keep
#sametypesequence=h
#description=Data from https://www.sanskrit-lexicon.uni-koeln.de/ as on 2026-04-02

आबाध|आबाधः<BR>ābādha (CII 1), illness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आबाधा<BR>ābādhā (EI 15), same as bādhā or vādhā; obstacle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अबातमाल<BR>abātamāla, abātamālā, Prakrit; meaning doubtful (cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XV, p. 272; ZDMG, Vol. XL, pp. 345-46); explained<BR>as a kind of sculptured slab (LL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्दप<BR>abdapa (IA 16), the entrance of the sun into the<BR>Aries (Meṣa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्दपूजा<BR>abda-pūjā (EI 32), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आब्दार्खानह्<BR>ābdārkhānah (IE 8-3; EI 31), Persian; ‘water-house’;<BR>cf. Pānīy-āgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्धि|अब्धिः<BR>abdhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आब्दिकश्राद्ध<BR>ābdika-śrāddha (CII 4), an annual rite in honour of a<BR>dead person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभाव्य<BR>ābhāvya (EI 11, 16), income or proceeds; cf. rāja-rāja-<BR>puruṣ ādibhiḥ svaṃ svam = ābhāvyaṃ parihartavyam; see also rāja-<BR>bhāvya, etc. Cf. ‘the income (ābhāvya) derived from the<BR>loads on bullocks going on their way or coming to Nāḍlāi’<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 36).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभय|अभयं<BR>abhaya (EI 24), pose of hand (mudrā); see abhaya-mudrā.<BR>(SITI), place of security to persons in distress; called<BR>añjinānpugal-idam in Tamil. Cf. abhaya-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभयहस्त<BR>abhaya-hasta (SII 2), pose of hand known as abhaya-mudrā<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभयमुद्रा<BR>abhaya-mudrā (HA), pose of hand offering protection, in<BR>which the palm of the right hand, facing the devotee, is held<BR>with fingers upwards. Cf. abhaya-hasta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभयशासन<BR>abhaya-śāsana (EI 12, 27; SITI), ‘grant of shelter’,<BR>‘charter of security’; a deed offering protection; a grant<BR>recording the provision of shelter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभिगामिकगुण<BR>ābhigāmika-guṇa (CII 3, 4), certain attractive qualities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिघात|अभिघातः<BR>abhighāta (LP), an injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिहार|अभिहारः<BR>abhihāra (CII 1), a reward.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिज्ञान|अभिज्ञानं<BR>abhijñāna (LP), a token by which the identity of a<BR>person is recognised.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिकार<BR>abhikāra, cf. kṛt-ābhikāra (CII 1), probably, one who has<BR>committed an offence under the instigation of another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिलेखितक<BR>abhilekhitaka (IE 8-8), probably, a written complaint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिनव|अभिनवः<BR>abhinava (EI 5; IA 18), name of a tax; cf. abhinava-mārga-<BR>ṇaka-prabhṛti-sarv-ādāyair = upetaḥ, epithet of the gift village. It<BR>may also mean ‘new’ and the reference may be to the new<BR>mārgaṇaka tax. See abhinava-mārgaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिनवमार्गणक<BR>abhinava-mārgaṇaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 264,<BR>note 1), name of a tax. See mārgaṇaka, mārg-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिप्रेत|अभिप्रेतं<BR>abhipreta (CII 1), intention.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभीर|आभीरः<BR>Ābhīra (IE 8-3), member of the cowherd community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिरक्त<BR>abhirakta (CII 1), beloved one.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेक|अभिषेकः<BR>abhiṣeka (EI 4), coronation; cf. abhiṣeka-kkāṇi, abhiṣeka-<BR>kkāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; presents offered to the<BR>king at the time of his coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेकमण्दप<BR>abhiṣeka-maṇdapa (SITI), a hall where ceremonial baths<BR>are taken; the coronation hall; also called tiru-mañjana-<BR>śālai and kuḻikkum-iḍam in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेकनामन्<BR>abhiṣeka-nāman (SITI), the name or title assumed by a<BR>king at the time of his coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषिक्त<BR>abhiṣikta (CII 1), cf. dvādaśa-varṣ-ābhiṣikta, ‘when one has<BR>been anointed twelve years’, ‘when twelve years have elapsed<BR>from one's coronation’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, pp. 333 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभीष्टदेवता<BR>abhīṣṭa-devatā (IA 18), same as iṣṭa-devatā; the favourite<BR>deity; the tutelary deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिस्थान<BR>abhisthāna, correctly abhiṣṭhāna; used in the sense of<BR>adhiṣṭhāna, ‘the residence’, ‘a city’, or ‘the headquarters’.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 219.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभित्वरमाण<BR>Abhitvaramāṇa, Abhitvaramāṇaka (IE 8-3; EI 31; HD),<BR>the letter-carrier or a special kind of messenger. Cf<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321 (dūta-praiṣaṇika-gamāgamik-ābhi-<BR>tvaramāṇaka); Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 125-26.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभोग|आभोगः<BR>ābhoga (IE 8-4), a territorial unit; similar to bhoga;<BR>cf. Gorajj-ābhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्र|अभ्रं<BR>abhra (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यङ्ग|अभ्यंग|अभ्यंगः|अभ्यङ्गः<BR>abhyaṅga (IA 22), smearing the body with oil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तर|आभ्यंतर<BR>Ābhyantara (HD), an officer specially intimate or in close<BR>contact with the king. Cf. Antaraṅga. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII.<BR>426. But cf. also Ābhyantarika, Abhyantar-opasthāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरभाण्डाराधिकारिन्<BR>Abhyantara-bhāṇḍār-ādhikārin, cf. Bhītara-bhaṇdār-ādhikārin<BR>(IE 8-3; EI 28).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरादाय<BR>ābhyantar-ādāya, cf. bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya (IE 8-5); internal<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-003" target="_blank">Page-003+ 40</a>]<BR>revenue income of a village; probably, taxes payable to the<BR>village authorities as against those payable to the king. Cf.<BR>antar-āya, abhyantara-siddhi, antaḥ-kara, etc. See bāhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धि<BR>abhyantara-siddhi, abhyantara-siddhika (IE 8-5; EI 20, 22),<BR>same as ābhyantara-siddhi; internal income or revenue, or taxes<BR>payable to the village authorities as against those payable to the<BR>king; cf. tribhog-ābhyantara-siddhi, bāhy-ābhyantara-siddhi, bāhy-<BR>ābhyantar-ādāya; also sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi (EI 20), and antaḥ-<BR>siddhika (CII 4), a privilege of the donee of rent-free land.<BR>According to some (CII 4), it refers to the privilege of the<BR>donee offering full power of adjudication in law-suits.<BR>But expressions like tribhog-ābhyantara-siddhi (q. v.) render it<BR>doubtful. See bāhya, siddhi, siddh-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरसिद्धि<BR>ābhyantara-siddhi (CII 4), same as abhyantara-siddhi;<BR>explained by some as ‘the powers of adjudication’; probably,<BR>taxes payable to the village authorities as against those payable<BR>to the king. See abhyantara-siddhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरिक<BR>Ābhyantarika (IE 8-3), a guard of the inner apartments<BR>of the palace; cf. Ābhyantarikā. See Ābhyantara, Abhyantar-<BR>opasthāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरिका<BR>Ābhyantarikā, a female guard of the inner apartment of the<BR>palace; probably also a concubine (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरोपस्थायक<BR>Abhyantar-opasthāyaka (LL), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यासिन्<BR>Abhyāsin (SII 13), a student.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यवहारमण्डप<BR>abhyavahāra-maṇḍapa (EI 3), dining hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्युपागम<BR>abhyupāgama (IE 8-8), arrival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यूष|अभ्यूषः<BR>abhyūṣa (EI 7), a cake.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्युत्सर्पित<BR>abhyutsarpita (CII 2-1), same as utsarpita; erected.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्युत्थित<BR>abhyutthita, cf. abbhuṭṭhio khāmavo (HA), obeisance to<BR>one's teacher (i. e. a Jain monk) with formal query about the<BR>his health and confession of one's own weakness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्ज|अब्जः<BR>abja (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्जदल<BR>abja-dala (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आबोटी<BR>Āboṭī (EI 11), an inferior class of Brāhmaṇas in Rajasthan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्क्कम्|आचन्द्रार्कम्<BR>ā-candr-ārkkam (SITI), ‘so long as the moon and the<BR>sun last’; ‘in perpetuity’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचलप्रवृत्ति<BR>acala-pravṛtti (SII 11-1), cf. ‘was administering Pandi-<BR>goḻa as acala-pravṛtti’; a kind of tenure; probably, a<BR>permanent holding. See vṛtti, the same as pravṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार|आचारः<BR>ācāra (IE 8-5; EI 30), a custom or customary law.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-004" target="_blank">Page-004+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 20), religious practice, being regarded as five in<BR>number.<BR>Cf. navanavaty-ācāreṇa (LP), ‘99 per cent’, i. e. ‘cer-<BR>tainly’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचारपात्र<BR>ācāra-pātra (EI 30), same as sthiti-pātra, ācāra-sthiti-pātra,<BR>etc.; a document relating to customary laws.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचारस्थितिपात्र<BR>ācāra-sthiti-pātra (IE 8-5), same as ācāra-pātra, etc.;<BR>regulation regarding customary laws; cf. sthiti-pātra, a charter<BR>relating to customary laws (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्य|आचार्यः|आचार्य्य|आचार्य्यः<BR>Ācārya (EI 33; BL), title of a religious teacher; used<BR>commonly by the Buddhists and Jains (LL; SII 1).<BR>(CII 3; EI 32; ML), a spiritual guide or teacher; a<BR>preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समे<BR>Same as Sthān-ācārya (EI 17), a temple priest.<BR>(EI 8; IA 14), an architect; used in the sense of ‘a<BR>master’, i. e. ‘a master-mason’; cf. Ācāri (EI 17), an artisan.<BR>Pāli Ācariya is explained as ‘a master goldsmith’ in the P. T. S.<BR>Pāli-Eng. Dict.<BR>(LL), title of a sculptor.<BR>(HA; IA 19), Jain; a Sādhu who has the right of both<BR>reading the sacred texts publicly and explaining them<BR>authoritatively.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यकुल<BR>ācāryakula (LL), a Buddhist temple; cf. devakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यपीठ<BR>ācārya-pīṭha (EI 16), a holy site; a site sanctified by a<BR>religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यपूजना<BR>ācārya-pūjanā (SITI), honorarium payable to priests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आच्छन्न|आच्छन्नं<BR>ācchanna (EI 30), a word of doubtful import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चु<BR>accu (IE 8-8; SITI), Tamil; name of a coin; cf. ānai-<BR>accu, nall-ānai-accu, paḻamudal-ānai-accu, paḻañjalāgai-accu, paducca-<BR>lāgai-accu, amudan-accu, uṇḍi-accu, etc. Cf. also pañcālav-accu<BR>(SITI), name of a coin probably struck by the body called<BR>pañcālattār or pañcakarmāra; uṇḍiy-accu (SITI); vaḻudiy-accu-<BR>varggam (SITI), a group of taxes payable in Pāṇḍya coins;<BR>yakki-accu (SITI), from Sanskrit Yakṣī; name of a coin current<BR>in the Koṅgu country.<BR>(EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुपन्नाय<BR>accu-pannāya (EI 16), department of taxation or coining.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुपन्नायदधिष्ठायक<BR>Accupannāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; superinten-<BR>dent of the revenue from mints; sometimes also called Mahā-<BR>sāmantādhipati, Mahāpradhāna, Bhānasavĕrgaḍĕ, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुवरि<BR>accuvari (SITI), Tamil; probably the same as pŏnvari;<BR>the duty payable for minting gold into coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आछु<BR>āchu (CII 4), same as āsu, the name of a coin; cf. Tamil<BR>accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचित<BR>acita (SITI), damage; injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आड<BR>āḍa, aḍḍa (CITD), Telugu; a measure of capacity equal<BR>to 2 mānikas or one-eighth of a tūm; half, especially half of a<BR>fanam or a certain measure called kuñcamu; a weight represent-<BR>ing the eighteenth portion of a varāha (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदान|आदानं<BR>ādāna (IE 8-5; EI 12; CII 4), a levy or impost; same<BR>as ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आडाणक<BR>āḍāṇaka (LP), same as aḍḍāṇaka; cf. āḍāṇake muktā,<BR>mortgaged; valitāya āḍāṇake muktam, Gujarātī vaḻat dāṇ mukyuṃ,<BR>‘something morgaged, the produce of which will pay off the<BR>debt in course of time’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदत्त<BR>ādatta (IE 8-5), adattā (EI 33), ādattā (EI 28), a tax of<BR>uncertain import; probably, interest or fine on arrears of tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदाय|आदायः<BR>ādāya (EI 33), income or impost; cf. bhūta-bhaviṣyad-<BR>vartamāna-niḥśeṣ-ādāya-sahita (IE 8-5); cf. also viseṇim-ādāya<BR>(EI 21), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्भुत|अद्भुतं|अद्भुतः<BR>adbhuta (EI 33), same as utpāta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्भुतधर्म|अद्भुतधर्मः<BR>adbhuta-dharma, cf. abbhuta-dhamma (EI 33), Buddhist. Cf.<BR>Childers, Pāli-Eng. Dict., s. v.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्भुतशान्ति|अद्भुतशान्तिः<BR>adbhuta-śānti (EI 33), a ceremony to avert evil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डचिन्न<BR>aḍḍa-cinna (EI 18), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डग<BR>aḍḍaga, aḍduga (CITD), Telugu; half a fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डाणक<BR>aḍḍāṇaka (LP), a morgaged thing; cf. gṛh-āḍḍāṇaka-patra<BR>(LP), deed for mortgaging a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदेशकारिन्<BR>Ādeśakārin (EI 10), an officer or agent, or a representative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदेशनैबन्धिक<BR>Ādeśa-naibandhika (EI 7; CII 4), official designation<BR>indicating the recorder of orders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदेय<BR>ādeya (EI 7, 12, 15; CII 3), ‘what is to be taken or<BR>levied’; a fiscal term meaning the same thing as ādāya, i. e.<BR>income or impost; dues (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आढ<BR>āḏha (IE 8-6), same as āḍhika or āḍhaka; a measure<BR>of capacity; a land measure also called āḍhavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आढा<BR>āḏhā (IE 8-6), Bengali form of āḍhaka and āḍhavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधः|अध<BR>adhaḥ, cf. s-ādha-ūrdhva (IE 8-5); what is below the<BR>surface of the ground; root-crops.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आढक|आढकं|आढकः<BR>āḍhaka (IE 8-6; EI 27), a measure of capacity; often<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-006" target="_blank">Page-006+ 40</a>]<BR>regarded as equal to 264 handfuls and to one-fourth of a droṇa;<BR>16 to 20 seers according to Bengali authors; also used as a<BR>shortened form of āḍhavāpa or ādhakavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधान|आधानं<BR>ādhāna, cf. dān-ādhāna-vikraya (IE 8-5); mortgaging. Cf.<BR>n = ādheyaṃ na ca vikreyam (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 218).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधवाप<BR>ādhavāpa, also called āḍhakavāpa (IE 8-6), ‘an area of land<BR>requiring one āḍhaka measure of seed grains for being sown’; a<BR>land measure which was not the same in all ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधि|अधिः<BR>Adhi (LP), contraction of Adhikārin, regarded by some<BR>as ‘a revenue officer like the Māmlatdār’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधि|अधिः<BR>Adhi, Ādhi (IE 8-1; 8-8), shortened forms of Adhikaraṇika<BR>or Ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधि|आधिः<BR>ādhi (SII 2; LP), a mortgage or deposit; ādhau kṛtam,<BR>‘mortgaged’; cf. ādhau muktam, ādhau dattam. Cf. vinaṣṭ-ādhi-<BR>sakta (LP), used in connection with a lost thing which had<BR>been given in mortgage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिक|अधिकं|अधिकः<BR>adhika (EI 3), intercalary [month].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकाक्षर<BR>adhik-ākṣara (LP), ‘with words in excess’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकपडि<BR>adhika-paḍi (CITD), Sanskrit-Telugu; an extra allowance<BR>in food (grain, salt, vegetables and all that is required to pre-<BR>pare a meal, including firewood), sometimes also in money,<BR>granted to servants, friends or poor people.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकार|अधिकारः<BR>Adhikāra, cf. Tamil Adigāram (EI 25); same as Adhikārin<BR>(SII 1), explained as ‘a magistrate’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारमेलेळुत्तु<BR>adhikāra-mel-el13uttu (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; revisional<BR>order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरण|अधिकरणं<BR>adhikaraṇa (IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28), an office; cf. rājakule ='dhi-<BR>karaṇasya, apparently referring to an office. See adhikaraṇ-āva-<BR>dhāraṇā, ‘official investigation’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 267).<BR>(EI 24), a court or department.<BR>(EI 30), a law-court.<BR>(SITI), a class of law courts; probably, the chief court.<BR>(EI 30, 31), an administrative office or a board of<BR>administration.<BR>(EI 31), a district.<BR>(SII 2), same as Adhikārin, a magistrate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरणदण्ड<BR>adhikaraṇa-daṇḍa (SITI), fine imposed by the adhikaraṇa<BR>or law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरणलेखक|अधिकरणलेखकः<BR>Adhikaraṇa-lekhaka (EI 30), a scribe pertaining to a law-<BR>court or office.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-007" target="_blank">Page-007+ 40</a>]<BR>(HD), the official recorder or scribe [who drew up deeds of<BR>sale and the like after having measured the land to be sold].<BR>Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 38; Viṣṇu Dh. S., VII, 3.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरणिक|अधिकरणिकः<BR>Adhikaraṇika, Ādhikaraṇika (IE 8-1; EI 28), an officer<BR>belonging to or in charge of an adhikaraṇa or office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारवर्त्तना<BR>adhikāra-varttanā (SITI), customary payments made to<BR>an officer at stipulated periods; probably the same as Sanskrit-<BR>Tamil adhikāra-ppeṟu, adhikāra-ppŏn, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारिक<BR>Adhikārika, Ādhikārika (IE 8-3; EI 2, 23, 28; CII 4;<BR>BL; HD), ‘an officer’; same as Adhikārin, Niyogika, Adhyakṣa, etc.,<BR>regarded as meaning a minister, magistrate, superintendent,<BR>governor or director. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 184.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारिमुख्य<BR>Adhikāri-mukhya (EI 33), explained as ‘the chief minister’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारिन्<BR>Adhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 28; BL), ‘an officer’; same as<BR>Ādhikārika; cf. Kannaḍa Vĕrgaḍĕ, etc., and Sanskrit Adhyākṣa,<BR>meaning a superintendent, governor or director.<BR>(ASLV), explained as ‘a special officer or royal agent’.<BR>(EI 7), explained as ‘a minister’.<BR>(SII 2), explained as ‘a magistrate’.<BR>Cf. Viḍaiy-adhikāri, Viḍaiyil-adhikāri (SITI), an officer issu-<BR>ing royal orders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकृत|अधिकृतः<BR>Adhikṛta (EI 23, 24), ‘an officer’; cf. Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिमहाराज<BR>Adhimahārāja (EI 15), royal title. Cf. Adhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिपति|अधिपतिः<BR>Adhipati (LL), a king; cf. pati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधिपत्र<BR>ādhi-patra (LP), a mortgage bond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिराज<BR>Adhirāja (IE 8-2), sometimes used as an imperial title,<BR>but sometimes as the title of a feudatory. Cf. Adhimahārāja.<BR>(BL), title of a subordinate ruler.<BR>(LL), designation of a supreme king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिराजराज<BR>Adhirājarāja (EI 9), royal title. Cf. Rājarāja, Rājādhirāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिराज्य|अधिराज्यं<BR>adhirājya (EI 24), a realm or kingdom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधिराज्य|आधिराज्यं<BR>ādhirājya (CII 3), a derivative from the title Adhirāja;<BR>supreme sovereignty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिस्थान<BR>adhisthāna, adhiṣṭhāna (CII 1), cf. dharm-ādhisthāna, dharm-<BR>ādhiṣṭhāna, ‘the establishment of morality’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिष्ठान|अधिष्ठानं<BR>adhiṣṭhāna (IE 8-3; EI 24, 28, 31; LL), the capital or<BR>headquarters of an administrative unit; a city or town; the<BR>chief city. See abhisthāna.<BR>(EI 9), probably, residence.<BR>(EI 8), same as sthāna.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-008" target="_blank">Page-008+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 24), cf. adhiṣṭhānam, ‘under the supervision of’.<BR>(SITI), the base of the vimāna in a temple; a seat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिष्ठानाधिकरण<BR>adhiṣṭhān-ādhikaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 23; BL), administrative<BR>office or board at the headquarters of a territorial unit;<BR>office of the administrators of a city; the city office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिष्ठायक<BR>Adhiṣṭhāyaka (EI 16), official designation; same as<BR>Adhyakṣa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिवास|अधिवासः<BR>adhivāsa, cf. adhivāsa-sakta-cāturvarṇya-samakṣam (LP), ‘in<BR>the presence of the people of the four castes living in the<BR>vicinity’; cf. adhivāsa-saktīya (LP); neighbours.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्वप<BR>Adhvapa (EI 20), official designation; same as Mārgapati,<BR>etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यक्ष|अध्यक्षः<BR>Adhyakṣa (EI 24; CII 4), the head of a department; the<BR>superintendent of a department; a superintendent or director;<BR>sometimes mentioned in the list of officials (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXI, p. 80). Cf. Mahādhyakṣa.<BR>(IA 20), explained as the Dūtaka or Ājñapti, i. e.<BR>executor of grants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यक्षप्रचार<BR>Adhyakṣa-pracāra (EI 12, 15), a list of superintendents of<BR>departments; probably also a notice setting forth the dis-<BR>tribution of the Adhyakṣas in various departments and stations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यापक|अध्यापकः<BR>Adhyāpaka (EI 32), a teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यातम्<BR>a-dhyātam, ‘without any consideration or hesitation’<BR>(Select Inscriptions, p. 239).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययन|अध्ययनं<BR>adhyayana (SII 1), study of the Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययनभट्ट<BR>Adhyayana-bhaṭṭa (IA 12), assistant officiating priest<BR>(also called Sādhācārya) at the temple at Rāmeśvaram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययनाङ्ग<BR>adhyayan-āṅga (SITI), same as adhyayana-vṛtti (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययनवृत्ति<BR>adhyayana-vṛtti (SITI), tax-free land endowed for reciting<BR>the Vedas in temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्येतृ<BR>adhyetṛ (EI 32), a student.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदि|आदिः<BR>ādi (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिकार<BR>ādikāra (CII 1), an initiator; one who starts a practice or<BR>to do a particular deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिकर्तृ|आदिकर्त्तृ<BR>Ādikartṛ (CII 3), ‘an originator’; epithet of the Jain<BR>Tīrthaṅkaras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिराज|आदिराजः<BR>Ādirāja (EI 12), an ancient king, e. g., Bharata, Nala,<BR>Nahuṣa, etc.; founder of a royal family (Select Inscriptions,<BR>pp. 412, 415).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदित्य|आदित्यः<BR>āditya (IE 8-2; EI 33), ending of royal titles like Vikramā-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-009" target="_blank">Page-009+ 40</a>]<BR>ditya, Kramāditya, Mahendrāditya, etc., probably popularised<BR>by the Imperial Guptas in the fourth century A. D.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदित्यकाच<BR>āditya-kāca (EI 32), probably, the jewel called sūryakānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिवराहद्रम्म<BR>ādivarāha-dramma (EI 30; CII 4), name of a coin (dramma)<BR>styled after Ādivarāha, i. e. Pratīhāra Bhoja I (c. 836-85 A. D.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्रि|अद्रिः<BR>adri (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आद्वलिश<BR>ādvaliśa (IA 17), or dvaliśa; regarded as a word of<BR>doubtful meaning; but really, a geographical name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आद्यमाष<BR>ādya-māṣa, the original māṣa 5 ratis in weight, later its<BR>weight being regarded as 6, 7 or 10 ratis (JNSI, Vol. XV,<BR>p. 139). See māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग|अगः<BR>aga (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR>(SII 3), earth or land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगम|आगमं|आगमः<BR>āgama (SII 1), a doctrine; cf. Lākul-āgama (EI 32),<BR>the doctrine of Lakula (Lakulīśa). Cf. āgama-samaya.<BR>Cf. s-āgama-nirgama-praveśa (IE 8-5), ‘together with<BR>approaches, ingress and egress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगमनिगमदान<BR>āgama-nigama-dāna (LP), tax for importing and exporting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगमार्ग<BR>agamārga (SITI), a variety of dance performed in the<BR>presence of the gods in temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगमसमय<BR>āgama-samaya, cf. Lākul-āgama-samaya (EI 32), the<BR>tenets of Lakula's doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगामिन्<BR>āgāmin (IE 8-5; EI 19; SITI), future income, future bene-<BR>fits; one of the 8 kinds of rights in the property; cf. aṣṭa-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगर<BR>agara (EI 19), a corrupt form of agrahāra, often noticed<BR>in Tamil inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगरब्रह्मदेय<BR>agara-brahmadeya (SITI), village granted to Brāhmaṇas;<BR>also called agara (agrahāra) and brahmadeya. See agara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगरप्प<BR>agara-ppaṟṟu (SITI), Tamil; same as agara or agrahāra;<BR>land granted to Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगसालि<BR>Agasāli (EI 28), a goldsmith; same as Akṣaśālin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आघाट|आघाटः<BR>āghāṭa (EI 16), boundary; cf. āghāṭana, āghāṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आघाटन<BR>āghāṭana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 264, text line 42), same<BR>as āghāṭa, boundary; see also āghāṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आघाटी<BR>āghāṭī (EI 23), same as āghāṭa; boundary; see also<BR>āghāṭana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अघोष|अघोषः<BR>aghoṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’ [being the number of surds<BR>in the Sanskrit alphabet].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्नि|अग्निः<BR>agni (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निचयन<BR>agni-cayana (EI 32; IA 19), a sacrificial rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निचित्<BR>Agnicit (SII 2), title of a Brāhmaṇa. cf. agni-cayana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निहोत्र|अग्निहोत्रं|अग्निहोत्रः<BR>agnihotra (EI 22; CII 3, 4), offerings to fire; a particular<BR>sacrifice, often mentioned as one of the five sacrificial rites<BR>(mahāyajña) which are the daily duties of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निहोत्रिन्<BR>Agnihotrin (CII 4), epithet of a Brāhmaṇa performing<BR>the agnihotra sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निकार्य|अग्निकार्य्य|अग्निकार्य्यं<BR>agni-kārya (EI 33; SII 3), fire-oblation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निकुल<BR>Agni-kula, ‘a family, the progenitor of which was born<BR>from the fire pit of a sage’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 162,<BR>for a 12th century ‘Fire family’ in the Nanded District,<BR>Maharashtra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निकुण्ड|अग्निकुंड<BR>agni-kuṇḍa (CII 4), fire-pit; an emblem of the worship<BR>of the Fire or Sun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निस्कन्ध<BR>agni-skandha (CII 1), masses of fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निष्ठा<BR>agniṣṭhā (SITI), firewood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निस्थितिका<BR>agni-sthitikā, fire-place (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निष्टोम|अग्निष्टोमः<BR>agniṣṭoma (CII 3), a particular sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्न्याहित<BR>Agnyāhita (EI 15), same as Āhitāgni, ‘a Brāhmaṇa per-<BR>petually maintaining and consecrating the sacred fire in his<BR>house’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्र|अग्रं|अग्रः<BR>agra (EI 24), same as agra-bhāga; the king's share.<BR>(CII 1), cf. anyatra agreṇa parākrameṇa, ‘without a great<BR>effort’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रभाग|अग्रभागः<BR>agra-bhāga (CII 2-1; ML), the principal share; same<BR>as agra, agra-pratyāya, the king's share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रभागप्रत्यंश<BR>agrabhāga-pratyaṃśa (CII 2-1), same as agra-bhāga, agra-<BR>pratyaṃśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रभृति<BR>agra-bhṛti (CII 1), a superior personage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रधर्मराजिका<BR>agra-dharmarājikā (ML), the chief Dharmarājikā (a<BR>stūpa enshrining the relies of the Dharmarāja or Buddha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगहर<BR>agahara, agāhara, āgahara (Chamba), corruptions of<BR>agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहर<BR>Agrahara (EI 24), a collector of the king's share. See<BR>agra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहार|अग्रहारः<BR>agrahāra (IE 8-4; EI 30; CII 4; SII 1; HRS; Chamba), rent-<BR>free land given to Brāhmaṇas; a rent-free village; a Brāhmaṇa<BR>village; sometimes suffixed to names of localities especially<BR>in South India. It was primarily, ‘a rent-free village in<BR>the possession of Brāhmaṇas’; but there are occasional references<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-011" target="_blank">Page-011+ 40</a>]<BR>to dev-āgrahāra (rent-free holding in the possession of a deity),<BR>vaiśy-āgrahāra (rent-free holding in the possession of the<BR>Vaiśyas), etc.; sometimes spelt agrāhāra (CII 3). See mah-<BR>āgrahāra, brahmapurī, caturvedi-maṅgala, etc.; also aṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारप्रदेयांश<BR>agrahāra-pradey-āṃśa (EI 33), a small rent payable for<BR>land granted to Brāhmaṇas and declared rent-free.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारिक<BR>Agrahārika, Āgrahārika (IE 3-8; EI 23; HD; CII 3; etc.),<BR>the owner of an agrahāra; sometimes probably, the superin-<BR>tendent of agrahāras; same as Agrahārin. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXIV, p. 127.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारिन्<BR>Agrahārin, Agrahārīṇa (EI 23, 24), the holder of an<BR>agrahāra; headman or owner of an agrahāra village. Cf.<BR>Agrahārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारीणमहत्तर<BR>Agrahārīṇa-mahattara (EI 24), headman among the<BR>Agrahārīṇas, i. e. owners of an agrahāra (rent-free village in the<BR>possession of Brāhmaṇas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आग्रहायणी<BR>āgrahāyaṇī (EI 8), Mārgaśīrṣa su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रज|अग्रजः<BR>agraja (EI 23), the elder brother (or cousin); rarely<BR>used wrongly in the sense of ‘the eldest son’ (EI 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रजन्मन्<BR>agrajanman (EI 9), same as agraja (q. v.); wrongly used to<BR>mean ‘the eldest son’ instead of ‘the elder brother’ (cf.<BR>agraja).<BR>(EI 24), a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमहादेवी<BR>Agra-mahādevī (SITI), chief queen of a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमहामहिषी<BR>Agra-mahāmahiṣī (IE 8-2), title of a chief queen; cf. Mahiṣī,<BR>Agra-mahiṣī, Mahāmahiṣī, Agra-mahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमहिषी<BR>Agra-mahiṣī (IE 8-2; EI 22; LL; ML), designation of<BR>the chief queen; cf. Mahiṣī, Agra-mahādevī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमण्डप<BR>agra-maṇḍapa (SITI), front hall of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रप्र<BR>agra-pra, āda, same as tala-vṛtti (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI,<BR>p. 166, note 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रप्रत्यंश<BR>agra-pratyaṃśa (EI 23; CII 2-1; ML), principal share;<BR>same as agra-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रप्रत्याय<BR>agra-pratyāya (EI 23), principal share or income; same<BR>as agra-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रशाला<BR>agra-śālā (SII 3), a temple-kitchen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आग्रयण|आग्रयणं|आग्रयणः<BR>āgrayaṇa (EI 7), the first Soma libation at the agniṣṭoma<BR>sacrifice; oblation consisting of first-fruits at the end of the<BR>rainy season.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रिक<BR>agrika (LP), ‘the previous one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रिकपाया<BR>agrika-pāyā (LP), original foundation; cf. Gujarātī<BR>pāyā, foundation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रोनोमोइ<BR>Agronomoi (IE 8-3), Greek; probably the same as Rajjuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहाड<BR>āhāḍa (EI 1), probably, a quarry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहंवीर<BR>Ahaṃvīra, see Amīra. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 178.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहन्<BR>ahan (CII 3), ‘a day’; used to denote the solar, or more<BR>properly civil, day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहार|आहारः<BR>āhāra (IE 8-4; EI 27; CII 1, 3, 4), a district; cf. āharaṇī.<BR>Cf. grām-āhāra (IE 8-4), a group of villages.<BR>(IA 17), cf. s-āhāra in Buddhist literature explained as<BR>sa-janapada. Āhāra = [land for] food; cf. bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहरणी<BR>āharaṇī (IE 8-4; EI 16), a district or its subdivision; cf.<BR>Hastakavapr-āharaṇī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 109); also cf. āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहारविषय<BR>āhāra-viṣaya (IE 8-4), originally an āhāra, but later a<BR>viṣaya; cf. Kheṭak-āhāra-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहवनीय|आहवनीयः<BR>āhavanīya (EI 32), the sacred fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहि|अहिः<BR>ahi (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहिदण्ड<BR>ahi-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28, 33), professional tax levied<BR>from snake-charmers or levy for their maintenance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐडूक|ऐडूकं<BR>aiḍūka, same as eḍūka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐरावत|ऐरावतं|ऐरावतः<BR>airāvata (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; sometimes hastin, etc., are used<BR>in this sense though they really mean ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐश्वर्याष्टक<BR>aiśvary-āṣṭaka (EI 33), same as aṣṭa-bhoga (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐतद<BR>aitada (EI 28), derived from elad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आजिवककासु<BR>ājivaka-kāsu (SITI), same as Tamil āśuva-kkāśu, āśuvikaḻ-<BR>kāśu, āśuva-kkaḍamai; tax payable by Ājīvakas or for the<BR>maintenance of Ājīvaka monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञा<BR>Ājñā (IE 8-3; EI 27; BL; CII 3), an order or command;<BR>same as ājñapti or ājñāpti supposed to be connected<BR>with giving the order for the drawing up of a charter; person<BR>receiving a king's order regarding the preparation of a charter;<BR>usually translated as ‘executor of a grant’; standing alone,<BR>the word is supposed to indicate the office of the Dūtaka,<BR>though the latter seems to have been additionally responsible<BR>for giving the donee the possession of the gift land. Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XIV, p. 362 (of the Gaṅga year 149) where the words are<BR>ājñā mahāmahattara-Śivarmā; also svayam = ājñā (CII, Vol.<BR>III, p. 115; Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 19) taken to mean that<BR>the king employed no Dūtaka to convey the details of his grant<BR>to the local officers, but that he gave the details in person.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-013" target="_blank">Page-013+ 40</a>]<BR>The expression sva-mukh-ājñā (literally, the oral order of the<BR>king) is also explained in the same way. The suggestion that<BR>Ājñādāpaka sometimes occurs as a synonym of Dūtaka is wrong.<BR>See Ājñapti, Ājñā-sañcārin, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 143-44.<BR>Cf. Tamil āṇai (EI 23), sign; the insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञाभोगिक<BR>Ājñā-bhogika (EI 21; BL), Ājñā and Bhogika wrongly<BR>made into a single official designation. See Ājñā and Bhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञादापक<BR>Ājñā-dāpaka (BL; HD), wrongly taken as a compound<BR>expression meaning an officer (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIV, p. 161).<BR>See Ājñā and Dāpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञाधारक<BR>Ājñādhāraka (ASLV), an executor of the royal order;<BR>cf. Ājñā-paripālaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञापरिपालक<BR>Ājñā-paripālaka (ASLV), an executor of the royal order;<BR>cf. Ājñā-dhāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञप्ति|आज्ञप्तिः<BR>Ājñapti, Ājñāpti (IE 8-3; EI 24, 27, 30; SII 1; HD), ‘the<BR>agency that obtains the command’; the executor of a grant; one<BR>who communicates, at the order of the king, the details about a<BR>land grant to local officers; probably the same as Dūtaka. Cf.<BR>Ājñā; also Tamil Vāy-kkeḻvi, Vāy-kkeḻviyār. See Ind. Ep., pp. 143-44;<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 184; Vol. VIII, p. 146. Cf. Ājñā-sañcārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञासञ्चारिन्<BR>Ājñā-sañcārin (EI 23, 24, 27), same as Ājñapti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञाशतप्रापयितृ<BR>Ājñā-śata-prāpayitṛ (EI 12), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञात<BR>ājñāta (IA 18), ‘an order’; sañcaritaṃ c = ājñātam, ‘and the<BR>command has been communicated or carried into effect.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकालिक<BR>a-kālika (CII 1), ‘not restricted to time’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकार|आकारः<BR>ākāra (CII 1), same as prakāra, a way or kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकर्षक<BR>ākarṣaka (EI 5), probably, the extent [of a piece of land].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाश|आकाशं|आकाशः<BR>ākāśa (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशमुखिन्<BR>Ākāśamukhin (ASLV), epithet of certain Śaiva ascetics,<BR>also called Ākāśavāsin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशपातालोत्पत्ति<BR>ākāśa-pātāl-otpatti (EI 30), fruits and roots produced in a<BR>piece of land. Cf. ākāś-otpatti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशवाणी<BR>ākāśa-vāṇī (IA 11), an unearthly voice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशवासिन्<BR>Ākāśa-vāsin (ASLV), same as Ākāśamukhin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशोत्पत्ति<BR>ākāś-otpatti (HRS), ‘produce of the sky’; fruits; wrongly<BR>regarded by some as the same as bhūta-vāta-pratyāya (q. v.).<BR>See ākāśa-pātāl-otpalli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अखण्डदीप<BR>akhaṇḍa-dīpa (EI 30), a lamp to be perpetually burnt<BR>before a deity in a temple, the installation of which was regard-<BR>ed as a meritorious act; same as nandā-dīpa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अखसालि<BR>Akhasāli (EI 7), same as Akṣaśālin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चिद्ग्राह्य<BR>akiñcid-grāhya (HRS), same as akiñcit-kara, ‘free from tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्कर<BR>akiñcit-kara (HRS), same as akiñcit-grāhya, ‘free from tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कम्<BR>akkam (SII 3; SITI), Tamil; name of a coin; one-twelfth<BR>of a kāśu; a mint (cf. akka-śālā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कशाला<BR>akka-śālā (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; a mint; cf. akkaśālai-vari<BR>(SITI), charges payable to the mint for minting coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कसालवरु<BR>akkasālavaru (CITD), cf. Telugu agasāli, akkasāla, akasālĕ;<BR>also Kannaḍa agasālavāḍu; a goldsmith or his workshop.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कसालिग<BR>Akkasāliga (EI 7), a goldsmith; same as Akṣaśālika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकृति<BR>akṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्ष|अक्षं|अक्षः<BR>akṣa, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटल|अक्षपटलः<BR>akṣapaṭala (BL), the department of records and accounts.<BR>See Akṣapaṭalika, etc. Cf. Mahāsāndhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलादाय<BR>akṣapaṭal-ādāya (IA 18), levy for the maintenance of the<BR>akṣapaṭala department or the Paṭvārī. Cf. akṣapaṭala-prastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलाधिकृत|अक्षपटलाधिकृतः<BR>Akṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (CII 3; HD; BL), an officer of the<BR>akṣapaṭala department or the officer in charge of it; same as<BR>Akṣapaṭalika, etc. See CII, Vol. III, p. 257; Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>V. 301, 397-98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलाधिपति<BR>Akṣapaṭal-ādhipati (BL), the head of the akṣapaṭala<BR>department; same as Akṣapaṭalin, etc.; also called Akṣapāla<BR>(cf. karaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलाध्यक्ष<BR>Akṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa (HD), the superintendent of records<BR>and accounts. Cf. Arthaśāstra, II. 7; Hist. Dharm., Vol. III,<BR>p. 143.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलप्रस्थ<BR>akṣapaṭala-prastha (IA 18; HRS), contributions paid by<BR>the villagers at the rate of a prastha of grain (probably, per<BR>standard measure) for the expenses of the akṣapaṭala department<BR>(probably for the maintenance of the Paṭvārī). Cf.<BR>akṣapaṭal-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलिक<BR>Akṣapaṭalika (EI 30; CII 4; HD; BL), same as<BR>Akṣapaṭal-ādhipati, officer in charge of accounts and records.<BR>Akṣapaṭala means ‘accounts office’ (Stein) or ‘records office’<BR>(Bühler). There is Grām-ākṣapaṭalika in the Harṣacarita (VII, para.<BR>2) probably meaning the Paṭvārī, and a section on the superin-<BR>tendent of the akṣapaṭala in the Arthaśāstra (II. 7). See Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XX, p. 128; Vol. IX, p. 305. Cf. Mahākṣapaṭalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आक्षपटलिक|आक्षपटलिकः<BR>Ākṣapaṭalika (HD), same as Akṣapaṭalika; officer in charge of<BR>the accounts and records office. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, pp. 316, 318.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलिन्<BR>Akṣapaṭalin (EI 19; BL), same as Akṣapaṭal-ādhipati,<BR>Akṣapaṭalika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षर|अक्षरं|अक्षरः<BR>akṣara, cf. hast-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a deed for borrowing money;<BR>also kṛṣṇ-ākṣarāṇi (LP), the record containing a censure; also<BR>ujjval-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a certificate of good conduct; also viśuddh-<BR>ākṣarāṇi (LP), an acknowledgement. Cf. uttar-ākṣarāṇi (LP),<BR>same as Marāṭhī utarāi; probably, a deed by which land is given<BR>at a favourable rent to merchants, etc., who helped the govern-<BR>ment with money.<BR>Cf. guṇ-ākṣara, also called guṇa-patra; see also gupt-ākṣara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षरपल्लि<BR>akṣarapalli (IA 11), the system of writing numbers by<BR>syllables; name applied to the system of writing numbers as<BR>found in inscriptions before the popularisation of the decimal<BR>system, though the symbols employed in the Brāhmī inscriptions<BR>do not appear to be akṣaras in all cases.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षशालिक<BR>Akṣaśālika (EI 29), same as Akṣaśālin, etc.; a goldsmith.<BR>(HD), explained as ‘an officer in charge of the gambling-<BR>hall’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षशालिन्<BR>Akṣaśālin (EI 29; BL), same as Akṣaśālika, etc.; a gold-<BR>smith; from Telugu-Kannaḍa Akkasālĕ (EI 3), Agasāli, etc.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 173.<BR>(HD), explained as ‘an officer in charge of the gambling<BR>hall’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षता<BR>akṣatā (IA 11), probably, rice grains mixed with red<BR>powder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षततृतीया<BR>akṣata-tṛtīyā (EI 24), same as akṣaya-tṛtīyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षौहिणी<BR>akṣauhiṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षावाप|अक्षावापः<BR>Akṣāvāpa (HD), superintendent of gambling. Cf. Hist.<BR>Dharm., Vol. II, p. 1216; Vol. III, p. 112.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनी<BR>akṣayanī, akṣayaṇī (EI 32), modified forms of akṣaya-nīvī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनिधिधर्म<BR>akṣayanidhi-dharma (EI 12), same as akṣayanīvī-dharma<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीका<BR>akṣayanīkā (EI 30), corrupt form of akṣaya-nīvikā, a<BR>perpetual endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीवि<BR>akṣaya-nīvi, akṣaya-nīvī (CII 3, 4; HRS), a permanent<BR>endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीवीधर्म<BR>akṣayanīvī-dharma (EI 29), the nature of a permanent<BR>endowment; also called akṣayanidhi-dharma (EI 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीविका<BR>akṣaya-nīvikā (EI 24, 30), same as akṣaya-nīvī; a perpetual<BR>endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयपूर्णमासी<BR>akṣaya-pūrṇamāsī (EI 23), probably, the same as Māgha<BR>su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयतृतीया<BR>akṣaya-tṛtīyā (EI 4, 23; CII 4; IA 18; BL), same as Vai-<BR>śākha su-di 3; see akṣata-tṛtīyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षि<BR>akṣi (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षीणिन्<BR>akṣīṇin (IE 8-5; EI 19; SITI), actual or fixed income;<BR>regarded as one of the eight rights of ownership. Cf. aṣṭa-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षोटभङ्ग<BR>akṣoṭa-bhaṅga (HRS), same as khoṭa-bhaṅga and ukkoṭa-<BR>bhaṅga (Abhidhānarājendra, s. v. parihāra). Cf. utkoṭa and bhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलगच्चु<BR>aḻag-accu (SITI), Tamil; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलम्<BR>alam (CII 1), ‘capable’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलम्बन|आलंबनं|आलम्बनं<BR>ālambana (LL), the base stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवण<BR>alavaṇa (IA 19), probably a Sanskritised form of aṟuvaṇa<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलय|आलयं|आलयः<BR>ālaya, cf. ālai (SII 3), a temple; a contraction of dev-ālaya.<BR>Cf. āyatana, bhavana, pura, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलेपन<BR>ālepana (SITI), anointing; coating the image with unguent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलि|आलिः<BR>āli (Chamba), wet land, irrigable land; also called kohlī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलिनी<BR>alinī (EI 26), ‘a swarm of bees’; female Jain devotees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलीपक<BR>alīpaka, also read as alīyaka (EI 32), a fiscal expression of<BR>uncertain import; see nidhān-ālīpaka. The word alipaka means<BR>‘a bee’. Thus ālipaka may refer to the right over wax, bee-hives,<BR>and honey. Alīyaka, from ali, ‘a bee’, would mean the same thing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलिय<BR>Aḻiya (EI 15), an official title. Cf. alīpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलीयक<BR>alīyaka, cf. alīpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्लवाट<BR>allavāṭa (IE 8-8; EI 30), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्पभाण्डता<BR>alpa-bhāṇḍatā (CII 1), moderation in the hoarding of<BR>wealth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्पमिरै<BR>alpam-irai (SITI) Sanskrit-Tamil; a minor tax payable<BR>in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमा<BR>amā (EI 21), abbreviation of amāvāsyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमच<BR>Amaca (HD), Prakrit Amacca = Sanskrit Amātya (q. v.).<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol VIII, pp. 71, 73.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमलसारक<BR>amalasāraka (CII 4), the circular fluted disc on the spire<BR>of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमलिमन्<BR>amaliman (EI 12), purity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमान्त|अमान्तः<BR>amānta (CII 3), the technical name for the scheme of the<BR>lunar months in Southern India, according to which a month<BR>ends with the new-moon day, and the bright fortnight precedes<BR>the dark. According to Fleet, it is always this arrangement<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-017" target="_blank">Page-017+ 40</a>]<BR>that is taken for calculation in astronomical works, though, even<BR>in Southern India, the arrangement was not applied to the<BR>Śaka years, for the civil reckoning, till between 804 and 866<BR>A. D.; on the other hand, according to him, even in Northern<BR>India, this arrangement was used in Nepal with the years of<BR>the Newār era, though it was abandoned there when the Newār<BR>era was followed by the Vikrama era in its northern<BR>variety. For its prevalence in Indonesia, see Sel. Ins., p. 470.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमर|अमरः<BR>amara (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’ [being the original<BR>number of the gods].<BR>(SITI; ASLV), land or revenue granted by a ruler to his<BR>retainers for military service; land assigned to military officers<BR>who were entitled to collect only certain revenues with the<BR>obligation to raise a contingent of army ready for service when-<BR>ever called upon and also to pay tribute to the king; same as<BR>amara-māgaṇi. Cf. Amara-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमरमागणि<BR>amara-māgaṇi (SITI; ASLV), same as amara; estate<BR>given to an Amara-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमरनायक<BR>Amara-nāyaka (EI 16; SITI; ASLV), a retainer chief<BR>enjoying amara, i. e. land or its revenue, for military service<BR>to be rendered to his master.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमारिरूढि<BR>amāri-rūḍhi (EI 11), Jain; an edict for the non-<BR>slaughter [of animals].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमात्य|अमात्यः<BR>Amātya (IE 8-3; EI 28, 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD; LL), a<BR>minister; sometimes, officer in charge of a district; explained<BR>as deś-ādi-kārya-nirvāhaka; in some cases, called Sarvādhikārin,<BR>etc., additionally. Cf. Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 114, note 150.<BR>See Mahāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमात्यसभा<BR>amātya-sabhā (EI 32), same as mantri-pariṣad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमावास्या<BR>amāvāsyā, cf. ṣaṣṭhī amāvāsyā, caturthī-amāvāsyā, nava rātri-<BR>amāvāsyā, mahānavamī-amāvāsyā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बोक<BR>amboka (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बाकपीलिका<BR>ambā-kapīlikā, same as āmra-pipīlikā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बर|अंबर|अंबरं|अम्बरं|अम्बरः<BR>ambara (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्भोनिधि|अम्भोनिधिः<BR>ambhonidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; cf. sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बिकाजनिक<BR>ambikā-janika (CII 1), ‘mothers and wives’; women in<BR>general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बुधि|अम्बुधिः<BR>ambudhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बुराशि|अम्बुराशिः<BR>amburāśi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंहति|अंहतिः<BR>aṃhati, also spelt aṃhiti (EI 4), a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आमि<BR>āmi (EI 28), same as Arabic amīn; an officer of the<BR>revenue or judicial department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमीर<BR>Amīra (IA 11), Indianised form of Arabic Amīr; often<BR>found in the form Hammīra in Indian records and rarely as<BR>Hambīra, Haṃvīra and Ahaṃvīra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 178).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्म<BR>amma (EI 24), literally ‘the mother’; a village goddess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्मनगन्धवारण<BR>Ammanagandhavāraṇa (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit;<BR>‘the musk-elephant of the father’; subordinate title; also found<BR>in the form Appanagandhavāraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्नात<BR>āmnāta (EI 12), cf. śrī-Mālava-gaṇ-āmnāte praśaste Kṛta-<BR>saṃjñite; explained as ‘authoritatively laid down’ or ‘constantly<BR>used’; cf. sthiti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्नाय|आम्नायः<BR>āmnāya (CII 4), a Jain sub-sect.<BR>(IA 20), same as kula or kula-krama; generations, succes-<BR>sions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्रपिपीलिका<BR>āmra-pipīlikā, cf. aṃbā-kapīlikā (EI 2; CII 1), usually<BR>interpreted as ‘the mother-ant’; but really, big red ants generally<BR>living in large numbers on mango trees. See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXV, pp. 99-100.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्रेडन|आम्रेडनं<BR>āmreḍana (EI 12), repetition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमृतगण<BR>amṛta-gaṇa (SII 12), same as Tamil amirta-gaṇattār<BR>(SITI), members of the committee for the management<BR>of village affairs; members in charge of the cash-receipts of<BR>a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमृतपडि<BR>amṛta-paḍi, cf. Tamil amuda-ppaḍi (SII 1; SITI), raw rice;<BR>food offering to a deity; (CITD), paḍi is an allowance in food<BR>(i. e. all the necessary commodities to prepare a meal) and some-<BR>times also in money and amuda-paḍi is an endowment often<BR>made in favour of a deity for daily offering of food as bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमृतयोग|अमृतयोगः<BR>amṛta-yoga (EI 9), a particular time regarded as auspicious.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंश|अंशः<BR>aṃśa, a small territorial unit (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 297,<BR>text line 26).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशबृहद्भोगिक<BR>Aṃśa-bṛhadbhogika (IE 8-3; EI 28), probably, the share-<BR>holder of a big jāgīr. See Bhāgika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशगण<BR>aṃśa-gaṇa (EI 33); a class of metres; cf. mātrā-gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशपति<BR>Aṃśapati (EI 30), co-sharer of a gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशुकभाण्डारकरण<BR>aṃśuka-bhāṇḍāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department<BR>of clothes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमुकाकसक्त<BR>amukāka-sakta (LP), ‘belonging to a certain man’, sakta<BR>being often used for satka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाच्छेद्य|अनाछेद्य<BR>anācchedya (IE 8-5), ‘uncurtailable’; ‘not to be resumed’;<BR>epithet of gift land. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 267, note 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनादेश्य<BR>anādeśya (EI 12), ‘not to be pointed out (or, ordered)’;<BR>epithet of gift land; same as anirdeśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाहार्य|अनाहार्य्य<BR>anāhārya (IE 8-5), ‘unresumbale’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आणक|आणकः<BR>āṇaka, see anna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनक|अनकः<BR>anaka, anikā (EI 20), Prakrit suffixes to male and female<BR>names respectively, known from early South Indian inscrip-<BR>tions; same as annaka, annikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनल|अनलं|अनलः<BR>anala (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आनन्दनिधि<BR>ānanda-nidhi (EI 24), a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आनन्दथु|आनंदथु|आनन्दथुः<BR>ānandathu (EI 12), joy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनन्त|अनंत|अनन्तं|अनन्तः<BR>ananta (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनन्तनिधि<BR>ananta-nidhi (EI 24), mistake for ānanda-nidhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आनन्तर्य|आनंतर्यं|आनन्तर्य्य<BR>ānantarya (CII 1), quickness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनासेध्य<BR>anāsedhya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 267, note 4), free from<BR>legal restraints (e. g. kāl-āsedha, ‘limitation of time’; sthān-<BR>āsedha ‘confinement to a place’; pravās-āsedha, ‘prohibition of<BR>removal or departure’; and karm-āsedha ‘restriction from<BR>employment’); epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाथसंरक्षण<BR>anātha-saṃrakṣaṇa (EI 23), ‘protection of the helpless’,<BR>mentioned as the purpose of a donation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आणत्ति<BR>āṇatti (SITI), Tamil; Sanskrit ājñapti; an executor of<BR>order; royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनावास<BR>anāvāsa (CII 1), ‘habitation which is quite unsuitable for<BR>one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्धारुवा<BR>andhāruvā, āndhāruvā (IE 8-5; EI 12), variant readings<BR>of arthāruvā or ārthāruvā (q. v.); Oḏiyā name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आन्ध्रदण्ड<BR>Āndhra-daṇḍa (IE 8-5), a tax; cf. Turuṣka-daṇḍa and<BR>Tiguḻa-daṇḍa. There is also reference to ‘an assembly of<BR>Āndhra-daṇḍa’, the meaning of which is doubtful unless daṇḍa<BR>is taken here in the sense of ‘an army’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अण्डिका<BR>aṇḍikā, weight equal to (1/4) of a māṣa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p.<BR>48); same as the copper paṇa (ibid., Vol. II, p. 7); also called<BR>dhānaka and regarded as equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or to (1/12)th<BR>suvarṇa (ibid., p. 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनेकान्तमत<BR>anekānta-mata (SII 1), same as syādvāda-mata (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनेसाहिणिवेर्गड<BR>Anĕsāhiṇi-vĕrgaḍa (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12), Kannaḍa;<BR>official designation; same as Sanskrit Gaja-sādhanik-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्ग|अंग|अंगं|अङ्गं|अङ्गः<BR>aṅga (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-020" target="_blank">Page-020+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 15), an abbreviation of aṅga-bhoga; cf. gātra (IA 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गभोग<BR>aṅga-bhoga (EI 17; CITD), often associated with raṅga-<BR>bhoga as aṅga-raṅga-bhoga, usually explained as ‘decora-<BR>tions and illuminations of a deity’. That aṅga-bhoga means<BR>decoration of the image of a deity is clear from the fact<BR>that a queen is known to have received a village as an agrahāra<BR>for her aṅga-bhoga, i. e. as her pin-money (Bomb. Gaz., Vol. I,<BR>Part ii, p. 448). Sometimes the land granted for the aṅga-<BR>bhoga of a deity came to be known as the deity's aṅga-bhoga<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 182); cf. aṅga, same as gātra<BR>(IA 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गडसिद्धाय<BR>aṅgaḍa-siddhāya (CITD), Telugu-Sanskrit; fixed revenue<BR>from shops.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गदेवता<BR>aṅga-devatā (SITI), attendant deity of a superior god;<BR>same as parivāra-devatā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गज|अंगज|अङ्गजं|अङ्गजः<BR>Aṅgaja (EI 16), same as the god Kāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गमणि<BR>aṅga-maṇi (SITI), property owned by a woman; cf.<BR>aṅga-maṇi-dravya (SITI), dowry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गनिगूहक<BR>Aṅga-nigūhaka (BL), an official designation of uncertain<BR>import; probably, a kind of spies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गार|अंगार|अंगारं|अंगारः|अङ्गारः<BR>aṅgāra, aṅgāraka, cf. a-carm-āṅgāraka (IE 8-5; EI 15);<BR>charcoal for cooking, which the villagers were obliged to supply<BR>to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरचना<BR>aṅga-racanā (HA), adorning of the various limbs of an<BR>image of the Jina with marks of sandal paste or leaves of gold,<BR>silver, etc., and with additional ornaments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरक<BR>Aṅgaraka (SII 11-1), corruption of Aṅgarakṣa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गारकी<BR>aṅgārakī (IA 26), same as ba-di 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरक्ष<BR>Aṅgarakṣa, Aṅgarakṣaka (IE 8-3; EI 15, 29; SITI),<BR>body-guard; the king's body-guard, or the head of the body<BR>guards.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरङ्गभोग<BR>aṅga-raṅga-bhoga (EI 23; SII 1), decorations and illumi-<BR>nations of a deity; various kinds of enjoyment provided for a<BR>deity; sometimes explained as ‘worship to include all kinds of<BR>enjoyments’ (SITI). Cf. aṅga-bhoga-raṅga-bhoga, raṅg-āṅga-<BR>bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरङ्गभोगवैभव<BR>aṅga-raṅga-bhoga-vaibhava (EI 3; SII 1; SITI), enjoyments<BR>of all kinds provided for a deity; same as aṅga-raṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरङ्गवैभोग<BR>aṅga-raṅga-vaibhoga (EI 3; SII 1; SITI), same as aṅga-<BR>raṅga-bhoga, i. e. aṅga-bhoga and raṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गशाला<BR>aṅga-śālā (SITI), same as aṅka-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गवैद्य<BR>Aṅga-vaidya (SITI), same as Tamil Aṅga-vavicciyar; a<BR>physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आङ्गीकरणिक<BR>Āṅgīkaraṇika (IE 8-3), officer in charge of administering<BR>oaths in a court of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गुल|अंगुल|अंगुलः|अङ्गुलः<BR>aṅgula, aṅguli (IE 8-6), a linear measure equal to the<BR>breadth of the middle finger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गुलि|अंगुलि|अंगुलिः|अङ्गुलिः<BR>aṅguli (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’; sometimes used to indicate<BR>‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिकेतोस्<BR>Aniketŏs (IE 8-2), Greek; royal title; ‘unopposed’;<BR>translated into Prakrit as Apadihata (Sanskrit Apratihata).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिमेषानोकह<BR>animeṣ-ānokaha (EI 4), same as sura-druma, i. e. kalpa-vṛkṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिवर्तकनिवर्तयितृ<BR>Anivartaka-nivartayitṛ (CII 4), ‘repeller of the unrepellable’;<BR>title of a ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिवृत्ति<BR>anivṛtti (LP), anxiety.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनियत|अनियतं<BR>aniyata, cf. niyat-āniyata (IE 8-5); occasional taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनियुक्त|अनियुक्तः<BR>aniyukta (IA 9), cf. niyukt-āniyukta-rājapuruṣa; probably<BR>refers to officials of the king, who were not actually appointed<BR>by the government, but occupied posts by virtue of heredity<BR>or election.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्जष्टसभा<BR>añjaṣṭa-sabhā, añjaṣṭa-śattu-sabhai (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit;<BR>village committee of five or eight members. Cf. pañca-kula<BR>and aṣṭa-kula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्जुवण्णम्<BR>añjuvaṇṇam (SITI; EI 35), Tamil; Sanskrit pañca-varṇa; the<BR>five artisan classes; called hañjamāna in Kannaḍa inscriptions;<BR>sometimes regarded as a form of Persian anjuman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्क|अंक|अंकः|अङ्कः<BR>aṅka (IA 19), a name, appellation or biruda.<BR>(IE 7-1-12; CII 4), ‘nine’.<BR>Cf. aṅke, aṅkena, aṅkataḥ (IA 15), ‘in figures’.<BR>Cf. aṅka, abbreviation of Telugu-Kannaḍa aṅkakāṟa; same<BR>as Sanskrit gaṇḍa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 270), ‘a hero,<BR>champion or warrior’. See aṅkakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्कदण्डखण्डन<BR>aṅka-daṇḍa-khaṇḍana, translated as ‘faults, fines and<BR>divisions’; cf. pañch-āṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्ककार<BR>aṅkakāra (EI 3, 4), a champion; same as Telugu-Kannaḍa<BR>aṅkakāṟa, sometimes explained as ‘a soldier or warrior who took<BR>a vow to defend his master and fight in the latter's cause to<BR>death’ (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34). See aṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्कशाला<BR>aṅka-śālā (SITI), probably, the place where duels were<BR>fought; cf. aṅga-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्न|अन्नं|अन्नः<BR>anna, Anglicised form of āṇaka; (1/16)th of a rupee (JNSI,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 142).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्नक<BR>annaka, annikā, cf. anaka, anikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अण्णनसिंह<BR>Aṇṇanasiṃha (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa; ‘the lion of the brother’;<BR>a subordinate title. Cf. Ayyanasiṃha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्त|अंत|अन्तं|अन्तः<BR>anta (IE 8-4; CII 1), a state beyond the borders of one's<BR>territories, or a bordering district; also its people; cf. pratyanta.<BR>(CII 1), cf. Anta-mahāmātra, officer employed in districts<BR>bordering on the frontiers of one's kingdom.<BR>(EI 3), a neighbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःकर<BR>antaḥ-kara (CII 4), explained as ‘excise duty’; probably,<BR>‘internal revenue’ or revenue income; same as antar-āya, antar-<BR>ādāya, abhyantar-ādāya, etc.; cf. antaḥ-kara-viṣṭika (EI 6), antara<BR>(EI 15), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःप्रतीहार<BR>Antaḥ-pratīhāra (IE 8-3), officer in charge of defending the<BR>back gate of the palace or of the palace-gates as distinguished<BR>from the gates of the capital city.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःपुर|अन्तःपुरं<BR>antaḥpura, cf. karaṇa (LP); the royal harem.<BR>(ML), the household; same as avarodhana in Aśoka's<BR>edicts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःपुराध्यक्ष|अन्तःपुराध्यक्षः<BR>Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3; EI 13; SII 11-2), superinten-<BR>dent of the royal harem; same as Āntaḥpurika, Stryadhyakṣa, etc.,<BR>and Sanskrit-Kannaḍa Antaḥpura-vĕrgaḍĕ (IE 8-3); sometimes<BR>also called Mahāpradhāna, Mahāpasāyita, Hĕri-Lāḻa-Kannaḍa-<BR>sandhivigrahin, Manĕ-vĕrgaḍĕ, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आन्तःपुरिक<BR>Āntaḥpurika (EI 13, 14, 18, 19, 23; HD), officer in charge<BR>of the royal harem; cf. Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःपुरमहामात्र<BR>Antaḥpura-mahāmātra (HD), officer in charge of the royal<BR>harem, mentioned in the Masulipatam plates of Amma II<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276). Cf. Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra<BR>of Rock Edict XII of Aśoka (CII 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःसिद्धिक<BR>antaḥ-siddhika (CII 4), same as abhyantara-siddhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तमहामात्र<BR>Anta mahāmātra (IE 8-3; CII 1), executive officers in<BR>charge of the bordering districts of an empire and probably not<BR>ambassadors at the courts of neighbouring kings. Cf. Antapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तपाल|अन्तपालः<BR>Antapāla (EI 9), frontier guard; explained by some as<BR>‘an officer in charge of the boundaries’ (HD). Cf. Arthaśāstra,<BR>I. 12 (one of the 18 tīrthas); II. 21; V, 1; Kāmandaka, XII.<BR>5; Mālavikāgnimitra, Act. I. See Anta-mahāmātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तर|अंतर|अन्तरं<BR>antara (CII 1), a period of time.<BR>(EI 15), name of a tax; cf. antar-ādāya, antaḥ-kara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरा|अंतरा<BR>antarā (CII 1), ‘in the interval’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरादाय<BR>antar-ādāya (CII 4), explained as ‘excise duty’; but same<BR>as antaḥ-kara, abhyantar-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तराल|अंतरालं|अन्तरालं<BR>antarāla (EI 1), part of a temple; cf. antarāla-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरालमण्डप<BR>antarāla-maṇḍapa (SITI), portion of a temple connecting the<BR>garbha-gṛha and the mukha-maṇḍapa; also called ardha-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरङ्ग|अन्तरंग|अन्तरङ्गः<BR>Antaraṅga (IE 8-3; BL), explained as ‘a privy councillor<BR>or a physician’, though the same person is known to be called<BR>Rāja-vaidya (i. e. the royal physician) and Antaraṅga; probably<BR>a private secretary; but mentioned along with Vaiśvāsika<BR>(EI 3); regarded by some as a class of royal servants very<BR>intimate with the king, probably the same as Ābhyantara (HD).<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 286; Vol. XII, p. 99.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आन्तरावड्डि<BR>āntarāvaḍḍi (IE 8-5; EI 12; 33), a variant reading of<BR>āturāvaḍḍi (q. v.); name of a tax; cf. rintakābaḍḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरविनियोग<BR>antara-viniyoga (SITI), individual share to make up the<BR>shortage in the total revenue occasioned by the grant of exemp-<BR>tion of antar-āya or uḻvari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तराय|अंतरायः|अन्तरायः<BR>antar-āya (EI 22, 23; SII 1, 2), explained as ‘a tax’,<BR>‘revenue’ or ‘a kind of revenue’; same as antar-ādāya; also<BR>explained as internal revenue or taxes levied by local bodies,<BR>called uḻvari in Tamil (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरायक्काशु<BR>antarāya-kkāśu, antarāya-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil;<BR>explained as ‘internal taxes or minor taxes like the profession<BR>tax, etc., payable to the village assembly’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरिका<BR>antarikā (CII 1), a period of time passed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरिक्ष|अंतरिक्षं|अन्तरिक्षं<BR>antarikṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरीप|अन्तरीपं|अंतरीपः|अन्तरीपः<BR>antarīpa (EI 12), an island.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तर्वंशिक|अन्तर्वंशिकः<BR>Antarvaṃśika (HD), officer in charge of the inner apart-<BR>ments or harem. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12 (mentioned among<BR>the 18 tīrthas); Kādambarī (para. 88); Daśakumāracarita, III;<BR>cf. Antarveśika in the Amarakośa, Kṣatriya-varga, 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तेवासिन्<BR>Antevāsin (LL), a male pupil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तेवासिनी<BR>Antevāsinī (EI 25; LL), a female pupil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुबन्ध|अनुबंधः|अनुबन्धः<BR>anubandha (CII 1), same as krama, order.<BR>(SITI), help.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुभवन<BR>anubhavana (IA 18), ‘the time or period of office [of a<BR>person]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुभोगप्प<BR>anubhoga-ppaṟṟ-ŏl13ugu (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; renewal<BR>of title deeds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुचित<BR>anucita (SITI), evil; damage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यै<BR>anudhyai (IE 8-2), ‘to meditate’, etc.; ‘to favour’, etc.;<BR>cf. anudhyāya (IE 8-2), ‘having favoured’; also Svāmi-Mahāsena-<BR>Mātṛgaṇ-ānudhyāt-ābhiṣikta (IE 8-2), ‘favoured and anointed<BR>[as king] by the lord Mahāsena and the Mothers’; also<BR>anudadhyuḥ (IE 8-2), same as anujagṛhuḥ, ‘[they] favoured’.<BR>See anudhyāna; also pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यान<BR>anudhyāna (IE 8-2), same as anugraha; favour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यानरत<BR>anudhyāna-rata (IE 8-2), see pād-ānudhyāna-rata, ‘engaged<BR>in meditating on the feet of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यात<BR>anudhyāta (IE 8-2), see pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्येय<BR>anudhyeya (IE 8-2), same as anugrāhya; ‘to be favoured’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुदिवसम्<BR>anudivasam (CII 1), daily.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुदृश्<BR>anudṛś, cf. anudarśayanti (EI 15), ‘inform [as follows]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुगजीवित<BR>anuga-jīvita, spelt in Kannaḍa as aṇuga-jīvita or aṇuṃga-jīvita<BR>(SII 11-1), a fief held by a king's subordinate for his main-<BR>tenance; similar to bīḻa-vṛtti, bīḻ-ānuvṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुग्रह|अनुग्रहः<BR>anugraha (IE 8-2), same as anudhyāna; favour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुग्रहस्थितिपात्र<BR>anugraha-sthiti-pātra (IE 8-5), same as sthiti-pātra or<BR>ācāra-sthiti-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुग्राह्य<BR>anugrāhya (IE 8-2), same as anudhyeya, ‘to be favoured’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुज|अनुजं|अनुजः<BR>anuja (Ep. Ind., Vol XXXIII, p. 271), a younger cousin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुलोम|अनुलोमः<BR>anuloma (CII 4), name of a kind of marriage, in which the<BR>bride belongs to a lower social order than the bridegroom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुनिध्याप्ति<BR>anunidhyāpti, cf. anunijhapayati (CII 1); explanation or<BR>exhortation; cf. nidhyāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुप्रतिपत्ति<BR>anupratipatti, cf. dharm-ānupratipatti (CII 1), practice of<BR>morality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुपूर्वी<BR>anupūrvī, cf. saṃvatsaraḥ dvitīyaḥ hemanta-pakṣaḥ caturthaḥ<BR>lithir = daśamī anay = ānupūrvyā. Cf. pūrvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुरूप|अनुरूपः<BR>anurūpa (CII 1), adequate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुसंयान<BR>anusaṃyāna (CII 1), a tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुसन्धान|अनुसंधान|अनुसंधानं|अनुसन्धानं<BR>anusandhāna, recitation (A. R. Ep., 1959-60, No. B. 335).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुशास्<BR>anuśās (CII 1), ‘to inculate’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुशासन|अनुशासनं<BR>anuśāsana, anuśāsanā (CII 1), same as anuśasti, inculcation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुशस्ति<BR>anuśasti (CII 1), inculcation, instruction; same as anuśāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुसेनापति<BR>Anusenāpati (EI 18), probably, a subordinate of the<BR>Senāpati (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुष्टुभ्<BR>anuṣṭubh (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुतार<BR>anutāra (SITI), protection, guardianship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुत्पन्नदानसमुद्ग्राहक<BR>Anutpanna-dāna-samudgrāhaka, an official title (Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., pp. 221-22); officer engaged in the forcible<BR>collection of unrealised dāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुत्तर|अनुत्तरं<BR>anuttara (EI 18), penance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवह्<BR>anuvah, cf. anuvahamānaka (EI 15), literally, ‘flowing on’;<BR>but actually, ‘ever-prospering’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवर्त्तना|अनुवर्तना<BR>anuvarttanā (SITI), a class of contingent dues which come<BR>under the head varttanā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुविधा<BR>anuvidhā (CII 1), ‘to conform to’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवृत्ति|अनुवृत्तिः<BR>anuvṛtti, same as vṛtti; cf. bīḻa-vṛtti, bīḻ-ānuvṛtti (SII 11-1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्वय|अन्वयः<BR>anvaya (EI 33; SII 1), a [spiritual] race; a Jain sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यजात<BR>anya-jāta (HRS), accidental revenue; one of the three<BR>kinds of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यत्<BR>anyat, ‘another thing’ (Ind. Ep., p. 133, note 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यथा<BR>anyathā (LP), ‘quite changed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यत्र<BR>anyatra (CII 1), ‘excluding’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपभार<BR>apabhāra (EI 8), a burden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपचार|अपचारः<BR>apacāra (IE 8-5), same as aparādha; cf. daś-āpacāra (EI<BR>15), same as daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपदान|अपदानं<BR>apadāna, cf. dharm-āpadāna (CII 1); a noble deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपग्रथ<BR>apagratha (CII 1), same as upaghāta; injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपकृष्ट|अपकृष्टं<BR>apakṛṣṭa (CII 1), distant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आपण|आपणः<BR>āpaṇa (IE 8-5), a shop.<BR>(CII 4), a market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आपान|आपानं<BR>āpāna (EI 2; CII 1), a watering station or shed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपराध|अपराधः<BR>aparādha, see daś-āparādha (IE 8-5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरपक्ष|अपरपक्षः<BR>apara-pakṣa (IA 16), used to indicate ‘the dark<BR>fortnight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरिगोध<BR>aparigodha (CII 1), same as aparibodha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरिपन्थ्य<BR>aparipanthya (IE 8-5), ‘not to be troubled’; an epithet of<BR>gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपसरक<BR>apasaraka (EI 1), probably, a porch or portico.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपत्य|अपत्यं<BR>apatya (CII 1), descendants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपवाह|अपवाहः<BR>apavāha (CII 1), the act of carrying away [as a prisoner].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपवरक|अपवरकः<BR>apavaraka, cf. Prakrit avaraka (EI 20; LL), a cell.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपविञ्छ्<BR>apaviñch, cf. apaviñchya (EI 15), ‘having separated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपोहन|अपोहनं<BR>apohana (SITI), waste or uncultivated; cf. Tamil agovana,<BR>waste land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रचराज<BR>Apracarāja (IE 8-2, 8-3), Prakrit; Sanskrit Apratyagrāja<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रदा<BR>apradā (EI 15) ‘[gift land] not to be alienated’; same as<BR>nīvī; sometimes used as an epithet of akṣaya-nīvī<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रदाधर्म<BR>apradā-dharma (EI 15), custom regarding inalienable<BR>gift land; same as nīvī-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रहत|अप्रहतं<BR>aprahata (EI 15), uncultivated; same as khila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रहर्तृ<BR>aprahartṛ (CII 1), ‘one who observes or maintains’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रतिहत<BR>Apratihata, see Aniketos.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रतिकर|अप्रतिकरः<BR>apratikara (HRS), explained as ‘without the right of<BR>alienation’; ‘without yield of revenue’; but cf. pratikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रतिष्ठापित<BR>apratiṣṭhāpita (ML), non-interred.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रत्यग्राज<BR>Apratyagrāja, ‘having no rival among kings’; feudatory title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आप्तक्रिय<BR>āptakriya (IA 18), a trusty agent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आप्तोर्याम|आप्तोर्यामः<BR>āptoryāma (CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपूर्व|अपूर्व्व|अपूर्व्वं<BR>apūrva, cf. apūrva-Brāhmaṇa (IA 18), a new Brāhmaṇa who<BR>was not fed on a previous occasion and is not to be fed again.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपूर्विन्<BR>apūrvin, apūri (SITI), a Brāhmaṇa well-versed in the<BR>Vedas on a visit to holy shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रधन|अपुत्रधनं<BR>aputra-dhana (IE 8-5; EI 25; CII 4), confiscation of the<BR>property of one dying without leaving a son or an heir.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रिकाधन<BR>aputrikā-dhana (EI 3; CII 4; HRS), same as aputra-dhana;<BR>the property of persons who died sonless, which the king could<BR>confiscate; escheat of the property of females.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रिकद्रव्य<BR>aputrika-dravya (EI 20), escheat property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराध्<BR>ārādh (CII 1), ‘to attain’; cf. svargam = ārādhayantu; also<BR>ārāddha (CII 1), ‘obtained’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराध्य<BR>Ārādhya (EI 15), ‘the worshipful one’; title of certain<BR>Śaivite Brāhmaṇas of Karṇāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरघट्ट|अरघट्टः<BR>araghaṭṭa (EI 10, 14, 22), a water-drawing machine; a<BR>well with a water-wheel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरक्षाधिकृत|आरक्षाधिकृतः<BR>Ārakṣ-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3); cf. Prakrit Ārakh-ādhikata (EI 2), a<BR>police officer; a magistrate looking after the maintenance of law<BR>and order, or the chief of the king's body-guards; same as<BR>Ārakṣika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरक्षिक|आरक्षिकः<BR>Ārakṣika (EI 10), cf. Prakrit Ārakhiya (EI 2), a police<BR>officer; same as Arakṣ-ādhikṛta, and also Talāra (q. v.) and<BR>Daṇḍapāśika (q. v.); cf. IHQ, December 1960, p. 266.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराम|आरामः<BR>ārāma (LL), a park.<BR>(ML), a grove or monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरामिक|आरामिकः<BR>ārāmika (LL), a gardener.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरण्य|अरण्यं|अरण्यः<BR>araṇya (IE 8-5), a jungle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरण्यक<BR>Āraṇyaka (LL), a Buddhist hermit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरति|आरतिः<BR>ārati, ārti (EI 1), a lamp; same as ārātrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरात्रिक|आरात्रिकं<BR>ārātrika (SII 1), same as nīrājana; cf. maṅgal-ārātrika<BR>(EI 4), ‘a lamp used in waving before an idol’; also the rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्चा<BR>ārcā (EI 24), the image of a god; cf. arcā, adoration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चादेश<BR>arcā-deśa (EI 24), an object of adoration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनाभोग<BR>arcanā-bhoga (EI 23), offerings to be made to a deity<BR>at the time of worship.<BR>(SII 3, 12; SITI), land set apart for meeting the expenses<BR>of worship (arcanā) in the temple; an endowment created for<BR>conducting worship; same as arcanā-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनाविभवकाणि<BR>arcanā-vibhava-kāṇi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; rent-free<BR>land granted to temple priests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनावृत्ति<BR>arcanā-vṛtti (SII 3; SITI); see arcanā-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धचन्द्र|अर्द्धचन्द्रः<BR>ardha-candra (SITI), literally, ‘half-moon’; a part of<BR>the tiruvāśi; a variety of ornament.<BR>(SII 2), the arch of an aureola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धजाम<BR>ardha-jā(yā)ma (SII 13), midnight; midnight service in a<BR>temple; cf. ardhajāma-ppuṟam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; land set<BR>apart for conducting the midnight worship in temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धकाकिणी<BR>ardha-kākiṇī (CII 4), the half of a kākiṇī; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धनमस्यवृत्ति<BR>ardha-namasya-vṛtti (IE 8-5); see namasya-vṛtti; a gift<BR>land, taxed at half of the normal rate; cf. pannāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धनारीश्वर|अर्द्धनारीश्वरः|अर्धनारीश्वरः<BR>Ardhanārīśvara (CII 4), a form of Śiva, in which<BR>the bodies of Śiva and Pārvatī are combined into one.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धनौवाटक<BR>Ardha-nauvāṭaka (EI 28), official designation; mention-<BR>ed together with Nauvāḷaka probably in the sense of an officer<BR>in command of half of a fleet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धाङ्गी<BR>ardhāṅgī (SITI), wife.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धपुरुषारिक<BR>ardha-puruṣārika (CII 4), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धसीरिक<BR>ardha-sīrika (EI 9), same as ārdhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धस्रोतिका<BR>ardha-srotikā (EI 4), probably, a small stream or half<BR>of a river bed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धतृतीय<BR>ardha-tṛtīya (CII 1), two and a half.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्धिक<BR>ārdhika (EI 9), a cultivator who tills other's lands and<BR>gets half the crop as his share.<BR>Cf. Prakrit addhika (EI 1), a slave.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धोदय|अर्द्धोदयः|अर्धोदयः<BR>ardhodaya (EI 5), the new-moon tithi falling on a<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-028" target="_blank">Page-028+ 40</a>]<BR>Sunday when, during day time, the nakṣatra is Śravaṇā and<BR>the yoga Vyatīpāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्द्रा<BR>ārdrā (SITI), Tamil ātrai; probably, the expenses for<BR>the ārdrā festival in the month of Mārgaḻi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्गल|अर्गलं|अर्गलः<BR>argala (IA 19), a check; used in certain dates and<BR>translated as ‘checked by’; cf. dvy-argala-catvāriṃśat-samadhika-<BR>vatsara-sahasra, ‘one thousand years, increased by forty [which<BR>have run into and are] checked by two’, i. e. the year 1042.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्घवञ्चन<BR>argha-vañcana (EI 30), probably, fraud committed<BR>in respect of the price of articles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हदाचार्य<BR>Arhad-ācārya (EI 29), a Buddhist or Jain teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धदायतन<BR>Ardhad-āyatana (LL), a Jain temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हद्दास<BR>Arhad-dāsa, a Jain monk; cf. Arhad-dāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हद्दासी<BR>Arhad-dāsī (EI 10), a Jain nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हत्|अर्हन्त्<BR>Arhat (EI 7-1-2), ‘twentyfour’.<BR>(CII 3; LL), Buddhist and Jain; a class of saints.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरि|अरिः<BR>ari (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’; cf. ari-ṣaḍ-varga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिषड्वर्ग<BR>ari-ṣaḍ-varga, also called ari-ṣaṭka (CII 3), the group<BR>of six enemies, viz. kāma, krodha, lobha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्जुनकर<BR>Arjuna-kara A (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्क|अर्कः|अर्क्क<BR>Arka (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR>(EI 7), explained as ‘metal’ in relation to Arkaśālika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्कशालिक<BR>Arkaśālika (EI 7), same as Akkasāliga, Akṣośālika; a<BR>goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्कशालिन्<BR>Arkaśālin (BL), same as Akṣaśālin; a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्कसालिन्<BR>Arkasālin (EI 29), same as Akṣaśālin; a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्णव|अर्णवः|अर्ण्णव<BR>arṇava (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्णिका<BR>arṇikā, weight equal to 2 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. VI, p. 46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरोग्यदक्षिणा<BR>ārogya-dakṣiṇā (ML), the gift of health.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरोग्यशाला<BR>ārogya-śālā (EI 24; ASLV), hospital; cf. Raṅgādhip-<BR>ārogyaśālā (EI 24), ‘the hospital of [the god] Raṅganātha<BR>[at Śrīraṅgam]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरोहक|आरोहकः<BR>Ārohaka (EI 27), official designation; possibly, same as<BR>Aśvāroha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थ|अर्थः<BR>artha (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’,<BR>(CII 1), a cause or matter.<BR>(CII 1), business.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थाभियुक्त<BR>Arth-ābhiyukta (IE 8-8), an accused.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थकर्मन्<BR>artha-karman (CII 1), performance of duty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थलेखिन्<BR>Arthalekhin (CII 4), a secretary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थारुवा<BR>arthāruvā (IE 8-5; EI 28), a tax of uncertain import;<BR>probably, Sanskrit artha-rūpyaka in the sense of a levy from the<BR>money-lenders on the amounts loaned out; also read as andhā-<BR>ruvā; see pratyarthāruvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्तिग<BR>artiga, a lover (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 58).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरुहण<BR>aruhaṇa (EI 27), probably, the tax also called āruvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरुवण<BR>āruvaṇa (EI 27), same as Tamil aṟuvaṇa (IA 19),<BR>the tax of six paṇas levied on mānya lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्य|अर्य्य|अर्य्यः<BR>Arya (CII 1), same as Vaiśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्य|आर्य्य|आर्य्यः<BR>ārya, cf. Tamil ayyar (EI 25), the father.<BR>Cf. bhadatasa aya-Isipālitasa, ‘of the Reverend Lord<BR>Ṛṣipālita’ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 29).<BR>(SII 1), a [Jain] saint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्या|आर्य्या<BR>āryā, cf. āī (EI 9), the mother.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यगुरु<BR>ārya-guru, cf. ajja-guru (EI 5), ‘a grandfather preceptor’;<BR>preceptor's preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यक|आर्यकः|आर्य्यक|आर्य्यकं|आर्य्यकः<BR>āryaka, Prakrit ajjaka, ayyaka (EI 20, 28; CII 3; IA 15),<BR>the grandfather; father's father. Cf. prārya, āryikā.<BR>Cf. Prakrit ajjaka (EI 24), an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यका|आर्य्यका<BR>āryakā, cf. Prakrit ajjakā (EI 24), Sanskrit āryikā;<BR>a female ascetic of the Jain order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यपुत्र|आर्यपुत्रः|आर्य्यपुत्त्रः|आर्य्यपुत्र<BR>Ārya-putra, Prakrit Aya-puta (IE 8-2; EI 3; HD),<BR>probably, title of a son of the ruling king. Cf. CII, Vol. I,<BR>p. 175.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यसंघ<BR>ārya-saṃgha (CII 3), ‘the community of the faithful<BR>(i. e. the Buddhist monks)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यसत्य<BR>ārya-satya, cf. Pali ariya-sacca (EI 5), Buddhist; four<BR>in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यिका|आर्य्यिका<BR>āryikā, cf. Prakrit āyikā (EI 20, 28), the grandmother;<BR>‘father's mother’; mentioned side by side with mahāmātṛkā,<BR>‘mother's mother’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 225).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशा<BR>āśā (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असमीया<BR>Asamīyā, see Assamese.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असंप्रतिपत्ति<BR>asaṃpratipatti (CII 1), unseemly behaviour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसन|आसनं|आसनः<BR>āsana (IE 8-8), a seat.<BR>Cf. a-cār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE 8-5; EI 15), probably,<BR>camping [of the royal officers in a village]; āsana-carma is<BR>sometimes taken as one expression meaning ‘a hide seat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसनपट्ट<BR>āsana-paṭṭa (EI 23, 24), a seat; a slab used as a seat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसनपीठिका<BR>āsana-pīṭhikā (LL), a bench for sitting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आषाण्मासिक<BR>ā-ṣāṇmāsika (CII 1), ‘less than six months in age’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशापाल|आशापालः<BR>Āśāpāla (HD), ‘the guardian of the quarters’; a chief<BR>ruling over 10,000 villages, according to the Śukranītisāra, I. 192.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशातना<BR>aśātanā (HA), Jain; disrespect or disobedience.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसेधभङ्गाधिकृत<BR>Āsedhabhaṅg-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 31), a police officer<BR>to check people's escape from prison or legal restraint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशेषमहाशब्द<BR>aśeṣa-mahāśabda (IE 8-2), same as pañca-mahāśabda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशेषविद्य<BR>aśeṣa-vidya (SII 1), belonging to all the branches of<BR>sacred studies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असिदण्डप्रहार<BR>asi-daṇḍa-prahāra (LP), war.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असिधाराव्रत<BR>asidhārā-vrata (EI 16), name of a vow.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसीहार<BR>āsīhāra, cf. udak-āsīhāra-kullaka; probably, a kind of<BR>channel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसीन|आसीनः<BR>āsīna (JAHRS, Vol. IX, Part i, p. 31, text line 12),<BR>literally ‘seated’; downcast, dejected. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXV, pp. 264-65.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्नव<BR>āsnava (CII 1), sin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्फोटन|आस्फोटनं<BR>āsphoṭana (SII 1), a challenge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्रम|आश्रमं|आश्रमः<BR>āśrama (EI 13) a stage of life; a religious establishment<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 67); cf. Caṇḍik-āśrama-guru (IA 11),<BR>‘the Superior of the hermitage of Caṇḍikā’.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्रय|आश्रयः<BR>āśraya (IA 20), subdivision of a viṣaya.<BR>Cf. āśiriyam, āśiriya-kkal, āśiriya-ppramāṇam (SITI), a<BR>document by which a person submits to another's protection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्समेसे<BR>Assamese, same as Asamīyā; language and alphabet of<BR>Assam, the alphabet being sometimes called Bengali-Assamese.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्ट<BR>aṣṭa, cf. aṣṭa-bhoga, probably ‘all kinds of enjoyment’<BR>(and not merely ‘eight’ kinds) ensuring tejaḥ-svāmya or owner-<BR>ship endowed with complete authority. Cf. aṣṭādaśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आष्टभागिक<BR>āṣṭa-bhāgika (CII 1), ‘[a village] paying one-eighth<BR>of the produce [instead of the usual rate of one-sixth or so]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभोग<BR>aṣṭa-bhoga (IE 8-5; EI 14, 17), privileges of the donee<BR>of a rent-free holding, believed to be grouped into eight<BR>classes which are sometimes enumerated as nidhi, nikṣepa, jala,<BR>pāṣāṇa, akṣīṇin, āgāmin, siddha and sādhya. Cf. aiśvary-āṣṭaka<BR>and aṣṭa-bhūti (EI 33); also aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya.<BR>(CITD), the eight privileges associated with the enjoy-<BR>ment of rent-free land, also enumerated as (1) nidhi (a<BR>treasure or a hoard, i. e. a natural hoard such as a mine),<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-031" target="_blank">Page-031+ 40</a>]<BR>(2) nikṣepa (a treasure hidden or stored up by some one),<BR>(3) akṣīṇa (permanent or lasting benefits), (4) āgāmin (future<BR>benefits); (5) sañcita (benefits already stored up), (6) jala<BR>(waters); (7) taru (trees) and (8) pāṣāṇa (stones). See<BR>JAHRS, Vol. X, p. 124. Pāṣāṇa seems to mean ‘hilly area’.<BR>(SITI), eight kinds of rights in enjoying landed property;<BR>mentioned sometimes as vikraya, dāna, vinimaya, jala, taru,<BR>pāṣāṇa, nidhi and nikṣepa, and also as nidhi, nikṣepa, jalāmṛta,<BR>pāṣāṇa, akṣīṇin, āgāmin, siddha and sādhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभोगतेजःस्वाम्य<BR>aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya (IA 8), unbridled ownership<BR>endowed with all the rights associated with the enjoyment of<BR>property; translated as ‘with the eight rights of full possession’<BR>though aṣṭa probably means ‘all’ and not merely ‘eight’ (cf.<BR>aṣṭādaśa, etc.); cf. aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmyaṃ ca krayeṇ = ādāya (EI<BR>23), ‘having secured the aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya rights by pur-<BR>chase’; (IA 19), translated as ‘the proprietorship of all the<BR>glory of the aṣṭa-bhoga’, and aṣṭa-bhoga explained as ‘the<BR>deposits of buried treasure (nidhi-nikṣepa), water, stones, the<BR>akṣīṇī, that which may accrue, that which has been made<BR>property, that which may be made property, and augmen-<BR>tation’. But there is probably no justification for taking<BR>nidhi-nikṣepa as a single unit.<BR>Cf. aṣṭabhoga-tejassvāmya-daṇḍaśulka-yukta (Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. XIX, p. 247, text line 102), mentioned along with nidhi-<BR>nikṣepa-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣ-prakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikh-āya-sahita. The<BR>separate mention of these two groups shows that aṣṭa-bhoga<BR>vaguely indicated all kinds of proprietary rights.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभूति<BR>aṣṭa-bhūti (EI 33), same as aṣṭa-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादश<BR>aṣṭādaśa, cf. aṣṭādaśa-jāti-parihāra (IE 8-5); literally,<BR>‘eighteen’; actually, ‘all’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 115). Cf.<BR>Oḏiyā aṭhara-gaḍajāta (EI 26). See aṣṭa, ṣaṭtriṃśat, ṣaṭpañcāśat,<BR>bāhattara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशदोष<BR>aṣṭādaśa-doṣa (SII 1), the eighteen or all sins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशजाति<BR>aṣṭādaśa-jāti (CITD), same as aṣṭādaśa-prajā; the 18<BR>castes. Kittel enumerates the 18 castes of the Kannaḍa-<BR>speaking area as the Brāhmaṇa, Kṣatriya, Vaiśya, Liṅgavanta,<BR>Baṇajige, Gaṅgaḍikāra-vokkaliga, Maḍivāli, Kelasiga, Kuṟuba,<BR>Kumbāṟa, Kaṭuka, Baḍagi, Akkasālĕ, Toreya, Uppāra, Besta,<BR>Holeya and Mādiga. But really the number 18 means ‘all’<BR>in such cases. The number 36 has the same meaning in the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-032" target="_blank">Page-032+ 40</a>]<BR>Bengali expression chatriś-jāti, ‘36 castes’. See Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXX, p. 115.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशप्रजा<BR>aṣṭādaśa-prajā (CITD), same as aṣṭādaśa-jāti, aṣṭādaśa-<BR>prakṛti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशप्रकृति<BR>aṣṭādaśa-prakṛti, cf. s-āṣtādaśa-prakṛty = opeta (EI 2);<BR>all classes of tenants; tenants belonging to all communities.<BR>(IA 17), ‘the eighteen (i. e. all) officials (i. e. classes of<BR>officials)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टदिग्गज<BR>aṣṭa-diggaja (EI 33), eight poets at king Kṛsṇadevarāya's<BR>court at Vijayanagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्तगिरि|अस्तगिरिः<BR>asta-giri (IA 22), the mythical Sun-set mountain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आष्टाहिका<BR>āṣṭ-āhikā (EI 8), Jain festival; same as aṣṭ-āhnika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाह्निक<BR>aṣṭ-āhnika, aṣṭ-āhnikā (EI 8, 33), Jain festival held in the<BR>months of Phālguna, Āṣāḍha and Kārttika; also called aṣṭ-<BR>āhnika-parvan; same as aṭṭhāi-mahotsava. See the Halsi plates<BR>of Kadamba Ravivarman (c. 490-538 A. D.) in Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. VI, pp. 25-26. Cf The Successors of the Sātavāhanas,<BR>p. 271; Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 47 and note; cf. p. xvi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टक|अष्टकः<BR>aṣṭaka (EI 7), same as ba-di 8; worship of the manes<BR>with oblations to them.<BR>Cf. aṭṭagam (SII 13), division of land, and aṭṭagattār<BR>(SII 13), share-holders in a land. See dvādaśaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टकुल<BR>aṣṭa-kula, cf. Tamil ūr-ĕṭṭu (SITI); the committee of eight<BR>members of the village assembly (ūr); taxes payable for the<BR>expenses of the committee (cf. eṇ-per-āyam which may also refer<BR>to the eight major items of revenue). See añjaṣṭa-sabhā.<BR>Cf. aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 31), an administrative<BR>board (like the Pañcāyat) consisting of eight (or more)<BR>members representing various classes or communities of people;<BR>cf. grām-āṣṭa-kul-ādhikaraṇa; mahattar-ādy-aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टमीपक्ष<BR>aṣṭamī-pakṣa (CII 1), used to indicate pakṣ-āṣṭamī, i. e.<BR>the eighth tithi of each fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्तम्ब<BR>astamba, cf. samudaya-bāhy-ādy-astamba (EI 23), ‘land<BR>originally devoid of vegetation which does not yield any<BR>revenue to the State’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टमिका<BR>aṣṭamikā, same as śalamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाङ्ग|अष्टांग<BR>aṣṭāṅga (CITD), the eight constituents of yoga consisting<BR>of (1) niyama (restraint of the mind), (2) āsana (a parti-<BR>cular posture or mode of sitting), (3) prāṇāyāma (restraining or<BR>suspending the breath during the mental recitation of the names<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-033" target="_blank">Page-033+ 40</a>]<BR>or attributes of a deity), (4) yama (self-control), (5) pratyā-<BR>hāra (restraining the organs), (6) dhāraṇa (the faculty of<BR>retaining in the mind, steady abstraction of mind), (7)<BR>dhyāna (abstract contemplation, religious meditation), and<BR>(8) samādhi (perfect absorption of thought in the one object<BR>of meditation, i. e. the Supreme Spirit); mentioned in connec-<BR>tion with obeisance, it means the 8 parts of the body, viz., the<BR>two hands, chest, forehead, two knees and two feet (cf. aṣṭāṅga-<BR>namaskāra).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाङ्गभक्तिक्रम<BR>aṣṭāṅga-bhakti-krama (EI 19), eight forms of worship;<BR>same as aṣṭa-vidh-ārcana, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाङ्गनमस्कार<BR>aṣṭāṅga-namaskāra (HA), obeisance with the eight<BR>limbs (viz. forehead, chest, two hands, two knees and two feet)<BR>done by lying straight on the ground, face downwards. See<BR>pañc-āṅga-namaskāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टपरिपालन<BR>aṣṭa-paripālana (SITI), deities of the eight cardinal<BR>points; same as aṣṭa-dikpāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टप्रहारिक<BR>Aṣṭaprahārika (IA 17), probably an official designation;<BR>may be derived from aṣṭa-prahara; probably ‘a watchman’.<BR>The correct form would, in that case, be āṣṭaprāharika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टप्राहरिका<BR>aṣṭaprāharikā, aṣṭapraharikyā (LP), ‘within 24 hours’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टपुष्पिका<BR>aṣṭa-puṣpikā (EI 15), ‘eightfold offering of flowers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टावधान<BR>Aṣṭāvadhāna (IA 11), one who has the power of<BR>listening and grasping eight things at a time; epithet of a poet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आष्टवर्गिक<BR>Āṣṭavargika (IE 8-3; EI 7), probably, the superintendent<BR>of eight departments; mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टविधभक्तिक्रिया<BR>aṣṭa-vidha-bhakti-kriyā (SITI), eight aspects of worship<BR>including arcanā, vandana, smaraṇa, pāda-sevana, stava, pradakṣiṇa,<BR>sakhya and ātma-nivedana or ātm-ārpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टविधार्चन<BR>aṣṭa-vidh-ārcana, aṣṭa-vidh-ārcanā (EI 19), same as aṣṭāṅga-<BR>bhakti-krama, the eight forms of worship.<BR>(IA 14; SITI), explained as ‘worship with eight<BR>materials, e. g., jala (water), gandha (scent), puṣpa (flower),<BR>akṣatā (grains), dhūpa (incense), dīpa (lamps), naivedya (food)<BR>and tāmbula (betel)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्थानमण्डप|आस्थानमण्डपः<BR>āsthāna-maṇḍapa (EI 4), an assembly hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्थायिकपुरुष<BR>Āsthāyika-puruṣa (IA 8), official designation; probably<BR>the same as Sthāyin; may be ‘hereditary village officials’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्ति<BR>asti (Ep. Ind., Vol XXVIII, p. 302, note 2), a mere<BR>particle used to introduce the narration of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टि|अष्टिः<BR>aṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशु|आशुः<BR>āśu (SII 2), probably, a hilt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसु<BR>āsu (CII 4), name of a coin; cf. āchu and accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशुद्धपक्ष<BR>a-śuddha-pakṣa (IA 16), used to indicate the dark fort-<BR>night.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुकवि<BR>Āśu-kavi (EI 5), epithet of a poet; cf. Sukara-kavi,<BR>Śīghra-kavi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशुक्ल<BR>a-śukla (IA 15), also called a-śukla-pakṣa (IA 16),<BR>the dark fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुलोप<BR>āśulopa (CII 1), hurry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसुरक्रिया<BR>āsura-kriyā (IA 23), the worship of spirits.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असुरविजयिन्<BR>Asura-vijayin (CII 4), ‘a devilish conqueror’; epithet<BR>of a conqueror.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्व|अश्वः<BR>aśva (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वाड्डाणकपत्र<BR>aśv-āḍḍāṇaka-patra (LP), deed for mortgaging a horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वाध्यक्ष|अश्वाध्यक्षः<BR>Aśv-ādhyakṣa (EI 18), superintendent of stables or<BR>cavalry officer; cf. Aśva-sādhanika, Aśvapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वघासकायस्थ|अश्वघासकायस्थः<BR>Aśva-ghāsa-kāyastha (HD), a petty officer in charge<BR>of the fodder for horses. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, III. 489.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वमेध|अश्वमेधः<BR>aśvamedha (CII 3, 4), a sacrificial ceremony centering<BR>in a horse, generally performed by independent monarchs.<BR>Kings celebrating the sacrifice sometimes assumed suitable<BR>titles (cf. Aśvamedha-parākrama and Aśvamedha-Mahendra claimed<BR>respectively by Samudragupta and Kumāragupta I on their<BR>coins). Some kings performed two, four or more horse-sacri-<BR>fices. For a list of the performers of aśvamedha known form<BR>epigraphic and numismatic records, see Sundaram Pillai Com.<BR>Vol., pp. 93 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्वमेध<BR>āśvamedha (EI 12), same as āśvamedhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्वामिक|अस्वामिकं<BR>asvāmika (EI 19), anarchy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वपति|अश्वपतिः<BR>Aśvapati (IE 8-2; CII 4)), cf. Aśvapati-Gajapati-Nara-<BR>pati-rāja-tray-ādhipati; royal title; the king as ‘the leader of the<BR>cavalry’; title of the Vijayanagara kings on account of their<BR>strength in horses (ASLV); title assumed by the rulers of<BR>some royal families.<BR>(EI 9, 21; CII 3; HD), an official title meaning either the<BR>master of the stables or the commander of the cavalry; cavalry<BR>officer; cf. Aśv-ādhyakṣa (EI 18). See CII, Vol. III,<BR>p. 259.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वपतिगजपतिनरपतिमूवरुरायरगण्ड<BR>Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-mūvaru-rāyara-gaṇḍa (IE 8-2),<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-035" target="_blank">Page-035+ 40</a>]<BR>title of the Vijayanagara kings; Kannaḍa translation of<BR>the title Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-rāja-tray-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वपतिगजपतिनरपतिराजत्रयाधिपति<BR>Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-rāja-tray-ādhipati (IE 8-2; CII<BR>4), holder (or, lord of the holders) of the three royal titles,<BR>viz., leader of the cavalry, leader of the elephant corps and<BR>leader of infantry; title assumed by the rulers of certain<BR>dynasties. Cf. Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-muvaru-rāyara-gaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वारोह|अश्वारोहः<BR>Aśvāroha (EI 18), a trooper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वसाधनिक<BR>Aśva-sādhanika (EI 21; CII 4), a cavalry officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वसंस्थ<BR>Aśva-saṃstha (EI 8), a horseman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वशालाकरण<BR>aśvaśālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of<BR>horses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वति<BR>Aśvati (EI 9), Tamil; same as Aśvinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्ववार|अश्ववारः<BR>Aśvavāra, cf. Asavāra (EI 2), a horseman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्ववारक|अश्ववारकः<BR>Aśvavāraka, Aśvavārika (LL), a trooper; same as<BR>Aśvavāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्विन्<BR>Aśvin (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; sometimes Āśvina is also<BR>used in this sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्विन|आश्विनः<BR>Āśvina (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. Aśvin. See IHQ, Vol.<BR>XXXIII, p. 101.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वीय|अश्वीयं|अश्वीयः<BR>aśvīya (EI 12), a number of horses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतपिक<BR>Atapika (LL), a Jain monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अटवी<BR>aṭavī (CII 1), the forest-folk.<BR>(SITI), troops.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आटविक|आटविकः<BR>āṭavika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 303, text line 50), a<BR>kind of grains.<BR>(EI 20; HD), an officer in charge of forest tracts. See<BR>Arthaśāstra, I 12 (mentioned among the 18 tīrthas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अठगानी<BR>aṭha-gānī, a coin equal to a ṭaṅka; there are do-gānī<BR>((1/4) ṭaṅka), cau-gānī ((1/2) ṭaṅka), cha-gānī ((3/4) ṭaṅka), bārah-<BR>gānī (1(1/2) ṭaṅkas), caubīs-gānī (3 ṭaṅkas), aḍatālīs-gānī<BR>(6 taṅkas). See JNSI, Vol. XXII, pp. 198-99.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अथर्ववेद<BR>Atharva-veda (CII 3; etc.), one of the four Vedas.<BR>See Veda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिब्रह्मण्य<BR>Ati-brahmaṇya (CII 3), probably meaning ‘extremely<BR>friendly to the Brāhmaṇas’ and not ‘a devout worshipper<BR>of the god Brahman’. See Parama-brahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिधृति|अतिधृतिः<BR>atidhṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘nineteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिजगली<BR>atijagalī (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिपर<BR>atipara (EI 24), an inveterate foe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिप्रसङ्ग|अतिप्रसंग|अतिप्रसंगः|अतिप्रसङ्गः<BR>atiprasaṅga (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 347, note 5), a<BR>case in which a grammatical rule exceeds its sphere.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिरात्र<BR>atirātra (CII 3), name of a particular sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिरेक|अतिरेकः<BR>atireka (CII 1), excess; cf. mano-'tireka, ‘enthusiasm’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिसत्त्र<BR>atisattra (EI 27), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतीत|अतीतं|अतीतः<BR>atīta (IA 17), ‘expired’; cf. Śaka-nṛpa-kāl-ātīta-<BR>saṃvatsareṣu. The word gateṣu, sometimes additionally used,<BR>refers to the expiry of the expired years.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतीलराज्य<BR>atīla-rājya (IA 19), indicates that so many years<BR>‘since [the commencement of] the reign have [now] passed’;<BR>used in connection with the regnal reckoning of Govindapāla<BR>and Lakṣmaṇasena and rarely with the years of an era (e. g.<BR>the Vikrama-saṃvat associated with the reign of a legendary<BR>king named Vikramāditya). See also gata-rājya and vinaṣṭa-<BR>rājya. Cf. JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, 1954, pp. 43 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिथि|अतिथिः<BR>atithi (EI 10; CII 3, 4), reception of guests; one<BR>of the five daily rites (mahāyajñas) of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR>See sattra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतिथ्य|आतिथ्यं|आतिथ्यः<BR>ātithya (HRS), land assigned to government officers for<BR>public charities, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतिवाहिक<BR>ātivāhika (HRS), escorting fee paid by the merchants,<BR>as indicated by the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst.,<BR>pp. 77.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतियात्र<BR>atiyātra (EI 30), same as atiyātrika; exit tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतियात्रिक<BR>atiyātrika (IE 8-8), tax for crossing the boundary; see<BR>śulk-ātiyātrika, ‘the boundary-crossing fee’; also atiyātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्मक<BR>ātmaka, cf. apaṇaga (ML), ‘one's own’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्मन्<BR>ātman (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्मपतिक<BR>ātma-patika (CII 1), independent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतोद्य|आतोद्यं<BR>ātodya (EI 23), music.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्रि|अत्रिः<BR>Atri (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्रिनयनज<BR>Atrinayanaja (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टपति<BR>Aṭṭapati (HD), the market-master. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 167.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टपतिभाग<BR>aṭṭapati-bhāga (HRS), office entrusted with the collection<BR>of the share of the lord of the market, as indicated by the Rāja-<BR>taraṅgiṇī; literally, ‘share of the market-master’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्ठाइमहोत्सव<BR>aṭṭhāi-mahotsava (HA), an eight-day festival celebrated<BR>by the Jains especially in the months of Āśvina and Caitra<BR>according to some but Phālguna, Āṣāḍha and Kārttika<BR>according to others; same as aṣṭāhnika-parvan (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अटु<BR>aṭu (Chamba), a land measure. Cf. jilo, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतुरशाला<BR>ātura-śālā, cf. ātula-śālai (EI 24; SITI), a hospital.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतुरावड्डि<BR>āturāvaḍḍi (IE 8-5; EI 28), tax of uncertain import;<BR>probably, a levy related to the treatment of the king when<BR>sick; also read as āntarāvaḍḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यग्निष्टोम|अत्यग्निष्टोमः<BR>atyagniṣṭoma (EI 26), name of a sacrifice. cf. agniṣṭoma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यन्तभगवद्भक्त<BR>Atyanta-bhagavad-bhakta (IE 8-2; CII 3), ‘extremely<BR>devoted to the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu)’; epithet of a pious<BR>Vaiṣṇava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यन्तमाहेश्वर<BR>Atyanta-māheśvara (EI 23; CII 3), epithet of a pious<BR>Śaiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यन्तस्वामिमहाभैरवभक्त<BR>Atyanta-svāmi-mahābhairava-bhakta (EI 23; CII 3), epithet<BR>of a pious Śaiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यष्टि|अत्यष्टिः<BR>atyaṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘seventeen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यय|अत्ययः<BR>atyaya (HRS), prescribed fine, as indicated in the Artha-<BR>śāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 26, 108. Cf. ātyayika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्ययिक<BR>ātyayika (CII 1; EI 22), a matter for urgent disposal;<BR>derived from atyaya, emergency, distress.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औदयन्त्रिक<BR>Audayantrika (LL), cf. Prakrit Odayantrika (EI 8); the<BR>maker of hydraulic machines or the person owning or working<BR>on such a machine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औद्रङ्गिक|औद्रङ्गिकः<BR>Audraṅgika (IE 8-3; EI 23), collector of the udraṅga<BR>tax meaning ‘tax on permanent tenants or the principal tax’;<BR>sometimes mentioned side by side with the Hiraṇyasāmudāyika<BR>or the collector of tax in cash. See Ṣaṣṭh-ādhikṛta, Dhruvasthān-<BR>ādhikaraṇika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औकपिण्ड<BR>aukapiṇḍa, cf. okapiṇḍa (CII 1), probably, household<BR>vermin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औलिकर<BR>aulikara, cf. aulikara-lāñchana (EI 26; CII 3), the lāñchana<BR>or crest of the kings of the Aulikara dynasty of Mandasor.<BR>The real meaning of auli is uncertain; sometimes aulikara<BR>is interpreted as himakara or the moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपरिक<BR>Auparika (EI 8-3), same as Uparika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपशतिक<BR>Aupaśatika, cf. Prakrit Opasati (EI 16), name of a<BR>gotra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपायनिक<BR>aupāyanika (HRS), earnings from presents, as indicated<BR>by the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 28, 38.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपायिक<BR>aupāyika (EI 25), probably, an adopted [son].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औरेउस्<BR>aureus (IE 8-8), name of the Roman gold coin, also<BR>called denarius (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

और्णस्थानिक|और्णस्थानिकः<BR>Aurṇasthānika (IE 8-3; EI 23), officer in charge of an<BR>ūrṇā-sthāna (wool factory) or of all the ūrṇā-sthānas. Cf.<BR>ūrṇā-sthāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औषध|औषधं<BR>auṣadha (EI 24), medicine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औत्खेटिक<BR>Autkheṭika (HRS), officer in charge of the collection of<BR>the impost called utkheṭana (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औत्तराह<BR>Auttarāha (EI 8), a northerner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औत्थितासनिक|औत्थितासनिकः<BR>Autthitāsanika (IE 8-3), same as Utthitāsanin; probably,<BR>courtier of a special rank provided with a special seat;<BR>perhaps, the chief nobleman at the royal court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवभृथ|अवभृथः<BR>avabhṛtha (EI 9; CII 4), name of the ceremonial bath<BR>at the end of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवचटित<BR>avacaṭita (EI 13), a crack; cf. khaṇḍa-sphuṭit-āvacaṭita-<BR>patita-saṃskār-ārtham, ‘for the repairs of dilapidated, broken,<BR>cracked and fallen [parts]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवच्छिन्न|अवच्छिन्नं<BR>avacchinna, cf. sva-sīm-āvacchinna (IE 8-5), demarcated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवदान|अवदानं<BR>avadāna, also spelt āvadāna (EI 28, 29, 33), Oḏiyā; a<BR>present; a tax; tax in general; also called āvedana.<BR>(SITI), same as Sanskrit avasāna; termination, end.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवदार<BR>avadāra (EI 13), cf. paśukul-āvadāra-karmānta-koṇakalikā-<BR>gaṅgāgrāme; meaning uncertain; possibly ‘a pound’ or<BR>‘a pen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधानिन्<BR>Avadhānin (EI 16), title of Brāhmaṇas; cf. Śatāvadhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधारणा<BR>avadhāraṇā, cf. adhikaraṇ-āvadhāraṇā, ‘official investiga-<BR>tion’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 267).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधि|अवधिः<BR>avadhi, cf. avadher = anantaram (LP), ‘after the time limit<BR>is over’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधी<BR>Avadhī, language of Avadh (Oudh).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवाह|आवाहः<BR>āvāha (CII 1), marriage of a son; cf. vivāha, ‘marriage<BR>of a daughter’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवकर|अवकरः<BR>avakara (EI 32), sweepings, a mound. Cf. avaṣkara;<BR>also niravakara, remainder after deduction (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXVIII, p. 188).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवकाश|अवकाशः<BR>avakāśa (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 347, note 5), ‘opportunity<BR>for a grammatical rule taking effect’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलगा<BR>avalagā (LP), same as Gujarātī oḻaga; cf.<BR>avalagā sad = aiv = āvalokyā (LP), ‘care should be constantly<BR>taken’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलगक<BR>avalagaka (EI 2; HRS), same as avalagā (q. v.); some-<BR>times regarded as presents or supplies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलगन<BR>avalagana (EI 2; HRS), same as avalagaka and avalagā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलम्बक|अवलंबकः|अवलम्बकः<BR>avalambaka (EI 30), probably, a rod from which loops<BR>are suspended for carrying bundles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलोक्य<BR>avalokya (IE 8-8), detection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवण<BR>āvaṇa (SITI), Tamil; a document; generally, a sale-deed;<BR>also called vilaiy-āvaṇam; cf. āvaṇa-kkaḻari (SITI), a place<BR>where documents like sale-deeds, etc., are registered; regis-<BR>tration office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनी<BR>avanī (EI 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR>(EI 3), a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनिमण्डल<BR>avani-maṇḍala, cf. Kon-āvani-maṇḍala (EI 32), also called<BR>Kona-maṇḍala, Kona-sīma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनिरन्ध्रन्याय<BR>avani-randhra-nyāya (CII 4), same as bhūmi-cchidra-nyāya<BR>(q. v.), ‘the maxim of the fallow land.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनिवेतन<BR>avani-vetana (SITI), police duties of a village; contri-<BR>bution for such duties; the same as Tamil pā ṭikāval.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवर<BR>āvara (CII 4), a stall. Cf. āvāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवार|आवारः<BR>āvāra (IE 8-5), cf. āpaṇeṣu āvāraḥ, ‘collections to be<BR>made from the shops in a market’. Cf. āvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवराधिक<BR>avar-ādhika (CII 1), ‘more or less’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवरज|अवरजः<BR>avaraja (ML), a younger brother or cousin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवरण|आवरणं<BR>āvaraṇa (EI 17), a shield.<BR>(SITI), shelter, covering; same as prākāra or wall around<BR>the temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवर्जनीय<BR>āvarjanīya (LP), ‘to be received’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवरोधन|अवरोधनं<BR>avarodhana (CII 1), household; cf. antaḥpura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवरोधजन<BR>avarodha-jana (EI 23), inmates of the royal harem or the<BR>king's wives and concubines; wrongly interpreted as ‘a<BR>watchman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवर्त|आवर्तः|आवर्त्त|आवर्त्तं|आवर्त्तः<BR>āvarta, cf. sarv-āvarta-yutā, ‘assigned as the date of pay-<BR>ment as it falls annually’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 310,<BR>note 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवास|आवासः<BR>āvāsa, cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (IE 8-5),<BR>shelter or accommodation [which the villagers were obliged<BR>to provide for the touring officers of the king]; cf. saṃvāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवासक<BR>āvāsaka (IE 8-5; EI 25), same as āvāsa or saṃvāsa, i. e.<BR>accommodation [which the villagers were obliged to provide<BR>to the royal officers on tour].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवासनिका<BR>āvāsanikā (EI 1), a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसर|अवसरः<BR>Avasara (SITI), an officer of the royal household having<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-040" target="_blank">Page-040+ 40</a>]<BR>the duty of bringing to the notice of the king anything that<BR>demanded his immediate attention. Cf. Kārtākṛtika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसर|अवसरः<BR>avasara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 347), one of the periods<BR>when the worship is performed and offerings are made to the<BR>deity in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसरवर्त्तना<BR>Avasara-varttanā (SITI), presents payable to an Avasara (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसथ|अवसथः<BR>avasatha (IE 8-3), explained as ‘a college or a dharma-<BR>śālā’. But see Āvasathika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवसथिक<BR>Āvasathika (IE 8-3), variously explained as ‘the superin-<BR>tendent of avasathas, i. e. colleges or dharma-śālās’, ‘the super-<BR>visor of the royal palace and other government buildings’<BR>(Hist. Beng., I, ed. Majumdar, p. 284); ‘one who keeps the<BR>domestic fire (āvasathya) burning with daily offerings’<BR>(D. Bhattacharya, Halāyudha's Brāhmaṇasarvasva, p. xx); etc.<BR>(EI 9, 11, 24), title or family name of Brāhmaṇas. Cf.<BR>Āvasathin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवसथिन्<BR>Āvasathin (EI 23), explained as ‘one who keeps the sacred<BR>fire called āvasathya’; cf. Āvasathika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवष्कर<BR>avaṣkara, sweepings, a mound; cf. s-oṣar-āvaṣkara-sthāha-<BR>nivīta-lavaṇākara (EI 22); also sa-gart-āvaṣkara (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXV, p. 135, text line 21). See avakara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवष्टब्धि<BR>avaṣṭabdhi (LP), detention.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवस्था<BR>avasthā (IA 16), a territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवस्थिक<BR>Āvasthika (EI 23), corruption of Āvasathika; same as<BR>Āvasathin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवात<BR>āvāta (IE 8-5), same as vāta, storm; cf. udvāta.<BR>(EI 32; CII 3; etc.), a fiscal term referring to the<BR>income from lands as a result of changes caused by natural<BR>agencies; an income probably resulting from storms. See<BR>vāta, probably meaning ‘a storm or tempest’; also āvāt-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवतार|अवतारः<BR>avatāra (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवतरण|अवतरणं<BR>avataraṇa, cf. gṛh-āvataraṇa (IE 8-5), probably the same<BR>as umbara-bheda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवतारिअमावास्या<BR>avatāri-amāvāsyā (IA 18), Kannaḍa name for the new-<BR>moon of Pauṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवाताय<BR>āvāt-āya (HRS), ‘the income derived from storms’;<BR>cf. āvāta and bhūta-vāta-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवत्रप्<BR>avatrap (CII 1), ‘to be disinclined’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवेदन|आवेदनं<BR>āvedana (EI 28), same as avadāna or āvadāna of Oḏiyā<BR>records; tax in general. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 115.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवेदनक<BR>āvedanaka (IE 8-8), a written complaint or application.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवण्डाय<BR>avaṇḍ-āya (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 96), Telugu; name<BR>of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवेशनिन्<BR>Āveśanin, cf. Prakrit Āvesani (EI 2; LL), the chief artisan;<BR>the foreman of artisans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अविमनस्<BR>avimanas (CII 1), pleased.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अविप्रहीन<BR>aviprahīna (CII 1), used in the sense of ahīna, ‘not lost’;<BR>undiminished.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अविरोध|अविरोधः<BR>avirodha (SITI), not inimical; amicability.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवृति|आवृतिः<BR>āvṛti (CII 1), order; cf. sakala-deś-āvṛtika (CII 1), ‘one<BR>whose order has reached all parts of the country’.<BR>Cf. anāvṛti (CII 1), ‘want of practice’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवृत्ति|आवृत्तिः<BR>āvṛtti (IE 8-4; EI 26), an administrative unit like a<BR>Pargana (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 205).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अय|अयः<BR>aya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आय|आयः<BR>āya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR>(EI 33; CII 3; SII 1, 2), a fiscal term meaning ‘revenue’,<BR>‘tax’.<BR>(SITI), literally, income; a general term denoting<BR>‘taxes’; cf. val13iy-āyam (SITI), tolls on the roadway.<BR>(HRS), revenue in general according to the Arthaśāstra<BR>and other authorities; a special branch of revenue according to<BR>the inscriptions of the Uccakalpa kings and later epigraphs.<BR>(CITD), profit, income, receipt; tribute; corn given<BR>by the well-to-do villagers to the hereditary servants of the<BR>village as their established fees of office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयाग|आयागः<BR>āyāga (EI 1), an object of homage; cf. āyāga-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयागपट<BR>āyāga-paṭa, āyāga-paṭṭa (EI 24; LL), Jain; tablet for<BR>worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयागसभा<BR>āyāga-sabhā (LL), Jain; a hall of homage.<BR>(SITI), administration of a village by a group<BR>of officers called āyāgār (village officers and servants).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयक<BR>āyaka (EI 21; LL), the entrance pavilion of a Buddhist<BR>monastery; a pavilion in front of the door of a Buddhist<BR>monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयमुख<BR>āya-mukha, ‘sources of income’; cf. āya-śarīra. See<BR>Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 26.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अयन|अयनं<BR>ayana (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अयनांश|अयनांशः<BR>ayan-āṃśa (CII 3), the degree of procession of the<BR>equinoxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयपद<BR>āya-pada (LP), income; property (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 145).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयशरीर<BR>āya-śarīra, ‘body of income’ separated from āya-mukha,<BR>‘source of income’. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 25-26.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयशुल्क<BR>āya-śulka (EI 33), taxes and tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयत|आयतः<BR>āyata (CII 1), engaged or appointed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयतन|आयतनं<BR>āyatana (EI 30), a temple or shrine. Cf. bhavana, ālaya,<BR>pura, etc.<BR>Cf. ṣaḍ-āyatana; an organ.<BR>Cf. tuṣṭy-āyatana (CII 1), same as tuṣṭi-pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयति|आयतिः<BR>āyati (EI 14), future prosperity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुधीय|आयुधीयः<BR>āyudhīya (HRS), land granted for supplying troops in<BR>lieu of tax, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra. See amara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुक्त|आयुक्तः<BR>Āyukta (CII 4; HD), literally ‘an officer’. Same as<BR>Āyuktaka. Pāṇini (II, 3. 40) knows the word in the sense<BR>of a servant or office. Cf. Āyukta-puruṣa (CII, Vol. III, p. 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुक्तक<BR>Āyuktaka (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; EI 30; BL; HD), same as<BR>Āyukta; often the governor of a district or subdivision. See<BR>Kāmasūtra, V. 5. 5; Kāmandaka, V. 82.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुक्तपुरुष<BR>Āyukta-puruṣa (CII 3), the same as Āyukta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुष|आयुषं<BR>āyuṣa, used in the sense of āyus in the Junagadh inscrip-<BR>tion of Rudradāman, text line 10 (Sel. Ins., p. 171).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुष्य|आयुष्यं<BR>āyuṣya (EI 10), Jain; a variety of karman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अय्यनगन्धवारण<BR>Ayyanagandhavāraṇa (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit;<BR>‘the musk-elephant of the grandfather’; a subordinate title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अय्यनसिंह<BR>Ayyanasiṃha (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; ‘the lion of the<BR>grandfather’; a subordinate title. Cf. Aṇṇanasiṃha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब|बः<BR>ba (IE 8-1; CII 3, etc.); an abbreviation of bahula or<BR>of bahula-pakṣa, i. e. the dark fortnight; used in connection<BR>with di or ti (see ba-di, la-ti) and also by itself. Cf. va.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बा<BR>Bā° (PJS), contraction of the honorific Bāi (q. v.)<BR>applied to ladies (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions of<BR>Western India).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाबू<BR>bābū (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 316), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाचक<BR>bācaka (LP), handful; cf. Gujarātī bācko.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाछ<BR>bācha, bāchī (Chamba), a tax in cash. See vākṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाड<BR>bāḍa (EI 5), Kannaḍa; a town or village.<BR>(IE 8-4), Kannaḍa; a small territorial unit like a<BR>Pargana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाडब<BR>bāḍaba (SII 1), the submarine fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदला<BR>badalā (Chamba), return, exchange; same as parata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदर|बदरं|बदरः<BR>badara, same as tolaka (q. v.) or tolā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बधा<BR>badhā (LP), obstacle; cf. Sanskrit bādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाधा<BR>bādhā (EI 15), obstacle; also spelt vādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाढतरम्<BR>bāḍhataram (CII 1), ‘more excessively’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदि<BR>ba-di (IE 8-1; CII 3; etc.), contraction of bahula-pakṣa-dina<BR>or °divasa; also spelt va-di, cf. śu-di; abbreviations of separate<BR>words (see ba, di, śu and va) and not words in themselves,<BR>ba-di or va-di referring to the dark fortnight and śu-di the<BR>bright fortnight; they denote the fortnight and the solar<BR>or civil day, with reference to the lunar tithi, in the fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बडिमाडुवुलु<BR>baḍi-māḍuvulu (CITD) Telugu; a coin of unknown value.<BR>Baḍi means ‘petty’ or ‘a tax’ and māḍuvu may be the same as<BR>māḍa meaning half a dīnār or the tenth of a paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बागुलि<BR>Bāguli, cf. Vārgulika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहत्तर<BR>bāhattara (IE 8-3), literally, ‘seventytwo’, but actually<BR>‘all’ (cf. aṣṭādaśa, etc.); see Bāhattaraniyogādhipati, Bāhattara-<BR>niyogin, Senādibāhattaraniyogādhiṣṭhāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहत्तरनियोगाधिपति<BR>Bāhattaraniyogādhipati (IE 8-3; EI 23, 30), the highest<BR>executive officer under South Indian kings like the Yādavas of<BR>Devagiri; same as Bāhattaraniyogin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहत्तरनियोगिन्<BR>Bāhattaraniyogin (EI 19), official designation; same as<BR>Bāhattaraniyogādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहिर्गृह<BR>bahir-gṛha, cf. vāra-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहिरिका<BR>bāhirikā (EI 20), a suburb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहिस्<BR>bahis, ‘excluding’; same as Bengali baï (JAS, Letters,<BR>Vol. XX, p. 215).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहु|बाहुः<BR>bāhu (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहुलेय|बाहुलेयः<BR>bāhuleya (CII 3; IA 1), a bull.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहुश्रुत<BR>bahuśruta (CII 1), well informed in various doctrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहुसुवर्ण<BR>bahusuvarṇa, bahusuvarṇaka (EI 4; IA 19; CII 4), name<BR>of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहुतावत्क<BR>bahutāvatka (CII 1), ‘many times that number’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहुवलय<BR>bāhu-valaya, cf. pāku-valayam (SITI), an armlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाह्य<BR>bāhya, cf. bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya (IE 8-5; Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-044" target="_blank">Page-044+ 40</a>]<BR>XVI, p. 276, text line 14); ‘income from the sale of things<BR>imported in a village’, same as Tamil puṟav-āyam (SITI),<BR>‘revenue from external sources (collected mainly in cash)’ or<BR>Tamil puṟa-kaḍamai (SITI), ‘external taxes’, explained as<BR>taxes and fees payable to the State. But puṟa-kaḍamai is the<BR>same as puṟav-āyam. Bāhya and ābhyantatra may thus mean<BR>respectively taxes payable to the king and those payable to<BR>the village authorities. See ābhyantara. Cf. samudaya-bāhy-<BR>ādya-stamba (EI 23), ‘land covered with original shrubs,<BR>i. e. waste which does not yield any revenue to the State’.<BR>(HD), a class of royal servants distinguished from<BR>Antaraṅga. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 426, 680, 1542.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाह्यालि<BR>bāhyāli (CII 4), the outskirt of a town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाइ<BR>Bāi, Bāī (EI 8), honorific epithet or name-ending of<BR>ladies in Western India; cf. Bāyi, Bā.°<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बल|बलं|बलः<BR>bala, an escort; cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधि<BR>Balādhi (LP), abbreviation of Balādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधिकृत<BR>Balādhikṛta (CII 3, 4; BL; HD), ‘the commander of<BR>an army’. See JBBRAS, Vol. XVI, p. 108 (Balādhikṛta<BR>following Senāpati); Kādambarī, para. 74. According to some<BR>(cf. Balādhi in LP), the Balādhikṛta was probably the head<BR>of a territorial unit like the present Māmlatdār. See<BR>Balādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधिप<BR>Balādhipa (BL), a leader of the army; cf. Balādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधीर<BR>Balādhīra (CII 4), official designation; probably,<BR>mistake for Balādhīśa, same as Balādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाध्यक्ष|बलाध्यक्षः<BR>Balādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), officer in charge of the army;<BR>mentioned along with the Senāpati who was probably a sub-<BR>ordinate officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलदी<BR>baladī, see valadī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलहरण<BR>balaharaṇa, cf. balaharaṇena (LP), same as Gujarātī lāine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बालकमहाराजकुमार<BR>Bālaka-mahārājakumāra (EI), a young prince.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलकौष्ठिक<BR>Balakauṣṭhika, cf. Valatkauṣan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बालालय<BR>bāl-ālaya (SITI) temporary shrine to lodge the images<BR>of gods when repairing a temple; small shrine probably consist-<BR>ing of a single room wherein the images of all the gods<BR>are lodged; same as Tamil iḻaṅ-koyil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलानक<BR>balānaka (HA), a maṇḍapa above the entrance of a Jain<BR>shrine or the courtyard of a shrine, later known as ṭhākorkhānā.<BR>(BL), a stone seat.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-045" target="_blank">Page-045+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 8), same as Marāṭhī balāṇī, ‘a raised seat along the<BR>walls of the gābhāra or sabhā-maṇḍapa of a temple.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलयष्टि<BR>bala-yaṣṭi (EI 33; CII 4), a stout memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बल्हरा<BR>Balharā (IE 8-2), Arabic corruption of Vallabha-rāja<BR>through Prakrit Ballaha-rāa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलि|बलिः<BR>bali (IE 8-5; HRS), voluntary gift (afterwards, com-<BR>pulsory contribution) and tribute from the subjects as indicated<BR>by Vedic literature; later, tax in general as suggested by the<BR>standard lexicons; king's grain share, identical with bhāga<BR>but different from kara according to the Arthaśāstra, but not<BR>the Junagadh inscription of Rudradāman (cf. bali-śulka-<BR>bhāga in line 14). The Rummindei inscription of Aśoka also<BR>distinguishes between bali and bhāga and seems to identify<BR>bali with kara (or with pilgrims' tax). See Select Inscriptions,<BR>pp. 71, 173.<BR>(EI 10, 23, 32; CII 3, 4), an offering to creatures; one<BR>of the five mahāyajñas or sacrificial rites. Cf. bali-caru-vaiśvadev-<BR>āgnihotra-kratu (EI 26), the five rites of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR>(SITI), offering of flowers, fruits, uncooked rice, etc.,<BR>to the gods; same as śrībali. Cf. Nārāyaṇa-baly-upahāra in the<BR>sense of Nārayaṇa-pūjā (Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, p. 363).<BR>Cf. varāha-bali, ‘pig sacrifice’ (Ep Ind., Vol. XXXVI,<BR>p. 39). Cf. śrī-bali, havir-bali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलीवर्द|बलीवर्दः|बलीवर्द्द|बलीवर्द्दः<BR>balīvarda, cf. a-paramparā-balīvarda, etc. (IE 8-5); a<BR>pair of bullocks (which the villagers were obliged to provide<BR>for the cart of the royal officers when they camped or toured<BR>in their villages). See also vara-balīvarda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाण|बाणः<BR>bāṇa (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बानसवेर्गडे<BR>Bānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ (599-11-2), variant spelling of Kannaḍa<BR>Bhānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्ध|बंध|बंधः|बन्धः<BR>bandha (EI 31), a dam or highway.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धदण्ड<BR>bandha-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12, 33), probably, ransom or<BR>fine in lieu of imprisonment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धाण<BR>bandhāṇa (Chamba), a settlement, an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धाणपट्ट<BR>bandhāṇa-paṭṭa (Chamba), an agreement, a deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धनीय<BR>bandhanīya (LP), ‘to be fixed’, i. e. to be served to one;<BR>cf. Gujarātī bāndhī āpavāṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धेज<BR>bandheja (Chamba), a settlement, an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धु|बंधु|बंधुः|बन्धुः<BR>bandhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बप्प<BR>bappa (EI 29, 30; CII 3; etc.), a Prakrit word meaning<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-046" target="_blank">Page-046+ 40</a>]<BR>‘the father’, often used in Sanskrit inscriptions. Cf. bappa-<BR>bhaṭṭāraka-pāda-parigṛhīta (EI 31), epithet of certain rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बप्पभट्टारक<BR>bappa-bhaṭṭāraka (EI 4), ‘the father, the lord’. Cf. bappa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बार<BR>bāra (EI 13), Telugu; the distance between the ends of<BR>out-stretched arms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाराड्<BR>bārāḍ, derived from Sanskrit varāṭa or varāṭaka, ‘a<BR>cowrie-shell (used as money)’ (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 18).<BR>Cf. varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बरट|बरटः<BR>baraṭa (CII 4), a plant grown for fencing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बार्हस्पत्य|बार्हस्पत्यः<BR>bārhaspatya (IA 11), name of a reckoning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बर्कन्दाष्<BR>Barkandāz, Persian; same as Pāik (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बर्तना<BR>bartanā (IE 3-5), Rājasthānī; a blunt stick for writing on<BR>a wooden slate; same as barthā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बर्था<BR>barthā (IE 3-5), same as bartanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बसिलेओस्<BR>Basilĕos Basilĕon Mĕgalŏu (IE 8-2), Greek; ‘of the great<BR>king of kings;’ used in the legend on the coins of the Scytho-<BR>Parthian kings; adapted from old Persian Khshyāthiya Khshāya-<BR>thiyānām, ‘the king of kings’; translated into Prakrit as Maha-<BR>rajasa Rajarajasa (or Rajadirajasa) mahalasa (Sanskrit Mahā-<BR>rājasya Rājarājasya mahataḥ or Rājātirājasya mahataḥ).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बसिलेओस्<BR>Basilĕos Mĕgalŏu (IE 8-2), Greek; ‘of the great king’,<BR>found in the legend on the coins of Indo-Greek kings at first<BR>translated in Prakrit as Rajasa mahatakasa (Sanskrit Rājñaḥ<BR>mahataḥ) and later as Maharajasa (Sanskrit Mahārājasya);<BR>adapted from old Persian Kshāyathiya vazrka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बति<BR>ba-ti (IE 8-1), abbreviation of bahula-pakṣa-tithi. See ba-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाव<BR>bāva (CII 3, etc.), a Prakrit word denoting ‘a relative<BR>of the same generation with the father’; generally, ‘an uncle’;<BR>used in Sanskrit inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बायि<BR>Bāyi (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 35),<BR>suffix to the name of respectable women; same as Bāi; wrongly<BR>regarded as derived from the Kannaḍa words abbĕ (Sanskrit<BR>ambā) and āyi (Sanskrit āryā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेहरामहापात्र<BR>Beharā-mahāpātra (EI 28), Oḏiyā; official designation;<BR>probably, Sanskrit Vyavahārika-mahāpātra. See Vyavahārika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेन्गलि<BR>Bengali, Anglicised spelling of Vaṅgālī; the name of the<BR>people, language and alphabet of Bengal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेण्टकार<BR>Beṇṭakāra (CITD), same as Beṭakāra, beṭa (Telugu-<BR>Kannaḍa) meaning ‘the separation of lovers’. As an epithet of<BR>a ruler, Beṇṭakāra means ‘one who causes the separation of his<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-047" target="_blank">Page-047+ 40</a>]<BR>enemies’ wives from their husbands’; cf. ripu-nārī-vaidhavya-vidhā-<BR>yak-ācārya, ‘one who renders the wives of his enemies widows’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ|भं|भः<BR>bha (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyseven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ|भं|भः<BR>Bha° (PJS), abbreviation of Bhagavān (especially in<BR>medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भा<BR>bhā° (PJS), abbreviation of bhāryā (especially in medieval<BR>Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाडक<BR>bhāḍaka (LP), same as Sanskrit bhāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भदन्त|भदंत|भदंतः|भदन्तः<BR>Bhadanta (IA 11; LL), a title of monks (Buddhist, Jain<BR>and Ājīvika); cf. Bhadatasa aya-Isipālitasa, ‘of the Reverend<BR>Lord Ṛṣipālita’; also cf. Bhadantī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भदन्ती<BR>Bhadantī (LL), used as the title of a Buddhist nun;<BR>cf. Bhadanta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्र|भद्रं|भद्रः<BR>bhadra (SII 2), probably, an auspicious mark.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रा<BR>bhadrā (IA 26), same as ba-di 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाद्र|भाद्रः<BR>Bhādra (IE 8-1), same as Bhādrapada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रभोग<BR>bhadra-bhoga, cf. ‘according to bhadra-bhoga’ (Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 215); principle of proper enjoyment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रघट|भद्रघटः<BR>bhadra-ghaṭa, cf. Tamil pattira-kaḍam (SITI), a pot<BR>filled with water and sanctified by rites.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रमुख<BR>bhadra-mukha (EI 16), an honorific used with personal<BR>names.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रनिगम<BR>bhadra-nigama (LL), a righteous hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रासन|भद्रासनं<BR>bhadr-āsana (EI 25), a throne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाग|भागः<BR>bhāga (IE 8-5; CII 3, 4; EI 30; HRS), the king's share<BR>of the produce, distinguished from bali in the Rummindei<BR>inscription and the Junagadh inscription of Rudradāman and<BR>from kara in many other records; later, tax in general,<BR>identical with bali and kara (according to lexicons); cf.<BR>references in the Arthaśāstra to (1) lavaṇa-bhāga (king's share<BR>of salt sold by private merchants), (2) udaka-bhāga (king's<BR>grain share levied as water-tax upon irrigated fields),<BR>(3) king's share of the produce of mines leased out to private<BR>persons; (4) share paid to the king by merchants for selling<BR>the royal merchandise.<BR>(IE 8-5), dues (see kara); generally, the king's share of<BR>grains, which was originally one-sixth.<BR>(IE 8-4), a subdivision of a district or a territory.<BR>(EI 23, 33), an allotment; a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागभोग<BR>bhāga-bhoga (CII 3; etc.), a fiscal expression in which<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-048" target="_blank">Page-048+ 40</a>]<BR>bhāga means the king's share of the produce and bhoga the<BR>periodical supplies made by tenants to the king; cf. bhāga-<BR>bhog-ādika, bhāga-bhoga-kara-hirany-ādika (EI 23), meaning<BR>‘royal dues’; see bhāga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागभोगकर<BR>bhāga-bhoga-kara (HRS), taken by some as a single levy<BR>and explained as the king's grain-share, identical with bhāga<BR>of the Arthaśāstra and bali of the Smṛtis, though distinguished<BR>from dhānya in a Maitraka record, where it has been supposed<BR>to mean a fixed contribution in kind as distinguished from<BR>the contribution consisting of a share of the produce. If<BR>bhāgabhogakara was a single levy (and did not indicate<BR>bhāga, bhoga and kara), it may have really been a tax collected<BR>in lieu of bhāga (grain share) and bhoga (periodical offerings).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागदुघ<BR>Bhāgadugha (HD), an official title; probably the same<BR>as Bhāgahāra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागहर|भागहरः<BR>Bhāgahara (EI 24), same as Bhāgin; a collector of the<BR>king's grain share. Cf. Bhāgahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागहार|भागहारः<BR>Bhāgahāra (HD), ‘he who recovers the [king's] share<BR>[of the produce of land]’; one of the six officers of each<BR>village, according to Śukra, II. 120. Cf. Bhāgahara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागलाग<BR>bhāgalāga, cf. bhāgalāg-ādika (LP), payments in kind or taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागकर्षण<BR>bhāga-karṣaṇa (LP), taking away the portion allotted to<BR>someone else.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगण|भगणः<BR>bhagaṇa (IA 19), a bangle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवद्भक्त|भगवद्भक्तः<BR>Bhagavad-bhakta (CII 3, etc.), a Vaiṣṇava sectarian<BR>title indicating ‘a follower of the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्|भगवन्त्<BR>Bhagavat (ML; CII 3, 4), ‘the lord’ or ‘the divine’; an<BR>epithet of divinities such as Viṣṇu, Buddha, Jinendra, Nārāyaṇa,<BR>Śiva, the Sun-god, Kārttikeya, etc; also applied to sages, etc.<BR>in the sense of ‘venerable’, e. g. to Vyāsa, the arranger of the<BR>Vedas; rarely applied to kings apparently on account of their<BR>saintliness (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागवत|भागवतं|भागवतः<BR>Bhāgavata (LL), a votary of the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu).<BR>(CII 3; etc.), a Vaiṣṇava sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवती<BR>Bhagavatī (CII 3, 4; etc.), feminine form of Bhagavat<BR>(q. v.); often applied to goddesses, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्पादाचार्य<BR>Bhagavatpād-ācārya (EI 6), epithet of a Vaiṣṇava religious<BR>teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्पादकर्मकर<BR>Bhagavatpāda-karmakara (CII 4), ‘a servant of the feet<BR>of the Bhagavat’; epithet of a temple official.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागिक|भागिकं<BR>Bhāgika (IE 8-3; HD), probably, the collector of the<BR>king's grain share; same as Bhāgahāra. See Vogel, Ant. Ch.<BR>St., p. 166. Cf. Bhāgin.<BR>(EI 13), mentioned along with Bhogika; probably, one<BR>getting a share [in a free-holding]. See Aṃśa-bṛhadbhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागिन्<BR>Bhāgin (EI 24), same as Bhāgika, a collector of the king's<BR>grain share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भग्न|भग्नं<BR>bhagna (CII 1), ‘departed’, ‘lost’, i. e. ‘inferior’; cf.<BR>the Hindī verb bhāgnā, Bengali bhāgā.<BR>Cf. bhagna-viśīrṇa-samāracana, repairs to the rents in and<BR>the wornout parts of a building (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p.<BR>144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भग्नक्रिया<BR>bhagna-kriyā (IA 7), same as bhagna-saṃskāra, repairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाग्यरेखा<BR>bhāgya-rekhā (EI 3), line of fortune on the palm.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भमाति<BR>bhamāti (EI 7), corruption of brahma-hatyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भैक्षक<BR>bhaikṣaka (EI 21), land set apart for charity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भैत्र<BR>bhaitra (IA 14), corruption of vahitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्षण|भक्षणं<BR>bhakṣaṇa, Tamil pakkiṇam (SITI), confection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्तादाय<BR>bhakt-ādāya (SITI), same as Tamil pakt-ātāyam (SITI),<BR>revenue in rice or paddy. Cf. bhakt-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्ताय<BR>bhakt-āya, cf. Kannaḍa bhatt-āya (SII 11-1); same as<BR>bhakt-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्तग्राम<BR>bhakta-grāma, cf. bhatta-grāma, provision-village; village<BR>granted for maintenance (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, pp. 8, 92; cf.<BR>Vol. XVIII, pp. 191, 193).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्ति|भक्तिः<BR>bhakti (CII 4), devotion to a god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्ती<BR>bhaktī (EI 8), name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्तोद्देशक<BR>bhakt-oddeśaka (LL), Buddhist; distributor of food.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भं|भ|भः<BR>Bhaṃ° (PJS), abbreviation of Bhaṇḍārin (especially in<BR>medieval Jain inscriptions). See Bhīṇḍārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भामण्डल<BR>bhā-maṇḍala (HA), halo, aureole; same as prabhā-<BR>maṇḍala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भमती<BR>bhamatī (HA), same as jagatī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भंडि|भण्डि|भंडिः|भण्डिः<BR>bhaṃḍi (CITD), same as Telugu baṃḍi, ‘a cart’; really<BR>‘a cart load’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भानसवेर्गडे<BR>Bhānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; same as Mahānas-<BR>ādhyakṣa; superintendent of the royal kitchen. Cf. Sūpakāra-<BR>pati, Khādyaṭapākika, Mahānasika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाणक|भाणकः<BR>Bhāṇaka (LL), Buddhist; a preacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्ड|भांड|भांडं|भाण्डं|भाण्डः<BR>bhāṇḍa, cf. bhaṇḍa (EI 5), a bale of goods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डभृतवहित्र<BR>bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra (IE 8-8), ‘a wagon full of pots or jars’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डाध्यक्ष<BR>Bhāṇḍ-ādhyakṣa (EI 28), officer in charge of the store-<BR>house. Cf. Bhāṇḍāgār-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागार|भांडागार|भाण्डागारः<BR>bhāṇḍ-āgāra (EI 23, 30), a treasury or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागाराधिकृत<BR>Bhāṇḍāgār-ādhikṛta (EI 12; BL; HRS), an officer employed<BR>in the treasury or store-house or the officer in charge of it.<BR>Cf. Bhāṇḍāgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागारप्रथम<BR>Bhāṇḍāgāra-prathama (HD), the chief of the royal store-<BR>house or treasury. See JBBRAS, Vol. IX, p. 219.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागारिक|भाण्डागारिकः<BR>Bhāṇḍāgārika (IE 8-3; CII 4; HD; BL), officer in charge<BR>of the treasury or the royal store-house. See Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भण्डार<BR>bhaṇḍāra, same as Sanskrit bhāṇḍāra; cf. Bhaṇdārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डार|भांडार|भांडारं<BR>bhāṇḍāra, cf. Tamil paṇḍāra-kkal (SITI), stone of standard<BR>weight used in the treasury; also cf. paṇḍāra-kkaṇkāṇi, treasury<BR>officer, supervisor of the treasury.<BR>(IA 23), the five images used in the worship of Bhūtas,<BR>e. g., Jārandāya, etc.<BR>Cf. paṇḍāram (SII 1), a treasury; a Śaiva mendicant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डारपुस्तक<BR>Bhāṇḍāra-pustaka, cf. Tamil baṇḍāra-ppottagam (EI 25),<BR>literally, ‘account book of the treasury’; a treasury accountant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भण्डारिन्<BR>Bhaṇḍārin, Bhāṇḍārin (EI 9; SITI), officer in charge<BR>of the treasury; same as Bhāṇḍāgārika. Cf. Sejjeya-bhaṇḍārī<BR>(EI 13), ‘officer in charge of the stores in the king's bed-<BR>chamber’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भङ्ग|भंग|भंगः|भङ्गः<BR>bhaṅga (Chamba), a land measure; a share or portion.<BR>(IA 23), hemp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भानु|भानुः<BR>Bhānu (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भार|भारः<BR>bhāra (EI 10), a weight equal to 2000 palas.<BR>(LP), probably, a load or bundle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भरक<BR>bharaka (CII 4), name of a measure or weight; one load<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR>Cf. mahiṣ-oṣṭra-bharaka (IE 8-8), ‘a load on a buffalo<BR>or a camel’; cf. bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भरण|भरणं|भरणः<BR>bharaṇa (CII 4), name of a measure.<BR>(EI 1), probably, a load [of stones].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भारतवर्<BR>Bhāratavar (SITI), Tamil; fishermen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भरतकला<BR>Bharata-kalā (EI 33), the art of dancing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भारतीवृत्ति<BR>Bhāratī-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart for expounding the<BR>Mahābhārata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भर्ग|भर्गः<BR>Bharga (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भारिका<BR>bhārikā (IE 8-5; EI 25), cf. bhārikāyāṃ vaṇik-putrasy =<BR>āṣṭottara-śataṃ rūpakāṇām; a crime, the nature of which is<BR>uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाषा<BR>bhāṣā (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, a written declaration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाषाभेद<BR>bhāṣā-bheda (LP), breach of words.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाष्यवृत्ति<BR>Bhāṣya-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart for meeting the ex-<BR>penses of expounding the Śrī-Bhāṣya of Rāmānuja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट|भटः<BR>Bhaṭa (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; EI 30; HD), same as Bhaṭa-<BR>manuṣya; probably derived from bhṛta which is sometimes used<BR>in its place. Generally used along with cāṭa or chātra; literally,<BR>‘a soldier’; but really a Pāik, Barkandāz or Piāda, i. e. a constable.<BR>It is spelt as bhaṭṭa in the medieval inscriptions of Eastern<BR>India, though rarely the two are distinguished. See Bhaṭṭa.<BR>(SITI), a personal servant or soldier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाटक|भाटकं|भाटकः<BR>bhāṭaka (EI 30), same as prabhāṭaka; rent or hiring<BR>charges; cf. naukā-bhāṭaka (EI 14).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भटमनुष्य<BR>Bhaṭa-manuṣya (IE 8-3; EI 31; LL), explained as ‘a<BR>soldier, policeman or warden’; a Barkandāz, Pāik or Piāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भटार<BR>Bhaṭāra (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa corruption of Bhaṭṭāraka;<BR>also spelt Bhaḍāra and Bhaḻāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्ट|भट्टः<BR>Bhaṭṭa (IE 8-3), cf a-caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-praveśa (IE 8-5);<BR>same as Bhaṭa of earlier records; but rarely distinguished<BR>from Bhaṭa, Bhaṭṭa in that ease meaning ‘a minstrel’.<BR>(CII 3, 4; etc.), a title of respect attached to the names<BR>of learned Brāhmaṇas.<BR>(IE 8-3), a minstrel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टा<BR>Bhaṭṭā° (PJS), abbreviation of Bhaṭṭāraka (in medieval<BR>Jain inscriptions); an epithet of Jain teachers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टभाग<BR>Bhaṭṭa-bhāga (EI 15), same as bhaṭṭa-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टग्राम<BR>Bhaṭṭa-grāma (EI 15, 25), a village owned by learned<BR>Brāhmaṇas as a rent-free holding; same as an agrahāra village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टामाकुतिक<BR>Bhaṭṭāmākutika (EI 7), an official designation of uncer-<BR>tain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टमहत्तर<BR>Bhaṭṭa-mahattara (EI 30), a Bhaṭṭa who was a Mahattara,<BR>or a leading Bhaṭṭa. Bhaṭṭa may not be a corruption of<BR>paṭṭa (cf. Bhaṭṭa-nāyaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टनायक<BR>Bhaṭṭa-nāyaka (EI 9), see Bhaṭṭa and Nāyaka (chief of a<BR>district) as well as Bhaṭṭa-mahattara. Cf. also Paṭṭa-nāyaka<BR>of medieval Orissan epigraphs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टपुत्र<BR>Bhaṭṭaputra (EI 4; LP; BL), title of Brāhmaṇas; epithet<BR>of a Brāhmaṇa whose father was famous for learning.<BR>(LP), explained as ‘sepoys or soldiers’.<BR>(EI 11), explained as ‘a panegyrist’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारक|भट्टारकः<BR>Bhaṭṭāraka (IE 8-2; CII 3; EI 30), title used in Sanskrit<BR>but really Prakrit derived from Sanskrit bhartṛ through the<BR>plural form bhartāraḥ = Prakrit bhaṭṭāra (see Svāmin); often<BR>suffixed to the personal names of paramount sovereigns as<BR>well as of feudatory Mahārājas, or Yuvarājas (crown-princes);<BR>applied to gods and priests in the sense of ‘worthy of worship<BR>or sacred’. Cf. bappa-bhaṭṭāraka-pāda-parigṛhīta, bhaṭṭāraka-<BR>Mahāsena-parigṛhīta, etc.<BR>(EI 33), the king.<BR>(SII 1), title of Jain religious teachers.<BR>(CII 4), title of Śaiva ascetics, etc.<BR>(LP), a respected man.<BR>(EI 11), probably, epithet of the chief priest of a temple.<BR>(SITI), a deity; a spiritual preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारकपादानुध्यात<BR>Bhaṭṭāraka-pād-ānudhyāta (CII 4), ‘meditating on (or,<BR>favoured by) the feet of the lord paramount’; epithet of the<BR>feudatories and officers of the Gupta emperors and later<BR>imperial rulers. See Paramabhaṭṭāraka-pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारकप्रभ<BR>Bhaṭṭārakaprabha (CII 4), a title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टराणक<BR>Bhaṭṭa-rāṇaka (EI 9) see Bhaṭṭa, Rāṇaka, Bhaṭṭa-mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टवृत्ति<BR>Bhaṭṭa-vṛtti (EI 25; SII 1), a grant for the maintenance<BR>of the Bhaṭṭas or learned Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टवृत्तिमान्य<BR>Bhaṭṭavṛtti-mānya (SITI), tax-free land (inām) given<BR>for the support of Brāhmaṇas; same as bhaṭṭa-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारिका<BR>Bhaṭṭārikā (EI 23; CII 3; etc.), feminine form of<BR>Bhaṭṭāraka (q. v.); a title of the wives of independent and<BR>feudatory rulers; often suffixed to personal names.<BR>Cf. Tamil paṭṭārikai (SITI), name of the goddess Durgā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टोपाध्याय<BR>Bhaṭṭ-opādhyāya (EI 23), title of a Brāhmaṇa teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भौलि<BR>bhauli, bhaulī (Chamba), a share, portion or allotment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भौमयन्त्र<BR>bhauma-yantra (IA 14), a particular mystic diagram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भव|भवं|भवः<BR>Bhava (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाव|भावः<BR>bhāva (EI 26), a brother-in-law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भवन|भवनं<BR>bhavana (LL), a temple. Cf. pura, āyatana, ālaya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भावना<BR>bhāvanā (CII 4), sentiment, e. g., maitrī, etc.<BR>(EI 3), Jain; a method of kāy-otsarga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भवसृज्<BR>Bhavasṛj (CII 3), ‘the creator of existence’; an epithet<BR>of the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भावशुद्धि|भावशुद्धिः<BR>bhāva-śuddhi (CII 1), purity of mind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भवत्|भवन्त्<BR>bhavat, cf. sa bhavān (EI 3), same as tatrabhavān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाविनी<BR>Bhāvinī (IA 10), same as Devadāsī; a dancing girl<BR>attached to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भविष्यक्किडैप्पु<BR>bhaviṣya-kkiḍai-ppuṟam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax-<BR>free land set apart to enable a teacher to reside permanently<BR>in a village for teaching.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भव्य|भव्यं|भव्यः<BR>bhavya (EI 3, 8), the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाव्य|भाव्यं<BR>bhāvya, cf. rāja-bhāvya-sarva-pratyāya-sameta (EI 23),<BR>income, levies; same as ābhāvya. According to some, bhāvya<BR>and ābhāvya mean pāghḏī. Cf. talār-ābhāvya.<BR>(LP), probably the same as bhāvyapada-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेरी<BR>bherī (SITI, ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेरुण्ड|भेरुंड|भेरुण्डं<BR>bheruṇḍa (EI 31), a shortened form of gaṇḍabheruṇḍa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेत्<BR>bhet (IA 11), Pañjābī; low lands inundated by rivers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेट<BR>bheṭa (IE 8-5; EI 29), presents to be offered by a sub-<BR>ject or subordinate to a ruler on occasions; occasional offering<BR>of money or presents; same as vandāpanā. See bheṭana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेटन<BR>bheṭana (LP), a present or gift; cf. bheṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीदा<BR>bhīdā (LP), ‘straitened circumstances’; cf. Gujarātī bhīd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षा<BR>bhikṣā (IE 8-4), a grant or endowment; cf. ekādaśa-<BR>Rudra-bhikṣā (EI 32), an endowment in the gods’ name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षु|भिक्षुः<BR>Bhikṣu (EI 7, 21; CII 3; ML), Buddhist monk, also<BR>called Śākya-bhikṣu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुहल<BR>Bhikṣu-hala (LL), ‘the monks’ land’; rent-free land in the<BR>possession of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुहलपरिहार<BR>Bhikṣuhala-parihāra, cf. Prakrit Bhikhuhala-parihāra (HRS),<BR>known from Śātavāhana records as a number of privileges<BR>relating to rent-free land belonging to the community of<BR>Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुणी<BR>Bhikṣuṇī (EI 25; CII 3; LL), feminine form of Bhikṣu;<BR>‘a Buddhist nun’; also called Śākya-bhikṣuṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुण्युपाश्रय<BR>Bhikṣuṇy-upāśraya (LL), Buddhist; a nunnery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुणीसङ्घ<BR>Bhikṣuṇī-saṅgha, cf. bhikkhuṇī-saṃgha (EI 23), a community<BR>of nuns.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुराज<BR>Bhikṣurāja (LL), title of a pious [Jain] king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुसङ्घ|भिक्षुसङ्घः<BR>Bhikṣu-saṅgha (EI 26; CII 4), community of Buddhist<BR>monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीमप्रिय<BR>Bhīmapriya (EI 11), name of a coin (dramma).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीमसेनिकर्पूर<BR>bhīmaseni-karpūra (SII 13), a kind of camphor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिषक्<BR>Bhiṣak (HD), the king's medical advisor. See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR>(EI 24), a physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीष्माष्टमी<BR>Bhīṣmāṣṭamī (IA 17), Māgha su-di 8 or amānta Māgha<BR>(i. e. pūrṇimānta Phālguna) va-di 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीट्<BR>bhīṭ (IA 15), see bhīṭī and bhṛṣṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भितरभण्डारअधिकारिन्<BR>Bhitara-bhaṇḍāra-adhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 28), Oḏiyā;<BR>Sanskrit Abhyantara-bhāṇḍār-ādhikārin, ‘officer in charge of the<BR>inner store-house or treasury (i. e. one within the palace or<BR>the harem)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीतरनवर<BR>bhītara-navara (EI 28), Oḏiyā = Sanskrit abhyantara-<BR>nagara; the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीठ<BR>bhīṭha (EI 31), probably, a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीटी<BR>bhīṭī (IA 15), see bhṛṣṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भित्तिचित्र<BR>bhitti-citra, wall-painting (Journ. Mad. Univ., Vol. XXXII,<BR>p. 141).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भित्वरमान्य<BR>Bhitvaramānya (IA 17), probably, a mistake for Abhitva-<BR>ramāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोग|भोगः<BR>bhoga (IE 8-4; CII 3; EI 23, 33), literally, ‘enjoyment’<BR>(cf. bhukti); a jāgīr (cf. Mahārāja-Sarvanātha-bhoga, Mahā-<BR>sāmantādhipati-Śrīdhara-bhoga, etc.); possession (cf. bhog-<BR>ādhīnā gṛhītā). Originally ‘enjoyment’; then ‘property’,<BR>‘a jāgīr’; then also a territorial unit which was generally the<BR>subdivision of a district (IE 8-4; EI 25; 28; CII 4). See<BR>bhukti, āhāra.<BR>Cf. Kaivarta-bhoga (IE 8-4; EI 2; CII 1), the fishermen's<BR>preserve.<BR>(IE 8-5; EI 29, 30; HRS), periodical supplies of fruits,<BR>firewood, flowers and the like which the villagers had to<BR>supply to the king; sometimes explained as ‘tax in kind’<BR>(CII 4).<BR>(EI 1), [an object of] enjoyment.<BR>(SITI), tax-free land set apart for the enjoyment of a<BR>person for the performance of specified services; same as<BR>mānya. See bhogottara, Bhogin, etc.<BR>Cf. bhoge (LP), ‘for the right of enjoyment’.<BR>Cf. sa-bhoga (IA 9), privilege of the donee of rent-free<BR>land; probably refers to aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगभाग<BR>bhoga-bhāga (CII 3, etc.,), the same as bhāga-bhoga. Cf.<BR>bhoga-bhāga-kara-hiraṇy-ādi (EI 23), royal dues; see bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगजनपद<BR>bhoga-janapada (EI 12), probably, a free-holding in the<BR>country-side, or a rent-free area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगलाभ|भोगलाभः<BR>bhoga-lābha (EI 33), usufruct in lieu of interest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगपति|भोगपतिः<BR>Bhogapati (IE 8-3; EI 25, 27; HD), an Ināmdār or Jāgīr-<BR>dār, or an officer in charge of inām lands or jāgīrs, or the<BR>officer in charge of a territorial unit called bhoga. The last<BR>alternative is more probable; cf. Bhogika, etc. See also<BR>Mitākṣarā on the Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 320; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX,<BR>p. 298. See Bhuktipati, Bhogikapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगपतिक<BR>Bhogapatika (IE 8-3; EI 23), same as Bhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगपत्र<BR>bhoga-patra (ASLV, SITI), a deed recording conveyance<BR>of land; a lease deed; the deed of re-conveyance of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगस्त्री<BR>bhoga-strī, a concubine (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 272).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगत्रा<BR>bhogatrā (IE 8-5), same as bhogottara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगावनीय<BR>bhogāvanīya (LP), ‘should be enjoyed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगायक<BR>bhog-āyaka (ASLV, SITI), land held as the result of a<BR>mortgage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिजन<BR>Bhogi-jana (EI 33), explained as ‘a village headman’.<BR>Cf. Bhogika,<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिक|भोगिकः<BR>Bhogika (IE 8-3; CII 3; HD; BL), the owner of a<BR>bhoga or jāgīr; a Jāgīrdār or Ināmdār; same as Bhogin. See<BR>Bhoktṛ. Explained by some as the head of a district, or the<BR>collector of the State's share of the produce of lands taken in<BR>kind (Bomb. Gaz., Vol. I, Part i, p. 82). See CII, Vol. III,<BR>pp. 96, 104.<BR>(IE 8-3); EI 18; 23), a groom or horse-keeper, accord-<BR>ing to lexicons; cf. its Telugu modification Bhoi, ‘a palanquin-<BR>bearer’. But these meanings may have been derived from the<BR>first as the people appear to have enjoyed rent-free land for<BR>their services.<BR>(EI 33), same as Bhojaka meaning a Jāgīrdār or Ināmdār.<BR>(CII 4), explained as ‘the head of a bhoga’.<BR>(EI 5), explained as ‘a village proprietor’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिकपाल<BR>Bhogikapāla, Bhogikapālaka (EI 5; CII 4; BL), superin-<BR>tendent of the jāgīrs and cess collector; cf. Bhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिन्<BR>Bhogin (IE 8-3; EI 12, 28, 29, 30; BL), one in possession<BR>of a bhoga or jāgīr; a Jāgīrdār; same as Bhogika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगीन<BR>bhogīna (EI 13), cf. dattidāyaka-sādhupratipādita-prāg-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-056" target="_blank">Page-056+ 40</a>]<BR>bhujyamān-āvicchinna-bhogīna-bhuvām translated rather loosely as<BR>‘of the pieces of land in all the places that have been obtained<BR>in good manner from liberal donors’; probably, ‘[land] under<BR>possession’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिनी<BR>bhoginī, cf. bogi (EI 7), a concubine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिरूप<BR>bhogi-rūpa (EI 12, 28), one who enjoys a free-holding<BR>as a representative of the real free-holder, or a title-holder<BR>who is not in actual possession of the land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगियार्<BR>bhogiyār (SITI), Tamil; mistress, concubine; cf. bhogyār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगोद्धरणिक<BR>Bhog-oddharaṇika (HD), explained as ‘the collector of the<BR>king's share of the grains’; cf. bhoga, caur-oddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगोत्तर<BR>bhogottara (IE 8-5; EI 33), corrupt form of bhogatrā;<BR>land granted to the family priest for his services; grant for the<BR>enjoyment of a Brāhmaṇa or deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोग्या<BR>bhogyā, cf. pokiyār (SITI), a concubine; see bhogiyār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोग्यतिथि<BR>bhogya-tithi (CII 3), the portion of a tithi that is still<BR>to run.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोइ<BR>Bhoi, Telugu modification of Sanskrit Bhogin (q. v.);<BR>palanquin-bearer (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 308, note 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोज|भोजः<BR>Bhoja, Bhojaka (IE 8-2; EI 1; 27; HD; LL), a Jāgīrdār;<BR>title of a feudatory; cf. the feminine form Bhojikī; also Mahā-<BR>bhoja. See Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5.<BR>(EI 3; CII 3), a priest; title of a class of priests.<BR>Cf. Tamil pośar (SITI), one who enjoys a thing; the<BR>possessor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनचतुःशाल<BR>bhojana-catuḥśāla (LL), Buddhist; a dining hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनआक्षयणी<BR>bhojana-ākṣayaṇī, bhojan-ākṣayaṇī (EI 32), a permanent<BR>endowment created for the maintenance of the donee; cf.<BR>akṣayanīvī, grāmagrāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनमण्डप<BR>bhojana-maṇḍapa (LL), Buddhist; a refectory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनशाला<BR>bhojana-śālā (EI 23), an almshouse; a free-feeding house.<BR>Cf. sattra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजिकी<BR>Bhojikī (LL), wife of a Bhojaka (q. v.). cf. Mahābhojī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोज्पुरी<BR>Bhojpurī, language and people of the Bhojpur Pargana<BR>of the Shahabad District of Bihar and the adjoining<BR>regions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोक्तृ<BR>Bhoktṛ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 193), same as Bhogin,<BR>Bhogika; an Ināmdār or Jāgīrdar; cf. Sammāṇaka-bhoktā; also<BR>Bhoktāri (EI 11), a free-holder.<BR>(BL), a proprietor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोट्टविष्टि<BR>Bhoṭṭa-viṣṭi (HRS), known from Nepal records; forced<BR>labour for carrying loads for officers sent to Tibet. See H.<BR>Rev. Syst., p. 233.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ्रमजलगति<BR>bhrama-jala-gati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 98), probably,<BR>a sluice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भृष्टी<BR>bhṛṣṭī (IA 15), ‘raised ground [near a tank] for plant-<BR>ing piper betel’; cf. bhīṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भृत|भृतः<BR>bhṛta (LP), loaded.<BR>(IE 8-8), cf. bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra, ‘a wagonful of pots<BR>or jars’. See bharaka.<BR>Cf. a-bhṛta-prāvesya for a-bhaṭa-prāveśya, bhṛta being<BR>used for bhaṭa in the sense of a Pāik, Barkandāz or Piāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भू<BR>bhū (IA 17), a land measure; equal to four bhū-māṣakas.<BR>See bhūmi.<BR>(EI 9), a land measure or a plot of land.<BR>(IE 7-1-2; EI 15, 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूभृत्<BR>bhūbhṛt (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूधर|भूधरः<BR>bhūdhara (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूच्छिद्रन्याय<BR>bhūcchidra-nyāya (EI 22), same as bhūmicchidra-nyāya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलन्माडै<BR>Bhujabalan-māḍai (SITI), name of a coin of the māḍai<BR>(māḍha) type. See māḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलप्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Bhujabalapratāpacakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलप्रौढप्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Bhujabalaprauḍhapratāpacakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजङ्ग|भुजंग|भुजंगः|भुजङ्गः<BR>bhujaṅga (IA 20), an ogre. The word bhujaṅga was<BR>adopted in Javanese in the sense of a ‘pupil, disciple, scholar;<BR>a philologist, poet, literary councillor; an officially appointed<BR>professional usually residing at or near the court’. It has been<BR>suggested on this basis that Bhavadeva-bhaṭṭa's title<BR>Bālavalabhī-bhujaṅga may really mean ‘the pupil of the<BR>Bālavalabhī school’. See IHQ, Vol. XXVII, pp. 80-82.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजिष्यपत्र<BR>bhujiṣya-patra (EI 24), a document granting maintenance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुज्यमान<BR>bhujyamāna (IA 18), also prabhujyamāna; ‘being enjoyed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्ततिथि<BR>bhukta-tithi (CII 3), the elapsed portion of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्ति|भुक्तिः<BR>bhukti (IE 8-4; EI 28, 33), a province including a group<BR>of districts called viṣaya or maṇḍala; small territorial unit<BR>like a Pargana in South India; cf. bhoga.<BR>(IE 8-3; 8-4; CII 3), literally, ‘enjoyment’; same as<BR>bhoga; a jāgīr; originally meaning ‘enjoyment’; then ‘property’<BR>or ‘a jāgīr’; then ‘a province’. See bhoga.<BR>(BL), personal property.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-058" target="_blank">Page-058+ 40</a>]<BR>Cf. putti, pukti (SITI), the enjoyment of a property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्तिमण्डल<BR>bhukti-maṇḍala (IE 8-4), originally a bhukti but later on<BR>a maṇḍala; cf. Daṇḍabhukti-maṇḍala, āhāra-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्तिपति<BR>Bhuktipati (IE 8-3), a Jāgīrdār; or, the officer in charge<BR>of a territorial unit called bhukti. See Bhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमाषक<BR>bhūmāṣaka (IA 17), a land measure, four bhūmāṣakas<BR>making one bhū (q. v.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुम्भुक<BR>bhumbhuka (EI 13), Kannaḍa; cf. bhuvana-bhumbhuka,<BR>probably, ‘an ornament of the world’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमि|भूमिः<BR>bhūmi, bhūmī (EI 3; CII 3), a particular land measure;<BR>sometimes also called bhū and regarded as equal to four bhū-<BR>māṣakas (cf. bhū).<BR>(CII 4), a territorial division.<BR>(EI 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्र<BR>bhūmicchidra (IE 8-5), sometimes explained as ‘unculti-<BR>vable land’. See bhūmicchidra-nyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रन्याय<BR>bhūmicchidra-nyāya (IE 8-5; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HRS),<BR>literally, ‘the maxim of the fallow land’; the principle of the<BR>rent-free enjoyment of land by one who brings it under cultiva-<BR>tion for the first time. See Ep. Ind., Vol XXIX, p. 86. The<BR>maxim is based on the old custom of allowing a person, who<BR>first brings a plot of fallow or jungle land under cultivation<BR>for the first time, to enjoy it without paying rent. Bhūmi-<BR>cchidra gradually came to mean ‘uncultivable land’. See<BR>bhūmicchidrapidhāna-nyāya, avanirandhra-nyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रपिधानन्याय<BR>bhūmicchidrapidhāna-nyāya (IE 8-5; EI 11), the same as<BR>bhūmicchidra-nyāya; but it means ‘the maxim of covering up the<BR>hole in the land’ referring probably to the reclamation of<BR>fallow land for the first time; cf. bhūmicchidra understood<BR>in the sense of kṛṣy-ayogyā bhū, ‘land unfit for cultivation’.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, p. 86.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रविधानन्याय<BR>bhūmicchidravidhāna-nyāya (EI 24); same as bhūmicchidra-<BR>nyāya, bhumicchidrapidhāna-nyāya. Chidra-vidhāna = furrowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिपेण्डे<BR>bhūmipeṇḍe (ASLV), a mark of honour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिपुत्र|भूमिपुत्रः<BR>bhūmi-putra. cf. pūmi-puttirar (SITI), husbandmen<BR>regarded as the sons of Mother Earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूप|भूपः<BR>bhūpa (IA 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुर्ज<BR>bhurja (IE 3-2), really ‘the birch’; but same as lekhana;<BR>a written document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूस्फोट|भूस्फोटः<BR>bhūsphoṭa (EI 9), a mushroom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूत|भूतं|भूतः<BR>bhūta (CII 1), a living being.<BR>(IE 8-5), the element or nature.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR>(CII 3, etc.), a fiscal term; cf. sa-bhūta-pāta-pratyāya,<BR>in which we have sometimes pātta (mistake for upātta), upātta,<BR>āvāta or vāta. See bhūta-pāta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतबलि|भूतबलिः<BR>bhūta-bali (EI 11; SII 13), explained as ‘offering of<BR>boiled rice to the ghosts’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतकोट्य<BR>bhūta-koṭya (IA 23), the place of residence of the<BR>family ghost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतपात<BR>bhūta-pāta, cf. sa-bhūta-pāta-pratyāya (IE 8-5); often written<BR>as bhūta-vāta and bhūt-opātta; probably, an event relating to<BR>the elements, such as an earthquake. See bhūta-pāta-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतपातप्रत्याय<BR>bhūta-pāta-pratyāya (CII 4), explained by some as ‘excise<BR>and octroi duties’; but really, ‘the income resulting from storms,<BR>earthquakes, changes in the course of a river, etc’. See bhūta-<BR>vāta-pratyāya, etc. Pāta may be a mistake for upātta or vāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतप्रत्याय<BR>bhūta-pratyāya (CII 3), an income derived from natural<BR>changes in the land. See bhūta-vāta-pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतपूर्व<BR>bhūtapūrva (CII 1), ‘existing in the past’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतवातप्रत्याय<BR>bhūta-vāta-pratyāya (EI 23; CII 4; HRS), ‘the income<BR>derived from the elements and the winds’; explained by some<BR>as ‘excise and octroi duties’; but really, ‘the income resulting<BR>from storms, earthquakes, changes in the course of a river,<BR>etc.’ See bhūt-opātta-pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतोपात्तप्रत्याय<BR>bhūt-opātta-pratyāya (EI 32), income brought about by<BR>elemental or natural changes (e. g. storms, earthquakes, etc.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूवर<BR>Bhūvara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 98), ‘a king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिघा<BR>bighā, bīghā (IE 8-6), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीजक|बीजकः<BR>bījaka, cf. bījak (EI 9), an inscribed stone or an inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीजसंस्कार<BR>bīja-saṃskāra (CII 4), an astronomical term.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीलानुवृत्ति<BR>bīḻ-ānuvṛtti, also called bīḻa-vṛtti (599 11-1), Kannaḍa-<BR>Sanskrit; fief held by a king's subordinate for his mainte-<BR>nance; cf. anuga-jīvita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिल्कोडे<BR>bilkoḍe (EI 28), Kannaḍa; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिं<BR>biṃ° (PJS), abbreviation of bimba, ‘an image’ (especia-<BR>cially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिम्ब|बिंब|बिंबं|बिम्बं|बिंबः|बिम्बः<BR>bimba (IA 3; HA), same as pratimā; an image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिन्दुक<BR>binduka, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिराड<BR>birāḍa (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीरवणपारिखाय<BR>bīravaṇa-pārikhāya (IA 19), levy stated to have been of four<BR>kinds; cf. nidhi-nikṣepa-jala-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-chatuṣ-prakāra-bīra-<BR>vaṇa-pārikhāya-sahitaṃ which is mentioned along with aṣṭabhoga-<BR>tejassvāmya-daṇḍa-śulka-yuktam; Sanskrit vīra-paṇa (tax for the<BR>maintenance of constables) and pārīkṣ-āya (pārīkṣika).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिरुद|बिरुदः<BR>biruda (SII 1), also spelt viruda; ‘a surname’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिशी<BR>Biśī (EI 24), derived from Viṣayin (Viṣayapati), the<BR>governor of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीस्व<BR>bīsva (EI 28), a land measure equal to (1/20) of a bīghā;<BR>derived from Sanskrit viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीटक<BR>bīṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 279), modern bīḏā (i. e. a<BR>betel bīḏā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बित्तुवट्ट<BR>bittuvaṭṭa (A.R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 10), Kannaḍa; probably<BR>also called bittukaṭṭe; explained as ‘a portion of the produce<BR>derived from the lands irrigated by tanks, or wet land irriga-<BR>ted by a tank, granted to the person who built the tank or<BR>repaired it.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोधि|बोधिः<BR>bodhi (LL), Buddhist; supreme knowledge attained by<BR>the Buddha; the tree of enlightenment; cf. mahābodhi, saṃbodhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोधिचक्र<BR>bodhi-cakra (LL), Buddhist; the wheel of enlightenment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोधिसत्त्व|बोधिसत्त्वं|बोधिसत्त्वः<BR>Bodhisattva (CII 2-1; LL), Buddhist; a would-be Buddha<BR>in a previous birth. Cf. Chadmastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोध्यङ्ग<BR>bodhyaṅga, cf. bojjhaṅga (EI 5), Buddhist; seven in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोडिया<BR>Boḏiyā, local name of the Gujarātī alphabet (Ind. Ep.,<BR>p. 55).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोम्मलाट<BR>bommalāṭa (ASLV), a puppet show.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोप्प<BR>boppa (CII 3), a Prakrit word meaning ‘the father’; see<BR>bappa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोट<BR>boṭa, also spelt voṭa (CII 3), a termination of geographical<BR>names; meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोत्कट<BR>botkaṭa (IA 19), a goat; cf. Deśī bokkaḍa; also varkara<BR>(IA 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रा<BR>Brā, abbreviation of Brāhmaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 55).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मचारिन्<BR>brahmacārin (SII 2; LL), a Brāhmaṇa student; an<BR>unmarried student of the Vedas.<BR>(BL), epithet of one who takes a vow of celibacy.<BR>(SII 2), a temple servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदान<BR>brahma-dāna, cf. pirama-dānam (SITI), gift to Brāhmaṇas;<BR>same as brahmadāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदाय|ब्रह्मदायः<BR>brahmadāya (EI 23; CII 4), gift to a Brāhmaṇa; the rent-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-061" target="_blank">Page-061+ 40</a>]<BR>free holding of Brāhmaṇas; same as brahmadeya. See brahmatrā,<BR>etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदेय<BR>brahmadeya (EI 30; ASLV; HRS; SITI), land or village<BR>given as gift (generally tax-free) to Brāhmaṇas; land to be<BR>granted to or in the possession of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदेयक्कि<BR>brahmadeya-kkil13avar (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; sole owner of<BR>a Brahmadeya village; sometimes supposed to be the headman<BR>or chief of a Brahmadeya village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्माधिराज<BR>Brahm-ādhirāja (SITI), title of distinguished Brāhmaṇa<BR>military commanders; also spelt Brahmādarāya in Tamil. See<BR>Brahma-mahārāja, Brahma-rāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्महत्या<BR>brahma-hatyā (CITD), killing a Brāhmaṇa, considered to<BR>be a great sin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मकल्प|ब्रह्मकल्पः<BR>brahma-kalpa (CITD), the kalpa or age of the god<BR>Brahman, extending to many thousands of years.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मक्षत्र<BR>Brahma-kṣatra, Brahma-kṣatriya (EI 5, 12, 24), a Kṣatriya<BR>family claiming descent from a Brāhmaṇa parent; a family in<BR>which the blood of the Brāhmaṇas and Kṣatriyas has been<BR>mixed. See Vishveshvaranand Ind. Journ., Vol. I, pp. 87 ff., etc.<BR>In one record (Journ. Karnatak Univ., Vol. II, No 2, January<BR>1959, p. 47), the Nāgavaṃśa, to which a Kadamba king's<BR>minister Māyideva belonged, is called Brahma-kṣatra because it<BR>originated from the intercourse of its progenitor Nāgarāja with<BR>a Brāhmaṇa girl. Brahma-vaiśya should be likewise explained.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्ममहाराज<BR>Brahma-mahārāja, cf. pirama-mārāyaṉ (SITI), title of Brāh-<BR>maṇa ministers. See Brahm-ādhirāja, Brahmarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्ममन्त्र<BR>brahma-mantra (IA 12), five in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्ममेध<BR>brahma-medha, cf. pirama-metam (SITI), special funeral rite<BR>for a saintly person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मन्<BR>Brahman (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मणराशक्काणम्<BR>brāhmaṇa-rāśa(rāja)-kkāṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax<BR>payable by the Brāhmaṇa (Purohita) to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मणविंशति<BR>brāhmaṇa-viṃśati (HRS), title upon villagers for the main-<BR>tenance of the Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्माण्ड|ब्रह्मांड|ब्रह्माण्डं<BR>brahmāṇḍa (EI 16, 21), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मण्य|ब्रह्मण्यः<BR>brahmaṇya (EI 22) ‘hospitable to the Brāhmaṇas’; see<BR>Paramabrahmaṇya, Atibrahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मण्य|ब्राह्मण्यः<BR>brāhmaṇya (SII 1), the community of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मपुर<BR>brahmapura (EI 2), same as brahmapurī; a rent-free village<BR>in the possession of Brāhmaṇas; same as agrahāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मपुरी<BR>brahmapurī (EI 4, 28; SITI), also called agara-brahmadeya<BR>(Sanskrit agrahāra-brahmadeya); a Brāhmaṇa settlement. See<BR>brahmapura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मराज<BR>Brahmarāja (SITI), title of a Brāhmaṇa minister.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मराक्षस|ब्रह्मराक्षसः<BR>Brahmarākṣasa (EI 3, 16), a Brāhmaṇa defeated in dis-<BR>putations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मराय<BR>Brahmarāya (SITI), same as Brahmarāja. Cf. Brahm-ādhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मर्षि|ब्रह्मर्षिः<BR>Brahmarṣi (EI 22), a Brāhmaṇa sage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मस्तम्ब|ब्रह्मस्तम्बः<BR>brahma-stamba (CII 4), a settlement of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मस्थान|ब्रह्मस्थानः<BR>brahma-sthāna (SII 13; SITI), explained as ‘an assembly<BR>hall’; the Brāhmaṇa quarters of a village; cf. Tamil pirumma-<BR>stānam (SITI), the quarters of the Brāhmaṇas where the village<BR>assembly (sabhā) used to meet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मास्य<BR>Brahmāsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मत्रा<BR>brahmatrā (IE 8-5), same as brahmadāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मवैश्य<BR>Brahma-vaiśya (A.R. Ep., 1919, No. 208); cf. Brahma-kṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मयज्ञ|ब्रह्मयज्ञः<BR>brahma-yajña (EI 22; CII 4), study of the Vedas; name<BR>of a mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मी<BR>Brāhmī, name of an early Indian alphabet, from which a<BR>large number of alphabets of India and some other countries<BR>have derived.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मोत्तर|ब्रह्मोत्तरं<BR>brahmottara (IE 8-5), Bengali; corrupt form of brahmatrā.<BR>(IA 15), explained as ‘the sanctuary of a temple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृह<BR>Bṛha, abbreviation of Bṛhatpuruṣa (q. v.). See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXIV, p. 143.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहच्छुल्क<BR>bṛhac-chulka, cf. Kannaḍa perjuṅka, perujuṅka, pejjuṅka,<BR>hejjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्भोगिक<BR>Bṛhad-bhogika (IE 8-3), same as Bṛhad-bhogin; see Bhogika<BR>and Aṃśa-bṛhadbhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्भोगिन्<BR>Bṛhad-bhogin (IE 8-3; EI 28, 29; BL), same as Bṛhad-<BR>bhogika; a chief jāgīrdār; see Bhogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्देव<BR>Bṛhaddeva, cf. Tamil Periya-devar (SITI), literally, ‘the<BR>great king’; the predecessor or predecessors of the ruling mon-<BR>arch; also called Periya-perumāḻ sometimes indicating the para-<BR>mount sovereign or emperor. Cf. Bṛhan-nṛpati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्धल|बृहद्धलं<BR>bṛhaddhala (EI 7), ‘the big plough’; name of a land<BR>measure (Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 125); cf. hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्राज्ञी<BR>Bṛhad-rājñī (EI 4), same as Paṭṭa-rājñī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहदुपरिक<BR>Bṛhad-uparika (EI 15, 26; HD), ‘the great governor of a<BR>province’; a viceroy. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9. Cf. Uparika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्वाछक<BR>Bṛhad-vāchaka (LL), a Jain preacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्वाजिक<BR>Bṛhad-vājika (LP), probably, a police officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहन्मान<BR>bṛhan-māna (EI 23; CII 4), a measure larger than the<BR>standard one; cf. viṣaya-māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहन्नृपति<BR>Bṛhan-nṛpati (IE 8-2), predecessor of the ruling monarch;<BR>called Periya-devar in Tamil; cf. Oḏiyā Baḏa-Narasiṃha and<BR>Telugu Pedda-Narasiṃha. See Bṛhaddeva. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXII, p. 231 and note 2; JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 212.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहस्पतिसव|बृहस्पतिसवः<BR>bṛhaspatisava (EI 22; CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहती<BR>bṛhatī (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्कुमारमहापात्र<BR>Bṛhat-kumāramahāpātra (EI 28), cf. Kumāra-mahāpātra which<BR>is similar to Kumārāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्पुरोहित<BR>Bṛhat-purohita, cf. Baḏā-purohit (EI 24), ‘the high priest’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्पुरुष<BR>Bṛhatpuruṣa, probably the same as Mahājana (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXIV, pp. 143-44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्सन्धिविग्रहिमहापात्र<BR>Bṛhat-sandhivigrahi-mahāpātra (EI 28), same as Mahā-<BR>sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्तन्त्रपति<BR>Bṛhat-tantrapati (IE 8-3; EI 33), explained by a Kashmirian<BR>commentator as the Dharmādhikārin who was a judge also in<BR>charge of charities; cf. the Muslim official designation şadruŞ-<BR>şudūr, etc., explained as ‘the chief judge and grand almoner,<BR>or the custodian of the king's bequests and charities’ (Journ.<BR>As. Soc. Pak., Vol. IV, pp. 53-54).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहवार<BR>bṛha-vāra, (EI 31; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 125<BR>and note), Saturday or Thurdsday (A. Venkatasubbiah, Some<BR>Śaka Dates in Inscriptions, pp. 57ff.); same as Vadḍa-vāra (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृन्दावन<BR>bṛndāvana (EI 12), a tomb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुद्ध|बुद्धः<BR>Buddha (LL), Buddhist; a class of saints. See Bodhisattva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुद्धचैत्य<BR>buddha-caitya (EI 28), a Buddhist shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुद्धाधिष्ठान<BR>buddh-ādhiṣṭhāna (EI 22), a city or locality in the possession<BR>of a Buddhist monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुढालेङ्का<BR>Buḏhāleṅkā (IE 8-3), Oḏiyā; same as Mahāpādamūlika,<BR>‘chief attendant.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुधाष्टमी<BR>budh-āṣṭamī (IA 26), the eighth tithi on a Wednesday.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुल्लगकर<BR>bullaga-kara (HRS), tax relating to the supervision of<BR>meals according to the Abhidhānarājendra, s.v. kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बूरेडु<BR>būreḍu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown quantity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुस|बुसं<BR>busa (IE 8-5), chaff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुसिभंडालु<BR>busi-bhaṃḍālu (CITD), Telugu; probably, stores of un-<BR>husked grain. Cf. kola-bhaṃdālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बूटीय<BR>būṭīya (EI 32), a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चब<BR>caba (Chamba), wet land, marshy land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चबूतरा<BR>cabūtarā (EI 32), Hindī; a platform.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाड<BR>Cāḍa (IE 8-3), same as Cāṭa (q. v.) and the modern<BR>Cāḏ of Chamba, the latter being the designation of the head of<BR>a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाढा<BR>cāḏā (LP), a camp; an attacking party.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्रपवित्र<BR>caitra-pavitra, caitra-pavitraka (EI 7, 18), name of a rite<BR>(Ind. Ant., Vol. XXXVIII, p. 52); caitra is the daman-āropaṇa<BR>ceremony which takes place in the month of Caitra and pavitra<BR>is the pavitr-āropaṇa ceremony which occurs in Śrāvaṇa<BR>(Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 274, notes 12-13); cf. Kannaḍa caitra-<BR>pavitr-ābhyāgat-ādi pūje gaḻgaṃ, translated as ‘for the caitra and<BR>pavitra and the entertainment of guests and other rites’ (IA 30).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्य|चैत्यं|चैत्यः<BR>caitya (EI 22, 33; BL), a prayer hall; usually, a place of<BR>worship in a Buddhist monastery; same as caitya-gṛha.<BR>(EI 6, CII 4), same as stūpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यागार<BR>caity-āgāra (SII 1), a Jain temple; same as caity-ālaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यगृह<BR>caitya-gṛha (EI 8, 33, LL), Buddhist; cf. Prakrit cetiya-ghara.<BR>(EI 24), the hall for worship or prayer; hall in a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यकशैल<BR>caityaka-śaila, a stone pillar raised in memory of a<BR>dead person on his cremation ground (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII,<BR>p. 133). See yaṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यालय<BR>caity-ālaya (EI 7), same as caitya.<BR>(EI 3; SII 1), a Jain temple; same as caity-āgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यपट्ट<BR>caitya-paṭṭa (LL), Buddhist; a slab bearing the represen-<BR>tation of a caitya. See cakra-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यशैल<BR>Caitya-śaila (EI 24), a Buddhist school.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यवन्दन<BR>caitya-vandana (HA), obeissance to and worship of the<BR>Jina with recitation of hymns, etc., and meditating on the<BR>qualities of a Jina.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यिक<BR>Caityika (EI 24), same as Caitya-śaila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चकली<BR>cakalī, a small coin, smaller than the ṭaṃka regarded as<BR>(1/02) of a rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाकान्तर<BR>cākāntara (EI 3), a village institution of uncertain meaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्र|चक्रं|चक्रः<BR>cakra, cf. Cakrin (EI 4); a district; same as maṇḍala.<BR>Cf. sakkaram (SITI), wheel of authority; the king's order;<BR>an officer entrusted with the execution of the king's order.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-065" target="_blank">Page-065+ 40</a>]<BR>(CII 3), ‘the discus’; an emblem on seals.<BR>Cf. śakkara-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax paid by<BR>potters; also called tirigai-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रपट्ट<BR>cakra-paṭṭa (LL), Buddhist; a slab bearing the represen-<BR>tation of a wheel. See caitya-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रवालगिरि<BR>Cakravāla-giri (SITI), same as Tamil Śakkaravāḻam; a<BR>mythical mountain encircling the earth; the horizon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रवर्तिक्षेत्र<BR>cakravarti-kṣetra (IE 8-2; EI 33), the sphere of influence<BR>of an Indian imperial ruler lying between the Himalayas and<BR>the three seas, viz. Bay of Bengal, Indian Ocean and<BR>Arabian Sea; sometimes regarded as conterminous with<BR>Āryāvarta or Dākṣiṇātya. See Sircar, Stud. Geog. Anc. Med. Ind.,<BR>pp. 1 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रवर्तिन्|चक्रवर्त्तिन्<BR>Cakravartin (IE 8-2; EI 21, 28; CII 3, 4), a title of para-<BR>mount sovereignty; the title of an emperor. See Saptama-<BR>cakravartin; also Cakreśvara, Cakrin.<BR>(IE 8-2), often suffixed to expressions like Pratāpa, Prau-<BR>ḍhapratāpa, Bhujabalapratāpa, Niḥśaṅkapratāpa, etc., and some-<BR>times also to dynastic names like Yādava.<BR>(EI 31), epithet of the Buddha.<BR>(IE 8-2), cf. cakravarti-kṣetra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रेश्वर|चक्रेश्वरः<BR>Cakreśvara (EI 3), same as Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रिन्<BR>Cakrin (EI 9), same as Cakravartin.<BR>(EI 4, 19), ‘the ruler of a cakra (circle) or district’; title<BR>of a provincial ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्षुस्<BR>cakṣus (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR>Cf. Pali cakkhu (EI 5), Buddhist; vision, five in number.<BR>Cf. cakṣur-vadha, ‘killing at sight’, ‘killing instantaneously’;<BR>or probably ‘blinding of the eyes’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII,<BR>p. 307 and note 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चलमर्तिगण्ड<BR>Calamartigaṇḍa (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a title of the<BR>Kākatīya kings; from Kannaḍa gaṇḍa meaning ‘the husband,<BR>lord, master,’ i. e. ‘one who can control or punish’, and Telugu<BR>calam meaning ‘obstinacy, rudeness, overbearing’; translated<BR>as ‘one who is the controller or punisher of spiteful men or<BR>men of overbearing conduct’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाली<BR>cālī (IA 15), a system of land revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चलिवंदीलि<BR>calivaṃdīli, caliveṃdala, caliveṃdra, calipaṃdili (CITD),<BR>Telugu-Kannaḍa; halting place for travellers, where they are<BR>supplied gratis with milk and whey or with water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामर|चामरं|चामरः<BR>cāmara (IE 8-8), name of a coin; cf. cāmara-māda.<BR>(SII 3), a fly-whisk. See cauri, cavarālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामरकुमार<BR>Cāmara-kumāra, cf. Cavari-kumāra (EI 10), probably, a<BR>prince in charge of the fly-whisk which was one of the royal<BR>insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामरमाड<BR>cāmara-māḍa (EI 7), name of a coin; cf. cāmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चम्पाषष्ठी<BR>campā-ṣaṣṭhī (EI 5), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चमूनायक<BR>Camūnāyaka (EI 27), a general; cf. Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चमूप|चमूपः<BR>Camūpa (IA 10), a general; same as Camūpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चमूपति|चमूपतिः<BR>Camūpati (EI 8-3); a general, same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चण्डप्रचण्ड<BR>Caṇḍa-pracaṇḍa (SITI), divinities guarding the inner shrine<BR>of a Viṣṇu temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चण्डेश्वर|चंडेश्वर|चण्डेश्वरः<BR>Caṇḍeśvara (SITI), traditional executive of Śiva temples;<BR>also called Ādi-dāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चण्देश्वरप्पेरुविलै<BR>Caṇdeśvara-pperuvilai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; literally, the<BR>sale-price of Caṇḍeśvara, the traditional executive of Śiva<BR>temples; actually, sale-price of land purchased from a Śiva<BR>temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्र|चंद्र|चन्द्रं|चन्द्रः<BR>candra (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रादित्यवत्<BR>candrādityavat (SITI), same as Tamil candrādittaval,<BR>candrādittavar; ‘as long as the moon and the sun last’; ‘in<BR>perpetuity’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रग्रहण|चंद्रग्रहण<BR>candra-grahaṇa (SII 1), lunar eclipse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रहास|चंद्रहास|चन्द्रहासं|चन्द्रहासः<BR>candrahāsa (EI 25), name of Rāma's sword.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रक|चंद्रक|चन्द्रकं|चंद्रकः|चन्द्रकः<BR>candraka (EI 2), the young moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रकालिकम्<BR>candra-kālikam (LP), permanently.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रमस्|चंद्रमस्<BR>candramas (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रार्कयोगपर्वन्<BR>candr-ārka-yoga-parvan (EI 19), same as amāvāsyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रविशद<BR>candra-viśada (LP), ‘as white as the moon’, i. e. guiltless.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्य्<BR>candy (IA 26), Anglicised form of khaṇdī, a weight of<BR>different value in different parts. See khaṇdikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चङ्ग|चंग|चङ्गः<BR>caṅga, see chaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चङ्क्रम<BR>caṅkrama (LL), Prakrit caṃkama (EI 24); a promenade,<BR>a walk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चपलं|चपल|चपलः<BR>capalaṃ (CII 1), quickly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर|चरः<BR>Cara (CII 4), a spy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चार|चारं|चारः<BR>Cāra (IE 8-3; EI 26), a spy; same as Cara; sometimes used<BR>in place of Cāṭa.<BR>(EI 15), cf. a-cār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE 8-5), probably,<BR>passage [of royal officers through a village]; cf. also a-pār-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-067" target="_blank">Page-067+ 40</a>]<BR>āsana-carm-āṅgāra with pāra (probably, ferrying) instead of<BR>cāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरबलीवर्द<BR>cara-balīvarda (IE 8-5), cf. vara-balīvarda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरण|चरणं|चरणः<BR>caraṇa (CII 4; IA 18, 20), a Vedic school; a sect or school<BR>studying a particular śākhā of the Vedas; e. g. Taittirīya-caraṇa.<BR>(CII 1), same as ācaraṇa; cf. dharma-caraṇa for dharm-ācaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चारण|चारणः<BR>Cāraṇa (EI 3), same as Vidyā-cāraṇa, a Jain monk endowed<BR>with magical powers.<BR>Cf. harita-pakva-sasy-ekṣu-cāraṇa-lavaṇ-opamardana (IE 8-5);<BR>grazing of cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरण्डि<BR>caraṇḍi (EI 31), Gujarātī; a narrow passage of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरी<BR>carī (EI 33), pasture land; same as carī-kṣetra.<BR>(EI 21), grazing tax; grazing land. Cf. cārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चारी<BR>cārī (LP), Gujarātī cāro, grass; probably, pasture land;<BR>cf. carī.<BR>(CII 4), grazing tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्मकार|चर्मकारः|चर्म्मकार|चर्म्मकारः<BR>Carmakāra (EI 32), a shoe-maker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्मन्|चर्म्मन्<BR>carman (EI 15), cf. a-carm-āṅgāraka (IE 8-5); hide-seat<BR>which the villagers were obliged to supply to the touring<BR>officers of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरु|चरुः<BR>caru (EI 10, 22, 23; CII 3, 4), an offering to the manes;<BR>one of the five mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरुक<BR>caruka (EI 1), same as caru, one of the five mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्या|चर्य्या<BR>caryā (CII 4), discipline in Śaivite practices.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चस्ह्<BR>cash (IE 8-8), Anglicised form of Tamil kāśu; name of a<BR>small copper coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चट्<BR>caṭ, cf. alīkaṃ caṭāpitam (LP), ‘circulated a false rumour’.<BR>Cf. caṭanti (LP); ‘to accumulate’; also cf. Gujarātī caḏhśe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाट|चाटः<BR>Cāṭa (HD), irregular soldiers according to Fleet and<BR>Bühler. Vogel (Ant. Ch. St., pp. 130-32) points out that<BR>Chamba is the only place where the ancient word Cāṭa is still<BR>extant in the modern form Cāḏ meaning ‘the head of a Parganā’.<BR>An important privilege of a gift village was ‘not to be entered<BR>by Cāṭas and Bhaṭas’. Inscriptions (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI,<BR>p. 221) often specify that the granted land was not to be entered<BR>by Cāṭas and Bhaṭas except for seizing robbers and those guilty<BR>of harm or treason to the king (cf. a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśyaṃ cora-<BR>drohaka-varjam in op. cit., Vol. VIII, p. 287). Sometimes we<BR>have bhaṭa-cāṭa-sevak-ādīn (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211) and<BR>caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-jātīyān janapadān (ibid., Vol. XIV, p. 160).<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-068" target="_blank">Page-068+ 40</a>]<BR>(IE 8-3; CII 3, 4), generally mentioned along with<BR>bhaṭa; sometimes replaced by cāra (spy) and chātra (literally,<BR>‘umbrella-bearer’, but really, a constable, i. e. a Pāik or Piāda);<BR>probably indicates the leader of a group of Bhaṭas, i. e. Pāiks<BR>and Piādas; a policeman leading a group of Pāiks. See caṭṭa.<BR>Yājñavalkya, I. 336, speaks of the duty of the king to<BR>protect people from the harassment caused by cāṭas, robbers<BR>and Kāyasthas and the Mitākṣarā explains cāṭa as persons<BR>who deprive people of their wealth after creating false confi-<BR>dence in them. According to Bṛhaspati quoted by Aparārka,<BR>‘dangers common to all are those arising from the cāṭas and<BR>thieves’. The word cāṭa in the passage tārkika-cāṭa-bhaṭa-rāj-<BR>āpraveśya in Śaṅkara's Bhāsya on the Bṛhadāraṇyaka Upaniṣad<BR>is explained by Ānandagiri by saying that the cāṭas are those<BR>that transgress the rules of conduct for decent people and that<BR>bhaṭas are servants telling falsehood (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 296).<BR>But cāṭa is used in inscriptions in the sense of a royal official.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटापक<BR>caṭāpaka (LP), ‘increasing [the rent already fixed]’; cf.<BR>Gujarātī caḏhāvo.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटाप्य<BR>caṭāpya (LP), ‘to be entered [on the back of the bond]’;<BR>cf. Gujarātī caḏhāvavā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटी<BR>ca-ṭī abbreviation of an expression probably meaning ‘a<BR>mound suitable for planting fruit trees’. See Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXX, p. 56. Cf. ṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटित<BR>caṭita (LP), one who makes an attack.<BR>(LP), accumulated.<BR>Cf. khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-caṭita-pratiṣaṃskāra; a crack.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चट्ट<BR>Caṭṭa (EI 25), Tamil corruption of Sanskrit Chātra;<BR>a student.<BR>(IE 8-3), cf. a-caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-praveśa (IE 8-5); same as Cāṭa<BR>of earlier records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चट्टना<BR>caṭṭanā (LP), food; sauce; cf. Gujarātī cāṭvuṃ, licking.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाटु|चाटुः<BR>cāṭu (IA 15), probably, a spoon.<BR>(EI 32), a eulogistic stanza.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुःशाल|चतुःशालं<BR>catuḥ-śāla, catuḥ-śālā (EI 20; SITI), a cloister.<BR>(SITI), a meeting hall; see catuś-śālā.<BR>(EI 24), same as catur-ālaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुपडि<BR>cātu-paḍi (CITD), Telugu; an offering of food to the deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर|चतुरः<BR>catura, cf. caturaka; a square.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरक<BR>caturaka (LP), same as Sanskrit catvara; Gujarātī coro;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-069" target="_blank">Page-069+ 40</a>]<BR>a public place in a village, or a police station; probably, a tax<BR>for the maintenance of a police station.<BR>(IE 8-4), a small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरालय<BR>catur-ālaya (EI 24), known, especially from Tamil inscrip-<BR>tions, in the sense of ‘a hall or pavilion attached to a temple’;<BR>also called caṭuḥ-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुराननवदन<BR>Caturānana-vadana (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरङ्ग|चतुरंग|चतुरङ्गं<BR>caturaṅga (EI 2), a complete army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरशीति<BR>caturaśīti (IE 8-4), a territorial unit like a Parganā; see<BR>caurāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्दन्तसमर<BR>caturdanta-samara, cāturdanta-samara, a war of elephants;<BR>cf. ghoṭaka-vigraha. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्दशविद्यास्थान<BR>caturdaśa-vidyā-sthāna (CII 3), the fourteen sections of<BR>science.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्धरप्रतीहार<BR>Caturdhara-pratīhāra, cf. Kannaḍa Sodare-vadiyara (Hydera-<BR>bad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34); explained as ‘the chief<BR>of the royal guards’. Caturdhara is modern Caudhari, written<BR>in Kannaḍa as Saudore, Saudare, Caudore, Cavudore and Cavudari<BR>and explained as ‘an officer of the royal guard’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्दिश<BR>cāturdiśa (EI 23; ML), ‘belonging to all the quarters’;<BR>cf. cāturdiś-ārya-bhikṣu-saṅgha, ‘Buddhist monks of all places’;<BR>‘all monks coming from different places’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्गर्भ<BR>catur-garbha (LL), a four-celled building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्जातक<BR>caturjātaka (IE 8-3), same as cauthiā, an administrative board<BR>of four members known from the Pañcāyat system of Western<BR>India; cf. pañcakula or pañcāyat. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII,<BR>p. 193. See caukaḍikā.<BR>(EI 20), four fragrant articles, viz. tvak, elā, patraka and<BR>nāgakesara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्जातक|चातुर्जातकं<BR>Cāturjātaka (EI 1), a member of the caturjātaka or cauthiā<BR>(q. v.). Cf. Pañcakulika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 193.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्जातकीय<BR>Caturjātakīya, same as Cāturjātaka (EI 1); a member of the<BR>caturjātaka (q. v.); cf. Pañcakulika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII,<BR>p. 193.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मासी<BR>cāturmāsī (EI 2; CII 1), the full-moon tithis of Phālguna,<BR>Āṣāḍha and Kārttika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मासीपक्ष<BR>cāturmāsī-pakṣa (IA 18), the fortnight ending in a cātur-<BR>māsī (i. e. the full-moon of Phālguna, Āṣāḍha and Kārttika).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मास्य|चातुर्मास्यं|चातुर्म्मास्य|चातुर्म्मास्यं<BR>cāturmāsya (SII 11-1, CITD), the season consisting of 4<BR>months, viz. grīṣma consisting of the pūrṇimānta months of Caitra,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-070" target="_blank">Page-070+ 40</a>]<BR>Vaiśākha, Jyeṣṭha and Āṣāḍha, varṣā consisting of Śrāvana,<BR>Bhādrapada, Āśvina and Kārttika; and hemanta consisting of<BR>Mārgaśīrṣa, Pauṣa, Māgha and Phālguna. This was the<BR>official division of the year which was popularly divided into six<BR>seasons, viz. grīṣma (Jyeṣṭha-Āṣāḍha), varṣā (Śrāvaṇa-Bhādra-<BR>pada), śarad (Āśvina-Kārttika), hemanta (Mārgaśīrṣa-Pauṣa),<BR>śīta (Māgha-Phālguna) and vasanta (Caitra-Vaiśākha). Some<BR>times, the word cāturmāsya specially means the four months of<BR>the year, containing the two seasons of varṣā and śarad, i. e.<BR>from Śrāvaṇa to Kārttika. During this period, Viṣṇu is<BR>supposed to sleep, so that religious celebrations are avoided.<BR>During the period, religious mendicants desisted from roving.<BR>(EI 7; BL), related to the cāturmāsī or the full-moon day<BR>of Phālguna, Āshāḍha and Kārttika; a rite; same as cātur-<BR>māsya-vrata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मास्यव्रत<BR>cāturmāsya-vrata (EI 32), a rite. See cāturmāsya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्मुखबिम्ब<BR>caturmukha-bimba (EI 2), Jain; a four-sided slab with<BR>images on all the sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्थ|चतुर्थः<BR>caturtha (IE 8-8), one-fourth of the standard measure [of<BR>liquids like liquor].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्थकुल<BR>caturtha-kula (EI 29), the Śūdra community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्थीअमावास्या<BR>caturthī-amāvāsyā, cf. cauti-amāvāse (EI 5), the new-moon<BR>following the Gaṇeśa-caturthī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्वैद्यमर्यादा<BR>cāturvaidya-maryādā (EI 27), custom relating to rent-free<BR>land granted to learned Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वर्णिन्<BR>caturvarṇin (LL), Jain; ‘consisting of four classes’; an<BR>epithet of the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वेदिभट्टत्तानप्पेरुमक्कल्<BR>caturvedi-bhaṭṭa-ttāna-pperumakkaḻ (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil;<BR>general assembly of the Vedic scholars in a Brāhmaṇa village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वेदिमङ्गल<BR>caturvedi-maṅgala (IE 8-4; SITI), same as agrahāra; a<BR>village owned by Brāhmaṇas, generally tax-free; also called<BR>maṅgala; written as śaruppeṭi-maṅgalam in Tamil; sometimes suffix-<BR>ed to names of localities especially in the Tamil-speaking area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वेदिन्<BR>Caturvedin (EI 23, 24; CII 3, 4; SII 1), a Brāhmaṇa<BR>versed in the four Vedas; one who has studied the four Vedas;<BR>later stereotyped as a family name among Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्वीद्य<BR>cāturvīdya (EI 23, 32), cf. Caturvedin; ‘relating to the<BR>Caturvedin’, a community of Brāhmaṇas; cf. cāturvidya-grāma,<BR>cāturvidy-āgrahāra, cāturvidya-sāmānya (EI 22).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरुपाय<BR>catur-upāya (SII 1), the four expedients. Cf. upāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्विंशतितीर्थङ्करपट्ट<BR>caturviṃśati-tīrthaṅkara-paṭṭa (EI 2), a slab with the images<BR>o all the 24 Jain Tīrthaṅkaras. See covīsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुष्किका<BR>catuṣkikā (EI 19; CII 4), a hall; a hall resting on four<BR>pillars (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 75).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुष्पथ|चतुष्पथं|चतुष्पथः<BR>catuṣpatha (LP), a place where four roads meet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुश्शाला<BR>catuś-śālā (SITI), a meeting hall; see catuḥ-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चत्वारक<BR>catvāraka (IA 17), used in the sense of catuṣṭaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छौ<BR>Chau° (PJS), contraction of Caudharī (Caturdhara) especially<BR>in medieval Jain inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौकडिका<BR>caukaḍikā (EI 11), a variety of the Pañcāyat system; cf.<BR>caturjātaka or cauthiā.<BR>(BL), explained as ‘a method of recovering stolen property’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौमुख<BR>caumukha (HA), Sanskrit caturmukha (cf. caturmukha-bimba);<BR>a quadruple image called pratimā sarvatobhadrikā (LL) in the<BR>Mathurā inscriptions of the Kuṣāṇa period, showing one Jina<BR>or several Jinas on each of the four faces; also seen on the top<BR>or in the centre of representations of the samavasaraṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरचरट<BR>Caura-caraṭa (LP), cf. Marāṭhī Cor-cilaṭāṃcā upadrav.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरासी<BR>caurāsī (IE 8-4; EI 3, 4), literally, ‘eightyfour’; same as<BR>caturaśīti (q. v.); a group of eightyfour villages; a Parganā<BR>consisting of eightyfour villages; sometimes the name of a<BR>Parganā and often suffixed to its name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरवर्जम्<BR>caura-varjam (CII 3; HRS), cf. cora-varjam, coradaṇda-<BR>varjam, cora-rājāpathyakāri-varjam; ‘with immunity from the<BR>police tax’ according to some; may really mean ‘without any<BR>right to inflict punishment on thieves and persons committing<BR>the crime of treason or to levy fines from them’; may also be<BR>connected with a-bhaṭa-praveśa so as to indicate that the bhaṭas<BR>should not enter except for catching thieves and persons<BR>committing the crime of treason; cf. Cāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरि<BR>cauri (ASLV), spelt chowrie in English; a flywhisk; some-<BR>times the right of its use was granted to persons as a mark<BR>of honour. See cāmara, cavarālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरिक<BR>Caurika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), official designation.<BR>Cf. Cāmara-kumāra, Caur-oddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरिका<BR>caurikā, cf. carma-caurikā (LP), ‘theft of skin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरोद्धरण<BR>caur-oddharaṇa (EI 33; HRS), according to some, the<BR>right to punish or levy fines from thieves; probably, the right<BR>to recover stolen property; recovery of stolen property; cf.<BR>sa-chauroddharaṇa (IE 8-5; EI 23).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरोद्धरणिक<BR>Caur-oddharaṇika (IE 8-3; EI 23; CII 3), an official desig-<BR>nation indicating an officer in charge of the recovery of stolen<BR>property; a police officer; same as Cor-oddharaṇika, Caur-oddhartṛ.<BR>(HD; CII, Vol. III, p. 216), explained as ‘the thief-catcher<BR>or one who exterminates thieves’. But cf. Daṇḍ-odddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरोद्धर्तृ<BR>Caur-oddhartṛ (HD), same as Caur-oddharaṇika (cf. Yājña-<BR>valkyasmṛti, II. 271; also Kātyāyana quoted by Aparārka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौथिआ<BR>cauthiā (IE 8-3; EI 33), an administrative board consis-<BR>ting of four members headed by the Nagarseṭh (Nagaraśreṣṭhin)<BR>as known from the Pañcāyat system of Western India; cf.<BR>caturjātaka, caukaḍikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चावडि<BR>cāvaḍi (IE 8-4; SITI; ASLV), same as śāvaḍi or<BR>uśāvaḍi; an administrative unit or a territorial division.<BR>(EI 16), same as rājya; a district or subdivision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवल<BR>cavala (EI 6), name of a coin, (1/8) of a pagoda; cf. cāmara,<BR>cavela.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवरालु<BR>cavarālu (CITD), Telugu; also called savarālu, savara-<BR>mulu; the hair of the camarī-mṛga, used by women as queue;<BR>also cavara, camara or cāmara, the chowrie (cauri) or long brush<BR>or fan usually made of the tail of the yak, which was one of<BR>the insignia of royalty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवरङ्ग<BR>cavaraṅga (EI 28), a Śaiva altar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवथे<BR>cavathe, a levy of one-fourth; see chavathā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवेल<BR>cavela (EI 6), same as cavala; name of a coin, (1/8) of a<BR>pagoda. Cf. cāmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चेटक|चेटकः<BR>ceṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 78), an attendant; some-<BR>times mentioned in the list of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छ|छं|छः<BR>cha (PJS) written as a mark indicating the end of a section<BR>of a record or of the whole of it. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 218.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छचोकी<BR>cha-cokī (HA), Sanskrit ṣaṭ-catuṣkikā; a hall adjacent to<BR>and in front of the gūḍha-maṇḍapa, with its ceiling divided into<BR>six sections by the pillars supporting it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छद्मस्थ<BR>Chadmastha (HA), a would-be Jina [living a monk's life]<BR>before attainment of kevala-jñāna. Cf. Bodhisattva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाद्य<BR>chādya, cf. tṛṇa-cchādya, thatch-covering (Ep. Ind., XXXIV,<BR>p. 145); same as Gujarātī chāj, thatch.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छल|छलं|छलः<BR>chala (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain; probably, a pretext.<BR>(EI 30), probably, a plea, or persecution, prosecution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाली<BR>chālī (LP), sheep.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छन्दस्|छंदस्<BR>chandas (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छङ्ग<BR>chaṅga (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 310), a measure of grain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छन्दोविचित<BR>chandovicita, the metrical science (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV,<BR>p. 146).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छप्पन्न<BR>chappanna, cf. ṣaṭpañcāśat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्र|छत्त्रं|छत्त्रः|छत्रं|छत्रः<BR>chatra, an umbrella; cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR>(EI 27), an attendant or Piāda; cf. Chātra.<BR>Cf. Varāha-kṣetra = Barāh-chatra (Sircar, Studies in the<BR>Geography of Ancient and Medieval India, p. 221); corruption of<BR>Sanskrit kṣetra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छात्र|छात्त्रः|छात्रं|छात्रः<BR>Chātra (IE 8-3, 8-8; EI 23, 30), cf. a-bhaṭa-cchātra-<BR>prāveśya (IE 8-5); literally, ‘one bearing an umbrella’ or ‘the<BR>king's umbrella-bearer’; but probably the same as the Cāṭa<BR>or the leader of a group of Bhaṭas (Pāiks or Piādas) as in a-cāṭa-<BR>bhaṭa-prāveśya; a peon of the law-court. See Chatracchāyika.<BR>(CII 3), used in composition with bhaṭa and also singly;<BR>literally, ‘an umbrella-bearer’; but actually, a constable like<BR>a Pāik or Piāda.<BR>(SITI), celibate (Brahmacārin) in charge of a temple<BR>and the śālai attached to it; also called Śaṭṭar, Śāttirar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्रभङ्ग|छत्त्रभङ्गः|छत्रभंग|छत्रभङ्गः<BR>chatra-bhaṅga (IA 8), ‘the breaking of the umbrella [of<BR>sovereignty]’; sometimes interpreted as ‘an interregnum’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्राभोग<BR>chatr-ābhoga (IA 17), corrected from ṣatr-ābhoga and<BR>explained as ‘the expanse of the royal umbrella’; but really,<BR>‘the ābhoga (a territorial unit) called Ṣa(Kha)tra’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्रच्छायिक<BR>Chatracchāyika (IE 8-3; HD), an umbrella-bearer; the<BR>king's umbrella-bearer. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 128. Cf.<BR>Chātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्रयष्टि<BR>chatra-yaṣṭi (LL), an umbrella on a post.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छवथा<BR>chavathā (IA 18), cf. viṃśati-chavathā, a levy of doubtful<BR>implication; may be a levy of 6 out of a unit of 20; cf. cavathe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाया<BR>chāyā (EI 1), an image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छायादीप<BR>chāyā-dīpa (EI 33), a lamp held by an image, often<BR>arranged to burn continuously in front of a deity in a temple;<BR>cf. akhaṇḍa-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छायास्तम्भ<BR>chāyā-stambha (EI 33, 35), memorial pillar bearing image<BR>of the deceased.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छेद|छेदः<BR>cheda (EI 13), a quarter, area or subdivision; cf. Brahma-<BR>cāri-ccheda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छेण्डिका<BR>cheṇḍikā (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छिद्र|छिद्रं<BR>chidra (7-1-2), ‘nine’; cf. randhra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छिम्पक<BR>Chimpaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), a dyer of clothes; same as<BR>Prakrit Chimpaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छोह<BR>choha, same as Gujarātī cho, mortar (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छोट्यमान<BR>choṭyamāna, cf. choṭyamāna-gṛhe (LP), ‘when the house is<BR>being vacated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छोउल्त्र्य्<BR>choultry, Anglicised form of a Dravidian word; a<BR>dharma-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छुरिप्रबन्ध<BR>churi-prabandha (BL), name of a grant made in favour of<BR>a Churikāra, ‘a maker of churis’. The word churi may be the<BR>same as kṣurikā, ‘a knife’, and a Churikāra may have been an<BR>officer in charge of the production of knives and swords.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छुट्<BR>chuṭ (LP), cf. choṭanīya; Gujarātī choḏāvavuṃ; also cf.<BR>granthi-baddhair = api drammaiḥ kṣetraṃ choṭayituṃ dhāraṇiko na<BR>labhate, ‘[when the date is already over], the debtor will not<BR>get his farm liberated by the ready money tied in a piece of<BR>cloth’.<BR>Cf. patra-grahāt chuṭanti (LP), ‘will be free from the bond’;<BR>also Gujarātī chaṭśe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिह्न|चिह्नं<BR>cihna (EI 33), flag; cf. Cihna-dhara (BL), standard-bearer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिखि<BR>ci-khi, abbreviation of cira-khila, ‘[land] never brought<BR>under cultivation’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिकित्सा<BR>cikitsā (CII 1), medical treatment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीनक्कनकम्<BR>Cīna-kkanakam (IE 8-8), Tamil; ‘the Chinese gold coin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीनपगोद<BR>Cīna-pagoda (SII 12), ‘Chinese shrine’; name of a Buddhist<BR>temple at Nāgapaṭṭanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिन्न|चिन्नः<BR>cinna (EI 3; SITI), name of a coin; sometimes regarded<BR>as a fanam (CITD); also spelt sinna in Telugu; a weight equal<BR>to (1/30) of a tola and called a Canteroy fanam; one-eighth part<BR>of a coin called pagoda; the weight of 4 guri-giñjas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिन्त्रिणी<BR>cintriṇī (EI 33), the tamarind tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरखिल<BR>cira-khila (EI 30), land which was never cultivated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरखिलशून्य<BR>cira-khila-śūnya (EI 23), epithet of gift land; fallow land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरञ्जीव<BR>cirañjīva (EI 30), ‘long-lived’; epithet of living (not<BR>dead) persons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरन्तनलोक<BR>cirantana-loka (LP), old men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरविद<BR>ciravida (CITD), Telugu; name of a coin; probably a<BR>special kind of gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीरिका<BR>cīrikā (EI 26), a document; cf. kraya-cīrikā, ‘a deed of<BR>purchase’, i. e. a sale-deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीर्णव्रतोपायनक<BR>cīrṇa-vrat-opāyanaka (LP), the gift (upāyana) for the vows<BR>practised. Cf. Sel. Ins., p. 210, text line 14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिटला<BR>ciṭalā (IE 8-5), a tax; cf. coṭāla, ciṭola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीठिका<BR>cīṭhikā (LP), a chit; cf. Gujarātī ciṭṭhī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिटोल<BR>ciṭola (IE 8-5), a tax or obligation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्र|चित्रं|चित्रः<BR>citra (ASLV), a kind of poetry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रजर्त<BR>citrajarta (LP), various kinds of armour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रक|चित्रकं|चित्रकः<BR>Citraka (IA 8), ‘a painter’; epithet of the engraver of an<BR>inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रकार|चित्रकारः<BR>Citrakāra, cf. Cittirakārar (EI 22), a painter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रकार्य<BR>citrakārya, cf. cittirakāri (EI 22), painting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रभास<BR>citra-bhāsa (ASLV), paintings on the walls and ceilings of<BR>temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रमे<BR>citramel13i (SITI), also spelt śittiramel13i, an organisation of<BR>the agriculturists; agricultural corporation of the Vĕḻḻāḻas;<BR>the plough which was the emblem of this organisation; the<BR>boundary stone with the representation of the plough emblem<BR>planted to mark the limits of their land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीवर|चीवरं<BR>cīvara, cf. cīvarika (EI 8); garments of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीवरिक<BR>cīvarika (EI 8), expenses of cīvara; Sanskrit caivarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीवरिक<BR>cīvarika (EI 20), a Buddhist monk's robe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोखा<BR>cokhā (EI 11), rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोल|चोलः<BR>cola (Chamba), rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोल्लिक<BR>collika (EI 3), collikā (EI 10), a load [of leaves];<BR>a quantity of betel leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोर|चोरः<BR>cora (IE 8-5), same as caura and cora-daṇḍa; probably,<BR>the power of punishing thieves and realising fines from them;<BR>cf. cora-varja; also Cāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरदण्डवर्जम्<BR>coradaṇḍa-varjam (HRS), same as caura-varjam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरदण्डवर्ज्य<BR>cora-daṇḍa-varjya (CII 3), a fiscal term which means either<BR>that no fines for theft should be collected from the gift village<BR>or, more probably, that the donee was not entitled to fines<BR>realisable on thieves in the gift villages. But see also caura-varjam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरद्रोहकवर्ज<BR>cora-drohaka-varja (CII 3, etc.), a fiscal term which is<BR>similar to coradaṇḍa-varja. The word drohaka means one<BR>committing a crime against the king. See caura-varjam, Cāḷa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरग्राह<BR>Cora-grāha (HD), a thief-catcher (cf. Nārada, Pariśiṣṭa,<BR>verse 18; also Kātyāyana quoted by Aparārka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरराजापथ्यकारिवर्जम्<BR>cora-rājāpathyakāri-varjam (HRS), ‘with immunity from<BR>the police tax’, according to some; seems to mean ‘without any<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-076" target="_blank">Page-076+ 40</a>]<BR>right to inflict punishment on or levy fines from thieves and<BR>rebels’. But see caura-varjam; also Cāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोररज्जू<BR>cora-rajjū (HRS), ‘the rope for binding thieves’; supposed<BR>to be the dues collected by the superintendent of the bound-<BR>aries of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोररज्जुक<BR>Corarajjuka (HD), probably the same as Dāṇdapāśika, an<BR>officer whose duty it was to secure robbers with ropes (cf.<BR>Arthaśāstra, IV. 13; II. 6 referring to cora-rajjū as a constituent<BR>of the rāṣṭra).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरासी<BR>corāsī (IE 8-4), same as caurāsī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्ज<BR>cora-varja, also spelt cora-varjya (CII 3; HRS); a fiscal<BR>term which is the same as coradaṇḍa-varjya (q. v.). See also<BR>caura-varja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्जित<BR>cora-varjita (CII 3), same as coradaṇda-varjya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्ज्य<BR>cora-varjya, see cora-varja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरोद्धरणिक<BR>Cor-oddharaṇika (EI 28, 30), same as Caur-oddharaṇika; a<BR>police officer in charge of the recovery of stolen goods; explained<BR>by some as ‘the eradicator of thieves’ (CII 4). But cf.<BR>Daṇdoddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोस्क|चोस्कः<BR>coska (EI 4), a horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोटाल<BR>coṭāla (IE 8-5), a tax of uncertain import; cf. ciṭola, ciṭalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोवीसी<BR>covīsī (HA); Sanskrit caturviṃśati or caturviṃśati-paṭṭa;<BR>a group of the 24 Jinas carved on one stone slab or cast in<BR>bronze together.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूडा<BR>cūḍā (IA 11), the top knot of hair; cf. cūḻā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूडामणि|चूडामणिः<BR>cūḍāmaṇi (IA 26), an eclipse on certain days.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चुक्क|चुक्कं<BR>cukka, error, fault (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 7, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूला<BR>cūḻā (IA 11), tresses; cf. cūdā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चुल्लक|चुल्लकः<BR>cullaka, cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (IE 8-5), ex-<BR>plained as ‘a pot’, i. e. cooking pot. The villagers were obliged<BR>to supply it to the touring officers of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूमा<BR>cūmā (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चुम्बक|चुंबक|चुंबकः|चुम्बकः<BR>cumbaka (EI 13), the balance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूना<BR>cūnā, same as Sanskrit cūrṇa, lime (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूणकर<BR>Cūṇakara, same as Sanskrit Cūrṇakāra, a lime-burner or<BR>white-washer (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 145).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूरकार<BR>Cūrakāra, cf. Cūṟakāra (CITD), from Telugu-Kannaḍa<BR>cūṟa and Sanskrit kāra; ‘one who has plundered’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूर्णि|चूर्णिः<BR>cūrṇi (EI 3), an appended note. Cf. cūrṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूर्णि|चूर्णिः<BR>cūrṇi, cūrṇī (EI 29, 33), one hundred cowrie-shells;<BR>cowrie-shells of the value of a purāṇa or kārṣāpaṇa (kāhaṇ).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दभ्रसभा<BR>dabhra-sabhā (SII 3), the golden hall in the Chhidam-<BR>baram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाढा<BR>dāḍhā (CII 4), a canine tooth; derived from Sanskrit<BR>daṃṣṭrā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दधि<BR>dadhi (IE 7-12), confused with udadhi and used to indi-<BR>cate ‘four’.<BR>Cf. a-dugdha-dadhi-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); curds which the<BR>villagers (probably, the milkmen) were obliged to supply to<BR>the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दहन|दहनं|दहनः<BR>dahana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दहरभिक्षु<BR>dahara-bhikṣu (LL), a young Buddhist monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैर्घायुष<BR>dairgh-āyuṣa (CII 1), ‘conducive to long life’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैवागारिक<BR>Daivāgārika (EI 7), the priest in charge of a temple or an<BR>officer in charge of temples.<BR>(IE 8-3), probably, a priest of the shrine of the king's tute-<BR>lary deity; sometimes mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैवज्ञ|दैवज्ञः<BR>Daivajña (IE 8-3; EI 7), an astrologer; sometimes men-<BR>tioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैवपुत्र<BR>Daivaputra (IE 8-2; EI 30), same as Devaputra; title of<BR>certain kings of the Kuṣāṇa dynasty; derived from a Chinese<BR>title meaning ‘the Son of Heaven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैव्य|दैव्यं<BR>daivya (SITI), an act of the gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्ष|दक्षः<BR>dakṣa, used in the late Tantra literature in the sense of<BR>dakṣiṇa, ‘the south’ (cf. Sircar, Studies in the Georgraphy of Ancient<BR>and Medieval India, p. 76, note 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिण|दक्षिणः<BR>dakṣiṇa (EI 32), the sacred fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणा<BR>dakṣiṇā (EI 32), perquisite.<BR>(BL), a present or gift to a Brāhmaṇa for a service.<BR>(CII 1), cf. prāṇa-dakṣinā, same as prāṇa-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणभुज<BR>Dakṣiṇa-bhuja (SITI), ‘the right hand’; a trusted lieutenant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणामूर्ति|दक्षिणामूर्तिः|दक्षिणामूर्त्ति<BR>Dakṣiṇāmūrti (SII 12), an aspect of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणापथ|दक्षिणापथः<BR>Dakṣiṇāpatha (CII 3), ‘the region of the south’; a name<BR>for Southern India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणापथसाधार<BR>Dakṣiṇāpatha-sādhāra (CII 3), ‘the Pillar of Dakṣiṇāpatha’;<BR>title of a ruler. Sādhāra may be a mistake for sv-ādhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणावर्तशङ्ख<BR>dakṣiṇāvarta-śaṅkha (SII 1), a conch-shell with convolutions<BR>from left to right.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणायन|दक्षिणायनं<BR>dakṣiṇ-āyana (IA 19), the period during which the sun<BR>moves from south to north; cf. uttar-āyaṇa (IA 17).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणी<BR>dakṣiṇī, dākṣiṇya, cf. Prakrit dachini (ML); same as dakṣiṇā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाक्षिण्य|दाक्षिण्यं<BR>dākṣiṇya, cf. dakṣiṇya (EI 23); same as dakṣiṇā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलअधिकारि<BR>Dala-adhikāri (IE 8-3; SITI; ASLV), Dravidian-Sans-<BR>krit; same as Sainyādhikārin or Senāpati, Dalada-adhikāri or<BR>Dalavāy, a commander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलदअधिकारि<BR>Dalada-adhikāri (ASLV), same as Dala-adhikāri or Dalavāy,<BR>the commander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवाय्<BR>Dalavāy (IE 8-3; ASLV; SITI), same as Dala-adhikāri,<BR>Dalada-adhikāri or Senāpati; the commander of forces; some-<BR>times also enjoying the title Daṇdanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवायग्रहार<BR>Dalavāy-agrahāra (ASLV), village granted for military<BR>service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवायि<BR>Dalavāyi (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a general, a chief-<BR>tain, or the minister of state; same as Dalavāy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवृत्ति<BR>Dala-vṛtti (CITD), from Telugu-Kannaḍa dala, ‘army’,<BR>and Sanskrit vṛtti; probably, a grant for the maintenance of<BR>the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम|दमः<BR>dama, cf. dāma (EI 23); same as dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाम<BR>dāma (EI 27; CII 4), name of a coin; derived from dramma.<BR>(EI 19), abbreviation of the name Dāmodara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमनक|दमनकः<BR>damanaka (SITI), a fragrant plant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमनकचतुर्दशी<BR>damanaka-caturdaśī (EI 23), same as Caitra su-di 14;<BR>also called damanaka-parvan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमनकपर्वन्<BR>damanaka-parvan (EI 23, 31), same as damanaka-caturdaśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डामर|डामरः<BR>ḍāmara (EI 12), tumultuous, terrible; a landlord or<BR>wealthy cultivator possessing much land [in ancient Kashmir],<BR>according to the Rājataraṅgiṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्म<BR>damma (SITI), same as dramma; name of a coin; derived<BR>from Greek drachma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दान|दानं<BR>dāna, dānā (ML), a gift.<BR>(HRS), known from Maitraka records to mean the so-<BR>called voluntary gifts of subjects.<BR>Cf. dānā-sambandhe (LP), ‘as regards the sale-tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण<BR>dāṇa (IE 8-5; LP), same as dāna, road-cess; customs<BR>duties; cf. the official designation Dāṇī (Sanskrit Dānin).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणचोरि<BR>dāṇa-cori (EI 32), smuggling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानादायदानीभोग<BR>dānādāya-dānībhoga (LP), explained as ‘local cess or road-<BR>cess’; dāya is explained as ‘a gift to Brāhmaṇas or temples’,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-079" target="_blank">Page-079+ 40</a>]<BR>dānī as ‘land tax’ and bhoga as ‘right of enjoyment’; but probably,<BR>dāṇ-ādāya means excise or customs duties and dāni-bhoga a<BR>tax for the maintenance of the tax-collector.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानाधिकारिन्<BR>Dān-ādhikārin (EI 12), officer in charge of gifts, mentioned<BR>along with the Śāsan-ādhikārika, ‘officer in charge of grants<BR>(or their writing)’. See Dharm-ādhikārin. It may also mean<BR>‘a tolls-collector’ (cf. dāna, Dānin).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दणाइक्<BR>Daṇāik (ASLV), corrupt form of Daṇdanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानमुख<BR>dāna-mukha (EI 7; ML), a gift; the principal gift; same<BR>as deya-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानपलं<BR>dāna-palaṃ (IA 11), actually dāna(ṃ*)palaṃ, i. e. ‘the dāna<BR>(levy) is one pala’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानपति|दानपतिः<BR>Dānapati (EI 28, 30; HD), one who gives a gift; one who<BR>dedicates the images of a deity (especially as the result of a<BR>previous vow); probably, also an official designation; see<BR>Horamurta (CII 2-1), Dānādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानप्पु<BR>dāna-ppuṟam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; land set apart for<BR>the purpose of charity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानप्रदानक<BR>dāna-pradānaka (CII 4), all kinds of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानशाला<BR>dāna-śālā (IA 11), a hall for the distribution of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानवोलापन<BR>dāna-volāpana (LP), dāna (road-cess) and volāpana (tax;<BR>cf. Gujarātī valāvaṇuṃ). See Volāpika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दनायक<BR>Danāyaka (IA 20), corrupt from of Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्ड|दंड|दंडं|दंडः|दण्डः<BR>daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12), fine or tax, mentioned along with<BR>suṅka (śulka); a levy or free service (cf. prayāṇa-daṇda).<BR>(EI 24), fines; authority.<BR>(HRS), fines; distinguished from atyaya in the Artha-<BR>śāstra.<BR>(CII 1), punishment.<BR>(ASLV), judicial punishment; sometimes possibly also<BR>‘administration’.<BR>(EI 25), ‘five’.<BR>(EI 30; LP), contraction of Daṇdanāyaka.<BR>(EI 28), Oḏiyā; a path (cf. daṇḍā).<BR>Cf. taṇḍu (SITI), a palanquin; a pole for carrying the<BR>vehicle on which the image of a deity is set up.<BR>Cf. daṇḍu, taṇḍu (SITI), an army; going on a military<BR>expedition.<BR>Cf. taṇdam (SII 1; CITD); fine, penalty or punishment;<BR>a punitive tax; a fine or tax payable as penalty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डा<BR>daṇḍā (EI 31), Oḏiyā; a boundary line or road. See<BR>daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डभोगिक<BR>Dāṇḍabhogika (HD), same as Dāṇdapāśika (q. v.), or the<BR>police magistrate. See Ep. Ind., Vol XIII, p. 339.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डदशापराध<BR>daṇḍa-daś-āparādha (CII 4), fines including those imposed<BR>for the ten offences; same as daś-āparādha. See daṇḍadoṣa-daś-<BR>āparādha, daṇḍa-śulka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डादाय<BR>daṇḍ-ādāya (EI 20), fines; see Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp.<BR>253-54.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिनाथ<BR>Daṇḍādhinātha (EI 16; SII 1; HD), same as Daṇḍapāla,<BR>Daṇḍanāyaka, etc. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XIV, p. 55.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिनायक<BR>Daṇḍādhināyaka (SII 1), a general; same as Daṇḍādhinātha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिप|दंडाधिप|दण्डाधिपः<BR>Daṇḍādhipa (BL; HD), the commander of forces; same<BR>as Daṇḍapāla, Daṇḍādhipati, etc. See the commentary on the<BR>Yaśastilaka, I, p. 91; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 151.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिपति<BR>Daṇḍādhipati (EI 26), cf. Daṇdanāyaka, etc.<BR>(LP), explained as ‘a governor’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधीश्वर<BR>Daṇḍādhīśvara (EI 5), same as Daṇḍādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डदोष<BR>daṇḍa-doṣa, cf. sa-daṇḍadoṣa (EI 23); fines. See daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डदोषदशापराध<BR>daṇḍadoṣa-daśāparādha (HRS), same as daṇḍa-daśāpa-<BR>rādha; cf. sahya-daś-āparādha; sa-daśāparādha means ‘with the<BR>privilege of remission for the ten offences’, according to some;<BR>seems to mean ‘with the right to enjoy fines for the ten offences’;<BR>cf. daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डक|दंडक|दंडकः|दण्डकः<BR>daṇḍaka (EI 30), probably, a regulation.<BR>(IE 8-8), meaning uncertain; probably, fines.<BR>Cf. daṇḍaku (IA 16), a boundary mark or land-mark.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डक्काणम्<BR>daṇḍa-kkāṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; amount imposed<BR>as fine; cf. daṇḍam kuṟṟam (EI 30; SITI), a levy of fines; fine<BR>and penalty imposed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डमार्ग<BR>daṇḍa-mārga (ASLV), military route.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डनाथ<BR>Daṇḍanātha (EI 16; CII 4; SII 1), commander of an<BR>army. See Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 31. Cf. Daṇḍanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डनायक|दंडनायक|दण्डनायकः<BR>Daṇḍanāyaka (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 4; BL), probably a<BR>translation of Greek Strategos; a general; a leader of forces,<BR>an army officer; a military commander; also called Daṇḍa-<BR>nātha, Daṇdanetṛ, etc.; sometimes also called Mahāsāmanta,<BR>Senādibāhattaraniyogādhiṣṭhāyaka, Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin,<BR>Mahāpasāyita, etc., additionally; see Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, Sarva-<BR>daṇḍanāyaka, Mahāsarvadaṇḍanāyaka.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-081" target="_blank">Page-081+ 40</a>]<BR>(LP), generally, the viceroy or governor of a province;<BR>representative of the king.<BR>(ASLV), the commander of forces and officer in charge<BR>of administration; title of the provincial governors; similar to<BR>the Mansabdār of the Mughal period.<BR>(HD), a prefect of the police, according to Stein (Rāja-<BR>taraṅgiṇī, VII. 951); ‘a General or Magistrate’, according to<BR>some (cf. Kielhorn's Southern List, Nos. 291, 292, 296). In<BR>the Bṛhatsaṃhitā (7. 2-4), the queen, Yuvarāja, Senāpati and<BR>Daṇḍanāyaka are placed on the same level in the matter of the<BR>staff (daṇḍa) to be prepared for them.<BR>Cf. Taḍeya-daṇḍanāyaka, explained as ‘the general in<BR>charge of reserves’, from Kannaḍa, taḍĕ, ‘far, restraint’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डनायक<BR>Dāṇḍanāyaka (EI 23; HD), same as Daṇdanāyaka. See<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 269.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डनेतृ|दंडनेतृ<BR>Daṇḍanetṛ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 233), designation of<BR>a leader of forces; cf. Daṇḍanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाल|दंडपाल|दण्डपालः<BR>Daṇḍapāla (HD), an officer in charge of all branches of<BR>the army (Arthaśāstra, I. 12); cf. Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR>(IE 8-3), cf. Dāṇḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाणिक<BR>Daṇḍapāṇika (IE 8-3), same as Daṇḍapāśika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपरीक्षा<BR>Daṇḍaparīkṣā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, p. 101); Oḏiyā;<BR>a governor; same as Sanskrit Daṇḍaparīkṣaka as well as Daṇda-<BR>nāyaka of other inscriptions; governor of a daṇḍapāṭa or province.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाशिक|दण्डपाशिकः<BR>Daṇḍapāśika (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), a policeman;<BR>an official who was probably the leader of a group of Dāṇḍikas;<BR>officer in charge of punishment (i. e. criminal justice), accord-<BR>ing to some; a policeman (same as Oḏiyā Daṇḍuāsi meaning<BR>‘a village watchman’); called Talāra and Ārakṣika (IHQ),<BR>December 1960, p. 266). See Yaśastilaka, I, p. 50; Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XI, p. 83; Vol. XII, p. 9. Cf. Dāṇḍabhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डपाशिक<BR>Dāṇḍapāśika (IE 8-3; EI 23; CII 3, 4; HD), same as<BR>Daṇḍapāśika or Daṇḍapāṇika, ‘an officer entrusted with the<BR>punishment of criminals’; see Pañcatantra II, Kathā 4 (spelt<BR>Daṇḍapāśaka meaning ‘a watchman’); Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाट<BR>daṇḍapāṭa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, p. 107); Oḏiyā; the<BR>province of a kingdom; an administrative unit under a Daṇḍa-<BR>parīkṣā; cf. Daṇḍa or Daṇdanāyaka called Daṇḍaparīkṣā in the<BR>Orissan records; also paṭṭa in the sense of ‘a district’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपति<BR>Daṇḍapati (BL; HD), a commander of forces, or a governor;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-082" target="_blank">Page-082+ 40</a>]<BR>same as Daṇdanātha, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, pp. 148,<BR>156.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डशक्ति<BR>Daṇḍaśakti (IE 8-3; HD), a police officer; possibly the<BR>same as Dāṇḍika or Daṇḍapāśika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 250.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डशुल्क<BR>daṇḍa-śulka, cf. daṇḍa-śulk-ādi-vividh-āya-samanvita (EI 23);<BR>income from fines and tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डवाणि<BR>daṇḍavāṇi (SII 2), standard gold.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डवासिक|दण्डवासिकः<BR>Daṇḍavāsika (HD), Prakrit form of Daṇḍapāśika. See<BR>Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 129.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डवासिक<BR>Dāṇḍavāsika (EI 23), same as Daṇḍavāsika, Dāṇḍapāśika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाय<BR>daṇḍ-āya (IA 29; SII 11-1), income from fines; explain-<BR>ed as ‘a tax’; cf. ‘the whole of the levy called daṇḍ-āya as<BR>much as accrued in the village’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डेश<BR>Daṇḍeśa (EI 5; SII 1; HD), official designation; same as<BR>Daṇḍanātha. See JBBRAS, Vol. XV, p. 386.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिक|दंडिक|दंडिकः|दण्डिकः<BR>Daṇḍika (HD), same as Daṇḍapāśika. See Vogel, Ant.<BR>Ch. St., p. 166. (CII 4), explained by some as a magistrate.<BR>Cf. Dāṇḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डिक|दांडिक|दांडिकः|दाण्डिकः<BR>Dāṇḍika (CII 3; HD), a police officer. See Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 306; CII, Vol. III, p. 216; Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII,<BR>p. 321. Generally Dāṇḍika and Dāṇḍapāśika are mentioned side<BR>by side (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 231); probably the Dāṇḍika<BR>was the head of a group or outpost of the Dāṇḍapāśikas. Cf.<BR>Daṇḍika, Daṇḍ-oddharaṇika (collector of fines).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिका|दंडिका<BR>daṇḍikā (SITI), also called daṇḍu; a palanquin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिकाजीवित<BR>daṇḍikā-jīvita (SITI), tax-free land given to palanquin-<BR>bearers for enjoyment during their life-time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिनदारि<BR>daṇḍinadāri (ASLV), military route. See ḍaṇḍudova.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डोद्धरणिक<BR>Daṇḍ-oddharaṇika (EI 9), literally, ‘collector of fines’;<BR>mentioned along with Daṇḍapāśika; may be the same as<BR>Dāṇḍika. Cf. Caur-oddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डोपजातक<BR>daṇḍ-opajātaka (EI 28), money exacted as fines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डोपरिक<BR>Daṇḍoparika (EI 13), probably Daṇda (i. e. Daṇdanāyaka)<BR>and Uparika; otherwise Daṇḍoparika may mean a judge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्ड|दंड|दंडं|दंडः|दण्डः<BR>daṇḍa (ASLV), a palanquin; its use was a privilege some-<BR>times specially granted to favourites or distinguished persons by<BR>the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डुआसि<BR>Daṇḍuāsi (IE 8-3), Oḏiyā; village watchman; derived<BR>from Sanskrit Dāṇḍapāśika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डुदोव<BR>daṇḍudova (ASLV), a military route. See daṇḍinadāri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डाङ्ग्<BR>ḍāṅg (IA 26), also spelt dāṅk, corrupt form of ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणि<BR>dāṇi (HRS), known from Caulukya records and explained<BR>by some as ‘the king's dues’; perquisite of the collector of the<BR>duties called dāṇa or dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानी<BR>Dānī (IE 8-5; EI 26), i. e. Dānin, officer collecting<BR>tax or corn; officer storing the corn collected as tax from the<BR>farmers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानिभाग<BR>dāni-bhāga, same as dāṇi-bhoga (q. v.). See Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 256.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणिभोग<BR>dāṇi-bhoga (HRS), periodical supplies of fruits, firewood<BR>and the like by the villagers, according to some; tax for main-<BR>taining the collectors of the tax called dāna; same as dāṇi-<BR>bhoga-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणिभोगभाग<BR>dāṇi-bhoga-bhāga (HRS), same as dāṇi-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानीवोलापिक<BR>Dānī-volāpika (LP), explained as ‘the collector of dānī<BR>(land cess) and volāpanā (tax, relating to Gujarātī vaḻāvaṇuṃ).’<BR>See Volāpika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डाङ्क्<BR>ḍāṅk (IA 26), corrupt form of ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्णाइक्<BR>Daṇṇāik (ASLV), corrupt form of Daṇḍanāyaka; some-<BR>times the designation of a judge at the capital of the Vijaya-<BR>nagara kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्णायक<BR>Daṇṇāyaka (IE 8-3; ASLV), corrupt form of Daṇḍanāyaka;<BR>a designation sometimes enjoyed by the Dala-adhikāri or<BR>commander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्त|दंत|दंतः|दन्तः<BR>danta (EI 7), a pin.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्तकार|दंतकार|दन्तकारः<BR>Dantakāra (LL), a worker in ivory; here danta means<BR>hasti-danta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्तिन्|दंतिन्<BR>dantin (IE 8-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दापक<BR>Dāpaka (EI 3; BL; HD), usually regarded as the same as<BR>Dūtaka; but really ‘one who causes another to give’, i. e. the<BR>creator of a rent-free holding which was ratified by the king.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, pp. 177, 243.<BR>(CII 1), a matter relating to giving gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दापन|दापनं<BR>dāpana, cf. dāpanāya (LP), ‘for making one pay’. See<BR>dāvāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दापित|दापितः<BR>dāpita (LP), ‘caused to be paid’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दारद्रणक<BR>dāradraṇaka (CII 3), a fiscal term of uncertain implication;<BR>an agricultural cess or marriage tax, according to some. See<BR>Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 242.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दारक|दारकः<BR>Dāraka (IA 18; CII 1), explained as ‘the son of a king,<BR>whose mother's rank does not assure him an official title’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्श|दर्शः<BR>darśa (IA 17), the new-moon; cf. darśa-tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्शन|दर्शनं<BR>darśana (IE 8-5; EI 32, 33), a levy; same as Persian<BR>nazrāna. Cf. Tamil tariśana-kāṇikkai (SITI), presents offered to a<BR>king or a chief when one meets him.<BR>(CII 1), used in the sense of pradarśana, ‘showing’.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘six’; cf. dṛṣti, ‘two’.<BR>(IA 14), used in the sense of ‘a religious procession for the<BR>purpose of visiting a deity’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्शपूर्णमास<BR>darśapūrṇamāsa (CII 4), name of a Vedic sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्शतिथि<BR>darśa-tithi (EI 13), name of a tithi. Cf. darśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्वीकर्मन्<BR>Darvīkarman (EI 21), measurer of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशबलमहाबल<BR>Daśabala-mahābala (EI 20), epithet of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशबन्ध|दशबन्धः<BR>daśabandha (SITI), variously explained as (1) one-tenth<BR>of the revenue set apart for repairs to the tanks and wells for<BR>irrigation purposes; (2) land, the income from which would<BR>be equal to the amount thus set apart; (3) the right of collect-<BR>ing one-tenth of the produce of lands irrigated from the waters<BR>of a tank or well by the person who repairs the water source;<BR>also explained as tax equal to one-tenth of the income of the<BR>subject (Ray, DHNI, Vol. II, p. 1113). See daśavandha.<BR>(SITI) tax or cess levied to keep the source of water<BR>supply like the tanks, etc., in good repair.<BR>(EI 4), rent-free land or probably land paying only<BR>one-tenth of the actual rent.<BR>(EI 20), one-tenth share.<BR>Cf. daśa-bandhe (LP), ‘at 10 per cent’.<BR>Cf. daśavandha (SII 3), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशबन्ध<BR>dāśabandha-visatia (viṃśatika) ttriprastha (HRS), kinds of tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दासभृतक<BR>dāsa-bhṛtaka (CII 1), slaves and servants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशग्रामिक<BR>Dāśagrāmika (IE 8-3; EI 24), the headman of a group of ten<BR>villages or the chairman of the council of a group of ten villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशहराव्रत<BR>Daśaharā-vrata (EI 27), a religious ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशक्रिया<BR>daśa-kriyā (SITI), work of the architects who were to<BR>look after the repairs of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशमूलिक<BR>Daśamūlika (CII 4), official designation; same as<BR>Daśamūlin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशमूलिन्<BR>Daśamūlin (EI 21; CII 4; BL), an official designation;<BR>probably, a physician; same as Daśamūlika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशापचार<BR>daś-āpacāra (IE 8-5; EI 29), same as daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशापराध<BR>daś-āparādha (CII 3, 4), literally, ‘the ten offences’; but<BR>really, the fines for the ten offences; cf. sa-daś-āparādha (IE 8-5);<BR>power to punish and realise fines for the ten offences; also<BR>called daś-āpacāra. According to the Buddhists, the ten sins<BR>were murder, theft, adultery, lying, calumny, insult, idle<BR>talk, hatred, covetousness and dogmatic error (A. Getty, The<BR>Gods of Northern Buddhism, p. xxv, note). For a Brahmanical<BR>list, see Dāśāparādhika; cf. pañca-mahāpātaka, pañc-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशापराधिक|दाशापराधिकः<BR>Dāśāparādhika (IE 8-3; EI 29; HD), a judge dealing<BR>with the ten offences (viz. theft, murder of women, adultery, use<BR>of abusive language, violation of order, mixing of castes, illegal<BR>pregnancy, obscenity, assault and abortion, according to some).<BR>It has been said that the ten offences or aparādhas are those<BR>of which the king could take cognisance suo moto. For the ten<BR>aparādhas, see Kane, Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 264; cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दसरा<BR>Dasarā (EI 5), Āśvina su-di 10.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशरथस्त्री<BR>Daśaratha-strī (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशरि<BR>Dāśari (ASLV; SITI), a class of subordinates of the<BR>headman of particular communities in the Vijayanagara empire;<BR>same as Samayācāra or Samayācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशवन्ध<BR>daśavandha, cf. daśavanna (IA 30), explained as ‘land<BR>granted to a person for repairing or building a tank on condi-<BR>tion of paying in money or kind one-tenth or some small<BR>share of the produce’ and as ‘land granted at one-tenth of the<BR>usual rates to a person in consideration of his constructing or<BR>repairing a tank’. See daśabandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दासी<BR>dāsī (CITD), a handmaid, slave, concubine, dancing girl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दस्र|दस्रं|दस्रः<BR>dasra (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दासूरिपट्टु<BR>dāsūri-paṭṭu (CITD), Telugu; probably, silk of the<BR>Tusser variety; cf. Hobson-Jabson, s. v. tussah, tusser.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दटित<BR>daṭita (LP), well-founded.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दत्ति|दत्तिः<BR>datti (EI 23; CII 4; CITD), a gift; cf. Sarvasiddhi-datti<BR>(EI 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौःसाधसाधनिक<BR>Dauḥsādhasādhanika (EI 30; HD), explained as ‘those who<BR>catch dangerous robbers whom it is difficult to secure’. See<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211. Cf. Duḥsādhasādhanika (ibid., Vol. XI,<BR>p. 310), Dussādhyasādhaka, Duṣṭasāhanī, Mahādauḥsādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौःसाधिक|दौःसाधिकः<BR>Dauḥsādhika (IE 8-3; HD), same as Dauḥsādhasādhanika,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-086" target="_blank">Page-086+ 40</a>]<BR>Duḥsādhyasādhanika, Dussādhyasādhaka, Duṣṭasāhani, etc. See Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9. Lexicons explain it as ‘gate-keeper’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौत्य|दौत्यं<BR>dautya, see dūtya and Dūtaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौवारिक|दौवारिकः<BR>Dauvārika (EI 28; SII 1; ASLV; BL; HD), a door-keeper;<BR>a gate-keeper. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12; Lalitavistara, p. 136;<BR>Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 30.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दावापन<BR>dāvāpana, cf. dāvāpanāya (LP), ‘for making one pay’; cf.<BR>dāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दावापित<BR>dāvāpita (LP), caused to be paid.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाय|दायः<BR>dāya (EI 23), a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दायाद|दायादः<BR>dāyāda (CII 4), an agnate.<BR>(LL), Buddhist; an heir of the faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देनरिउस्<BR>denarius (IE 8-3), name of the Roman silver coin and also<BR>of the Roman gold coin usually called aureus; cf. dīnāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देश|देशः<BR>deśa (IE 8-4; CII 3, 4), a territorial term meaning a<BR>small area or a group of villages in some cases but a kingdom,<BR>district, tract or country in others.<BR>(IE 8-4), a country of which there were seventy two in<BR>Bhārata or Bhāratavarṣa.<BR>(CII 1), a part of anything.<BR>(EI 24), a synonym of āspada.<BR>(ASLV), a school of music.<BR>Cf. Kona-deśa (EI 32), also called a maṇdala, rāṣṭra, sīma,<BR>sthala, etc.<BR>Cf. deśa-bhāṣā (EI 17), ‘vernacular of a province’.<BR>Cf. teśa-kālam (SITI), locality and time; also teśa-vāḻi,<BR>officer in charge of a village or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशाधिकृत<BR>Deś-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; HD), same as Deśādhipati; governor<BR>of a deśa or a province, district or sub-division. See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. I, p. 5 (Prakrit Desādhikata). See Sarva-deś-ādhikṛta.<BR>(LL), explained as ‘a local prefect’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशाधिपति<BR>Deś-ādhipati (EI 26, 30), same as Deśādhikṛta; ruler of the<BR>territorial or administrative unit called deśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशाक्षपटलाधिकृत<BR>Deś-ākṣapaṭalādhikṛta (EI 28), officer of the records and<BR>accounts office pertaining to a territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशकूट<BR>Deśakūṭa (AI 7), official designation; cf. Rāṣṭrakūṭa,<BR>Grāmakūṭa, Deś-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशमर्यादा<BR>deśa-maryādā, custom prevalent in a locality; cf. deśa-<BR>maryād-āṟuvaṇa-ānvita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247, text line<BR>103), aṟuvaṇa being a tax of six paṇas levied on rent-free lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशना<BR>deśanā, Prakrit desanā (EI 21), exposition of the Buddhist<BR>doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशरीत<BR>deśa-rīta (Chamba), customary taxes of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशतलार<BR>Deśa-talāra (LP), probably, a police superintendent.<BR>Cf. Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशठक्कुर<BR>Deśa-ṭhakkura (LP), probably, a small chieftain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशवालि<BR>Deśavāḻi (EI 18), official designation. Cf. deśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशायि<BR>Deśāyi (ASLV), same as Sanskrit Deśādhipati or Deśādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशी<BR>deśī (EI 11), a guild of local merchants. This is<BR>also the name of Prakrit words which are neither Sanskrit<BR>(tat-sama) nor derived from Sanskrit (tad-bhava).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिक|देशिकः<BR>Deśika (SII 1), a [Jain] teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिलक<BR>Deśilaka, official designation (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71);<BR>same as Deśillaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिल्लक<BR>Deśillaka (EI 28), official designation as in rāṣtra-grāma-<BR>kūṭa-deśillaka-mahattar-ādhikārik-ādīn; same as Desilaka, Deśakūṭa;<BR>cf. Purillaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिमुख्य<BR>Deśi-mukhya (EI 31), same as modern Deśmukh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशोत्तार<BR>deś-ottāra (LP), permission for allowing the cargo to go<BR>from one place to another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देव|देवं|देवः<BR>deva, a god; cf. te-aḍimai (SITI), a dancing woman as<BR>the servant of a god; maid servant attached to a temple; cf.<BR>teva-kuḍimai, tenancy under the control of a temple; tevakulam<BR>(deva-kula), a temple.<BR>(EI 7), the king.<BR>(EI 3), a saint.<BR>(EI 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवभोग|देवभोगः<BR>deva-bhoga (EI 23, 31; SITI), rent-free property of a<BR>temple; land given for the enjoyment of temples; same as<BR>deva-dāya, etc., Cf. devabhoga-hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवभोगहल<BR>devabhoga-hala (EI 7, 8, 15, 24), rent-free land in the<BR>possession of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवच्छन्द|देवच्छंद|देवच्छन्दः<BR>deva-cchanda (SII 2), name of a jewel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदान<BR>deva-dāna (EI 5, 23, 25, 30; SITI; ASLV), gift made<BR>to a god; rent-free land in the possession of a temple; same as<BR>deva-bhoga, deva-deya, deva-dāya, dev-āgrahāra.<BR>Cf. devadāna-iṟaiyili (SITI), village or land granted to<BR>a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदासी<BR>deva-dāsī (EI 22, 33; LL), a dancing girl attached to a<BR>temple; a female temple-servant. See vilāsinī, gaṇikā, mahārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदाय<BR>deva-dāya (IE 8-5; EI 23; CII 4; SITI), a rent-free<BR>holding in the possession of a temple; a gift made in honour<BR>of a god; same as deva-deya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदेय<BR>deva-deya (IE 8-5; HRS), grant made in favour of temples;<BR>same as deva-dāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवधर्म|देवधर्मः<BR>deva-dharma (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 144), same as<BR>deya-dharma when the gift was the image of a god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवाध्यक्ष<BR>Dev-ādhyakṣa, superintendent of religious foundations.<BR>See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 99.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदि<BR>devadi (IA 19), ‘the establishment of a temple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवद्रोणी<BR>deva-droṇī (IE 8-3; EI 10), usually taken to mean ‘a pro-<BR>cession of the images of gods’, or ‘procession or ablution of<BR>images’; but probably, ‘rent-free property of a temple’ (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXIV pp. 143-44); cf. deva-droṇī-sambaddha (EI<BR>23). A Prakrit inscription (A.R. Ep., 1959-60, No. B 173)<BR>has deva-doṇi data = Sanskrit deva-droṇī dattā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवद्रोणीसम्बद्ध<BR>Devadroṇī-sambaddha (IE 8-3), same as Devadroṇy-adhikṛta;<BR>officer in charge of temple property (devadroṇī, usually taken<BR>in the sense of ‘a procession of the images of gods)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवद्रोण्यधिकृत<BR>Devadroṇy-adhikṛta (IE 8-3; BL), explained as ‘the superin-<BR>tendent of the procession of idols’; but probably, the superin-<BR>tendent of the property of a temple or of temple property in<BR>general; same as Devadroṇī-sambaddha; cf. deva-droṇī (EI 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवागार|देवागारः<BR>dev-āgāra, cf. tevāram, devāram (SITI), a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवाग्रहार<BR>dev-āgrahāra (IE 8-5; EI 23, 25, 30; SITI), rent-free<BR>village granted to a temple; same as deva-bhoga, etc.; see agra-<BR>hāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवगृह|देवगृहं<BR>deva-gṛha (EI 24), a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवगृहजगती<BR>devagṛha-jagatī (IA 14), explained as ‘a temple and its<BR>ground’ or ‘a temple with the buildings attached to it.’ But<BR>cf. jagatī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवक|देवकः<BR>devaka (IA 23), the guardian spirit or a god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकरण<BR>deva-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as the deva-sthāna<BR>department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकर्मन्<BR>devakarman (SII 1), divine rites.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकर्मिन्<BR>Devakarmin (EI 30; SII 1, 3, 12); cf. tevar-kaṉmi, devar-<BR>kaṉmi (EI 3; SITI); a Pūjāri or temple priest, a temple<BR>servant; servant of a god; an officer in charge of the affairs<BR>of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवक्रिया<BR>deva-kriyā (IA 23), worship of gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुल|देवकुलं<BR>devakula (EI 9, 23), a temple; cf. ācāryakula (LL).<BR>(EI 21), a gallery of portrait statues of deified or semi-<BR>deified ancestors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलपुष्करिणी<BR>devakula-puṣkariṇī (IE 8-5), temples and tanks [the cons-<BR>truction of the former and the excavation of the latter requiring<BR>the permission of the king or landlord].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुली<BR>devakulī (CII 4), a small shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलिक<BR>devakulika (LL), a temple-servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलिका<BR>devakulikā (EI 8; HA), a shrine; a cell; a supplementary<BR>or smaller shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुटीकाष्ठ<BR>devakuṭī-kāṣṭha (EI 7), a measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवालय|देवालयः<BR>dev-ālaya (EI 23), a temple; same as devakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवानांप्रिय|देवानाम्प्रिय|देवानाम्प्रियः<BR>Devānāṃpriya (EI 21; CII 1; LL), a royal title; title assu-<BR>med by the Maurya kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवाण्डज<BR>Devāṇḍaja (EI 32), same as Garuḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवनिकाय|देवनिकायः<BR>deva-nikāya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 115), probably, temple<BR>authorities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवपुत्र<BR>Devaputra (IE 8-2; EI 8, 21, 30), royal title of foreign<BR>origin; ‘the Son of Heaven’; title of certain Kuṣāṇa kings;<BR>same as Daivaputra.<BR>(LL), Buddhist; an angel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवरडियाल्<BR>devaraḍiyāḻ (ASLV), Tamil; a dancing girl attached to<BR>a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवारम्<BR>devāram (SITI), Tamil corruption of Sanskrit devāgāra;<BR>a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवातिदेव|देवातिदेवः<BR>Devātideva (EI 1), epithet of the Buddha and gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवटिसलम्<BR>devaṭisalam (EI 12), a ceremony indicative of royalty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवत्रा<BR>devatrā (IE 8-5), same as deva-dāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देववारिक<BR>Deva-vārika (EI 33), superintendent of a temple; cf.<BR>Vārika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 142, text line 35.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देववेश्मकरण<BR>devaveśma-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of<BR>temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवविहार<BR>deva-vihāra, land in the possession of temples. See Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 217.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देववृत्ति<BR>deva-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart for the maintenance of<BR>temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवयज्ञ|देवयज्ञः<BR>deva-yajña (CII 4), offerings to gods; one of the five<BR>mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवायतन|देवायतनं<BR>dev-āyatana (EI 23), a temple; same as devakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवी<BR>Devī (IE 8-2; CII 1, 3; LL), a title originally of wives<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-090" target="_blank">Page-090+ 40</a>]<BR>of independent monarchs and later also of feudatory rulers;<BR>often used as a termination of the names of wives of rulers of<BR>all classes; cf. Mahādevī; also means the Mother-goddess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवीकर्मान्तिक<BR>Devī-karmāntika (EI 16), a temple officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवीकुमार<BR>Devī-kumāra (IA 18; CII 1), explained as ‘the son of a<BR>king, who has the rank of a prince’; the king's son born of a<BR>queen and not of a concubine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवोत्तर<BR>devottara (IE 8-5), Bengali corruption of devatrā; same as<BR>deva-dāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देय|देयं<BR>deya (IE 8-5), periodical offerings to be presented to the<BR>king or landlord; cf. ādeya, deya-meya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देयधर्म|देयधर्मः<BR>deya-dharma (EI 1; CII 3; ML), a pious gift; an appro-<BR>priate religious gift; an expression used in numerous donative<BR>inscriptions. A deity installed for worship was also called<BR>deya-dharma (sometimes deva-dharma) in medieval records. Same<BR>as dharma-deya, dharma-dāya, dharma-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देयधर्मपरित्याग<BR>deyadharma-parityāga (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 10, text<BR>line 2), donation of a religious gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देयमेय<BR>deya-meya (HRS), known from a Śātavāhana record;<BR>king's share in kind and in cash; same as dhānya-hiranya of later<BR>records. See deya, meya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देय्यधर्म<BR>deyya-dharma (EI 32), Pali-Prakrit form of deya-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धडा<BR>dhaḍā, dhaḍī, a small measure of capacity (Ind. Ant., Vol.<BR>XLI, p. 20).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढक्का<BR>ḍhakkā (CII 3), a war drum; used in the Rājataraṅgiṇī<BR>in the sense of a watch-station (cf. Sircar, Geog. Anc. Med. Ind.,<BR>p. 238).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धलवादि<BR>dhaḻa-vādi, dhala-vali (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a tax<BR>probably connected with dala-vṛtti, or at least with dala or<BR>the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानक|धानकं|धानकः<BR>dhānaka, see hema-dhānyaka; also called aṇḍikā; equal to<BR>4 kārṣāpaṇas or to 4 suvarṇas or dīnāras (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 7).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धनिक|धनिकः<BR>dhanika, dhanin (LP), the owner; cf. Gujarātī dhaṇī; used<BR>in the sense of ‘one who is spending or lending money’ in the<BR>Maithilī documents (Proc. IHRC, Vol. XVIII, p. 90).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानिक<BR>dhānika, a coin equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or 64 paṇas according<BR>to the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K.V. Ranga-<BR>swami Aiyanger, p. 125); cf. dhānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धनिकत्व<BR>dhanikatva, cf. dhanikatvaṃ vidhāya (LP), ‘having claimed<BR>ownership’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्य|धान्यं<BR>dhānya, cf. sa-hiraṇya-dhānya-praṇaya-pradeya (IE 8-5); pro-<BR>duce of the fields, a share of which was payable to the king or<BR>landlord; cf. dhāny-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यादाय<BR>dhāny-ādāya (SITI), tax payable in grains; cf. dhāny-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्याधिवास<BR>dhāny-ādhivāsa (EI 32), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यहिरण्य<BR>dhānya-hiraṇya (HRS), revenue in kind and in cash; same<BR>as dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यहिरण्यादेय<BR>dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya (EI 32), tax in crops and cash. See<BR>dhānya-hiraṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यमाष<BR>dhānya-māṣa, weight equal to 1 yava or 2 taṇdulas (JNSI,<BR>Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यवर्ग<BR>dhānya-varga (SITI), literally, ‘the grain group’; actually,<BR>a class of taxes payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्याय<BR>dhāny-āya (EI 7), tax in-grains; cf. dhāny-ādāya; called<BR>nĕll-āyam (SII 12) in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यिक<BR>Dhānyika (LL), a dealer in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर|धरः<BR>dhara, cf. Vinaya-dhara (EI 33), ‘one who has committed<BR>the [Buddhist] Vinaya texts by heart’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरा<BR>dharā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारादत्त<BR>dhārā-datta, cf. tārā-tattam (SITI), a gift made with the<BR>ceremony of libation of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरामण्डल<BR>dharā-maṇḍala (SII 1), a country.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरण|धरणं|धरणः<BR>dharaṇa (CII 4), name of a coin.<BR>(IE 8-8), a silver coin weighing 24 ratis (cf. JNSI, Vol.<BR>II, pp. 28-29) or the half of a gadyāṇaka according to the Līlāvatī;<BR>silver coin of 32 ratis according Manu, etc.<BR>(IE 8-8), same as kārṣāpaṇa or purāṇa.<BR>(EI 3), a gold coin or weight (320 ratis).<BR>(JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 44), sometimes called śāna and ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरणी<BR>dharaṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारणी<BR>dhāraṇī (IA 9; BL), a magic litany usually of the Bud-<BR>dhists; an occult Indian charm, especially Buddhistic; a short<BR>formula intended to represent a particular Tantra text, the<BR>recitation of the dhāraṇī being regarded as equally meritorious<BR>as that of the Tantra itself (Univ. Cey. Rev., January-April,<BR>1960, p. 62, note 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारणिक<BR>dhāraṇika (LP), a debtor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारापूर्वकम्<BR>dhārā-pūrvakam, cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc. See dhātrā-datta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्म|धर्मः|धर्म्म|धर्म्मः<BR>dharma (SII 1), the sacred law; religious merit; a meri-<BR>torious gift, a pious work, a charity; moral precept.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-092" target="_blank">Page-092+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 24), law or law and order.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 116) virtue or religious merit.<BR>(IE 8-2), sometimes prefixed to the titles of kings<BR>and crown-princes; cf. Dharma-mahārāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मबद्ध<BR>dharma-baddha, cf. tarma-pattar (SITI), persons bound by the<BR>law; judicial officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मबान्धव<BR>dharma-bāndhava, ‘one whose only friend is his religious<BR>faith’ or ‘a person who has become the friend of another on an<BR>oath in the name of his religious faith’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मचक्र|धर्मचक्रः|धर्म्मचक्र|धर्म्मचक्रः<BR>dharma-cakra (CII 3; LL), Buddhist; the wheel of Dharma<BR>which was the symbol representing the Buddha on early<BR>Buddhist sculptures, on stone inscriptions and on seals attached<BR>to copperplate grants.<BR>(HA) Jain; the wheel of law supposed to move in<BR>the sky in front of a Jina when he goes on his wanderings from<BR>place to place; one of the members of the parikara of a Jina<BR>image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मचक्रमुद्रा<BR>dharmacakra-mudrā (EI 29), seal bearing the emblem of<BR>the Buddhist wheel of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मदान|धर्म्मदानं<BR>dharma-dāna (ML; SITI), a religious gift; a gift for religious<BR>merit; grant of tax-free land; same as deya-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मदेय<BR>dharma-deya (IA 9; HRS), same as deya-dharma, dharma-<BR>dāya, etc.; a religious grant in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मदेशना<BR>dharma-deśanā (SII 1), a discourse on the sacred law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकार|धर्माधिकारः|धर्म्माधिकार<BR>dharm-ādhikāra (EI 15; IA 9), court of law; an office<BR>relating to the civil and criminal courts as well as to religious<BR>and charitable institutions. See Dharmādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकरण|धर्म्माधिकरण|धर्म्माधिकरणं|धर्म्माधिकरणः<BR>dharm-ādhikaraṇa (EI 18, 23, 25; CII 4; LP), a law-<BR>court; a court of justice. See Dharm-ādhikaraṇin.<BR>Cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of justice.<BR>(HD), a judge. See Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 24-25.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकरणिक|धर्माधिकरणिकः<BR>Dharm-ādhikaraṇika (IE 8-3), a judge; mentioned as a<BR>Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकरणिन्|धर्म्माधिकरणिन्<BR>Dharm-ādhikaraṇin (HD), a judge. See Matsya Purāṇa,<BR>215. 24. The reading is Dharm-ādhikaraṇa in some<BR>manuscripts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकारिन्|धर्म्माधिकारिन्<BR>Dharm-ādhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 33), cf. dharm-ādhikāra (IA<BR>9); an officer in charge of civil and criminal justice as well as<BR>charitable and religious institutions; same as Bṛhat-tantra-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-093" target="_blank">Page-093+ 40</a>]<BR>pati, according to a Kashmirian commentator; usually explained<BR>as ‘a judge’; same as Dharmakarm-ādhikārin and Dharm-ādhyakṣa.<BR>Cf. the Muslim official designations şadruŞ-Şudūr, Dādbak,<BR>etc., explained as ‘the chief judge and grand almoner, or custo-<BR>dian of the king's bequests and charities’ (Journ. As. Soc. Pak.,<BR>Vol. IV, pp. 53-54).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माध्यक्ष|धर्माध्यक्षः|धर्म्माध्यक्ष|धर्म्माध्यक्षः<BR>Dharm-ādhyakṣa (EI 15; HD), generally explained as ‘a<BR>judge’; but he was probably also the superintendent of charities,<BR>etc.; cf. Dharm-ādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्महल<BR>dharma-hala (EI 7), a rent-free holding. See hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मजयस्तम्भ<BR>dharma-jaya-stambha (IA 19), ‘a pillar of the victory of<BR>religion’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकर्माधिकारिन्<BR>Dharmakarm-ādhikārin (EI 21; CII 4), officer in charge of<BR>charities and other religious works; probably the same as<BR>Dharm-ādhyakṣa; cf. Dharm-ādhikārin, Dharma-Pradhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकर्तृ<BR>Dharma-kartṛ (EI 19; IA 12), a temple superintendent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकथिक<BR>Dharma-kathika (LL), cf. Prakrit dhamma-kadhika (EI<BR>15), a [Buddhist] preacher; a preacher of the [Buddhist]<BR>religious system; same as Dharma-kathin; also spelt Dharma-<BR>kathaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकथिन्<BR>Dharma-kathin (CII 2-1; ML), Buddhist; the preacher of<BR>the [Buddhist] religious system; same as Dharma-kathika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मलाभ<BR>dharma-lābha (LP), expression uttered by the Jain monks<BR>[of the Śvetāmbara sect] when they bless a householder saluting<BR>them.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मलेखिन्<BR>Dharma-lekhin (EI 4; CII 4; BL), a writer of charters or<BR>religious documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मलिपि<BR>dharma-lipi (EI 2, 33; CII 1), an edict on the subject of<BR>dharma (religion or moral precepts).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममहाधिराज<BR>Dharma-mahādhirāja (EI 12, 28), royal title; cf. Mahādhi-<BR>rāja and Dharma-mahārāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममहामात्र|धर्ममहामात्रः<BR>Dharma-mahāmātra (IE 8-3; EI 26; CII 1; HD), superin-<BR>tendent of morality; a Mahāmātra (high executive officer)<BR>of the department of religion; an executive officer superin-<BR>tending matters relating to religious affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममहाराज<BR>Dharma-mahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 15, 28), royal title; supposed<BR>to mean ‘a Mahārāja who, at the particular time of issuing a<BR>record, was engaged in an act of religious merit.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममाहाराजाधिराज<BR>Dharma-māhārājādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 5, 15, 28), imperial<BR>title; title assumed by certain rulers. Cf. Dharma-mahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मनिगम<BR>dharma-nigama (LL), probably, a pious hamlet or its<BR>administrative council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मप्रधान|धर्म्मप्रधान<BR>Dharma-pradhāna (EI 21; CII 4), head of the religious<BR>department; cf. Dharm-ādhyakṣa and Dharmakarm-ādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मपुत्र|धर्मपुत्रः|धर्म्मपुत्त्र|धर्म्मपुत्त्रः|धर्म्मपुत्र<BR>dharma-putra (EI 32), ‘one theoretically accepted as a<BR>son’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मराज|धर्मराजः|धर्म्मराज|धर्म्मराजः<BR>Dharmarāja (EI 28), royal title; title of a pious king; cf.<BR>Dharma-mahārāja, etc.; also dharmarājikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मराजगुरु<BR>Dharma-rājaguru (EI 11), designation of the king's pre-<BR>ceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मराजिका<BR>dharmarājikā (IA 14; ML), Buddhist; a stūpa built on<BR>the relics of the Buddha called Dharmarāja; a Buddhist stūpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशाला|धर्म्मशाला<BR>dharma-śālā (IE 8-3; IA 9), a house for accommodating<BR>pilgrims free of cost; cf. śrī-Vāgmatī-jal-āvatāra-sopān-ārāma-ghaṇṭā-<BR>dharmaśālā-pratiṣṭhā-karma. See choultry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मासन|धर्म्मासन|धर्म्मासनं<BR>dharm-āsana (EI 26; SII 3, 13; SITI), a court of justice;<BR>cf. Tamil daṉm-āsanam (EI 22), the seat of justice; a law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मासनभट्ट<BR>Dharmāsana-bhaṭṭa (SITI) a Brāhmaṇa versed in law<BR>assisting in a dharm-āsana or law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशासन|धर्म्मशासन<BR>dharma-śāsana (EI 18, 22, 33; SII 1), an edict relating<BR>to dharma; a religious edict.<BR>(EI 22; SITI), same as tāmra-śāsana; a document<BR>recording a gift made for charitable purposes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशासनपट्ट<BR>dharmaśāsana-paṭṭa (EI 3), a slab containing a religious<BR>edict.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशास्त्र|धर्म्मशास्त्र|धर्म्मशास्त्रं<BR>dharma-śāstra (BL), scriptures.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मस्थान<BR>dharma-sthāna (EI 24, 26, 32), a temple; a holy place;<BR>a place of religious worship. Cf. a mijigiti or mosque referred<BR>to as a dharma-sthāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144); see<BR>also dharmasthāna-goṣṭhika.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 279, note 52), land or money assigned<BR>for a religious purpose.<BR>(EI 23), the office of justice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मस्थानगोष्ठिक<BR>dharmasthāna-goṣṭhika (EI 33), member of a committee<BR>managing the affairs of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मस्थित<BR>Dharma-sthita (IE 8-2), ‘steadfast in religion’; epithet of<BR>a Kuṣāṇa king who may have been a convert to Buddhism.<BR>See Satyadharma-sthita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मवारियम्<BR>dharma-vāriyam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; committee look-<BR>ing after charitable endowments and institutions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मविजयशासन<BR>dharmavijaya-śāsana (EI 33), same as dharma-śāsana; a<BR>royal record relating to one of the king's meritorious acts;<BR>cf. vijaya-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मविजयिन्<BR>Dharma-vijayin (CII 4), a righteous conqueror; epithet of<BR>certain rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मवृत्तिइ<BR>dharma-vṛtti-iṟaiyili (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax-free land<BR>for the maintenance of some charity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मयात्रा<BR>dharma-yātrā, cf. dhaṃma-yātā (EI 5; CII 1), pilgrimage;<BR>a tour of pilgrimage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मयुवमहाराज<BR>Dharma-yuvamahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 24, 32), designation of<BR>a crown-prince engaged in a pious activity; cf. Dharma-<BR>mahārāja and Yuvamahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धार्मिक|धार्म्मिक|धार्म्मिकः<BR>dhārmika (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, a cess collected in<BR>the name of a religious institution or festival.<BR>(IE 8-2), royal title; same as Prakrit Dhramika,<BR>translated from Greek Dikaios.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मिन्|धर्म्मिन्<BR>Dharmin, cf. dharmikaḻ (SITI), a body or commission<BR>managing endowments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धार्तराष्ट्र|धार्तराष्ट्रः|धार्त्तराष्ट्र|धार्त्तराष्ट्रः<BR>Dhārtarāṣṭra (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धाटी<BR>dhāṭī (LP), campaign; cf. para-rāṣtṛ-opari datta-dhāṭyām,<BR>‘in the course of an expedition led against a foreign country’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धाटिवाह<BR>dhāṭivāha (Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 277, note 24), meaning<BR>doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धात्री<BR>dhātrī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातु|धातुः<BR>dhātu (ML), Buddhist; corporeal relics [of the Buddha].<BR>(IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR>Cf. Dhātu-parigṛhīta, an epithet of the Buddha; probably,<BR>salvation (Select Inscriptions, p. 228).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातुगर्भ|धातुगर्भः<BR>dhātu-garbha, ‘containing the corporeal relies of the<BR>Buddha’ (Journ. Mad. Univ., Vol. XXXII, p. 136).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातुवर<BR>dhātu-vara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 16, text line 13),<BR>a Buddhist stūpa containing the Buddha's relics.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातुवरपरिगृहीत<BR>Dhātuvara-parigṛhīta (EI 20), ‘one who has attained<BR>nirvāṇa’; epithet of the Buddha. Cf. dhātu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धौकणपत्र<BR>dhaukaṇa-patra (LP), permission of divorce; cf. Gujarātī<BR>chuṭāchedā meḻvavā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढौर<BR>ḍhaura (LP), cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धावक|धावकः<BR>Dhāvaka (EI 18), the fore-runner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धवलच्छत्र<BR>dhavala-cchatra (SII 2), a white parasol which was one<BR>of the royal insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धवलागार<BR>dhaval-āgāra, cf. dhavalāra (IA 14), ‘a mansion’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढेङ्कु<BR>ḍheṅku (EI 30), a machine for extracting juice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढेङ्कुकड्ढक<BR>ḍheṅku-kaḍḍhaka (IE 8-8), probably, one whose profession<BR>was to draw water from a well by means of a machinery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धी<BR>dhī (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढिंक<BR>ḍhiṃka (EI 13), a well.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धीर्मर<BR>dhīrmara (CII 4), probably, ‘a fish-basket’, according<BR>to some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धिष्णि<BR>dhiṣṇi (EI 5), a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धृति|धृतिः<BR>dhṛti (LP), consolation or encouragement.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘eighteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुव|ध्रुवं|ध्रुवः<BR>Dhruva (EI 16, 32; HD), [a collector of] the fixed royal<BR>share of grains; contraction of Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika; cf. the<BR>Gujarātī family name Dhruva; same as dhruva-sthāna. See Bomb.<BR>Gaz., Vol. I, Part i, p. 477.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR>(CII 1), regular.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवा<BR>dhruvā (CII 1), certainty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवाधिकरण<BR>Dhruv-ādhikaraṇa (EI 30), office of [the collector of] the<BR>king's share of the produce of the fields from the farmers. Cf.<BR>Dhruva, Dhruvapati, Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवाधिकरणिक<BR>Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika (IE 8-3; CII 3; HD; HRS), known<BR>from Maitraka records; according to some, the officer in charge<BR>of persons entrusted with the superintendence of the collection<BR>of the king's grain-share from the farmers; an official title of the<BR>Kathiawar region indicating an officer collecting the king's<BR>share of grains; sometimes called Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇika;<BR>the same as Dhruva or an employee of the dhruva-sthāna or<BR>Dhruva's office. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 339.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवपति<BR>Dhruvapati (EI 32), cf. Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवस्थान<BR>dhruva-sthāna (IE 8-3), a station for the collection of the<BR>king's fixed grain share; cf. Dhruva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवस्थानाधिकरण<BR>Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 30), the station for<BR>collecting the king's share or the office in its charge; cf.<BR>Dhruv-ādhikaraṇa and Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वज|ध्वजः<BR>dhvaja (CII 3), banner or standard as distinguished from<BR>lāñchana or crest. Cf. cihna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 135 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वजारोहण<BR>dhvaj-ārohaṇa (EI 31), a ceremony; cf. dhvaj-āvarohaṇa<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वजस्तम्भ<BR>dhvaja-stambha (CII 3, 4), a flag-staff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वजावरोहण<BR>dhvaj-āvarohaṇa (SITI), function at the conclusion of a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वंशी<BR>dhvaṃśī, same as vaṃśya; a theoretical unit of measure-<BR>ment (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दि<BR>di (IE 8-1; CII 3), abbreviation of dina, dine, divasa<BR>or divase; used in connection with śu or su and ba in the case<BR>of lunar months and by itself in the case of solar months.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिबिर<BR>Dibira, same as Divira (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिगम्बर|दिगंबर|दिगम्बरः<BR>Digambara (IA 7), a Jain sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिग्गज|दिग्गजः<BR>diggaja (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’. Eight poets patronised by<BR>Kṛṣṇadevarāya were called the aṣṭa-diggaja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिग्विजय|दिग्विजयः<BR>dig-vijaya, used in Kannaḍa inscriptions in the sense of<BR>‘going in state; going in a triumpal procession; making a state<BR>progress through one's dominions’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 223,<BR>note 5; Vol. VI, p. 51, note 5). See vijaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिकैओस्<BR>Dikaios (IE 8-2) Greek; royal title; ‘pious’; translated in<BR>Prakrit as Dhramika (Sanskrit Dhārmika).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीकोला<BR>dīkolā (LP), same as dāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिक्पाल|दिक्पालः<BR>Dikpāla (HD), probably, officers in charge of the borders<BR>of a kingdom. See Nārada, Jolly's ed., Pariśiṣṭa, verse 17;<BR>Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 271; Kātyāyana (v. 813)<BR>quoted by Aparārka. (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीक्षा<BR>dīkṣā (HA), initiation as a monk or recluse; initiation<BR>into any doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीक्षागुरु<BR>dīkṣā-guru (EI 32, 33), preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीक्षित|दीक्षितः<BR>Dīkṣita (EI 22; CII 3, 4), same as Yajña-dīkṣita; epithet<BR>of Brāhmaṇas; later stereotyped as a Brahmanical family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिन|दिनं|दिनः<BR>dina (CII 3), a day; used to denote the solar, or more<BR>properly civil, day. See also di and divasa.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘fifteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनार<BR>dināra (SITI), name of a coin; same as dīnāra; derived<BR>from the Roman coin name denarius; a cowrie-shell according<BR>to the Rājataraṅgiṇī (Stein's trans., Vol. II, pp. 308 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीनार|दीनारः<BR>dīnāra (IE 8-8; EI 9, 23, 30; CII 3; SITI), a gold coin,<BR>the name being derived from the Roman denarius; gold coin<BR>equal to 16 silver rūpakas in the Gupta age (JNSI, Vol. II,<BR>p. 5); sometimes called kāśu in Tamil records; sometimes<BR>regarded as half of a satera or sateraka (Greek stater); men-<BR>tioned as a silver coin (K. V. Rangaswami Aiyanger, Kṛtya-<BR>kalpataru, Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, p. 125); also spelt dīnnāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारि<BR>dināri (IE 8-8), name of a coin probably modified from<BR>the Roman denarius; cf. dīnāra and dināri-māṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारिमाषक<BR>dināri-māṣaka (IE 8-8), name of a coin; cf. dināri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपमाला<BR>dīpa-mālā, cf. tīpa-mālai (SITI), the string of lights hung<BR>in temples; same as śara-viḻakku.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपना<BR>dīpanā (CII 1), glorification.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपपूजा<BR>dīpa-pūjā (EI 9), dīpa and pūjā wrongly taken as a<BR>compound word of special significance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपस्कम्भ<BR>dīpa-skambha (LL), a lamp-post.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपावली<BR>dīpāvalī (EI 5; CII 4), name of a festival; the festival of<BR>lights; cf. dīp-otsava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपोत्सव|दीपोत्सवः<BR>dīp-otsava (EI 11, 32), same as dīpāvalī, the festival of<BR>lights.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिरमम्<BR>diramam (IE 8-8), Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घमान्य<BR>dīrgha-mānya (SITI), land set apart for the supply of water<BR>for the holy bath of idols.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घा<BR>dīrghā (CII 1), distance or the distant future.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घनासिक्यार्चा<BR>dīrghanāsiky-ārcā (EI 24), the image of a deity with long<BR>nose.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घिका<BR>dīrghikā (SITI), bath; a long or oval pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिश्<BR>diś, diśā (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’; rarely used to indicate<BR>‘four’ also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशा<BR>diśā (IA 7), precepts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशः|दिश<BR>diśaḥ (EI 2), the nymphs of the quarters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशाम्पति<BR>Diśāmpati (EI 29), a provincial governor. A Cakravartin<BR>was sometimes conceived as a Dig-vijayin or a Diśāmpati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशापट<BR>Diśāpaṭa (EI 16), Kannaḍa; ‘causing one's enemies to be<BR>scattered in all directions’; same as Diśāpaṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशापट्ट<BR>Diśāpaṭṭa (EI 5, 16), Kannaḍa; ‘causing one's enemies<BR>to be scattered in all directions’; same as Diśāpaṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिष्ट|दिष्टं|दिष्टः<BR>diṣṭa (IA 18), same as kāla, time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दित्य|दित्यः<BR>ditya (EI 9, 12, 28; CII 4; HRS), known from Maitraka<BR>records; name of a tax, according to some; probably, the<BR>same as datti, i. e. a gift or occasional present to be offered<BR>to the landlord; cf. sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna or<BR>°parihṛta (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 298, text line 20); also cf.<BR>sa-ditya-dāna-karaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 301, text line 14),<BR>an epithet of the gift land. Ditya is probably derived from<BR>Prakrit dijja = Sanskrit deya, ‘to be given’, ‘an object that has<BR>been given away’ in the sense of ‘customary presents’. For<BR>ditta, cf. Bhār. Vid., Vol. XVII, Nos. 3-4 pp. 125-26. See<BR>Dity-odgrāhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दित्योद्ग्राहक<BR>Dity-odgrāhaka (CII 4), probably, ‘an officer in charge<BR>of collecting customary presents’; cf. ditya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिव|दिवं<BR>diva (CII 3, etc.), abbreviation of divasa or divase; used<BR>to denote the solar or, more properly, civil day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिवा<BR>divā (CII 3), ‘by day’; an indeclinable used in some of the<BR>Nepal inscriptions in composition with words denoting tithis<BR>or lunar days.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिवाकर|दिवाकरः<BR>divākara (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीवान्<BR>Dīvān (BL), the chief administrator or finance minister;<BR>see Dīwān, Dīwānjī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिवस|दिवसः<BR>divasa (CII 3, etc.), a day; sometimes used for the week-<BR>day, instead of the usual term vāra; generally used to denote the<BR>solar or, more properly, civil day; sometimes used in connec-<BR>tion with words denoting tithis or lunar days. See also di, dina,<BR>diva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिविर<BR>Divira (HD), same as Persian Dabīr, ‘a clerk’. See<BR>Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 131, mentioning Divira as distinct from<BR>Kāyastha; also CII, Vol. III, p. 122. Cf. Divirapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिविरपति<BR>Divirapati, Divīrapati (IE 8-3; EI 5, 28; BL; HD),<BR>chief secretary or the chief of the clerks; cf. Divira. See Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XI, p. 180 (Sandhivigrahādhikṛta-Divirapati); Vol.<BR>XXII, p. 117 (Divirapati also called Sandhivigrahika, Mahā-<BR>pratīhāra and Sāmanta).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिव्य|दिव्यं|दिव्यः<BR>divya (IA 10; LP), an ordeal; same as parīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिव्यप्रबन्ध<BR>divya-prabandha, see prabandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीटान्<BR>Dīwān, Dīwānjī (BL), the chief administrator or finance<BR>minister. See Dīvān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोड्डि<BR>doḍḍi (EI 4), a yard.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डोहलिका<BR>ḍohalikā (EI 13), explained as ‘a piece of land granted to<BR>Brāhmaṇas, Svāmins, Sādhus and others’ (Prog. Rep. A. S. I.,<BR>W. C., 1908-09, p. 53); cf. dohalikā dattā. See dohalikā-bhūmi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डोहलिकाभूमि<BR>ḍohalikā-bhūmi (LP), explained as ‘land, of which the<BR>ownership is doubted and hence taken by government’; cf.<BR>Gujarātī ḍūlā, dulavuṃ, ḍohalavum; also lupta-ḍohalikā (LP),<BR>explained as ‘the ḍohalikā which is lost to the owner’. But<BR>see ḍohalikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोकारा<BR>dokārā (LP), an old man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोलयात्रा<BR>dola-yātrā (IA 9), the festival of the swinging of the image<BR>of Kṛṣṇa on Phālguna su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोण्<BR>doṇ (IE 8-6), Bengali form of droṇavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोङ्गक<BR>doṅgaka (EI 24), a variety of resin or aloe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोष|दोषः<BR>doṣa (LP), doing anything wrongly.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR>(EI 9), black or red spots on the tongue supposed to be a<BR>foreboding of death.<BR>Cf. daṇḍa-doṣa; fines; see also pradhān-āpradhāna-doṣa-<BR>samanvita used as an epithet of the gift village (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>III, p. 274). Here doṣa apparently means daṇda-doṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोस्य<BR>dosya (IE 8-8; EI 30), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोयरक<BR>doyaraka (EI 33), probably, ‘the singer who repeats part<BR>of a song after it has been once sung’; cf. Hindī dohrānā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्र<BR>dra (EI 33; LP), abbreviation of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रछ्म<BR>drachma (IE 8-8; CII 4), name of an old Greek coin;<BR>Indian dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रह्यितव्य<BR>drahyitavya (CII 1), ‘should be firm’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षण|द्रक्षणं<BR>drakṣaṇa, see draṃkṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षुण<BR>drakṣuṇa, see draṃkṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम<BR>drama (EI 23), same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रंक्षण|द्रङ्क्षण|द्रङ्क्षणं<BR>draṃkṣaṇa, same as tolaka (q. v.); a weight of 8 māṣas, also<BR>spelt drakṣaṇa, drakṣuṇa, etc.; cf. maṃkṣūṇa, equal to 7 māṣas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्म|द्रम्मं<BR>dramma (EI 25, 30; CII 4; SITI; BL), name of a coin;<BR>originally derived from Greek drachma.<BR>(IE 8-8), a silver coin, equal to one-sixteenth of a gold<BR>niṣka according to the Līlāvalī.<BR>Cf. pañciyaka-dramma (EI 30), Śrīmadādivarāha-dramma,<BR>Vigraha-dramma, Vigrahapāla-dramma, Vigrahapāla-satka-dramma,<BR>Vigrahapālīya-dramma, Vigrahatuṅgīya-dramma (IE 8-8; EI 1);<BR>Bhīmapriya-dramma (IE 8-8); poruttha-dramma (EI 23).--(IE 8-8),<BR>cf. gara-dramma, dāya-dramma, belliya-dramma (i. e. silver dramma),<BR>etc., of Kannaḍa inscriptions; the name dramma was also applied<BR>to the silver coin called purāṇa, dharaṇa or kārṣāpaṇa, though it<BR>was often used as the name of copper coins; money. For gold<BR>and ordinary (copper) dramma, cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 111.<BR>Cf. vāśal-tiramam (SITI), door tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मार्ध<BR>dramm-ārdha (CII 4), ‘half of a dramma’; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मत्रिभाग<BR>dramma-tribhāga (CII 4), ‘three-fourths of a dramma’;<BR>name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रङ्ग|द्रङ्गः<BR>draṅga (EI 32), used to indicate dramma; name of a coin.<BR>(EI 10), cf. Navagrāma-draṅga, ‘the draṅga of Nava-<BR>grāma’; possibly ‘a station for the collection of revenue’.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-101" target="_blank">Page-101+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 8-3), a town or watch-station; possibly also a station<BR>for the collection of revenue; also called udraṅga which may<BR>thus indicate both revenue and the station for its collection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रङ्गपाल<BR>Draṅgapāla (EI 28), same as Drāṅgika official design-<BR>ation. See draṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्राङ्गेश<BR>Drāṅgeśa (EI 20; HD), supposed to be the designation of<BR>a guardian of the frontiers (cf. Stein, Rājataraṅgiṇī, Vol. II,<BR>pp. 291-92 for draṅga or draṅgā); cf. Draṅgapāla and Drāṅgika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्राङ्गिक<BR>Drāṅgika (IE 8-3; EI 10, 30; CII 3, 4; HD), probably, an<BR>officer in charge of a city-station or watch-tower for collection<BR>of customs duties. Draṅga means either ‘a town’ (Bhandarkar's<BR>List, No. 810) or ‘a watch-station’ (Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 2010).<BR>Drāṅgika was an officer in charge of a draṅga probably mean-<BR>ing a watch station or a station for revenue collection; similar<BR>to Audraṇgika in the latter sense; mentioned along with the<BR>Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇa or ‘the collector of the king's grain-<BR>share’. Cf. draṅga, Draṅgapāla, etc. See CII, Vol. III, p. 169.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रव|द्रवः<BR>drava (EI 20), a kind of dancing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्राविडी<BR>Drāviḍī, name applied to the South Indian variety of the<BR>Brāhmī alphabet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रव्यभाण्डारकरण<BR>dravyabhāṇḍāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department<BR>of stores.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोण|द्रोणः<BR>droṇa (IE 8-6; Chamba), a grain measure; often regarded<BR>as equal to four āḍhakas; between one maund fourteen seers<BR>and two maunds, according to Bengali authors.<BR>(IE 8-1; EI 24, 29, 30), name of a land measure derived<BR>from that of a measure of capacity; shortened form of<BR>droṇavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणागीक<BR>Droṇāgīka (EI 33), official disignation; possibly a mistake<BR>for Droṇāgraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणाग्रक<BR>Droṇāgraka (EI 27), official disignation; probably an<BR>officer in charge of a droṇamukha or an important city, or one who<BR>collected the king's grain-share fixed per droṇa measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणमापक<BR>Droṇamāpaka, measurer of the king's grain-share<BR>(Ghoshal, Ag. Syst. Anc. Ind., pp. 26-27).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणवाप<BR>droṇavāpa (IE 8-6; EI 30), ‘an area of land requiring one<BR>droṇa measure of seed grains to be sown’; a land measure which<BR>was not the same in different ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणि|द्रोणिः<BR>droṇi, droṇī (CH 4; IA 11), treasury; property (cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144--‘the droṇī of Śrī-Somanāthadeva’ to<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-102" target="_blank">Page-102+ 40</a>]<BR>which a piece of land was attached); see devadroṇī probably<BR>meaning ‘rent-free property of a temple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणीकर<BR>droṇī-kara, cf. Tamil toni-kkaḍamai (SITI), tax on boats.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृश्<BR>dṛś, cf. peṭaṃ (Sanskrit udaraṃ) darśayitum (EI 11), lite-<BR>rally, ‘to show one's belley’; but actually ‘to ask for the means<BR>of livelihood’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृशिधारिका<BR>Dṛśidhārikā (EI 32), a female torch-bearer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृष्ट|दृष्टं<BR>dṛṣṭa (EI 3, 23; CII 3; etc.), Prakrit diṭṭham, ‘has been seen’,<BR>i. e. ‘found correct and approved’, found on some copper-<BR>plate grants indicating the approval of the proper authorities<BR>endorsed on the original document later engraved on the plates.<BR>Cf. ni (an abbreviation of nibaddha or nirīkṣiṭa) in certain<BR>medieval copper-plate grants of Eastern India. In dṛṣṭa-<BR>pañcāśat-padāti (LP), dṛṣṭa-ghoṭaka (LP), etc., the word dṛṣṭa<BR>indicates that money should be paid after actually seeing the<BR>foot-soldiers and horses in question.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृष्टादृष्ट<BR>dṛṣṭ-ādṛṣṭa (IA 20), dimly seen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृष्टि|दृष्टिः<BR>dṛṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra; also darśana, ‘six’.<BR>(IA 19), Buddhist; theory or doctrine; a peculiar or<BR>heretical doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दू<BR>Dū (IE 8-1; LP), abbreviation of Dūtaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुग्ध|दुग्धः<BR>dugdha, cf. a-dugdha-dadhi-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); milk which<BR>the villagers (probably, the milkmen) were obliged to supply<BR>to the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःखन<BR>duḥkhana (CII 1), causing pain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाधसाधनिक<BR>Duḥsādha-sādhanika (IE 8-3; HD), the leader of police-<BR>men engaged in apprehending robbers, etc., or of expeditionary<BR>forces requisitioned on occasions of emergency; cf. Sādhanika,<BR>Duṣṭa-sādhaka, Dauḥsādhanika, Dussādhya-sādhaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाध्य|दुःसाध्यः<BR>Duḥsādhya (EI 2), abbreviation of Duḥsādhya-sādhanika,<BR>etc., or a criminal; cf. dussādhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाध्यादाय<BR>duḥsādhy-ādāya (EI 21), a tax probably levied from habitu-<BR>ally criminal people or for the maintenance of certain police<BR>or military officers called Duḥsādhya, etc. See duṣṭasādhy-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाध्यसाधनिक<BR>Duḥsādhya-sādhanika (IE 8-3), same as Dauhsādha-sādhanika,<BR>etc. Cf. Dussādhya-sādhaka, Duṣṭa-sāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःशम्य<BR>duḥśamya (ML), unpreventable.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डुलित<BR>ḍulita (LP), ‘[land, etc.,] that has become ḍohalikā (q. v.)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुम्फक<BR>dumphaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably the same as Sanskrit<BR>dṛmphaka, ‘one who presses’; see nīla-ḍumphaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुन्दुभि|दुंदुभि|दुंदुभिः|दुन्दुभिः<BR>dundubhi (ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्ग|दुर्गं|दुर्गः<BR>durga (ASLV), a fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गदण्डनायक<BR>Durga-daṇḍanāyaka (ASLV), the ruler of a fort; cf.<BR>Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गपाल<BR>Durgapāla (HD), superintendent of a fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गपति<BR>Durgapati (EI 27), governor of a fortress.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गापुत्र<BR>Durgā-putra (EI 33), epithet of one devoted to the goddess<BR>Durgā; used along with such similar epithets as Rudra-putra<BR>and Puruṣottama-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुरित|दुरितं<BR>durita (SITI), famine; disturbance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्लभ|दुर्लभः|दुर्ल्लभ<BR>Durlabha (EI 23), an official designation of uncertain<BR>import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्वाछक<BR>dur-vāchaka, cf. tur-vāyakam (SITI), abusive language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्कृत|दुष्कृतं<BR>duṣkṛta (CII 1), a bad deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुस्साध्य<BR>dussādhya (CII 4), ‘a criminal’; abbreviation of Duḥsādhya-<BR>sādhaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुस्साध्यसाधनिक<BR>Dussādhya-sādhanika, same as Duṣṭa-sāhaṇi (EI 33), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाधक<BR>Duṣṭa-sādhaka (EI 7; CII 4; HD), official designation;<BR>‘the mentor of criminals’; same as Duḥsādhya-sādhanika, Dauḥsā-<BR>dhanika, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाध्य<BR>Duṣṭa-sādhya (EI 21; CII 4), same as dus-sādhya or a<BR>criminal; abbreviation of the official designation Duṣṭa-sādhya-<BR>sādhanika; same as Duṣṭa-sādhaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाध्यादाय<BR>duṣṭasādhy-ādāya, probably, a tax levied for maintaining<BR>the police engaged in suppressing dacoits. Cf. Ghoshal, H.<BR>Rev. Syst., p. 254, note. See duḥsādhy-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाध्यसाधनिक<BR>Duṣṭasādhya-sādhanika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 132),<BR>same as Duṣṭa-sādhaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाहणि<BR>Duṣṭa-sāhaṇi (EI 33), same as Duṣṭa-sādhaka, Duṣṭasā-<BR>dhya-sādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूष्य|दूष्यं|दूष्यः<BR>dūṣya (CII 1), robe or clothes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूत|दूतः<BR>Dūta (IE 8-3; EI 23, 30; CII 1; HD), a messenger or<BR>envoy. See Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 13-14, 28; CII, Vol. I,<BR>p. 67.<BR>(EI 23; CII 3, 4), an occasional substitute for Dūtaka,<BR>the executor of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूतक|दूतकः<BR>Dūtaka (IE 8-3; HD), messenger; conveyor of a request<BR>or message; cf. the Khalimpur plate of Dharmapāla (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. IV, p. 250), according to which the king was reques-<BR>ted to make a grant by a Mahāsāmantādhipati through prince<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-104" target="_blank">Page-104+ 40</a>]<BR>Tribhuvanapāla as the Dūtaka. His function is called dūtya<BR>in the Nalanda plate of Devapāla (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII,<BR>318 ff., text line 51).<BR>(IE 8-3; EI 23, 30; CII 3, 4), according to some, the<BR>technical title of an officer connected with royal charters,<BR>whose duty it was to carry the king's orders to the local officials<BR>by whom the charter was then drawn up and delivered. But<BR>the Dūtaka seems to have been responsible for putting the<BR>document and also perhaps the gift land in the donee's possession.<BR>There are instances of more Dūtakas than one (IA 19). See<BR>also Ājñā, Dūta, and sva-mukh-ājñā. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 143-44.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूतप्रैषणिक<BR>Dūta-praiṣaṇika (HD), officer in charge of sending<BR>envoys; same as Dūta-preṣaṇika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p.<BR>321; Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306. Cf. Preṣaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूतप्रेषणिक<BR>Dūta-preṣaṇika (CII 4), also called Duta-saṃpreṣaṇika<BR>and Dūta-praiṣaṇika; the officer who despatched Dūtas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूत्य|दूत्यं<BR>dūtya, same as dautya; function of the Dūtaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूयक<BR>Dūyaka (LP), Sanskrit Dūtaka; a messenger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वादशभाग<BR>dvādaśa-bhāga (Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 203); name of an<BR>additional levy which was (1/12) of the fixed tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वादशक<BR>dvādaśaka (SII 13), partnership in a land; cf. aṣṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वादशस्थानाधिपति<BR>Dvādaśasthān-ādhipati, the head of twelve departments<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वन्द्व|द्वंद्व|द्वंद्वं|द्वन्द्वं|द्वन्द्वः<BR>dvandva (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वार|द्वारं<BR>dvāra (CII 1), a way or means.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR>(EI 4), the mouth of a river.<BR>(IE 8-3), cf. ‘the lord of the dvāra’ which was the desig-<BR>nation of a commander of forces in Kashmir; possibly, a pass<BR>[leading into the Kashmir valley].<BR>Cf. Tamil vāśal-paṇam, ‘door-tax’; periodical payment<BR>due to the palace. Cf. dvār-ādeya.<BR>Cf. dvāra-koṣṭḥaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारादेय<BR>dvār-ādeya (HRS), ‘gate-dues’; explained as a surcharge<BR>over and above the tolls on goods imported into a city. See<BR>Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 60, note. But cf. Tamil vāśal-paṇam<BR>explained as ‘door-tax’, i. e. the periodical payment due to<BR>the palace.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वाराधिप|द्वाराधिपः<BR>Dvār-ādhipa (IE 8-3; HD), same as Dvāranātha, Dvāra-<BR>pati, etc.; ‘the lord of the pass’; cf. dvāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारकोष्ठक<BR>dvāra-koṣṭhaka (Lüders, Mathurā Inscriptions, p. 135, text<BR>line 4), translated as ‘gateway’; gate-chamber.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारमण्डप<BR>dvāra-maṇḍapa (HA), a hall or pavilion on the entrance<BR>or door of a shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारनाथ<BR>Dvāranātha (IE 8-3; HD), superintendent of the passes<BR>leading into the kingdom, according to Stein (Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>V. 214); same as Dvār-ādhipa, Dvārapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारपाल|द्वारपालः<BR>Dvārapāla (EI 22), a door-keeper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारपरीक्षा<BR>Dvāra-parīkṣā (IE 8-3; EI 28), Oḏiyā; Sanskrit Dvāra-<BR>parīkṣaka; same as Pratīhāra. Cf. Parīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारपति<BR>Dvārapati (IE 8-3; HD), ‘lord of the gate’; a commander<BR>of forces under the Kampanāpati [in Kashmir]; the guardian of<BR>a pass [leading into the Kashmir valley]; same as Dvāranātha,<BR>Dvār-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारोष्ठ<BR>dvāroṣṭha (EI 1), meaning doubtful; probably a mistake<BR>for dvāra-koṣṭha, a gate-chamber.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वय|द्वयं<BR>dvaya (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वेद<BR>Dveda (EI 24, 29), contracted form of Dviveda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वेस<BR>dvesa (CII 3), an epithet applied to land; a term of un-<BR>certain significance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वि|द्विः<BR>Dvi (EI 11), abbreviation of Dviveda.<BR>(IE 8-1), abbreviation of dvitīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वीभूमिक<BR>dvī-bhūmika (LP), two-storied.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विगर्भ<BR>dvi-garbha (LL), a two-celled building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विजातिदाय<BR>dvijāti-dāya (EI 22), same as brahma-dāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विका<BR>dvikā, double measure (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 52,<BR>note 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विप|द्विपः<BR>dvipa (EI (7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वीप|द्वीपं|द्वीपः<BR>dvīpa (IE 7-12), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विवल्लक्य<BR>dvi-vallakya (LP), [coins] in which there is a mixture of<BR>two vāls (6 ratis) of a base metal. Cf. JNSI, Vol. XXII,<BR>p. 197.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विवेद<BR>Dviveda (CII 4), also called Dvivedin; epithet of Brāhma-<BR>ṇas; later stereotyped as a Brahmanical family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्व्यर्ध<BR>dvyardha (CII 1), one and a half.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्यु|द्युः<BR>dyu (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्युमणि|द्युमणिः<BR>dyu-maṇi (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्यूत|द्यूतं|द्यूतः<BR>dyūta (HRS), gambling; the king's dues collected by the<BR>superintendent of gambling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्यूतसभापति<BR>Dyūtasabhāpati (BL), superintendent of the gambling hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडूक|एडूकं|एडूकः<BR>eḍūka, cf. eḍuo (CII 2-1), supposed to be ‘a wall into which<BR>bones (meaning planks and other hard substances) have been<BR>inserted in order to strengthen the structure’, because it is<BR>explained in a commentary as asthy-aṅkita kuḍya; but asthy-<BR>aṅkita-kuḍya seems to mean a Buddhist stūpa raised on cor-<BR>poreal relics which were an object of worship. Although<BR>the word kuḍya is reckoned in the lexicons in the sense of a wall,<BR>it seems to mean ‘a mound’ in this case. The word aidūka<BR>derived from eḍūka is used in Buddhist Sanskrit in the<BR>sense of a Buddhist stūpa. See IHQ, Vol. XXIX, pp.<BR>302-03.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकभोग<BR>eka-bhoga (EI 16; SITI; ASLV), a tenure indicating<BR>exclusive ownership of a property invested in a single indivi-<BR>dual; sole possession and enjoyment of a village by a single<BR>person (without any joint owner); cf. ekabhoga-iṟaiyili, tax-free<BR>land or village in the sole enjoyment of a single owner. Same<BR>as eka-bhogya. Cf. gaṇa-bhoga.<BR>(SITI), single crop; same as Tamil oru-pū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकभोग्य<BR>eka-bhogya (EI 13, 14), a tenure; same as eka-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकदा<BR>ekadā (CII 1), sometimes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशप्रसूति<BR>ekādaśa-prasūti (LP), probably, eleven births.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशरुद्रभिक्षा<BR>ekādaśa-Rudra-bhikṣā (EI 32), arrangement of free supply<BR>of food to Śaiva ascetics in the name of the eleven Rudras;<BR>land granted for such an arrangement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशशत<BR>ekādaśa-śata (ML), same as ekādaś-ottara-śata, one hundred<BR>and eleven.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशीव्रत<BR>ekādaśī-vrata (EI 31; CII 4), name of a vrata rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकधन|एकधनः<BR>eka-dhana (LP), joint family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकलमूर्ति<BR>ekala-mūrti (HA), a single Jina image without any orna-<BR>mental parikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकमुष्टि<BR>eka-muṣṭi, cf. eka-muṣṭyā (LP), ‘collectively’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकाङ्ग|एकांग|एकाङ्गं|एकाङ्गः<BR>Ekāṅga (HD), probably, an officer belonging to a body<BR>organized in military fashion for collecting revenue or per-<BR>forming police duties. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 249; VII. 1604.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकाङ्गिन्<BR>Ekāṅgin (SITI), a single person; one who has no family,<BR>especially the Vaiṣṇava devotee in charge of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकपात्र<BR>Ekapātra (EI 27), probably, Yāvadeka-pātra (q. v.); official<BR>designation; cf. Pātra and Mahāpātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकशाट<BR>Eka-śāṭa (EI 29), same as Eka-cīvara; epithet of a monk<BR>who has taken a vow to wear only one piece of cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकतीर्थी<BR>eka-tīrthī (HA), a sculpture showing only one Jina<BR>(Tīrthaṅkara) together with his parikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकत्य<BR>ekatya (CII 1), ‘of one kind’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकावली<BR>ekāvalī, ekāvallī (SITI), necklace of a single string.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरदुबिल्कोदे<BR>eradu-bilkode (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एर्झुन<BR>Erjhuna (ML), a title of foreign origin; ‘a prince’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एतत्क<BR>etatka cf. etaka (CII 1); same as etat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एवंपरिणा<BR>evaṃpariṇā (LP), ‘in this way’; cf. Gujarātī evī-pere.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअनम्<BR>fanam, English spelling of Tamil paṇam; see paṇa. It was<BR>sometimes regarded as a gold coin equal to (1/10) of a partāb<BR>and (1/20) of a varāha (SII, Vol. I, p. 161).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअर्मान्<BR>farmān, also spelt firmān; Persian; cf. phuramāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋईल्<BR>fīl, Arabic-Persian; cf. pīlu, Pīlupati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋइर्मान्<BR>firmān, cf. farmān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग|गं|गः<BR>ga (IE 8-1), used for gā (in Kharoṣṭhī) as an abbrevia-<BR>tion of gāthā; also abbreviation of gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गभारो<BR>gabhāro (HA), Sanskrit garbha-gṛha; the sanctum of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गच्छ|गच्छः<BR>gaccha (IA 11; BL), name of particular communities of<BR>Jain monks; cf. the eightyfour gacchas of the Jains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्दी<BR>gaddī (EI 8), a throne; cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधैया<BR>gadhaiyā, also called gadhaiyā paisā; same as gadhiyā;<BR>a copper coin modified from old Sasanian types.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधिया<BR>gadhiyā, same as gadhaīyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदिआणक<BR>gadiāṇaka, cf. Kumāra-gadiāṇaka (EI 8); same as<BR>gadyāṇaka.<BR>(EI 27), also called gadyāṇa; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदियाण<BR>gadiyāṇa (EI 27; CII 4), same as gadyāṇa, gadyāṇaka;<BR>name of a coin called suvarṇa-gadiyāṇa, ‘gold gadiyāṇa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्या<BR>gadyā, abbreviation of gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यान<BR>gadyāna (EI 3), a gold coin or weight; also spelt gadyāṇa.<BR>generally regarded as 48 ratis in weight (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याण<BR>gadyāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 27, 30), also called gadyāṇaka, often<BR>contracted as ga or gadyā; sometimes called pon-gadyāṇa or<BR>gadyāṇa-ponnu indicating that it was a gold coin; sometimes<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-108" target="_blank">Page-108+ 40</a>]<BR>called suvarṇa; cf. bhairava-gadyāṇa, lokki-gadyāṇa (SII 11-2),<BR>aṅka-gadyāṇa, gāva-gadyāṇa, komarina-gadyāṇa, priyaśrāha-gaja-<BR>malla-gadyāṇa, ambili-gadyāṇa, jagadalaṃ-gadyāṇa, etc. Cf. also<BR>aṟu-gadyāṇa (IA 12) and kula-gadyāṇa (EI 17), names of coins.<BR>Cf. parameṣṭhi-gadyāṇa-ponna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 61).<BR>(SITI), name of a coin, probably equal to a varāha or<BR>pagoda; cf. bṛhad-bhairava-gadyāṇa (EI 30); also kaṭhāri-<BR>aṅkuśa-gadyāṇa (EI 8), name of a coin with the representation<BR>of a dagger and a goad; varāha-gadyāṇa (EI 8), name of the<BR>gold coin called both varāha and gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याण<BR>gadyāṇa (CITD), same as gadyāṇa; a coin like a farthing<BR>equal to (1/4) or (1/5) of the paikamu; also a dināra or varāha;<BR>a weight used in weighing silver; equal in some places to 20<BR>vals, 8 māṣas, or half a tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यानक|गद्यानकं|गद्यानकः<BR>gadyānaka (EI 28), gadyāṇaka (IE 8-8; EI 27), same<BR>as gadyāna or gadyāṇa; name of a coin; a coin weighing 48 ratis<BR>according to the Lilāvatī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गगन|गगनं<BR>gagana (IE 7-1-2; EI 52), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गाह्ण<BR>gāhṇa (Chamba), threshing floor; from Sanskrit gāhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गैराट<BR>gairāṭa, cf. gelāṭa (CII 1); probably, a hill bird.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गज|गजः<BR>gaja (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजधर<BR>Gajadhara (EI 4), same as Sūtradhara or Sūtradhāra, ‘mason’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजाधीश<BR>Gajādhīśa (CII 4), ‘the lord of elephants’; official designa-<BR>tion; title of certain rulers. Cf. Gajapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजलक्ष्मी<BR>Gajalakṣmī (EI 32), representation of Lakṣmī receiving<BR>water on the head from a jar held in the trunk of an elephant<BR>on either side; found on the seals of certain rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजमाल<BR>gajamāla (HA), row of elephants in the plinth of shrines;<BR>also called gajathara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजमृगयाविहार<BR>Gaja-mṛgayā-vihāra (ASLV), ‘sportful hunting of ele-<BR>phants’; a title of the Vijayanagara kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजपति|गजपतिः<BR>Gajapati (IE 8-2; EI 9, 30; CII 4; HD), ‘the lord of<BR>elephants’; officer in charge of the elephant arm in an army;<BR>title of certain rulers; dynastic name of the Sūryavaṃśīs of<BR>Orissa. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 7. See Mahāgajapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजसाहणी<BR>Gaja-sāhaṇī (EI 32), a leader of the elephant force; same<BR>as Gaja-sāhiṇi, Gaja-sādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजसाहिणि<BR>Gaja-sāhiṇi (IE 8-3; EI 27), same as Gaja-sāhaṇi, Gaja-<BR>sādhanika; leader of the elephant corps; cf. Sāhiṇi or Sāhaṇī,<BR>derived from Sādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजथर<BR>gajathara (HA), same as gajamāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजवाहराउत<BR>Gajavāha-rāuta (EI 31), title of a subordinate chief.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गल्पुट्टि<BR>gal-puṭṭi (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of land;<BR>a variation of puṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गाण्ठि<BR>gāṇṭhi (LP), a package; cf. Gujarātī gāṇṭhḏī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गमागमिक<BR>Gamāgamika (IE 8-3; EI 4, 23; CII 4; HD), same as<BR>Gamāgamin; official designation; probably, an officer in charge<BR>of regulating the people's entrance and departure into cities;<BR>explained by some as ‘a kind of messenger’ (Ind. Ant., Vol.<BR>XV, p. 306). Utpala on the Bṛhatsaṃhitā, 85. 34, explains<BR>Dūta as Gamāgamika, though some Pāla inscriptions have dūta-<BR>khola-gamāgamik-ābhitvaramāṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, pp. 250,<BR>text line 45).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गमागमिन्<BR>Gamāgamin (EI 31), same as Gamāgamika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गम्पण<BR>gampaṇa (EI 27), same as kampaṇa; an administrative and<BR>territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गामुण्ड<BR>Gāmuṇḍa (EI 15), Kannaḍa; same as Gāvuṇḍa; a village<BR>headman; probably derived from Grāmakūṭa, ‘headman of a<BR>village’, through Gāmaūḍa>Gāmuḍa under the influence of<BR>muṇḍa, ‘head’. Cf. Nāḍa-gāmuṇḍa Nāṟ-gāmuṇḍa, ‘headman of<BR>a district (nāḍu)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण|गणः<BR>gaṇa (LL), a section of the Jains.<BR>(SITI), a group of persons; a community or religious guild.<BR>(EI 26; CII 4), a guild or corporation.<BR>(EI 3), wrongly explained as a share.<BR>(SII 12), managing committee.<BR>(SII 2), the attendants of Śiva; also the fourteen divi-<BR>sions of learning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभोग<BR>gaṇa-bhoga (SITI, ASLV), a tenure in which land is held<BR>in common by a group of persons; joint ownership of a village<BR>or villages by a number of persons; same as gaṇa-bhogya, gaṇa-<BR>bhojya. Cf. eka-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभोग्य<BR>gaṇa-bhogya (EI 13, 15), see gaṇa-bhoga or gaṇa-bhojya.<BR>Cf. eka-bhoga or eka-bhojya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभोज्य<BR>gaṇa-bhojya (EI 16), same as gaṇa-bhoga or gaṇa-bhogya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभृत्<BR>Gaṇabhṛt (EI 3; SII I), the head of a [Jain] school;<BR>same as Gaṇin, Gaṇa-dhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणाचार्य<BR>Gaṇ-ācārya (LL), the teacher of a Buddhist community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणदण्ड<BR>Gaṇadaṇḍa (EI 30), epithet of a hero; probably, an abbre-<BR>viation of Gaṇa-daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणदण्डनायक<BR>Gaṇa-daṇḍanāyaka, also called Gaṇa-daṇdapāla (EI 18);<BR>official designation; probably, a Daṇdanāyaka serving under a<BR>gaṇa or corporation or commanding several gaṇas or contingents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणदण्डपाल<BR>Gaṇa-daṇḍapāla, same as Gaṇa-daṇdanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणधर|गणधरः<BR>Gaṇadhara (HA), chief disciple of a Jina.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणक|गणकः<BR>Gaṇaka (EI 18), official designation; cf. Tamil kaṇakaṉ<BR>(SITI), a village accountant; also vāśal-kaṇakkaṉ (SITI),<BR>accountant at the vāśal (palace or palace-gate); ūrkkaṇakkar-<BR>jīvitam (SITI), land assigned in lieu of salary to the village<BR>accountant or perquisites of the office of the village accountant<BR>(i. e. the Paṭvārī as he is called in many parts of India).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणना<BR>gaṇanā (EI 20), accountancy.<BR>(CII 1), ‘taking into account’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणपक<BR>Gaṇapaka (CII 4), official designation; probably the same<BR>as Sanskrit Gaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणपण<BR>gaṇa-paṇa (EI 20), communal and professional guilds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणप्पेरुमक्कल्<BR>Gaṇa-pperumakkaḻ (SII 12; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; the<BR>elders of a gaṇa managing its affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणश्रेष्ठ<BR>Gaṇa-śreṣṭha (CII 3), probably, the head of a corporation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणस्थ<BR>Gaṇastha (EI 15), probably, the member of a corporation;<BR>same as Tamil Gaṇattār; see Mahāgaṇastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणस्थिति<BR>gaṇa-sthiti (IA 19), cf. Mālavānāṃ gaṇa-sthityā, Mālava-<BR>gaṇa-sthiti-vaśāt, explained as ‘by, or according to, the rec-<BR>koning of the Mālavas’, gaṇa being taken to mean gaṇanā. But<BR>see sthiti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणत्तार्<BR>Gaṇattār (SITI), Tamil; Sanskrit Gaṇastha; people be-<BR>longing to a gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणवारियम्<BR>gaṇa-vāriyam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; committee mana-<BR>ging the affairs of a gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणवारियप्पेरुमक्कल्<BR>Gaṇa-vāriya-pperumakkaḻ (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; elders<BR>of the committee called gaṇa-vāriyam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्ड|गंड|गंडः|गण्डः<BR>Gaṇḍa (EI 12), cf. Tamil Gaṇḍaṉ; a hero, probably from<BR>the meaning ‘rhinoceros’; cf. similar use of vyāghra, siṃha, etc.;<BR>also cf. Paragaṇḍabhairava (EI 29). See Gaṇdaṉ and Gaṇda-<BR>peṇḍāra; also Calamartigaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डा<BR>gaṇḍā (IE 8-6; EI 19; IA 27), in the monetary system<BR>of some areas of medieval and modern India, regarded as<BR>equal to four cowrie-shells and (1/20) of a paṇa; also a small area<BR>of land, twenty of which make one kānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डभेरुण्ड<BR>gaṇḍabheruṇḍa (EI 3), a mythical double-headed eagle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डगोपाल<BR>Gaṇḍagopāla (EI 30), title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डक|गंडक|गंडकः|गण्डकः<BR>gaṇḍaka (EI 21), name of a coin; cf. gaṇdā.<BR>(EI 27), an official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डकानायक<BR>Gaṇḍakānāyaka (EI 33), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डमाड<BR>gaṇḍa-māḍa (EI 5), name of a coin; sometimes specified<BR>as ‘small’; also called kārṣāpaṇa, niṣka or gaṇḍa-niṣka; cf.<BR>māḍa. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 43.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्ड|गंड|गंडः|गण्डः<BR>Gaṇḍaṉ (SITI), Tamil; a warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोण्डपेण्डार<BR>goṇḍa-peṇḍāra (ASLV), Tamil; ‘the anklet of a hero’<BR>which was worn by men of distinction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डशैल|गंडशैल|गण्डशैलः<BR>gaṇḍa-śaila (EI 12), a boulder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्धकुटी|गंधकुटी<BR>gandhakuṭī (EIA9, 18; IA 14), originally, ‘a chamber for<BR>the Buddha's use’; later ‘the chamber enshrining the Buddha<BR>image in a monastery’; a shrine where the image of the Buddha<BR>is worshipped; a Buddhist temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गान्धर्व|गांधर्व|गान्धर्व्वं|गान्धर्व्वः<BR>gāndharva (EI 28), dance and music.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्धशालि|गन्धशालिः<BR>gandha-śāli (EI 5), a kind of rice or paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गान्धिक|गांधिक|गांधिकः|गान्धिकः<BR>Gāndhika (EI 28; LL), a perfumer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणेशचतुर्थी<BR>Gaṇeśa-caturthī (EI 5; IA 17; CII 4), name of a tithi and<BR>festival; same as Bhādrapada su-di 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गनेशहोम<BR>Ganeśa-homa (EI 26), a rite; same as Vināyaka-homa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गैकोण्ड<BR>Gaṅgaikoṇḍa (IE 8-2), title of a Col13a king meaning ‘the<BR>conqueror of the Gaṅgā’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गामार्ग<BR>gaṅgā-mārga (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गापुपुटक<BR>gaṅgāpupuṭaka (IA 18; CII 1), probably gaṅgā-puppuṭaka;<BR>a particular fish of the Ganges.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गायमुना<BR>Gaṅgā-yamunā (EI 24, 29), royal insignia probably con-<BR>sisting of the representation of the Gaṅgā and Yamunā on the<BR>flags or at the gate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गाङ्गेय|गांगेय|गाङ्गेयं|गाङ्गेयः<BR>gāṅgeya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 38), gold.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गास्नान<BR>Gaṅgā-snāna (LP), ‘absence of sin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गिनिका<BR>gaṅginikā (EI 18), a stream.<BR>(EI 12), a dried up river bed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गानी<BR>gānī, cf. aṭha-gānī, a coin equal to a ṭaṅka (JNSI, Vol.<BR>XII, p. 198); cf. jītal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणिका<BR>gaṇikā (EI 33), same as devadāsī.<BR>(EI 7), a female elephant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणिकाकरण<BR>gaṇikā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the amuse-<BR>ment department.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणिन्<BR>Gaṇin (SII 2), an astrologer.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-112" target="_blank">Page-112+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 3), head of a school.<BR>(IA 19; LL), Jain; a Jain ecclesiastic; an ācārya who has<BR>disciples but has not risen to be the head of his gaccha or śākhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्ज|गंज|गंजः|गञ्जः<BR>gañja (EI 30), Persian ganj; a treasury or store-house.<BR>Utpala on the Bṛhatsaṃhitā, 52. 13, explains gañja as kośa-bhavana,<BR>i. e. treasury. See Gañjavara.<BR>(IE 8-8), a store-house of liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्जाधिकारिन्<BR>Gañj-ādhikārin (HRS), a treasury-officer according<BR>to the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See Gañjapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्जपति<BR>Gañjapati (EI 13; HRS; HD), same as Persian Ganjwar,<BR>treasurer (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 115). See gañja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्जवर|गञ्जवरः<BR>Gañjavara (IE 8-3; EI 9; HD), Persian Ganjwar; a treasurer<BR>or store-keeper (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 247; Rājataraṅgiṇī, V.<BR>177). See Gañjapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्ज्टर्<BR>Ganjwar, Persian; see Gañjavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भ|गर्भः<BR>garbha (LL), a cell; cf. pañca-garbha (LL), ‘a five-celled<BR>building’; nava-garbha (LL), ‘a nine-celled building’; sapta-<BR>garbha (LL), ‘seven-celled building’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भद्वार<BR>garbha-dvāra (LL), the hall-front.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भागार|गर्भागारं<BR>garbh-āgāra (CII 1), the inner apartment of a temple or<BR>palace; same as garbha-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भगृह<BR>garbha-gṛha (SITI), the innermost sanctuary of a temple;<BR>inner part of palace; same as garbh-āgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्चा<BR>garcā (Chamba), same as gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्गयवन<BR>Garga-yavana (EI 33), name applied to the Turkish Muslim<BR>invaders of North India, Garga probably being Ghaznī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्जनकाधिराज<BR>Garjanak-ādhirāja, Garjanik-ādhirāja (LP), ‘the emperor<BR>of Ghaznī’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्त|गर्तं|गर्तः|गर्त्त|गर्त्तः<BR>garta, gartā (EI 3, 27; CII 3), a trench or pit; a boundary<BR>trench; a pit or valley; cf. sa-gart-oṣara (IE 8-5); also found<BR>as the termination of names of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गरुड|गरुडः<BR>garuḍa (IA 20), the royal eagle; the white kite (in areas<BR>like Bihar and Madras).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गरुडध्वज|गरुडध्वजः<BR>Garuḍadhvaja (CII 4), title of a ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गतराज्य<BR>gata-rājya, same as vinaṣṭa-rājya or atīta-rājya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गति|गतिः<BR>gati (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘four’; also explained as five in<BR>number (EI 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गात्र|गात्रं<BR>gātra (IA 14), same as aṅga-bhoga.<BR>(EI 33), same as gotra or gotra-śailikā, i.e. a memorial<BR>pillar for the dead members of one's family. See yaṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गात्री<BR>gātrī (LP), cf. Gujarātī gāḏa, a cart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौद<BR>Gauda (EI 5; ASLV), Kannaḍa; same as Gāvuṇḍa; a<BR>village headman; the chief farmer of a village. See Gavuḍa.<BR>(EI 1), a temple priest.<BR>(IE 8-5; EI 28), Oḏiyā; same as gokuṭa; a cowherd or<BR>milkman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौडमहासान्धिविग्रहिक<BR>Gauḍa-mahāsāndhivigrahika (IE 8-3), ‘the Mahāsāndhivi-<BR>grahika of the Gauḍa country’; cf. Mahāsāndhivigrahika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौडी<BR>Gauḍī, name applied to the East Indian alphabet, langu-<BR>age and style of composition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौडिक|गौडिकं<BR>Gauḍika (EI 28), maker and seller cf sugar; see Guḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौग्गुलिक<BR>Gauggulika (EI 13), a dealer in guggulu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौल्मिक|गौल्मिकः<BR>Gaulmika (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HD), same as Gulma-<BR>pati (q. v.); ‘chief of a troop’; officer in charge of a gulma or<BR>outpost or group of guards, soldiers or policemen; ‘superin-<BR>tendent of woods and forests’ according to Fleet (CII, Vol.<BR>III, p. 50). See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 246.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौरी<BR>gaurī, a virgin; cf. gaurī-varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौरीपट्ट|गौरीपट्टः<BR>gaurī-paṭṭa, same as the yoni-paṭṭa of a Śiva-liṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौरीवराटिका<BR>gaurī-varāṭikā, ‘virgin-money’. Gaurī means ‘a virgin’<BR>and varāṭikā is used primarily in the sense of varāṭa or varāṭaka,<BR>‘a cowrie-shell’, and secondarily in that of ‘money’. In the<BR>records of Mithilā, gaurī-varāṭikā means ‘money to be paid<BR>to the master of a slave girl of marriageable age by the master<BR>of her bridegroom’. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 264 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौतमीपुत्र<BR>Gautamī-putra (IE 2-8), metronymic meaning ‘the son of<BR>a lady born in a family belonging to the Gautama gotra’. Such<BR>metronymics refer to the absence of gotr-āntara (i. e. the change<BR>of the bride's paternal gotra to that of her husband at the time<BR>of marriage) in a popular form of ancient Indian marriage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गवुड<BR>Gavuḍa (EI 5; ASLV), Kannaḍa; same as Grāmakūṭa,<BR>Gauḍa, Gāvuṇḍa; village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गावुण्ड<BR>Gāvuṇḍa, Gavuṇḍu (HD), same as Grāmakūṭa, Gavuḍa,<BR>Gauḍa. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 74; JBBRAS, Vol. X, p. 208.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गव्य|गव्यं<BR>gavya (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गव्यूत|गव्यूतं<BR>gavyūta (EI 22), a distance of about 4 miles; same as<BR>gavyūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गव्यूति|गव्यूतिः<BR>gavyūti (EI 27), a linear measure; same as gavyūta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गयाड<BR>gayāḍa, cf. guyāḍa (EI 22), courtyard. Cf. the royal names<BR>Gayāḍa and Gayāḍatuṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गयामुक्त<BR>Gayā-mukta (EI 33), one whose śrāddha ceremony has<BR>been performed at Gayā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गायत्री<BR>gāyatrī (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyfour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गेलाट<BR>gelāṭa (IA 18; CII 1), probably Sanskrit gairāṭa, ‘a<BR>hill bird’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गेणु<BR>geṇu (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; ‘one span’; a unit of measurment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गेवक<BR>gevaka (CII 1), inferior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाडा<BR>ghāḏā (Chamba), a system by which the tiller receives one<BR>half of the produce. See ghāḏotā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाडक<BR>ghāḏaka, also called ghāḏī (Chamba); land cultivated on<BR>the ghāḏā system.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घदम<BR>ghada-maṟuturu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure<BR>of land; a variation of maṟuturu (q. v.). Cf. kāl-maṟuturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घडपुट्टि<BR>ghaḍa-puṭṭi (CITD), Telugu; a variation of puṭṭi. Cf.<BR>gāl-puṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाडी<BR>ghāḏī, cf. ghāḏaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घडियारमु<BR>ghaḍiyāramu (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a gong, a watch,<BR>a clock, an hour glass; a cup with a hole at the bottom placed<BR>on water for measuring time, an hour being counted when<BR>it sinks. Cf. ghaṭikā-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाडोता<BR>ghāḏotā (Chamba), spoken of a land tilled on the condition<BR>that one half of the produce should go to the owner. See<BR>ghāḏā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घले<BR>ghale (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; measuring rod; cf. Gaṅgana<BR>ghale, ‘the rod [measured by the length of the forearm] of a<BR>person named Gaṅga’; cf. hasta in Śivacandra-hasta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाणक<BR>ghāṇaka (EI 2, 32), an oil-mill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घरहण<BR>gharahaṇa (Chamba), same as garaṭhā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोरक्षेत्र<BR>ghora-kṣetra (SITI), gṛha-kṣetra; a building site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घरठा<BR>gharaṭhā (Chamba), also called gharahana, gharaṭhāi,<BR>gharṭhāi; a house site; homestead; from Sanskrit gṛha-sthāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाञ्चिक<BR>Chāñcika, maker of or dealer in oil (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>pp. 145-46); same as Gujarātī Ghāṃci.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घस्र|घस्रं|घस्रः<BR>ghasra (IE 7-1-2), ‘fifteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाट|घाटः<BR>ghāṭa (EI 21), name of a tax. Cf. ghatṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटक|घटकः<BR>ghaṭaka, a jar (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटशासुलु<BR>Ghaṭaśāsulu (CITD), Telugu; logicians. See Ghaṭikāsāhasa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटि<BR>ghaṭi, ghaṭī (CII 3), same as ghaṭikā, the sixtieth division<BR>of a day (i. e. day and night); equal to twentyfour English<BR>minutes. Cf. ghaḍīyāramu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटी<BR>ghaṭī (CII 4), name of a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिक|घटिकं|घटिकः<BR>ghaṭika (CII 2-1), used in the sense of ghaṭikā, an hour<BR>equal to twentyfour English minutes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिका<BR>ghaṭikā (CII 3; ML), an hour; time equal to twentyfour<BR>English minutes; same as ghaṭi, ghaṭī.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 34, note 6), an establishment of<BR>holy and learned men. Cf. Tamil ghaṭikai (SII 12).<BR>Cf. ghaṭige (SII 3), an assembly.<BR>(SITI), an educational institution for advanced studies;<BR>a university; probably the same as śālā and mahāśālā. Cf.<BR>Prakrit ghaḍia-ghaḍā (EI 8), same as goṣṭhī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकागृहकरण<BR>ghaṭikāgṛha-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of<BR>time-keeping. Cf. ghaḍiyāramu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकैयार्<BR>Ghaṭikaiyār (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; members of a<BR>ghaṭikā managing its affairs; officials who declare to the public,<BR>by beat of tomtom, the orders of kings and other officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकालय<BR>ghaṭik-ālaya (EI 1), a water-clock.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकामध्यस्थ<BR>Ghaṭikā-madhyastha (SITI), an intermediary officer having<BR>the authority of the ghaṭikā or recognised by the ghaṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकासाहस<BR>Ghaṭikāsāhasa (EI 8), same as the Brahmanical family<BR>name Ghaisāsa, also called Ghaṭaśāsin, etc. See Ghaṭaśāsulu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकाशाला<BR>ghaṭikā-śālā (EI 25), same as ghāṭikā-sthāna; an establish-<BR>ment of holy and learned men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकास्थान<BR>ghaṭikā-sthāna (EI 14, 16) ‘a religious centre’; the official<BR>meeting place of learned and godly men; cf. ghaṭikā-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटित<BR>ghaṭita (CII 1), ‘put together’.<BR>(Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 121, text line 55), engraved.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटितहीनद्रम्मा<BR>ghaṭita-hīna-drammā (LP), ‘drammas that are wanting’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटियन्त्र<BR>ghaṭi-yantra (EI 14), a clock. Cf. ghaḍiyāramu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घट्ट|घट्टः<BR>ghaṭṭa (BL), bathing or landing place on the bank of a<BR>river.<BR>(IE 8-5), a harbour or a mountain pass.<BR>(ASLV), a contingent of elephants, the number being ten<BR>according to some authorities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घट्टपाल<BR>Ghaṭṭapāla (IE 8-3); EI 31), the superintendent of landing<BR>places on the river banks or of passes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घट्टपति<BR>Ghaṭṭapati (EI 7; CII 4; HD), same as Ghaṭṭapāla; gene-<BR>rally explained as ‘an officer in charge of quays or landing<BR>places (ghāṭs)’; may also be an officer in charge of a pass<BR>(cf. the Orissan royal title Aṣṭādaśa-ghaṭṭa-gondram-ādhipati);<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-116" target="_blank">Page-116+ 40</a>]<BR>see Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91; JBORS, Vol. V, pp. 582,<BR>588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोष|घोषं|घोषः<BR>ghoṣa (CII 4), a settlement of the milkmen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोटकविग्रह<BR>ghoṭaka-vigraha (CII 4; BL), ‘a battle of horses’; probably,<BR>an encounter of horsemen; cf. caturdanta-samara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोटिका<BR>ghoṭikā (EI 31), a boundary post bearing the represen-<BR>tation of a mare.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घृणि|घृणिः<BR>ghṛṇi (EI 12), a ray.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घृष्टमूर्धक<BR>ghṛṣṭa-mūrdhaka (LP), ‘with hairs of one's head fallen off.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घृतप्रदीप<BR>ghṛta-pradīpa (LL), a lamp to be burnt with ghee instead<BR>of oil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घुमर<BR>ghumara (EI 23), used in Bastar in the sense of ‘water-<BR>falls’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गि<BR>gi (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Prakrit gimha = Sanskrit<BR>grīṣma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिद्द<BR>gidda (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a gill, or a liquid ounce;<BR>a quarter especially of a sola weighing 16 dubbus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिम्ह<BR>gimha (CII 4), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit grīṣma; name<BR>of a season consisting of eight fortnights or four months.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिरि|गिरिः<BR>giri (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिरिदुर्ग<BR>giri-durga (ASLV), hill fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिरीन्द्र|गिरींद्र|गिरीन्द्रः<BR>girīndra (SII 2), ‘a hill-chief’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गो<BR>go (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; rarely used in the sense of ‘nine’<BR>(cf. graha).<BR>Cf. a-paramparā-go-balivarda (IE 8-5); a cow. See balī-<BR>varda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोचर|गोचरः<BR>gocara (EI 15; Chamba), pasture land.<BR>(LP), a tax for allowing cattle to graze in the pasture<BR>land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोचरक<BR>gocaraka (Chamba), pasture land; same as gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोचर्मन्|गोचर्म्मन्<BR>gocarman (IE 8-6; EI 28; CITD), an area of land often<BR>regarded as equal to ten nivartanas although the exact area<BR>varied in different ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोच्छकपति<BR>Gocchakapati (EI 28), official designation of uncertain<BR>import. Cf. the Bengali family name Guchāita 〈 Gochāyati<BR>〈 Gocchakapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोद्वादशी<BR>go-dvādaśī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 161, 163-64), name<BR>of a tithi; Āśvina su-di 12; regarded doubtfully also as Mārga-<BR>śīrṣa su-di 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोगौड<BR>go-gauḍa (EI 12, 28), name of a tax probably levied on the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-117" target="_blank">Page-117+ 40</a>]<BR>cowherds; gauḍa is the same as gokuṭa meaning a cowherd or<BR>milkman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोग्रास|गोग्रासः<BR>go-grāsa, troughful of fodder for the cattle (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXV, p. 108).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोहर|गोहरः<BR>gohara, gohārā (Chamba), a path.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोहरि<BR>gohari (EI 31), Oḏiyā; cattle track or pasture land; or<BR>probably, a road (cf. gohara, gohārā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोज<BR>goja, the moon (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 58).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोझ<BR>gojha (Chamba), pocket; pocket money; personal pro-<BR>perty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकर<BR>gokara (IE 8-5; EI 4, 8, 13), probably, grazing tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकर्ण|गोकर्णः<BR>gokarṇa (EI 9), gokarṇa-kuśa-kusuma-karatal-odaka-pūrṇa<BR>(EI 23), gokarṇa-kuśalatā-pūta-hast-odakena (Ind. Ant., Vol. XV,<BR>p. 10, note 57), referring to an elaborate form of the ritual<BR>relating to donation generally indicated by the expression<BR>udak-ātisargeṇa; same as gaṇḍūṣa (in Bengali); palm hollowed to<BR>hold water and resembling a cow's ear.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुल|गोकुलं<BR>gokula (EI 9), cf. ‘officer in charge of the gokulas’;<BR>cf. Gokul-ādhikārin, Gokulika, Gomaṇḍalika.<BR>(SITI), a temple of Kṛṣṇa; also called āyappāḍi in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुलाधिकारिन्<BR>Gokul-ādhikārin (EI 24), superintendent of cattle;<BR>officer in charge of the royal cattle and cowpens (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XIV, p. 194). See Gokulika, Gomaṇḍalika. Cf. Vivīt-<BR>ādhyakṣa, Vrajabhūmika, Gomahiṣāj-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुलिक|गोकुलिकः<BR>Gokulika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), same as Gokul-ādhi-<BR>kārin, Gomaṇḍalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुट<BR>Gokuṭa (IE 8-5; EI 28), same as Oḏiyā Gauḍa; a milk-<BR>man or cowherd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोला<BR>golā (IA 21), a district.<BR>(EI 31), a granary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोलका<BR>golakā (SITI), also called gulikā, goḻakkai, koḻakkai, kuḻigai;<BR>name of a coin, probably circular in shape.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोल्ल<BR>Golla (EI 3), a cowherd.<BR>(IE 8-4), a small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोल्लवारु<BR>Golla-vāru (CITD), Telugu; a caste of watchmen [emplo-<BR>yed as treasure-guards], generally herdsmen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमहिषाजाविकावडवाध्यक्ष<BR>Go-mahiṣ-āj-āvikā-vaḍav-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), cf. Kiśora-<BR>vaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमहिष्यजाध्यक्ष<BR>Go-mahiṣy-aj-ādhyakṣa (EI 28), official designation; cf. Go-<BR>mahiṣ-āj-āvikā-vaḍav-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमण्डलिक<BR>Gomaṇḍalika (EI 18), officer in charge of the royal cattle.<BR>See Gokulika, Gokul-ādhikarin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमठ<BR>gomaṭha (EI 12), name of a sattra-like institution built by<BR>a Musalman chief together with a step-well and a garden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमिन्<BR>Gomin (IA 13), epithet of a Buddhist priest hailing from<BR>Gauḍa-viṣaya; supposed to denote a learned lay brother who<BR>held some high office on the establishment of a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमूत्रिकाबन्ध<BR>gomūtrikā-bandha (CITD), the style of composition of a<BR>stanza, the second half of which repeats nearly all the syllables<BR>of the first.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोन्द्रम<BR>gondrama (EI 30), Oḏiyā; probably, a hill fort or a state<BR>having its headquarters on a hill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोणी<BR>goṇī (CII 4), name of a measure of capacity; cf. goṇī-prasṛti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोणीप्रसृति<BR>goṇī-prasṛti (EI 1), a measure of uncertain weight; pro-<BR>bably, a handful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोप|गोपः<BR>Gopa (EI 24), a watchman.<BR>(HD), officer in charge of the royal cattle; officer over<BR>five or ten villages according to the Arthaśāstra, II. 35.<BR>(HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) officer in charge<BR>of five or ten villages with revenue and police functions; (2)<BR>officer in charge of ten, twenty or forty families in the city;<BR>similar to the Paṭel, or Paṭvārī (H. Rev. Syst., pp. 146-47).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपाल|गोपालः<BR>Gopāla (IE 8-8), a milkman or cowherd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपथ|गोपथः<BR>go-patha (EI 31), a cattle-track.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपथशर<BR>gopathaśara (CII 3), perhaps ‘a cattle-path’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपीचन्दन<BR>gopīcandana (IA 16), a kind of coloured earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोप्रचार|गोप्रचारः<BR>gopracāra (EI 24, 31, 32; CII 4), pasture land.<BR>(EI 30), right of grazing cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोप्रचारभूमि<BR>go-pracāra-bhūmi (SITI), grazing-ground; same as Tamil<BR>kaṇṟu-meypāḻ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपुर|गोपुरं<BR>gopura (EI 3, 19, 24) a gateway; the gateway of a temple;<BR>a tower.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपुरवाशल्<BR>gopura-vāśal (SII 1), Sanskrit-Tamil; the gate of a gopura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोरचर<BR>goracara (Chamba), same as Sanskrit gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोरचरका<BR>goracarakā (Chamba), same as Sanskrit gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोरव<BR>Gorava (EI 7), a Śaiva priest; same as Gurava, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोसहस्र<BR>go-sahasra (EI 16, 24), name of a gift (mahādāna).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोस्तन|गोस्तनः<BR>go-stana (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोष्ठी<BR>goṣṭhī (EI 24; SII 3; BL), an assembly; a corporate body;<BR>cf. Tamil goṣṭhiśeydāṉ, convener of a pariṣad.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-119" target="_blank">Page-119+ 40</a>]<BR>(LL), Buddhist; a committee; cf. Bauddha-goṣṭhī, Goṣthī-<BR>śramaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोष्ठिक<BR>Goṣṭhika (EI 4, 24, 33; CII 4), member of a committee<BR>or assembly; member of a managing committee; mem-<BR>ber of a committee like that of the trustees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोत्र|गोत्रं|गोत्रः<BR>gotra (CII 3; IA 19; CITD), a family or clan, a tribe or<BR>lineage; a caste. No Hindu can marry a girl of his own gotra<BR>or stock, though some forms of ancient Indian marriages did<BR>not involve the gotr-āntara, i. e. the change of the wife's gotra<BR>to that of the husband at the time of marriage (Proc. IHC,<BR>Annamalainagar, 1945, pp. 48 ff.). Cf. Gautamī-putra, etc.<BR>(EI 33), abbreviation of gotra-śailikā, a memorial pillar<BR>raised for the dead members of one's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोत्रान्तर<BR>gotr-āntara (IE 8-2), the change of the wife's paternal gotra<BR>to that of her husband, which was absent in some popular forms<BR>of marriage in ancient India (Proc. IHC, Annamalainagar,<BR>1945, pp. 48 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोत्रशैलिका<BR>gotra-śailikā (EI 33), a pillar raised in memory of the<BR>dead members of one's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोउड्<BR>Gouḍ (ASLV), Anglicised spelling of Gauḍa or Gavuḍa<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोवल्लभ<BR>Go-vallabha, cf. Prakrit Go-vallava (EI 24; II), a cow-<BR>herd; keeper of the royal cattle; see Mahāgovallabha (EI 24).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोवल्लव<BR>Go-vallava (IE 8-3), a cowherd; Sanskrit Go-vallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोयूथी<BR>go-yūthī, cf. sva-sīmā-tṛṇagoyūthī-gocara-paryanta (EI 8-5); yuthī<BR>is the same as yūti (or pūti) used in the same context in many<BR>other records in the compound tṛṇa-yūti (or tṛṇa-pūti). Goyūthī-<BR>gocara may be ‘the enclosure for cattle and pasture ground’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोयूति<BR>go-yūti, same as ga-yuthī; cf. yūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रह|ग्रहः<BR>graha (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR>(IA 21), seizure; cf. go-graha, cattle-lifting.<BR>Cf. sūrya-graha (EI 24), an eclipse of the sun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रहण|ग्रहणं<BR>grahaṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रहणक<BR>grahaṇaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, the custody or<BR>mortgage of an object.<BR>(LP), an ornament; cf. Gujarātī ghareṇuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राह्य<BR>grāhya (IE 8-8), ‘to be apprehended or recruited’.<BR>Cf. a-kiñcid-grāhya; ‘to be levied’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राम|ग्रामः<BR>grāma (IE 8-4), ‘a village’; often suffixed to the names of<BR>localities.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-120" target="_blank">Page-120+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 24), a village assembly.<BR>(IE 8-4), sometimes used to indicate the number of villages<BR>in a territory or geographical unit; but the number was often<BR>either exaggerated or traditional without relation to reality;<BR>sometimes wrongly interpreted as ‘a unit of revenue assess-<BR>ment’. Cf. navanavati-sahasra-grāma-bhāj (IE 8-4), epithet of<BR>a territory. See Sircar, Stud. Geog. Anc. Med. Ind., pp. 200 ff.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 146-47), a villager; same as<BR>Grāmeyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामभर्तृ<BR>Grāmabhartṛ (HD), same as Grāmapati (Yājñavalkyasmṛti,<BR>II. 271).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामभोगिक<BR>Grāma-bhogika (EI 24, 29; CII 4), probably the Jāgīrdār<BR>of a village or one who enjoys a village as a free-holding. Cf.<BR>rāja-sāmanta-viṣayapati-grāmabhogika-purillaka-cāṭa-bhaṭa-sevak-ādīn<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, pp. 114-15).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामदेव<BR>grāma-deva (IA 14), a village god; cf. grāma-devatā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामदेवता<BR>grāma-devatā (EI 3; SII 2), a village divinity; cf. grāma-<BR>deva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाधिपति|ग्रामाधिपतिः<BR>grām-ādhipati (IE 8-4), ‘headquarters of a Parganā’ (cf.<BR>triṃśad-grām-ādhipati-śrī-Kukkunūru); also called modala-vāḍa or<BR>rājadhāni in Kannaḍa inscriptions.<BR>(HD), same as Grāmapati (Kāmasūtra, V. 5. 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामद्रोहिन्<BR>Grāma-drohin (SITI), traitor to the village; cf. Grāmakaṇtaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाग्रामभोजक<BR>Grāmāgrāma-bhojaka (IE 8-3; LL), free-holders or Jāgīr-<BR>dārs of various villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामग्रास<BR>grāma-grāsa (EI 5, 6, 31), a village granted for the main-<BR>tenance of the donee; cf. grām-opahāra (EI 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाहार<BR>grām-āhāra (IE 8-4; LL), ‘a village-district’; a group of<BR>villages; a small territorial unit; cf. mahāgrāma and āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामक|ग्रामकः<BR>grāmaka (EI 8), a small village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकण्टक|ग्रामकंटक|ग्रामकण्टकः<BR>Grāma-kaṇṭaka (EI 24; SII 13; SITI), a traitor to the<BR>village; enemy of the security of a village; annoyance to a<BR>village. Cf. Grāma-drohin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकार्य<BR>grāma-kārya (IA 8), explained as ‘village rites’; probably,<BR>‘the various functions of the village’; village business (SITI);<BR>administration; committee of administration (SII 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकायस्थ<BR>Grāma-kāyastha (HD), a village scribe or Paṭvārī. See<BR>Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 175.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकूट|ग्रामकूटः<BR>Grāmakūṭa (EI 8-3); EI 30; CII 4; HD), cf. Grāmamahattara;<BR>the headman of a village (or probably, a member of the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-121" target="_blank">Page-121+ 40</a>]<BR>village council). Paiṭhīnasi and Kauṭilya (IV 5) use the<BR>word, and the commentary on the Kāmasūtra (V. 55) explains<BR>Grāmakūṭa as halottha-vṛtti. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 285; Ind.<BR>Ant., Vol. XVI, p. 24. See Rāṣṭrakūṭa, Deśakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकूटक<BR>Grāmakūṭaka (EI 7, 12; HD), same as Grāmakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राममहत्तर<BR>Grāma-mahattara (IE 8-3; EI 12, 28), same as Grāmakūṭa<BR>and Mahattara; the village headman and a member of the<BR>village council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राममहत्तराधिकारिन्<BR>Grāmamahattar-ādhikārin (EI 25), official designation;<BR>probably, Grāma-mahattara and Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राममर्यादा<BR>grāma-maryādā (EI 32), fixed local usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामनेतृ<BR>Grāma-netṛ (HD), a village headman. See Śukra, II. 120.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामणी<BR>Grāmaṇī (EI 27; LL; HD), a village headman; same as<BR>Grāmakūṭa. See Hist. Dharm., pp. 153-54; Pāṇini, V. 2. 78.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामपरिहार<BR>grāma-parihāra (SITI), obligatory dues of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामपति<BR>Grāmapati (EI 24, 26, 29; IA 9; HD), cf. Grāmakūṭa; the<BR>headman, owner or Jāgīrdār of a village (Mitākṣarā on Yājña-<BR>valkyasmṛti, II. 281). See Grāma-svāmika, etc.<BR>Cf. Kuḍipati (EI 18), the headman of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामपत्र<BR>grāma-patra (EI 9), a document indicating the revenue<BR>fixed for a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामप्रधान<BR>Grāma-pradhāna (EI 2), a village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामसंस्था<BR>grāma-saṃsthā (LP), a village institution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाष्टकुलाधिकरण<BR>grām-āṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa (EI 31), the administrative board<BR>(e. g. Pañcāyat) of a village; see aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामस्वामिक<BR>Grāma-svāmika, cf. Gāma-sāmika (EI 24); same as Grāma-<BR>pati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामटक<BR>Grāmaṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), official designation;<BR>probably a mistake for Grāmakūṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामतलार<BR>Grāma-talāra (LP), probably, something like a Faujdār.<BR>See Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामटिका<BR>grāmaṭikā (EI 9, 19; SII 1), a hamlet; a small village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामेयक|ग्रामेयकः<BR>Grāmeyaka (EI 31; LL), a villager; inhabitant of a village;<BR>probably also the village headman, the same as Grāmika (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 327); cf. Vaṭṭa-grāmeyaka (EI 27); also<BR>Grāmeyika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामेयिक<BR>Grāmeyika (LL), a villager; same as Grāmeyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामिक<BR>Grāmika (IE 8-5; EI 15; CII 3; LL; HD), a village head-<BR>man (Manusmṛti, VII. 116; Arthaśāstra, III. 10; CII, Vol.<BR>III, p. 112); same as Grāmaṇī, etc.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-122" target="_blank">Page-122+ 40</a>]<BR>Cf. grāmika-jana-samūha (EI 24), ‘an assembly of the<BR>villagers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामीयकुल<BR>grāmīya-kula (EI 24), an assembly of the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामोपहार<BR>grām-opahāra (EI 5), same as grāma-grāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रन्थवारि<BR>granthavāri (IA 24), household histories in Travancore.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रास|ग्रासः<BR>grāsa (EI 11; LP), food; land granted for maintenance;<BR>cf. grāsa-lopana (LP), confiscation of the lands given for main-<BR>teanance; also cf. grāma-grāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रासग्रह<BR>grāsagraha, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रासवासस्<BR>grāsa-vāsas (CITD), food and raiment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृ<BR>gṛ (IE 8-1), also spelt gri; wrong abbreviation of grīṣma<BR>in Prakrit records.<BR>Cf. gṛ-ṭī; abbreviation of gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृचटी<BR>gṛ-ca-ṭī, abbreviation of an expression probably meaning<BR>‘a mound on which houses can be (or, have been) built and<BR>fruit trees can be (or, have been) planted’. Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXX, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृह|गृहं<BR>gṛha, cf. ghara (EI 7), a caitya; a cave. Cf. gṛha-mukha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहकर<BR>gṛha-kara, cf. ilvari, manai-iṟai, manai-ppaṇam (SITI),<BR>house-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहकृत्य<BR>gṛha-kṛtya (HRS), an office concerned with domestic<BR>affairs of the kingdom as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See<BR>Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 250.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहमुख<BR>gṛha-mukha, cf. ghara-mugha (LL), the door of a cave.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहपति|गृहपतिः<BR>Gṛhapati (EI 25; CII 3; LL), a householder; same as Gṛhastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहस्थ|गृहस्थः<BR>Gṛhastha (LL), a householder; same as Gṛhapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहस्थान<BR>gṛha-sthāna (EI 24), a house-site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहवार्ता<BR>gṛha-vārtā (LP), household articles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहवेटक<BR>Gṛha-veṭaka (EI 9), possibly a mistake for Gṛha-ceṭaka, ‘a<BR>servant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहीतसाहस्र<BR>Gṛhīta-sāhasra (EI 33), probably, ‘one from whom one<BR>thousand coins have been realised’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रीष्म|ग्रीष्मः<BR>grīṣma (EI 24; CII 4), one of the three seasons constituting<BR>the ancient Indian official year; the four months from Caitra<BR>ba-di 1 to Āṣāḍha su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृटी<BR>gṛ-ṭī, abbreviation of gṛha-ṭikkara (ṭīkara) or gṛha-vāstu-<BR>ṭīkara, ‘a mound suitable for building houses’. Cf. Ep. Ind,<BR>Vol. XXX, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुड|गुडः<BR>guḍa, cf. a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (IE 8-5); sugar, the pro-<BR>duction of which was the monopoly of the king or landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुडान्तपत्र<BR>guḍānta-patra (Journal of the Bihar Research Society, Vol.<BR>XL, Part 2, pp. 96-97), name of a type of document, the exact<BR>nature of which is doubtful; probably, a kind of lease deed.<BR>Cf. guṇa-patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुड्ड<BR>guḍḍa, guḍḍa-dhvaja (IA 10), Kannaḍa; the meaning<BR>of guḍḍa is doubtful; probably, a disciple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गूढजालबन्ध<BR>gūḍha-jāla-bandha (CITD), probably, the style of a verse<BR>with an artificial arrangement of the letters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गूढमण्डप<BR>gūḍha-maṇḍapa (HA), an adjacent hall; hall in front<BR>of the sanctum, where devotees carry on worship, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गूढपुरुष|गूढपुरुषः<BR>Gūḍha-puruṣa (HD), an officer of the secret service. See<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 156.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुडिक<BR>Guḍika (EI 28, 31), maker or seller of sugar; see Gauḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुग्गुल|गुग्गुलः<BR>guggula (CII 4), bdellium.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुहा<BR>guhā (SITI), literally, ‘a cave’; a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुहाविहार<BR>guhā-vihāra (CII 2-1), a cave-monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुजराती<BR>Gujarātī, the people, language and alphabet of Gujarat.<BR>See Boḏiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुलिका<BR>gulikā, cf. pudu-kkuḻigai (SITI), name of a coin; also<BR>śeṇapaka-kkuḻigai (SITI), name of a coin probably struck by the<BR>Śambuvārāyas; puḻḻi-guḻikai-varāhaṉ (SITI), name of a gold coin;<BR>vīracampaṉ-kuḻigai (SITI), a coin struck and issued by the<BR>Śambuvarāya king Vīracampa; vāḻāl-vaḻitiṟantāṉ guḻikai<BR>(SITI), a Pāṇḍya coin supposed to have been issued by Jaṭā-<BR>varman Sundara-pāṇḍya I who had the title Vāḻāl-vaḻi-tiṟantāṉ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्म|गुल्मं|गुल्मः<BR>gulma (EI 8, 12), a battalion, squadron or outpost. Cf.<BR>Gaulmika. (IE 8-5), a bush; cf. sa-gulma-latāka as an epithet of<BR>a gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्मदेय<BR>gulma-deya (HRS), dues paid at the military or police<BR>station as indicated in the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev.<BR>Syst., pp. 78, 227.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्मपति<BR>Gulmapati (HD), officer in charge of a gulma which means<BR>a group or outpost of guards, soldiers or policemen; same as<BR>Gaulmika. Cf. JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्फ|गुल्फः<BR>gulpha (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुण|गुणः<BR>guṇa (IE 7-1-2; EI 15, 17, 25), ‘three’; rarely in late<BR>records, ‘six’.<BR>(EI 8), six in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुणचरित<BR>Guṇacarita (BL), supposed to be an epithet of a Pratīhāra<BR>king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुणाक्षर<BR>guṇ-ākṣara (LP), a document for a lease of land by the pro-<BR>prietors to cultivators; see guṇa-patra.<BR>Cf. guṇ-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a concession letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुणपत्र<BR>guṇa-patra (LP), a lease of land granted by proprietors<BR>to tenants or cultivators for the purpose of cultivating or im-<BR>proving it; cf. Pañcāladeśīya-kulānāṃ guṇa-patra-vidhiḥ, ‘an order<BR>of royal favour concerning the farmers of the Pañcāla country’;<BR>also cf. Gujarātī gaṇotnāmuṃ. See guṇākṣara, guḍāntapatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुण्ड|गुंडः|गुण्डः<BR>guṇḍa (EI 8), probably, a niche.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुञ्जा|गुंजा<BR>guñjā (IE 8-8; IA 26), same as raktikā or rati.<BR>(EI 12), a kettle-drum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुण्ठ<BR>guṇṭha (IE 8-6; EI 28, 31), a land measure of Orissa;<BR>equal to one-twentififth of a Māṇa.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 62), Telugu; a pond; cf. silā-guṇṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्त|गुप्तं<BR>gupta, cf. gupt-ākṣarāṇi (LP), same as gupta-patḷaka, a deed<BR>of permanent lease. See Tamil guttagai = Sanskrit guptakā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्तका<BR>guptakā, see guttagai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्तपट्टक<BR>gupta-paṭṭaka (LP), a deed of permanent lease; called<BR>gupta probably because it reserved the right of use to a parti-<BR>cular man; cf. gupt-ākṣara (also gupta).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्ति|गुप्तिः<BR>gupti (EI 4), three in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरचरका<BR>guracarakā (Chamba), same as gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरव<BR>Gurava, same as Gorava; epithet of a Śaiva priest (Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. XIV, p. 140, note 4); also supposed to be a Jain priest.<BR>(EI 4), a teacher; cf. Gorava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुराव<BR>Gurāva (IA 11), same as Gorava; a Śaiva priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरु|गुरुः<BR>guru (SII 1), a preceptor; also ‘the head’ as in Caṇḍik-<BR>āśrama-guru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरुदक्षिणा<BR>guru-dakṣiṇā (EI 32), money paid to the preceptor for<BR>initiation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरुमुखी<BR>Gurumukhī, also spelt Gurmukhī; alphabet in which the<BR>Punjabi language is written by the Sikhs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरुआयतन<BR>guru-āyatana (EI 21, 28) a temple where one's deceased<BR>guru (preceptor) is worshipped.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुत्तगै<BR>guttagai (ASLV), Sanskrit guptakā; a contract or lease.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुत्तिगे<BR>guttige (ASLV), a contract; cf. guttagai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुवाक|गुवाकः<BR>guvāka, cf. sa-guvāka-nārikela (IE 8-5); arecanut palms,<BR>the enjoyment of which was not allowed to the ordinary ten-<BR>ants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाद<BR>hāda (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit pāda; a land<BR>measure equal to one-fourth of the standard measure which was<BR>the mattaru or nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हडपद<BR>Haḍapada (EI 11), the bearer of the king's betel-bag (cf.<BR>Oḏiyā Vāguli, etc.); also explained as ‘a courtier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाग<BR>hāga (IE 8-8, EI 5), Kannaḍa; same as pāga, or Sanskrit<BR>bhāga; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हैरण्यक|हैरण्यकः<BR>Hairaṇyaka (LL), Hairaṇyika; a treasurer; also a goldsmith<BR>or mint-master. Cf. Hiraṇyakāra, Sauvarṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हल|हलं|हलः<BR>hala (IE 8-6), literally ‘a plough’; a free-holding (cf.<BR>bhikṣu-hala); an area of land, which was not exactly the<BR>same in different ages and localities (EI 7, 24, 29, 30, 31; CII 4).<BR>(IA 18), a land measure equal to one-fourth of a sīrā<BR>(cf. halavāhā); half of a kula; one plough-measure.<BR>(EI 3), probably, ‘arable land’; cf. sītā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाल|हालः<BR>hāla (EI 19), a land measure; same as hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलदगाङ्ग<BR>haladagāṅga (IA 19), explained as ‘the portion having<BR>(ga) water (da) and arable land (hala)’; meaning doubtful;<BR>probably the name of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलदण्ड|हलदण्डः<BR>hala-daṇḍa (EI 33), tax on ploughs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलकलित<BR>hala-kalita, ‘cultivated [land]’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p.<BR>297, text line 25).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हालकीय<BR>Hālakīya (LL), a ploughman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलवाहा<BR>halavāhā (IA 18), a land measure; cf. hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलि|हलिः<BR>hali (EI 24), a land measure; same as hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हालिक|हालिकः<BR>Hālika (LL), a ploughman (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 274<BR>and note).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हालिका<BR>Hālikā (EI 15), feminine form of Hālika, ‘an agriculturist<BR>or ploughman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलिकाकर<BR>halikā-kara, cf. halirākara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलिराकर<BR>halirākara (CII 3), a fiscal term of uncertain implica-<BR>tion; probably a mistake for halikā-kara, ‘plough-tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हम्मीर<BR>Hammīra (EI 24, 33, 34), derived from Arabic Amīr,<BR>often adopted by Hindu princes as a personal name;<BR>sometimes written as Hambīra and Ahaṃvīra (EI 34).<BR>Cf. Suratrāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंस|हंसः<BR>Haṃsa (EI 15), an ascetic; cf. Paramahaṃsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंसपद|हंसपदः<BR>haṃsapada, same as suvarṇa (q. v.); same as kākapada<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंयमन<BR>haṃyamana (EI 32, 35), same as hañjamana; regarded by<BR>some as derived from Persian anjumān; cf. haṃyamana-paura,<BR>explained as ‘the assembly of the Parsees’. But see añjuvaṇṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हण<BR>haṇa (IE 8-8; EI 8), Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit paṇa;<BR>name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हण्डिकापति<BR>Haṇḍikāpati (EI 5), epithet of a Brāhmaṇa donee; mean-<BR>ing uncertain. Haṇḍikā means ‘an earthern pot [for cooking]’,<BR>and the expression may mean ‘the head of a joint family (i. e<BR>one responsible for feeding the family)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हञ्जमण<BR>hañjamaṇa, hañjamana (EI 25, 32), regarded by some<BR>as ‘a Parsee colony’, same as Persian anjumān (cf. haṃyamana),<BR>though really it is the same as Tamil añjuvaṇṇam = Sanskrit<BR>pañca-varṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हर|हरः<BR>hara (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हारक|हारकः<BR>hāraka, cf. ‘one hāraka of barley corn’ (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XI, p. 30, text line 2); possibly bhāraka, a load or measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरनयन<BR>hara-nayana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरणी<BR>haraṇī, cf. Hastavapra-haraṇī (EI 17), a district; probably<BR>a mistake for āharaṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरिबाहु<BR>haribāhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरिचन्दन|हरिचंदन|हरिचन्दनं|हरिचन्दनः<BR>haricandana (CITD), a sort of yellow sandal-wood; one<BR>of the five trees of svarga; a title of nobility in medieval Orissa<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 4); cf. Śrīcandana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरिदिन<BR>hari-dina (SITI), ‘the day of Hari’; Saturday; the ekādaśī<BR>day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हारित|हारितः<BR>hārita (CII 1), ‘caused to be imported’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरीतक<BR>harītaka, cf. a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); myro-<BR>balan [which the villagers were obliged to supply to the king<BR>or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हारीतीपुत्र<BR>Hārītī-putra (IE 8-2), originally a metronymic (cf. Gautamī-<BR>putra), but later sometimes adopted by members of a royal<BR>family like a dynastic usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हर्मिका<BR>harmikā (EI 28), a pavilion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हर्म्य|हर्म्म्यं|हर्म्यं<BR>harmya (LL), a temple or pavilion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हसन्तिका|हसंतिका<BR>hasantikā (IA 15), a brazier or portable heater; also<BR>called kaṅgār in Kashmiri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त|हस्तं|हस्तः<BR>hasta (IE 8-6), a cubit (24 aṅgulas); sometimes regarded<BR>as 36 aṅgulas (27 inches), 20(3/4) inches, 34 inches, etc., in length;<BR>cf. Śivacandra-hasta, ‘the cubit measured according to the length<BR>of the forearm of Śivacandra’ (cf. ghaḻe).<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-127" target="_blank">Page-127+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 23; SII 2), a square cubit; a land measure.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol XIV, p. 366 and note), probably the same<BR>as pakṣa, ‘a fortnight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तभां<BR>hasta-bhāṃ (LP), abbreviation of hastaka-bhāṇḍārin; ‘by<BR>the hand of (i. e. through) the Bhāṇḍārin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तक|हस्तकः<BR>hastaka (EI 31), same as hasta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तप्रक्षेप<BR>hasta-prakṣepa (EI 23), obstruction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिबन्ध<BR>hasti-bandha (EI 32), name of a tax; cf. hasti-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिदण्ड<BR>hasti-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 33), name of the tax for keep-<BR>ing elephants. Cf. hasti-bandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिदन्त|हस्तिदंत|हस्तिदन्तं|हस्तिदन्तः<BR>hasti-danta (IE 8-5, EI 1), ‘ivory’, referring to the<BR>right to keep elephants’ tusks without surrendering them to<BR>the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिकोश<BR>Hastikośa, official designation (cf. The Successors of the<BR>Sātavāhanas, p. 110, note 2), mentioned along with Vīrakośa<BR>as an officer related to a district; probably, an officer in charge<BR>of elephants or the elephant corps.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिन्<BR>hastin (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिपक|हस्तिपकः<BR>Hastipaka, cf. Hāthivaka (EI 18), keeper of elephants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिसाधनिक<BR>Hasti-sādhanika (EI 30), leader of the elephant corps; cf.<BR>Gajasāhanī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिशालाकरण<BR>hastiśālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of ele-<BR>phants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिवैद्य<BR>Hasti-vaidya (EI 38), the physician for elephants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तोदक<BR>hast-odaka, cf. hatha-paṃni, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यध्यक्ष|हस्त्यध्यक्षः<BR>Hasty-adhyakṣa (BL; EI 18), keeper of elephants; officer<BR>in charge of the elephant corps. Cf. Hasti-sādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यारोह|हस्त्यारोहः<BR>Hasty-āroha (Sel. Ins., p. 54), elephant-rider or elephant-<BR>driver; cf. Hāthāroha (EI 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वगोमहिषाजाविकाध्यक्ष<BR>Hasty-aśva-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), officer or officers<BR>in charge of elephants, etc.; Nauk-ādhyakṣa, Bal-ādhyakṣa, etc.,<BR>are often mentioned separately in the same context.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वजनव्यापृत<BR>Hasty-aśva-jana-vyāpṛta, Hasty-aśva-jana-vyāpṛtaka (EI 33),<BR>leader or leaders of the elephant corps, cavalry and infantry.<BR>Cf. Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-bala-vyāpṛta, Kari-turagapaṭṭasāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वोष्ट्रबलव्यापृत<BR>Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-bala-vyāpṛta (EI 33), Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-<BR>bala-vyāpṛtaka (EI 23, HD), military officer or officers in<BR>charge of the elephant, horse and camel corps.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वोष्ट्रगोमहिषाजाविकाध्यक्ष<BR>Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), cf.<BR>Kiśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वोष्ट्रनौबलव्यापृतक<BR>Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-nau-bala-vyāpṛtaka (IE 8-3; EI 24, 29;<BR>HD), military officer or officers in charge of the elephant force,<BR>cavalry, camel corps and navy. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St.,<BR>p. 166; Ep. Ind. Vol. XVII, p. 321. Cf. Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-go-<BR>mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa. It has to be noted that these two are<BR>never mentioned together while, on the other hand, one is used<BR>in place of the other. See Naubala-hasty-aśva-go-mahiṣ-ājāvik-ādi-<BR>vyāpṛtaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हथपंणि<BR>hatha-paṃṇi, hatha-pāṇi, hatha-pāṇī (Chamba), libation<BR>of water; from Sanskrit hasta-pānīya. See hast-odaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्ट|हट्टः<BR>haṭṭa (EI 1, 30, LP), a market or market-place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टदान<BR>haṭṭa-dāna (EI 3), name of a tax; tolls collected at the<BR>market place. Cf. aṭṭapati-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टमार्ग<BR>haṭṭa-mārga (EI 19), the main bazar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टरथ्या<BR>haṭṭa-rathyā (EI 30), passage between rows of stalls in the<BR>market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टव्यवहरमाण<BR>haṭṭa-vyavaharamāṇa (LP), probably, ‘current in the mar-<BR>ket (haṭṭa)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टिका<BR>haṭṭikā (LP), a market.<BR>(EI 4) probably ‘market-dues’, mentioned along with<BR>talapāṭaka or talavāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हवन|हवनं<BR>havana (SII 3), a burnt oblation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हविर्बलि<BR>havir-bali (SITI), same as śrī-bali; bali offered with cooked<BR>food; same as Tamil ti-yeṟiśoṟu; tax payable for meeting the<BR>expenses of the same in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हयपति|हयपतिः<BR>Hayapati (EI 1, 24, 29; BL; CII 4), same as Aśvapati;<BR>‘the lord of horses’; keeper of horses or a leader of<BR>horsemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हे<BR>he (IE 8-1), abbreviation of hemanta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेड|हेडः<BR>heḍa, cf. heḍāu, heḍavālā (LP), a man who wanders along<BR>with a herd of cattle (heḍa) for selling them.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेडाविक<BR>heḍāvika (EI 12), also called heḍāvuka; a horse-dealer.<BR>See heḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेग्गडे<BR>Hĕggaḍĕ (IE 8-3; EI 28; ASLV) Kannaḍa; official desig-<BR>nation indicating a chief, superintendent or director; same as<BR>Vĕrgaḍĕ, Pĕrgaḍĕ, Adhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेज्जुङ्क<BR>hĕjjuṅka (EI 21), Kannaḍa; name of a tax; also called<BR>pĕrjuṅka; Sanskrit mahāśulka or bṛhac-chulka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेम|हेमं|हेमः<BR>hema (IE 8-1), abbreviation of hemanta. See also hema-<BR>dhānyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमधान्यक|हेमधान्यकः<BR>hemadhānyaka, same as māṣa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 45);<BR>sometimes hema or dhānaka is used in the same sense (ibid.,<BR>p. 44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमगर्भ<BR>hema-garbha (EI 12, 16; SII 3), name of a mahādāna;<BR>same as hiraṇya-garbha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमाश्व<BR>hem-āśva (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमाश्वरथ<BR>hemāśva-ratha (EI 12), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमटङ्क<BR>hema-ṭaṅka, ‘a gold ṭaṅka (q. v.)’. See JNSI, Vol.<BR>XXII, p. 197.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमिद्रछ्म<BR>hemidrachma (IE 8-8), name of a Greek coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिलालकन्नडसन्धिविग्रहिन्<BR>Hĕri-Lāḻa-Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), same as Sanskrit<BR>Mahā-Lāṭa-Karṇāṭa-sandhivigrahin; the same officer is some-<BR>times also called Mahāpradhāna, Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa, Manĕ-vĕrgaḍĕ,<BR>etc., additionally. Cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिलालसन्धिविग्रहिन्<BR>Hĕri-Lāḻa-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), ‘the great Sandhivigrahin<BR>of Lāṭa’; cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिलाटकर्णाटसन्धिविग्रहिन्<BR>Hĕri-Lāṭa-Karṇāṭa-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), ‘the great<BR>Sandhivigrahin of Lāṭa and Karṇāṭa’; cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिसन्धिविग्रहिन्<BR>Hĕri-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; same<BR>as Mahāsandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेवक<BR>hevaka (IA 18), love or desire; same as Arabic hawwa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हि<BR>hi (IE 8-1), abbreviation of hiraṇya, ‘cash’ or ‘revenue<BR>income in cash’. Cf. sāṃ-hi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीनाक्षर<BR>hīn-ākṣara (LP), ‘with some words wanting’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीनवादिन्<BR>hīnavādin (LP), the defeated party.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिण्डिपक<BR>Hiṇḍipaka (LP), explained as ‘a touring revenue officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीण्डोली<BR>hīṇḍolī (LP), a swing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिन्दुराजसुरत्राण<BR>Hindurāja-suratrāṇa (IE 8-2), title assumed by some of the<BR>Vijayanagara kings, adopted from the Muslim royal title<BR>Sulṯān. See Suratrāṇa, Hindurāya-suratrāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिन्दुरायसुरत्राण<BR>Hindurāya-suratrāṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 363), title of the<BR>Vijayanagara kings, Suratrāṇa being the same as Arabic Sulṯān.<BR>See Hindurāja-suratrāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीनि<BR>hīni (CII 1), same as Sanskrit hāni; loss or diminution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्य|हिरण्यं<BR>hiraṇya (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28, 29), same as hiraṇy-āya, hiraṇya-<BR>deya; tax payable to the king in cash; dues payable in coins;<BR>cash; sometimes abbreviated as hi as in sāṃ-hi = sāṃvatsarika-<BR>hiraṇya, annual revenue income in cash; cf. a-hiraṇya-dhānya-<BR>praṇaya-pradeya (IE 8-5); it may be in addition to the tax in<BR>grain or in lieu of the latter. Cf. Tamil kāś-āya, etc.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-130" target="_blank">Page-130+ 40</a>]<BR>(HRS), king's share of certain crops paid in cash.<BR>(CII 1), probably, ‘money’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यगर्भ|हिरण्यगर्भः<BR>hiraṇyagarbha (EI 16; IA 10; SII 3), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यकार|हिरण्यकारः<BR>Hiraṇyakāra (LL), a treasurer; also a goldsmith or mint-<BR>master. Cf. Hairaṇyika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यसामुदायिक<BR>Hiraṇyasāmudāyika (IE 8-3), a collector of revenue in cash;<BR>sometimes mentioned along with the Audraṅgika or the collector<BR>of the udraṅga tax probably levied in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्याश्व|हिरण्याश्वः<BR>hiraṇyāśva (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्याश्वरथ|हिरण्याश्वरथः<BR>hiraṇyāśvaratha (EI 12), name of a mahādāna; same as<BR>hemāśvaratha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्याय<BR>hiraṇy-āya (EI 7), tax in cash; cf. hiraṇya-deya, kāś-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरियभाण्डागारिन्<BR>Hiriya-bhāṇḍāgārin (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; same as<BR>Mahābhāṇḍāgārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यदेय<BR>hiraṇya-deya (EI 17), tax in cash; cf. hiraṇy-āya, kāś-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होबलि<BR>hobaḻi, also spelt hobḻi (IE 8-4; ASLV), Kannaḍa; a<BR>small territorial unit like a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होब्लि<BR>hobḻi, cf. hobaḻi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होली<BR>holī (EI 3, 5), the spring festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होम|होमः<BR>homa (BL; SII 3), an oblation; name of a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होन्<BR>hon, same as hūn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होर<BR>hora, horaka (EI 9), probably, a foreign word meaning ‘a lady’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होरमुर्त<BR>Horamurta (CII 2-1), a foreign word explained as<BR>‘donation-master [of someone else]’; cf. Dānapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होतृ<BR>hotṛ (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ह्रद|ह्रदः<BR>hrada (LL), a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ह्रसित<BR>hrasita (IE 8-3), cf. svayaṃ hrasite karṇe; partly cut off.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हृतप्रग्राहामात्य<BR>Hṛtapragrāh-āmātya (EI 31), officer in charge of the re-<BR>covery of stolen property. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 29.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हूहूकान्त<BR>hūhūkānta (IA 18), the moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हून्<BR>hūn (IE 8-8), same as varāha; name of a gold coin of<BR>about 50 grains, called pagoda or ‘star pagoda’ in English.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हुण्डिका<BR>huṇḍikā (LP), a bill of exchange (Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 266).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हुताशन|हुताशनः<BR>hutāśana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इभ|इभः<BR>ibha (EI 25), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इभ्य|इभ्यः<BR>Ibhya (CII 1), same as Rājanya or Kṣatriya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडङ्ग<BR>iḍaṅgal13i (EI 28), Tamil; a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईडरवारु<BR>īḍara-vāru, īḍige-vāḍu (CITD), Telugu; a toddy-man<BR>or arrack-drawer; from īḍa, ‘a date tree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इला<BR>ilā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईलम्<BR>Īḻam (SII 1), Tamil name of Ceylon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इ|इः<BR>Il13aiya-nāyanār (SITI), the same as the god Subrahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ई<BR>īl13a-kkāśu, also called īl13a-kkaruṅ-kāśu and karuṅ-kāśu<BR>(SITI); the Ceylonese coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इम्मडि<BR>Immaḍi (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa; literally, ‘double’ or ‘twice’;<BR>prefixed to the names of certain kings in order to distinguish<BR>them from their predecessors bearing the same name; cf.<BR>Nūrmaḍi, Mummuḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्र|इंद्रः|इन्द्रः<BR>indra (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR>(EI 7), a Jain priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रच्छन्द|इन्द्रच्छन्दः<BR>indracchanda (SII 2), name of a jewel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रदण्ड<BR>indra-daṇḍa (CII 4), a pole raised in honour of Indra;<BR>also called indra-dhvaja, śakra-dhvaja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रदृष्टि<BR>indra-dṛṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रासन<BR>indr-āsana (IA 23), hemp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रिय|इंद्रिय|इन्द्रियं<BR>indriya (IE 7-1-2; EI 5), five in number; ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्दु|इंदुः|इन्दुः<BR>indu (IE 7-12), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईश|ईशं|ईशः<BR>Īśa (EI 23), the god Śiva; the king.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईशदृश्<BR>īśa-dṛś (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इष्टापूर्त्त|इष्टापूर्त|इष्टापूर्तं|इष्टापूर्त्तं<BR>iṣṭāpūrtta (EI 4; SII 3), a charitable deed; performance<BR>of charitable deeds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इष्टि|इष्टिः<BR>iṣṭi, used in the sense of viṣṭi; cf. sarv-eṣṭi-parihāra-parihṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इषु|इषुः<BR>iṣu (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईश्वर|ईश्वरं|ईश्वरः<BR>īśvara (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’; name-ending of Śiva-liṅgas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईश्वरालय<BR>īśvar-ālaya (SII 11-1), a temple; a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इतिहास|इतिहासः<BR>itihāsa (EI 13), legendary lore.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जदिआक्षेत्र<BR>jadiākṣetra (IA 16), explained as ‘a kind of land’, but<BR>may be ‘land of a person named Jadiā’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगत्<BR>jagat (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगति<BR>jagati, jagatī (EI 11), explained variously as ‘ground’;<BR>(EI 3), ‘lower ground or compound’; (EI 1), ‘a kind of build-<BR>ing’; also as ‘railed parapet’ (R. Narsimhachar, The Keśava<BR>Temple at Somanāthapura, p. 2). Cf. devagṛha-jagatī (IA 14);<BR>also jagati-ppaḍai (SII 2), the upper tier of the basement.<BR>See jagatī below.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगती<BR>jagatī (HA), same as bhamatī; the corridor of a shrine<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-132" target="_blank">Page-132+ 40</a>]<BR>on the four sides of its open court, used for circumambulation<BR>of the main shrine.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’; sometimes also ‘fortyeight’; rarely<BR>used in the sense of ‘the earth’ to indicate ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगतीपुर<BR>jagatīpura (EI 3), supposed to be the same as brahma-<BR>purī or Kannaḍa jagati-kaṭṭĕ which is ‘the raised square seat<BR>around a tree before a village’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जागीर्<BR>jāgīr (EI 33; BL), Persian; a fief; a tenure under<BR>Muhammadan rule, in which the public revenues of a given<BR>tract of land were made over, either conditionally or uncondi-<BR>tionally, to persons like a servant of the State together with<BR>the powers required to enable them to collect and appropriate<BR>such revenues and administer the general government of the<BR>tract. Cf. Wilson's Glossary. See Jāgīrdār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जागीर्दार्<BR>Jāgīrdār (EI 33), Persian; a fief-holder. Cf. jāgīr.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जागृ<BR>jāgṛ (CII 1), cf. [yūyaṃ] jāgṛta sampratipādayitum, ‘you<BR>would succeed in accomplishing [your duty]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाह्नवीवक्त्र<BR>jāhnavī-vaktra (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जल|जलं|जलः<BR>jala, cf. sa-jala-sthala (IE 8-5); the waters [in a village].<BR>(IE 7-1-2), used in the sense of jaladhi to indicate ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाल|जालं|जालः<BR>jāla (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309), cf. Sanskrit jālaka,<BR>‘a bunch of buds’; a load.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलधि|जलधिः<BR>jaladhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलदुर्ग<BR>jala-durga (ASLV), a fort surrounded by water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलजकरण्ड<BR>jalajakaraṇḍa (CITD), probably, some sort of drum which<BR>was either made of conch or shell or was shaped like a lotus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलकर<BR>jala-kara (IE 8-5; EI 4), ‘water-tax’ paid for fishing<BR>rights, etc., in tanks, lakes and rivers; sometimes wrongly read<BR>as jāta-kara (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 157, note 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलकरण<BR>jala-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘navy’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलक्रीडा<BR>jala-krīḍā (ASLV), water sports.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलनिधि|जलनिधिः<BR>jalanidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलपवित्र<BR>jala-pavitra (SII 3), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलाशय|जलाशयं|जलाशयः<BR>jal-āśaya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलयन्त्र|जलयंत्र<BR>jala-yantra (SII 2, 3), a water-lever.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलयात्रा<BR>jala-yātrā (IA 13), Jain; the festival of bathing a Tīrthaṅ-<BR>kara on the occasion of the consecration of an image or of the<BR>erection of a dhvaja-stambha or of the prevalence of a plague.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाली<BR>jālī (EI 5), a trellis window.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जमलिकाम्बलि<BR>jamalikāmbali (IA 18), also spelt yamalikāmbali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जमाथ<BR>jamātha (IA 11), Indianised form of Arabic jamā'at; the<BR>congregation of a community. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 144.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जम्बुद्वीप|जंबुद्वीप|जम्बुद्वीपः<BR>jambu-dvīpa, jambū-dvīpa (CII 1), used in the sense of<BR>‘the earth’ or the dominions of the Maurya emperor Aśoka;<BR>cf. pṛthivī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जन|जनः<BR>jana (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनपद|जनपदः<BR>janapada, jānapada (IE 8-3; EI 23, 33), people of the<BR>countryside; regarded by some as an official designation (EI<BR>26), and by others as a corporate body (EI 21).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनप्रधानिन्<BR>Jana-pradhānin (SITI), probably, a minister governing<BR>a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनेन्द्र|जनेंद्र|जनेन्द्रः<BR>Janendra (CII 3; IA 15), wrongly interpreted as ‘the<BR>lord of a people or tribe, a tribal ruler’; really, the same as<BR>Narendra, ‘a king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाङ्गल|जांगल|जाङ्गलं|जाङ्गलः<BR>jāṅgala (IA 18), cf. s-ānūpa-jāṅgala, an epithet of the gift<BR>land; either ‘arid’ or ‘covered with jungle’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्गम|जंगम|जङ्गमः<BR>jaṅgama, cf. sa-sthāvara jaṅgama (IE 8-5); the moveable<BR>belongings of a village.<BR>(SITI), a priest of the Liṅgāyat or Vīraśaiva sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्घा|जंघा<BR>jaṅghā (HRS), forced service as messenger, as indicated by<BR>the Jātakas; also same as Jaṅghākarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्घाकरिक|जङ्घाकरिकः<BR>Jaṅghākarika (HRS), ‘one who pays the royal dues by<BR>means of his legs’; ‘one who is liable to compulsory service as a<BR>messenger’, according to the Amarakośa. Same as Jaṅghā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्घाल|जंघाल|जङ्घालः<BR>jaṅghāla, an embankment (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाङ्घिक|जांघिक|जाङ्घिकः<BR>Jāṅghika (HRS), same as Jaṅghā or Jaṅghākarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जानी<BR>Jānī (EI 22), a corruption of Yājñika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनीनो<BR>janīno (IA 17), ‘kind to people’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनिथ<BR>janitha (EI 13), cf. sudhā-janitha-niḥsyandad-vapuḥ, ‘its<BR>body welling forth from nectarous sources’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जन्मभूमि<BR>janma-bhūmi, called janma-kkāṇi in Tamil (SITI), gift<BR>of land, probably made for the lifetime of a person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जन्मपत्र<BR>janma-patra (EI 1), a document recording the birth of<BR>a child prepared by an astrologer on payment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जानु<BR>jānu (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जात|जातं<BR>jāta (EI 2; CII 1), a living being.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातक|जातकं|जातकः<BR>jātaka (LL), Buddhist; birth-story [of one who is to be<BR>a Buddha in a future life]; story of a previous birth of Gautama<BR>Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातकक्कुडि<BR>jātaka-kkuḍi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; persons who have<BR>undertaken to serve for their lifetime in a temple, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातकर<BR>jāta-kara (IA 15), explained as ‘a tax on things grown’;<BR>a mistake for or misreading of jala-kara (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातकर्मन्|जातकर्म्मन्<BR>jāta-karman (EI 4), a ceremony performed at the birth of<BR>a child.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाति|जातिः<BR>jāti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातिसिद्धाय<BR>jāti-siddh-āya (SITI), communal tax payable in coin;<BR>cf. inavari or inavari-kkāśu of Tamil inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जटिल|जटिलः<BR>Jaṭila (LL), an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातिस्मरणज्ञान<BR>jāti-smaraṇa-jñāna (HA), knowledge of previous births.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातीय|जातीयः<BR>jātīya, cf. jñātīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जतुक|जतुकं<BR>jatuka (EI 2), a bat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जौहर्<BR>jauhar (IA 29), javhar (IA 6), Rājasthānī; funeral pile;<BR>commitment of suicide en masse; same as sākā or śākā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जया<BR>jayā (IA 23), hemp.<BR>(EI 12), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयधर<BR>Jayadhara (IE8-2), royal title; translated from Greek Nikephoros.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयघण्टा<BR>jaya-ghaṇṭā (EI 15; IA 12), a gong.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जायाम्य<BR>jāyāmya (IA 19), a kind of charm.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयनपति<BR>Jayanapati (EI 13), probably, an officer in charge of<BR>armour or the armoury. Cf. jayanaśālā-karaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयनशालाकरण<BR>jayanaśālā-karaṇa cf. karaṇa (LP), explained as ‘the armour<BR>department’. Cf. Jayanapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयन्तपुर<BR>jayantapura (EI 4), probably, the same as brahmapurī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयन्ती|जयंती<BR>jayantī (EI 9, IA 26), the twelfth tithi; the 12th tithi of<BR>a lunar month joined with the Punarvasu nakṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयन्तीव्रत<BR>jayantī-vrata (IA 6), a festival in which maṇḍapanirmāṇa-<BR>jāgaraṇa-pratimādān-ādi (erection of a shed, watching through<BR>the night, distribution of images, etc.) take place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयपाल|जयपालः<BR>Jayapāla (SITI), a class of merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जायापर<BR>Jāyāpara (LL), probably, a householder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयपत्र|जयपत्रं<BR>jaya-patra, jayarekha-patra (SITI), a certificate of victory<BR>in a dispute; a copy of the judgement. See jayarekha-patrikā.<BR>(EI 5), a certificate of success.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयरेखपत्रिका<BR>jayarekha-patrikā (ASLV), a certificate of victory. See<BR>jayapatra, jayarekha-patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयस्कन्धावार<BR>jaya-skandhāvāra (EI 30, 33; CII 3; BL) ‘camp of victory’;<BR>the royal camp or capital; epithet of royal camps or residences;<BR>same as skandhāvāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयस्तम्भ|जयस्तंभ|जयस्तम्भः<BR>jaya-stambha (EI 23, 30, 33; CII 4; SII 1, 11-1), a pillar<BR>of victory; cf. dharma-jaya-stambha (IA 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयिक<BR>jayika (IE 8-8), the party that comes off victorious in a<BR>dispute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जेमक<BR>jemaka (IE 8-5; EI 25, 28), melas or food which the<BR>villagers were obliged to provide to the royal officers on tour;<BR>the obligation of the villagers to provide food to such officers;<BR>wrongly explained by some as ‘a tax for the boarding of touring<BR>royal officers’ (CII 4). Cf. Marāṭhī jevā, ‘a feed, a meal; sub-<BR>sistence which the villagers were bound to provide for the<BR>subordinate servants or Peons when sent to receive the collec-<BR>tions’ (Wilson's Glossary, s. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जेन<BR>jena (CITD), Telugu; a span (about 7 inches).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जेना<BR>Jenā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 304), Oḏiyā; ‘a prince’;<BR>a title of nobility; later stereotyped as a family name in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

झम्पिन्|झंपिन्<BR>jhampin (EI 12), ‘excelling’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

झाट|झाटः<BR>jhāṭa (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 183), a shrub, wood or thicket;<BR>Bengali jhāḏ; a bush; used in sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa (EI 27).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

झाटविटप<BR>jhāṭa-viṭapa (EI 8-5), bushes and shrubs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिलो<BR>jilo, jiḻo, jīlo (Chamba), a land measure. Cf. aḷu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिन|जिनः<BR>Jina, same as Tīrthaṅkara.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyfour’.<BR>(LL), an epithet of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनभवन<BR>jina-bhavana (EI 24), a Jain temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनकल्पिन्<BR>Jina-kalpin (HA), a Jain monk practising rigorous<BR>austerities like those practised by the Jinas before their attain-<BR>ment of kevala-jñāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनमातृ<BR>Jina-mātṛ (HA), the mother of a Jina.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिननगर<BR>jina-nagara, cf. Tamil śinakaram (SITI), a Jaina temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिननिगम<BR>jina-nigama (EI 24), a township in the possession of a<BR>Jain temple or, more probably, a Jain temple (cf. jina-<BR>nagara).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनयुग्म<BR>Jina-yugma (HA), an image showing two Tīrthaṅkaras;<BR>a pair of Jina images.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णश्रेष्ठिश्रीमल्लप्रिय<BR>jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-śrīmalla-priya (LP), name of a coin struck by<BR>the old Śreṣṭhin named Śrīmalla. Cf. śreṣṭhijīrṇa-viśvamalla-<BR>priya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय<BR>jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya (LP), literally, ‘the favourite (coin)<BR>of old Viśvamalla’; name of a coin. Cf. jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-śrīmalla-<BR>priya and śreṣṭhi-jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya; also cf. vīsalapriya-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णोद्धार|जीर्णोद्धारः<BR>jīrṇ-oddhāra (EI 23, 26; HA), repairs or renovation and<BR>conservation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जित|जितः<BR>jita, jīta (EI 28, 29), income or wages; revenue income;<BR>derived from Sanskrit jīvita in the same sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीतल्<BR>jītal (SII 1), a copper coin; Indianised as jithala; (1/48)th<BR>of a silver ṭaṅka of the Delhi Sulṯāns (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 44);<BR>sometimes regarded as a copper coin equal to (1/3) of a silver<BR>tār which was itself equal to (1/8) of a gold fanam (SII, Vol. I,<BR>p. 161); also called dehlīwāl (Num. Supl., No. 38, p. 33).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जितंभगवता<BR>jitaṃ bhagavatā, also quoted as jitaṃ Viṣṇunā (CII 3, etc.);<BR>‘victory has been achieved by the Divine One, i. e. Viṣṇu’;<BR>an invocation used at the commencement of certain ins-<BR>criptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीथल<BR>jīthala, same as jītal. See JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 197.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवलोक|जीवलोकः<BR>jīva-loka (EI 3), a village institution of uncertain mean-<BR>ing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवन|जीवनं|जीवनः<BR>jīvana (SITI), maintenance; cf. jīvaṇa-śiṣa. See also<BR>bhṛtyebhyo jīvanam kartuṃ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 109-10).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवनशेष<BR>jīvana-śeṣa (SITI), maintenance. Cf. jīvana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवपुत्रा<BR>Jīva-putrā, Prakrit Jīva-putā (EI 24), a lady whose son is<BR>(or, sons are) still living.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवित|जीवितं<BR>jīvita (EI 28; SII 13; ASLV; SITI), maintenance; in-<BR>come or wages; also called jīvita-ppaṟṟu, jita and jīta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिवितक्कारर्<BR>Jivita-kkārar (SITI), persons in enjoyment of lands in the<BR>jīvita (maintenance) tenure; a class of officials enjoying jīvita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीयर्<BR>Jīyar (EI 25; SITI), an ascetic (sannyāsin) looking after<BR>the affairs of a temple; same as Maṭh-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्ञानदीक्षा<BR>jñāna-dīkṣā (EI 32), a kind of initiation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्ञापक<BR>jñāpaka (SITI; ASLV), remembrancer; memorandum<BR>of events and happenings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्ञातिय<BR>jñātiya (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, pp. 208, 229), used in the sense<BR>of jātīya; e. g. Prāgvāṭa-jñātīya=Prāgvāṭa-jātīya (i. e. ‘belonging<BR>to the Prāgvāṭa community).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जो<BR>Jo (EI 30), an abbreviation of Joṣī, same as Jyotiṣin, an<BR>astrologer or astronomer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोड|जोडः<BR>joḍa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 19), used in some East<BR>Indian records in the sense of ‘a canal’. Cf. joṭī, jolaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोलक<BR>jolaka (EI 4), a canal; same as Bengali jolā; cf. joḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोषी<BR>Joṣī (EI 30), modification of Sanskrit Jyotiṣin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोटी<BR>joṭī, same as joṭikā (EI 28), a stream.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोटिका<BR>joṭikā (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253, text line 37), a canal;<BR>same as joḍa and joṭī or joḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जूहक<BR>jūhaka (EI 3), a village institution of uncertain meaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्वलन|ज्वलनः<BR>jvalana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठाधिकरणिक<BR>Jyeṣṭh-ādhikaraṇika (EI 18, 31), explained as ‘the chief<BR>judge’; senior officer, chief officer of a class, or officer in charge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठदेवर<BR>Jyeṣṭha-devara (LP), elder brother of the husband.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठकायस्थ<BR>Jyeṣṭha-kāyastha (IE 8-3; EI 4, 24), the chief scribe, or the<BR>foreman of the Kāyastha class, or the scribe-member of the<BR>board of administration; explained as ‘the senior registrar’<BR>(EI 31). Cf. Prathama-kāyastha, Paṭvārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठपिता<BR>Jyeṣṭha-pitā, elder brother of one's father.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठिकाग्राम<BR>jyeṣṭhikā-grāma (CII 4), ‘the chief village’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्योतिस्कन्ध<BR>jyoti-skandha (CII 1), masses of light; cf. agni-skandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्योतिष्टोम|ज्योतिष्टोमः<BR>jyotiṣṭoma (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः<BR>ka (IE 8-1), for kā (in Kharoṣṭhī), abbreviation of kāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

का<BR>kā (PJS), abbreviation of kārita and kāritā (especially in<BR>medieval Jain inscriptions); also of Kāyastha; also of kāṇḍa,<BR>‘a cluster’ (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कचकदा<BR>kacakadā (LP), Gujarātī; tortoise-shell.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कच्छ|कच्छं|कच्छः<BR>kaccha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 177), a field bordering on a<BR>stream; land near a well (Ep. Ind., Vol XXXIV, p. 175, line 15).<BR>(EI 22), a resolution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कच्छक<BR>kacchaka (EI 19), a low hill.<BR>(IA 18), wrongly read also as kasthaka; cf. khalaka-<BR>kacchaka-bhūmī-sahitā as an epithet of the gift land; probably,<BR>‘land around a well’. See kūpaṃ khalakaṃ kacchakaṃ (Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. XVIII, p. 114, text line 55, cf. line 43); also kūpa-kaccha<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 175, text line 15).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कच्छप|कच्छपः<BR>kacchapa, cf. sa-matsya-kacchapa (IE 8-5); tortoise; see jala-<BR>kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडा<BR>kaḏā (IE 8-6; EI 19), Bengali; the cowrie-shell regarded<BR>as a coin; a small area of land; one-fourth of a gaṇḍā and one-<BR>eightieth of a paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कदरु<BR>kadaru (CII 4), same as kṛdara; a granary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कड्ढक<BR>kaḍḍhaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably the same as Sanskrit<BR>karṣaka; see ḍheṅku-kaḍḍhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कादि<BR>kādi (EI 28), a grain measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडितामात्य<BR>Kaḍit-āmātya (EI 23), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; official desig-<BR>nation; same as Kaḍita-vĕrgaḍĕ (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडितवेर्गडे<BR>Kaḍita-vĕrgaḍĕ (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; superintendent of<BR>accounts and records; same as Akṣapaṭalika; sometimes also<BR>called Mahāpradhāna, Hĕrisandhivigrahin, Senādhipati, etc., addi-<BR>tionally. See Kaḍit-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडीय<BR>Kaḍīya (LP), a bricklayer or mason; cf. Gujarātī Kaḍīyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहल|काहलं|काहलः<BR>kāhala, kāhalā (EI 24; IA 15), a musical instrument;<BR>a trumpet. See kākala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहण<BR>kāhaṇa, kāhāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 29), Bengali-Oḏiyā; modified<BR>forms of kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कै<BR>kai (IE 8-6), Dravidian; same as hasta, ‘cubit’; a unit<BR>of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कइसर<BR>Kaïsara (EI 26), title of a Kuṣāna king; derived from<BR>Roman Caesar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कैटाल<BR>kaiṭāla (IA 12), a castanet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कैवर्तभोग<BR>kaivarta-bhoga (IE 8-5), fishermens’ preserve.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काक|काकं|काकः<BR>kāka (IE 8-6), same as kākinī.<BR>(EI 14), name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकबिन्दु<BR>kāka-bindu (SII 2), name of a flaw in diamonds.<BR>(SITI), a black dot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकल|काकलं|काकलः<BR>kākala (IA 12), a trumpet. See kāhala, kāhalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककलि<BR>kakali (IE 3-4), paper; same as kakari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकणी<BR>kākaṇī, kākaṇikā (EI 15), same as kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकपद|काकपदः<BR>kākapada, kākapāda (SII 2), name of a flaw in diamonds;<BR>a mark indicating omission of letters written outside the line.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककरि<BR>kakari (IE 3-4), paper; same as kakali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकवृन्त<BR>kāka-vṛnta (SII 2), a variety of diamond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकिनी<BR>kākinī (IE 8-6), also called kāka.<BR>(IE 8-6), a small land measure; cf. kānī.<BR>(IE 8-8; EI 1; CII 4), name of a small coin; equal to 20<BR>cowrie-shells according to the Līlāvatī; (1/4) of a paṇa according<BR>to the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K. V. Ranga-<BR>swami Aiyangar, p. 125).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककुभ|ककुभः<BR>kakubha (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कला<BR>kalā (IE 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काल|कालं|कालः<BR>kāla (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR>(CII 3, etc.), time, a period of time; used in the sense of<BR>‘an era’; cf. kāl-ānuvartamāna-saṃvatsara (Select Inscriptions, p.<BR>270, text lines 3-4), etc. See prakāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलभशालाकरण<BR>kalabhaśālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the camel<BR>department’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालचक्र|कालचक्रं<BR>kāla-cakra, a mechanical weapon placed at the gate of<BR>forts according to the Vasudevahiṇḍī (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No.<BR>1, p. 15). See śataghnī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालाक्षरित<BR>kāl-ākṣarita (LP), probably, ‘a word of censure passed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलम्<BR>kalam (EI 28), a grain measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलम्ब|कलंब|कलंबः|कलम्बः<BR>kalamba (EI 12), an arrow; ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलन|कलनं|कलनः<BR>kalana, a betelnut plantation (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX,<BR>p. 205).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः<BR>kal13añju (IE 8-8; EI 28, 30; SITI), Tamil; name of a<BR>gold coin; also of the equivalent weight; about 32 ratis (JNSI,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 141).<BR>Cf. ūr-kal13añju (EI 28), name of a coin.<BR>(SII 13), same as suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलापच्छन्द<BR>kalāpacchanda (SII 2), name of an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलस|कलसः<BR>kalasa (CITD), a vase, flagon or water-pot; an orna-<BR>mental piece of painted wood, stone, brass, etc., fixed on the<BR>spires of temples, carts, etc.; a rounded pinnacle or ball on the<BR>top of a temple; a dome.<BR>(EI 5), the pinnacle of a temple; same as kumbha.<BR>(EI 11, 33), a measure; cf. droṇa.<BR>(SII 3), a pot.<BR>(EI 33), also called kalasikā; probably, the same as droṇa;<BR>a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालसन्धि<BR>kāla-sandhi (SII 1), same as trikāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलसी<BR>kalasī (LP), a measure of capacity equal to sixteen maunds;<BR>cf. kalasikā, kalasikāvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलसिका<BR>kalasikā (EI 33), same as kalasī or kalasa; probably the<BR>same as droṇa; cf. kalasikāvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलसिकावाप<BR>kalasikāvāpa (EI 33), a land measure; originally, a plot<BR>of land on which one kalasī measure of seed could be sown;<BR>cf. droṇavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलत्र|कलत्रं<BR>kalatra (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलवाड<BR>Kalavāḍa, Kalavāḍā, Kālavāḍa, Kālavāḍā (EI 24),<BR>same as Kālavāḻa, Kālavāḻā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालवाल<BR>Kālavāḻa, Kālavāḻā (EI 24), designation of uncertain<BR>meaning if it is not the same as Sanskrit Kalyapāla, a vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालिगणत्तार्<BR>kāḻi-gaṇattār (SITI), Tamil; a committee for the temple<BR>of Kāḻi (Kālī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलिका<BR>kalikā (LP), quarrel; cf. Gujarātī kali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलिकावलिक<BR>kalikāvalika (LP), a quarrel; cf. kalikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलिङ्गवारियम्<BR>kaliṅga-vāriyam (SITI), Tamil; committee looking after<BR>the sluice; derived from kaliṅgu, ‘a sluice’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काल्म<BR>kāl-maṟuturu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of<BR>land. Cf. maṟuturu, ghaḍa-maṟuturu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्नाडु<BR>kal-nāḍu (SITI), Tamil; a hero-stone; setting up of a<BR>hero-stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्प|कल्पः<BR>kalpa (CII 1), same as saṃvarta-kalpa, the aeon of des-<BR>truction.<BR>(CII 3, etc.), name of a fabulous tree in Indra's paradise,<BR>supposed to grant all desires.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्पादि|कल्पादिः<BR>kalpādi (EI 5; IA 18), name applied to certain tithis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्पाल<BR>Kalpāla (EI 30), also called Kalvapāla, Kalyapāla, Kalyā-<BR>pāla; a distiller of liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालु<BR>kālu (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; ‘one foot’; a unit of measure-<BR>ment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्वपाल<BR>Kalvapāla (EI 30), same as Kalpāla, etc.; a vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्वपालवारिक<BR>Kalvapāla-vārika (IE 8-8), official designation indica-<BR>ting a spirit-distiller.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याण|कल्याणं<BR>kalyāṇa (CII 1), a good deed which is beneficial to the<BR>people; a ceremony to bring health and prosperity to a person<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 147); cf. maṅgala in the same<BR>senses.<BR>(EI 19), a festival (especially, marriage); cf. kalyāṇa-<BR>maṇdapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणागम<BR>kalyāṇ-āgama (CII 1), ‘having pure knowledge’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणधन<BR>kalyāṇa-dhana (HRS), tax levied for the expenses of festi-<BR>vals or for the performance of rites to avert evil. Cf. prathama-<BR>kalyāṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 147).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणक<BR>kalyāṇaka (HA), a chief auspicious event in the life of a<BR>Tīrthaṅkara, there being five such events, viz. cyavana or des-<BR>cent from heaven, janma or birth, dīkṣā or initiation as monk,<BR>jñāna or attainment of kevala-jñāna, and mokṣa or nirvāṇa, i. e.<BR>death which means freedom from the last bondage in the life<BR>of a Jina. See kalyāṇikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणसुन्दर<BR>Kalyāṇasundara, Śiva represented as marrying Umā<BR>Haimavatī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणी<BR>kalyāṇī (EI 8), a square pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणिका<BR>kalyāṇikā (EI 8), a festival.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-141" target="_blank">Page-141+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 11), certain auspicious days with the Jains. Cf.<BR>kalyāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्यपाल|कल्यपालः<BR>Kalyapāla, Kalyāpāla (EI 30), same as Kalpāla, etc.; a<BR>vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्यश्रेष्ठिन्<BR>Kalya-śreṣṭhin (IA 18), a dealer in liquors, Kalya being<BR>an abbreviation of Kalyapāla, or a word meaning ‘distillery’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काम|कामं|कामः<BR>kāma (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामधेनु|कामधेनुः<BR>kāma-dhenu (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामकोष्ठ<BR>kāma-koṣṭha, cf. kāma-kkoṭṭam (SITI), a shrine of the goddess<BR>Pārvatī as an adjunct of the Śiva temple in the same compound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कमलपूजा<BR>kamala-pūjā (BL), probably, worship of a deity with<BR>lotuses or flowers of gold or silver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामलि<BR>kāmali (EI 24), often written as kambalin, which<BR>means ‘a bull’; a levy probably on prize bullocks (cf.<BR>vara-balīvarda). Cf. yamali-kambali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामत|कामतः<BR>kāmata (EI 21; CII 4), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामावचर<BR>kām-āvacara (IA 10), Buddhist; belonging to the domain<BR>of sensual pleasure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्ब<BR>kamba, kambha (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; name of a land<BR>measure; see kamma and stambha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्बल|कंबल|कम्बलं|कंबलः|कम्बलः<BR>kambala (IA 23), an agricultural ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्बलिन्|कंबलिन्<BR>kambalin (EI 24), ‘a bull’; a levy probably on prize<BR>bullocks (cf. vara-balīvarda); see kāmali and yamali-kambali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कंदासघूट<BR>kaṃdāsaghūṭa (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काम्गार्<BR>Kāmgār (BL), an official designation meaning a servant,<BR>a manager, a public officer; a person employed on public works.<BR>Cf. Wilson's Glossary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्म<BR>kamma (IE 8-6; EI 12, 19), Kannaḍa; same as stambha=<BR>skambha; a land measure equal to one-hundredth of a mattaru<BR>or nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्मालर्<BR>kammāḻar (SITI), Tamil; the five artisan classes; also<BR>called añju pañcālattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पल<BR>kampala (ASLV), same as kampaṇa; name of an adminis-<BR>trative division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पन|कंपन|कम्पनं|कम्पनः<BR>kampana, kampanā (IE 8-3), the army [in ancient<BR>Kashmir]; cf. Kampanapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पण<BR>kampaṇa (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit like a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनाधिपति<BR>Kampan-ādhipati (HD), commander-in-chief [in ancient<BR>Kashmir]; same as Kampanapati, etc. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 447;<BR>VII. 1362, 1366.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनपति<BR>Kampanapati (IE 8-3), same as Kampan-ādhipati, etc.;<BR>commander-in-chief [in ancient Kashmir].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनापति<BR>Kampanāpati (HD), same as Kampan-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनेश<BR>Kampaneśa (HD), same as Kampan-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनोद्ग्राहक<BR>Kampan-odgrāhaka (HD), probably, collector of levies<BR>for the army. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 1430.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कंसकार|कंसकारः<BR>Kaṃsakāra (EI 1, 19, 23), also called Kaṃsāra, Kāṃsāra;<BR>same as Kāṃsyakāra, ‘a brazier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कंसार|कंसारं<BR>Kaṃsāra, Kāṃsāra (EI 23), same as Kāṃsyakāra. See<BR>Kāṃsāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कांसारक<BR>Kāṃsāraka (BL), a worker in bell metal; a brazier. See<BR>Kaṃsāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कांस्यकार|कांस्यकारः<BR>Kāṃsyakāra (EI 19, 32), a worker in bell-metal; a brazier.<BR>See Kaṃsāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्<BR>kan (EI 12), to glitter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणभक्तक<BR>kaṇa-bhaktaka (LP), undressed provisions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक<BR>kaṇaka (LP), grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकहय<BR>kanaka-haya (EI 24), same as hiraṇy-āśva; name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकमणितुलापुरुष<BR>kanakamaṇi-tulāpuruṣa (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकसभापति<BR>Kanakasabhāpati (EI 3), ‘the god worshipped in the<BR>Kanakasabhā’, i. e. Naṭarāja Śiva in the Chidambaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकतुलापुरुष<BR>kanaka-tulāpuruṣa (EI 16; BL), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक्कक्काणि<BR>kaṇakka-kkāṇi (SITI), Tamil; cf. kaṇakka-ppeṟu; land<BR>set apart for the village accountant, Kaṇakka being the<BR>same as Sanskrit Gaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक्कप्पे<BR>kaṇakka-ppeṟu (SITI), Tamil; cf. kaṇakka-kkāṇi; tax,<BR>payable in grains, for the maintenance of the village<BR>accountant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणम्<BR>kāṇam (EI 21, 28; SII 3; SITI), Tamil; name of a coin;<BR>a gold coin; a weight; a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनरेसे<BR>Kanarese, see Kannaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काञ्चनमेदिनी<BR>kāñcana-medinī (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काञ्चनतुला<BR>kāñcana-tulā (EI 23), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कञ्चोल<BR>kañcola (IA 15), same as kañcūla; a bodice or waistcoat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कञ्चूल|कंचूलं<BR>kañcūla, same as kañcola (IA 15), a bodice or waist-coat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्द|कंद|कंदं|कन्दं|कंदः|कन्दः<BR>kanda (CITI), name of a metre common in Telugu<BR>and Kannaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्दाचार<BR>kandācāra (ASLV), the military department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्दल|कंदल|कंदलं|कन्दलं|कंदलः|कन्दलः<BR>kandala (LP), controversy; beating (from Sanskrit kand,<BR>to strike).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काण्डपति<BR>Kāṇḍapati (IE 8-3); EI 31), an official designation of<BR>uncertain import; probably ‘the custodian of the arrows or the<BR>armoury’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काण्डपटिक<BR>kāṇḍapaṭika (EI 9), probably, a quiver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्डार<BR>kaṇḍāra, Prakrit; cf. utkṛ, ‘to engrave’. See kaṇḍāraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्डारण<BR>kaṇḍāraṇa, Kannaḍa; carving or engraving; see Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XVI, p. 36.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कान्दिशीक|कांदिशीक|कान्दिशीकः<BR>kāndiśīka (EI 13; LP), frightened; eager to flee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्दुक|कंदुक|कंदुकं|कंदुकः|कन्दुकः<BR>kanduka (EI 1), probably, a sugar-boiler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्डूल|कंडूल|कण्डूलः<BR>kaṇḍūla (EI 14), ‘itching’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानी<BR>kānī (IE 8-6), Bengali; a land measure equal to one-<BR>sixteenth of a Doṇ; cf. kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणि<BR>kāṇi (IE 8-6; EI 24, 28, 30; SII 3) Tamil; a land measure<BR>equal to one-eightieth of a veli.<BR>(SITI), Tamil; a weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानिक<BR>kānika (IE 8-5), Tamil; also spelt kānuka; same as<BR>kāṇika. (EI 33), also called kānikĕ or kānikĕ-kappa in Kannaḍa;<BR>tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिक<BR>kāṇika (IE 8-5), same as Kannaḍa kāṇika-kānĕ, kāṇikĕ-<BR>kappa or kappa-kānikĕ, ‘presents from an inferior to a<BR>superior’, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानिके<BR>kānikĕ, kānikĕ-kappa (EI 33), Kannaḍa; same as<BR>kānika; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिके<BR>kāṇikĕ, kāṇiki (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a land measure<BR>of 57000 square feet; sixty-fourth part [especially of any coin];<BR>also (1/8) or (1/34) part; a visit; a present or gift. See<BR>kānuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणिक्का<BR>kaṇikkā (IE 8-8), same as Sanskrit kaṇikā, common<BR>seed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणिक्कै<BR>kaṇikkai (EI 17), kāṇikkai (EI 21; SITI), a voluntary<BR>offering; a present offered like nazarāna; presents or customary<BR>payments to the king and other high officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्काणि<BR>Kaṇkāṇi (EI 25; SII 2), Tamil; overseer; cf. Māhe-<BR>śvara-Kaṇkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कङ्कट|कंकट|कंकटः|कङ्कटः<BR>kaṅkaṭa (EI 9; IA 18), boundary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्नड<BR>Kannaḍa, written in English as Kanarese; language and<BR>alphabet of the Kannaḍṙgas, i. e. the people of Karṇāta (Sans-<BR>krit form of Kannada).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्नडसन्धिविग्रहिन्<BR>Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), ‘the Sandhivigrahin of<BR>the Kannaḍa (Karṇāṭa) country’; cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्नदिग<BR>Kannadiga, see Kannada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्टक|कंटक|कंटकं|कंटकः|कण्टकः<BR>kaṇṭaka, cf. catuṣ-kaṇṭaka-viśuddha (EI 23), same as<BR>catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha; probably, ‘the boundary demarcated by<BR>planting thorny shrubs’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्टकशोधना<BR>kaṇṭaka-śodhanā (SITI), criminal justice; cf. the Madras<BR>Museum plates of Jaṭilavarman Parāntaka-pāṇḍya and the<BR>Arthaśāstra of Kauṭilya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्ठिका|कंठिका<BR>kaṇṭhikā (EI 4, 25, 31; SII 1), a necklace; the emblem of<BR>heir-apparency.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्ठिकापट्टबन्ध<BR>kaṇṭhikā-paṭṭa-bandha (IA 11), the ceremony of anointing<BR>the Yuvarāja with a necklace which was his sign.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानुक<BR>kānuka (CITD), Telugu; an offering or courtesy made in<BR>homage to a superior or a god. See kāṇikĕ, etc.<BR>(EI 33), same as kānika, tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्यादान|कन्यादानं<BR>kanyā-dāna (SII 1), giving a daughter in marriage.<BR>(EI 29; ASLV), a form of marriage in which bride-<BR>price was not demanded or paid; offering one's daughter in<BR>marriage without demanding bride-price.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्याधर्म<BR>kanyā-dharma (EI 25), same as kanyā-dāna-dharma, the<BR>gift of a girl in marriage without demanding bride-price.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपहडी<BR>kapahaḏī (Chamba), field meant for growing cotton only.<BR>Cf. kaphāḏī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपालसन्धि|कपालसंधि|कपालसंधिः<BR>kapāla-sandhi (CII 4), a peace treaty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कापालिका<BR>kāpālikā (EI 3), a cloud [of dust].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्द|कपर्दः|कपर्द्द|कपर्द्दः<BR>kaparda (CII 4), also called kapardī, kapardaka, etc.;<BR>cowrie-shell used as coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दक|कपर्दकः|कपर्द्दक|कपर्द्दकः<BR>kapardaka (EI 1), a cowrie-shell used as coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकपुराण<BR>kapardaka-purāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 14, 21), ‘a purāṇa [of silver]<BR>counted in cowrie-shells’. Cf. paṇa-purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकवोडि<BR>kapardaka-voḍi (EI 23), a cowrie-shell used as coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दी|कपर्द्दी<BR>kapardī, kapardikā (EI 9; CII 4), a cowrie-shell used as<BR>coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कफाडी<BR>kaphāḏī (Chamba), same as kapahaḏī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपिला<BR>kapilā (BL), a kind of cow.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपिलषष्ठी<BR>Kapila-ṣaṣṭhī (EI 25), cf. Kapila-caṭṭi (EI 5), name of a<BR>tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कप्प<BR>kappa (EI 33), Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit śulka or kara.<BR>(SITI), Tamil-Telugu-Kannaḍa; periodical and custo-<BR>mary payments by persons engaged in some professions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर|करः<BR>kara (IE 8-5), explained by a commentator as ‘the dues<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-145" target="_blank">Page-145+ 40</a>]<BR>(bhāga) to be realised by the king for the enjoyment of royal<BR>land by using it for cultivation and for grazing cattle’; tax in<BR>general.<BR>(IE 8-5) rent or tax to be paid in grains when mentioned<BR>side by side with hiraṇya.<BR>(HRS), tax in general, according to the lexicons; accord-<BR>ing to the Arthaśāstra, (1) periodical tax over and above the<BR>king's customary grain-share; (2) emergency tax levied upon<BR>the villagers over and above the normal grain-share; (3)<BR>tax upon merchants' profits.<BR>(EI 29; Chamba; CITD), a tax or impost; royal revenue;<BR>rent, dues; toll, tribute.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करघटिका<BR>karaghaṭikā (EI 2), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करग्राम<BR>kara-grāma (ASLV; SITI), a revenue-paying or ryotwari<BR>village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करैयीदु<BR>karaiyīdu (ASLV), system of periodical redistribution<BR>of lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारक|कारकं|कारकः<BR>kāraka (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR>Cf. Prakrit Karavaka (EI 12), same as Prakrit Kārāpaka;<BR>superintendent of the construction of a building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करकच|करकचः<BR>karakaca (LP), ‘talk that may annoy the hearer’; cf.<BR>Gujarātī kackac.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कराकरकरण<BR>karākara-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करण|करणं|करणः<BR>Karaṇa (EI 4), an accountant.<BR>(EI 28; HD), a clerk; a scribe. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII,<BR>p. 155.<BR>(EI 19), same as Marāṭhī Kulkarṇī.<BR>(SITI), a type of law-court lower in rank than an<BR>adhikaraṇa.<BR>(IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28, 30), same as or a shortened form of<BR>adhikaraṇa; a court of law.<BR>(IE 8-3), an office or department.<BR>(CII 4), a committee.<BR>(LP), a department, according to the editors of the<BR>Lekhapaddhati, the thirtytwo karaṇas or departments being the<BR>following; śrī-karaṇa, vyaya-karaṇa, dharm-ādhikaraṇa, maṇḍapikā-<BR>karaṇa, velākula-karaṇa, jala-karaṇa, [sthala] patha-karaṇa, ghaṭi-<BR>kāgṛha-karaṇa, ṭaṅkaśālā-karaṇa, dravya-bhāṇdāra-karaṇa, aṃśuka-<BR>bhāṇdāra-karaṇa, vārigṛha-karaṇa, devaveśma-karaṇa, gaṇikā-karaṇa,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-146" target="_blank">Page-146+ 40</a>]<BR>karaṇa, hastiśālā-karaṇa, aśvaśālā-karaṇa, kalabhaśālā-karaṇa, śreṇi-<BR>karaṇa, vyāpāra-karaṇa, tantra-karaṇa, koṣṭhāgāra-karaṇa, upakrama-<BR>karaṇa, karākara-karaṇa, sthāna-karaṇa, deva-karaṇa, sandhi [vigraha]-<BR>karaṇa, mahākṣapāla-karaṇa, mahārasa-karaṇa, jayanaśālā-karaṇa.,<BR>sattrāgāra-karaṇa, antaḥpura-[karaṇa] and koṣṭhikā-[karaṇa].<BR>(CII 3, 4), a document.<BR>Cf. Karaṇam (SII 1; SITI), Tamil; also spelt Karṇam;<BR>a document; an accountant, also called Kaṇakkaṉ or Karaṇikka.<BR>(IA 17), name of the half of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारण|कारणं<BR>kāraṇa, cf. ahaṃ kāraṇaṃ karomi (LP), ‘I shall prove’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणदण्ड<BR>karaṇa-daṇḍa (SITI), fine imposed by the karaṇa (court).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणक<BR>Kāraṇaka (EI 32), a scribe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणकर्मन्<BR>karaṇa-karman (EI 30), the profession of the scribe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणकायस्थ<BR>Karaṇa-kāyastha (EI 7; HD; BL), official designation of a<BR>scribe; a writer of legal documents. Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St.,<BR>p. 133.<BR>(IE 8-3), mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणपूजा<BR>kāraṇa-pūjā (IA 9), translated as ‘occasional worship’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणत्तार्<BR>Karaṇattār (SII 12), same as Kāraṇavan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणवन्<BR>Kāraṇavan (SITI), Tamil; an accountant; also called<BR>Kāraṇika and Karaṇattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिक<BR>Karaṇika (CII 4; BL), official designation of a scribe; the<BR>writer of legal documents; explained by some as ‘an officer<BR>in charge of a State department or office’ (HD); but really,<BR>a scribe. Cf. karaṇika-ṭhakkura (i. e. a Karaṇika who enjoyed the<BR>dignity of a Ṭhakkura) in Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, p. 44; Vol. VIII,<BR>p. 158; and Karaṇika-Brāhmaṇa (i. e. a Karaṇika who belonged<BR>to the Brāhmaṇa community) in Bhandarkar's List, No. 350.<BR>See Mahākaraṇika.<BR>(EI 6; ASLV), same as Korṇam or Senabova; a village<BR>accountant.<BR>Cf. Vāśal-karaṇikam (SITI), same as Vāśal-kaṇakkam<BR>(°gaṇaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणिक|कारणिकः<BR>Kāraṇika (EI 31), same as Karaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिक्कजोडि<BR>Karaṇikka-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), the quit-rent of the Karaṇam<BR>or Karṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिकठक्कुर<BR>Karaṇika-ṭhakkura (EI 33), see Karaṇika and Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिन्<BR>Karaṇin (HD), same as Karaṇika. Cf. karaṇi-parikara<BR>(Harṣacarita, VII, para. 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करङ्क|करंक|करंकः|करङ्कः<BR>karaṅka (EI 30), a cup made of coconut shell, used in<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-147" target="_blank">Page-147+ 40</a>]<BR>measuring liquids; a karaṅka measure; also the same as tāmbūla-<BR>karaṅka (the king's betel-box). Cf. Karaṅkika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करङ्किक<BR>Karaṅkika (EI 13), officer in charge of the karaṅka (i. e.<BR>tāmbūla-karaṅka or the king's betel-box).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारापक|कारापकः<BR>Kārāpaka (EI 19; IA 19), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit<BR>Kāraka; an agent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करशासन<BR>kara-śāsana (EI 29, 33), charter recording a grant of land<BR>for which the donee had to pay rent; a grant for which<BR>revenue (either in full or at a concessional rate) was fixed; land<BR>granted in the said way.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करटिका<BR>karaṭikā, cf. karaḍigai (SII 13), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करवृन्द<BR>karavṛnda (SITI), a variety of diamond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिक<BR>Karika (Ep. Ind., Vol XIII, p. 119, text line 8), official<BR>designation; probably a mistake for Tarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिणीभ्रमण<BR>kariṇī-bhramaṇa (EI 24, 25), ‘taking the she-elephant<BR>around’; a ceremony in fixing the boundaries; cf. piḍi~śūl13ndu<BR>(SITI), walking around by a female elephant to mark the<BR>boundary of the gift land, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिणीपरिभ्रमण<BR>kariṇī-paribhramaṇa (EI 15), same as kariṇī-bhramaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करीष|करीषं|करीषः<BR>karīṣa (IA 9), name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करितुरगपत्तनाकरस्थानगोकुलाधिकारिन्<BR>Kari-turaga-pattan-ākarasthāna-gokul-ādhikārin (EI 18, 24, 33),<BR>designation of an officer (or designations of several officers)<BR>in charge of elephants, horses, townships, mines and cowpens.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करितुरगपट्टसाहणि<BR>Kari-turaga-paṭṭasāhaṇi (EI 5), military officer (or<BR>officers) in charge of the elephant force and cavalry. Sāhaṇi is<BR>the same as Sādhanika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करितुरगोष्ट्रनौसाधनिक<BR>Kari-turag-oṣṭra-nau-sādhanika (EI 23), military officer<BR>(or officers) in charge of the elephant force, cavalry, navy and<BR>camel corps. See Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-bala-vyāpṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिवाहिनीश<BR>Karivāhinīśa (EI 30), leader of the elephant force. Cf.<BR>Hasty-adhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिवृन्दनाथ<BR>Karivṛndanātha (EI 30), leader of the elephant corps.<BR>cf. Hasty-adhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्खाना<BR>kārkhānā (HA), office of the managing body of a Jain<BR>shrine or of a group of Jain shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मन्|कर्म्मन्<BR>karman (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR>(EI 3), eight in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मान्त|कर्मांत|कर्मान्तः|कर्म्मान्त|कर्म्मान्तः<BR>karmānta (EI 13), cf. paśukul-āvadāra-karmānta-konakalika-<BR>gaṅgā-grāme. The reference seems to the karmānta, etc., at<BR>Gaṅgā-grāma. Cf. Karmāntika, Kārmāntika, etc.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-148" target="_blank">Page-148+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 31), also called karmānta-sthalikā, a barn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मान्तक<BR>karmāntaka (EI 15), cf. Khaliṣa-karmāntaka-prabhu-Bhaṭṭa-<BR>Jayasomasvāmin in the description of a donee Brāhmaṇa who was<BR>the master of a karmānta at Khaliṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मान्तिक|कर्मांतिक|कर्म्मान्तिक<BR>Karmāntika (IA 14; LL), ‘the superintendent of a work’.<BR>Cf. Kārmāntika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्मान्तिक|कार्मान्तिकः<BR>Kārmāntika (HD), superintendent of the mines and<BR>state manufactories. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12 (mentioned among<BR>the 18 tīrthas); II. 12 (section called ākara-karmānta-pravartanam,<BR>‘the working of mining operations and manufactories’). Cf.<BR>Karmāntika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मार|कर्मारः|कर्म्मार|कर्म्मारः<BR>Karmāra (LL), a blacksmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मसचिव|कर्मसचिवः|कर्म्मसचिव|कर्म्मसचिवः<BR>Karma-saciva (IE 8-3; HD), an administrative officer;<BR>an executive minister; cf. Mati-saciva, a counsellor or minister.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 36.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मस्थान|कर्म्मस्थान<BR>karma-sthāna (IA 18), a public building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मस्थाय<BR>karma-sthāya (LP), building operation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मिक<BR>Karmika (LL), a labourer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मिन्|कर्म्मिन्<BR>Karmin, cf. Tamil Kaṉmi (SITI), an official; ‘an officer’<BR>as distinct from ‘a servant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्ण|कर्णः|कर्ण्ण<BR>karṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णम्<BR>Karṇam, also spelt Karaṇam. See Karaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णप्रावृत<BR>Karṇaprāvṛta (SII 2), same as Karṇaprāvaraṇa, ‘a people<BR>whose ears are so large that they use them as a cloak’. Cf.<BR>Sircar, Stud. Geog. Anc. Med. Ind., pp. 36, 67.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णपूर|कर्णपूरः|कर्ण्णपूर<BR>karṇapūra (EI 17), an ear-ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णत्रोडनिका<BR>karṇa-troḍanikā, see karṇa-troṭana (EI 30).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णत्रोटन<BR>karṇa-troṭana (IE 8-8), cutting off a bit from some-<BR>body's ears.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पट|कर्पटं|कर्पटः<BR>karpaṭa, cf. karpaṭa-pade (LP), supposed to be<BR>something like nazarāna; literally, ‘[payment] on account of<BR>clothes’ (same as karpaṭa-bhāvena).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पटभाव<BR>karpaṭa-bhāva (LP), explained as Pāghḏī, i. e. a present,<BR>bribe or inām; but cf. also aśana-karpaṭā(ṭa)-bhāvena (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXVIII, p. 50, text lines 16-17 and note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्पटिक|कार्पटिकः<BR>Kārpaṭika (BL), probably, a hermit or mendicant;<BR>cf. karpaṭi-vrata.<BR>(EI 11), explained as ‘a pilgrim’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पटीव्रत<BR>karpaṭī(ṭi)-vrata (EI 31), observance of the life of a hermit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पूरमूल्य<BR>karpūra-mūlya, cf. kappūra-vilai (SITI), the sale-price<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-149" target="_blank">Page-149+ 40</a>]<BR>paid for temple lands; the price paid for cultivation rights of<BR>temple lands and in commutation of the taxes thereon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्ष|कर्षः<BR>karṣa (IE 8-8; CII 4), name of a weight equal to 80<BR>ratis; same as tolā; sometimes regarded as 100 or 120 ratis<BR>in weight (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 3).<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 309), a measure of capacity for<BR>liquids.<BR>(CII 4), name of a coin; cf. kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्षापण|कार्षापणं|कार्षापणः<BR>kārṣāpaṇa (IE 8-8; EI 29; CII 4), name of a gold, silver<BR>or copper coin one karṣa (80 ratis) in weight; name of a<BR>silver coin of 32 ratis, same as purāṇa or dharaṇa; name applied<BR>to the gold gaṇḍa-māḍa also called niṣka or gaṇḍa-niṣka (JNSI,<BR>Vol. XVI, p. 43). The weight of a copper or gold kārṣāpaṇa<BR>was 80 or 100 ratis (JNSI, Vol XV, p. 143); copper kārṣāpaṇa<BR>was also called paṇa. Cf. kāhāpaṇa (EI 8), Prakrit for<BR>Sanskrit kārṣāpaṇa; see kāhāṇa, kāhaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्षार्ध<BR>karṣ-ārdha, ‘half karṣa (q. v.)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्तव्य|कर्त्तव्य|कर्त्तव्यं|कर्त्तव्यः<BR>kartavya (LP), derived from kṛt; ‘to be cut’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्ताकृतिक<BR>Kārtākṛtika (IE 8-3), probably, an officer who reported<BR>to the king about the progress of important undertakings;<BR>cf. kṛt-ākṛta-jño bhṛtyānām (Matsya Purāṇa, CCXV, 17).<BR>See Mahākārtākṛtika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्तृ|कर्त्तृ<BR>Kartṛ (CII 3, etc.), the maker; a technical term for the<BR>composer of a record, as opposed to the person who reduced it to<BR>writing.<BR>Cf. Karttār (EI 33), Tamil; an officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिक|कार्तिक|कार्त्तिकः<BR>kārttika (CITD), crops reaped in the month of Kārttika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिकेयमुख<BR>kārttikeya-mukha, cf. kumār-āsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिकोद्यापन<BR>kārttik-odyāpana (IA 18), also called kārttik-odyāpana-<BR>parvan (BL), a festival in honour of Viṣṇu, connected with<BR>Kārttika su-di 11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुदेय<BR>kāru-deya, cf. sarva-parihāra-kāru-deya (EI 24); tax realised<BR>from the artisans; same as kāruka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुक|कारुकः<BR>Kāruka (LB), an artisan. The five classes of artisans may<BR>be the carpenter, the blacksmith, the potter, the barber and<BR>the washerman.<BR>(IE 8-5; EI 25, 32), tax on artisans and craftsmen; same<BR>as kāru-deya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुकर<BR>kārukara (HRS), traced by some in the Prakrit passage<BR>sa-karukara in a Śātavāhana record and identified with<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-150" target="_blank">Page-150+ 40</a>]<BR>udraṅga and uparikara; but may be Sanskrit kar-otkara, i. e.<BR>kara and utkara (probably the same as upakara or uparikara),<BR>or kāru-kara=kāru-deya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुणा<BR>karuṇā (CII 4), one of the bhāvanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुशिल्पिगण|कारुशिल्पिगणः<BR>kāru-śilpi-gaṇa, various types of artisans. Cf. Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्वटक<BR>karvaṭaka (EI 13), a market town; cf. Sanskrit kharvaṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्य|कार्य्य|कार्य्यं<BR>kārya, cf. Tamil kāriyavārāycci (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR>Cf. Vāśal-kāriyam (SITI), the officer in charge of the<BR>palace gate; also known as Vāśal-mudali or Vāśal-nirvāham.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यचिन्तक|कार्यचिंतक|कार्य्यचिन्तक<BR>Kārya-cintaka (CII 4), a member of the executive commi-<BR>ttee of a corporation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यदर्शिन्<BR>Kārya-darśin (EI 22), a secretary or manager.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यकर्तृ<BR>Kārya-kartṛ (SITI), an agent; also called Kāriyattukku-<BR>kkaḍavar, a designation sometimes enjoyed by the Pradhāni<BR>or the provincial governor (ASLV).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यवाराय्च्चि<BR>kārya-vārāycci (SITI), Tamil; also spelt ārāycci; cess<BR>paid for the superintendence of transactions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कासार|कासारं|कासारः<BR>Kāsāra (EI 4), a brazier; same as Kāṃsyakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कषाय|कषायः<BR>kaṣāya (CII 4), a spirituous liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशाय<BR>kāś-āya (SITI), same as kāśu-āyam; taxes and dues payable<BR>in coin; also called kāś-āya-vargam, kāśu-vargam and kāśu-<BR>kaḍamai. Cf. hiraṇy-āya, dhānya-varga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठ|काष्ठं<BR>kāṣṭha, cf. a-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-grahaṇa (IE 8-5), fuel or wood which<BR>the villagers were obliged to supply to the king or landlord<BR>on occasions or to the touring officers. See also devakuṭī-kāṣṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठागार|काष्ठागारः<BR>kāṣṭh-āgāra, cf. kaṭṭāgara (SII 3), a wooden house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठकार<BR>Kāṣṭhakāra (SII 3), a carpenter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठयूति<BR>kāṣṭha-yūti, cf. yūti; ‘a wood for preserving fuel’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशु<BR>kāśu (SII 1), Tamil; money; a coin; ‘a tax’; cf. kāśu-<BR>kaḍamai, tax payable in cash.<BR>(IE 8-8), name of a coin; sometimes called dīnāra (q. v.);<BR>cf. ūr-kāśu (EI 28), vīrapañcālaṅ-kāśu (SITI), sambiraṇippalaṅ-<BR>gāśu; also īl13a-kkāśu (EI 28), ‘the Ceylonese coin’; śol13iya-kkāśu<BR>(SITI), name of a copper coin believed to have been intro-<BR>duced by the Col13as; palaṅ-kāśu, nat-kāśa, nal-kāśu (SII 12);<BR>generally regarded as (1/100) of a paṇam; cf. triśūla-kāśu (SII 3).<BR>Cf. āśuva-kkāśu (SITI), or ājīvaka-kāśu, tax payable by the<BR>Ājīvakas.<BR>Cf. aḍimai-kkāśu (SITI), fees collected from the temple<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-151" target="_blank">Page-151+ 40</a>]<BR>servants; also adi-kkāśu, tax collected from stall-keepers in the<BR>markets.<BR>Cf. uppu-kkāśu (SITI), salt-tax.<BR>Cf. vagainda-kāśu (SITI), tax payable in cash for marking<BR>details of land, etc.; fees for the division of land; also the fee<BR>for settlement of a dispute, etc.<BR>Cf. veli-kkāśu, veli-ppayaṟu (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in<BR>cash, the exact nature of which is not clear. Cf. veli-kkuḻ-<BR>ppaṇam.<BR>Cf. inavari-kkāśu (SITI), communal tax payable in coin;<BR>cf. jāti-siddh-āya of Telugu inscriptions.<BR>(SITI), Tamil; a measure of weight equal to (1/4) palam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटक|कटकं|कटकः<BR>kaṭaka (EI 8, 17), the camp or capital.<BR>(SITI), a fortified place; a cantonment; a military camp.<BR>Cf. kaṭakaṃ kartavyam (LP), ‘an army should be sent<BR>[against one]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकाधिराज<BR>Kaṭak-ādhirāja (EI 4), same as Kaṭakarāja, etc.; a military<BR>officer in charge of the royal camp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकाधीश<BR>Kaṭakādhīśa (HD), same as Kaṭakarāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकनायक<BR>Kaṭaka-nāyaka (EI 23), same as Kaṭakarāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकराज<BR>Kaṭakarāja (EI 9; HD), officer in charge of the royal camp;<BR>same as Kaṭakādhīśa, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 309, note 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकवारिक<BR>Kaṭaka-vārika (EI 30), probably, officials serving under the<BR>superintendent of the royal camp (Kaṭakarāja, etc.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकेश<BR>Kaṭakeśa (EI 29; HD), superintendent of the royal<BR>camp; same as Kaṭakarāja, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 185.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटपयादि<BR>ka-ṭa-pa-y-ādi (IE 7-1-3; EI 33; IA 19, 24), a system of<BR>recording numbers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कठारि<BR>kaṭhāri (ASLV), same as Sanskrit kartarī, a sword.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कठ|कठः<BR>kaṭha (LP), cf. Gujarātī kāṭmāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कथित|कथितः<BR>kathita, drawn up or dictated (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 179). Cf. cintita, ‘composed’ (ibid., Vol. XXXV, p. 58).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटीसूत्र<BR>kaṭī-sūtra (EI 16), an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टण<BR>kaṭṭaṇa (SITI), periodical presents made to superiors<BR>by their subordinates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टुगुत्तगै<BR>kaṭṭu-guttagai (ASLV), Tamil; a contract.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटुक|कटुकं|कटुकः<BR>Kaṭuka (EI 13; HD), an official designation of uncertain<BR>import; cf. Mahākaṭuka. See Ep. Ind., Vol XIII, p. 117.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटुमुख<BR>kaṭumukha (EI 5), name given to a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौबेरच्छन्द<BR>kauberacchanda (CII 3), a particular kind of pearl-necklace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौलिकनिकाय<BR>kaulika-nikāya (LL), the weaver's guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौमारसौध<BR>kaumāra-saudha (EI 34), a prince's palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौपित्क<BR>Kaupitka (EI 1, 23), official designation of uncertain<BR>import; probably, a collector of tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काउसग्गिया<BR>kā-usaggiyā (HA), Sanskrit kāyotsargikā; the image of a<BR>Tīrthaṅkara standing in the kāy-otsarga posture. See kā-ussagga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काउस्सग्ग<BR>kā-ussagga (HA), Sanskrit kāy-otsarga (q. v.); a posture<BR>of meditation in which one stands erect with arms hanging<BR>and the soles of the feet kept four inches apart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौष्ठेयक<BR>kauṣṭheyaka (HRS), occurring in the Arthaśāstra and<BR>understood by some in the sense of earnings from the king's<BR>store-houses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौस्तुभ|कौस्तुभः<BR>kaustubha (CII 3, etc.), a jewel worn on the breast of Viṣṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौटुम्बिक|कौटुंबिक|कौटुम्बिकः<BR>Kauṭumbika, cf. Prakrit Koṭubika (EI 24), a householder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कवच|कवचं|कवचः<BR>kavaca (SITI), same as Tamil tiru-kkōl13gai, the metallic<BR>cover exactly fitting the image of a deity; same as kholī, kholikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कवले<BR>kavale, also called kavaleḍu, kavaligĕ (CITD), Telugu-<BR>Kannaḍa; a pack of written leaves; palm leaves prepared for<BR>writing accounts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कवेलुक<BR>kaveluka, kāveluka (LP), tile; cf. kivelu, Marāṭhī kaul,<BR>etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 144-45.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कविराज|कविराजः<BR>Kavirāja (IA 26), title; sometimes found also among the<BR>Musalmans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काय|कायं|कायः<BR>kāya (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कायस्थ|कायस्थः<BR>Kāyastha (EI 24; ASLV; HD), a clerk; explained by some<BR>as ‘a registrar’ (EI 31); a scribe or writer in the king's revenue<BR>department according to some. See Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 322;<BR>Viṣṇu Dharma Sūtra, VII. 3; etc. Cf. Aśvaghāsa-kāyastha and<BR>Grāma-kāyastha (Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 175; IHQ, Vol. IX,<BR>p. 12). See also Hist. Dharm., Vol. II, pp. 75-77. For<BR>derivation, cf. Bhār. Vid., Vol. X, pp. 280 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कायव्रत<BR>kāya-vrata (EI 11), self-immolation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कायोत्सर्ग|कायोत्सर्गः<BR>kāy-otsarga (EI 3), a kind of obeisance.<BR>Cf. Prākrit kā-ussagga (HA), a posture of meditation in<BR>which one stands erect with arms hanging and the soles of<BR>feet kept four inches apart. Cf. kāusaggiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केदार|केदारः<BR>kedāra (EI 28), a corn-field.<BR>(EI 32), low land.<BR>Cf. bhū-kedāra (EI 19); a land measure; cf. the land<BR>measure called keyār in the Sylhet region of East Pakistan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केदारिका<BR>kedārikā (IA 15), a small field; cf. kedāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केला<BR>kelā (IE 8-8; EI 30), meaning uncertain; probably, a doll<BR>or toy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केलि|केलिः<BR>keli (EI 9), the earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केन्द्र|केंद्र|केंद्रं|केन्द्रं<BR>kendra (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR>(CII 3), anomaly of the moon, taken to be her distance<BR>from apogee, from which point it is always reckoned by Hindu<BR>astronomers; the annual variation in the moon's kendra is 3<BR>signs 2 degrees and 6.2 minutes, or 7 tithis 9 ghaṭīs and 42<BR>palas. See also nīcocca-māsa, tithi-kendra, tithi-madhyama-kendra<BR>and tithi-spaṣṭa-kendra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केतु|केतुः<BR>ketu (EI 24), the shape or form.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केवलज्ञान<BR>kevala-jñāna (HA), Jain; omniscience; a technical term<BR>for the highest knowledge; the Jain doctrine of unity (IA 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख|खं|खः<BR>kha (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खद<BR>khada (LP), grass.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खद्गधर<BR>Khadgadhara, cf. Mahākhaḍgadhara, Khaḍagrāhin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गग्राह<BR>Khaḍgagrāha (IE 8-3; EI 30), probably the same as Khāḍgika;<BR>swordsman; sometimes distinguished from Khaṇḍapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गग्राहिमहापात्र<BR>Khaḍgagrāhi-mahāpātra (EI 28, 31), official designation<BR>in which Khaḍgagrāhin seems to indicate an officer in charge of<BR>swordsmen (as opposed to the clubmen); see Mahāpātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गग्राहिन्<BR>Khaḍga-grāhin (EI 28), same as the Khaṇḍāita (originally,<BR>swordsmen of the kings of Orissa); cf. Khaḍgagrāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गरक्ष<BR>Khaḍga-rakṣa (EI 30), same as Khaḍga-grāha; used in<BR>place of Aṅgarakṣa and Khaṇḍarakṣa of some records (Ind.<BR>Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 11, text line 14); probably, the king's<BR>bodyguards.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाड्गिक<BR>Khāḍgika (IE 8-3), ‘swordsman’; probably ‘a palace-<BR>guard’; mentioned separately from Khaṇḍarakṣa which is also<BR>spelt Khaḍgarakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाड्गिन्<BR>Khāḍgin (EI 23), same as Khāḍgika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाडी<BR>khāḍī (EI 31), a canal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाडूरिका<BR>khāḍūrikā (EI 9), a military exercise ground.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाद्यकूटपाकिक<BR>Khādyakūṭapākika, see Khādyaṭapākika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाद्यटपाकिक<BR>Khādyaṭapākika (IE 8-3), probably a mistake for<BR>Khādyakūṭa-pākika (cf. anna-kūṭa, ‘a heap of food’); same<BR>as Mahānas-ādhyakṣa; called Sandhivigrahika, Kumārāmātya, Mahā-<BR>daṇḍanāyaka, etc., additionally. See Bhānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ, Mahānas-<BR>ādhyakṣa, Sūpakārapati, Mahānasika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाजण्<BR>khājaṇ (IE 8-8), Marāṭhī, etc.; see khajjana, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खज्जन<BR>khajjana, khajjaṇa, khajjāna, khajjaṇaka (IE 8-8; EI 33),<BR>same as Marāṭhī and Koṅkaṇī khājaṇ; an area near the<BR>sea shore, on which a thin layer of sand accumulates after<BR>the ebbtide coming through inlets; a rice field created out of<BR>such an area near a hillock by erecting embankments on the<BR>three other sides; a field created by reclaiming a river bed;<BR>cultivable land created from the bed of a river which carries<BR>the flood-water from the sea; a salty marsh or meadow; a<BR>rice field created near the bed of a nullah on the sea shore<BR>by putting embankments. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, pp.<BR>53-54. It is sometimes called pukkoli-khajjana, pukkoli probably<BR>meaning a similar kind of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खल|खलं|खलः<BR>khala (Chamba, etc.), threshing floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलभिक्षा<BR>khala-bhikṣā (EI 3, 25; HRS), a levy; cess payable at the<BR>threshing floor; portion of crop over and above the usual<BR>grainshare, collected from grains heaped upon the threshing<BR>floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलक|खलकः<BR>khalaka (IA 18), a threshing floor [probably situated<BR>near a well]; cf. khala.<BR>Cf. khalak-ānte (LP), ‘at the end of the threshing<BR>season’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलकीय<BR>khalakīya (LP), tax payable at or for using the threshing<BR>floor; cf. khala-bhikṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलरक्षक<BR>Khala-rakṣaka, cf. Mahā-khalarakṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खल्ल|खल्लः<BR>khalla (IE 8-5), same as Oḏiyā khāl; low land; cf. sa-<BR>khall-onnata (EI 12), ‘with low land and high land’.<BR>(IE 8-8), a hide.<BR>(EI 30), leather vessel for carrying wine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खल्लर<BR>khallara (IA 13), probably, a pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खं|ख|खः<BR>khaṃ, abbreviation of khaṇḍa, ‘a piece’ (JAS, Letters,<BR>Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खम्पण<BR>khampaṇa (EI 23), a territorial division; same as kampaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खम्पणक<BR>khampaṇaka (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit; same as<BR>khampaṇa or kampaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खानक<BR>khānaka (EI 15), same as khātaka in the sense of<BR>khanana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्द<BR>khaṇda (IE 8-4; EI 23), a territorial division; the sub-<BR>division of a deśa.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-155" target="_blank">Page-155+ 40</a>]<BR>Cf. nava-khaṇḍa (IE 8-4), ‘having nine divisions’; an<BR>epithet of Bhārata or Bhārata-varṣa.<BR>(EI 30), a habitation.<BR>(EI 3, 24), also called khaṇḍi; a land measure. See<BR>khaṇḍaka.<BR>Cf. Tamil kaṇḍam (SITI), a portion of the mukha-<BR>maṇḍapa of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्ड|खंड|खण्डं|खण्डः<BR>khaṇḍa, khaṇḍā (IA 15), a sword.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डाइत्<BR>Khaṇḍāit (IE 8-3), a community in Orissa; probably the<BR>swordsmen maintained by kings as opposed to their<BR>Pāiks or clubmen; cf. Khaṇḍarakṣa and Khaṇḍapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डक|खंडक|खण्डकः<BR>khaṇḍaka (SITI), cf. Tamil kaṇḍakam, a land measure.<BR>See khaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डक्षेत्र<BR>khaṇḍa-kṣetra (EI 3, 16, 23), a plot of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डल|खंडल|खंडलं|खंडलः|खण्डलः<BR>khaṇḍala (IE 8-4; EI 12, 18), a territorial unit; a district<BR>or its subdivision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डल|खंडल|खंडलं|खंडलः|खण्डलः<BR>khaṇḍala, khaṇḍalaka, same as khaṇḍa; cf. kṣetra-khaṇḍala<BR>or °khaṇḍalaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135, text time 22;<BR>p. 139, text line 22).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डपाल|खंडपाल|खण्डपालः<BR>Khaṇḍapāla (IE 8-3; EI 28), official designation; same<BR>as Khaṇḍapati or Khaṇḍarakṣa (q. v.). See Khaṇḍavāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डपाल|खंडपाल|खण्डपालः<BR>khaṇḍapāla, also called khaṇḍapālīya (IE 8-3; EI 24, 28),<BR>tax for the maintenance of swordsmen; tax for the main-<BR>tenance of the Khaṇḍapāla or Khaṇḍapālas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डपति<BR>Khaṇḍapati (EI 12, 28), official designation; same as<BR>Khaṇḍapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डरक्ष<BR>Khaṇḍarakṣa (IE 8-3; HD), sometimes spelt as Khaḍga-<BR>rakṣa, ‘swordsman’; probably the king's bodyguard; mentioned<BR>separately from Khāḍgika; cf. Khaṇḍapāla; also Khaṇḍāit; some-<BR>times regarded as the same as Khaṇḍapāla meaning the ruler<BR>of a small territorial unit. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR>Cf. Khaḍgarakṣa (Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 127-28).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डस्फुटितजीर्णोद्धार<BR>khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-jīrṇ-oddhāra (EI 23), also called khaṇḍa-<BR>sphuṭita-navakarman, khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-prakaraṇa; repairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डवाल<BR>Khaṇḍavāla (EI 7; HD), modification of Khaṇḍapāla.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91; JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डि<BR>khaṇḍi (EI 3), also called khaṇḍa, a land measure. Cf.<BR>khaṇḍī spelt in English as candy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डी<BR>khaṇḍī (CII 4), a measure of capacity; cf. khaṇdīkā. See<BR>candy.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-156" target="_blank">Page-156+ 40</a>]<BR>(IA 15), a land-measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डिक|खंडिकः|खण्डिकः<BR>khaṇḍika, khaṇdikā (EI 22; CII 4; IA 20), measure of<BR>capacity; same as khaṇḍī or candy; often regarded as equal<BR>to between 800 and 1000 seers. See puṭṭi.<BR>Cf. Ṛgveda-khaṇḍikā, a school for teaching the Ṛgveda<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 37 and notes).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डुग<BR>khaṇḍuga (IE 8-6; EI 4; CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a<BR>weight of 192,000 tolās for silk, sugar, drugs and cotton; a land<BR>measure; a land measure of 64,000 square yards of dry and<BR>10,000 square yards of wet land [in Mysore]; a dry measure<BR>of 409,6000 or 134,400 or 128,000 tolās in different places.<BR>Cf. khaṇḍuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डुक<BR>khaṇḍuka (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity; cf. khaṇḍukavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डुकवाप<BR>khaṇḍukavāpa (IE 8-6), an area of land requiring one<BR>khaṇḍuka measure of seed grains for sowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खनिक<BR>khanika, cf. Prakrit khaniya (EI 20), a pillar. Cf. khāṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाणु<BR>khāṇu (EI 24), a pillar; cf. khanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारि|खारिः<BR>khāri (EI 17), a land measure; cf. khārī, khārīvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारी<BR>khārī (IE 8-6; CII 4), a measure of capacity equal to<BR>sixteen droṇas.<BR>(IE 8-6), shortened form of khārīvāpa or khārikāvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारिका<BR>khārikā (IE 8-6), shortened form of khārikāvāpa or khārī-<BR>vāpa; also same as khārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारिकावाप<BR>khārikāvāpa (IE 8-6), same as khārīvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारीवाप|खारीवापः<BR>khārīvāpa (IE 8-6), an area of land requiring a khārī<BR>measure of seed grains for sowing; a land measure equal to<BR>sixteen droṇavāpas or two kulyavāpas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खरोष्ठी<BR>Kharoṣṭhī, an early Indian alphabet which was an Indian<BR>modification of the Aramaic alphabet; called Kharoṣṭrī by some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खर्वड<BR>kharvaḍa (EI 5), Sanskrit kharvaṭa; a market town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खर्वट|खर्वटं|खर्वटः|खर्व्वट|खर्व्वटः<BR>kharvaṭa (ASLV), an administrative unit. See also<BR>kharvaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खश्चा<BR>khaścā (LP), also spelt ṣaścā; teasing; cf. khāṃc-khuṃc<BR>in Gujarātī. See khaśrā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खश्रा<BR>khaśrā (EI 1), loss or injury. Cf. khaścā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खात|खातं<BR>khāta (EI 19), a well.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खातक|खातकं|खातकः<BR>khātaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253, text line 33, note 4),<BR>probably, a canal; same as Bengali khāt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खतिब<BR>Khatiba, same as Arabic Khatīb, preacher (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXIV, p. 145).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाटिका<BR>khāṭikā (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253); the mouth of a river;<BR>same as Bengali khāḏī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खत्तक<BR>khattaka (EI 8), Kannaḍa; a pedestal or seat.<BR>(EI 11; HA), a niche; a term found in Jain inscriptions<BR>in the said sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खट्वा<BR>khaṭvā, cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (IE 8-5); a<BR>cot which the villagers were obliged to provide for a touring<BR>officer of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खट्वाङ्ग|खट्वांग|खट्वाङ्गं|खट्वाङ्गः<BR>khaṭvāṅga (EI 5; SII 2), a club with a skull fixed at the<BR>top; a Śaiva emblem.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खट्वापाद<BR>khaṭvāpāda (EI 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खेडनीय<BR>kheḍanīya (LP), same as pātanīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खेट|खेटं|खेटः<BR>kheṭa (IE 8-5), a village or hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खिल|खिलं|खिलः<BR>khila (EI 15; Chamba), uncultivated land; fallow land;<BR>cf. sa-khila-nāla (IE 8-5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खिलक्षेत्र<BR>khila-kṣetra (EI 23), fallow land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोज<BR>Khoja (EI 6), a merchant. Cf. Khwāja, the Muslim title<BR>of distinction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोल|खोलः<BR>Khola (IE 8-3); HD), an official designation of uncertain<BR>meaning (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, pp. 250, 253); probably a kind<BR>of messenger. Utpala on the Bṛhatsaṃhitā, 85. 34, explains<BR>Dūta as Gamāgamika while some Pāla inscriptions place Khola<BR>between the two; probably the same as Preṣaṇika or Dūta-<BR>preṣaṇika, a dispatcher of messengers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोली<BR>Kholī, kholikā, same as kavaca (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोट<BR>khoṭa (HRS), what is payable to the king in the shape of<BR>hiraṇya, etc., and of compulsory labour and the provision<BR>of food for the Cāṭas and Bhaṭas, according to the Abhidhāna-<BR>rājendra, s. v. parihāra. See khoṭa-bhaṅga, ukkoṭa-bhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोटभङ्ग<BR>khoṭa-bhaṅga (HRS), applies to a person residing for<BR>one, two or three years, or as long as the king's favour extends,<BR>without contributing the hiraṇya, etc., and without providing<BR>food for the Gāṭas and Bhaṭas, according to the Abhidhānarā-<BR>jendra, s. v. parihāra; also called ukkoṭa-bhaṅga, akṣoṭa-bhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोवा<BR>khovā (IE 8-8), cf. khovādāna; meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख्स्हथ्रपावन्<BR>Khshathrapāvan (IE 8-2, 8-3), Old Persian; ‘a provincial<BR>governor.’ See Kṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख्स्हायथियख्स्हायथियानाम्<BR>Khshāyathiya Khshāyathiyānām (IE 8-2), Old Persian;<BR>‘king of kings’; same as Modern Persian Shāhān Shāh. See<BR>Basilĕos Basilĕon, Ṣāhānuṣāhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख्स्हायथियवष्र्क<BR>Khshāyathiya vazrka (IE 8-2), Old Persian; ‘the great<BR>king’; royal title. It was translated by the Indo-Greek kings<BR>in Greek and Prakrit in the legend of their coins and was the<BR>original of the Indian royal title Mahārāja. See Basilĕos<BR>Mĕgalŏu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किल|किलः<BR>kila, cf. Paṭṭakila, Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीलक|कीलकः<BR>kīlaka (EI 23), a peg [for marking boundaries].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीलमुद्रा<BR>kīla-mudrā, letter written on wedge-shaped wooden tablets<BR>(Select Inscriptions, pp. 236-37).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किंछन्दः<BR>kiṃ-chandaḥ (CII 1), cf. kiṃ-chandaḥ svit rājā asmāsu,<BR>‘of what attitude is the king towards ourselves?’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किण्वक्रेणि<BR>kiṇva-kreṇi (EI 15), mistake for kliṇva-kreṇi meaning such<BR>articles as sugar, liquor, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तन|कीर्तनं|कीर्त्तन|कीर्त्तनं<BR>kīrtana (EI 24, 28, 33; SII 1; CII 4), same as kīrti;<BR>a temple or any other thing that renders famous the name of<BR>the person responsible for it; often interpreted as ‘a building<BR>or temple’; but really, ‘any fame-producing work’; ‘a monu-<BR>ment of fame’; a pious work like a temple. See kīrtanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तना|कीर्त्तना<BR>kīrtanā (EI 33), same as kīrtana and kīrti; cf. kīrtita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्ति|कीर्तिः|कीर्त्ति|कीर्त्तिः<BR>kīrti (EI 20, 24; CII 3, 4), literally, ‘the thing that<BR>speaks of or glorifies one’; used in the special meaning of ‘any<BR>work which renders the constructor of it famous’; a merit-<BR>orious work; a pious deed; same as kīrtana, kīrtanā; often inter-<BR>preted as ‘a building or temple’; but actually, ‘any fame-<BR>producing work’. See kīrti-sthāna.<BR>(CII 1), fame of a dead person; cf. yaśo vā kīrtir = vā.<BR>See yaśas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तिमुख<BR>kīrti-mukha (CII 4), a decorative motif.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तिस्तम्भ|कीर्तिस्तम्भः<BR>kīrti-stambha, cf. mahāmeru-śrī-kīrtistambha (BL); ‘the pillar<BR>of fame’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तिस्थान<BR>kīrti-sthāna (EI 1), same as kīrti or kīrtana; a temple or<BR>some such object calculated to render famous the name of the<BR>person responsible for it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तित|कीर्त्तित|कीर्त्तितः<BR>kīrtita (EI 24), ‘built’; cf. prakīrtita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीशोरवडवागोमहिषाजाविकाध्यक्ष<BR>Kīśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), cf. Go-<BR>mahiṣ-āj-āvikā-vaḍav-ādhyakṣa, Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-<BR>ādhyakṣa, Kari-turaga-pattan-ākarasthāna-gokul-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किशोरवदवागोमहिष्यधिकृत<BR>Kiśoravadavā-go-mahiṣy-adhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 17, 23), cf.<BR>Go-mahiṣy-aj-ādhyakṣa, Kiśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किशोरवडवागोमहिष्यजाविकाध्यक्ष<BR>Kiśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣy-aj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (EI 29), cf. Go-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-159" target="_blank">Page-159+ 40</a>]<BR>mahiṣy-aj-ādhyakṣa, Kiśora-vaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किटिका<BR>kiṭikā (EI 14), Sanskritised form of kiḍi or kiḍā, ‘a matting<BR>screen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किवेलु<BR>kivelu (LP), ‘tile’; cf. Marāṭhī kaul. See kaveluka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्लिण्व<BR>kliṇva, cf. a-lavaṇa-kliṇva-khātaka (IE 8-5); probably, such<BR>things as sugar and liquor; same as kliṇva-kreṇi; cf. also<BR>a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (IE 8-5), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्लिण्वक्रेणि<BR>kliṇva-kreṇi, cf. a-lavaṇa-kliṇva-kreṇi-khanaka (IE 8-5);<BR>same as kliṇva meaning articles like sugar, liquor, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कॢप्त|कॢप्तः<BR>kḷpta (CII 3, 4; HRS), cf. sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta (IE 8-5); pro-<BR>bably, the tax on permanent tenants or the fixed revenue;<BR>fixed tax which is one of the seven sources of revenue specified<BR>in the Arthaśāstra; cf. upakḷpta, kḷpta-kara, udraṅga, kḷpta-śluka,<BR>etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कॢप्तकर<BR>kḷpta-kara (IE 8-5), fixed tax; same as kḷpta-śulka; cf.<BR>sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कॢप्तशुल्क<BR>kḷpta-śulka (IE 8-5), fixed duty; same as kḷpta, kḷpta-kara;<BR>cf. sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडे<BR>koḍe (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of capacity.<BR>Cf. Kannaḍa koda-visa, an allowance of a visa of grain, etc.,<BR>for every bullock-load that comes into a town, paid to a person<BR>employed to check the demands of the toll-collector.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडेवण<BR>koḍevaṇa (EI 27), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोद्रव|कोद्रवः<BR>kodrava (EI 5, 12), name of a grain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोह्ली<BR>kohlī (Chamba), wet land, irrigable land; same as āli;<BR>opposed to otaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्<BR>kol (IE 8-6), Tamil; a measuring rod; cf. śrīpāda-kkol,<BR>‘rod measured according to the length of the king's foot’;<BR>māliga-kkol, ‘the measuring rod of the palace’; etc.<BR>(EI 25), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल|कोलं|कोलः<BR>kola, same as tolaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलग<BR>kolaga (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलग<BR>koḻaga (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; measure of capacity<BR>equal to 4 baḻas; a dry measure of 768 or 384 or 72 tolas in<BR>different places.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलभण्डालु<BR>kola-bhaṇḍālu, also called kolla-baṇḍi (CITD), Telugu;<BR>a bullock-cart load. Cf. busi-baṇḍi or busi-bhaṇḍālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलिक<BR>Kolika (IE 8-8; EI 30), same as Sanskrit Kaulika, a weaver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलिकनिकाय<BR>kolika-nikāya (CII 4), a guild of the Kaulikas or weavers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्लबण्डि<BR>kolla-baṇḍi, see kola-bhaṇḍālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलु<BR>kolu (IE 8-6), a measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोमटि<BR>Komaṭi (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a Vaiśya shop-keeper;<BR>a member of the mercantile caste.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोम्मुमर्तुरु<BR>kommu-maṟturu (CITD), Telugu; see maṟuturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोञ्जल्ल<BR>koñjalla, cf. a-kara-viṣṭi-koñjalla (IE 8-5); a fiscal term<BR>of doubtful import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोरट<BR>koraṭa (CII 3), a fiscal term of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष|कोषं|कोषः<BR>koṣa, treasure, see Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 15-16.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोशाधिप<BR>Koś-ādhipa (EI 32, 33), a treasurer; same as Koś-<BR>ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोषगृह<BR>koṣa-gṛha (HRS), treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोशजा<BR>Kośajā (EI 9), a cocoon-producer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोषवाह<BR>koṣavāha (EI 14), name of a land measure; as much land<BR>as can be irrigated by one koṣa or leather bucket.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठ|कोष्ठः<BR>koṣṭha (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’. Cf. koṣṭhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठागार<BR>koṣṭh-āgāra (HRS), the royal granary.<BR>(EI 29), cf. Tamil koṭṭagāram, koṭṭāram (EI 22; SITI),<BR>treasury or store-house.<BR>Cf. Tamil koṭṭagāram, etc. (SII 2), stables.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठागारकरण<BR>koṣṭhāgāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), department of the<BR>collection of the king's share of grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठागारिन्<BR>Koṣṭhāgārin, officer in charge of the treasury or store-<BR>house; cf. Mahākoṣṭhāgārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठक|कोष्ठकः<BR>koṣṭhaka (BL; LP), a granary or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठकरण<BR>Koṣṭha-karaṇa (EI 29), a treasury accountant; also the<BR>revenue department (cf. koṣṭha-vyāpāra).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठव्यापार<BR>koṣṭha-vyāpāra (EI 29), the revenue department (cf.<BR>koṣṭha-karaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठी<BR>koṣṭhī, cf. Prakrit koḍhi (LL), a hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठिका<BR>koṣṭhikā (EI 15), same as koṣṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठिकाकरण<BR>koṣṭhikā-karaṇa (LP), the royal treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट|कोटः<BR>koṭa (LP), also called koṭaḍī; ‘wall of the compound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटाधिकरणिक<BR>Koṭ-ādhikaraṇika (BL), officer in charge of or related to the<BR>government of a koṭa or koṭṭa (fort).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटडि<BR>koṭaḍi, kotaḍī; cf. koṭaḍi-sahita (LP), ‘together with walls of<BR>the compound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटक|कोटकः<BR>koṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 313), ‘a district’; same as<BR>koṭṭaka; cf. koṭṭa-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटपाल|कोटपालः<BR>Koṭapāla (EI 17), same as Koṭṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोठव्यापार<BR>koṭha-vyāpāra (EI 28), same as koṣṭha-vyāpāra; the revenue<BR>department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटिहोम|कोटिहोमः<BR>koṭi-homa (EI 12, 33), name of a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटिका<BR>koṭikā, a load [of cloth] (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR>(EI 14), a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्ट|कोट्टं|कोट्टः<BR>koṭṭa (EI 24), a fort. See koṭṭai and koṭṭam of the South<BR>Indian inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टै<BR>koṭṭai (ASLV), a fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टक<BR>koṭṭaka, see koṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टम्<BR>koṭṭam (IE 8-4; EI 27), Tamil; a district; a district<BR>within a maṇḍala or province.<BR>(ASLV), a division of the rājya; sometimes subdivided<BR>into nāḍus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टनिग्रह<BR>Koṭṭa-nigraha (EI 8; IA 30; BL), commander of a fort;<BR>same as Koṭṭapāla. Cf. Koṭṭanigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टनिग्रहिन्<BR>Koṭṭanigrahin (IA 30), probably, the commander of a<BR>fort; same as Koṭṭanigraha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टपाल<BR>Koṭṭapāla (IE 8-3; EI 12, 18, 25, 30; BL), officer in<BR>charge of a fort; governor of a fort. Cf. the Bhagalpur plate of<BR>Nārāyaṇapāla (Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306); sometimes<BR>spelt Koṭapāla (cf. the Nalanda plate of Devapāla in Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XVII, p. 321). Same as Koṭṭapati.<BR>(EI 25), the city prefect; same as Kotwāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टपति<BR>Koṭṭapati (IE 8-3), same as Koṭṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टविषय<BR>koṭṭa-viṣaya (IE 8-4; CII 1), a viṣaya or district around<BR>a fortress; a district with its headquarters in a fort.<BR>See koṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोत्टाल्<BR>Kotwāl (IE 8-2, 8-3), same as Talāra or the prefect<BR>of the city police; the chief police officer of a city or town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोवै<BR>kovai (SITI), Tamil; name of a gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोवेर<BR>kovera (IE 8-5), cf. karaṇe koveram; probably, some levy at<BR>the court of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोयिल्नायकम्<BR>Koyil-nāyakam (EI 25), Tamil; temple officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोयिल्श्रीकार्यम्<BR>Koyil-śrīkāryam (EI 25), Tamil; a temple officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमादित्य<BR>Kramāditya (IE 8-2), see āditya. The word krama here<BR>seems to mean vikrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमक|क्रमकः<BR>Kramaka (EI 5), also called Kramavid, Kramayuta; epithet<BR>of Brāhmaṇas. Cf. Krama-vitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमविद्<BR>Kramavid (EI 5), epithet of Brāhmanas; same as<BR>Kramaka, Kramayuta. Cf. Krama-vitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमवित्त<BR>Krama-vitta (SITTI), a Brāhmaṇa well-versed in the method<BR>of reciting the Vedas according to the krama order. Cf. Kramaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमयुत<BR>Kramayuta (EI 5), epithet of Brāhmaṇas; same as Kramaka,<BR>Kramavid. Cf. Krama-vitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रयचीरिका<BR>kraya-cīrikā (EI 26), a deed of purchase or sale-deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृदर|कृदरं|कृदरः<BR>kṛdara (CII 4), a granary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रीडायित<BR>krīḍāyita (EI 12), sporting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृशान्न<BR>kṛś-ānna, ‘minor food’; cf. kṛśānna-mūlya which is the<BR>money to meet expenses of light food (Select Inscriptions,<BR>p. 159). See mukh-āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रिया<BR>kriyā (CII 4), Śaiva ceremonies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रियणका<BR>kriyaṇakā (LP), cf. Gujarātī kariyāṇuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रोड|क्रोडं|क्रोडः<BR>kroḍa, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रोश|क्रोशः<BR>krośa (CII 1), a distance of about two miles and a quarter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृपण|कृपणः<BR>kṛpaṇa (CII 1), poor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृशानु|कृशानुः<BR>kṛśānu (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णल|कृष्णलः<BR>kṛṣṇala (IA 26), same as rati or guñjā. One kṛṣṇala is regarded<BR>by the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K. V. Ranga-<BR>swami Aiyangar, p. 125) as equal to three guñjās or raktikās<BR>apparently through confusion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णराजरूपक<BR>kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka (EI 30), name of a silver coin issues by<BR>the Kalacuri king Kṛṣṇarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृत|कृतं<BR>kṛta (EI 12, 14, 23; BL; CII 3), literally ‘accomplished’.<BR>i. e. ‘completed’; used in earlier records in connection with the<BR>era later associated with Vikramāditya. Often spelt<BR>krita, possibly standing for krīta meaning ‘purschased’, which<BR>was a name sometimes applied to certain foreign rulers of<BR>North-Western Bhāratavarṣa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p.<BR>152).<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR>(CII 1), ‘arranged for’, ‘made arrangements for’.<BR>(EI 23), fruit, booty, reward.<BR>(Sel. Ins., p. 202), ‘engraved’.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 41, verse 13), written, drafted or<BR>composed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतान्त|कृतांत|कृतान्तः<BR>kṛtānta (EI 3), same as siddhānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतप्रान्त<BR>kṛta-prānta, cf. sa-kṛta-prānta (IE 8-5), Prakrit sa-kuta-<BR>ppanta; probably, demarcated boundaries.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृति|कृतिः<BR>kṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty’; cf. kṛtin, ‘twentytwo’.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 98), a composition or performance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतिन्<BR>kṛtin (EI 7-1-2), ‘twentytwo’; cf. kṛti, ‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतोपसन्न<BR>kṛt-opasanna (EI 30), an expression of doubtful import;<BR>epithet of a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृत्तिदार<BR>kṛttidāra (IA 15), an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रूरदृश्<BR>krūra-dṛś (EI 12), designation of Mars and Saturn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षान्ति|क्षांति|क्षांतिः|क्षान्तिः<BR>kṣānti (CII 1), forgiveness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षपेश्वर<BR>kṣapeśvara (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षार|क्षारं|क्षारः<BR>kṣāra (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षत|क्षतं<BR>kṣata (EI 23), engraved; cf. utkīrṇa, udghāṭita, etc.<BR>Cf. Prakrit chata (EI 7), ‘written’ (Select Inscriptions, p.<BR>202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षत्रप|क्षत्रपः<BR>Kṣatrapa (IE 8-2, 8-3; ML; HD), feudatory title of<BR>foreign origin; Old Persian Khshathrapāvan, ‘a provincial<BR>governor’; a Satrap. See CII, Vol. II, pp. xxxiv, 23, 28;<BR>Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 166. See Mahākṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षत्तृ<BR>Kṣattṛ (HD), a chamberlain. See Hist. Dharm., Vol.<BR>III, p. 111. According to Manu (X. 16) and Yājñavalkya<BR>(I. 94), the offspring of a Kṣatriya woman from a Śūdra male<BR>was called Kṣattṛ. This apparently refers to a tribe or community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षौणी<BR>kṣauṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेमराज<BR>Kṣemarāja (LL), title of a pious king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्र|क्षेत्रं<BR>kṣetra (EI 24), a department or committee.<BR>(SII 1), a sacred place. Cf. Varāha-kṣetra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रकर|क्षेत्रकरः<BR>Kṣetrakara (EI 12, 15), a cultivator.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रप|क्षेत्रपः<BR>Kṣetrapa (IE 8-3; HD), same as Kṣetrapāla; superintendent<BR>of the king's Khās Mahāl. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रपाल|क्षेत्रपालः<BR>Kṣetrapāla (IE 8-3; EI 17; HD), same as Kṣetrapa. Cf.<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रसीमन्<BR>kṣetra-sīman (SII 1), explained as ‘a hamlet’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षीर|क्षीरः<BR>kṣīra, cf. a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇīya (IE 8-5); milk which the<BR>villagers (probably, the milkmen) were obliged to supply<BR>to the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षिति|क्षितिः<BR>kṣiti (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षितिदान<BR>kṣiti-dāna (EI 23), same as bhūmi-dāna; name of a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्ष्मा<BR>kṣmā (I 7-1-2; E 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षोभ|क्षोभः<BR>kṣobha, cf. a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (IE 8-5; EI 1); obligation<BR>or trouble.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षोणी<BR>kṣoṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्र|क्षुद्रः<BR>kṣudra, cf. Prakrit cūla=culla ‘small’; prefixed to the names<BR>of persons, localities, etc., in order to distinguish them from<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-164" target="_blank">Page-164+ 40</a>]<BR>others; e. g., Kṣudra-Mūla, Mahā-Mūla; Kṣudra-Dharmagiri,<BR>Mahā-Dharmagiri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रक|क्षुद्रकः<BR>Kṣudraka (CII 1), a person of a low position; a poor man.<BR>(JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 44), same as tolaka or draṃkṣaṇa;<BR>also spelt kṣudrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रम<BR>kṣudrama, see kṣudraka; same as tolaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुण|क्षुणः<BR>kṣuṇa (CII 2-1), corruption of kṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षूण<BR>kṣūṇa (EI 3), fault or defect.<BR>Cf. kṣūṇāni (LP), probably, ‘expenses’; kṣūṇ-ādika, ‘ex-<BR>penses, etc.’<BR>Cf. mānak-aikaṃ yāvat kṣūṇaṃ na hi (LP), ‘it matters not<BR>if there is a loss of one maund only’, i. e. such a case should<BR>not be considered a loss.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कु|कुः<BR>ku (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR>(CITD), a contraction of Telugu kuṇṭalu or kuccelu, a<BR>certain measure of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुच|कुचः<BR>kuca (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुचट<BR>kucaṭa (LP), disturbance of the peace of mind; cf. Guja-<BR>rātī kacvāṭ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुड्य|कुड्यं<BR>kuḍya, probably, ‘a mound’; see eḍuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल|कुलं|कुलः<BR>kula (LL), Jain; a particular section of the Jains.<BR>Cf. udhaḏīyā-jhumpaḏīya-kula (LP), ‘farmers on whom<BR>revenue is fixed in a lump sum and who live in huts’.<BR>Cf. kulam (EI 25), a land measure; equal to 2 halas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूल|कूलं<BR>kūla (SITI), tax on grains and pulses; cf. Tamil kiru-<BR>kūlam.<BR>Cf. Tamil kūlam (SII 1), a market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलब्राह्मण<BR>Kula-brāhmaṇa (SII 1), a family priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलचारिक<BR>Kulacārika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 119, text line 8),<BR>wrong reading of Kulavārika=Kulavāra (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलकरणि|कुलकरणिः<BR>Kulakaraṇi (EI 15; SII 11-1), a hereditary clerk or officer;<BR>a clerk; cf. the modern family name Kulkarṇī. The word<BR>occurs in the Sūdi inscription of Śaka 981 (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV,<BR>p. 91).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलाख्या<BR>kul-ākhyā (CII 3), a family appellation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलकुटुम्बिक<BR>Kula-kuṭumbika (LP), farmers who are permanently settled.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपञ्जिका<BR>kula-pañjikā, cf. vaṃśāvalī (IA 30).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपति|कुलपतिः<BR>Kulapati (EI 9), probably, the head of a school or institution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपुत्र|कुलपुत्रः<BR>Kulaputra (EI 22; CII 8), literally, ‘high-born’; epithet<BR>of a nobleman. See Kulaputraka.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-165" target="_blank">Page-165+ 40</a>]<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 156); explained as ‘the chief<BR>architect’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपुत्रक<BR>Kulaputraka (EI 22, 23), a nobleman. See Kulaputra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलरिक<BR>Kularika (CII 4), a potter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवार|कुलवारः<BR>Kulavāra (EI 23), arbitrator; also called Kulavārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवारिक<BR>Kulavārika, see Kulacārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवाय्<BR>kulavāy (IE 8-6), Bengali form of kulyavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलि|कुलिः<BR>kuli (IE 8-6; EI 28), Tamil; a small land measure equal<BR>to (1/240) of a pāḍagam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूलि<BR>kūli (SII 1), Tamil; hire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलिक|कुलिकः<BR>Kulika (EI 15, 35), ‘the head of a guild’; but<BR>cf. Prathama-kulika, ‘the foremost among the Kulikas’, who<BR>was the member of a board of administration like the Pañcāyat<BR>Board. Some inscriptions of the Gupta age mention a board<BR>of administration consisting of the Nagara-śreṣṭhin Sārthavāha,<BR>Prathama-Kulika and Prathama-Kāyastha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV,<BR>p. 130), where Kulika seems to mean ‘an artisan’. Kulika<BR>is also mentioned as a people probably meaning mercenary<BR>soldiers of the Kullu valley (ibid., Vol. XVII, p. 321); cf.<BR>Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 126-27.<BR>(HD), an officer in charge of ten villages who was granted<BR>a kula of land for his salary (Manu, VII. 119, and Kullūka<BR>thereon); also ‘an arbitrator as a tribunal’ (IHQ, Vol. XIX, p. 14).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्लक<BR>kullaka, cf. udak-āsīhāra-kullaka; probably, a kind of channel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्य|कुल्यं|कुल्यः<BR>kulya (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity equal to 8 droṇas.<BR>(IE 8-6; EI 29), a land measure; shortened form of<BR>kulyavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्यवाप<BR>kulyavāpa (IE 8-6; EI 28), ‘an area of land requiring one<BR>kulya measure of seed grains to be sown’; a land measure<BR>which was not the same in different ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्या<BR>kulyā (EI 13), a channel for irrigation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमार|कुमारं|कुमारः<BR>Kumāra (IE 8-2; EI 28, 30; BL; HD), designation of a<BR>prince or the king's heir-apparent; usually a prince younger<BR>than the Yuvarāja (heir-apparent). See CII, Vol. I, pp. 93,<BR>97; Vol. II, pp. 40, 48.<BR>Cf. Devī-kumāra (IA 18; CII 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमाराधिराज<BR>Kumārādhirāja (EI 12, 28), title of a ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारदिवान<BR>Kumāra-Divāna (BL), possibly, a Divāna or minister enjoying<BR>the status of a Kumāra or a Kumāra who was the Divāna. Cf.<BR>Kumār-āmātya, Kumāra-mahāpātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगदिआणक<BR>kumāra-gadiāṇaka (CII 4), taken to be the name of a coin<BR>by some scholars; but probably, a tax. Same as kumāra-gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगद्याण<BR>kumāra-gadyāṇa (IE 8-5; EI 4; HRS), probably, a tax<BR>of one gadyāṇa (i. e. the coin of that name) payable on the<BR>occasion of a prince's birth. See kumāra-gadiāṇaka, komarina-<BR>gadyāṇa, etc. Cf. Tamil kumara-kaccāṇam (EI 21), supposed to<BR>be a tax payable in coin for the maintenance of the temple of<BR>Kumāra or Subrahmaṇya (SITI). But kumāra-gadyāṇa is found in<BR>the records of the Gāhaḍavālas of Vārāṇasī, in whose dominions<BR>the god in question was not as popular as in the South.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगुरु<BR>Kumāra-guru (BL), probably, the royal preceptor enjoying<BR>the status of a Kumāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमरकच्चाणम्<BR>kumara-kaccāṇam (EI 21), a tax; cf. kumāra-gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारमहापात्र<BR>Kumāra-mahāpātra (EI 8-3; EI 28), a Mahāpātra enjoying<BR>the status of a Kumāra or a Kumāra who was the Mahāpātra;<BR>cf. Kumār-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारामात्य<BR>Kumār-āmātya (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), probably<BR>‘an Amātya enjoying the status of a Kumāra’. Cf. Tamil<BR>piḻḻaigaḻ-tanam (SITI), ‘the status of a Piḻḻai (prince)’, an<BR>officers’ cadre mainly composed of the junior members of<BR>the royal family. See Proc. 6th AIOC, pp. 211 ff.; Vogel,<BR>Ant. Ch. St., p. 123.<BR>(IE 8-3), in one case, a Kumār-āmātya was at first a<BR>Mantrin, but later became a Mahābalādhikṛta; in another case,<BR>a Kumārāmātya was also a Mantrin. Cf. Kumāra-mahāpātra, etc.<BR>Cf. Kumāra-varga=piḻḻaigaḻ-tanam (SITI), literally, ‘the<BR>status of the Piḻḻai or prince’; supposed to be an officers’ cadre<BR>composed mainly of the junior members of the royal family.<BR>(IE 8-3), also called Khādya(kū*)ṭapākika, Sāndhivigrahika,<BR>Mahādaṇdanāyaka, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारामात्याधिकरण<BR>Kumārāmāty-ādhikaraṇa (BL), office of the Kumār-āmātya<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारपादीयआमात्य<BR>Kumārapādīya-āmātya (BL), an Amātya serving a Kumāra<BR>or enjoying the status of a Kumāra. Cf. Kumār-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारास्य<BR>kumār-āsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारवर्ग<BR>Kumāra-varga (SITI), subordinate chieftains who consi-<BR>dered themselves as sons of the king or members of the royal<BR>family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारवृत्ति<BR>kumāra-vṛtti, cf. Tamil piḻḻai-vari (SITI), tax for the upkeep<BR>of the order of Piḻḻais or Kumāras (princes). Kumāra-vṛtti occurs<BR>in the inscriptions of the Western Cālukyas of Kalyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारीसाहस<BR>kumārī-sāhasa (IE 8-5; EI 3, 25; CII 4), ‘offence against<BR>an unmarried girl’; fine for abducting an unmarried girl;<BR>same as kumārīsāhasa-doṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हुमारीसाहसदोष<BR>humārīsāhasa-doṣa (EI 32), fine for abducting an<BR>unmarried girl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुम्भ|कुंभ|कुम्भं|कुंभः|कुम्भः<BR>kumbha (EI 5), the pinnacle of a temple; same as kalaśa.<BR>See also kumbhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुम्बाभिषेक<BR>kumb-ābhiṣeka (SII 3), same as Tamil tiru-kkalaśa-muḍittal<BR>(SITI), the consecration ceremony of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुम्भक|कुंभक|कुंभकः|कुम्भकः<BR>kumbhaka (LL), the base of a pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमोस<BR>kumosa (Chamba), forced labour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुंवर<BR>Kuṃvara (BL), regional modification of Kumāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणम्<BR>kāṇam (EI 16), name of a gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुञ्चि|कुंचि|कुंचिः|कुञ्चिः<BR>kuñci (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity usually regarded<BR>as equal to eight handfuls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुण्ड|कुंड|कुंडं|कुण्डं|कुंडः|कुण्डः<BR>kuṇḍa (EI 23), a spring.<BR>(EI 31), a pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूण्डि<BR>kūṇḍi (EI 23), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुण्डिका|कुंडिका<BR>kuṇḍikā (LP), a reservoir of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुञ्जर|कुंजर|कुंजरः|कुञ्जरः<BR>kuñjara (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुङ्कुमवस्त्र<BR>kuṅkuma-vastra (ASLV), ‘saffron-coloured cloth’; some-<BR>times the privilege to wear it was granted to particular persons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुन्नु<BR>kunnu (Chamba), also called kunu; a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुन्त|कुंत|कुंतः|कुन्तः<BR>kunta (Chamba), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुण्ट<BR>kuṇṭa (EI 21), a land measure; cf. guṇṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुन्तल|कुंतल|कुंतलः|कुन्तलः<BR>kuntala (EI 24), ‘one who wields the spear’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुनु<BR>kunu (Chamba), also called kunnu; a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूप|कूपः<BR>kūpa (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), an ordinary well;<BR>cf. vāpī which is a well with a flight of stairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूपदर्शक<BR>Kūpadarśaka (EI 24), a water-diviner; an inspector of<BR>wells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुप्यगृह<BR>kupya-gṛha (HRS), a store-house for forest produce as<BR>indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूर|कूरं|कूरः<BR>kūra, cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-vāsa (IE 8-5); ex-<BR>plained as ‘boiled rice’; but probably ‘unboiled rice’. The<BR>villagers were obliged to supply it to the touring officers of<BR>the king. See vodā, siddh-ānna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुरङ्गमद<BR>kuraṅga-mada (IA 18), musk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूर्म|कूर्मः|कूर्म्म|कूर्म्मः<BR>kūrma (EI 14), see madhya-kūrma, ‘a plot of land elevated<BR>in the middle.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कु|कुः<BR>kuṟṟam (IE 8-4), Tamil; a district or its subdivision;<BR>sometimes the same as nāḍu, but sometimes only the part of a<BR>nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुरुविन्द|कुरुविंद|कुरुविंदं|कुरुविन्दं|कुरुविंदः|कुरुविन्दः<BR>kuruvinda, cf. kuṟuvindam (SII 2), an inferior ruby.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुश|कुशं|कुशः<BR>kuśa, cf. kuśa-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil, tax on the potters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशल|कुशलं<BR>kuśala (IA 17), used in the sense of puṇya, religious merit;<BR>cf. kuśala-mūla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशलमूल<BR>kuśala-mūla (CII 2-1; ML), ‘the root of merit’; used<BR>to indicate ‘a pious deed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशलिन्<BR>Kuśalin (CII 3; SII 3; IA 9), ‘being in good health’,<BR>used in the preamble of charters to indicate the genuineness<BR>and validity of the grant made by the donors when they were<BR>in a healthy state of body and mind; epithet of a donor of<BR>copper-plate grants to indicate that the charters were issued when<BR>the donor was not subject to any disease like madness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुसूत्र<BR>kusūtra, (LP), wrong.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूट|कूटः<BR>Kūṭa (IA 7), cf. Rāṣṭrakūṭa, Deśakūṭa, Grāmakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटक|कूटकं|कूटकः<BR>Kūṭaka (EI 5), probably, headman of the cultivators;<BR>same as Grāmakūṭaka.<BR>(IE 8-5; EI 4, 26), tax for the maintenance of the Kūṭaka;<BR>see pravaṇikara-kūṭaka-prabhṛti-samast-ādāya (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p.<BR>101).<BR>(CII 4), a measure of capacity.<BR>(EI 2), a load or measure of salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटकोलस<BR>Kūṭakolasa (IE 8-3; EI 29), known from the Bhauma-<BR>Kara records of Orissa; official designation of uncertain import;<BR>cf. Kūṭa or Kūṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुताम्र<BR>ku-tāmra (IA 30), a fraudulent charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटशासन<BR>kūṭa-śāsana (EI 7; IA 30; BL), a forged charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटायुक्त<BR>Kūṭāyukta (EI 22), official designation; probably Kūṭa<BR>(Kūṭaka) and Āyukta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटी<BR>kuṭī (IE 8-8), a factory; cf. nīla-kuṭī.<BR>(LL), a Buddhist temple; an abbreviation of gandhakuṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटिल|कुटिलं<BR>Kuṭila, cf. Siddhamātṛkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्<BR>Kuṭum (EI 33; LP), abbreviation of Kuṭumbika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्ब|कुटुंब|कुटुंबं|कुटुम्बः<BR>kuṭumba (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बक्षेत्र<BR>kuṭumba-kṣetra (CII 4), an ancestral field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बवृत्ति<BR>kuṭumba-vṛtti, cf. Kannaḍa kuttumbitti (EI 18), gift of<BR>land for the maintenance of the donee's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बयात्रा<BR>kuṭumba-yātrā (EI 12; BL), name of a religious ceremony;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-169" target="_blank">Page-169+ 39</a>]<BR>a procession of the royal family to the temple of the family<BR>deity on the occasion of the king's coronation or a marriage<BR>in the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बिन्|कुटुंबिन्<BR>Kuṭumbin (EI 12, 17, 23; SII 1), a cultivator; an agri-<BR>culturist householder; a householder or ryot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बिनी|कुटुंबिनी<BR>kuṭumbinī (EI 19; CII 2-1; ML), originally, ‘the wife<BR>of a householder’; later, ‘wife’ in general (cf. Sel. Ins., p. 164).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुत्तुम्बित्ति<BR>kuttumbitti, Kannaḍa; cf. grant of certain towns and kuttum-<BR>bittis as aṅuga-jīvita or fief (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, pp.<BR>81-83); mentioned along with bhatta-grāma (Sanskrit bhakta-<BR>grāma), ‘provision village’ (ibid., Vol. XVIII, p. 193); pro-<BR>bably, Sanskrit kuṭumba-vṛtti, grant made for the maintenance<BR>of the donee's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुवर|कुवरः<BR>Kuvara (BL), regional modification of Kumāra. Cf.<BR>Kuṃvar (Kuñar), Kunwar, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लब्धि|लब्धिः<BR>labdhi, ‘nine’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 345).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाभ|लाभः<BR>lābha (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाभारिका<BR>lābhārikā, lābhālikā (Chamba), Sanskritised form of the<BR>land measure called lāhaḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्<BR>lag, cf. lagitvā (EI 9), ‘commencing from, beginning<BR>with’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाग<BR>lāga (EI 11), a cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लगडा<BR>lagaḍā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309), a load; a bar of<BR>metal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लगण|लगणः<BR>lagaṇa (Chamba), fines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लागसम्बन्ध<BR>lāga-sambandha, lāga-bhāga (LP), ‘any connection.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्गावयित्वा<BR>laggāvayitvā (IE 8-5), ‘having planted’; cf. Bengali lāgāiyā.<BR>See JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 202.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लागिद्रम्माः<BR>lāgi-drammāḥ (LP), ‘expenses incurred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्न|लग्नं|लग्नः<BR>lagna (IA 17; SII 1), an astronomical term; the rising<BR>of a sign of the zodiac or its passing the meridian. See Ind.<BR>Ant., Vol. XVIII, pp. 16 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्नदेवी<BR>lagna-devī (IA 30), Jain; a stone-cow.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाहडि<BR>lāhaḍi, lāhaḍī (Chamba), a land measure. See lābhā-<BR>rikā, lābhālikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लकार<BR>lakāra (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लकटा<BR>lakaṭā (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain. Cf. ārdraka-lakaṭā,<BR>probably, dried ginger stick or undried fire-wood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षदान<BR>lakṣa-dāna (EI 12), name of a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षहोम|लक्षहोमः<BR>lakṣa-homa (SII 11-1), name of a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षण|लक्षणं|लक्षणः<BR>lakṣaṇa (IA 18), the sexual parts; the male organ; cf.<BR>nirlakṣitavya, to be castrated.<BR>(CII 1), branding.<BR>(SII 3; SITI), a document or deed; an inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षणाध्यक्ष<BR>Lakṣaṇ-ādhyakṣa (HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra,<BR>the superintendent of the mint, or royal dues received by the<BR>superintendent of the mint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाकुल<BR>Lākula, also called Lākuleśvara (EI 15), a Śaiva sect follow-<BR>ing Lakulīśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लकुलेश्वरागम<BR>Lakuleśvar-āgama (CITD), a form of Śaivism associated<BR>with Lakulīśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लालखण्डेयका<BR>Lāḻa-khaṇḍeya-kāṟar-adhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sans-<BR>krit; ‘superintendent of the revenue from Lāṭa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लम्बापटह<BR>lambā-paṭaha (EI 12), a kind of drum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाञ्छन|लांछन|लांछनं|लाञ्छनं|लाञ्छनः<BR>lāñchana (EI 28), an emblem. Cf. cihna.<BR>(EI 9), the [royal] emblem; cf. Tamil lāñjanai-ppeṟu,<BR>lāñjinai-ppeṟu, ilāñjai-ppeṟu (SITI), the royal seal.<BR>(CII 3, etc.), a crest as distinguished from dhvaja or a<BR>banner. Cf. cihna.<BR>(HA), the distinguishing mark or symbol of a Jina<BR>image, which helps one to identify the different Jinas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाञ्छित|लांछित<BR>lāñchita (EI 29), ‘registered with a seal (lāñchana)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाङ्गडि<BR>lāṅgaḍi (LP), a cart or carriage; cf. uchālaka-bhṛta-lāṅgaḍi,<BR>‘a cartful of household furniture’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लङ्क<BR>Laṅka (EI 19), a carpenter; cf. Leṅka, Leṅkā, Buḏhāleṅkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लपित|लपितं<BR>lapita (CII 1), used in the sense of ukta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लसं|लस<BR>la-saṃ (IA 18), abbreviation of lakṣmaṇasena-saṃvatsara,<BR>‘the era of Lakṣmaṇasena’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लष्टि<BR>laṣṭi (CII 4), same as Sanskrit yaṣṭi; a memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लत्तलूरपुरपरमेश्वर<BR>Lattalūrapura-parameśvara (IE 8-2), a typical title of the<BR>Rāṣṭrakūṭas claiming the city of Lattalūra to have been their<BR>original home. Similar titles are quite common in the early<BR>medieval records especially of the Kannaḍa-speaking area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लौकि<BR>lauki°, laukika° (IA 18), abbreviation of laukika-gaṇanayā.<BR>Laukika-saṃvatsara is a year of the Laukika era.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लवलिका<BR>lavalikā (LP), loquacity; cf. Gujarātī lavlav or lavāro.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लवण|लवणं|लवणः<BR>lavaṇa, cf. a-lavaṇa-khātaka (IE 8-5); salt [the produc-<BR>tion of which was the monopoly of the king or landlord].<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-171" target="_blank">Page-171+ 40</a>]<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘five’; also ‘cutting [of plants]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लवणाकर|लवणाकरः<BR>lavaṇ-ākara (EI 24, EI 30), a salt pit or mine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लयन|लयनं<BR>layana (LL, EI 22), Prakrit leṇa; an excavated cave; a<BR>cave; the residence of monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेख|लेखः<BR>lekha (LP), official letter; cf. likhita, a private letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखाधिकारिन्<BR>Lekh-ādhikārin (HD), secretary. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, III. 206.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखहार|लेखहारः<BR>Lekhahāra, Lekhahāraka (EI 21; HD), the carrier of letters<BR>(see Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 319).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखक|लेखकः<BR>Lekhaka (CII 3, etc.), a writer; a technical term for one<BR>who wrote a record [on copper plates, stone slabs, etc., in<BR>order to facilitate its correct engraving by an artisan], as<BR>opposed to the composer of the document (see also likhita).<BR>(IE 8-3; EI 28, 30; LL; HD), a writer, scribe or clerk<BR>(see Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XVI, pp. 582 and 605; Viṣṇudharmottara,<BR>II. 24. 26-28; Śukranītisāra, II. 120).<BR>(LP), a record or document; mistake for lekhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखनाध्यक्ष<BR>Lekhan-ādhyakṣa (CII 3), the superintendent of the<BR>writing of documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखयितृ<BR>Lekhayitṛ (EI 12), one who is responsible for getting a<BR>grant recorded; mentioned together with Śāsayitṛ; cf. Ājñapti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखित|लेखितं<BR>Lekhita, Lekhitṛ (EI 24), same as Lekhaka; a writer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेण्क<BR>Leṇka (EI 3; SII 11-1), Leṅkā (EI 28), a servant; a<BR>Śūdra servant; a writer, according to some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेप्यकार<BR>Lepyakāra, model-maker (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1,<BR>p. 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिखित|लिखितं<BR>likhita (CII 3, 4, etc.), ‘written’; a technical term indi-<BR>cating the manual drafting or writing of a record, as opposed<BR>to the composition and engraving of it; see also lekhaka.<BR>(LP), a private letter; cf. lekha, an official letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिङ्ग|लिंग|लिंगं|लिङ्गं<BR>liṅga (BL; SII 1; CII 3, etc.), same as śiva-liṅga; the<BR>phallic emblem of Śiva; the emblem connected with the worship<BR>of Śiva; generally named after the founder with the suffix<BR>īśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिङ्गोरण<BR>liṅgoraṇa (IA 11), conjecturally translated as ‘the festival<BR>of rams [to be sacrificed] to the liṅgas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिपि|लिपिः<BR>lipi (SII 3), a letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिपिकर|लिपिकरः<BR>Lipikara (IE 8-3; EI 3; HD), a scribe or writer. See<BR>CII, Vol. I, p. 176; Pāṇini, III. 2. 21.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिपिकृत्कुल<BR>Lipikṛt-kula (EI 33), the community of scribes; the<BR>Kāyastha community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोभविजयिन्<BR>Lobha-vijayin (CII 4), ‘an avaricious conqueror’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोचन|लोचनं<BR>locana (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोह|लोहं|लोहः<BR>loha, cf. so-loha-lavaṇ-ākara (IE 8-5), ‘together with mines<BR>of metals and salt pits [the right of which normally belonged<BR>to the king]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहचर्मकार<BR>Loha-carma-kāra (EI 24), workers in metal and leather.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहडिया<BR>lohaḍiyā, name of a coin equal to 20 pāvīsās and 100<BR>cowrie-shells; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 238.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहार<BR>Lohāra (EI 4; BL), modification of Lohakāra; a black-<BR>smith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहवाणिज<BR>Loha-vāṇija (LL) an iron-monger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहिककारुक<BR>Lohika-kāruka (LL), a worker in metal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहित|लोहितं|लोहितः<BR>Lohita (ML), a blood relation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहितक|लोहितकं|लोहितकः<BR>lohitaka, weight equal to 3 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p.<BR>46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोक|लोकः<BR>loka (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’; sometimes also ‘three’;<BR>rarely used to indicate ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोकपाल|लोकपालः<BR>Lokapāla (CII 3, etc.), a guardian of one of the quarters<BR>of the world, originally conceived as four in number and later<BR>as eight.<BR>(EI 15), cf. the king called ‘the fifth Lokapāla’, the four<BR>Lokapālas (guardians of the four quarters) being originally<BR>Yama of the south, Varuṇa of the west, Kubera of the north<BR>and Vāsava of the east. In the same sense, the king was<BR>also called madhyama-loka-pāla, though madhyama-loka may<BR>also mean ‘the earth’ standing midway between the heavens<BR>and the netherworld. See Suc. Sāt., pp. 196, 202; Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXII, p. 93. Cf. Pañcama-lokapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः<BR>Ma (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Maṅgala-vāra, Tuesday.<BR>(PJS), abbreviation of Mahattama, Mantrin, Mahetā<BR>(meaning ‘a clerk’ or ‘a teacher’ in Gujarātī), etc. (especially<BR>in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मा<BR>mā (IE 8-6; SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a land measure equal<BR>to one-twentieth of a veli; also the name of a weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माड|माडः<BR>māḍa (IE 8-8; EI 7), Telugu; same as Oḏiyā māḏha or<BR>māḏhā and Tamil māḍai; a coin of gold or silver; 40 ratis in<BR>weight; cf. biruda-māḍa, malla-māḍa, mallanandi-māḍa, surabhi-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-173" target="_blank">Page-173+ 40</a>]<BR>māḍa, gaṇḍa-māḍa, kulottuṅga-māḍa (EI 29), gandhavāraṇamāḍa (or<BR>gandhahasti-māḍa), cāmara-māḍa, uttama-gaṇḍamāḍa, padmanidhi-<BR>malla-māḍa, rājarāja-māḍa, rājendracol13a-māḍa, etc. The gaṇḍa-māḍa<BR>is sometimes called kārṣāpaṇa, niṣka and gaṇḍaniṣka and is also<BR>characterised in a few cases with the epithet ‘small’. See<BR>māḍai, māḍha. Note names like kulottuṅga-māḍa, a coin issued by<BR>the Col13a king Kulottuṅga. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 43.<BR>(CITD), Telugu; half a pagoda; half of a dīnār or the<BR>tenth of a paṇa (cf. badi-māḍuvulu); half or 50 per cent of<BR>revenue, etc.; a weight of gold; money in general. Four<BR>māḍas are equal to one carṣam (karṣa?).<BR>(IE 8-5), probably, payment of 50 per cent; see māḍalu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडबडिपातुक<BR>māḍa-baḍi-pātuka (CITD), Telugu; an unknown coin<BR>with a fraction of the value of a māḍa. Baḍi means ‘petty’ and<BR>pātika ‘a quarter’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मदहस्तिपादरक्षापालक<BR>Madahastipādarakṣā-pālaka (IA 30), explained as ‘the captain<BR>of the guards of elephants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडै<BR>māḍai (IE 8-8; EI 7), Tamil; same as māḍha, māḍhā<BR>and māḍa; cf. rājarājaṉ-māḍai, madhurāntakaṉ-māḍai, bhujabala-<BR>māḍai (EI 7), etc.; often a gold coin (SII 12). Tamil māḍai<BR>is the same as māṣā derived from Sanskrit māṣaka.<BR>(SITI), name of a gold coin; a half pagoda; cf. nellūr-<BR>māḍai (SITI), a coin current in olden days and issued from<BR>Nellore; also known as nellūr-ppudu-māḍai; also cf. gaṇḍagopālaṉ-<BR>māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडलु<BR>māḍalu (IE 8-5; EI 33), same as māḍa, a levy; probably,<BR>‘payment of 50 per cent’; cf. Kannaḍa pannasa or pannāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मडम्ब<BR>maḍamba (EI 24), a territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मदनतिथि<BR>Madana-tithi (IA 17), Caitra ba-di 13.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडास्यात<BR>māḍāsyāta (CII 3), usually taken to be a word of uncertain<BR>import, but may really be the name of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मद्दल<BR>maddala (SII 3), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माढ<BR>māḍha, māḍhā (IE 8-8; EI 28, 29, 30, 33), Oḏiyā; a silver<BR>coin; also a gold coin; 40 ratis in weight; same as māḍa or<BR>māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्य|मध्यं|मध्यः<BR>madhya (CII 1), middle course.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यदिवस<BR>madhya-divasa (ML), mid-day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यकूर्म<BR>madhya-kūrma (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV p. 98), probably, a<BR>plot of land elevated in the middle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यम|मध्यमं|मध्यमः<BR>madhyama (CII 1), a class between the upper and the lower.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यमलोकपाल<BR>Madhyamalokapāla, epithet of kings; cf. Lokapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यस्थ|मध्यस्थः<BR>madhyastha (EI 8, 25; SII 2; ASLV; SITI), a neutral<BR>person, generally the village headman; a mediator or arbitrator;<BR>secretary of the village assembly (SII 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मद्यपान<BR>madya-pāna (SII 3), intoxicating drinks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मद्यवहनक<BR>madya-vahanaka (IE 8-8), a carrier of wine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मग|मगः<BR>Maga (EI 9; BL), the same as Śākadvīpīya; a community<BR>of Brāhmaṇas; name of the members of the Persian priestly<BR>community (Magi) settled in India and absorbed in the Brāh-<BR>maṇa class.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मागाणि<BR>māgāṇi (ASLV), an administrative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मागाणिस्थान<BR>māgāṇi-sthāna (EI 13), epithet of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महा<BR>Mahā (PJS), abbreviation of Mahājana (especially in<BR>medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR>Cf. Mahā-Mūla (i. e. the elder Mūla) distinguished from<BR>Kṣudra-Mūla (i. e. the younger Mūla); also Mahā-Dharmagiri<BR>and Kṣudra-Dharmagiri, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलाधिकरणिक<BR>Mahābalādhikaraṇika (IE 8-3), superintendent of the<BR>office of the Mahābalādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलाधिकृत<BR>Mahābalādhikṛta (HD), ‘the great commander’; desig-<BR>nation of a military officer who was, in one case, originally a<BR>Mantrin (IE 8-3); see Balādhikṛta and Mahābalādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलाध्यक्ष<BR>Mahābalādhyakṣa (CII 3), military title. See Balādhyakṣa<BR>and Mahābalādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलकोष्ठिक<BR>Mahābalakoṣṭhika (IE 8-3), treasurer of the military<BR>department. Cf. raṇabhāṇḍāgār-ādhikaraṇa (Raychaudhuri, PHAI,<BR>1950, p. 563).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभाण्डागार<BR>mahābhāṇḍāgāra (EI 12), treasury; cf. bhāṇḍāgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभाण्डागारिक<BR>Mahābhāṇḍāgārika (IE 8-2; HD) treasurer; one of the<BR>designations often included in the pañca-mahāśabda as indicated<BR>by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 39; Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>IV. 142. Cf. Bhāṇḍāgārika.<BR>(CII 4), explained as ‘the Chancellor of the Exchequer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभाण्डागारिन्<BR>Mahābhāṇḍāgārin (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa Hiriyabhaṇḍāgārin; some-<BR>times also called Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभारतवृत्ति<BR>Mahābhārata-vṛtti (SITI), land endowed to persons for<BR>expounding the Mahābhārata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोगपति<BR>Mahābhogapati (EI 26), official designation; probably, the<BR>superintendent of rent-free holdings; cf. Mahābhogika, Bhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोगिक<BR>Mahābhogika (EI 26; HD), a big Jāgīrdār; cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-175" target="_blank">Page-175+ 40</a>]<BR>Vol. XII, p. 9; also cf. Bhogika and Mahābhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोज<BR>Mahābhoja (IE 8-2; EI 7, 22, 28; LL), a big Jāgīrdār;<BR>title of a feudatory ruler; see Bhojaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोजी<BR>Mahābhojī (LL), wife of a Mahābhoja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभूत|महाभूतं<BR>mahābhūta (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभूतघटदान<BR>mahābhūtaghaṭa-dāna (SITI), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभूतक<BR>mahābhūtaka (EI 14), name of a mahādāna; same as<BR>mahābhūtaghaṭa-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाचतुर्दशीपर्वन्<BR>mahācaturdaśī-parvan (EI 9), 14th tithi of the bright half<BR>of a month.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाचैत्य<BR>mahācaitya (LL), a great caitya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादाह<BR>mahādāha (SITI), name of a hell which one is supposed to<BR>pass through after death on the way to the other world.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादान|महादानं<BR>mahādāna (EI 7, 16; CII 4); a great gift, 16 of which are<BR>enumerated in the Purāṇas (see Hist. Dharm., Vol. II, pp.<BR>869-70; Suc. Sāt. L. Dec., pp. 50f.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानाक्षपटलाधिकृत<BR>Mahādān-ākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (EI 31), officer in charge of<BR>the accounts section of the gift department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानपति<BR>Mahādānapati (EI 23; ML; HD), ‘the great gift-lord’,<BR>designation of one who gives a gift. Cf. CII, Vol. II, Pt. i., p.<BR>28. Cf. Dānapati (EI 28), dedicator of an image of a god on<BR>the fulfilment of a desire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानपत्नी<BR>Mahādānapatnī (EI 20), feminine form of Mahādānapati;<BR>a female bestower of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादण्डनायक<BR>Mahādaṇḍanāyaka (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL.; HD);<BR>commander of forces; also called Khādya(kū*) ṭapākika, Sān-<BR>dhivigrahika, Kumārāmātya, etc., additionally; one of the desig-<BR>nations sometimes included in the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case<BR>of Maitraka Dhruvasena I (Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, p. 7; Ind.<BR>Ant., Vol. IV, p. 105). The five mahāśabdas applied to Dhruva-<BR>sena are Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, Mahāsāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra, Mahā-<BR>kārtākṛtika and Mahārāja. See Daṇḍanāyaka, Sarvadaṇḍa-<BR>nāyaka, Mahāsarvadaṇḍanāyaka, Daṇḍapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानिक<BR>Mahādānika (CII 4), head of the department of charity;<BR>officer in charge of donations; sometimes explained as ‘the officer<BR>superintending the performance of the mahādāna ceremonies’<BR>(HD). See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91. Cf. Dharmādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादौःसाधसाधनिक<BR>Mahādauḥsādhasādhanika (HD), cf. Dauḥsādhasādhanika.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादेव|महादेवः<BR>mahādeva (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादेवी<BR>Mahādevī (IE 8-2; EI 7; CII 3, 4; HD), a queen;<BR>often wrongly taken as the first wife of a king or his chief<BR>queen (SITI); a title of the wives originally of paramount<BR>sovereigns and later also of feudatory rulers; cf. Devī, Agra-<BR>mahādevī, Mahāmahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाधर्माधिकरणिक<BR>Mahādharmādhikaraṇika (CII 4), explained as the chief<BR>justice (HD), Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309. See Dharmādhikara-<BR>ṇika and Mahādharmādhyakṣa, head of the department of<BR>religious; affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाधर्माध्यक्ष<BR>Mahādharm-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3; EI 12, 21, 26, 33; HD),<BR>explained as ‘the chief judge’; but really ‘officer in charge of<BR>charities, etc.’; cf. Dharmādhyakṣa and Mahādharmādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाधिराज<BR>Mahādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 12), royal title; cf. Adhirāja;<BR>also cf. Dharmamahādhirāja (EI 12).<BR>(CII 3), a feudatory title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाध्यक्ष<BR>Mahādhyakṣa (EI 12; CII 4), ‘the chief superintendent’;<BR>cf. Adhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादीक्षित<BR>Mahādīkṣita (EI 4), cf. Dīkṣita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादोष<BR>mahā-doṣa, cf. mahādoṣa-vivarjita (EI 23) as an epithet of<BR>the gift village; probably, fines for great crimes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाद्वादशक<BR>mahā-dvādaśaka (IE 8-4), ‘the great twelve’; suffixed<BR>to the name of a district probably consisting of twelve<BR>Parganās or sub-districts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाद्वादशी<BR>mahā-dvādaśī (EI 9; IA 26), also called pāpanāśinī; name<BR>of a tithi; eight kinds of the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाद्वाराधिपति<BR>Mahādvār-ādhipati (BL), possibly the same as ‘the lord<BR>(i. e. the guard) of the Dvāra (a pass)’ of the Rājataraṅgiṇī;<BR>mentioned along with the Mahāsainyapati and Mahāpratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागजपति<BR>Mahāgajapati (EI 30), ‘the great lord of elephants’; cf.<BR>Gajapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागणस्थ<BR>Mahāgaṇastha (IE 8-3; EI 26; HD), probably, the<BR>chairman of a guild or superintendent of guilds; cf. Gaṇastha<BR>and Gaṇattār. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 160.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागन्धकूटी<BR>mahā-gandhakūṭī (LL), a Buddhist temple; cf. gandhakuṭī<BR>and kūṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागोवल्लभ<BR>Mahāgovallabha (EI 24), the superintendent of cattle;<BR>see Govallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाग्रहार<BR>mahāgrahāra (SII 11-1), see agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाग्राम|महाग्रामः<BR>mahāgrāma (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit; a group<BR>of villages; cf. grām-āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाग्रामिक<BR>Mahāgrāmika (IE 8-3), ruler of a mahāgrāma (subdivision<BR>of a district or a group of villages).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाजन|महाजनः<BR>Mahājana (SITI; ASLV), Brāhmaṇa residents of the<BR>entire village; all the members of the village assembly;<BR>general body of the sabhā or village assembly.<BR>(IE 8-3), a member of village council.<BR>(EI 8), a merchant.<BR>(LP), generally, the merchants, magnates, grandees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाजनसभा<BR>mahājana-sabhā (IE-3), village council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाजय<BR>mahājaya, mahājayā (EI 7; IA 26), name of a tithi; same<BR>as su-di 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकरण<BR>mahākaraṇa, cf. sa-mañca-mahākaraṇa (IE 8-5), an expression<BR>of doubtful import; probably, ‘official records’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकरणाध्यक्ष<BR>Mahākaraṇādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), head of the department of<BR>records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकरणिक<BR>Mahākaraṇika (CII 4; HD), the chief secretary; the chief<BR>scribe. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309. Cf. Karaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकर्तक<BR>Mahākartaka (LL), epithet of an artisan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकार्ताकृतिक<BR>Mahākārtākṛtika (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3; HD), official<BR>designation of uncertain import; probably, a reporter who<BR>informed the king about the progress of big undertakings; some-<BR>times explained as ‘the royal agent or judge’; one of the desig-<BR>nations sometimes included in the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case<BR>of Maitraka Dhruvasena I. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306.<BR>See Kārtākṛtika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकार्त्तिकी|महाकार्तिकी<BR>Mahākārttikī (EI 11; CII 4), full-moon day of the month<BR>of Kārttika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकटुक<BR>Mahākaṭuka (IE 8-3), official designation of uncertain<BR>import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकवि|महाकविः<BR>Mahākavi (CII 4), ‘great poet’; title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकविचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Mahākavicakravartin (EI 30; BL), title of a poet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाखड्गधर<BR>Mahākhaḍgadhara (EI 30), official designation. See<BR>Khaḍgadhara, Khaḍgagrāha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाखलरक्षक<BR>Mahākhalarakṣaka (LP), superintendent of the king's<BR>threshing floors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाखेट<BR>mah-ākheṭa (EI 5), a great hunting expedition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकोष्ठागारिन्<BR>Mahākoṣṭhāgārin (SII 2), ‘great treasurer’; cf.<BR>Koṣṭhāgārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकोट्टपाल<BR>Mahākoṭṭapāla (CII 4), chief guardian of a fort or the<BR>forts; cf. Koṭṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्ष|महाक्षः<BR>Mahākṣa (EI 33), abbreviation of Mahākṣpaṭalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षनि<BR>mahākṣa-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of mahākṣapaṭalika-<BR>nirīkṣita, ‘examined by the Mahākṣapaṭalika’; ni may not be<BR>an abbreviation of nibaddha (registered) in this case since<BR>mahākṣa-ni is often used along with several other expressions<BR>of the kind. See ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपालकरण<BR>mahākṣapāla-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the<BR>depository of legal documents’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलाधिकरणाधिकृत<BR>Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhikaraṇ-ādhikṛta (BL) superintendent of the<BR>office of the akṣapaṭala or mahākṣpaṭala department; some-<BR>times regarded as the same as Mahākṣpaṭalika (HD). Cf.<BR>Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलाधिकृत<BR>Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (BL), same as Mahākṣapaṭalādhi-<BR>karaṇ-ādhikṛta or Mahākṣapaṭalādhyakṣa; also called Mahā-<BR>kṣapāla (cf. karaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलाध्यक्ष<BR>Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa (BL), see Akṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलिक<BR>Mahākṣapaṭalika (IE 8-3; CII 3; EI 30; BL; HD), record-<BR>keeper and accountant; same as Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa; see<BR>Akṣapaṭalika, sometimes explained as ‘the chief keeper of records’<BR>(CII 4), Cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 120.<BR>(IE 8-3), mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलिन्<BR>Mahākṣapaṭalin (EI 33), same as Mahākṣapaṭalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षत्रप|महाक्षत्रपः<BR>Mahākṣatrapa (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 16, 27; CII 4; BL; ML;<BR>HD), the great Satrap or provincial governor; feudatory title<BR>of foreign origin; originally, title of a provincial governor;<BR>later the Śakas of Western India continued to use it even when<BR>they were practically independent. Cf. CII, Vol. II, p. 48. See<BR>Kṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकुलपति<BR>Mahākulapati (EI 29), epithet of a priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकुमार|महाकुमारः<BR>Mahākumāra (CII 4), title of a prince or the crown-<BR>prince.<BR>(IE 8-2; EI 28; BL), title of certain rulers; title of some<BR>semi-independent Paramāra rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकुमारामात्य<BR>Mahākumārāmātya (EI 29; CII 3; HD), see Kumārāmātya.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महालया<BR>mahālayā (EI33), name of a tithi; pūrṇimānta Āśvina-badi 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महले<BR>Mahale, Mahaleka (IA 9), Ceylonese; official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महल्लक|महल्लकः<BR>Mahallaka (IE 8-5; EI 25), probably, a member of the<BR>Pañcāyat; explained as ‘city elders’; cf. yat … nagara-mahallakā<BR>vicārya vadante, etc.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-179" target="_blank">Page-179+ 40</a>]<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20); also called Mahallāka,<BR>Mahallika.<BR>(CII 4), same as Mahattara.<BR>(EI 2; CII 1), an old man. In Oḏiyā, it means a guard<BR>of the royal harem.<BR>(CII 1), big, vast.<BR>(EI 23), a landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महं|मह|महः<BR>Mahaṃ (BL), abbreviation of Mahattama.<BR>(LP), abbreviation of Mahantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मह|महं|महः<BR>Maha, Mahaṃ (IA 18), abbreviations of Mahattara or<BR>Mahattama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहादेवी<BR>Mahāmahādevī (BL), designation of a queen or the chief<BR>queen; cf. Mahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहन्तक<BR>Mahāmahantaka (EI 7; CII 4; HD), same as Mahā-<BR>mahattaka. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहत्तक<BR>Mahāmahattaka (EI 25, 33; CII 4; HD; BL), head of<BR>a group of villages or of the village council; chief among the<BR>village headmen; same as Mahāmahattara, Mahāmahattama.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 362. See Mahattaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहत्तम<BR>Mahāmahattama (BL), same as Mahāmahattaka, Mahā-<BR>mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहत्तर<BR>Mahāmahattara (IE 8-3; EI 26, 29; BL), mentioned along<BR>with the Mahattara; probably, the chairman of the council<BR>of Mahattaras; same as Mahāmahattaka, Mahāmahattama; see<BR>Mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहावारुणी<BR>mahāmahāvāruṇī (EI 4), name of a tithi; same as vāruṇī<BR>and mahā-vāruṇī; amānta Caitra-badi 13 with Śatabhiṣā-nakṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहिषी<BR>Mahāmahiṣī (IE 8-2), cf. Piriya-arasi (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa;<BR>title of a chief queen; see Mahiṣī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहोपाध्याय|महामहोपाध्यायः<BR>Mahāmahopādhyāya, title of certain scholars like Jīvadeva<BR>of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महमै<BR>mahamai (EI 17), Tamil magamai; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामख<BR>mahāmakha (EI 25), a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Mahāmaṇḍala-cakravartin (EI 9), royal title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलाचार्य<BR>Mahāmaṇḍal-ācārya (EI 26), title of a Buddhist teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलाधिपति<BR>Mahāmaṇḍal-ādhipati (EI 29), same as Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलनाथ<BR>Mahāmaṇḍala-nātha (HD), same as Mahāmaṇḍleśvara. Cf.<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 227.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलेश्वर<BR>Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 4; HD; BL;<BR>SITI; CITD), according to the lexicons, a sovereign ruler<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-180" target="_blank">Page-180+ 40</a>]<BR>who is the lord of 40 yojanas of land and a lakh of villages; but,<BR>in inscriptions, generally, the governor of a district or pro-<BR>vince; title of a feudatory ruler or governor (see Bomb. Gaz.,<BR>Vol. XXI, p. 354); see Maṇḍaleśvara essentially meaning ‘the<BR>ruler of a maṇḍala or district’; also called Mahāmaṇḍalika, etc.,<BR>cf. Mahāmaṇḍaleśvar-ādhipati. The status of a Mahāmaṇdal-<BR>eśvara seems to have been superior to that of a Maṇḍaleśvara,<BR>while Mahāmaṇḍaleśvarādhipati apparently enjoyed a still higher<BR>rank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलेश्वराधिपति<BR>Mahāmaṇḍaleśvar-ādhipati (IE 8-2; EI 23), title of a<BR>feudatory higher in rank than a Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara (cf. Mahā-<BR>sāmantādhipati); a feudatory who had some subordinate chiefs<BR>under him; cf. Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara, Maṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलिक<BR>Mahāmaṇḍalika (IE 8-3), feudatory title; see Mahā-<BR>maṇḍalīka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलीक<BR>Mahāmaṇḍalīka (HD), same as Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara. Cf.<BR>Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 35. See Mahāmaṇḍalika, Mahāmaṇḍale-<BR>śvar-ādhipati, Māṇḍalika etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डप<BR>mahāmaṇḍapa (SITI), a large pillared hall next to the<BR>ardha-maṇḍapa in a temple; also called mukha-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामन्त्रिन्|महामंत्रिन्<BR>Mahāmantrin (EI 12, 30; CII 4; IA 19; BL; HD), ‘the<BR>chief minister or counsellor’. See Mantrin. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>II, p. 309.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामनुष्य<BR>Mahāmanuṣya (IE 8-3), probably, a landlord; mentioned<BR>in the list of a king's subordinates. cf. Mahājana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्र|महामात्रः<BR>Mahāmātra (IE 8-3), cf. Prakrit Mahāmāta (EI 3); a high<BR>executive officer employed in various capacities; cf. Nagara-<BR>vyavahārika-mahāmātra, Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra, Dharma-mahāmātra,<BR>etc.; adopted in Greek as Mamātrai. See CII, Vol. I, p. 92,<BR>etc.; Arthaśāstra, I. 12, V. 1; etc.; Kāmasūtra, V. 5. 17. 33 and<BR>35. The word Mahāmātra in Manu, IX. 259, is explained by<BR>Medhātithi as ‘the Mantrin, Purohita and others’ and by Kullūka<BR>as meaning ‘the professional tamers of elephants’. (SITI)<BR>explained as ‘a senior minister.’ See Mātra in a similar sense.<BR>Cf. Antaḥpura-mahāmātra in the Masulipatnam plates of<BR>Amma II (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR>(EI 28; CII 4), ‘an elephant-driver’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्रगण<BR>Mahāmātra-gaṇa (CII 4), corporation of elephant-drivers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्रनगरव्यवहारिक<BR>Mahāmātra-nagaravyavahārika (CII 1), an executive officer<BR>who is the judge or administrator of a city.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामातृका<BR>mahāmātṛkā, ‘mother's mother’; used side by side with<BR>āryikā, ‘father's mother’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 225).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्य|महामात्यः<BR>Mahāmātya (IE 8-3; EI 25; CII 4; BL), the chief minister<BR>or executive officer; the prime minister or a viceroy (HD);<BR>see Amātya; sometimes also called a Mahāpradhāna additionally.<BR>Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 122; Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 242.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्यवर<BR>Mahāmātya-vara (EI 30), chief minister; cf. Amātya and<BR>Mahāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामेरुश्रीकीर्तिस्तम्भ<BR>mahāmeru-śrī-kīrtistambha (BL), name of Mahārāṇā<BR>Kumbhā's tower at Chitor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामुद्राधिकृत<BR>Mahāmudr-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 12, 14, 15; HD), the<BR>keeper of the royal seal; officer in charge of the royal seal; cf.<BR>Mahāmudr-āmātya. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामुद्रामात्य<BR>Mahāmudr-āmātya (IA 11), same as Mahāmudr-ādhikṛta;<BR>cf. Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामुरज<BR>mahā-muraja (ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महान<BR>Mahāna (Chamba), a writer; possibly from Sanskrit<BR>Mahantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानाड्प्रभु<BR>Mahānāḍ-prabhu (ASLV), the Paṭṭanasvāmin (q. v.) of<BR>the rural areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानाडु<BR>mahā-nāḍu (SITI), general assembly of the mercantile<BR>community of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानगर<BR>mahā-nagara (SITI), merchants' guild of a city; cf.<BR>nagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महणलोक<BR>mahaṇaloka, possibly the same as Sanskrit mahalloka=<BR>mahājana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानसाध्यक्ष<BR>Mahānas-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa Bhānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ<BR>(EI 5); superintendent of the royal kitchen; sometimes also<BR>called Mahāsāmantādhipati, Mahāpradhāna, Accupannāyadadhiṣṭhā-<BR>yaka, etc., additionally; cf. Mahānasika, Sūpakārapati, Khādya-<BR>(kū*) ṭapākika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानसिक<BR>Mahānasika, ‘the kitchen-officer’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII,<BR>p. 156); cf. Mahanas-ādhyakaṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानवमीअमावास्या<BR>mahānavamī-amāvāsyā (EI 5; IA 18), Kannaḍa name for<BR>the new-moon of Bhādrapada; new-moon preceding the<BR>mahānavamī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानाविक<BR>Mahānāvika (EI 27), the captain of a ship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानायक|महानायकः<BR>Mahānāyaka (EI 4; BL), official designation probably<BR>indicating a class of feudatories; a subordinate title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानि<BR>mahā-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of some such expression<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-182" target="_blank">Page-182+ 40</a>]<BR>as Mahāsāndhivigrahika-nirīkṣita, ‘approved by the Mahāsāndhivi-<BR>grahika’. See ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानियोग<BR>mahā-niyoga (SITI), king's order; royal command; an<BR>officer bearing the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महन्त्|महत्<BR>Mahant (EI 4), variant spelling of Mahanta; the same<BR>as Mahantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महन्त|महंतः|महन्तः<BR>Mahanta (EI 8; BL), head of a monastery; title of a pontiff.<BR>(ML), Prakrit form of Sanskrit mahat; ‘the great’; a<BR>title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महन्तक<BR>Mahantaka (LP), an accountant; a clerk. It is a term<BR>of respect among the Baniyās of Gujarat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापादमूलिक<BR>Mahāpādamūlika (IE 8-3), the king's chief personal<BR>attendant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापलुपति<BR>Mahāpalupati (Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 22), same as Mahā-<BR>pīlupati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापण<BR>mahāpaṇa, cf. māppaṇam (SITI), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापञ्चकुलिक<BR>Mahāpañcakulika (CII 4; HD), ‘head of the department<BR>of Pañcāyats’ or ‘the chairman of a Pāñcāyat board’; see pañca-<BR>kula. Cf. JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापान्धाकुलिक<BR>Mahāpāndhākulika (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 87), a mistake<BR>for or wrong reading of Mahāpāñcakulika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापाप|महापापं<BR>mahā-pāpa (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापण्डित<BR>Mahāpaṇḍita (EI 9; BL), title of a learned man, generally<BR>a learned Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापरमविश्वासिन्<BR>Mahāparamaviśvāsin (IE 8-3; EI 5), probably, a private<BR>secretary or privy councillor; same as Rahasyādhikṛta, etc.;<BR>sometimes called Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, etc., additionally.<BR>See Paramaviśvāsin, Vaiśvāsika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापरिनिर्वाण<BR>mahāparinirvāṇa (CII 4), the passing away of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापर्षद्<BR>mahāparṣad (EI 32), an assembly or committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापार्षिक<BR>mahāpārṣika (EI 32), used in the sense of ‘a member of the<BR>mahāparṣad’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापर्वन्<BR>mahā-parvan (EI 12), auspicious time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापात्र|महापात्रः<BR>Mahāpātra (IE 8-3; EI 19, 30), a minister; a minister<BR>higher in rank than the Pātra; cf. Pātra and Ekapātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापसायित<BR>Mahāpasāyita (IE 8-3; EI 5, 27), probably from Sanskrit<BR>Prasādita, ‘favoured’, meaning a Jāgīrdār of a particular type;<BR>sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Antaḥpuravĕrgaḍĕ, Daṇḍa-<BR>nāyaka, Sarvādhikārin, Mahāsāmanta, Senādibāhatta raniyogādhiṣṭhā-<BR>yaka, etc., additionally; cf. Pasāita, Pasāyita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापेरियप्रधान<BR>Mahāpĕriyapradhāna (EI 24), Sanskrit Mahābṛhatpradhāna;<BR>see Mahāpradhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापीलुपति<BR>Mahāpīlupati (IE 8-3; EI 28), ‘the great superintendent<BR>of elephants’; chief of the elephant corps; the master of ele-<BR>phants; sometimes also called Mahārāja, Mahāsāmanta, Pañcā-<BR>dhikaraṇ-oparika, Mahāpratīhāra, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika,<BR>etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 298. The word<BR>pīlu is the same as Perso-Arabic fīl. See Mahāpalupati and Pīlupati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रभु|महाप्रभुः<BR>Mahāprabhu (EI 21, 32), sometimes used in respect of<BR>subordinate rulers; (HD), a governor; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII,<BR>p. 335. (SITI) ‘the great banker’; the senior merchant; the<BR>title by which the leader of the nānādeśi merchant community<BR>was designated.<BR>(IA 30), a village official; see Prabhu.<BR>(EI 19), explained as ‘the high sheriff’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रचण्ड<BR>Mahāpracaṇḍa (EI 12), either a separate official desig-<BR>nation or an epithet prefixed to the designation Nāyaka or<BR>Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रचण्डदण्डनायक<BR>Mahāpracaṇḍa-daṇḍanāyaka (EI 20), official designation;<BR>cf. Mahāpracaṇḍa and Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रचण्डनायक<BR>Mahāpracaṇḍa-nāyaka (EI 29), official designation; cf.<BR>Mahāpracaṇḍa-daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रधान<BR>Mahāpradhāna (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 4; BL; HD), ‘the<BR>great minister’; ‘the chief minister or administrator’; sometimes<BR>also called Mahāsāmant-ādhipati, Antaḥpura-vĕrgaḍĕ (°ādhyakṣa),<BR>Mahāpasāyita, Senāpati, Hĕri (Mahā) sandhivigrahika, Manĕ-<BR>vĕrgaḍĕ, Kaḍitavĕrgaḍĕ, Senādhipati, Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa, Hĕri-Lāḻa-<BR>Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin, Bhānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ, Accupanāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka,<BR>Sarvādhikārin, Hĕri (Mahā) bhāṇḍāgārin, Bāhattaraniyogādhipati,<BR>Paṭṭasāhaṇ-ādhiṣṭhāyaka, Senāpati, Daṇḍanāyaka, Mahāsāmanta,<BR>Senādibhāhattaraniyog-ādhiṣṭhāyaka, Mahāmātya, Paramaviśvāsin,<BR>Mahāparamaviśvāsin, etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 28.<BR>(SITI), senior councillor of the king, usually a military<BR>officer; same as Mahāpradhāni. See Pradhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रधाननायक<BR>Mahāpradhāna-nāyaka (IA 12), regarded as a single official<BR>designation; but probably Mahāpradhāna and Nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रधानि<BR>Mahāpradhāni (CITD; ASLV), often, the chief minister<BR>or administrator; same as Mahāradhāna; a high executive officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमातार<BR>Mahāpramātāra (BL; MD), same as Mahāpramātṛ, Mahā-<BR>pramātra or Mahāpramattavāra. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 280.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमातृ<BR>Mahāpramātṛ (CII 4), explained as ‘the chief surveyor’;<BR>same as Mahāpramātāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमात्र<BR>Mahāpramātra (EI 12), same as Mahāpramātṛ, Mahā-<BR>pramātāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमत्तवार<BR>Mahāpramattavāra (HD), probably, the same as Mahā-<BR>pramātāra, etc.; explained wrongly as ‘the chief of the elephant<BR>corps’ (CII 4); cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 141.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रति<BR>Mahā-prati (IA 18), abbreviation of Mahāmātya-<BR>Pratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रतिहार<BR>Mahāpratihāra, Mahāpratīhāra (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3;<BR>BL), head of the door-keepers of the palace or the king's<BR>chamber, or of the capital; city; sometimes explained as ‘the<BR>chief usher’ (CII 4). See Pratihāra.<BR>(HD), the superior officer above all door-keepers, the<BR>great chamberlain. See Kādambarī, para. 97; Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV.<BR>142; Ep. Ind., Vol. X, p. 75; etc.<BR>(IE 8-2), one of the designations often included in the<BR>pañca-mahāśabda, as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī.<BR>(IE 8-3), sometimes also called Mahārāja, Mahāsāmanta,<BR>Mahāpīlupati, Pañcakaraṇ-oparika, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika,<BR>etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रतिहारपीडा<BR>mahāpratihāra-pīḍā (EI 12), occurs in the Rājataraṅgiṇī;<BR>explained as ‘the office of the high chamberlain’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रतोली<BR>mahā-pratolī (BL), main gateway; cf. pratolī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापुरोहित<BR>Mahāpurohita (IE 8-3; CII 4), chief priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापुरोहितठक्कुर<BR>Mahāpurohita-ṭhakkura (IE 8-3), ‘the head of the chief<BR>priests’; mentioned as a Pātra along with Mahāpurohita,<BR>Dharmādhikaraṇika, Daivāgārika, Śaṅkhadhārin, Paṇḍita, Upā-<BR>dhyāya, Daivajña, Mahārthaśāsanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापुरुष|महापुरुषः<BR>Mahāpuruṣa (BL), same as the god Viṣṇu.<BR>(EI 7), official designation; probably, the same as Mahā-<BR>manuṣya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महर<BR>Mahara (EI 1), probably a mistake for Mahattara, ‘a<BR>village-headman’ or ‘a member of the village Pañcāyat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराज|महाराजः<BR>Mahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HD), royal title<BR>first assumed by the foreign rulers of India and later adopted by<BR>indigenous rulers; originally, an imperial title; later (when the<BR>emperors assumed more dignified titles), a title of feudatories<BR>and smaller rulers; cf. Greek Basileos Megalou and Old Persian<BR>Kshāyathiya vazrka. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-185" target="_blank">Page-185+ 40</a>]<BR>(IE 8-2), one of the designations sometimes included in<BR>the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case of Maitraka Dhruvasena I.<BR>(IE 8-3), sometimes also called Mahāsāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra,<BR>Mahāpīlupati, Pañcādhikaraṇ-oparika, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika,<BR>etc., additionally.<BR>(IE 8-2), often used in the South even when Mahārājā-<BR>dhirāja became the popular imperial title in the North.<BR>(ASLV), designation of a priest of the members of the<BR>Vallabhācārya sect. Cf. Mahanta-mahārāja, title of pontiffs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजबप्पस्वामिन्<BR>Mahārāja-bappa-svāmin (IE 8-2), designation by which<BR>the father and predecessor of a ruling king is sometimes<BR>referred to.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधि<BR>Mahārājādhi (CII 3), abbreviation of Mahārājādhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधिराज<BR>Mahārājādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 3; CII 3, 4), one of the<BR>technical titles of paramount sovereignty closely connected<BR>with Paramabhaṭṭāraka and Parameśvara; later sometimes also<BR>assumed by subordinate rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधिराजपरमेश्वरी<BR>Mahārājādhirāja-parameśvarī (IE 8-2), title of certain<BR>ruling queens of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधिराजपति<BR>Mahārājādhirāja-pati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 242), title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजकुल<BR>Mahārājakula (IE 4; BL), official designation of a feuda-<BR>tory; same as Mahārāval of the Rajasthan region; cf. Rājakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजकुमार<BR>Mahārājakumāra, cf. Bālaka-mahārājakumāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजमाता<BR>Mahārāja-mātā (IE 8-2), epithet of the mother of a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजनक<BR>Mahārājanaka (EI 21), feudatory title; cf. Rājanaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजपण्डित<BR>Mahārājapaṇḍita (EI9), official designation; see Rājapaṇḍita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजपितामही<BR>Mahārāja-pitāmahī (IE 8-2), epithet of the grandmother<BR>of a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजप्रयोजन<BR>Mahārāja-prayojana (SITI), probably, fees collected for the<BR>performance of police duties; same as Tamil araśu-ppeṟu (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजपुत्र<BR>Mahārājaputra (EI 26; CII 4; HD), ‘son of the Mahārāja’;<BR>designation of a prince. See Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजासाहेब्<BR>Mahārājā-sāheb (BL), the same as Mahārāja with the<BR>Arabic honorific expression sāhib suffixed to it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजातिराज<BR>Mahārājātirāja (LL), imperial title; cf. Rājātirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराज्ञी<BR>Mahārājñī (IE 8-2; EI 4, 21; CII 4; BL; HD), designation<BR>of queens; see Rājñī. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराज्य<BR>mahārājya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 313), ‘a province’; cf. rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराणा<BR>Mahārāṇā (EI 21, 24; BL), derived from Mahārāṇaka;<BR>feudatory title; later, also a royal title. See Rāṇā and Rāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराणक<BR>Mahārāṇaka (EI 27; CII 4; BL; HD), title of feudatory<BR>rulers; see Rāṇaka. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 214.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारसकरण<BR>mahārasa-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the liquor department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराष्ट्रिन्<BR>Mahārāṣṭrin (IE 8-3; LL), Prakrit Mahāraṭhi; ‘ruler<BR>of a rāṣṭra (a district or subdivision or a group of villages)’;<BR>see Rāṣṭrin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराष्ट्रिणी<BR>Mahārāṣṭriṇī (LL), cf. Prakrit Mahāraṭhiṇī (EI 7), wife<BR>of a Mahārāṣṭrin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारथ|महारथः<BR>Mahāratha (EI 7), explained as ‘a race’ (EI 17); official<BR>designation; cf. Mahārathin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारथिन्<BR>Mahārathin (IE 8-3; EI 7), wrong Sanskritization of<BR>Prakrit Mahāraṭhi (sometimes read as Mahārathi) which really<BR>stands for Mahārāṣṭrin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराउल<BR>Mahārāula (EI 24; BL), same as Mahārāvala; derived<BR>from Mahārājakula; designation of a feudatory; title of<BR>nobility.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराउत<BR>Mahārāuta (BL), designation of a feudatory; from Sans-<BR>krit Mahārājaputra. See Rāuta, Rāvata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराव<BR>Mahārāva (BL), designation of a feudatory; from Sanskrit<BR>Mahārāja,<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारावल्<BR>Mahārāval, Mahārāvala (BL), same as Mahārāula; desig-<BR>nation of a fendatory; from Sanskrit Mahārājakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराय<BR>Mahārāya (EI 4, 24; BL), from Sanskrit Mahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महरी<BR>Maharī, Mahārī, Māhārī (EI 33), same as Mehari, a dancing<BR>girl or Devadāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारुण्डा<BR>Mahāruṇḍā, a name of the Mother-goddess (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXIII, p. 36).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महार्थमहामहत्तक<BR>Mahārtha-mahāmahattaka (CII 4), official designation;<BR>see Mahāmahattaka, Mahārtha may also be a separate official<BR>designation or an abbreviation of Mahārthaśāsanika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महार्थशासनिक<BR>Mahārthaśāsanika (EI 8-3; EI 7), probably, an officer<BR>in charge of gifts; sometimes mentioned as a Pātra. Cf. Mahā-<BR>rtha-mahāmahattaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महार्यक<BR>mah-āryaka (EI 8), probably, the great-grandfather;<BR>tentatively explained as ‘mother's grandfather’ (Select Inscrip-<BR>tions, p. 202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाशब्द<BR>mahā-śabda (IE 8-2), cf. aśeṣa-mahāśabda (EI 22), same<BR>as pañca-mahāśabda (q. v.). Cf. paṭaha-ḍhakkā-mahāśabda (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXVI, p. 325).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासभा<BR>mahā-sabhā (SII 1; ASLV; SITI), ‘the great assembly’;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-187" target="_blank">Page-187+ 40</a>]<BR>meeting of the general body of the sabhā; meeting of the Mahā-<BR>janas in session; body of the Mahājanas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाधनभाग|महासाधनभागः<BR>mahāsādhanabhāga (IE 12; IA 14; HD), occurring in<BR>the Rājataraṅgīṇī; explained as ‘the office of the chief executive<BR>minister’; but cf. Mahāsādhanika; one of the five offices insti-<BR>tuted by Lalitāditya of Kashmir (Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142-43).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाधनिक<BR>Mahāsādhanika (IE 8-2, 8-3; CII 4; BL; HD), official<BR>designation indicating a commander of forces; the chief mili-<BR>tary officer; one of the designations often included in the pañca-<BR>mahāśabda as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See Sādhanika<BR>derived from sādhana or army. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR>(IE 8-3), sometimes mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाहनी<BR>Mahāsāhanī (BL), cf. Masāhaṇī (EI 5), a military officer;<BR>the same as Sanskrit Mahāsādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाहसिक|महासाहसिकः<BR>Mahāsāhasika (IE 25), official designation; cf. Duḥ-<BR>sādhya-sādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासैन्यपति<BR>Mahāsainyapati (EI 29; HL), commander of forces; cf.<BR>Sainyapati and Mahāsenāpati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाशाइत्<BR>mahāśāit (EI 5), a kind of rice or paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासांकरणनि<BR>mahāsāṃ-karaṇa-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of mahāsāndhi-<BR>vigrahika-karaṇa-nirīkṣita, ‘examined by the clerk of the<BR>Mahāsāndhivigrahika’. Karaṇa here may also be an abbreviation<BR>of Adhikaraṇa or office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासामन्त|महासामन्तः<BR>Mahāsāmanta (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL), ‘the<BR>great chieftain’; title of a feudatory of a higher rank than the<BR>Sāmanta; sometimes called Mahārāja, Mahāpratīhāra, Pañca-<BR>karaṇ-oparika, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika, Senādibāhattara-<BR>niyogādhiṣṭhāyaka, Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, Mahāpasāyita,<BR>Daṇḍanāyaka, etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 217;<BR>Vol. IX, p. 107.<BR>(SITI), a vassal chief, sometimes holding the position of<BR>a minister or governor.<BR>(IE 8-2), one of the designations sometimes included in<BR>the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case of Maitraka Dhruvasena I.<BR>(IE 8-3), sometimes a feudatory of a lower grade than<BR>Rājan and Rājanaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासामन्ताधिपति<BR>Mahāsāmantādhipati (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 29, 30; CII 4; BL;<BR>HD), a feudatory title; cf. Sāmantādhipati (EI 16); title of<BR>feudatories who had some subordinate chiefs under them;<BR>title of a feudatory of a higher rank than the Mahāsāmanta;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-188" target="_blank">Page-188+ 40</a>]<BR>cf. Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara, Samasta-mahāsāmant-ādhipati; sometimes<BR>also called Mahāpradhāna, Bhānasavĕrgaḍĕ, Accupannāyadadhiṣṭhā-<BR>yaka, etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 259. See<BR>Mahāsāmanta, Mahāmaṇḍaleśvarādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासामन्तराज<BR>Mahāsāmantarāja (EI 33), feudatory title; cf. Mahāsāmant-<BR>ādhipati. It may also indicate one enjoying the titles Mahā-<BR>sāmanta and Rājan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासानि<BR>mahāsā-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of mahāsāndhivigrahikaṇirī-<BR>kṣita, ‘examined by the Mahāsāndhivigrahika’. See ni, mahākṣa-ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिकरण<BR>mahāsandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇa (EI 12; CII 4), the office or<BR>department of the Mahāsandhivigrahika; the department of<BR>peace and war.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिकरणआधिकृत<BR>Mahāsandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇa-ādhikṛta (BL), superintendent<BR>of the office of war and peace or foreign affairs. See Sandhi-<BR>vigrah-ādhikaraṇ-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिकृत<BR>Mahāsandhivigrah-ādhikṛta (CII 4; HD), same as Mahā-<BR>sāndhivigrahika; minister of peace and war. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XI, p. 80; Harṣacarita, Parab's ed., p. 194.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिपति<BR>Mahāsandhivigrah-ādhipati (EI 21; CII 4), same as Mahā-<BR>sāndhivigrahika; cf. Sandhivigrah-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाक्षपटलाधिकृत<BR>Mahāsandhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (EI 31), officer in<BR>charge of the accounts section of the foreign affairs department;<BR>same as Mahāsandhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासान्धिविग्रहाक्षपटलाधिपति<BR>Mahāsāndhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhipati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV,<BR>p. 274), same as Mahāsandhivigrah-akṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहिक<BR>Mahāsandhivigrahika (BL; HD), same as Mahāsāndhivigra-<BR>hika; designation of the minister for war and peace or of foreign<BR>affairs. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309. See Sandhivigrahika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासान्धिविग्रहिक|महासांधिविग्रहिकः<BR>Mahāsāndhivigrahika (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL;<BR>HD), same as Mahāsandhivigrahika; minister for peace and war<BR>or of foreign affairs; a civil or military title; one of the designa-<BR>tions often included in the pañca-mahāśabda as indicated by<BR>the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See Sāndhivigrahika.<BR>(IE 8-3), cf. Gauḍa-mahāsāndhivigrahika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहिन्<BR>Mahāsandhivigrahin (BL), designation of the minister for<BR>war and peace or of foreign affairs. See Sandhivigrahin, Mahā-<BR>sāndhivigrahika, etc.<BR>(IE 8-3), sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Manĕ-<BR>vĕrgaḍĕ, Senādhipati, Kaḍita-vĕrgaḍĕ, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासप्तमी<BR>mahāsaptamī (EI 4), a tithi; Māgha-sudi 7; Āśvina-sudi 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासर्वदण्डनायक<BR>Mahāsarvadaṇḍanāyaka (CII 3), the commander-in-chief.<BR>See Sarvadaṇḍnāyaka and Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासर्वाधिकृत<BR>Mahāsarvādhikṛta (EI 12, 28), the chief minister or adminis-<BR>trator. Cf. Sarvādhikṛta and Sarvādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासती<BR>mahā-satī (EI 31), spelt mā-sati in Tamil, etc.; a lady who<BR>has committeed satī; cf. satī.<BR>Cf. mā-sati-kal, a stone raised in memory of a satī (Journ.<BR>Mad. Univ., Vol. XXXII, p. 136).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासत्त्रपति<BR>Mahāsattrapati (EI 13), superintendent of the sattras<BR>(houses for free distribution of food).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनाधिपति<BR>Mahāsenādhipati (EI 19), commander of forces. Cf.<BR>Mahāsenāpati, Senādhipati, Samastasenādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनानी<BR>Mahāsenānī, commander of forces (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII,<BR>p. 156).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनापति<BR>Mahāsenāpati (EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), ‘the great<BR>commander of armies’. See Senāpati, Mahāsenādhipati. Cf.<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनापत्नी<BR>Mahāsenāpatnī (IE 8-2; EI 20; LL), wife of a Mahāsenā-<BR>pati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाशिरःप्रधानि<BR>Mahāśiraḥ-Pradhāni (ASLV), a high officer who had a<BR>seat in the Imperial Council of the Vijayanagara kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्रमण|महाश्रमणः<BR>Mahāśramaṇa (EI 32), the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्रेष्ठिन्<BR>Mahāśreṣṭhin (EI 7; CII 4; HD), ‘the great banker’;<BR>the chief banker; see Śreṣṭhin. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महास्थान<BR>mahāsthāna (EI 7), a holy place.<BR>(EI 24), a great temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महास्थविर<BR>Mahāsthavira (LL), Buddhist; cf. Sthavira, an Elder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महास्वामिक<BR>Mahāsvāmika (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), probably, ‘the<BR>king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वपति<BR>Mahāśvapati (BL), designation of the leader of horsemen.<BR>See Aśvapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वसाधनिक<BR>Mahāśvasādhanika (EI 12; HD), commander of a cavalry<BR>force. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309.<BR>(CII 4), the great equerry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वशाला<BR>mahāśvaśālā (EI 12; HD), explained as ‘the office of the<BR>chief master of the horses’; one of the five high offices<BR>instituted by Lalitādiya of Kashmir (Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वशालाधिकृत<BR>Mahāśvaśāl-ādhikṛta (IE 8-2), superintendent of the<BR>stables; one of the designations often included in the pañca-<BR>mahāśabda (cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महता<BR>Mahatā (EI 32), the same as Mahattaka, Mahattara or<BR>Mahattama. Cf. Mahato.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातलवर<BR>Mahātalavara (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 25; HD), explained by some<BR>authorities as a subordinate ruler and by others as the police<BR>magistrate of a city or the prefect of the city police. Cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XX, pp. 6, 16. See Talavara, Talāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातलवरी<BR>Mahātalavarī (IE 8-2; EI 20, 25), wife of a Mahātalavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातन्त्र<BR>mahātantra (SITI; ASLV), often mentioned in South<BR>Indian records in the sense of ‘the army’; the army council;<BR>the great assembly of the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातन्त्राधिकृत<BR>Mahātantrādhikṛta (IE 8-3), explained by some authori-<BR>ties as ‘an officer in charge of judicial and charitable affairs’;<BR>but the word tantra also means ‘administration’ or ‘the army’;<BR>probably ‘the chief administrator’. The designation may have<BR>also indicated different functions in different localities and ages.<BR>See Tantrapāla, Tantrapati and Mahātantrādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातन्त्राध्यक्ष<BR>Mahātantrādhyakṣa (EI 28), official designation; same as<BR>Mahātantrādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाठक्कुर<BR>Mahāṭhakkura (IE32; IA17), a title indicating office or rank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातीर्थ<BR>Mahātīrtha (BL), epithet of a holy place or shrine. Cf.<BR>tīrtha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातिथि|महातिथिः<BR>mahātithi (EI 13), an auspicious tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महात्मन्<BR>Mahātman (CII 1), a person of high rank; a rich man;<BR>explained in some cases as ‘a magistrate’ (cf. Select Inscriptions,<BR>p. 248, note 6).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माहात्म्य|माहात्म्यं<BR>māhātmya (IA 30), a culogistic work on deities or holy<BR>places, rivers, etc.; cf. sthala-purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महतो<BR>Mahato (EI 8-3), same as Mahattaka, Mahattara or Maha-<BR>ttama. Cf. Mahatā; also Mahto in Wilson's Glossary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातोरण<BR>mahātoraṇa (SITI), a variety of temple lamps; pro-<BR>bably the same as makaratoraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तक<BR>Mahattaka (EI 8; BL; HD), probably, a village head-<BR>man or a member of the Pañcāyat board; same as Mahattara.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 30 (Mahāmahattaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तम<BR>Mahattama (IE 8-3; EI 29; CII 4; BL; HD), probably<BR>the village headman or a member of the Pañcāyat board; cf.<BR>Mahattara. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306; Ep. Ind., Vol. III,<BR>p. 266 (Mahattara and Mahattama occur one after another,<BR>Mahattama being senior or superior to Mahattara); Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>VII. 438.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-191" target="_blank">Page-191+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 26), same as Gujarātī Mahetā or Mehtā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तर|महत्तरः<BR>Mahattara (IE 8-3; EI 23, 29, 30; CII 4; BL; HD),<BR>literally, ‘an elder [of a town or village]’; according to Stein<BR>(Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 659); a chamberlain, a village headman<BR>or head of a family or community and a member of the village<BR>council; cf. Hindī Mahato; Gujaratī Mahetā. Cf. Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. VI, p. 114 (rāṣṭra-grāma-mahattara); Daśakumāracarita, III,<BR>p. 77 (janapada-mahattara).<BR>Cf. mahattar-ādy-aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa (EI 31), ‘office of the<BR>administrative board of the aṣṭakula headed by the Mahattara’;<BR>see Mahattara and aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa.<BR>(IE 3-3), official guide. (Beal, Life of Hiuen Tsiang, p. 190).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तरक|महत्तरकः<BR>Mahattaraka (EI 23; LL), explained as ‘a chamberlain’;<BR>same as Mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महात्राण<BR>mahātrāṇa (IE 8-5), Bengali; a rent-free holding in<BR>the possession of non-Brahmanical communities, e. g. the<BR>Vaiṣṇavas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावड्डव्यवहारिन्<BR>Mahāvaḍḍavyavahārin (EI 13; SII 11-2), see Vaḍḍavya-<BR>vahārin and Mahāvaṇḍavyavahārin; Sanskrit Mahāvṛddhavyavahārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावलाकोष्ठिक<BR>Mahāvalākoṣṭhika (IE 8-3), probably a mistake for Mahā-<BR>balakoṣṭhika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावण्डव्यवहारिन्<BR>Mahāvaṇḍavyavahārin (EI 19; SITI), the great banker<BR>or chief merchant; head of a mercantile guild; same as<BR>Mahāvaḍḍavyavahārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावारुणी<BR>mahāvāruṇī (EI 4), name of a tithi. See mahāmahāvāruṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविहार<BR>mahāvihāra (BL), Buddhist convent or monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविहारस्वामिन्<BR>Mahāvihāra-svāmin (EI 8; CII 3; BL), designation of the<BR>builder of a Buddhist monastery and his heirs who were res-<BR>ponsible for its maintenance; the builder or owner of a big<BR>monastery; cf. Vihāra-svāmin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविहारायतन<BR>mahāvihār-āyatana (EI 22), a monastic establishment.<BR>Cf. āyatana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविनयधर<BR>Mahāvinayadhara (LL), Buddhist; cf. Vinayadhara, ‘one<BR>who has committed the Vinaya texts to memory’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावरतिन्<BR>Mahāvaratin (EI 27; SITI), name of a Śaiva sect; followers<BR>of the said sect of Śaivism; an ascetic of the Kālāmukha sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाव्यवस्था<BR>mahā-vyavasthā (SITI), probably, the regulations framed<BR>by the mahā-sabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाव्यूहपति<BR>Mahāvyūhapati (EI 19, 28, 30; HD), the chief master of<BR>battle arrays. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 40.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महायज्ञ|महायज्ञः<BR>mahāyajña (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’. See pañca-mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महायुवराज<BR>Mahāyuvarāja (EI 32), title of a crown prince; see Yuva-<BR>rāja and Yuvamahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेन्द्रादित्य<BR>Mahendrāditya (IE 8-2), see āditya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेश्वर|महेश्वरः<BR>Maheśvara (SITI), Māheśvara, followers of the Śaiva reli-<BR>gion; a congregation of Śaiva devotees having a voice in the<BR>management of the affairs of a Śiva temple.<BR>(ASLV), trustee of a Śaiva temple.<BR>(IE 8-2), ‘devotee of Maheśvara (Śiva),’ epithet of a<BR>Kuṣāṇa king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेश्वर|महेश्वरः<BR>maheśvara (EI 28), the Pāśupta faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेश्वरपुत्र<BR>Maheśvara-putra (EI 33), sometimes used as an epithet of<BR>one devoted to the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मही<BR>mahī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महीधर|महीधरः<BR>mahīdhara (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महिमद<BR>Mahimada (EI 32), Indianised form of the Muhammadan<BR>name Muḥammad or Mahmūd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महीमण्डलेश्वर<BR>Mahīmaṇḍaleśvara (BL), rare modification of the feuda-<BR>tory title Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महिषकर<BR>mahiṣa-kara, cf. Tamil erumai-ppon (SITI), tax on buffa-<BR>loes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महिषी<BR>Mahiṣī, cf. Agaramahiṣī Agramahāmahiṣī, Mahāmahiṣī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महोदय|महोदयं|महोदयः<BR>Mahodaya (IA 18), used in the sense of Svāmin or possessor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महोद्रङ्ग<BR>mah-odraṅga, cf. udraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महोपाध्याय|महोपाध्यायः<BR>Mahopādhyāya (EI 6, 15), a title of teachers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माहुत्<BR>Māhut (CII 4), derived from Mahāmātra, an elephant-<BR>driver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मह्य<BR>mahya (EI 28), same as namasya. See Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXVIII, pp. 77 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैरा<BR>mairā (CII 4), boundary of a field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैथिली<BR>Maithilī, language and alphabet of Mithilā or the Tirhut<BR>region of North Bihar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैथुन|मैथुनं<BR>maithuna (SITI), wife's brother; elder sister's husband.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैत्री<BR>maitrī (CII 4), benevolence; one of the bhāvanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरसङ्क्रमण<BR>makara-saṅkramaṇa (SITI), entrance of the sun into Cap-<BR>ricorn; commencement of the Tamil month Tai; same as<BR>Makara-saṅkrānti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरसङ्क्रान्ति<BR>makara-saṅkrānti (SITI), same as makara-saṅkramaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरतोरण<BR>makara-toraṇa (EI 29), one of the royal insignia.<BR>(EI 3; SII 1, 3), an ornamental arch; an arch in the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-193" target="_blank">Page-193+ 40</a>]<BR>shape of a makara (crocodile); gateway with figures of<BR>crocodiles. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol XXXV p. 107.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरिका<BR>makarikā (CITD), figures of crocodiles drawn in gold<BR>dust on the cheeks and breasts of women; same as makarikā-<BR>patra.<BR>(EI 14), cf. mukuṭa-makarikā-marakata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरिकापत्र<BR>makarikā-patra (CITD), same as makarikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकुति|मकुतिः<BR>makuti (CII 4), an edict addressed to the Śūdras. Cf.<BR>Mākutika, official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माल|मालं|मालः<BR>māla (EI 22), an elevated ground.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलधारि<BR>Maladhāri (BL), epithet of a Jain religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालाकार|मालाकारः<BR>Mālākāra (LL), a florist. See Mālin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलमार्गण<BR>malamārgaṇa (LL), cf. Gujarātī maḻavero; a tax to be utilised<BR>when the whole village wants to honour a particular man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालवगणाम्नात<BR>Mālava-gaṇ-āmnāta, Mālava-gaṇa-sthiti, Mālava-pūrvā (EI<BR>23), expressions used in early records in connection with the<BR>Vikrama-saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालवी<BR>Mālavī, dialect of Hindī prevalent in Mālava (Malwa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालवीय<BR>Mālavīya (EI 22), ‘the king of Mālava’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलय|मलयः<BR>malaya (IA 14), derived from Dravidian malai, ‘a hill’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलयालम्<BR>Malayāḻam, name of a language and alphabet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलेयसाहणि<BR>Maleya-sāhaṇi (Naik's List, No. 264); mentioned along-<BR>with Peyiya-sāhaṇi; official designation. See Sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालिम<BR>Mālima, same as Arabic Mualim, ‘an instructor’ (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्ल|मल्लः<BR>Malla (CII 4), a wrestler, a match.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लक|मल्लकः<BR>mallaka (EI 21) a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लकर<BR>malla-kara (HRS), found in Nepal inscriptions; tax levied<BR>as tribute to the Mallas or for defence against their attack.<BR>Cf. turuṣka-daṇḍa, etc. It may also be a professional tax on<BR>wrestlers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लकवुन्धक<BR>mallaka-vundhaka, cf. talabhedyā-ghāṇaka-mallaka-vundhaka<BR>(IA 18); probably, a professional tax on wrestlers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलिक्<BR>Malik, Malika (EI 4; BL), Muslim title of nobility; same<BR>as Arabic Malik; also spelt in Indian languages as Mallika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालिन्<BR>Mālin (EI 9), a florist. See Mālākāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ममत्रै<BR>Mamátrai (IE 8-3), Greek modification of Mahāmātra;<BR>explained as ‘commanders or rulers among Indians’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मंक्षूण<BR>maṃkṣūṇa, see draṃkṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मामूलादाय<BR>māmūl-ādāya (SITI), customary payment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्<BR>man, cf. mānayitvā (LP) ‘having accepted’; cf. Gujarātī<BR>mānine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान|मानं|मानः<BR>māna (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; (1/16)th part of the<BR>measure called tūmu; that which can hold rice of the weight<BR>of 4 ṭaṅkalamulu (varying in different localities); a particular<BR>measure or weight often regarded as half of a seru; a measur-<BR>ing rod.<BR>(EI 16), also called mānaka; name of a measure; a liquid<BR>measure (SII 11-1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान|मानं|मानः<BR>māna, māṇa (IE 8-6; EI 30, 31), used in medieval Orissan<BR>records in the sense of a land measure; a land measure regarded<BR>as equal to an English acre in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानभोग<BR>māna-bhoga (SITI), enjoyment of tax-free lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानदण्ड|मानदंड|मानदण्डः<BR>māna-daṇḍa (SITI), measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानक|मानकं<BR>mānaka (EI 14, 16), name of a measure; also called māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानपौतव<BR>māna-pautava (EI 30), probably, a store-house where<BR>grains were measured and stored. Cf. mānya (aḻḻāya-mānya).<BR>(IE 8-8), scales and measures.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानस्तम्भ<BR>māna-stambha (EI 5, 8), a pillar; an elegant tall pillar with<BR>a small pinnacled maṇṭapa at the top erected in front of Jain<BR>temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनवर्ति<BR>manavarti, manavartika (EI 32), grant for maintenance;<BR>also spelt as manovarti, manuvṛtti, etc., probably derived from<BR>Sanskrit mānya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानव्य|मानव्यं<BR>Mānavya (EI 16), name of a gotra that was claimed by<BR>royal families which had originally no real Brāhmanical gotra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्च|मंच|मंचः|मञ्चः<BR>mañca, cf. sa-mañca-mahākaraṇa (IE 8-5); probably, elevated<BR>platforms for official use.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्ड|मंडं|मण्डं|मंडः|मण्डः<BR>maṇḍa, weight equal to 5 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46);<BR>cf. māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डई<BR>maṇḍaī (EI 23), derived from maṇḍapikā; same as maṇḍī,<BR>‘market’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डक|मंडकः|मण्डकः<BR>maṇḍaka (SITI), same as maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डल|मंडल|मण्डलं|मण्डलः<BR>maṇḍala (IE 8-4; EI 29, 30; CII 4), an administrative<BR>unit; a district or province.<BR>(SITI), a province consisting of several koṭṭams or<BR>valanāḍus.<BR>(IE 8-4), sometimes mentioned as bigger than a viṣaya and<BR>sometimes smaller than it; sometimes a viṣaya was included in a<BR>maṇḍala, but sometimes a maṇḍala was included in a viṣaya; some-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-195" target="_blank">Page-195+ 40</a>]<BR>times maṇḍala and viṣaya are identical; sometimes a maṇḍala<BR>was smaller than the vīthī or subdivision.<BR>(IE 8-4; SII 3; ASLV), sometimes used in a wider sense<BR>to indicate a country.<BR>Cf. Kona-maṇḍala (EI 22), also called an avani-maṇḍala<BR>or deśa. Here maṇḍala means a kingdom or territory.<BR>(ASLV), an assembled body. Cf. mātṛ-maṇḍala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलाचार्य<BR>Maṇḍal-ācārya (EI 33, IA 14), same as Paṭṭ-ācārya; desig-<BR>nation of a high priest.<BR>(BL), epithet of a [Jain] religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलाधिपति<BR>Maṇḍal-ādhipati (EI 25), the ruler of a maṇḍala; cf.<BR>Maṇḍaleśvara Maṇḍalapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलगणिन्<BR>Maṇḍala-gaṇin (EI 33), title; cf. Gaṇin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलकरण<BR>maṇḍala-karaṇa (LP), department dealing with the ad-<BR>ministration of districts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलमुदलियार्<BR>Maṇḍala-mudaliyār, official designation; cf. maṇḍala-mudan-<BR>mai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलमुदन्मै<BR>maṇḍala-mudanmai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; leadership or<BR>governorship of a province, its governor or chief being known as<BR>Maṇḍala-mudaliyār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलपति<BR>Maṇḍalapati (IE 8-3; EI 26, 33), ruler or officer-in-charge<BR>of a maṇḍala; the governor of a district or a feudatory ruler (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 78, text line 9); same as Maṇḍaleśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलेश|मण्डलेशः<BR>Maṇḍaleśa (BL; HD), ‘lord of a maṇḍala’; a provincial<BR>governor; same as Maṇḍaleśvara. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 73; VII.<BR>996; VIII. 1228, 1814, 2029.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलेश्वर|मण्डलेश्वरः<BR>Maṇḍaleśvara (IE 8-2; BL; HD), title of a feudatory or<BR>governor lower in rank than a Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara; same as Maṇ-<BR>ḍaleśa. Cf. Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354. Cf. Mahāmaṇḍa-<BR>leśvara, ‘governor of the provinces’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV,<BR>p. 110).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलिक<BR>Maṇḍalika (EI 26), ruler of a maṇḍala or district; same<BR>as Māṇḍalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माण्डलिक|मांडलिक<BR>Māṇḍalika (IE 8-2; BL; CII 4), ruler of a maṇḍala or<BR>district; title of a feudatory chief; cf. Maṇḍalika, Maṇḍalīka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलीक|मंडलीकः|मण्डलीकः<BR>Maṇḍalīka (IE 8-2; SII 1; SITI; BL), feudatory title;<BR>ruler of a maṇḍala; same as Maṇḍalika and Māṇḍalika, also called<BR>Maṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डप|मंडपः|मण्डपः<BR>maṇḍapa (IE 8-3), customs house; Marāṭhī māṇḍavī, from<BR>Sanskrit maṇḍapikā; explained by some as ‘a market place’<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-196" target="_blank">Page-196+ 40</a>]<BR>(Hindī maṇḍī); but Hindī maṇḍī seems to be derived from the<BR>same word because the toll-stations were often situated in market-<BR>places.<BR>(BL), name of a structure in front of a temple.<BR>(LL), a porch or hall.<BR>(CII 4), the hall in a temple.<BR>(CII 4), a temple.<BR>(EI 31), a temple or public building.<BR>Cf. vaiccamudu-maṇḍapa (SITI), kitchen; same as maḍaip-<BR>paḻḻi.<BR>Cf. vakkāṇikku-maṇḍapa (SITI), hall where disputations<BR>in the śāstras are held. Cf. śanivāra-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिका|मंडपिका<BR>maṇḍapikā (EI 1, 3, 33), customs house; same as śulka-<BR>maṇḍapikā (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 339 and note 31). See<BR>Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 238-39.<BR>(EI 3; CII 4); market; a market pavilion.<BR>(CII 4), a small temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माण्डपिक<BR>Māṇḍapika (IE 8-2), cf. Prakrit Maṃḍavika (EI I), officer<BR>in charge of a maṇḍapikā or customs house; a collector of tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिकादाय<BR>maṇḍapik-ādāya (EI 23), explained as ‘the market tax’;<BR>customs duties.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिकाकरण<BR>maṇḍapikā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), the customs depart<BR>ment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिकापट्टक<BR>maṇḍapikā-paṭṭaka (LP), a contract for market-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माण्डवी<BR>Māṇḍavī (LP), one who gets the market-tax; same as<BR>Māṇḍapika.<BR>(LP), a tax levied on articles that are to be sold in a<BR>market-place.<BR>(IE 8-3), Marāṭhī; same as maṇḍapikā, ‘customs house’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डवो<BR>maṇḍavo (EI 22), market place; regarded as the same as<BR>maṇḍapikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनेवेर्गडे<BR>Manĕ-vĕrgaḍĕ (IE 8-3; EI 16; SII 11-2), Kannaḍa;<BR>superintendent or steward of the royal household (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 77); sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Hĕri-<BR>sandhivigrahin, Antaḥpurādhyakṣa, Hĕri-Lāḻa-Kannaḍa-sandhivi-<BR>grahin, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनेयसमस्तसैन्याधिपति<BR>Maneyasamastasainyādhipati (IE 8-3), leader of all the<BR>troops in the royal household. Cf. Samastasenādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गल|मंगल|मङ्गलं|मङ्गलः<BR>maṅgala (CII 1), a ceremony for one's good or for averting<BR>evil; cf. kalyāṇa.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-197" target="_blank">Page-197+ 40</a>]<BR>(SITI), a Brāhmaṇa village; shortened form of caturvedi-<BR>maṅgala.<BR>(ASLV), a small administrative unit.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गलकलस<BR>maṅgala-kalasa (CII 4), an auspicious vase. Cf. nidrā-kalasa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गालिहा<BR>maṅgālihā (IA 15), probably, an upper garment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माङ्गलिक्य<BR>māṅgalikya (LP), some present (made in lieu of the benefit<BR>one is going to get).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माङ्गलीयक<BR>māṅgalīyaka (LP), probably, a tax collected on the occa-<BR>sion of auspicious events in the royal family, such as the birth<BR>of a son to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माङ्गल्य|मांगल्य|माङ्गल्यं<BR>māṅgalya (SITI), Tamil maṅgiliyam; the ornament called<BR>tāli worn round the neck as the marriage badge by a married<BR>woman with her husband living.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गणि<BR>maṅgaṇi, maṅgaṇī, maṅaṇī (Chamba), a tax in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणि|मणिः<BR>maṇi (IA 20), a burning glass.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानि<BR>māni (LP), a measure of capacity equal to about 6 maunds.<BR>(SII 11-1), Kannaḍa; also spelt Māṇi; a bachelor;<BR>Brahmacārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माणि<BR>māṇi (EI 14; Chamba), name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणिभण्डलु<BR>maṇi-bhaṇḍalu (CITD), Sanskrit-Telugu; probably, from<BR>Sanskrit maṇi-bhāṇḍa or the receptacle of jewels.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणिग्राम<BR>maṇi-grāma (SITI), a mercantile guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माणिक|माणिकः<BR>māṇika (CITD), Telugu; a measure; (1/4) of a kuñcamu<BR>and (1/15) of a tūmu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणिकार|मणिकारः<BR>Maṇikāra (LP), a jeweller.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माणिक्यभाण्डार<BR>māṇikya-bhāṇḍāra, cf. maṇikka-paṇḍāram-kāppār (SITI), ‘keeper<BR>of the treasury [of precious stones] in the temple or palace.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानिन्<BR>Mānin, cf. Māṇi (IA 18), an Elder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानित<BR>mānita (LP), accepted.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जाडि<BR>mañjāḍi (IE 8-8; EI 21, 33; SII 2, 12; SITI), Tamil; name<BR>of a weight for measuring gold and silver; about 2 or 3 ratīs or<BR>4 or 5 grains; a weight equal to two kuṉṟi-maṇi used in weighing<BR>gold; (1/10) of a kal13añju and (1/100) of a śatamāna (JNSI, Vol.<BR>XV, p. 141).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जूर<BR>Mañjūra (LP), day-labourer; cf. Majūr.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जूषा|मंजूषा<BR>mañjūṣā (LL), casket.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्नेय<BR>Manneya (CITD), Telugu; same as Sanskrit Mānya; a<BR>respectable man; a chieftain; a commander; a chief. Cf.<BR>Mannīḍu, Manniya.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-198" target="_blank">Page-198+ 40</a>]<BR>(SII 11-1), ruler of a group of villages; cf. manneya-<BR>svāmya, tenure held by a Manneya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्नीडु<BR>Mannīḍu (CITD), same as Manneya (Sanskrit Mānya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्निय<BR>Manniya (CITD), same as Manneya (Sanskrit Mānya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनोहारी<BR>manohārī (LP), cf. nija-manohāryā, ‘at one's own will’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनोतिरेक<BR>mano-'tireka (CII 1), eagerness; cf. atireka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनोवर्ति<BR>manovarti (EI 32), same as manavarti or manuvṛtti in the<BR>sense of namasya-vṛtti or mānya; probably derived from Sanskrit<BR>mānya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्थनयन्त्रक<BR>manthana-yantraka (IA 20), a fire-producing instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रदेवमनुजभूतपितृगण<BR>mantra-deva-manuja-bhūta-pitṛgaṇa (IA 15), refers to the<BR>pañca-mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रपाल<BR>Mantrapāla (EI 22), official designation; probably, a<BR>private secretary or privy councillor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रपुष्प<BR>Mantrapuṣpa (IA 12), designation of a priest who repeats<BR>the mantra when the chief priest asks forgiveness at the conclusion<BR>of each pūjā at the Rāmeśvaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रशक्ति|मन्त्रशक्तिः<BR>mantra-śakti (CII 4), the power of good counsel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रस्नान<BR>mantra-snāna (EI 4), repetition of prayers used at ablution<BR>without the actual bath.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रिन्|मंत्रिन्<BR>Mantrin (EI 12, 25; CII 4; BL; HD), a minister or coun-<BR>cillor; a counsellor; an executive officer. See Arthaśāstra, I. 80;<BR>Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 312; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR>(IE 8-3), explained as vyavahāra-draṣṭṛ. Cf. Mahāmantrin.<BR>(IE 8-3), in one case, the Mantrin later became a Mahā-<BR>balādhikṛta; in another case, also a Kumārāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रिपरिषद्<BR>mantri-pariṣad (CII 4; ASLV), the council of ministers;<BR>same as pariṣad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनु|मनुः<BR>Manu (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनुष्य|मनुष्यः<BR>Manuṣya, cf. Mānisi (EI 24), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनुष्ययज्ञ|मनुष्ययज्ञः<BR>manuṣya-yajña (CII 4), reception of guests; one of the<BR>five mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनुवृत्ति<BR>manuvṛtti (EI 32), a grant made for the maintenance of<BR>the donee; same as manavarti, etc.; probably derived from<BR>Sanskrit mānya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्वादि<BR>manvādi (IA 18), name applied to certain tithis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्य|मान्यः<BR>mānya (IE 8-5; EI 20, 23; ASLV), a rent-free holding,<BR>tax-free land; same as sarva-mānya; cf. mānya-sthiti, manuvṛtti,<BR>etc.<BR>Cf. sthāna-mānya (CITD), an honour or glebe-land<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-199" target="_blank">Page-199+ 40</a>]<BR>granted by the ruler on quit-rent or on various favourable<BR>tenures.<BR>(EI 13), land either liable to a trifling quit-rent or alto-<BR>gether exempt from tax.<BR>Cf. aḻḻāya-mānyam (SITI), right to receive a handful of<BR>grain or the prescribed quantity of an article brought for sale<BR>in the market as charges for measuring; cf. māna-pautava.<BR>Cf. guḍḍe-mānya (IA 19), a particular kind of rent-free<BR>holding.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यकणिके<BR>mānya-kaṇikĕ (EI 25), a small amount of tax levied from<BR>land declared rent-free. Cf. nikara, tṛṇodaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यकपट्ट<BR>mānyaka-paṭṭa, a rent-free village (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX,<BR>p. 71).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यस्थिति<BR>mānya-sthiti, cf. mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्यवान्तरराष्ट्र<BR>manyavāntara-rāṣṭra (SII 1), same as nāḍu or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यवृत्ति<BR>mānya-vṛtti, cf. manuvṛtti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पणम्<BR>māppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; same as Sanskrit mahā-paṇa;<BR>name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्<BR>mār (IA 15), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर|मरः<BR>mara (EI 14), name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरमक्कतयम्<BR>maramakkatayam (EI 9), system of inheritance prevalent<BR>in the Malayāḻam-speaking area, according to which property<BR>is owned by females and passes from female to female.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मराठी<BR>Marāṭhī, language and people of Maharashtra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरवडै<BR>maravaḍai (EI 17), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्ग|मार्गः<BR>Mārga (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Mārgaśīrṣa, Mārgaśira, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गादाय<BR>mārg-ādāya (EI 23; SITI), same as vartma-daṇḍa; levy for<BR>passage of articles of merchandise through the gift village by the<BR>village road; tolls; tolls on the articles on transit. See mārgaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गक|मार्गकः<BR>mārgaka (EI 26), name of a levy; same as mārg-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गण|मार्गणं|मार्गणः<BR>mārgaṇa (EI 24), a beggar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गणक|मार्गणकः<BR>mārgaṇaka (EI 3; IA 18; CII 4; HRS), known from re-<BR>cords like those of the Caulukyas; a levy; a kind of cess or tax;<BR>explained as ‘benevolences of a general character, as distin-<BR>guished from the special types called prasthaka and skandhaka’.<BR>See mārgaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गणिक<BR>mārgaṇika (IE 8-5), same as mārgaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गप<BR>Mārgapa (EI 20), same as Mārgapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गपाल<BR>Mārgapāla (HD), same as Mārgapati, etc. See Nārada<BR>quoted in the Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 71. Cf. Dikpāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गपति|मार्गपतिः<BR>Mārgapati (BL; HE), explained as ‘the guardian of the<BR>frontiers or passes’ (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, pp. 37, 41); probably,<BR>a collector of customs duties on the roads. See mārg-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गेश<BR>Mārgeśa (EI 20), same as Mārgapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरीछि<BR>marīchi, a theoretical unit of measurement (JNSI, Vol.<BR>XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्झक<BR>Marjhaka (ML), title of foreign origin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्तण्ड|मार्तंड|मार्तंडः|मार्तण्डः|मार्त्तण्ड|मार्त्तण्डः<BR>mārtaṇḍa (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः<BR>maṟutu (CITD), same is maṟuturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः<BR>maṟuturu (IE 8-6; CITD); also called maṟutu, mattaru,<BR>etc.; Telugu; Kannaḍa mattar or mattaru; a certain land measure<BR>of uncertain area generally used as an equivalent of nivartana,<BR>different kinds being mentioned as kāl-maṟuturu, ghaḍa-maṟuturu,<BR>kommu-maṟutu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्वाडी<BR>Marvāḏī, spelt Marwari in English; name of the Rājasthānī<BR>dialect prevalent in Marwar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्यादा|मर्य्यादा<BR>maryādā (SITI), Tamil mariyādi; customary dues; manners;<BR>ways; extent; limit; also spelt in Tamil as marjādi, mariśādi,<BR>maruśādi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्यादाधुर्य<BR>Maryādā-dhurya (BL), explained as ‘the Warden of Marches.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्यादापरिहार<BR>maryādā-parihāra (EI 22), customary exemptions of taxes.<BR>See parihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मास|मासं|मासः<BR>māsa (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माष|माषः<BR>māṣa (EI 21, 25, 30, 33; CII 4), according to the Kṛtya-<BR>kalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K. V. Rangaswami Aiyangar, p.<BR>125), a gold coin as opposed to silver māṣaka; name of a weight;<BR>name of a coin; 5 ratis in weight; sometimes regarded as 10<BR>ratis in weight and as equal to (1/4) of a śāna. See JNSI, Vol.<BR>XVI, p. 41. It was sometimes regarded as (1/20) of a paṇa of<BR>100 ratis (ibid., Vol. XV, p. 143). Cf. māṣaka, ādya-māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माषक|माषकः<BR>māṣaka (IE 8-8), name of a coin; cf. māṣa and dināri-<BR>māṣaka; mentioned as a silver coin (K. V. Rangaswami<BR>Aiyangar, Kṛtyakalpataru, Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, p. 125).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मासार्ध<BR>māsārdha (IE 7-1-2), used to indicate ‘six’; cf. māsa,<BR>‘twelve’; also pakṣa, ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माशु<BR>Māśu (Chamba), one enjoying land, who does not pay<BR>rent or tax but renders service; e. g., a carpenter, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मसूर|मसूरः<BR>masūra (ML), small-pox.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत|मतं|मतः<BR>mata, cf. guru-mata (CII 1), ‘a matter considered to be<BR>serious’.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-201" target="_blank">Page-201+ 40</a>]<BR>(LP), a signature; cf. the use of the word with the<BR>signature as in mataṃ mama amukasya found copied in many<BR>copper-plate grants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातङ्ग|मातंग|मातंगः|मातङ्गः<BR>mātaṅga (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातापितृपादानुध्यात<BR>mātā-pitṛ-pād-ānudhyāta (IE 8-2), ‘meditating on or<BR>favoured by the feet of one's parents’; epithet of rulers; cf.<BR>mātā-pitṛ-pād-ānudhyāna-rata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातरः|मातर<BR>Mātaraḥ (CII 3), the Divine Mothers, sometimes indicat-<BR>ed as seven in number; cf. Mātṛ and Mātṛ-gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठ|मठं|मठः<BR>maṭha (EI 17, 19, 23, 31, 32; CII 3, 4; SII 1; BL; ASLV;<BR>CITD), a school or religious college; a temple; a monastery;<BR>hermitage or convent; a monastery which was a religious and<BR>educational institution. See maṭhikā. In Telugu records, it<BR>also means ‘a bullock cart’ and ‘a cart load’ (cf. Kannaḍa<BR>maṭṭī, ‘a load’).<BR>(SITI), place where pilgrims and religious mendicants<BR>(tapasvins) are fed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठाधिपति|मठाधिपतिः<BR>Maṭhādhipati (EI 25), same as Jīyar and Mudaliyār; cf.<BR>Maṭhapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठपति<BR>Maṭhapati (EI 33), superintendent of a monastery; the<BR>chief priest of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माठापत्य<BR>māṭhāpatya (SITI), the office or position of a Maṭhapati;<BR>management of the affairs of a maṭha or temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठस्थान<BR>maṭha-sthāna (EI 26), a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठिका<BR>maṭhikā (EI 31), a hut, cottage or cell.<BR>(EI 26, 32), a shrine or temple; cf. maṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मतिसचिव<BR>Matisaciva (IE 8-3; HD), counsellor or minister; cf. Karma-<BR>saciva, administrative officer. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 44.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातृ<BR>Mātṛ (EI 9), the Divine Mothers, often described as seven<BR>in number; cf. mātṛ-maṇḍala, various forms of the Mother-<BR>goddess installed around a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मात्र|मात्रं<BR>Mātra, designation of a class of officers; cf. Mahāmātra<BR>in a similar sense. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 117<BR>(mentioned along with Mūlaprakṛti; cf. Prakṛti).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातृगण|मातृगणः<BR>Mātṛ-gaṇa (IA 7), the Divine Mothers, often described<BR>as seven in number. Cf. mātṛ-maṇḍala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्स्याकर<BR>matsy-ākara, cf. sa-matsy-ākara (IE 8-5), ‘together with the<BR>sources of fish’, the fishing right belonging to the king or land-<BR>lord; cf. jala-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मात्स्यन्याय|मात्स्यन्यायः<BR>mātsya-nyāya (EI 4), ‘the law of the fish’; anarchy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्त|मत्तः<BR>matta (LP), a signature; corrupt form of mata, ‘approved’,<BR>written along with the signature as in mataṃ mama amukasya.<BR>See mata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्तल्<BR>mattal (EI 16; IA 11), land measure; same as mattar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्तर्<BR>mattar (EI 16, 20), Kannaḍa; land measure; same as<BR>maṟuturu or nivartana; cf. gaṇṭi-mattar (IA 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्तरु<BR>mattaru (IE 8-6; CITD), same as mattar or nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मट्टस्कन्ध<BR>maṭṭa-skandha (LP), a layer of mud; cf. maṭṭa-skandha-<BR>rahita (LP), free from the layers of mud.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मट्टिवा<BR>Maṭṭivā (IA 10), Hindī; an exorcist.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मट्टु<BR>maṭṭu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मौख|मौखं<BR>maukha (EI 13), same as mukhya; ‘chief disciple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मौलिक|मौलिकः<BR>maulika (IE 8-5; EI 32), a tax; the principal or main tax<BR>or the perquisites of hereditary officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मवाड<BR>mavāḍa (CII 4), name of a tax; cf. māvaḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मावडै<BR>māvaḍai (EI 17), name of a tax. cf. mavāḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मयूर|मयूरः<BR>mayūra (CII 1), a peacock; a bird in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मयूट<BR>mayūṭa (HRS), probably, the contributions of fruits, fire-<BR>wood, etc., paid by villagers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मे<BR>Me (Chamba), abbreviation for Mehtā (Mahattaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेढि<BR>meḍhi (LP), a barn-yard, a threshing floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेढिहारक<BR>meḍhi-hāraka (LP), a special tax on the threshing-floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेध्य|मेध्यं|मेध्यः<BR>medhya, cf. a-paśu-medhya (IE 8-5), ‘free from the obligation<BR>of supplying animals for sacrifices’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेडि<BR>meḍi (EI 9), also called meli, a kidnapper of victims for<BR>sacrifices.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेघाडम्बर|मेघाडंबर|मेघाडम्बरः<BR>meghāḍambara (SII 3), Hindusthānī; a covered howdā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेह|मेहः<BR>Meha (IA 18), abbreviation of Mehara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेहर<BR>Mehara (EI 33), village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेहरी<BR>Meharī (EI 33), same as Devādāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेलापक|मेलापकः<BR>melāpaka (LP), a group.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेलि<BR>meli (EI 9), same as meḍi. (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्शान्ति<BR>Mel-śānti (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; chief priest in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्विट्टियवड्डारवुल<BR>melviṭṭiya-vaḍḍāravuḻa (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax;<BR>see vaḍḍāravuḻa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेर<BR>mera (EI 6), Telugu; a fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरिदर्ख<BR>Meridarkha (IE 8-3; ML), an official designation of foreign<BR>origin; same as Greek Meridarkhes, ‘a district officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरिदर्खेस्<BR>Meridarkhes (IE 8-3), Greek; see Meridarkha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरु|मेरुः<BR>meru (SII 3), name of a gift.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-203" target="_blank">Page-203+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 2; CII 4), a kind of temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेषसङ्क्रान्ति<BR>meṣa-saṅkrānti (CII 3, etc.), the entrance of the sun into<BR>the sign Aries, regarded as the starting point of the Śaka year;<BR>see also abdapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेय<BR>meya (IE 8-5; EI 31; HRS), the share of grains to be paid<BR>to the king or landlord; revenue from agricultural land paid in<BR>kind; same as bhāga. Cf. tulya-meya, tax on commodities<BR>brought to market for sale.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेय्कावल्<BR>Meykāval (ASLV), watchman in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मजिगिति<BR>majigiti (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 242), also spelt mijigiti;<BR>Indianised form of Arabic masjid, a mosque.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिजिगिति<BR>mijigiti (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12); see majigiti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिलिवलित<BR>milivalita, same as Sanskrit sammilita, ‘taken collectively’<BR>(JAS, Latters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिश्र|मिश्रं|मिश्रः<BR>miśra (IA 18), an honorific title; cf. Mahāmiśrapaṇdita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मीठिक<BR>Mīṭhika (LL), a polisher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिति|मितिः<BR>miti (IA 20), cf. Saṃvat 1384 miti Bhādra-vadi 3 Guru-dine;<BR>probably a corruption of Sanskrit mita, ‘counted’, ‘calculated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म्लेच्छ|म्लेच्छं|म्लेच्छः|म्लेछ<BR>Mleccha (EI 22), name applied to the Muhammadans<BR>and other foreigners; cf. Mleccheśvara (EI 32).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोचि<BR>moci, mocī (EI 2; CII 4), a shoe-maker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोदलवाड<BR>modala-vāḍa (IE 8-4), Kannaḍa; the chief village in a<BR>Pargana consisting of a number of villages, i. e. headquarters;<BR>sometimes called rājadhānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोदति<BR>modati, cf. svarge modati bhūmidaḥ; parasmaipada in place of<BR>the expected ātmanepada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोदिन<BR>Modina, same as Arabic Muazzin, ‘a public crier to prayers’<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोहिनी<BR>Mohinī (IA 19), female devils who possess men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोकीरक<BR>mokīraka (LP), a den in a mountain forest; Gujarātī<BR>bhokaruṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृड|मृडः<BR>mṛḍa, also called pṛḍa or pruḍa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 40);<BR>unit of metal weight like the mañjāḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृग|मृगः<BR>mṛga (CII 1), a deer; an animal in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृगाङ्क|मृगांक|मृगाङ्कः<BR>mṛgāṅka (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृत्युकवृत्ति<BR>mṛtyuka-vṛtti (BL; HRS), land granted by the king as<BR>military pension to the heir of a person killed in a battle against<BR>the king's enemies; compensatory grant made in favour of the<BR>heir of a person who died fighting on behalf of his master.<BR>See rakta-mānya, etc. Cf. vīra-śeṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूडा<BR>mūḍā (LP), same as mūḍaka or mūṭaka; a measure of<BR>capacity equal to a hundred maunds or to 24 maunds in the<BR>Surat District.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूडक|मूडकः<BR>mūḍaka (LP), same as mūṭaka or mūḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल्<BR>Mudal, cf. Evi-mudal (EI 25), an official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल्<BR>mudal (SII 3), Tamil; cost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल<BR>mudala (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 18), used in some Orissan<BR>inscriptions in the sense of a royal order [regarding the grant<BR>of land or its execution]. Cf. ibid., Vol. XXVIII, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदलि<BR>Mudali, Mudaliyār (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a chief.<BR>(EI 25), same as Maṭhādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदिरथ<BR>Mudiratha (EI 33), Oḏiyā; same as Mudrāhasta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदिता<BR>muditā (CII 4), cheerfulness; one of the Buddhist bhāvanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्रा<BR>mudrā (CII 4), the position of fingers in worship.<BR>(LP), the government seal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूर्धाधिकार<BR>mūrdh-ādhikāra, cf. Tamil mūtt-ādikāram (SITI), supreme<BR>authority.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राधिकारिन्<BR>Mudrādhikārin (EI 30), officer in charge of the royal seal;<BR>also called Mudr-ādhyakṣa, etc. Mudrādhikāri-saciva, may be<BR>Mudrādhikārin and Saciva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राधिकृत<BR>Mudr-ādhikṛta (EI 14, 15), same as Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राध्यक्ष|मुद्राध्यक्षः<BR>Mudr-ādhyakṣa, same as Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.; cf. Rājamudrā-<BR>dhikārin. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 96.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राहस्त<BR>Mudrāhasta (EI 33), official designation; same as Oḍiyā<BR>Mudiratha, designation of a class of servants in the temple of<BR>Jagannātha at Purī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्रापवार<BR>mudr-āpavāra (IE 8-8; EI 30), the crime of using coun-<BR>terfeit coins or the misuse of official seals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राशङ्ख<BR>mudrā-śaṅkha, cf. Tamil muttirai-ccaṅgu (SITI), a variety<BR>of conch-shell; conch-shell marked with a seal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्रावतार<BR>mudr-āvatāra, cf. Tamil muttir-āvatāram (SITI), an ear-<BR>ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राव्यापार<BR>mudrā-vyāpāra (IE 8-2); 8-3; BL), ‘the affairs associated<BR>with the royal seal’; often used in connection with the function<BR>of the viceroy described as conducting the said business; cf.<BR>samasta-mudrā-vyāpārān paripanthayati, śrī-śrīkaraṇ-ādi-samasta-mu-<BR>drāvyāpārān paripanthyati. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 154.<BR>See also vyāpāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदुड<BR>Muduḍa (EI 27), same as Mutuḍa; probably, a village<BR>headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुहपत्ति<BR>muha-patti (HA), a piece of cloth held in front of the mouth<BR>by Jain monks and nuns, while they are talking, in order to avoid<BR>small living beings being destroyed by breath.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुहूर्त|मुहूर्तं|मुहूर्तः|मुहूर्त्त|मुहूर्त्तः<BR>muhūrta (CII 3; IA 17), the thirtieth part of a mean day<BR>and night; equal to fortyeight minutes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुख|मुखं|मुखः<BR>mukha (EI 22; LL), the face, the gate; a door.<BR>Cf. dāna-mukha (ML), the principal gift.<BR>(EI 16), used at the end of compounds in the sense<BR>of mukhya; ‘head’ ‘heading’ or ‘sum’. Cf. pañca-mukha-nagara.<BR>Cf. muha-patti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखकट्टण<BR>mukha-kaṭṭaṇa (SITI), porch; also called darśana-kāṇikkai;<BR>front side of a building (SII 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखमण्डप<BR>mukha-maṇḍapa, Tamil muga-maṇḍaka (SITI), the front hall<BR>in a temple; cf. mahāmaṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखमुद्रा<BR>mukha-mudrā (EI 5), same as mauna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुक्ता<BR>muktā (BL), epithet of a grant; a grant; possibly Arabic<BR>mukhta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुक्तिभूमि<BR>mukti-bhūmi (EI 27, 30), a holy place where salvation is<BR>attainable on death.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखाहार<BR>mukh-āhāra, ‘principal food or meals’; same as mukhy-āhāra.<BR>See Sel. Ins., p. 162, text line 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुख्य|मुख्यः<BR>Mukhya (EI 32), city elder; member of the city council.<BR>Cf. Hindī Mukhiyā, a village elder.<BR>(CII 1), chief officer.<BR>(EI 16), see mukha meaning ‘head’, ‘heading’ or ‘sum’.<BR>mukhy-āhāra, cf. mukh-āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूक्कुत्ति<BR>mūkkutti (ASLV), an ornament; the nose-screw.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूल|मूलं|मूलः<BR>mūla (SITI), original; a document regarding a title to<BR>the property or right.<BR>(HRS), investment of capital which is one of the seven<BR>sources of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 26.<BR>(Sel. Ins., p. 163), seedling. Cf. sa-mūla (EI 13), a tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलभृत्य|मूलभृत्यः<BR>Mūla-bhṛtya (SITI), the chief servant; also called Caṇḍe-<BR>śvara who was the chief servant of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलगभारो<BR>mūla-gabhāro (HA), Jain; same as garbha-gṛha; the sanctum<BR>where the Mūla-nāyaka is installed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलाइटन<BR>mūlāiṭana (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलनायक<BR>Mūla-nāyaka (BL), epithet of a Jain Tīrthaṅkara; Mahāvīra<BR>called ‘the Mūla-nāyaka of the Saṇḍeraka-gaccha’.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-206" target="_blank">Page-206+ 40</a>]<BR>(HA), the main deity in the sanctum of a shrine or in a<BR>devakulikā; also the central Jina in a sculpture representing a<BR>group of Jinas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलपरिषद्<BR>mūla-pariṣad, cf. Tamil mūla-pariṣai (SITI), chief assembly<BR>[of a Śiva temple]; variously written in Tamil as mūla-paraḍai,<BR>mūla-paruḍai, mūla-pariḍai, mūla-paruṣai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलप्रकृति|मूलप्रकृतिः<BR>Mūlaprakṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR>(EI 18), probably ‘the prominent subjects’ or ‘landlords’<BR>or the six important officers styled Prakṛti (q.v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलरत्नभण्डरत्तार्<BR>Mūlaratnabhaṇḍarattār (SII 2), Sanskrit Mūlaratnabhāṇ-<BR>ḍārastha; treasures of the chief jewels.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलसङ्घ|मूलसंघ|मूलसंघः<BR>Mūla-saṅgha (EI 16, 25), name of a Jain sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलस्थान<BR>mūla-sthāna, cf. Tamil mūla-ttānam (SII 3; SITI; CITD),<BR>a place; the origin, base or foundation; the supreme spirit; the<BR>central shrine in a temple (SII 13); the place where the main<BR>image stands.<BR>(EI 18), an important seat of monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलवीस<BR>mūla-vīsa (EI 6; ASLV), cf. Telugu-Kannaḍa vīsa, (1/16) of<BR>a haṇa (paṇa); name of a tax or levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलिआ<BR>Mūliā (EI 31), Oḏiyā; a day-labourer; from Sanskrit<BR>Mūlika, possibly an abbreviation of Pādamūlika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलुड<BR>Mūḻuḍa (LL), same as Mutuḍa or Muduḍa; probably, a<BR>village headman. Cf. Śīrṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूल्य|मूल्यं<BR>mūlya (CII 3), an endowment; equivalent to akṣaya-nīvī,<BR>a perpetual endowment.<BR>(HRS), proceeds of sale of metal-ware manufactured in<BR>the government workshops, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुम्मुडि<BR>Mummuḍi, cf. Mummuḍi-col13a, ‘three times a Coḻa king’;<BR>cf. Nūrmaḍi and Immaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुम्मुरिदण्ड<BR>mummuri-daṇḍa (ASLV), name of an organisation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुमोद<BR>mumoda (EI 13), parasmaipada form instead of the expected<BR>ātmanepada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूना<BR>Mū°-nā° (PJS), contraction of Mūla-nāyaka, ‘the principal<BR>deity in a Jain temple’; often found in medieval Jain inscrip-<BR>tions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुण्डमोल<BR>muṇḍamola (IE 8-5), cf. khaṇḍapāla-muṇḍamola (EI 24);<BR>name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुन्दिरि<BR>mundiri (EI), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुनि|मुनिः<BR>muni (SII 1; IA 30; LL), a Jain monk.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुरा<BR>murā (EI 33), a measure of capacity; cf. muraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुरक<BR>muraka (EI 9), a measure; cf. murā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूर्ति|मूर्तिः|मूर्त्ति|मूर्त्तिः<BR>mūrti (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’; rarely used to indicate ‘eight’;<BR>but cf. rūpa used in the sense of ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुरुण्ड<BR>Muruṇḍa (EI 14, 19), Śaka title of a chief; a title or tribal<BR>name; supposed to be derived from a Scythian word meaning<BR>‘a king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूसरवारु<BR>Mūsara-vāru (CITD), Telugu; probably, goldsmiths or<BR>manufacturers of metallic objects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुष्टि|मुष्टिः<BR>muṣṭi (IE 8-6), a handful.<BR>Cf. eka-muṣṭyā (LP), ‘at the same time’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुटक<BR>muṭaka, mūṭaka (IE 8-5; EI 25), a measure or head-load;<BR>cf. caṇā-satka-mūṭaka, ‘one mūṭaka of peas’ (LP). See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 303, text line 50; cf. moṭ (a load) in Hindī and<BR>other dialects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूटक|मूटकः<BR>mūṭaka (LP), same as mūḍā, a measure of capacity equal<BR>to a hundred or twentyfour maunds; a bullock's load (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XIV, p. 309; cf. Marāṭhī mūṭh, ‘a bullock's pack-saddle’).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुटी<BR>mu-ṭī, abbreviation of an expression probably meaning<BR>‘a mound covered with jungle’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुतिरिगै<BR>mutirigai (IE 8-6), Tamil; a small land measure equal to<BR>(1/320) of a veli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुत्कलनीय<BR>mutkalanīya (LP), ‘may be sent’; cf. Gujarātī mokalavuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुत्तावरण<BR>muttāvaraṇa (EI 21), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुतुड<BR>Mutuḍa (EI 27), also spelt as Muduḍa, Muḻuḍa; probably,<BR>the headman of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नभस्<BR>nabhas (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ना<BR>nā, cf. nā-bhū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाभू<BR>nā-bhū (IE 1), abbreviation of nāla-bhūmi, ‘cultivated<BR>land’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाड्<BR>nāḍ (ASLV), same as nāḍu; a district; the assembly of a<BR>district; the professional association and guild of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नड|नडं|नडः<BR>naḍa (IE 8-6), same as nala, a measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडगौड<BR>Nāḍa-gauḍa, same as Nāḍu-gauḍa, Nār-gāvuṇḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडक<BR>nāḍaka, same as nāḍuka (IE 8-4); same as nāḍ, nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडसेनबोव<BR>Nāḍa-senabova (ASLV), officer in charge of the accounts<BR>of a nāḍu or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडी<BR>nāḍī (IA 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नदीकूल<BR>nadī-kūla (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नदीपाल<BR>nadīpāla (HRS), fixed tax on villages situated upon the<BR>banks of rivers and lakes as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नदीतरस्थान|नदीतरस्थानं<BR>nadītara-sthāna (IE 8-5), ferry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडीयक<BR>nāḍīyaka (LP), same as aṇāḍīyaka; a place where the carts<BR>stand to dispose of goods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडु<BR>nāḍu (IE 8-4; SII 1; SITI), a country; a territorial divi-<BR>sion; a district or a subdivision; the local assembly to govern<BR>the civic affairs of the division called nāḍu.<BR>(EI 31), a chamber.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुगौद<BR>Nāḍu-gauda (ASLV), the head of an organisation relating<BR>to a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुक<BR>nāḍuka (EI 12; ASLV), same as nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नग|नगः<BR>naga (IE 8-1-2), ‘seven’; rarely used to indicate ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाग|नागं|नागः<BR>nāga (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागदल<BR>nāgadala (BL), meaning uncertain; cf. ‘a race subsisting<BR>on nāgadala’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागामावास्या<BR>nāg-āmāvāsyā, cf. nāgara-amāvāsyā (EI 5), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगकार<BR>Nagakāra (BL), wrong reading for Taṭṭhakāra, ‘a<BR>brazier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगर|नगरं<BR>nagara (IE 8-4), city; palace; cf. navara.<BR>(EI 21; SITI), a commercial guild; guild of merchants;<BR>a mercantile town; often spelt in Kannaḍa inscriptions as nakara<BR>or nakhara; cf. pañca-nagara.<BR>(CITD), in Telugu inscriptions, a territorial assembly<BR>like the sabhā and ūr; the merchant community in general or<BR>the organization of the merchant community of a town. In<BR>some places, the nagara and ūr carried on their functions side<BR>by side. The word is sometimes used to indicate occupational<BR>groups like śāleyanagarattom. Cf. K. A. Nilakanta Sastri,<BR>The Col13as, Vol. II, 1st ed., p. 294.<BR>(EI 4), same as Kaliṅga-nagara. Cf. śrī-Nagara-bhukti=<BR>Pāṭaliputra-bhukti (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 311).<BR>(IA 17), represented in Prakrit by nera further corrupted<BR>to ner or nar. See nagarī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगराधिकृत|नगराधिकृतः<BR>Nagar-ādhikṛta (HD), the city prefect. See Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>IV. 81; VI. 70; VIII. 3334.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगराधिप|नगराधिपः<BR>Nagar-ādhipa (HD), same as Nagar-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागरक|नागरकः<BR>Nāgaraka (HD), same as Nāgarika; chief officer of the<BR>city; the city prefect of police. See Arthaśāstra, II. 36; Kāma-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-209" target="_blank">Page-209+ 40</a>]<BR>sūtra, V. 5. 9 (the commentator explaining Nāgaraka as Daṇḍa-<BR>pāśika). Cf. Talavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगराक्षदर्श<BR>Nagar-ākṣadarśa (LL), the city-judge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरमहल्लक<BR>Nagara-mahallaka (EI 25), the City Elder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरपरिवार<BR>nagara-parivāra (ASLV), an organisation relating to a town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरपति<BR>Nagarapati (EI 12, 32; HD), the city prefect; ruler of a<BR>city. See Ind. Ant., Vol. IV, p. 35.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगररक्षक<BR>Nagara-rakṣaka (IE 8-2), same as Talāra, Nagararakṣin,<BR>Nāgarika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगररक्षिन्<BR>Nagara-rakṣin, same as Nagara-rakṣaka, etc; prefect of the<BR>city police (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 156-57).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरश्रेष्ठिन्<BR>Nagara-śreṣṭhin (IE 8-3; EI 15, 21; BL; HD), according<BR>to some, the city banker or guild president of the town; but<BR>actually, the chairman of a board of administration like the<BR>Pañcāyat; same as the Nagarseṭh who was the chairman of the<BR>board called Cauthiyā in late medieval Rajasthan. See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 115; Proc. IHC, Ahmadabad, 1954, pp. 52 ff. See<BR>Pura-śreṣṭhin, Pura-pradhāna, Śeṭṭi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरस्वामिन्<BR>Nagara-svāmin (SITI), headman of the merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरत्तार्<BR>Nagarattār (EI 30), Sanskrit Nagarastha; leading men of<BR>the city.<BR>(ASLV; SITI), members of a guild of a town; members<BR>of a mercantile guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरव्यवहारिक<BR>Nagara-vyavahārika (IE 8-3; CII 1; HD), Prakrit Nagala-<BR>viyohālaka; judicial officer of a city; superintendent of the<BR>judicial affairs of a city; the city magistrate; also styled a Mahā-<BR>mātra. See Paura-vyavahārika (Arthaśāstra, I. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरी<BR>nagarī (IA 17), represented in Prakrit by nerī; further<BR>corrupted into nar. See nagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागरिक<BR>Nāgarika (HD), chief of the police. See Vikramorvaśīya,<BR>V (after verse 4); Daśakumāracarita, II, pp. 58-59. The<BR>Vaijayantī explains the word as Kārāpati, the superintendent of<BR>jails.<BR>(ASLV), the chief bailiff or prefect at Vijayanagara.<BR>See also Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 95-96. Cf. Nagara-rakṣin,<BR>etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगर्सेठ्<BR>Nagar-seṭh (IE 8-3), Sanskrit Nagara-śreṣṭhin (q.v.); desig-<BR>nation of the chairman of an administrative board called Cauthiyā<BR>in Western India. See Śeṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागवन<BR>nāga-vana (IE 8-4), an elephant-forest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नहरण<BR>naharaṇa, a thief's weapon to dig a hole in the walls (Journ.<BR>Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1, p. 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैधानीशिला<BR>naidhānī-śilā (EI 32), a boundary pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैगम|नैगमः<BR>Naigama, cf. Negama (EI 24; LL), the inhabitant of a<BR>nigama (township); a merchant. See Nigama-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैजायमान<BR>naijāyamāna (LP), from nija; ‘when they are going to get<BR>themselves separated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैमित्तिक|नैमित्तिकं<BR>Naimittika (EI 19, 26; HD), a soothsayer or astrologer.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैर्गमिक<BR>nairgamika (IE 8-8; EI 30), exit tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैवेद्य|नैवेद्यं<BR>naivedya (EI 30), daily offerings to gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैयामिक<BR>Naiyāmika, Naiyamika (EI 24), also called Naiyāvika; a<BR>law officer or judge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैयोगिक<BR>Naiyogika (IE 8-3; EI 12, 24), cf. Niyogika (EI 8), ‘an<BR>officer’; officer-in-charge of an administrative unit; same as<BR>Niyogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैय्योक<BR>Naiyyoka (EI 2), a mistake for Naiyogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नकर<BR>nakara, Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit nagara (q. v.); also<BR>spelt nakhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नख|नखं|नखः<BR>nakha (IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नखर|नखरं|नखरः<BR>nakhara, Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit nagara (q. v.); also<BR>spelt nakara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाखुदा<BR>Nākhudā Arabic; captain or commander of a ship (Ep.<BR>Ind. Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नक्षत्र|नक्षत्रं<BR>nakṣatra (CII 3), a lunar mansion.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyseven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल|नलं|नलः<BR>nala (IE 8-6), measuring rod; same as daṇḍa; sometimes<BR>regarded as 12 cubits, 22 cubits, 56 cubits, etc., in length; cf.<BR>Samataṭīya-nala, ‘the rod as used in the Samataṭa country’;<BR>Vṛṣabhaśaṅkara-nala, ‘the rod introduced by king Vṛṣabha-<BR>śaṅkara’, ‘the rod of the village of Pattiyamattavura’, etc.<BR>See kol, kolu, ghaḻe, etc.<BR>(IE 8-6), cf. aṣṭaka-navaka-nala, ṣaṭka-nala, etc., the first<BR>probably referring to the custom of measuring the length and<BR>breadth of a plot of land by rods of different length.<BR>(EI 28), used in some Orissan inscriptions in the sense of<BR>measurement of the area [of the gift land] (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXI, p. 20).<BR>(EI 21), a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नला<BR>nalā, same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाल|नालं<BR>nāla, cf. sa-khila-nāla (IE 8-5; EI 14); cultivated land;<BR>same as nāla-bhūmi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालभूमि<BR>nāla-bhūmi (IE 8-1), cultivated land; see nāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालि|नालिः<BR>nāḻi, nāl13i (EI 9, 28), a grain measure; same as nālikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालिका<BR>nālikā (IE 8-6), same as Pali nālī or nāḻi; regarded as the<BR>same as prastha, i. e. one-sixteenth of a droṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालिकावाप<BR>nālikāvāpa (IE 8-6; EI 31), a land measure; an area of<BR>land requiring one nālikā measure of seed grains for sowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नलु<BR>nalu, nāluka (EI 7; CII 4), a measure of land; same as<BR>nalva; 400 (or 100 or 120) square cubits.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नामगृह<BR>nāma-gṛha, cf. nāmghar (IA 25), Assamese; a place of<BR>worship of the Vaiṣṇavas, where plays, etc., are performed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमक<BR>namaka (IA 18), name applied to the first section of the<BR>Rudrajapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नामकरण|नामकरणं<BR>nāmakaraṇa (BL), naming ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नामलिङ्ग<BR>nāma-liṅga (EI 15), a deity bearing the name of a person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमस्<BR>namas (CII 3), ‘reverence’; an invocation, generally con-<BR>nected with the names of gods, at the commencement of ins-<BR>criptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमस्य|नमस्यः<BR>namasya (IE 8-5; EI 5, 13, 28), same as mānya, sarva-na-<BR>masya, namasya-vṛtti, etc.; a rent-free tenure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमस्यवृत्ति<BR>namasya-vṛtti (IE 8-5; EI 32), same as sarva-namasya, etc.;<BR>a tax-free holding.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणा<BR>nāṇā (EI 30), name of a coin; same as nāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नानादेशि<BR>nānādeśi (EI 31; SITI; ASLV), guild of merchants<BR>coming from outside.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणै<BR>nāṇai (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 197, text line 18), same<BR>as Sanskrit nāṇaka; ‘a coin.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणक|नाणकं<BR>nāṇaka, see nāṇai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नङ्ग|नंग|नंगः|नङ्गः<BR>naṅga (IE 8-5; EI 25), cf. naṅge gṛhītasya yac=c=āṣṭau<BR>ṣoḍaśa vā nagara-mahallakā vicārya vadante tad=eva pranāṇam; a<BR>word of uncertain meaning; but a fine is prescribed for a<BR>merchant's son described as naṅge gṛhīta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणी<BR>Nāṇī (CII 4), an engraver; probably a corruption of<BR>Vijñānin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्द|नंद|नंदः|नन्दः<BR>nanda (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दादीप<BR>nandā-dīpa, also called nandā-dīvigĕ (CITD); used in<BR>Telugu and Kannaḍa inscriptions in the sense of a lamp that<BR>is always kept burning before a deity in a temple; same as<BR>akhaṇḍa-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दवन<BR>nandavana, nandāvana, cf. tiru-nandavanam, etc. (SII 1);<BR>a sacred flower-garden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दाविलक्कु<BR>nandā-viḻakku (SII 1, 2), also spelt as nondā°, nundā°; a<BR>perpetual lamp; same as nandā-dīpa, akhaṇḍa-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दीमुख<BR>nandīmukha (CII 1), a species of water-birds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नान्दीसमारोहण<BR>nāndī-samārohaṇa (EI 32), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दीश्वराष्टमी<BR>nandīśvar-āṣṭamī (SII 11-1), same as Phālguna-sudi 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नप्तृ<BR>naptṛ (CII 1), a grandson.<BR>(EI 4, 9), a great-grandson.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नप्तृक<BR>naptṛka, cf. natika (EI 22), a grandson.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नराधिपति|नराधिपतिः<BR>Narādhipati (IA 15), royal title; same as Narapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नरपति|नरपतिः<BR>Narapati (IE 8-2; EI 12, 19; HD; SITI), ‘lord of men’,<BR>‘leader of the infantry’; title borne by the Col13a monarchs;<BR>Vijayanagara rulers, etc., in view of the large infantry they<BR>possessed; cf. the titles Aśvapati and Gajapati, and also Aśvapati-<BR>gajapati-narapati-rāja-tray-ādhipati which was the title of some<BR>kings. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 7; JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नरस्वामिन्<BR>Narasvāmin, probably ‘a Jāgīrdār’; cf. °grāme mahattama-<BR>narasvāminaḥ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 51).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नार्गावुण्ड<BR>Nār-gāvuṇḍa (EI 23, 27), village headman; also called<BR>Nāḍa-gauḍa; cf. Nār-gāvuṇḍa-svāmya-bhūta, ‘being in the posse-<BR>ssion of the Nār-gāvuṇḍas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नारिकेल|नारिकेलः<BR>nārikela, cf. sa-guvāka-nārikela (EI 8-5); coconut palms<BR>[which the ordinary tenants had no right to enjoy].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नर्मसचिव|नर्मसचिवः|नर्म्मसचिव<BR>Narma-saciva (EI 13), minister of amusement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नासत्य<BR>Nāsatya (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्ट|नष्टः<BR>naṣṭa (LP), disappeared.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्टभरट<BR>naṣṭabharaṭa (HRS), name of a levy; same as naṣṭibharaṭa;<BR>(see Ep. Ind., Vol. III, note 4); may be ‘compensation for losses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्टराज्य<BR>naṣṭa-rājya (IA 22), former rule of a dead king. Cf. also<BR>vinaṣṭa-rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्टिभरट<BR>naṣṭibharaṭa (HRS), same as naṣṭabharaṭa; name of a levy<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 264, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नट|नटः<BR>Naṭa (EI 31), a dancer; sometimes mentioned in the list<BR>of officials probably indicating ‘the chief dancer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाटकशाला<BR>nāṭaka-śālā (SII 3; 11-1), a theatre hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाथ|नाथः<BR>Nātha (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 313), same as Nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नट्टकार<BR>Naṭṭakāra (BL), mistake for Taṭṭhakāra, a brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टवर्<BR>Nāṭṭavar (ASLV), Tamil; members of an organisation<BR>relating to a nāḍu or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्यशाला<BR>nāṭya-śālā (EI 4), dance hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौबलहस्त्यश्वगोमहिषाजाविकादिव्यापृत<BR>Naubala-hasty-aśva-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādi-vyāpṛta (IE 8-3; EI<BR>12), an officer in charge of the royal navy and cattle; looks like<BR>a combination of Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-naubala-vyāpṛtaka and Hasty-<BR>aśv-oṣṭra-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādi-vyāpṛtaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौदण्ड|नौदंड|नौदण्डः<BR>naudaṇḍa, same as naupatha (IHQ, Vol. XXIII, pp.<BR>255-56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौकाबन्ध<BR>naukā-bandha (EI 32), a levy from the boatmen at landing<BR>places.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौकाध्यक्ष<BR>Nauk-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), officer in charge of the navy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौकाभाटक<BR>naukā-bhāṭaka (EI 14), charges for hiring a boat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौक्रम|नौक्रमः<BR>nau-krama (EI 19), a bridge of boats or a ferry station.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौवाह|नौवाहः<BR>Nauvāha (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 244), a ship-owner, mari-<BR>ner or captain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौवाटक<BR>Nauvāṭaka (EI 24), a naval officer. Cf. Ardha-nauvāṭaka.<BR>(EI 15), probably, a wall (so to say) made of a large<BR>number of boats.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौवित्तक<BR>Nauvittaka, leader or owner of ships (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवचतुष्किका<BR>nava-catuṣkikā, cf. nava-cokī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवचोकी<BR>nava-cokī (HA), Sanskrit nava-catuṣkikā; a hall (open on<BR>three sides) adjacent to and in front of the gūḍha-maṇḍapa, so<BR>called because it is divided into nine sections by means of the<BR>pillars supporting its ceiling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नावः|नाव<BR>nāvaḥ (HRS), charges for hiring royal boats; same as<BR>nau-bhāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकार<BR>navakāra (HA), Sanskrit namaskāra; the chief Jain formula<BR>for worship or an obeissance to the arhats, siddhas, ācāryas, upā-<BR>dhyāyas and sādhus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मन्<BR>nava-karman, cf. Tamil nava-karumam (SITI); renovation;<BR>repairs. Cf. Prakrit nava-kama (EI 20), foundation, extension<BR>or repairs to buildings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मपति<BR>Navakarmapati (EI 22), an architect or the supervisor of<BR>building operations; same as Navakarmika and Navakarmin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मिक<BR>Navakarmika (EI 16, 23; LL), superintendent of a work<BR>(possibly of repairs); cf. Navakamika (EI 4, 20), an overseer<BR>of work (building or repairing operations); superintendent of<BR>building operations. Cf. Navakarmapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मिन्<BR>Navakarmin (ML), same as Navakarmika, the superinten-<BR>dent of a work. Cf. Navakarmapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवखण्ड<BR>nava-khaṇḍa (IE 8-4), epithet of Bhārata or Bhāratavarṣa;<BR>see khaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवमिका<BR>navamikā (EI 9), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवाङ्ग|नवाङ्गः<BR>navāṅga, cf. Pali navaṃga (EI 33); cf. navāṅga-Śāstṛ-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवनिधान<BR>nava-nidhāna, cf. nava-nidhāna-sahita (IA 11), epithet of gift<BR>land; see Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, pp. 180 ff. (Inscriptions Nos. 4-11);<BR>explained as ‘new taxes imposed for the first time’; probably<BR>‘a fresh assessment of tax’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवर<BR>navara, Oḏiyā; same as Sanskrit nagara; capital city, palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवरत्न|नवरत्नं<BR>nava-ratna (BL), the nine gems at Vikramāditya's court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवरात्र|नवरात्रं<BR>navarātra, navarātri (EI 11, 25; CII 4), the festival of<BR>Durgā; Āśvina-sudi 1 to 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवरात्रिअमावास्या<BR>navarātri-amāvāsyā (EI 5), new-moon preceding the nava-<BR>rātri; also called mahālayā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवतरभूमी<BR>navatara-bhūmī (LP), land as yet uncultivated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवीनपञ्जिकाकरण<BR>navīna-pañjikā-karaṇa (LP), probably, ‘to have new fences’,<BR>i. e. ‘to have additional land in one's possession.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नय|नयः<BR>naya (EI 3), argumentation.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, pp. 318 ff, text lines 26-27), a<BR>territorial division like a Pargana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायक|नायकः<BR>Nāyaka (EI 33; CII 4), a royal officer or ruling chief.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 142, text line 35.<BR>(HD), explained as ‘the head of ten villages.’ See Artha-<BR>śāstra, I. 12; Śukra, I. 192.<BR>(EI 32; BL), title of a subordinate ruler.<BR>(ASLV), one who held lands from the Vijayanagara<BR>kings on the condition of offering military service (cf.<BR>Amara-nāyaka).<BR>(EI 7), a general.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 313), head of a nāḍu or district.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायकनरक<BR>nāyaka-naraka (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; the principal<BR>hell.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायकवाडि<BR>Nāyakavāḍi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; watchmen stationed<BR>by the State or landlord to keep watch over the crops before or<BR>during harvest time; the inām granted to such persons was<BR>known as kākku-nāyaka-viḻāgam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नयन|नयनं<BR>nayana (IE 8-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायङ्कर<BR>nāyaṅkara, nāyaṅkāra (EI 16; ASLV), the feudal system<BR>prevalent in the Vijayanagara kingdom, in which the Nāyakas<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-215" target="_blank">Page-215+ 40</a>]<BR>enjoyed royal land on condition of offering military service; see<BR>Nāyaka, Amara-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नयिनार्<BR>Nayinār (IA 12), Tamil; the chief temple-servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्रान<BR>nazrāna (EI 26), Persian; customary presents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेल्लायम्<BR>nell-āyam (SII 1), Tamil, revenue in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेमक<BR>nemaka (EI 1), probably, salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेत्र|नेत्रं<BR>netra (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; in some areas of Eastern India, it<BR>was used in the sense of Hara-netra, ‘three’. The word dṛk<BR>seems to bear the sense of three in the Pamulavaka plates of<BR>Eastern Cālukya Vijayāditya VII (JAHRS, Vol. II, p. 287,<BR>text line 67).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेत्तरगोडग<BR>nettara-goḍaga (ASLV), a kind of compensation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नि|निः<BR>ni (IE 8-1; EI 33), abbreviation of nibaddha or nirīkṣita,<BR>i. e. registered or approved.<BR>(Select Inscriptions, pp. 238-39, 247-48), explained as an<BR>abbreviation of nija and as a sort of genitive suffix often with a<BR>word indicating relationship understood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नी<BR>nī (LP), used for the verb ānī.<BR>(LP), to make.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबद्ध<BR>nibaddha (IE 8-1; EI 29), explained as ‘registered’.<BR>(IA 13), used in respect of a copper-plate grant and trans-<BR>lated as ‘prepared’.<BR>(IA 15), interpreted as ‘assigned’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबन्ध्|निबंध्<BR>nibandh (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), to register.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबन्ध|निबंध|निबन्धं|निबंधः|निबन्धः<BR>nibandha (EI 7), an endowment.<BR>(Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 49), a register.<BR>(SII 2), also spelt nivanda or nimanda in Tamil; the fixed<BR>requirements of a temple; cf. Nivandakkārar, temple servants<BR>who attend to the nibandha.<BR>(SII 3; SITI), expenses or arrangements; arrangement<BR>for the conduct of affairs in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबरव<BR>nibarava (CITD), Telugu; an unknown weight used in<BR>the case of salt and paddy (unhusked rice).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीच|नीचः<BR>nīca (CII 1), mean or low.<BR>(CII 1), southern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीचोच्चमास<BR>nīcocca-māsa (CII 3), the anomalistic month, the<BR>period in which the moon comes from perigee or apogee to<BR>the same point again; its duration is 27 days, 33 ghaṭīs<BR>and 16. 65 palas, or 27 tithis 59 ghaṭīs and 33. 36 palas; see<BR>also kendra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निदान|निदानं<BR>nidāna (CITD), Telugu; same as Sanskrit nidhāna; a<BR>treasure; a hoard or fund; store, wealth or property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधान|निधानं<BR>nidhāna (HRS), explained as ‘cess imposed upon agricultural<BR>land’; but ‘freshly assessed tax’; cf. nava-nidhāna. cf. sa-nidhi-nidhāna<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139, text line 20), in which it is the<BR>same as nikṣepa; also sa-vana-śvabhra-nidhāna; probably, a mine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधानालिपक<BR>nidhān-ālipaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 274, text line 61),<BR>probably the same as nidhi-nikṣepa or nidhy-upanidhi. But ālipaka,<BR>also read as āliyaka and often spelt as ālīpaka, may refer to the<BR>right on beehives and honey (see alīpaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधि|निधिः<BR>nidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR>Cf. nidhi-nikṣepa (IE 8-5; HRS; SITI); treasure trove;<BR>a treasure-hoard; hidden treasure under the ground; one of the<BR>eight kinds of enjoyments allowed to the donees of rent-free land.<BR>Cf. nidhāna.<BR>(CITD), a treasure; a repository; store; a place where<BR>anything is placed.<BR>Cf. nidhi-nikṣepa-jala-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣ-prakāra-bīravaṇa-<BR>pārikh-āya-sahita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247; text lines 101-02),<BR>privilege mentioned along with aṣṭabhoga-tejassvāmya-daṇdaśulka-<BR>yukta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निध्याप्ति<BR>nidhyāpti, cf. Prakrit nijhati (EI 2; CII 1), explanation, ex-<BR>hortation or argumentation; to cause understanding; cf. anu-<BR>nidhyāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निध्यायन<BR>nidhyāyana, cf. nijhati (CII 1); the act of explaining; argu-<BR>mentation [in favour of a particular view]; consolation. See<BR>nidhyāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निद्राकलस<BR>nidrā-kalasa, a pūrṇa-ghaṭa kept near the head of the bed<BR>(Matsya Purāṇa, 265. 14; Harṣacarita, IV).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निगमपुत्र<BR>Nigama-putra (LL), inhabitant of a nigama (township); a<BR>merchant; cf. Naigama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निगमसभा<BR>nigama-sabhā (EI 7, 8), a public hall or the assembly of the<BR>town Pañcāyat; the city council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निग्रह|निग्रहः<BR>nigraha (EI 27), ‘reducer’. Cf. also koṭṭa-nigraha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निहेलपति<BR>Nihelapati (IE 8-3; HD), official designation of uncertain<BR>import; probably, the governor of a territorial unit; also spelt<BR>Nihilapati. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 124; CII, Vol. III, p. 289.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निहिलपति<BR>Nihilapati (IE 8-3; CII 3; HD), an official title of uncertain<BR>import. See Nihelapati. Cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 289.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निःसार|निःसारः<BR>niḥsāra, cf. nissāreṇa (LP), ‘in an excellent manner.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निकर|निकरः<BR>nikara (EI 12, 33), cf. yathādīyamāna-bhoga-bhāga-kara-<BR>nikara-ādikam; a small tax or cess; small amount of rent fixed<BR>for a gift land; practically the same as kara or tax (IHQ, Vol.<BR>XXXIV, p. 279). Cf. upakara, tṛṇodaka, mānya-kaṇikĕ, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निकाय|निकायः<BR>nikāya (EI 7), a religious corporation.<BR>(EI 18; LL), a Buddhist school or community; a frater-<BR>nity of Buddhist monks.<BR>Cf. Kaulika-nikāya (LL), a guild of the Kaulikas or weavers.<BR>(CII 1), a class or group.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निकेफोरोस्<BR>Nikephoros (IE 8-2), Greek; royal title; ‘victorious’; trans-<BR>lated into Prakrit-Sanskrit as Jayadhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निक्षेप|निक्षेपः<BR>nikṣepa, cf. nidhi-nikṣepa (IE 8-5; HRS), deposits and finds<BR>on the soil (probably including beehives, cf. alīpaka, nidhāna);<BR>deposits; same as upanidhi; one of the eight kinds of enjoyment<BR>of the property allowed to the donees of rent-free land;<BR>sometimes wrongly explained as a treasure-trove (SITI).<BR>See nidhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीलडुम्फक<BR>nīla-ḍumphaka (IE 8-8), probably, one whose profession<BR>was to press indigo plants for getting blue dye; ḍumphaka may<BR>be Sanskrit dṛmphaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीलकूटी<BR>nīla-kūṭī (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, an indigo manufactory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निलय|निलयः<BR>nilaya (EI 9), cf. grāma-nilaya-nāḍa-sarva-bādhā-parihāreṇa;<BR>probably a territorial unit like a Parganā; the inhabited area<BR>of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निमन्त्रण|निमंत्रण|निमंत्रणं|निमन्त्रणं<BR>nimantraṇa (IA 20), explained as ‘an invitation which<BR>admits of no refusal’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निमित्त|निमित्तं<BR>nimitta (SII 1), a sign.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निम्नोन्नत<BR>nimn-onnata (IA 16), explained as ‘what is above and<BR>below’; but really, ‘low and high lands’; cf. khalla-unnata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निन्दन|निंदन|निंदनं|निन्दनं<BR>nindana (LP), weeding out grass growing along with the<BR>crops; cf. Gujarātī nindavuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नि|निः<BR>niṉraiṟai (EI 30), Tamil; permanent tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निपान|निपानं<BR>nipāna, same as pāna, cf. grāma-nipāna-kūpaka (EI 4); ‘the<BR>drinking well of a village’; may also be the same as āpāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निप्रतिष्ठापित<BR>nipratiṣṭhāpita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248), same as<BR>pratiṣṭhāpita; established, installed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीरगृह<BR>nīra-gṛha (EI 31), ‘a water-house’; same as Persian abdār-<BR>khāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीराजन|नीराजनं<BR>nīrājana (SII 1), the waving of a lamp before an idol; same<BR>as ārātrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरस्त|निरस्तः<BR>nirasta, nirasti, cf. sarvajāta-bhoga-nirastyā (IE 8-5), ‘with<BR>all kinds of the [king's] rights renunciated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरवकर<BR>niravakara (EI 31), used in some Orissan inscriptions in<BR>the sense of ‘the nett total after deductions’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरयण<BR>nirayaṇa (CII 3), destitute of precession of the equinoxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्ग्रन्थ|निर्ग्रंथ|निर्ग्रन्थः<BR>Nirgrantha (CII 1), a follower of the Jain religion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्ग्रन्थनाथ<BR>Nirgranthanātha (BL), epithet of a Jain poet of the Digam-<BR>bara sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरीक्षित|निरीक्षितं<BR>nirīkṣita (IE 8-1), same as ḍṛṣṭa, ‘examined [and approv-<BR>ed]’. See ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्लक्षण|निर्लक्षणः<BR>nirlakṣaṇa (CII 1), castration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीरोग<BR>nīroga, the science of medicine (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV,<BR>p. 146).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूध्य<BR>nirūdhya (LP), ‘up to’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीरुनेल<BR>nīru-nela, nīr-nela (CITD), Telugu; low lying land irri-<BR>gated by water from a tank, canal, well, etc.; usually called<BR>‘wet land’ and considered the most valuable. Cf. veli-volamu<BR>or veli-cenu, i. e. land on a comparatively higher level, which<BR>depends solely on rain and is called ‘dry land’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूप<BR>nirūpa (SITI), written order; communication from<BR>the king or other superiors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूप<BR>Nirūpa (ASLV), the carrier of a royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूपण|निरूपणं<BR>nirūpaṇa (LP), order for transfer of service; appointment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूपित|निरूपितः<BR>nirūpita (LP), appointed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूपितदण्ड<BR>nirūpita-daṇḍa (IA 18), wrongly regarded as a doubtful<BR>technical expression; actually, ‘appointed as Daṇḍa (i.e. Daṇda-<BR>nāyaka)’. Cf. niyukta-Daṇda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वचनीय<BR>nirvacanīya, cf. bhoga-sambandha-nirvacanīya (EI 12), ‘the<BR>relations [of the gift land] with the district [to which it belong-<BR>ed] should not be reckoned’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वह्<BR>nirvah, cf. nirvahanīya (LP), ‘should be observed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाह|निर्वाहः|निर्व्वाह|निर्व्वाहः<BR>nirvāha, cf. vāśal-nirvāham (SITI), same as vāśal-kāriyam<BR>(kārya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाह|निर्वाहः|निर्व्वाह|निर्व्वाहः<BR>Nirvāha (ASLV), probably, a manager.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाहसभा<BR>nirvāha-sabhā (SITI), a managing or executive committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाण|निर्व्वाण|निर्व्वाणं|निर्व्वाणः<BR>nirvāṇa (CII 3), annihilation of human passion; a stage<BR>in the Buddhist practices, anterior to parinirvāṇa or complete<BR>annihilation of personal existence by absorption into the all-<BR>pervading spirit.<BR>(HA), same as mokṣa; liberation from all bondage includ-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-219" target="_blank">Page-219+ 40</a>]<BR>ing that of this earthly body; the death of the Jinas or monks<BR>who have obtained kevala-jñāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाणचैत्य<BR>nirvāṇa-caitya (BL), name of the Buddhist memorial built<BR>at Kasia (ancient Kuśīnagara) in the Deoria District, where<BR>the Buddha obtained mahāparinirvāṇa (death).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाप|निर्वापः|निर्व्वाप|निर्व्वापः<BR>nirvāpa (EI 11), dole.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वृत्ति|निर्वृत्तिः<BR>nirvṛtti (ASLV), same as viṣaya or koṭṭam; an administrative<BR>division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्यामक|निर्यामकः<BR>Niryāmaka (LP), probably, an officer who allowed licensed<BR>articles to pass.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्यातित|निर्य्यातित<BR>niryātita (CII 2-1; ML), given.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्योगक्षेम|निर्य्योगक्षेम<BR>niryoga-kṣema (LP), ‘renouncing all claims’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशदम्<BR>niśadam, also called niśadi (SII 1), supposed to be the same<BR>as nityam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशधि<BR>niśadhi (EI 28), also spelt nisidhi, niṣidhi, niṣedhikā, etc.;<BR>the tomb of Jain monks. Cf. niśīdikā, etc. (Sanskrit niṣadyā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशदि<BR>niśadi, cf. niśadam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषद्या<BR>niṣadyā, cf. Prakrit nisidiyā (LL), a dwelling. Cf. niśliṣṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषेध|निषेधः<BR>niṣedha (LP), same as vyāṣedha (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषेधिका<BR>niṣedhikā (BL), memorial on the burial ground of Jain<BR>religious teachers; cf. nisidhi, etc.; also niśīdikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषिधि<BR>niṣidhi, niśidhi, niśīdhi (IA 12), Jain; the tomb of Jain monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषीदी<BR>niṣīdī (EI 20), a Jain tomb; cf. niṣīdhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशीदिका<BR>niśīdikā, also spelt niśīdigai (SITI), the death of a Jain<BR>by fasting; the memorial set up for such a person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निसिम<BR>nisima (ML), Prakrit; supposed to be the same as stūpa;<BR>cf. nissīma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्क|निष्कं|निष्कः<BR>niṣka (IE 8-8; EI 15, 27, 30), name of a gold coin; name<BR>sometimes applied to śatamāna, śāna, ṭaṅka, gaṇḍa-māḍa, etc.;<BR>cf. gaṇḍa-niṣka, also called gaṇḍa-māḍa. See JNSI, Vol. XVI,<BR>pp. 41 ff.<BR>(IE 8-8), a gold coin equal to sixteen silver drammas.<BR>(EI 5), a coin equal to a half-pagoda.<BR>(JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 139), a silver coin equal to one śata-<BR>māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्कावल<BR>niṣkāvala (LP), a thing on which no one has any right; cf.<BR>Sanskrit kavala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निश्लिष्टक<BR>niśliṣṭaka, Prakrit nisiḍhayā (CII 1), explained as ‘a rest-<BR>house’. But the correct reading is nisidiyā = Sanskrit niṣadyā<BR>(q. v.). See Nach. Akad. Wissen. Goetting., 1959, No. 4, pp. 47ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निश्रानिक्षेपहट्ट<BR>niśrā-nikṣepa-haṭṭa (EI 11), probably, a place in the market<BR>for storing goods to be exported.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निस्सीम<BR>nissīma (CII 2-1), explained as ‘a piece of land outside a<BR>monastery’. See nisima.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्ठापित<BR>niṣṭhāpita, ‘caused to be completed’ (Sel. Ins., p. 224).<BR>Cf. nipratiṣthāpita, niṣṭhita.<BR>(LP), finished.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्ठित|निष्ठितं<BR>niṣṭhita (Select Inscriptions, p. 203), completed. Cf. anuṣ-<BR>ṭhita, niṣṭhāpita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नित्य|नित्यं|नित्यः<BR>nitya (EI 19), compulsory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवन्द<BR>nivanda (SITI), allocated duties of servants in temples;<BR>temple expenses; same as Sanskrit nibandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीवपात<BR>nīva-pāta (LP), the falling of rain-water from the eaves;<BR>cf. Gujarātī nev or nevāṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवर्तन|निवर्त्तन<BR>nivartana (IE 8-6; EI 21, 26, 28; CII 4), an area of land,<BR>which was not the same in different ages and localities. See<BR>Ind. Ep., pp. 409-10; also Matsya Purāṇa, 283. 14-15, represent-<BR>ing a gocarman as (2/3) of a nivartana (210×210 sq. cubits).<BR>(CITD), same as maṟuturu, the identification of the two<BR>being established by bilingual Sanskrit-Telugu inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवर्तनिन्<BR>nivartanin (CII 4), name of a land measure, same as<BR>nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेदनक<BR>nivedanaka (EI 13), cf. Vāmanasvāmi-pādānāṃ nivedanaka-<BR>nimittam, ‘in order to be presented at the feet of Vāmana-<BR>svāmin.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेद्य|निवेद्यं<BR>nivedya (EI 15), same as naivedya; the food offering to a<BR>god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेश|निवेशः<BR>niveśa (EI 28), a house-site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेशन|निवेशनं<BR>niveśana (LL), a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेशित<BR>niveśita (CII 1), written [on stone].<BR>Cf. prāsādo = yaṃ niveśitaḥ (Select Inscriptions, p. 295, text<BR>line 19); erected.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीवी<BR>nīvī (EI 17), a permanent endowment; same as akṣaya-nīvī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीवीधर्म<BR>nīvī-dharma (EI 15, 17; HRS), the custom regarding per-<BR>manent endowments; the condition that the donee should not<BR>destroy the principal but should only enjoy the income arising<BR>from it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवीत|निवीतं<BR>nivīta, cf. s-oṣar-āvaṣkara-sthāna-nivīta-lavaṇākara (EI 22).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवृत्<BR>nivṛt (EI 8), a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियतभोग<BR>niyata-bhoga (EI 30), regular offerings to gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियतानियत<BR>niyat-āniyata (IE 8-5), regular and fixed taxes and those<BR>which were occasional.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियायत्तार्<BR>Niyāyattār (ASLV), Tamil; Sanskrit Nyāyastha; a judge.<BR>Cf. Nyāyattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोग|नियोगः<BR>niyoga (EI 24; SITI), an appointment; authority; the<BR>officer bearing the same. Cf. Niyogin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगनियुक्त<BR>Niyoga-niyukta (EI 23), cf. Niyogin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगस्थ<BR>Niyogastha (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 11, text line 13), ‘an<BR>officer’; same as Niyog-niyukta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगि<BR>Niyogi (ASLV), a class of Brāhmaṇas in the Telugu-<BR>speaking land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगिक<BR>Niyogika (IE 8-3; EI 8, 25, 32), same as Niyogin or<BR>Naiyogika, ‘an officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगिन्<BR>Niyogin (EI 5, 24, 30), same as Niyogika; ‘one having a<BR>niyoga’. Cf. Parameśvara-niyogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्त|नियुक्तः<BR>Niyukta (IE 8-3; EI 12, 21, 24), official designation; same<BR>as Niyuktaka, Tanniyukta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्तदण्ड<BR>niyukta-daṇḍa (IA 18), wrongly regarded as a doubtful<BR>technical expression; actually, ‘appointed as Daṇḍa (i. e. Daṇḍa-<BR>nāyaka’). Cf. nirūpita-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्तक<BR>Niyuktaka (HD), probably, a subordinate officer under<BR>the Āyuktaka; same as Niyukta. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 84.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्तकाधिकारिक<BR>Niyuktak-ādhikārika (EI 33), better Niyuktaka and Adhi-<BR>kārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नृत्यभोग<BR>nṛtya-bhoga (SITI), same as Tamil śākkai-kkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नृप|नृपः<BR>nṛpa (IE 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नूर्मडि<BR>Nūrmaḍi (IE 8-2; SII 3), Kannaḍa, ‘hundred times’; word<BR>prefixed to the names of certain kings in order to distinguish<BR>them from their predecessors bearing the same name; e. g.<BR>Nūrmaḍi Taila, ‘one who is a hundredfold Taila’; cf. Savāi<BR>Jayasiṃha, ‘one and one-fourth of Jayasiṃha’. See Immaḍi<BR>and Mummuḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्याय|न्यायः<BR>nyāya, cf. niyāyam (SII 2), an appointment or pledge.<BR>(SITI), body or association of persons having the same<BR>duties or interests.<BR>Cf. gardabha-cāṇḍāla-nyāyena (LP), ‘like a donkey or a<BR>Caṇḍāla’.<BR>Cf. khaṇḍa-badarīphala-nyāyena (LP), ‘like sugar and the<BR>badarī fruit’.<BR>Cf. śāka-phalaka-nyāyena (LP), ‘like vegetables and fruits’.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-222" target="_blank">Page-222+ 39</a>]<BR>Cf. vṛddhi-phala-bhoga-nyāya (LP), principle of enjoying the<BR>interest of a deposit; also cf. gṛhasya bhāḍakaṃ na hi; drammāṇāṃ<BR>vyājaṃ na hi; eṣa vṛddhi-phala-bhoga-nyāyaḥ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्यायकरणिक<BR>Nyāya-karaṇika (EI 12), one responsible for settling disputes<BR>regarding the gift land.<BR>(BL), official designation of the writer of complaints or<BR>the scribe of the law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्यायत्तार्<BR>Nyāyattār (SII 12; SITI), Sanskrit Nyāyastha; judges;<BR>members of the court of justice; a committee of judges. Cf.<BR>Niyāyattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्यायवाद<BR>nyāya-vāda (LP), a judgment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओडय<BR>Oḍaya (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a king, ruler, master<BR>or leader.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओदयन्त्रिक<BR>Odayantrika (CII 4), correctly Audayantrika; a manufacturer<BR>of hydraulic machines or, more probably, a person in charge<BR>of such a machine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओडिया<BR>Oḏiyā, spelt as Oriya in English; people, language and<BR>alphabet of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओघो<BR>ogho (HA), same as rajo-haraṇa; usually made of twisted<BR>woollen threads tied to a wooden handle, used by Jain monks<BR>and nuns, for removing dust particles and insects and for<BR>protecting the latter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओहोरु<BR>ohoru (IE 8-5), Oḏiyā; cf. daṇḍoāsi-ohoru, ‘tax for the<BR>maintenance of watchmen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओज|ओजः<BR>Oja (SII 11-1), same as Ojhā; designation derived from<BR>Sanskrit Upādhyāya; cf. Bengali Ojhā, Maithilī Jhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओकपिण्ड<BR>okapiṇḍa (IA 18; CII 1), explained as ‘a fox’; probably,<BR>‘household vermin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओलीपात<BR>olīpāta (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओम्<BR>om, the praṇava sometimes found at the commencement of<BR>inscriptions; often represented by a sign which should not be con-<BR>fused with the symbol standing for the auspicious word siddham.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओणी<BR>oṇī (EI 27), a territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओण्टुदारु<BR>Oṇṭudāru (EI 27), Telugu; a revenue officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओरिय<BR>Oriya, same as Oḏiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओष्ठ|ओष्ठः<BR>oṣṭha (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओत<BR>otaḏa, otaḏā, otaḏī (Chamba), dry land, unirrigable land;<BR>opposed to kohlī or āli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प|पं|पः<BR>Pa (CITD), abbreviation of the Telugu name of a certain<BR>measure of grain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पा<BR>Pā (EI 32), contraction of the surname Pāṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पा<BR>pā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of pāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पबासण<BR>pabāsaṇa (HA), the seat (āsana) on which the figure of a<BR>Jina is placed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पचन|पचनं|पचनः<BR>pacana (LL), a cooking place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद|पदं<BR>pada (EI 33), share; quarter of the standard land measure.<BR>(EI 4, 9; IA 17), a share.<BR>(EI 21), a land-measure; cf. paḍa (paṭa) in Sel. Ins.<BR>p. 408.<BR>Cf. sv-āṅgabhoga-pada (LP), ‘under the head of personal<BR>expenditure’.<BR>(LL; ML), foot-print.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाद|पादः<BR>pāda (IE 8-6), same as Kannaḍa hāda; ‘one-fourth’; a<BR>measure equal to one-fourth of the standard land measure.<BR>Cf. poā (EI 19), literally, ‘one-fourth’; name of a land<BR>measure.<BR>Cf. sa-pādika (LP), ‘with one-fourth in addition’.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248), foot-print, foot-mark.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडा<BR>paḍā, pāḍā (IE 8-4), corrupt forms of pāṭaka, ‘part of a<BR>village’; often suffixed to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादभक्त<BR>Pāda-bhakta (IE 8-2), ‘devoted to the feet of’; cf. Pād-ānu-<BR>dhyāta and Pād-ānudhyāna-rata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादचारिन्<BR>Pādacārin (CII 3), ‘moving on feet’; ‘personified’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडग<BR>paḍaga (SITI), Tamil; name of a measure of land; cf.<BR>pāḍaga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडग<BR>pāḍaga (IE 8-6), Tamil; same as Sanskrit pāṭaka; a land<BR>measure which was equal to 240 kul13is, and 6(1/4) of which made<BR>one veli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादघट<BR>pāda-ghaṭa (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडैक्काण्वर्<BR>Paḍaikkāṇvar (ASLV), a military class.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडैपर्रु<BR>paḍaipaṟṟu (ASLV), a military station or cantonment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदका<BR>padakā (Chamba), same as paduka; foot-print.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदकार|पदकारः<BR>padakāra (IE 8-8), probably, a shoe-maker or a hawker<BR>(Hindī pāukār).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदक्क<BR>padakka (ASLV), Tamil; a chest ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादकुल<BR>pāda-kula (EI 12; IA 15), probably, ‘a tribe of attendants’,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-224" target="_blank">Page-224+ 40</a>]<BR>Pāda being the same as Pāḍamūla or Pādamūlika, ‘an attendant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदलेख्यक<BR>pada-lekhyaka (LP), the ledger in which items of income<BR>are written.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडलिकै<BR>paḍalikai (SITI), Sanskrit paṭalikā; name of a measure of<BR>quantity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादमूल|पादमूलं<BR>Pādamūla (EI 12), an attendant.<BR>(EI 25), foot-prints.<BR>(EI 21), a sanctuary (p. 156; Sel. Ins., 2nd ed., p. 512).<BR>(SII 13), cf. pādamūlattār, temple servants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादमूलिक<BR>Pādamūlika (EI 4; LL), a servant.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 156), a temple attendant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादानुध्यानरत<BR>Pād-ānudhyāna-rata (IE 8-2), ‘engaged in meditating on<BR>the feet of … ’; cf. Pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादानुध्यात<BR>Pād-ānudhyāta (IE 8-2; EI 2; CII 3), ‘meditating on the<BR>feet or favoured by the feet of … ’, a technical expression for<BR>the relations of a feudatory to his paramount sovereign, of a<BR>subordinate to a chief, of a successor to his predecessor, of a son<BR>to his parents, of a nephew to his uncle, of a grandson to his<BR>grandfather, and of a younger to his elder brother; used also in<BR>respect of gods. In rare cases, the word pāda is omitted. Cf<BR>Pāda-bhakta and Pād-ānudhyāna-rata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपद्मोपजीविन्<BR>Pāda-padm-opajīvin (CII 3; IA 18), ‘subsisting [like a bee]<BR>on the lotuses that are the feet of … ’; a technical expression<BR>(often occurring in medieval South Indian inscriptions) for the<BR>relations of a feudatory or officer to his master; cf. Pāda-piṇḍ-<BR>opajīvin, Pād-opajīvin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपाश|पादपाशः<BR>pāda-pāśa (SITI), name of a foot-ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपिण्डोपजीविन्<BR>Pāda-piṇḍ-opajīvin (CII 3, etc.), ‘subsisting on the food<BR>supplied by the feet of … ’; a technical expression to denote<BR>the relationship of officials or subordinates to their master;<BR>same as Pād-opajīvin and Pāda-padm-opajīvin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपीठ|पादपीठं|पादपीठः<BR>pāda-pīṭha (SII 2), a foot-stool.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपुष्प<BR>pāda-puṣpa (SITI), same as Sanskrit-Tamil pāda-kāṇaikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादरक्षा<BR>pāda-rakṣā, cf. Tamil pāda-raṭcai (SITI), shoes; sandals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादशैव<BR>Pādaśaiva (IA 12), designation of a conch-blower at the<BR>Rāmeśvaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादसङ्घाट<BR>pāda-saṅghāṭa, a pair of feet (i. e. foot-prints). Cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदातिजीव्य<BR>padāti-jīvya (IE 8-5; EI 12, 29), also spelt padāti-jīva; tax<BR>for the maintenance of Pāiks; same as Oḏiyā pāikāli; cf. khaṇḍa-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-225" target="_blank">Page-225+ 40</a>]<BR>pāla or khaṇḍapālīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदातिक|पदातिकः<BR>Padātika (IE 8-3), modern Pāik (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादवक्काणि<BR>pādava-kkāṇi (SITI), Tamil; land given as wage for temple<BR>service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदवार<BR>padavāra (SITI), also called paduvāra; fee payable for<BR>exchanging landed property; transfer fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादावर्त|पादावर्तः|पादावर्त्त|पादावर्त्तः<BR>pādāvarta (IE 8-6; EI 4, 21, 24; CII 3), a land measure,<BR>an area of 100 pādāvartas being 100 feet each way, i. e. 10,000<BR>square feet; also spelt padāvarta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदवी<BR>padavī (EI 24), ‘an office’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादविंशोपक<BR>pāda-viṃśopaka (viṃśaka), see pāvīsā, paisā, viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडि<BR>paḍi (EI 21), a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडिहार<BR>Paḍihāra (BL), same as Sanskrit Pratīhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादिक<BR>pādika, cf. Telugu-Kannaḍa pātika (CITD); one-fourth of<BR>anything; (1/64)th part of the coin termed pagoda (q.v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडिकावल्<BR>pāḍikāval (ASLV), the right of policing, which was some-<BR>times leased to people.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडिरा<BR>Paḏirā, cf. Oḏiyā Sāmanta-paḏirā (EI 32); Sanskrit Prati-<BR>rāja; title of a fendatory or governor; cf. Pratirājya = Pratirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादिशाह्<BR>Pādiśāh (IA 20), Persian; spelt Pādisāha, Pātisāha, etc.,<BR>in Indian records; a [Muhammadan] emperor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडियारि<BR>Paḍiyāri (EI 27), Sanskrit Pratīhārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मबन्ध|पद्मबंध|पद्मबन्धः<BR>padma-bandha (CITD), a kind of artificial composition of<BR>verses, in which the syllables are arranged in the form of a lotus.<BR>Cf. padma-vṛtta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मनिधि|पद्मनिधिः<BR>padma-nidhi (IE 8-8), a sacred deposit made in the temple<BR>treasury. Cf. the coin called padmanidhi-malla-māḍa which was<BR>probably issued by the temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मपीठ<BR>padma-pīṭha (SII 2), a lotus-pedestal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मासन|पद्मासनं|पद्मासनः<BR>padm-āsana (IA 18), used to indicate ‘the sun’; cf. padma-<BR>sadman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मसद्मन्<BR>padma-sadman (IA 18), used to indicate ‘the sun’; cf. padm-<BR>āsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मवृत्त<BR>padma-vṛtta (CITD), probably, the same as padma-bandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादोनलक्ष<BR>Pādonalakṣa (IE 8-4), name of a territory with reference<BR>to the number of villages in it; cf. Sapādalakṣa, Caurāśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादोपजीविन्<BR>Pād-opajīvin (IA 18), same as Pāda-padm-opajīvin and<BR>Pāda-piṇḍ-opajīvin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्र|पद्रः<BR>padra (IE 8-4; EI 24; CII 4), ‘a village’; often suffixed<BR>to the names of villages; see padraka. Cf. pādrīyaka (LP), those<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-226" target="_blank">Page-226+ 40</a>]<BR>living in the confines of a village.<BR>(IE 8-5), probably, ‘inhabited area’; may also be ‘com-<BR>mon land’ (cf. padraka); cf. sa-padr-āraṇyaka as an epithet of<BR>a gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्रक<BR>padraka (IE 8-4; CII 3; etc.); ‘a village’; generally used<BR>as the termination of the name of a village; interpreted as ‘com-<BR>mon-land’ in expressions like Bhumbhusa-padraka and Śivaka-<BR>padraka. Wilson's Glossary explains pādar (i. e. padra) as<BR>‘common-land, land adjacent to a village left uncultivated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुक<BR>paduka (Chamba, etc.), sacred foot-prints; from Sanskrit<BR>pādukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुक|पादुकः<BR>pāduka (EI 22; LL; HA), foot-prints. See pādukā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुका<BR>pādukā (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 11), foot-prints.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुकपट्ट<BR>pāduka-paṭṭa, pādukā-paṭṭa (LL), cf. Prakrit paduka-paṭa<BR>(EI 20), a foot-print slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुकापट्टी<BR>pādukā-paṭṭī, cf. Prakrit pājugā-paṭī (EI 24), a slab with<BR>foot-marks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुवार<BR>paduvāra (SITI), same as padavāra (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाग<BR>pāga (bhāga ?), cf. Kannaḍa hāga (EI 9), name of a coin.<BR>(IA 11), same as Kannaḍa hāga; one-fourth [of the revenue<BR>collected]; may be Sanskrit bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाघ्डी<BR>pāghḏī, cf. talār-ābhāvya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पगोद्<BR>pagod, pagoda (EI 8-8), also called ‘star pagoda’; English<BR>name of the gold coin called hūn (hon) or varāha; probably so<BR>called because the coins often bore the representation of a<BR>temple called pagod or pagoda by the early European travellers.<BR>The word seems to have been derived from Sanskrit bhagavat or<BR>bhagavatī meaning the deities worshipped in the temples and<BR>also often figuring on the coins. Cf. ‘ṭaṅkakas stamped with the<BR>figure of the Bhagavat’ (Bhandarkar's List, No. 2033).<BR>Cf. Cīna-pagoda (SII 12), ‘the Chinese temple’; name of<BR>a Buddhist shrine at Nāgapaṭṭanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाहुड<BR>pāhuḍa, Sanskrit prābhṛta; cf. pāhuḍa-pramāṇena (LP), ‘in<BR>proportion to the gift given by him’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइक्<BR>Pāik (IE 7-3; EI 33), Sanskrit Padātika; same as Bhaṭa or<BR>Bhaṭa-manuṣya; a footman; cf. Piāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइका<BR>pāikā (IE 8-5; EI 29), Oḏiyā; also called pāikāli; same as<BR>padāti-jīvya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइकालि<BR>pāikāli, see pāikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैकमु<BR>paikamu (EI 6), Telugu; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइला<BR>pāilā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 42), a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैण्डपातिक<BR>Paiṇḍapātika (LL), a Buddhist mendicant; cf. piṇḍapāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैसा<BR>paisā, used in Hindi, Bengali, etc., for pāvīsā or pāda-viṃśaka-<BR>(vimśopaka); ‘a copper coin’; ‘money’; also a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैटकिन्<BR>Paiṭakin (LL), Buddhist; a teacher of the piṭakas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाकदण्ड<BR>pāka-daṇḍa (EI 14), cf. Kannaḍa kiṟu-kula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाखी<BR>pākhī (IE 8-6), Bengali; a land measure in parts of<BR>Bengal, which is smaller than the bīghā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पखिल<BR>pakhila (IA 17), apparently a mistake for upakhila (q. v.);<BR>cf. sa-khilaṃ pakhilam wrongly read or written for sa-khil-opakhilam;<BR>semi-waste land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पक्ष|पक्षः<BR>pakṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; sometimes also ‘fifteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पक्षपात|पक्षपातः<BR>pakṣa-pāta, ‘one who works on behalf of someone else’ (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 250).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पक्व|पक्वं<BR>pakva, cf. pakva-pura, ‘a brick-built house’, same as Bengali<BR>pākā-bāḏi. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 184.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल|पलं|पलः<BR>pala (EI 9, 21, 30; CII 3), name of a weight.<BR>(IA 26), a weight equal to 320 ratīs; sometimes spelt phala<BR>in Pāli.<BR>(CITD), in Telugu-Kannaḍa records, a weight equal to<BR>that of 10 pagodas; four karṣas or (1/100) of a tula; the 8th part of<BR>a ser, or 3 tolas or rupees; 4 tolas or 320 guñjās.<BR>(CII 3), the sixtieth division of a ghaṭī; equal to twenty-<BR>four English seconds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाला<BR>pālā (LP), sheds.<BR>(LP), a foot-soldier; cf. Gujarātī pāḻo.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालक|पालकः<BR>pālaka (EI 3), cf. grāmasya pālakaḥ, ‘the headman of a<BR>village’.<BR>(Select Inscriptions, p. 236), escort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलकाय<BR>pala-kāya (SITI), sundry spices as pepper, etc., used<BR>in preparing curry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलम्पुल्लिमाडै<BR>paḻampuḻḻi-māḍai (SITI), Tamil; name of an ancient<BR>coin; see māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलनियायम्<BR>Palaniyāyam (EI 21), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालापन<BR>pālāpana (LP), cf. Gujarātī paḻāvavuṃ, ‘to compel to obey’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलार्ध<BR>palārdha, weight equal to half of a pala (JNSI, Vol. XVI,<BR>p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालि|पालिः<BR>Pāli, name of a language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाली<BR>pālī (EI 3), embankment.<BR>(CII 3), a bridge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिध्वज<BR>pāli-dhvaja (EI 30, 32; CII 4), name of the banner of cer-<BR>tain kings or dynasties, which was their royal insignia; same<BR>as pāli-ketana; sometimes explained as ‘flags in rows’ (SII 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलिका<BR>palikā, pālikā (EI 1, 11), same as pālī; a measure of capa-<BR>city; measure of capacity for liquids (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p.<BR>309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिकेतन<BR>pāli-ketana (EI 29; IA 7), name of the banner of certain<BR>kings or dynasties, which was their royal insignia; also called<BR>pāli-dhvaja, explained as ‘flags in rows’ (SII 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिया<BR>pāliyā (CII 4), Gujarātī; a memorial stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लडिका<BR>pallaḍikā (IA 11, 18), cf. gṛhāṇāṃ pallaḍikā-sametā, an<BR>epithet of the gift land; probably, a cluster; sometimes referred<BR>to as property belonging to a deity (Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, pp. 180<BR>ff., Inscriptions Nos. 5-11). Cf. ‘the entire pallaḍikā belonging<BR>to the god Vakuleśvaradeva and consisting of houses facing<BR>different directions’ and ‘another [pallaḍikā] which lay close<BR>to a two-storied temple’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 144-45).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लव|पल्लवं|पल्लवः<BR>pallava (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्ली<BR>pallī (IE 8-4; EI 23), ‘a hamlet’; ‘a village or its part’;<BR>often suffixed to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लि|पल्लिः<BR>paḻḻi (SII 1, 2; SITI), Tamil; often, a Jain temple; the<BR>shrine of non-Hindu communities like the Jains, Buddhists,<BR>Christians, Muhammadans, etc.; cf. paḻḻi-ccandam, temple land;<BR>paḻḻi-grāma, a village belonging to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लीच्छन्द<BR>pallī-cchanda, cf. paḻḻi-ccanda (EI 23, 24), ‘temple land’;<BR>‘land granted to a Jain or Buddhist temple’; mentioned along<BR>with devadāna and brahmadeya; see paḻḻi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लिदेव<BR>palli-deva (EI 29), a village deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लिका<BR>pallikā (EI 4), a village.<BR>(EI 31), a habitation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलोल<BR>palola (IA 22), marshes or swamps.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पं|प|पः<BR>Paṃ (IE 8-1; PJS), abbreviation of Paṇḍita.<BR>(PJS), abbreviation of Paṃnyāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण|पणः<BR>paṇa (IE 8-8; EI 23, 24, 30; SII 11-1), same as Tamil<BR>paṇam, spelt in English as fanam; cf. Yādavarāyan-paṇam (SITI),<BR>name of a coin issued by the Yādavarāyas; name of a coin<BR>80 ratis in weight; same as the copper kārsāpaṇa; equal to 80<BR>cowrie-shells according to the Līlāvatī; copper coin (1/16) of a<BR>silver kārṣāpaṇa according to the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-<BR>kāṇḍa, ed. K.V. Rangaswami Aiyangar, p. 125), and (1/48) of a<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-229" target="_blank">Page-229+ 40</a>]<BR>suvarṇa (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 7); also used to indicate ‘money’.<BR>In Tamil, paṇam means a particular coin (usually, a small gold<BR>coin), or money in general, or taxes; cf. paṇa-vargam (SITI), a<BR>class of taxes payable in cash, same as kāśāya-vargam; also paṇa-<BR>vāśi, ‘discount payable for the exchange of coins; amount pay-<BR>able to make up the wear in the coin’. Cf. vil-paṇam (SITI),<BR>sale-tax; also understood as a tax on bows or archery; vāśal-<BR>paṇam (SITI), door-tax or periodical payment due to the<BR>palace.<BR>(ASLV), a sect or caste, eighteen in number theoretically.<BR>(EI 19), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणक<BR>pāṇaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309), small quantity of<BR>a liquid; name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणपुराण<BR>paṇa-purāṇa (IE 8-8), a purāṇa [of silver] counted in paṇas<BR>[of copper]. Cf. kapardaka-purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणव|पणवः<BR>paṇava (EI 24), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणविक<BR>Pāṇavika, one who plays on the paṇava (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXIII, p. 241).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्च|पंच<BR>pañca (EI 22, 23), abbreviation of pañcakula; same as<BR>Mahājana; a Pañcāyat Board.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाचार्य<BR>Pañc-ācārya (SITI), a temple priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चधार<BR>pañcadhāra (CITD), the five paces of a horse called dhorita,<BR>valgita, pluta, uttejita and utterita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाधिकरणोपरिक<BR>Pañc-ādhikaraṇ-oparika (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 29; BL), official<BR>designation; cf. Pañca-karaṇ-oparika and Pañca-karaṇ-ādhikṛta;<BR>the head of five departments; sometimes also called Mahārāja,<BR>Mahāsāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra, Mahāpīlupati, Pāṭy-uparika and<BR>Purapāl-oparika, additionally. See Sapt-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चद्रव्य<BR>pañca-dravya (SITI), five articles used in bathing an idol.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चगव्य|पंचगव्य|पञ्चगव्यं<BR>pañca-gavya (SITI), same as Tamil ān-āñju; the five pro-<BR>ducts of the cow, viz., milk, butter, curds, urine and dung.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाञ्चाहण<BR>Pāñcāhaṇa, Pāñcāhaṇaṃvāru (ASLV), same as Pāñcāḻa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाञ्चक<BR>pāñcaka (CII 3), a committee. See pañca-maṇḍalī and<BR>pañcakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चक|पंचक|पञ्चकं<BR>pañcaka (CII 4), same as Pañcāyat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकल्पिन्<BR>Pañcakalpin (EI 9), same as Pañcolī; title and family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकरणाधिकृत<BR>Pañcakaraṇ-ādhikṛta (EI 30), head of five departments; cf.<BR>Pañcakaraṇ-oparika, etc. See Saptā-mātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकरणोपरिक<BR>Pañcakaraṇ-oparika (EI 29), same as Pañcādhikaraṇ-oparika,<BR>etc.; head of five departments. See Sapt-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकर्मार<BR>pañca-karmāra, also called pañca-kammāḻar (SITI), the five<BR>castes of artisans, viz., goldsmith, blacksmith, brassmith, car-<BR>penter and stone-mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकशालाप्रत्या<BR>pañcaka-śālā-pratyā (LP), ‘at five per cent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकुल<BR>pañcakula (IE 8-3; EI 5, 25; CII 4; LP; HRS), the Pañ-<BR>cāyat Board; an assembly of administrators and arbitrators,<BR>usually consisting of five members; a board of administration<BR>charged with control of the customs house, with the deposit of<BR>property of persons dying without heirs into the royal treasury,<BR>etc.; also called pañcapa (EI 4); members of such a board; ac-<BR>cording to some, an officer over a certain number of villages<BR>(HD). Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 242. Cf. Pañcavīra, Pāñca-<BR>kulika, añjaṣṭa-sabhā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाञ्चकुलिक<BR>Pāñcakulika (CII 4), the head or a member of a pañcakula<BR>or Pañcāyat board; cf. Caturjātakīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाल|पंचाल|पञ्चालः<BR>Pañcāla (EI 3; ASLV), an artisan; members of the artisan<BR>classes also called Pāñcāḻaṃvāru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चलगुडिक<BR>Pañca-laguḍika (BL), title of a warrior who could pro-<BR>bably fight with five clubs at a time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चलाङ्गल<BR>pañcalāṅgala (IA 18), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चालत्तार्<BR>Pañcāḻattār (ASLV), an organisation of the artisans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाली<BR>Pañcālī (IA 10), same as Pañcālikā; a Pañcāyat board or<BR>its members.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाली<BR>pañcālī (EI 27; IA 16), territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चालिका<BR>Pañcālikā (IA 9), same as Pañcālī; a Pañcāyat board or its<BR>members.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहापातक|पंचमहापातक<BR>pañca-mahāpātaka (EI 26; CII 3; CITD), the five great<BR>sins or heinous crimes, viz., killing a Brāhmaṇa, drinking intoxi-<BR>cating liquors, stealing gold, committing adultery with the<BR>wife of a guru and associating with any one guilty of these<BR>crimes. Cf. daś-āparādha, pañc-ānantarya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहाशब्द<BR>pañca-mahāśabda (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4; SITI; CITD;<BR>BL), refers to the privilege of enjoying the sounds of five<BR>musical instruments, or five titles beginning with mahat; five<BR>official designations or musical instruments mentioned in con-<BR>nection with feudatories; five official designations beginning<BR>with the word mahā in the North and five kinds of musical<BR>instruments in the South; in South India, it was the same as<BR>pañca-mahānināda, i. e. the sounds of the five great musical ins-<BR>truments called the pañca-mahāvādya enumerated by some as a<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-231" target="_blank">Page-231+ 40</a>]<BR>horn, a tabor, a conch-shell, a kettle-drum and a gong; in<BR>some parts of North India, the expression indicated five<BR>official designations with the prefix mahā.<BR>(CII 3), sounds of five musical instruments, the use of<BR>which was allowed to persons of high rank and authority;<BR>usually a title of feudatories; cf. tat-pradatta-pañcamahāśabda (IE<BR>8-2), used in respect of feudatory rulers who received the right<BR>of enjoying the pañca-mahāśabda from their overlords; rarely<BR>used in the South by independent monarchs. Cf. pañca-vādya (EI<BR>4) and pañca-mahāvādya. See Samadhigata-pañcamahāśabda, etc.<BR>Cf. pañca-māśattam (SITI), the five musical instruments,<BR>to the use of which a nobleman was entitled; sometimes enu-<BR>merated as ceṇḍai, timilai, śegaṇḍi, cymbals and kāhaḻam or as<BR>tattaḻi, maddaḻi, karaḻikai, cymbals and kāhaḻam.<BR>(SII 11-1), cf. grant of 40 mattars of land to a piper for<BR>arranging to play the five musical instruments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहावाद्य<BR>pañca-mahāvādya (EI 12), enumerated as the horn, conch-<BR>shell, tambourine, trumpet and gong. See pañca-mahāśabda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहायज्ञ|पंचमहायज्ञ<BR>pañca-mahāyajña (EI 29; CII 3, 4), ‘the five great sacri-<BR>fices’; the five daily duties of a Brāhmaṇa enumerated as bali,<BR>caru, vaiśvadeva, agnihotra and atithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमलोकपाल<BR>Pañcama-lokapāla (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 93), epithet<BR>of certain kings; cf. Lokapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमण्डली<BR>pañca-maṇḍalī (CII 3, 4; HD), an assembly of five persons;<BR>equivalent to the modern Pañcāit, Pañcāyat or Pañc, i. e., a village<BR>jury. See pāñcaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमातृका<BR>pañca-mātṛkā, cf. Prakrit paṃca-mātuka (EI 20), five princi-<BR>pal texts of the Buddhists, also called pañca-nikāya, viz., the<BR>Dīgha-nikāya, Majjhima-nikāya, Aṅguttara-nikāya, Khuddaka-nikāya<BR>and Saṃyutta-nikāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमौष्टिकलोच<BR>pañca-mauṣṭika-loca (HA), plucking out five handfuls of<BR>hair by a would-be Jina at the time of dīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमीबलि<BR>pañcamī-bali (EI 11), a particular tithi of the year.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चामृत|पंचामृत|पञ्चामृतं<BR>pañc-āmṛta (SITI), mixture of five objects for anointing<BR>idols, viz. banana, honey, sugar, ghee and grape.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमुखनगर<BR>pañca-mukha-nagara (LP), explained as ‘a city in which<BR>there are five leading men’; cf. pañca-mukha-nagara-viditam (LP),<BR>‘having informed the five leading men of the city’; explained<BR>as ‘the five-fold people of the town’ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XLI, p. 20);<BR>really ‘the citizens headed by the members of the Pañcāyat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चनगर<BR>pañca-nagara, a mercantile guild (cf. nagara, also pañca);<BR>see A.R. Ep., 1956-57, No. B 190.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चनैकायिक<BR>Pañcanaikāyika (LL), Buddhist; a teacher of the five nikāyas<BR>(e. g. Dīgha-nikāya, Majjhima-nikāya, Khuddaka-nikāya, Saṃyutta-<BR>nikaya and Aṅguttara-nikāya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चानन्तर्य<BR>pañc-ānantarya (CII 3), the five sins that entail immediate<BR>retribution. See pañca-mahāpātaka, daś-āparādha, pañc-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाङ्ग|पंचांग|पञ्चाङ्गं|पञ्चाङ्गः<BR>pañcāṅga (CII 3), the Hindu almanac; in the Deccan<BR>and in some other parts, the pañcāṅgas are now prepared from<BR>the Grahalāghava and the Tithicintāmaṇi of Gaṇeśa-daivajña. The<BR>right of reading the pañcāṅga was sometimes granted by the<BR>rulers to individuals (ASLV).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाङ्गनमस्कार<BR>pañcāṅga-namaskāra (HA), bowing down in such a way<BR>that five limbs of the body (viz., two hands, two knees and the<BR>head) touch the ground. Cf. aṣṭ-āṅga-namaskāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाङ्गप्रसाद<BR>pañcāṅga-prasāda, cf. pañcāṅga-pasāya (Ind. Ant., Vol. IX,<BR>p. 95), translated as ‘five manners of gifts’; cf. pañcāṅga-pasāya<BR>chatra sukhāsana bbala gaddi aṅka-daṇḍa-khaṇḍane, translated as<BR>‘gave [to that Māro-śĕṭṭi] five manners of gifts--an umbrella,<BR>a palanquin, an escort, a throne and with the faults, fines and<BR>divisions (really ‘with fines and the grain share’).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चप<BR>pañcapa (EI 4), same as pañcakula (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चापराध<BR>pañc-āparādha (HRS), known from the Gupta and other<BR>records; donee's privilege relating to the enjoyment of fines<BR>payable by persons committing five offences. Cf. daś-āparādha,<BR>pañc-ānantarya, pañca-mahāpātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चपरमेष्ठिपद<BR>pañcaparameṣṭhi-pada (EI 2), also called °paṭṭa; a slab for<BR>worship containing the oṅkāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चपाठिन्<BR>Pañcapāṭhin (EI 32), epithet or family name of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चपात्र|पंचपात्र|पञ्चपात्रं<BR>pañca-pātra (SITI), literally, ‘a vessel made of five<BR>[metals]’; offerings of food made to a deity along with cooked<BR>rice; probably the same as pañca-bhakṣya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चार्थ<BR>Pañcārtha (CII 4), the Pāśupata sect of the Śaivas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चार्थिक<BR>Pañcārthika, Pāñcārthika (CII 4; IA 18), same as Pañcārtha,<BR>the Pāśupata sect of the Śaivas; a follower of the Pāśupata sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चरत्न|पंचरत्न|पञ्चरत्नं<BR>pañca-ratna (EI 19), a group of five stanzas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चशब्द<BR>pañca-śabda (CII 4; BL), five [musical] sounds or five<BR>official designations [beginning with the word mahā]; same as<BR>pañca-mahāśabda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाशत्|पंचाशत्<BR>pañcāśat, see pannasa, pannāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाष्टकुल<BR>pañc-āṣṭa-kula, see añjaṣṭa-sabhai (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चस्तूपनिकायिक<BR>Pañcastūpanikāyika (BL), epithet of a Jain religious teacher.<BR>See Pañcanaikāyika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवाद्य<BR>pañca-vādya (EI 4), cf. pañca-mahāśabda, pañca-mahāvādya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवार<BR>pañca-vāra (EI 23), a tax; cf. pañcavāri, pañcupīli, etc.;<BR>also pañca-vāram (SITI), one-fifth of the produce due to the<BR>government as land-revenue.<BR>(SITI), five branches in the administration of big villages,<BR>each looked after by a committee called pañcavāra-vāriyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चविंशति|पंचविंशति|पञ्चविंशतिः<BR>pañcaviṃśati, see pannavīsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवीर<BR>pañca-vīra (EI 24), also called pañcavīra-goṣṭhī; an adminis-<BR>trative board of five members; cf. pañcakula. Also 5 deified<BR>heroes of the Vṛṣṇi clan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चायत्<BR>pañcāyat (EI 26), a board of administration usually con-<BR>sisting of five members; cf. pañcakula, pañcavīra, pañcāyati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चायति<BR>pañcāyati (IE 8-3), an administrative board consisting of<BR>five members; same as pañcāyat, pañcakula, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चायतन<BR>pañc-āyatana (EI 28; CII 4), a type of temple ‘consisting<BR>of five rooms’; a five-shrine temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चिक<BR>Pañcika (EI 1), a member of the pañcakula or Pañcāyat<BR>board.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चीयकद्रम्म<BR>pañcīyaka-dramma (EI 1; CII 4), name of a coin. It is<BR>uncertain whether it was so called owing to its issue by some<BR>Pañcāyat board or because it was equal to five copper coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चोली<BR>pañcolī (HD), same as pañcakula. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXIV, p. 89.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चुपीलि<BR>pañcupīli (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डा<BR>Pāṇḍā (EI 32), a temple superintendent; same as Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्डारवाडै<BR>paṇḍāravāḍai (ASLV), crown lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डव|पांडव|पांडवः|पाण्डवः<BR>pāṇḍava (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्डित|पंडित|पण्डितः<BR>Paṇḍita (HD), same as Dharmatattvavit according to<BR>Śukra, II. 85; head of the ecclesiastical department (Hist.<BR>Dharm., Vol. III, p. 115).<BR>(CII 4), epithet of Brāhmaṇas.<BR>(IE 8-3), the court Pandit, mentioned as Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डुलेख|पांडुलेख|पाण्डुलेखः<BR>pāṇḍu-lekha, pāṇḍu-lekhya (IE 3-5), chalk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डुसुत<BR>pāṇḍu-suta, cf. pāṇḍava (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्ग<BR>paṅga, pāṅga (IE 8-5; EI 30, 33), Telugu-Kannaḍa; one-<BR>fourth of the produce sometimes collected from rent-free hold-<BR>ings in the possession of gods and Brāhmaṇas; a kind of tax;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-234" target="_blank">Page-234+ 40</a>]<BR>sometimes used to indicate ‘taxes in general’; cf. paṅga-śulka,<BR>paṅga-tappu, paṅga-tappu-śulka, paṅga-parihṛta, paṅga-parihṛta-<BR>parihāra, sarva-paṅga-parihṛta, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII,<BR>pp. 54 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्गतप्पु<BR>paṅga-tappu (IE 8-5), probably, interest or fine on arrears<BR>of paṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्गोत्कोट<BR>paṅg-otkoṭa (EI 33), see paṅga and utkoṭa, names of levies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्गु|पंगु|पङ्गुः<BR>paṅgu (EI 33), a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणि|पाणिः<BR>pāṇi, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणिग्राहिन्<BR>Pāṇigrāhin (EI 26), Oḏiyā; Sanskrit Pānīya-grāhin, ‘one<BR>who receives water’; the principal donee who received the water<BR>on behalf of all the other donees of a gift village; stereotyped as<BR>a family name in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयभाजन<BR>pānīya-bhājana (LL), a water-cistern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयछायामण्डप<BR>pānīya-chāyā-maṇḍapa (EI 28), probably, a shaded hall<BR>cooled by water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयागारिक<BR>Pānīyāgārika (IE 8-3), superintendent of the water-chamber.<BR>See Pānīyagṛhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयग्राहिन्<BR>Pānīya-grāhin (EI 31), ‘one who receives ceremonial water<BR>as the donee of a gift’; recipient of a grant. See Pāṇigrāhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयगृहिक<BR>Pānīyagṛhika (LL), superintendent of a water-house.<BR>Cf. Pānīyāgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयक<BR>pānīyaka (LL), a cistern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्जाबी<BR>Pañjābī, name of the language of the Pañjāb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्क|पंक|पंकं|पंकः|पङ्कः<BR>paṅka (EI 33), a share; cf. paṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्क्ति|पंक्ति|पंक्तिः|पङ्क्तिः<BR>paṅkti (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नस<BR>pannasa, also spelt pannāsa, pannāsu (IE 8-6; EI 5, 12; Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XV, p. 336, note 3), Kannaḍa; probably derived from<BR>Sanskrit pañchāśat in the sense of a tenure in which the donee<BR>enjoyed fifty per cent of the revenue of the donated land. Cf.<BR>pannavīsa. (EI 20), explained as ‘a gift’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नास<BR>pannāsa (EI 30; IA 11), Kannaḍa; same as pannasa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नासु<BR>pannāsu (IA 10), Kannaḍa; same as pannasa (q.v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नवीस<BR>pannavīsa (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, No. B. 17), Kannaḍa; Sans-<BR>krit pañcaviṃśati; probably a tenure in which the donee enjoyed<BR>twentyfive per cent of the revenue of the donated land. Cf.<BR>pannāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नाय<BR>pannāya (IE 8-5; EI 27), Kannaḍa, name of a tax; cf. pannāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नायदसुङ्कवेर्गडे<BR>Pannāyadasuṅkavĕrgaḍĕ (SII 11-2), Kannaḍa; official desig-<BR>nation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पान्थशाला<BR>pāntha-śālā (CII 4), a sarāi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्यसंस्था<BR>paṇya-saṃsthā (HRS), various dues collected for the king<BR>by the superintendent of the market and the superintendent of<BR>merchandise, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 76.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पापनाशिनी<BR>pāpanāśinī (IA 26), the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर|परं|परः<BR>Para, abbreviation of a modified form of Purohita (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर|परं|परः<BR>para (LL), possibly, the chief.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार|पारं|पारः<BR>pāra, cf. a-pār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE 8-5); probably, [free]<BR>ferrying of rivers [by the royal officers], which the villagers were<BR>obliged to provide.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परब्रह्मन्<BR>parabrahman (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परदत्ति<BR>paradatti (SII 2), Tamil; an assembly; cf. Tamil paraḍai=<BR>Sanskrit pariṣad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परदेशिन्<BR>Para-deśin (SITI; CITD), an outsider; an emigrant; used<BR>along with Sva-deśin (i. e. native), while mentioning two classes<BR>of merchants or their respective guilds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परगना<BR>paraganā (Chamba, etc.), parganā; a territorial division;<BR>subdivision of a district, same as pratijāgaraṇaka of the Paramāra<BR>charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिकाल्<BR>Parakesari-kāl (EI 30), Tamil; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिक्कल्<BR>Parakesari-kkal (EI 30), Tamil; name of a weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिना<BR>Parakesari-nāḻi (EI 30), Tamil; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिउळक्कु<BR>Parakesari-ul13akku (EI 30), Tamil; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पराख्य<BR>parākhya (CII 3), a correction in time, to be applied to<BR>the mean tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकोणा<BR>parakoṇā (EI 31), probably, the same as parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पराक्रम्<BR>parākram (CII 1), ‘to make an effort’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पराक्रम|पराक्रमः<BR>parākrama (CII 1), an effort; zealous activity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभागवत<BR>Parama-bhāgavata (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3), ‘highly de-<BR>voted to the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu)’, epithet of the followers of the<BR>Bhāgavata form of Vaiṣṇavism; cf. Paramavaiṣṇava (highly<BR>devoted to Viṣṇu), etc. See Atyanta-bhagavad-bhaktā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभगवतीभक्त<BR>Parama-bhagavatī-bhakta (IE 8-2), ‘a devout worshipper<BR>of the goddess Bhagavatī (Śiva's consort)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभट्टारक<BR>Paramabhaṭṭāraka (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4), one of the<BR>technical titles of paramount sovereignty, closely connected<BR>with Mahārājādhirāja and Parameśvara; sometimes applied to a<BR>priest (generally of the Śaiva order); cf. Paramabhaṭṭārak-ety-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-236" target="_blank">Page-236+ 40</a>]<BR>ādi-rājāvalī (IA 19); also Paramabhaṭṭārak-etyādi-rājāvalī-tray-opeta<BR>(IE 8-2), ‘endowed with the three royal titles beginning with<BR>Paramabhaṭṭāraka.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभट्टारिका<BR>Paramabhaṭṭārikā (IE 8-2; EI 6, 7; CII 3), a title of the<BR>wives of paramount sovereigns and of ruling queens.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमब्रह्मण्य<BR>Parama-brahmaṇya (IE 8-2; EI 29), probably not ‘highly<BR>devoted to the god Brahman’, but ‘highly devoted to the Brāh-<BR>maṇas’; epithet of certain Brāhmanical rulers. See Atibrahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदैवत<BR>Parama-daivata (IE 8-2; EI 28, 30; BL), ‘highly devoted<BR>to the god (i. e. Viṣṇu)’; epithet of Vaiṣṇava rulers; epithet of<BR>a devotee of the Brahmanical gods. Cf. Parama-de(dai)vat-<BR>ādhidaivata, Parama-guru-de(dai)vat-ādhidaivata-viśeṣa (EI 28),<BR>epithets of pious rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदैवताधिदैवत<BR>Parama-daivat-ādhidaivata (EI 23), same as Parama-de(dai)-<BR>vatādhidaivata (q. v.); epithet of pious kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदेवताधिदैवत<BR>Parama-de(dai)vat-ādhidaivata (IE 8-2; EI 23), ‘one who<BR>is a great devotee of the various gods and of the supreme<BR>god’; see Paramadaivata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदेवी<BR>Paramadevī (IE 8-2; CII 3), designation of the chief queen;<BR>cf. Devī, Mahādevī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदीक्षीत<BR>Paramadīkṣīta (EI 26), see Dīkṣita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमादित्यभक्त<BR>Param-āditya-bhakta (IE 8-2; CII 3), ‘a devout worshipper<BR>of the Sun-god’; cf. Parama-saura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमगुरु<BR>Parama-guru (EI 31, 33), ‘the supreme teacher [of the<BR>subjects]’; royal title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमगुरुदेवताधिदैवतविशेष<BR>Parama-guru-de(dai)vat-ādhidaivata-viśeṣa (IE 8-2), ‘one<BR>who is a great teacher to his subjects and is devoted to the<BR>various gods and of the supreme deity’; see Parama-daivata and<BR>Paramade(dai)vat-ādhidaivata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमहंस|परमहंसः<BR>Paramahaṃsa (EI 5; BL), an ascetic; epithet of an ascetic.<BR>See Haṃsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परममाहेश्वर<BR>Parama-māheśvara (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3, 4), a devout<BR>worshipper of Maheśvara (Śiva)’; epithet of Śaiva rulers; see<BR>Māheśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमनारसिंह<BR>Parama-nārasiṃha (IE 8-2; EI 26), ‘highly devoted to the<BR>man-lion incarnation of Viṣṇu’; epithet of a devotee of the man-<BR>lion form of Viṣṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमपाशुपताचार्य<BR>Parama-pāśupat-ācārya (BL), epithet of a Śaiva religious<BR>teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमराज|परमराजः<BR>Paramarāja (EI 31, 33), royal title. See Paramarājādhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमराजाधिराज<BR>Paramarājādhirāja, royal title. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 219; cf. Paramarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमसौगत<BR>Parama-saugata (IE 8-2; EI 29; CII 3; BL), ‘a devout<BR>worshipper of the Sugata (Buddha)’; cf. Parama-tāthāgata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमसौर<BR>Parama-saura (IE 8-2), ‘a devout worshipper of the Sun-<BR>god’; cf. Param-āditya-bhakta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमस्वामिन्<BR>Parama-svāmin (EI 28; SII 3), epithet of deities.<BR>(EI 3), title of an imperial ruler; an overlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमलाथागत<BR>Parama-lāthāgata (IE 8-2; EI 29; BL), ‘a devout worshipper<BR>of the Tathāgata (Buddha)’; usually spelt Parama-tathāgata;<BR>cf. Parama-saugata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमवैष्णव<BR>Parama-vaiṣṇava (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4), ‘highly devoted<BR>to Viṣṇu’; epithet of Vaiṣṇava rulers; cf. Parama-bhāgavata, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमविश्वासिन्<BR>Parama-viśvāsin (IE 8-3), probably, a private secretary;<BR>same as Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.; sometimes called Mahāpradhāna,<BR>Sarvādhikārin, etc., additionally. See Vaiśvāsika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेष्ठिगद्याण<BR>parameṣṭhi-gadyāṇa (SII, Vol. IX, Part i, No. 68), cf. gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वर|परमेश्वरः<BR>Parameśvara (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3, 4), an imperial<BR>title; one of the technical titles of paramount sovereignty closely<BR>connected with Māhārājādhirāja and Paramabhaṭṭāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरहस्त<BR>parameśvara-hasta (SII 2), the royal cubit; cubit measured<BR>according to the length of the king's forearm. Cf. śrīpāda-kol.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरमहाकोष्ठकारिन्<BR>Parameśvara-mahākoṣṭhakārin (EI 27), officer in charge of<BR>the royal treasury or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरनियोगिन्<BR>Parameśvara-niyogin (A.R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 9), a special<BR>officer attached to the king. Cf. Niyogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरेत्यादि<BR>Parameśvar-ety-ādi (IE 8-2), shortened form of Parameśvar-<BR>ety-ādi-raj-āvalī-tray-opeta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरी<BR>Parameśvarī (EI 6), title of a queen, especially a ruling queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमोपासक<BR>Param-opāsaka (BL; LL), epithet of a male member of the<BR>Buddhist laity; cf. upāsaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमोपासिका<BR>Param-opāsikā (EI 22, 32; LL; BL), epithet of a female<BR>member of the Buddhist laity; cf. upāsikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारम्पर<BR>pārampara (EI 15), same as paramparā-balīvarda-grahaṇa;<BR>refers to the obligation of the villagers to supply bullocks in suc-<BR>cession for the cart of a royal agent on tour in their villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परम्परा|परंपरा<BR>paramparā, cf. a-paramparā-balīvarda (IE 8-5); ‘succession’;<BR>refers to the obligation of the villagers to supply bullocks for<BR>the cart of the touring officers visiting different villages in suc-<BR>cession.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारशव|पारशवः<BR>Pāraśava (BL), name of a community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारसीक|पारसीकः<BR>Pārasīka (EI 12), originally, a Persian; but used to indi-<BR>cate any foreigner; a Dutch in the present case.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारसि<BR>Pārasi, Pārasī, Pārasika (EI 5; SII 1), a Persian.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारशिव<BR>Pāraśiva (SITI), probably Pāraśava; explained as ‘one<BR>who wields a weapon; a soldier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परस्वत्|परस्वन्त्<BR>parasvat (CII 1), a rhinoceros.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परत<BR>parata (Chamba), return, exchange, substitute, compen-<BR>sation; derived from Sanskrit parivarta; same as badalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारत्रिक|पारत्रिकं<BR>pāratrika (CII 1), ‘benefit in the other world’; merit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परसमय<BR>para-samaya (EI 24), explained as a particular Jain<BR>doctrine; doctrines other than one's own.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्गना<BR>parganā (EI 9, 32), a group of villages; same as pratijā-<BR>garaṇaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारि<BR>Pāri (EI 31; LP; PJS), abbreviation of Gujarāti Pārikha,<BR>Pārekha (Sanskrit Pārīkṣaka), originally meaning ‘an examiner<BR>of coins’; a surname among the Baniās of Gujarat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिभूतनामन्<BR>paribhūta-nāman (CII 3), a nickname.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिबोध|परिबोधः<BR>paribodha (CII 1), obstacle, fetters; being in fetters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिचक्र<BR>paricakra (LL), a circular panel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिचारक|परिचारकः<BR>Paricāraka (EI 31), a servant; sometimes mentioned in the<BR>list of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिच्छन्द|परिच्छंद|परिच्छंदः|परिच्छन्दः<BR>paricchanda (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 16), a vessel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिच्छेद|परिच्छेदः|परिछेद<BR>pariccheda (CII 3), a territorial term meaning a group of<BR>villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिछा<BR>Parichā (IE 8-3; EI 31), Oḏiyā; same as Sanskrit Parīkṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिदर्शना<BR>paridarśanā (IE 8-5; EI 29), a supervision tax probably<BR>related to division of property; may also be the same as Persian<BR>nazrāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिघ|परिघः<BR>parigha (HRS), ‘door-bolt’; one of the seven sources of<BR>revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिग्रह|परिग्रहः<BR>parigraha (ML), acceptance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिगृहीत<BR>parigṛhīta (IE 8-2; EI 31), ‘accepted’, sometimes used in<BR>place of anudhyāta (‘meditating’ or ‘favoured’) in passages like<BR>tatpāda-parighṛhīta; cf. bappa-bhaṭṭāraka-pāda-parigṛhīta, bhaṭṭāraka-<BR>Mahāsena-parigṛhīta, etc.; refers to selection or acceptance of a<BR>succession or appointment or receipt in one's favour.<BR>Cf. catuḥśāla-parigṛhītaṃ śaila-maṇḍapam and Samyaksam-<BR>buddhasya dhātu-parigṛhītasya (Select Inscriptions, p. 228).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिहार|परिहारः<BR>parihāra (IE 8-5; EI 6; SITI), same as maryādā-parihāra;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-239" target="_blank">Page-239+ 40</a>]<BR>exemptions from taxes and obligations granted to the donees of<BR>rent-free land; privileges of the donee of rent-free holdings; for<BR>many such privileges, see Appendix I. Cf. certain privileges<BR>in respect of a number of taxes and obligations enumerated in<BR>Tamil records as follows: vaṭṭi-nāḻi (payment of one nāḻi per<BR>vaṭṭi), pudā-nāḻi (or pidā°, cess on each door or tax for the main-<BR>tenance of sluices), maṇṟupādu (fine imposed by a court of law),<BR>ūrāṭci (tax for running the village administration), taragu (tax<BR>on brokers), kūlam (tax on grains), īl13am-puṭi (tax on toddy-<BR>drawers), nāḍu-kāval (tax for the policing of a district), ūḍupokku<BR>(meaning uncertain), uppu-kocceygai (tax for the manufacture of<BR>salt), nall-ā (tax for maintaining specimen cows), nallerudu (tax<BR>for maintaining specimen buffaloes), nerv-āypuvum (meaning un-<BR>certain) and others. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 124.<BR>(IA 17), a ring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिहारिक|पारिहारिकः<BR>pārihārika (HRS), land exempted from revenue, as sug-<BR>gested by the Arthaśāstra; privileges enjoyed by the donee<BR>of a rent-free holding.<BR>Cf. sarva-jāta-pārihārika; same as parihāra or the parihāras<BR>collectively. See Select Inscriptions, pp. 192, 194.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिहीनिक<BR>pārihīnika (HRS), damage-fee which was a branch of<BR>accidental revenue, according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 28.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिकर|परिकरः<BR>parikara (IE 8-5; CII 4), same as uparikara, occasional or<BR>minor taxes; cf. sa-parikara (EI 23) which is the same as s-opari-<BR>kara.<BR>(SITI), requisites of a village.<BR>(HA), accessory decoration round the figure of a Jina,<BR>the motifs being taken from the Jain conception of the eight<BR>chief objects attendant upon a Jina (aṣṭa-mahāprātihāryāṇi, viz.<BR>the wheel of law, the caitya-tree, the lion-seat, the aureole behind<BR>the head, two attendant flywhisk-bearers, drum-beaters and<BR>pipe-players, and garland-bearers).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिकार<BR>Parikāra (SITI), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिख्<BR>Pārikh (EI 31), Gujaratī; Sanskrit Pārīkṣa; an examiner of<BR>coins; a family name amongst the Baniās. See Rūpa-darśaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिखाय<BR>pārikh-āya (IA 19), a levy; cf. Pārikh, pārīkṣika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिक्रय|परिक्रयः<BR>parikraya (SII 1), an exchange.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिक्रेय<BR>parikreya (Sel. Ins., p. 236), remuneration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षा<BR>Parīkṣā (IE 8-3; EI 28, 31), same as Sanskrit Parīkṣaka; Sans-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-240" target="_blank">Page-240+ 40</a>]<BR>kritised from Oḏiyā Parichā; superintendent of a department<BR>or a governor; cf. Dvāra-parīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षा<BR>parīkṣā (IA 10), same as divya, an ordeal.<BR>(CII 1), self-examination.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षक|परीक्षकः<BR>Parīkṣaka (IE 8-3), see Parīkṣā = Oḏiyā Parichā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारीक्षिक<BR>pārīkṣika (HRS), testing-charge for private minting of<BR>coins, according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst.,<BR>p. 43. Cf. pārikhāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षिपट्ट<BR>parīkṣi-paṭṭa (IE I), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिमोटन<BR>parimoṭana (EI 12), cracking.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिनिर्वाण<BR>parinirvāṇa (EI 8), the death of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपन्थ्<BR>paripanth, cf. paripanthayati (IE 8-2), same as vyavaharati;<BR>cf. samasta-mudrā-vyāpārān paripanthayati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपन्थना<BR>paripanthanā, ‘creation of obstacles’; same as vidhāraṇā<BR>(EI). See vādhā or bādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपर|परिपरः<BR>paripara (EI 3), a fight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिपार्श्विक|पारिपार्श्विकः<BR>Pāripārśvika (IA 11), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपृच्छा<BR>paripṛcchā (CII 1), questioning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपूर्ण<BR>paripūrṇa (LP), probably, ‘in full youth’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिषद्<BR>pariṣad (LL), four classes of the Buddhist order.<BR>(EI 32), used in the sense of pāriṣada, ‘a councillor’.<BR>Cf. Tamil paraḍai, etc. (SII 3), an assembly.<BR>(CII 1), cf. Prakrit parisā (EI 8), a council; the council<BR>[of ministers]; cf. mantri-pariṣad, ‘council of ministers.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिसर|परिसरः<BR>parisara (EI 11), an area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिषदा<BR>pariṣadā (HD), same as sabhā; an assembly or audience.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिश्रव<BR>pariśrava (CII 1), sin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिशु<BR>pariśu (SII 1), probably, a contract.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिसूत्र<BR>parisūtra (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34),<BR>explained as ‘an establishment.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परित्याग|परित्यागः<BR>parityāga (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 10, text line 2), do-<BR>nation; cf. deyadharma-parityāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवार|परिवारः<BR>Parivāra (SII 3), a servant.<BR>Cf. horaka-parivāra (ML), explained as ‘the following of<BR>horakas.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवारालय<BR>parivār-ālaya (SII 3), surrounding verandah of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवस्त्र<BR>parivastra, cf. Tamil parivaṭṭam, pariśaṭṭam, pariyaṭṭam (SITI),<BR>literally, garment; honour done to a nobleman in a temple by<BR>tying a piece of cloth (generally, silk cloth) round his head.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवृद्ध<BR>Parivṛddha (EI 12), same as Prabhu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्णाकर<BR>parṇ-ākara, cf. sa-parṇ-ākara (IE 8-5), ‘together with the<BR>fields producing leaves (i. e. betel-leaves).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्णशशन्<BR>parṇa-śaśan (CII 1), an animal; probably, a rabbit<BR>living on leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परोक्षम्<BR>parokṣam (IA 18), ‘in the absence of’; ‘behind the back of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प|पं|पः<BR>paṟṟu (IE 8-4), Tamil; a small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्षद्<BR>parṣad (LL), a congregation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार्षद|पार्षदः<BR>pārṣada, cf. Prakrit pāṣaṃḍa (CII 1), a religious community;<BR>one belonging to a parṣad or religious group.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार्श्व|पार्श्वं|पार्श्वः<BR>pārśva (HRS), extra charge upon land over and above<BR>the king's grain-share, which was a branch of ‘accidental re-<BR>venue’ according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev.<BR>Syst., pp. 28, 38.<BR>(IE 8-4), explained by some as a small territorial unit;<BR>but may be ‘side’; cf. prāveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार्श्विक|पार्श्विकं|पार्श्विकः<BR>Pārśvika (EI 9; CII 4), an aide-de-camp; also used to in-<BR>dicate a neighbour or one having land in the neighbourhood<BR>of the gift land (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 197, text line 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्ताब्<BR>partāb (SII 1), Sanskrit pratāpa; a half pagoda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्वमासोत्सव<BR>parva-mās-otsava (EI 15), a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारुत्थ<BR>pāruttha, a silver coin equal to 8 drammas of copper or billon<BR>(JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 196).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्वन्|पर्व्वन्<BR>parvan (IA 18), used in relation to eclipses.<BR>Cf. Koṅkaṇa-vijaya-parvan (EI 33), festival celebrating the<BR>conquest of the Koṅkaṇ; an anniversary of the said conquest.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्वत|पर्वतः|पर्व्वत|पर्व्वतः<BR>parvata (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्याय|पर्यायः|पर्य्याय|पर्य्यायः<BR>paryāya (IA 18), used in relation to an allotment.<BR>(CII 1), cf. dharma-paryāya, ‘exposition of the doctrine’; a<BR>religious text.<BR>Cf. Pallānakāra (EI 23), Sanskrit Paryāyakāra, a saddler,<BR>a saddle-maker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्युषित|पर्य्युषित|पर्य्युषितं<BR>paryuṣita (HRS), ‘outstanding revenue’ which was one<BR>of the three kinds of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाश|पाशः<BR>pāśa (CII 4), fetters of worldly existence.<BR>(IA 18), a land measure.<BR>(EI 26), a girdle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसाइत<BR>Pasāita (EI 29, 33), also spelt Pasāyita; official designation;<BR>probably Sanskrit Prasādita in the sense of ‘a fief-holder’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाषाण|पाषाणः<BR>pāṣāṇa (IE 8-5; SITI), one of the eight kinds of enjoyment<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-242" target="_blank">Page-242+ 40</a>]<BR>of landed property; rocky soil and its products; mineral pro-<BR>ducts; probably, stony and hilly land referring to the right of<BR>quarrying, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशानम्<BR>paśānam (EI 23), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसापालक<BR>Pasāpālaka (EI 33), official designation; cf. Pasāyita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसायति<BR>Pasāyati (EI 33), same as Pasāyita (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसायित<BR>Pasāyita (IE 8-3; EI 33), probably Sanskrit Prasādita used<BR>to indicate a Jāgīrdār. See Pasāita pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाश्चात्यलिखित<BR>pāścātya-likhita (LP), written on the back of the bond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशु|पशुः<BR>paśu (EI 8), animal sacrifice.<BR>Cf. a-paśu-medhya (IE 8-5), ‘free from the obligation of<BR>supplying animals for sacrifices.’<BR>(CII 4), the individual soul.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशुपाल|पशुपालः<BR>Paśupāla (IA 22), nomads.<BR>(EI 1), also called Paśupālaka; a person in charge of cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपत|पाशुपतः<BR>pāśupata (SII 2), same as pāśupat-āstra; name of a<BR>weapon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपत|पाशुपतः<BR>Pāśupata (EI 32), name of a Śaiva sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपताचार्य<BR>Pāśupat-ācārya (BL), epithet of a Śaiva religion teachers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपतराज्ञी<BR>Pāśupata-rājñī (BL), epithet of a Śaiva queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट|पटं|पटः<BR>paṭa, paṭā, pāṭa (EI 28; Chamba), charter, deed; same<BR>as Sanskrit paṭṭa or paṭṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट|पाटः<BR>pāṭa, cf. daṇḍapāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातक|पातकं|पातकः<BR>pātaka (IE 8-1-2), ‘five’. Cf. pañca-mahāpātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटक|पाटकः<BR>pāṭaka (IE 8-4; EI 4, 24; IA 18), ‘part of a village’, a<BR>quarter; the outlying part of a village; a hamlet; often prefixed<BR>to the name of localities; often modified to vāṭaka.<BR>(EI 15, 17, 28), a land measure.<BR>(IE 8-6), a land measure equal to forty droṇavāpas or to<BR>five kulyavāpas; part of a village.<BR>(EI 23, 24), a territorial division.<BR>(SITI), portion of a field.<BR>(SITI), anklet worn by women.<BR>(LP), same as Gujarātī pāḍo, a street or the division of a<BR>town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटकार|पटकारः<BR>Paṭakāra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 186), a weaver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटकार<BR>Pāṭakāra (EI 28), a splitter of wood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटकील<BR>Paṭakīla (EI 23), village headman; same as Paṭṭakila,<BR>modern Paṭel or Pāṭīl; cf. Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाताल|पातालं|पातालः<BR>pātāla (IE 7-1-2), sometimes used to indicate ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातलकरणिन्<BR>Pātala-karaṇin (IA 12), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटलिका<BR>paṭalikā, cf. Tamil paḍaligai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतङ्ग|पतंग|पतङ्गं|पतंगः|पतङ्गः<BR>pataṅga (IA 11), a paper kite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातनीय<BR>pātanīya (LP), ‘should be left aside’, i. e. ‘should not be<BR>taken into account’.<BR>(LP), to be kept uncultivated; see kheḍanīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातसाह<BR>Pātasāha (EI 11, 30; BL), Muslim imperial title; same<BR>as Persian Pādshāh. Cf. Pātasāhi, Pātisāha, Pātusāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातसाहि<BR>Pātasāhi (BI), Indian modification of an imperial title of<BR>the Muhammadans; same as Persian Pādshāh; cf. Pātasāha,<BR>Pātisāhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातयिष्यामि<BR>pātayiṣyāmi (LP), ‘I shall deduct and thus take less.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटेल्<BR>Paṭel, Pāṭel (IE 8-3; EI 7), also called Pāṭīl; village<BR>headman; a member of the administrative board called Cauthiyā<BR>in Western India; cf. Paṭṭakila, Paṭakīla, Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाथ|पाथं|पाथः<BR>pātha (IE 8-6; IA 11), a land measure regarded as equal<BR>to 240 square feet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पथक|पथकः<BR>pathaka (IE 8-4; EI 4, 23, 27; CII 3, 4; LP), a group of<BR>villages; a territorial division like a Parganā of later days.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पथकीयक<BR>Pathakīyaka (LP), explained as one who collects the road-<BR>tax [for the maintenance of the road] or the transit tax. But<BR>cf. pathaka also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाथि|पाथिः<BR>pāthi (IA 15), a territorial unit; same as pathaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाठिन्<BR>Pāṭhin (EI3 1), epithet or family name of<BR>Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटी<BR>pāṭī (IE 8-3); ‘arithmetic’; cf. the designation Pāṭy-<BR>uparika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पति|पतिः<BR>pati (LL), a king; cf. adhipati.<BR>(EI 18), same as Kuḍipati = Sanskrit Grāmapati.<BR>Cf. grāma-patyā (probably the same as grāma-jana-patitvāt)<BR>and nānā-patyā (probably nānā-grāma-jana-patitvāt). See JAS,<BR>Letters, Vol. XX, pp. 203-04.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटि|पटिः<BR>paṭi (IA 18), same as Sanskrit prati, but sometimes substi-<BR>tuted for Sanskrit pari in Prakrit; cf. paṭibhoga, ‘consumption<BR>[of food].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतिभाग<BR>pati-bhāga (CII 4), a share of the produce payable to the<BR>landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतिहारि<BR>Patihāri (EI 27), Sanskrit Pratihārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटिका<BR>pāṭikā (CII 4), a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातिका<BR>pātikā, cf. rāja-pātikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटील्<BR>Pāṭīl, see Paṭel, Pāṭel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातिसाह<BR>Pātisāha, also spelt Pādisāha (EI 30; BL); same as Persian<BR>Pādshāh; ‘Muslim imperial ruler’. See Pādishāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातिसाहि<BR>Pātisāhi (BL), Indian modification of an imperial title of<BR>the Muslim rulers; same as Persian Pādshāh. See Pātisāha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतित|पतितः<BR>patita (LP), uncultivated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातित<BR>pātita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 14), ‘killed in a battle’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्र|पत्त्रं|पत्रं<BR>patra (CITD), a letter or document; a note; a written<BR>paper or deed.<BR>(LP), a bond.<BR>Cf. tāmra-patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पात्र|पात्त्रं|पात्रं|पात्रः<BR>Pātra (IE 8-3; EI 28, 29; BL), a minister; cf. Mahāpuro-<BR>hita-ṭhakkura, Paṇḍita, Upādhyāya, Karaṇa-kāyastha, etc., men-<BR>tioned as Pātra probably meaning ‘a courtier.’ See Ekapātra and<BR>Mahāpātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पात्र|पात्त्रं|पात्रं|पात्रः<BR>pātra, probably, a document (patra). See Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXX, p. 169.<BR>(EI 9), a donee.<BR>Cf. Pātrapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पात्रपति<BR>Pātrapati, probably, the driver or owner of a horse-cart<BR>(ṭaṅgā). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 145.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्रसमय<BR>patra-samaya (LP), the conditions laid down in a bond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्ट|पट्टं|पट्टः<BR>Paṭṭa, abbreviation of Paṭṭakila (A.R. Ep., 1958-59, No.<BR>B 296).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्ट|पट्टं|पट्टः<BR>paṭṭa (IE 8-4; CII 3, 4), a territorial term meaning a<BR>group of villages; cf. apara-paṭṭa (EI 22) ‘the western district’.<BR>(EI 7, 9, 11; SII 1; BL), a school or spiritual line; a<BR>pontificate; a pontifical seat; the dignity of the head of a Jain<BR>school; cf. reference to a Jain religious teacher as belonging to<BR>the paṭṭa of another teacher and the santāna of a third teacher;<BR>cf., e. g., ‘in the paṭṭa of Dharma-sūri’; also cf. ‘paṭṭ-āvalī of<BR>the Kharatara gaccha’.<BR>Cf. rāja-paṭṭa, paṭṭa-bandha, paṭṭ-ābhiṣeka, etc.<BR>(EI 18), a piece of land.<BR>(LL), a slab; cf. Prakrit paṭa (EI 20), a stone slab. Cf.<BR>yoni-paṭṭa; Gaurī-paṭṭa.<BR>(Chamba), also called paṭha; a grain measure, derived<BR>from Sanskrit prastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समे<BR>Same as paṭṭaka (q.v.); cf. Paṭṭa-lekhin, etc.<BR>(ASLV), an account book.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-245" target="_blank">Page-245+ 40</a>]<BR>(LP), abbreviation of Paṭṭadhara; probably one who has<BR>the charter for collecting government revenues; cf. Paṭṭakila.<BR>Cf. Paṭṭarājñī, Paṭṭanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्ट<BR>pāṭṭa, same as or a mistake for paṭṭa, a district. See Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 235.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टबन्ध|पट्टबन्धः<BR>paṭṭa-bandha (EI 5, 22, 26), coronation; crowning cere-<BR>mony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टाचार्य<BR>Paṭṭ-ācārya (IA 14), a religious title; same as Maṇḍal-<BR>ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टक|पट्टकः<BR>paṭṭaka (EI 30; IA 17), a passport; a charter; a copper-<BR>plate grant. Cf. paṭṭak-ārtha-samasta-karaṇāya (LP), ‘for fulfill-<BR>ing all the conditions in the charter’; also Tamil paṭṭayam<BR>(SITI), grant inscribed on copper-plates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकधार्मिक<BR>paṭṭaka-dhārmika (IEZ 8-8; EI 30); probably, an authorised<BR>cess to be collected for performing a religious function; cf.<BR>dhārmika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकापचारिक<BR>Paṭṭak-āpacārika (IE 8-3; EI 31), officer in charge of deal-<BR>ing with paṭṭak-āpacāra (crime relating to the misuse or fraud<BR>concerning grants).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकार<BR>Paṭṭakāra (EI 24), also called Paṭṭalekhin; writer of docu-<BR>ments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकिल|पट्टकिलः<BR>Paṭṭakila (EI 25; CII 4; HD), village headman; same<BR>as modern Paṭel, Pāṭel or Pāṭīl. See Ind. Ant., Vol. VI,<BR>pp. 51, 53. Cf. Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकिलादाय<BR>paṭṭakil-ādāya (EI 21; CII 4), tax for the maintenance<BR>of the Paṭṭakila or village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टक्कारै<BR>paṭṭakkārai (ASLV), neck-ring; an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकूल<BR>paṭṭa-kūla (LP), silk cloth; cf. pāṭoluṃ in Gujarātī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तला<BR>pattalā (EI 8-3; EI 19, 24; 26; CII 4), a territorial divi-<BR>sion; a district.<BR>(IA 18; LP), same as paṭṭa, a royal charter; cf. prasāda-<BR>pattalā (LP), a deed recording the grant of rent-free land; (IA<BR>18), cf. prabhoḥ prasād-āvāpta-pattalayā, explained as ‘[area<BR>enjoyed] under a patent obtained through the favour of the lord’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तलक<BR>Pattalaka (IE 8-3; EI 3, 9, 23), official designation; pro-<BR>bably, not an officer in charge of a territorial unit called pattalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टलेखिन्<BR>Paṭṭa-lekhin, cf. Paṭṭakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तलिका<BR>Pattalikā (EI 9), official designation; feminine form of<BR>Pattalaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टम्<BR>pāṭṭam (EI 21), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टमहादेवी<BR>Paṭṭamahādevī (IE 8-2; EI 4, 20, 22; BL), designation of<BR>the chief queen; cf. Mahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टमहिषी<BR>Paṭṭamahiṣī (EI 28), a crowned queen; chief queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टन|पट्टनं<BR>paṭṭana (HRS), duties levied upon merchants at the ports,<BR>as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR>(EI 19), same as pattana, a township.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तन|पत्तनं<BR>pattana (IE 8-4; IP), a township; suffixed to the names of<BR>cities like Aṇahillapura-pattana (modern Pāṭan in the Kadi Dis-<BR>trict of the former Baroda State).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तनाकरस्थानगोकुलाधिकारिपुरुष<BR>Pattan-ākarasthāna-gokul-ādhikāri-puruṣa (IA 15), official<BR>designation or designations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टनस्वामिन्<BR>Paṭṭana-svāmin (ASLV), head of an organisation or a<BR>guild in a city; sometimes regarded as the same as Mahānāḍ-<BR>prabhu. See Seṭṭi-Paṭṭanasvāmi.<BR>(SITI), chief or leader of the mercantile community of a<BR>town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टनायक<BR>Paṭṭanāyaka (IE 8-3; EI 29), the chief officer or a ruling<BR>chief; same as Puronāyaka (cf. Tamil Poṟṟu). It is a family name<BR>in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टराज्ञी<BR>Paṭṭarājñī (IE 8-2; EI 23, 30; BL), designation of the<BR>chief queen; cf. Rājñī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टराणी<BR>Paṭṭarāṇī (BL), title of a chief queen; cf. Rāṇī. Same as<BR>Paṭṭarājñī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टसाहनाधिपति<BR>Paṭṭasāhanādhipati (IE 8-3; EI 15), same as Mahāsādha-<BR>nika, etc.; see Paṭṭasāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टसाहणि<BR>Paṭṭasāhaṇi (EI 15), same as Paṭṭasāhanādhipati; see Sāhaṇi =<BR>Sanskrit Sādhanika; cf. Kari-turaga-paṭṭasāhaṇi (EI 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टशाल<BR>paṭṭa-śāla (CITD), Sanskrit °śālā; a reading hall; probably,<BR>‘the main hall’; in Kannaḍa, ‘a silk-shop’.<BR>(EI 3), name applied to the abode of certain Brāhmaṇas.<BR>(LP), cf. Gujaratī Paḍaśāla; the first room in a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टावली<BR>paṭṭ-āvalī (IA 19; SITI; BL), a list of Jain pontiffs; suc-<BR>cession list of spiritual heads among the Jains; cf. ‘paṭṭ-āvalī<BR>of the Bṛihat-Kharatara gaccha [of the Jains].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टवारिक<BR>Paṭṭavārika, same as modern Paṭvāri; cf. Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टेल<BR>Paṭṭela (EI 7), same as Paṭṭakila, Paṭel or Pāṭīl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टि<BR>paṭṭi (IE 8-6; EI 8), a measure of land; same as nivart-<BR>tana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टी<BR>paṭṭī (EI 9), a plot of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समे<BR>Same as paṭṭa; cf. rāja-paṭṭī (EI 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्ति|पत्तिः<BR>patti (SII 2), same as nivartana.<BR>(SII 1), a sheep-fold; a square measure.<BR>(CII 4), share of the produce.<BR>(IE 8-3), the smallest division of the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्ती<BR>pattī (IA 15), an extra land cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तिभाग<BR>patti-bhāga (CII 4), same as pati-bhāga, a share of produce<BR>payable to the landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तिक<BR>Pattika (IE 8-3), leader of the patti, the smallest division<BR>of the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तिका<BR>pattikā (CII 4), a share; same as patti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिका<BR>paṭṭikā (EI 8, 17), same as tāmra-paṭṭa or tāmra-paṭṭikā; a<BR>copper plate or copper-plate grant.<BR>(EI 3), a document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिकापालक<BR>Paṭṭikā-pālaka, same as Pustapāla (Select Inscriptions, p. 202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टीपद<BR>paṭṭī-pada (EI 24), footprints on a slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तियाणक<BR>Pattiyāṇaka (IA 132), official designation of doubtful im-<BR>port; probably, an administrator or document-writer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोला<BR>paṭṭolā, cf. Tamil paṭṭolai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोलै<BR>paṭṭolai (SII 1), Tamil = Sanskrit paṭṭolā; a document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टोलै<BR>Pāṭṭolai (EI 21, 22), Tamil; official designation; cf. paṭ-<BR>ṭolai, ‘a document’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोली<BR>paṭṭolī, ‘a deed of purchase’ also ‘land purchased by means<BR>of a paṭṭolī’ (Jour. As. Soc., Letters, Vol. XX, p. 205). See<BR>Tamil paṭṭolai = paṭṭolā, ‘a document’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोपाध्याय|पट्टोपाध्यायः<BR>Paṭṭ-opādhyāya (HD), a writer or keeper of official docu-<BR>ments. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातुसाह<BR>Pātusāha (BL), Indian modification of a Muslim imperial<BR>title; same as Persian Pādshāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्वारि<BR>Paṭvāri (IE 8-3), probably Sanskrit Paṭṭavārika; the<BR>accountant-clerk; a member of the administrative board called<BR>Cauthiyā in Western India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्युपरिक|पाट्युपरिकः<BR>Pāṭy-uparika (IE 8-2; 8-3; BL), official designation of<BR>uncertain implication; possibly indicating ‘the head of the de-<BR>partment of accounts’; sometimes also called Mahārāja, Mahā-<BR>sāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra, Mahāpīlupati, Pañc-ādhikaraṇ-oparika<BR>and Purapāl-oparika, additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाउका<BR>pāukā (IE 8-5; EI 29), same as Oḏiyā pāuseri; tax on the<BR>money realised by creditors from debtors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पऊक<BR>paūka (EI 31), misprint for Pāli pattha = Sanskrit prastha;<BR>a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौण्डरीक|पौंडरीक|पौण्डरीकं<BR>pauṇḍarīka (EI 4; IA 19), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौराणिक|पौराणिकः<BR>Paurāṇika (EI 30; BL), a reciter of the Purāṇas; also pro-<BR>bably, an astrologer. Cf. Vyāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौर|पौरं<BR>paura (CII 4), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौरवीथिल्लक<BR>Paura-vīthillaka, probably officers in charge of a city and<BR>a subdivision; cf. Paura-vi(vī)thillaka-grāmakūṭa-niyuktāniyukta-<BR>pradhān-āpradhāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 169, where the<BR>reading is given as visvillaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौरव्यवहारिक<BR>Paura-vyavahārika, cf. Nagara-vyavahārika. See Hist. Dharm.,<BR>Vol. III, pp. 112, 147.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौषध|पौषधः<BR>pauṣadha (HA), Sanskrit uposatha; living like a Jain monk<BR>for 12 or 24 hours; the observance of fast on the eighth and<BR>fourteenth of the fortnight, the full-moon day and the day<BR>before the new moon and abstention from wicked acts, chastity,<BR>abandonment of bathing, etc., i. e. living temporarily like a monk.<BR>See poṣadha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाउसेरि<BR>pāuseri, cf. pāukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौतव|पौतवं<BR>pautava (HRS), various dues collected by the superinten-<BR>dent of weights and measures, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR>(EI 30), measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौटि<BR>pauṭi (EI 29, 32), same as Sanskrit pravarti; a measure<BR>of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावाडै<BR>pāvāḍai (SITI), Tamil; cloth spread on the ground for<BR>persons of distinction to walk on; also food-offering on a large<BR>scale spread over a cloth in front of the deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावै<BR>pāvai (IE 8-5), same as darśana or nazrāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावक|पावकः<BR>pāvaka (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवन|पवनं|पवनः<BR>pavana (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावीसा<BR>pāvīsā (EI 33), probably, Sanskrit pāda-viṃśaka (viṃśopaka);<BR>name of a coin; regarded as equal to five cowrie-shells; same<BR>as modern paisā. See lohaḍiyā and dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवित्र|पवित्रं|पवित्रः<BR>pavitra (EI 9), the argha vessel.<BR>(Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 187), thread, 360 of which are tied<BR>round the neck of the image of Kṛṣṇa on Śrāvaṇa su-di 12.<BR>Cf. Caitra-pavitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवित्रक|पवित्रकं|पवित्रकः<BR>pavitraka (EI 1), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पायला<BR>pāyalā (EI 11), also called pāyalī; name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेडा<BR>peḍā (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piṭha, piḍā,<BR>pyoḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेडार्पात<BR>Peḍārpāta (BL), mistake for Peḍāpāla, ‘keeper of the record-<BR>boxes’. See Peṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेद्दगड्यमु<BR>pĕdda-gaḍyamu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown unit of<BR>measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेज्जुङ्क<BR>pĕjjuṅka (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax; same as<BR>pĕrjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्गडे<BR>Pĕrgaḍĕ (IE 8-3; EI 4), Kannaḍa; a chamberlain; a<BR>superintendent or director (Sanskrit Adhyakṣa); see Vĕrgaḍĕ,<BR>Hĕggaḍĕ, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्ग्गावुण्ड<BR>Pĕrggāvuṇḍa (EI 26), Kannaḍa, official designation. Cf.<BR>Gāvuṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्जुङ्क<BR>pĕrjuṅka (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; same as pĕjjuṅka; name of<BR>a tax or toll.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्जुङ्कदपेर्गडे<BR>Pĕrjuṅkadapĕrgaḍĕ (EI 16), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुजुङ्क<BR>perujuṅka (EI 28), same as pĕrjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुमानडिगल्<BR>Perumān-aḍigaḻ (SITI), Tamil; a term of reverence used<BR>to indicate a god or a king. Cf. personal names like Pramāḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुम्बडैयोम्<BR>perumbaḍaiyom (ASLV), military classes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटकपाल<BR>Peṭakapāla (EI 28, 29), keeper of the boxes containing<BR>records; record-keeper; same as Peṭāpāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटपाल<BR>Peṭapāla (EI 30; BL), keeper of boxes containing<BR>official records; the record-keeper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटापाल<BR>Peṭāpāla (EI 29), also called Peṭakapāla; record-keeper;<BR>same as Peṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटविक<BR>Peṭavika (EI 30), a class of officials; Peṭavika-vārika (IE 8-8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेठ<BR>peṭha (IE 8-4; CII 3), a small territorial unit; a group of<BR>villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेट्टपाल<BR>Peṭṭapāla (EI 15, 28), keeper of the record-boxes; same<BR>as Peṭāpāla, Peṭakapāla, Peḍāpāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेयियसाहणि<BR>Peyiya-sāhaṇi (Naik's List, No. 264), mentioned along<BR>with Maleya-sāhaṇi; official designation. Cf. Sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फा<BR>Phā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Phālguna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फदिया<BR>phadiyā, see phadyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फद्यक<BR>phadyaka (EI 23), same as phadiyā; name of a coin; (1/20)<BR>of a rupee and equal to 5 dukrās and 2 dukānīs (JNSI, Vol. XXII,<BR>p. 295).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फैण्डिआयायि<BR>phaiṇḍi-āyāyi (CITD), Telugu; same as phaiṇḍivāya-maṟuturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फैण्डिवायम<BR>phaiṇḍivāya-maṟuturu (CITD), Telugu; a maṟuturu measure<BR>of land which brought an income in coin and not kind; in<BR>Telugu, paiḍi means gold and āyam income.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फल|फलं|फलः<BR>phala (IA 27), a Pāli form of Sanskrit pala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फालदिव्य<BR>phāla-divya (IA 17), the ordeal of taking a heated plough-<BR>share in hand.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलहिक<BR>phalahika, cf. sa-phalahikaṃ (LP), with an open space<BR>round about the house; same as Gujarātī phaliyuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलक|फलकं|फलकः<BR>phalaka (IE 3-5), a wooden slab used as a slate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलसंस्कार<BR>phala-saṃskāra (CII 3), equation of the centre.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलित|फलितं<BR>phalita, cf. phalita-pade (LP), also Gujarātī huṃḍī pāke<BR>tyāre, ‘when the bill of exchange becomes due’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फिक<BR>phika (LP), a bull which is not castrated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फुरमाण<BR>phuramāṇa (EI 2), Persian farmān; a royal order or grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फुट्ट<BR>phuṭṭa (CII 3), a Prakrit word meaning a break or damage<BR>in a construction, sometimes Sanskritised as sphuṭita (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 144, note 3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिआद<BR>Piāda (IE 8-3), same as Bhaṭa or Bhaṭa-manuṣya; cf. Pāik.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचु|पिचुः<BR>picu, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचुल|पिचुलः<BR>picula, weight equal to 6 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिडा<BR>piḍā (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piṭha, peḍā, pyoḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिडागै<BR>piḍāgai (ASLV), a hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिदानालि<BR>Pidā-nāḻi (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिढ<BR>piḍha (LL), probably, a chair; cf. Sanskrit pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिल्लैगल्तनम्<BR>piḻḻaigaḻ-tanam (SITI), Tamil; status of the prince, sup-<BR>posed to be an officers' cadre composed of the junior members<BR>of the royal family. Cf. Kumār-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीलु|पीलुः<BR>pīlu (IE 8-3), Indian form of Arabic-Persian fīl, an ele-<BR>phant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीलुपति<BR>Pīlupati (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 13, 28; CII 4), leader of the<BR>elephant force or keeper of the elephants; cf. Mahāpīlupati, pīlu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिञ्छ<BR>piñcha (IA 18), bunch of feathers carried by a Jain ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डादान<BR>piṇḍ-ādāna (EI 12), quit rent. Cf. also piṇḍa-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डक|पिंडक|पिंडकं|पिण्डकं|पिंडकः|पिण्डकः<BR>piṇḍaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 254, text line 55), same as<BR>piṇḍ-ādāna or bhāga-bhoga; cf. samucita-kara-piṇḍak-ādi-samasta-<BR>pratyāya; taxes assessed in a lump; cf. piṇda-kara.<BR>(IA 2), same as grāsā; probably, a part of the produce of<BR>the fields for the maintenance of certain persons.<BR>(HRS), known from Pāla records; same as hiraṇya,<BR>according to some.<BR>(LL), probably, a slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डकर<BR>piṇḍa-kara (HRS), lump assessment upon villages, as<BR>suggested by the Arthaśāstra. Cf. also piṇḍ-ādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डपात|पिंडपात|पिण्डपातः<BR>piṇḍa-pāta (EI 25), food [for the Buddhist monks].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिशाचचतुर्दशी<BR>piśāca-caturdaśī (EI 1), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिषारडि<BR>Piṣāraḍi (IA 24), Malayāḻam; the manager of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिशुनवेत्रिक<BR>Piśunavetrika (EI 33; HD), probably, an officer who drives<BR>away undesirable persons with a cane; or, one engaged in a<BR>court for caning culprits. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 94. See<BR>Vetrika, Yāṣṭika, Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिटक|पिटकं|पिटकः<BR>piṭaka (CII 4), a measure of capacity.<BR>Cf. Traipiṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितलहार<BR>Pitalahāra (EI 20, 32), a brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितामह|पितामहः<BR>Pitāmaha (EI 24, 33), epithet of the Buddha.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; but cf. Brahman used to indicate ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिठ|पिठः<BR>piṭha (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piḍā, peḍā,<BR>pyoḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठ|पीठं<BR>pīṭha (CII 4; IA 12), receptacle of a Śiva-liṅga; the<BR>ablution trough of a Śiva-liṅga; also called Yoni-paṭṭa.<BR>(SITI), pedestal for the image of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठी<BR>pīṭhī (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 16), a pedestal or seat; same<BR>as pīṭha and pīṭhikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठिक<BR>pīṭhika (ASLV), Sanskrit pīṭhikā; a throne; same as rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठिका<BR>pīṭhikā (EI 2), a platform.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठिकावित्त<BR>Pīṭhikāvitta (IE 8-3; EI 12; HD), probably, ‘those who<BR>have acquired [special] seats’; same as Utthitāsanika. The<BR>word occurs in such records as the Belava plate of Bhojavarma-<BR>deva (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 40). Cf. Velāvitta. Pīṭhikāvitta<BR>is sometimes explained as the collector of state dues from pil-<BR>grims or religious institutions (Sen, Hist. Asp. Ins. Beng., p. 552).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठीपति<BR>Pīṭhīpati (BL), explained as ‘the lord of Magadha’ in the<BR>commentary of Sandhyākaranandin's Rāmacarita; title of the head<BR>of the Buddhist religious institution at Bodhgayā, who was<BR>the precursor of the later Mahant Mahārājas of Bodhgayā.<BR>The word pīṭhī in this title is the same as pīṭha or pīṭhikā meaning<BR>the vajrāsana at Bodhgayā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितृपर्वन्<BR>pitṛ-parvan (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 37), probably,<BR>śrāddha or dāna on each amāvāsyā day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितृयज्ञ|पितृयज्ञः<BR>pitṛ-yajña (CII 4), offerings to the manes; one of the<BR>pañca-mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्ल<BR>pla (IE 8-1), contraction of pala; often found in the re-<BR>cords of the Orissa region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोचिलभूमि<BR>pocila-bhūmi (LP), soft land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोढी<BR>poḍhī (LL), a cistern; cf. Sanskrit prahi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोदुवा<BR>Poduvāl13 (EI 18), Tamil-Malayalam; an officer super-<BR>vising charitable endowments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोलाच्य<BR>polācya, cf. sa-khila-polācya (IE 8-5); cultivated land; same<BR>as nāla; Hindī polach, ‘land constantly under cultivation.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोंद<BR>poṃda (Chamba), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोंदी<BR>poṃdī (Chamba), bottom; foot of a hill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्<BR>pon (SITI), also spelt poṉ; name of a gold coin also called<BR>māḍai. Cf. pon-bhaṇḍāram, ‘gold-treasury’; pon-paṇḍāra-vāśal,<BR>‘the gate of the gold-treasury; royal gold-treasury’; pon-vargam<BR>(SITI), ‘a class of taxes payable in gold or coin; ponvari,<BR>‘tax payable in gold (cash)’; also ‘the fee for minting gold into<BR>coins’; probably, the same as ponvari-māḍai.<BR>Cf. turai-miṉṉaṟ-pon (SITI), name of a coin.<BR>(IE 8-8; EI 16), name of a coin; same as gadyāṇa, hūn<BR>or varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्<BR>ponṉ (EI 24), a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो<BR>Poṉ-bhaṇḍāram (ASLV), a treasurer; treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोरपाञ्जिधरपरीक्षा<BR>Pora-Pāñjidhara-parīkṣā (EI 28), chief astrologer; cf.<BR>puro prefixed to certain official designations in Orissa. See<BR>Paṭṭanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोरश्रीकरण<BR>Pora-Śrīkaraṇa (EI 28), chief secretary; cf. puro prefixed<BR>to certain official designations in Orissa. See Poṟṟu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो<BR>Poṟ-Bhaṇḍāri (EI 25), Tamil; temple officer mentioned<BR>along with Śāsana-bhaṇḍāri (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 132);<BR>cf. pora prefixed to Oḏiyā official designations like Pora-Śrīkaraṇa;<BR>also Tamil Poṟṟu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोर्रु<BR>Poṟṟu (EI 25), Tamil; official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोषध|पोषधः<BR>poṣadha, derived from Sanskrit uposatha; also called poṣa-<BR>dha-vrata; cf. pauṣadha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत|पोतः<BR>pota (EI 9), a sacrificial victim.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोतक|पोतकः<BR>potaka (LP), the government's money-bag.<BR>(LP), cf. Gujarātī poluṃ; the amount of revenue of a village<BR>sent to the Government treasury. Cf. pottaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत्र|पोत्रं<BR>potra (EI 26), name of a tax. Cf. potta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत्त<BR>potta, cf. milita-potta-drammā (LP), collected government<BR>money. Cf. potra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत्तक<BR>pottaka (LP), same as Gujarātī potuṃ; the amount of the<BR>revenue of a village sent to the government treasury. Cf. potaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोट्टलिका<BR>poṭṭalikā (IE 8-8), a bundle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्र<BR>pra (PJS), abbreviation of pratimā (especially in medieval<BR>Jain inscriptions).<BR>(IE 8-1), abbreviation of prathama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रबन्ध|प्रबंध|प्रबंधः|प्रबन्धः<BR>prabandha, name of hymnal compositions in Tamil by<BR>ancient Vaiṣṇava devotees. The contributions of hymns and<BR>prayers by the twelve āl13vārs in praise of Viṣṇu make up the<BR>Nālāyiradivyaprabandham. Nālāyira (four thousand) indicates the<BR>rough total number of items and prabandham is regarded as mean-<BR>ing a compilation. The first thousand is known as Tirumol13i and<BR>comprises hymns of Periyāl13vār, Āṇḍāl, Kulaśekhara, etc.; the<BR>second thousand contains the hymns of Tirumaṅgai; the third<BR>comprises the compositions of the first three āl13vārs called<BR>Iyaṟpā, viz. Tirumal13iśai, Nammāl13var and Tirumaṅgai, and the<BR>fourth called Tiruvāymol13i is entirely the work of Nammāl13vār.<BR>Nāthamunigal13 is stated to be the compiler of this anthology.<BR>See M. S. Purnalingam Pillai, Tamil Literature, pp. 181 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रबर्ह<BR>prabarha (EI 13), a worthy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राब्द<BR>prābda (EI 16), same as abda, ‘the year.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभा<BR>prabhā (SII 2), an aureole or nimbus. Cf. prabhā-valaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभाटक<BR>prabhāṭaka (EI 24), same as bhāṭaka; rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभावलय<BR>prabhā-valaya (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 16), aureole or nimbus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राभृतीकृत<BR>prābhṛtīkṛta (EI 14), ‘presented’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभु|प्रभुः<BR>Prabhu (IA 30; BL), a village official; cf. Mahāprabhu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभुज्यमान<BR>prabhujyamāna (IA 18), cf. bhujyamāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभुशक्ति<BR>prabhu-śakti (CII 4), power derived from the royal position.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभुस्वाम्य<BR>prabhu-svāmya (SII 11. 1), a tenure held by a Prabhu (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रबोधनी<BR>prabodhanī (EI 8), prabodh-otsava (EI 32), same as utthāna-<BR>dvādasī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदक्षिण|प्रदक्षिणं<BR>pradakṣiṇa (CITD), circumambulation from left to right;<BR>paying homage to a temple, etc., by solemnly walking round<BR>it with the right hand towards it, so that the right side is always<BR>turned towards the person or object circumambulated; a rever-<BR>ential salutation made by walking in this manner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदेश|प्रदेशः<BR>pradeśa (IE 8-4), a province or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रादेशिक<BR>Prādeśika (IE 8-3; HD), cf. Prakrit Pādesika (EI 3), pro-<BR>vincial governor; governor of a pradeśa or province. Cf. CII,<BR>Vol. I, pp. 4-5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदेष्टृ<BR>Pradeṣṭṛ (HD), a class of magistrates; the police magis-<BR>trate. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 147; Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII,<BR>p. 156; Arthaśāstra, I. 12; IV. 1 and 10 (last verse).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदेय|प्रदेयः<BR>pradeya (EI 12), same as deya; dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधान|प्रधानं|प्रधानः<BR>Pradhāna (SII 1; HD; BL), an official designation some-<BR>times indicating the chief minister or administrator also called<BR>Pradhāna-saciva (EI 23); cf. pañca-Pradhānāḥ (EI 5) ‘the five<BR>ministers’. See Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 35 where Mantrin, Amātya<BR>and Pradhāna are separately mentioned.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानमण्डप<BR>pradhāna-maṇḍapa (LL), Buddhist; the hall for practising<BR>religious exercises.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानिन्<BR>Pradhānin (CITD), according to lexicons, a governor,<BR>minister or president; noble or courtier; etc.<BR>(EI 31; ASLV), a high executive officer; same as Pradhāna.<BR>(EI 30), a village headman.<BR>Cf. Mahāpradhāni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानिजोडि<BR>pradhāni-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; an inām<BR>held on a fixed quit-rent by a minister; the chief minister's quit-<BR>rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राधिराज्य<BR>prādhirājya (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रद्वार|प्रद्वारं<BR>pradvāra (IA 7), a place in front of the gate; explained as<BR>‘a suburb’ (EI 21); same as Gujarātī parā. Cf. Valabhī-prad-<BR>vāra-Homba-vāsakāt (IA 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राड्विवाक|प्राड्विवाकः<BR>Prāḍvivāka (HD), the chief justice; a judge. See Manusmṛti,<BR>IX. 234.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रघट्टक|प्रघट्टकः<BR>praghaṭṭaka (EI 15), probably, a conflict.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राघूर्णक|प्राघूर्णकः<BR>prāghūrṇaka (LP), a present or gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रग्राह्य<BR>pragrāhya (EI 12), cf. a-kiñcit-pragrāhya; same as grāhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रहणीक<BR>prahaṇīka (LL), a class of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रहर|प्रहरः<BR>prahara (SII 2; SITI), flaw in rubies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राहरिक्य<BR>prāharikya (LP), cf. Gujarātī pahero; a guard or custo-<BR>dian.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रहितक<BR>prahitaka (IA 6), doubtfully explained as ‘a messenger’ or<BR>‘a committee man.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रैषणिक<BR>Praiṣaṇika (IE 8-3), same as Preṣaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकाल<BR>prakāla (Select Inscriptions, p. 305, text line 15); an era;<BR>cf. Gupta-prakāle gaṇanāṃ vidhāya. See kāla in kāl-ānuvartta-<BR>māna-saṃvatsare (ibid., p. 270, text lines 3-4), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकरण|प्रकरणं<BR>prakaraṇa (CII 1), proper occasion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकीर्तित|प्रकीर्त्तित|प्रकीर्त्तितं<BR>prakīrtita (EI 24), built; same as kīrtita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रम|प्रक्रमः<BR>prakrama (CII 1), an effort; zealous activity; same as<BR>parākrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रान्त|प्रक्रांत|प्रक्रान्तः<BR>prakrānta (CII 1), active or zealous.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रय<BR>prakraya (HRS), income from mines and salt-works, as<BR>suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकृत|प्रकृतः<BR>prakṛta, cf. saṅgha-prakṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रित्<BR>Prakrit, Anglicised spelling of Prākṛta, the name of a<BR>language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राकृत|प्राकृतः<BR>Prākṛta, see Prakrit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकृति|प्रकृतिः<BR>prakṛti (HD); cf. Mahābhārata, II. v. 23, speaking of<BR>the seven prakṛtis which Nīlakaṇṭha explains as referring to<BR>Durg-ādhyakṣa (commandant of the citadel), Bal-ādhyakṣa (con-<BR>troller general of the army), Dharma-ādhyakṣa (chief of the<BR>departments of charity and justice), Camūpati (commander of<BR>the army in the field), chaplain, physician and astrologer. The<BR>Milindapañha (IV. i. 36) mentions six officers, e.g., the com-<BR>mander-in-chief, prime minister, chief judge, chief treasurer,<BR>bearer of the sun-shade and bearer of the sword of state (cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XV, p. 77, note 6). Cf. Mātra.<BR>(EI 16), a temple official.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyone.’<BR>(EI 9), the Kṣatriya community.<BR>Cf. sa-tantuvāya-gokuṭa-śauṇḍik-ādi-prakṛtika (IE 8-5);<BR>subjects of a king.<BR>(CII 1), usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रिया<BR>prakriyā (IA 18), cf. samasta-rāja-prakriy-opeta; prerogative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्षेप|प्रक्षेपः<BR>prakṣepa (EI 13), cf. amīṣāṃ prakṣepa-pratiṣedhau na karaṇ-<BR>īyau, ‘they should not be ousted [from the possession] or<BR>hindered [from their enjoyment of the gift land].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमदाकुल<BR>pramadā-kula (EI 11), a host of courtesans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमाण|प्रमाणं<BR>pramāṇa (EI 6; SII 1; SITI), a document; a title deed.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 109), authority; witness.<BR>(SII 12), cf. mūla-pramāṇa, original order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमाणयष्टि<BR>pramāṇa-yaṣṭi (LL), measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमातार<BR>Pramātāra (HD), an officer concerned with the administra-<BR>tion of justice, according to some (Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 122-<BR>23). See Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211. Cf. Pramātṛ, Pramattavāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमत्तवार<BR>Pramattavāra (EI 21), official designation; same as Pramātṛ<BR>or Pramātāra (q. v.); the commander of the elephant corps<BR>according to some (CII 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमातृ<BR>Pramātṛ (BL), same as Pramātāra, Pramattavāra (q. v.); a<BR>civil judge, according to some (HD); cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII,<BR>p. 321; literally, ‘measurer [of the king's grain share]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमुख|प्रमुखं|प्रमुखः<BR>Pramukha (CII 4), a member of the executive committee of<BR>a corporation.<BR>(EI 28), probably the same as Pradhānin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राण|प्राणः<BR>prāṇa (CII 1), living being; same as prāṇin.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणाचार्य|प्राणाचार्यः<BR>Prāṇ-ācārya (EI 8), title of a physician; explained as the<BR>medical adviser of the king (HD). Cf. Viṣṇudharmottara, II.<BR>24. 33-34 (for his qualifications).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणदाक्षिण्य<BR>prāṇa-dākṣiṇya (CII 1), gift of life.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणाली<BR>praṇālī (CII 3), a conduit, a channel, an irrigation canal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणान्तिक|प्राणांतिक<BR>prāṇāntika (SITI), ‘till the close of one's life’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रनप्त्रिक<BR>pranaptrika (CII 1), cf. panatika (EI 22), the great-<BR>grandson; but cf. naptṛ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणसमेत<BR>prāṇa-sameta, cf. Prakrit praṇa-sameda (EI 24), ‘endowed<BR>with life’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणश्य<BR>praṇaśya (LP), ‘going out of sight’; cf. Gujarātī nāśīne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणय|प्रणयः<BR>praṇaya (IE 8-5; HRS), known from the Arthaśāstra, the<BR>Junagadh inscription of Rudradāman, etc.; emergency tax or<BR>benevolence; also called praṇaya-kriyā (IE 8-5); cf. a-hiraṇya-<BR>dhānya-praṇaya-pradeya, an epithet of rent-free land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणयक्रिया<BR>praṇaya-kriyā (EI 8), benevolence or emergency impost;<BR>same as praṇaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रान्तपाल<BR>Prāntapāla (IE 8-3; EI 18, 29, 31), warden of the marches;<BR>also explained as the governor of a province or guardian of the<BR>frontiers (HD). Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 124.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपा<BR>prapā (EI 3; IA 18; LL), watering trough; a cistern or<BR>reservoir.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), a place of distributing<BR>water gratis to travellers; a cistern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राप<BR>prāpa (EI 17), ‘sub-division of a district’; but see prāpīya,<BR>prāveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपापूरक<BR>Prapā-pūraka (IE 8-8; EI 30), a person responsible for<BR>filling the cisterns with water in a place for watering cattle or<BR>supplying water to travellers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपर्णक<BR>praparṇaka, royal order; same as Persian parwāna (Select<BR>Inscriptions, p. 248).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपौत्र|प्रपौत्रः<BR>prapautra, cf. pautra-prāpautrika (CII 1); the great-grandson.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रापीय<BR>prāpīya (EI 17), same as prāveśya; cf. Akṣasaraka-prāveśya<BR>and Akṣasaraka-prāpīya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 109); cf. prāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राप्तपञ्चमहाशब्द<BR>Prāpta-pañcamahāśabda (IE 8-2), same as Samadhigata-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-257" target="_blank">Page-257+ 40</a>]<BR>pañcamahāśabda; subordinate title or epithet; sometimes applied<BR>to a crown prince. See pañca-mahāśabda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राप्ति|प्राप्तिः<BR>prāpti (SII 2), benefit.<BR>(EI 7), revenue.<BR>(SITI), enjoyment; what is obtained from someone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रारब्धि|प्रारब्धिः<BR>prārabdhi (EI 2), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रार्य<BR>prārya (EI 15), father's father or father-in-law's father.<BR>Cf. āryaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसाद|प्रसादः<BR>prasāda (EI 3), gift (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 162, note 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रासाद|प्रासादः<BR>prāsāda (CII 4; LL), a palace or temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसादक<BR>prasādaka, cf. Pali and Prakrit pasādaka (EI 20), one who<BR>converts some one to the Buddhist faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसादमुक्त<BR>prasāda-mukta (LP), cf. Gujarātī prasād choḍvā khāt, ‘for<BR>allowing this favour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसन्न|प्रसन्नः<BR>prasanna (CII 1), devoted or attached.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रशस्ति|प्रशस्तिः<BR>praśasti (EI 15, 23, 24; CII 3, 4), a culogy; a culogistic<BR>inscription generally on stone; a copper-plate charter (with<BR>reference to the introductory section of medieval charters);<BR>rarely praśastā (Ep. Ind., Vol. 36, p. 52), śubhā (Vol. 35, p. 59).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रास्तरिकश्रेणी<BR>prāstarika-śreṇī (EI 23), a guild of stone-masons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रशास्तृ<BR>Praśāstṛ (EI 31), probably, a judge; the chief magistrate,<BR>according to some (HD); cf. Arthaśāstra, I. 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रशिष्य|प्रशिष्यः<BR>Praśiṣya (ML; SITI), the disciple's disciple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसृमर<BR>prasṛmara (EI 13), explained as ‘spreading out in some<BR>corner’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसृति|प्रसृतिः<BR>prasṛti (EI 30), a measure; a handful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रस्थ|प्रस्थः<BR>prastha (IE 8-6; CII 4; Chamba), a measure of capacity,<BR>often regarded as one-sixteenth of a droṇa; cf. Pāli pattha, a land<BR>measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रष्ठ|प्रष्ठः<BR>praṣṭha, cf. praṣṭham (Sel. Ins., p. 236), ‘immediately’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रस्थक<BR>prasthaka (HRS), known from the Gurjara-Pratihāra re-<BR>cords; cess at the rate of a prastha of grain over and above the<BR>usual grain-share. Cf. akṣapatala-prastha, pratihāra-prastha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रताप|प्रतापः<BR>pratāpa, see partāb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Pratāpa-cakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथम|प्रथमः<BR>Prathama (EI 21), prefixed to Kāyastha and Kulika to indi-<BR>cate representatives of certain classes as members of an adminis-<BR>trative board of the Pañcāyat type.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमद्वादाशी<BR>prathama-dvādāśī (EI 12; SII 2), Āṣāḍha su-di 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमकायस्थ<BR>Prathama-kāyastha (IE 8-3; EI 27; BL), representative<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-258" target="_blank">Page-258+ 39</a>]<BR>of the scribal class on the local council of administrators; the<BR>clerk-member of the Pañcāyat board (see Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p.<BR>130); the chief scribe, according to some (HD).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमकुलिक<BR>Prathama-kulika (IE 8-3; BL), literally, ‘the chief artisan’;<BR>designation of a member of the artisan class represented on an<BR>administrative board like the Pañcāyat (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 130).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमपुस्तपाल<BR>Prathama-pustapāla (EI 15), wrongly regarded as occurr-<BR>ing in some epigraphs; see Pustapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमस्कन्ध<BR>prathama-skandha (LP), the first instalment. See skandha,<BR>skandhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमतरम्<BR>prathamataram, ‘at first’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 240).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमतृतीया<BR>prathama-tṛtīyā (EI 7), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रति<BR>Prati (LP), abbreviation of Pratihārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रति<BR>prati, cf. śata-pratyā (LP), ‘per hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिबद्ध|प्रतिबद्धः<BR>pratibaddha (IA 15), generally used in the sense of ‘attached<BR>to’ or ‘belonging to’ in respect of a village pertaining to a terri-<BR>torial unit; sometimes used in the sense of ‘hailing from’ or ‘one<BR>whose family hails from’ (cf. vinirgata generally used in the same<BR>sense).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिभाग|प्रतिभागः<BR>pratibhāga (HRS), offerings of fruits, firewood, roots and<BR>the like payable by villagers to the king as indicated in the<BR>Manusmṛti.<BR>Cf. pati-bhāga.<BR>(CII 1), one's lot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिभेदिका<BR>prātibhedikā (IE 8-5; EI 9, 12), an obligation or impost<BR>of uncertain meaning; may be the same as prātivedhanika.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 298, text line 20), explained by<BR>some as ‘a special right’ (CII 4); but cf. viṣṭi-prātibhedikā (EI<BR>14); supposed to be related to umbara-bheda (q. v.) and meaning<BR>a special levy on defaulters in the payment of taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिभोग|प्रतिभोगः<BR>pratibhoga, prātibhoga (HRS), same as pratibhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिबोध|प्रतिबोधः<BR>pratibodha (HA), teaching in the Jain doctrine; conversion<BR>to the Jain faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिबोधित<BR>pratibodhita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVI, p. 132, note 3), same<BR>as vijñāpita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिभू<BR>pratibhū (EI 30), a security.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिच्छन्द|प्रतिच्छंद|प्रतिच्छंदः|प्रतिच्छन्दः|प्रतिछन्द<BR>praticchanda, a model for artists (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X,<BR>No. 1, p. 12). See lepyakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिदिश्<BR>pratidiś, cf. bhuñjato bhojayatah kṛṣataḥ karṣayataḥ pratidiśato<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-259" target="_blank">Page-259+ 40</a>]<BR>vā na ken = āpi paripanthanā kāryā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 280,<BR>text lines 65-66); probably, ‘to dispose of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिढक्का<BR>pratiḍhakkā (EI 4, 29), a kind of drum; one of the royal<BR>insignia of certain kings of South India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिगणक<BR>pratigaṇaka (EI 26), subdivision of a district; same as<BR>pratijāgaraṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिग्रह|प्रतिग्रहः<BR>pratigraha (SITI), acceptance of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहार|प्रतिहारः<BR>Pratihāra, Pratīhāra (EI 23; BL), also called Pratihārin<BR>(EI 3, 23), ‘a door-keeper’; but cf. Mahāpratihāra who was a<BR>high officer; officer in charge of the defence of the royal palace<BR>or bed-chamber or the head of the guards of the city gate; a<BR>chamberlain or inditer of grants, according to some (HD);<BR>personal attendant of a king, according to others (CII; 4). See<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 73; Vol. IX, p. 192; Bṛhaspati quoted by<BR>Viśvarūpa on the Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 307 (for his qualifications);<BR>Mahābhārata, Ādiparvan, 85. 28-29; Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24.<BR>12; Śukra, I. 121. Cf. Antaḥ-pratīhāra (IE 8-3), Rajju-pratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहार|प्रतिहारः<BR>pratihāra (IE 8-5), levy for the maintenance of the door-<BR>keepers of the city gates; cf. pratihāra-prastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहारप्रस्थ<BR>pratihāra-prastha (HRS), tax paid by the villagers at the<BR>rate of one prastha of grain for payment to the Pratihāra; see<BR>pratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहाररक्षी<BR>Pratihāra-rakṣī (IE 8-3; LL), ‘a female door-keeper’; a<BR>female officer in charge of the gates of the royal harem or the<BR>personal attendant of a queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहारिन्<BR>Pratihārin (EI 23, 30), official designation; same as Prati-<BR>hāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहस्त|प्रतिहस्तः<BR>Pratihasta, cf. Oḏiyā Paḍihasta (EI 28), a representative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिजागरणक<BR>pratijāgaraṇaka (IE 8-4; EI 9, 32; CII 4), a territorial<BR>unit often found in Paramāra inscriptions; same as parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिक|प्रतिकः<BR>pratika, cf. Prakrit paḍika (EI 8), see pratikaṃ śatam, ‘one<BR>coin per cent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिकर|प्रतिकरः<BR>pratikara, cf. kara; also a-kiñchit-pratikara (EI 23),<BR>‘land without any yield of revenue’.<BR>(HRS), compensatory allowance paid by the government<BR>to dispossessed owners of rent-fee land, as indicated by the Rāja-<BR>taraṅgiṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिकरण<BR>pratikaraṇa, repairs; cf. khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-pratikaraṇa, same<BR>as khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-jīrṇoddhāra (q.v.).<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 114, note 2), meeting the expenses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिक्रमण|प्रतिक्रमणं<BR>pratikramaṇa (LP), morning and evening prayers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिमा<BR>pratimā, cf. pratimam (SII 2), image of a human being;<BR>usually, the image of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिनर्तक<BR>Pratinartaka (CII 3; BL; HD), an official title; perhaps<BR>meaning ‘a herald’; cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 190 (a person described<BR>as tanniyukta-pratinartaka-kulaputr-āmātya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिनिधि|प्रतिनिधिः<BR>Pratinidhi, a representative (Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 150).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिनिवासिन्<BR>Pratinivāsin (EI 20), same as Nivāsin, a resident.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपद्<BR>pratipad (CII 1), ‘to follow’; same as anuvṛt, anupratipad.<BR>(Select Inscriptions, p. 281, text line 10); cf. pratipādya,<BR>‘having decided’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपदा<BR>pratipadā (EI 24), a slab with foot-prints. Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXIII, p. 247.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपादितक<BR>pratipāditaka (EI 13), given or granted.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपन्न|प्रतिपन्नं<BR>pratipanna, ‘decided’; cf. pratipad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपत्ति|प्रतिपत्तिः<BR>pratipatti, cf. pratipattau (LP), explained as ‘convincing’;<BR>but actually ‘during the administration of … ’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिराज्य<BR>Prātirājya (EI 3, 6), same as Pratirāja, ‘a hostile king.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिराज्यिक<BR>Prātirājyika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), probably, an<BR>envoy at the court of a hostile king; but cf. Paḍirā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसमासन|प्रतिसमासनं<BR>pratisamāsana (IE 8-8), refutation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसांवत्सरिकश्राद्ध<BR>pratisāṃvatsarika-śrāddha (CII 4), the annual śrāddha cere-<BR>mony; same as sāṃvatsarika-śrāddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसरक<BR>Pratisaraka (IA 7), cf. Vartmapāla-Pratisaraka-Rājasthānīya;<BR>official designation; same as Pratisāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसारक<BR>Pratisāraka (EI31; HD), explained as an officer who<BR>collects tax and allows carts to go out of the nālī or a strip of<BR>low ground (LP); see Pratisārin; same as Pratīsāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतीसारक<BR>Pratīsāraka (LP), explained as ‘a gate-keeper’. See Prati-<BR>sāraka, Pratisārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिसारक<BR>Prātisāraka (HD), same as Pratisāraka. See Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 187.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसारिन्<BR>Pratisārin (LP) explained as ‘one who allows the merchants<BR>to go through strips of low ground’. See Pratisāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशरीर<BR>Pratiśarīra (BI), a representative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशासन|प्रतिशासनं<BR>pratiśāsana (SII 11-1), a renewed charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषेध|प्रतिषेधः<BR>pratiṣedha, cf. prakṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषिद्धाय<BR>pratiṣiddh-āya (IA 19), same as siddh-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिश्रय|प्रतिश्रयः<BR>pratiśraya (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), a shelter-<BR>house for travellers. See ucchraya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिष्ठा<BR>pratiṣṭhā (EI 11; SII 1; BL; HA), installation, consecra-<BR>tion; ceremony of installation or consecration (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XII, p. 20).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिष्ठान|प्रतिष्ठानं<BR>pratiṣṭhāna, cf. yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāna (CII 2-1), used in the sense<BR>of pratiṣṭhāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिष्ठापित<BR>pratiṣṭhāpita, cf. a-pratiṣṭhāpita (ML); interred.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशूरक<BR>Pratiśūraka (EI 31), probably, the superintendent of<BR>wrestling; cf. Pratiśūrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशूरिक<BR>Pratiśūrika (IE 8-3), probably, the superintendent of<BR>gladiatorial combats; cf. Pratiśūraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिटिप्पनक<BR>pratiṭippanaka (LP), a receipt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवासुदेव<BR>Prati-vāsudeva (HA), an enemy of Vāsudeva in Jain my-<BR>thology.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवेदक<BR>Prativedaka (IE 8-3; CII 1), a reporter or spy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवेदना<BR>prativedanā (CII 1), reporting of news.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिवेधनिक<BR>prātivedhanika (HRS), punching-fee collected from mer-<BR>chants at the time of the inspection of weights and measures, as<BR>indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवेश्य|प्रतिवेश्यः<BR>prativeśya, prātiveśika (CII 1), a neighbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिविधान|प्रतिविधानं<BR>pratividhāna (CII 1), supporting [with money]; gift [of<BR>money].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिव्यञ्जन<BR>prativyañjana, Tamil paḍi-viñjanam (SITI), articles other<BR>than rice for the preparation of food-offerings in a temple, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतोली<BR>pratolī (EI 9; CII 3; BL), a gate-way; a gate-way with a<BR>flight of steps; a gate-way strongly built and considerably high.<BR>(EI 31), probably, a street.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतोलिका<BR>pratolikā (EI 1), same as pratolī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यब्दकाल<BR>pratyabda-kāla (EI 3), an anniversary [of death].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यादाय<BR>pratyādāya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 21; Vol. XIV, p. 196;<BR>Vol. XXXV, p. 127), income or tax; cf. pratyāya in the same sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यंश<BR>pratyaṃśa, see agra-pratyaṃśa (ML); a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यन्धारुवा<BR>pratyandhāruvā (IE 8-5; EI 12, 33), Oḏiyā; probably<BR>pratyarthāruvā (Sanskrit pratyartha-rūpyaka), name of a tax or<BR>levy of uncertain import; probably, a levy on the money rea-<BR>lised by money-lenders from debtors. See arthāruvā, pāukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यन्त|प्रत्यंत|प्रत्यन्तः<BR>pratyanta (IE 8-4; CII 1), a state beyond the borders of<BR>one's territories; a land outside one's dominions; also its people;<BR>cf. anta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यन्तनृपति<BR>Pratyanta-nṛpati (EI 15), ruler of a bordering state.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यर्थारुवा<BR>pratyarthāruvā (IE8-5), a tax of uncertain import; pro-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-262" target="_blank">Page-262+ 40</a>]<BR>bably Sanskrit pratyartha-rūpyaka in the sense of a levy on<BR>amounts realised by the money lenders from debtors; also read<BR>as pratyandhāruvā; see arthāruvā and pāukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यय|प्रत्ययः<BR>Pratyaya, probably, a lessee (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp.<BR>143-44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यय|प्रत्ययः<BR>pratyaya (EI 11, 15), a holding; sometimes also written<BR>as pratyāya (cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 170, note 5).<BR>Cf. Prakrit avija-pracaga saṃkara (CII 2-1) = Sanskrit avidyā-<BR>pratyayāḥ saṃskārāḥ, ‘in inter-connection with delusion are the<BR>saṃkāras’, i. e. the saṃkāras spring from avidyā.<BR>Cf. etat-pratyaye, in this matter (Select Inscriptions, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्याय|प्रत्यायः<BR>pratyāya (IE 8-5; EI 29; HRS), revenue; income or tax;<BR>dues payable to the king including bhāga-bhoga-kara and hiraṇya;<BR>cf. bhūla-vāta-pratyāya (EI 10). See pratyaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यय|प्रत्ययः<BR>pratyaya, pratyāya (CII 3), primarily ‘income’ and secon-<BR>darily ‘a holding, the income of which is enjoyed.’ Cf. amuka-<BR>pratyaya-amuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्येकबुद्ध<BR>Pratyeka-Buddha, cf. Prakrit Pracega-Budha (CII 2-1),<BR>Buddhist; name of certain Buddhas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्युपगमन<BR>pratyupagamana (CII 1), meeting personally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रौढप्रताप<BR>Prauḍha-pratāpa (IE 8-2), cf. Pratāpa and Vīrapratāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रौढप्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Prauḍha-pratāpa-cakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवचन|प्रवचनं<BR>pravacana, exposition of texts (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p.<BR>150).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवहण|प्रवहणं<BR>pravahaṇa (LP), same as vāhana; a boat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवहणघोटक<BR>pravahaṇa-ghoṭaka, (LP), a carriage horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवण|प्रवणः<BR>pravaṇa (EI 1), ‘excellent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवणि<BR>Pravaṇi (CII 4), a banker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवणिकर<BR>pravaṇikara (EI 18, 24, 26; HRS), cf. yathādīyamāna-bhāga-<BR>bhoga-kara-pravaṇikara-kūṭaka-prabhṛti-samast-ādaya (IE 8-5),<BR>known from the Gāhaḍavāla records; a minor tax other than<BR>what was bhāga-bhoga-kara, according to some; explained by<BR>some as a tax levied from a class of merchants. See pravaṇivāda.<BR>(IA 15), explained as hiraṇya or tax in cash.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवणिवाद<BR>pravaṇivāda (EI 21), name of a tax; cf. pravaṇikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर|प्रवरं|प्रवरः<BR>pravara (IA 19), an invocation of ancestors at the perfor-<BR>mance of certain rites.<BR>(CII 4), a member of the executive committee of a corpo-<BR>ration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रावारञ्चर<BR>Prāvārañcara (EI 24), supposed to be ‘a licensed spy’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्ह|प्रवर्हः<BR>pravarha (EI 13), see prabarha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्तवाप<BR>pravartavāpa (EI 32), also called pravarta; a land measure;<BR>cf. pravarti and pravartikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्तमान|प्रवर्त्तमान<BR>pravartamāna (IA 18, 19), current [year]; cf. atīta or expired.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्तन|प्रवर्तनं|प्रवर्त्तन|प्रवर्त्तनं<BR>pravartana (CII 1), establishment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्ति<BR>pravarti, pravartikā (EI 32), a measure of capacity; cf.<BR>pauṭi, pravarta and pravartavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवेश|प्रवेशः<BR>praveśa, prāveśa (EI 17), explained as ‘a small territorial<BR>unit’; but probably refers to the assessment of the rent of a loca-<BR>lity along with another; cf. Siviḍi-praveśa-Kandalivāḍa-grāma inter-<BR>preted as ‘Kandalivāḍa-grāma having its rent assessed along<BR>with Siviḍi’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 59, note 1). See prāveśya,<BR>prāpīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवेशभागिक<BR>Praveśa-bhāgika (HD), a subordinate officer of the treasury<BR>who received cash payments, according to Stein (Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>VIII, 278).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवेशक|प्रवेशकः<BR>praveśaka (SITI), admission, entry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रावेश्य<BR>prāveśya (EI 31), also spelt praveśya; explained by some<BR>as a small territorial unit; sometimes translated as ‘situated in’<BR>(CII 4); but may refer to the revenue assessment of a village<BR>along with another; cf. Ardhaṭi-prāveśya-Lavaṅgasikāyām (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XV, p. 143); same as praveśa. Cf. Hastiśīrṣa-prāveśya-<BR>Tāpasapottake with Siviḍi-praveśa-Kandalivāḍa-grāma interpreted<BR>as ‘Kandalivāḍa-grāma having its rent assessed along with<BR>Siviḍi.’ Same as prāpīya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 109); cf. Akṣa-<BR>saraka-prāveśya used in the sense as Akṣasaraka-prāpīya.<BR>Cf. praveśa, prāveśa, prāpīya (LP), also patra-pṛṣṭhato praveśyo<BR>dātavyaḥ, ‘should get [the sum] entered at the back of the docu-<BR>ment’ (dātavya from dā ‘to cut’).<BR>Cf. a-prāveśya, etc. (IE 8-5); entrance.<BR>(IE 8-8; EI 30), an entry tax or levies relating to the<BR>entry of royal agents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रव्रजित|प्रव्रजितः<BR>pravrajita (CII 1; LL), a Buddhist monk; an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रव्रजिता<BR>pravrajitā (LL), a Buddhist nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रयाणदण्ड<BR>prayāṇa-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 25, 26), cf. rājasevakānāṃ vasati-<BR>daṇḍa-prayāṇa-daṇḍau na staḥ; refers to the obligation of the<BR>villagers to provide free conveyance and carriage of loads, etc.,<BR>when royal officers passed through their village. Prayāṇa thus<BR>seems to mean ‘passage, transit’, and daṇḍa ‘levy’; cf. rūḍhabhāroḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रयोजन|प्रयोजनं<BR>prayojana (LP), need; cf. drammaiḥ hasta-prāptaiḥ prayojanaṃ<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-264" target="_blank">Page-264+ 40</a>]<BR>jāyate (LP), ‘when there is a necessity of having the money<BR>back [before the stated time].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रायोपवेशाधिकृत<BR>Prāyopaveś-ādhikṛta (HD), officer who watched those that<BR>had resolved to fast unto death at the palace gate. See Rājata-<BR>raṅgiṇī, VI. 14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रयुक्त|प्रयुक्तं<BR>prayukta (IA 15), ‘drawn up’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेगडा<BR>Pregaḍā (EI 9), Kannaḍa; a minister. Cf. Pĕrgaḍĕ, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेषण|प्रेषणं<BR>preṣaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 9, text lines 13-14), service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेक्षणक|प्रेक्षणकं<BR>prekṣaṇaka (EI 22), a show.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेषणिक<BR>Preṣaṇika (IE 8-3), officer in charge of the despatch of<BR>messengers; the dispatcher of messengers; cf. Praiṣaṇika, Vaik-<BR>ṣepika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेष्यकुल<BR>Preṣya-kula (EI 33), a batch of workers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेतदक्षिणा<BR>preta-dakṣiṇā, cf. peta-dakkhinā (EI 24), a gift to one's dead<BR>ancestors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रियदर्शिन्<BR>Priyadarśin (CII 1), cf. Priyadasi (EI 5), secondary name<BR>of the Maurya king Aśoka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रो<BR>Pro, abbreviation of Prohita = Sanskrit Purohita (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXX, p. 192).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रोहत<BR>Prohata, Prohita (Chamba, etc.) a priest; from Sanskrit<BR>Purohita.<BR>Cf. Para.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृड<BR>pṛḍa, see mṛḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृष्ठ|पृष्ठं<BR>pṛṣṭha, cf. pṛṣṭhe hastaḥ (LP), ‘hand on someone's back’;<BR>a sign of warning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृथिवी<BR>pṛthivī, cf. Prakrit sava-puṭhaviyaṃ (CII, Vol. I, p. 87, text<BR>line 7); used to indicate the dominions of the Maurya emperor<BR>Aśoka, versions other than Dhauli (Rock Edict V) having<BR>sarvatra vijite (i. e. ‘everywhere within the dominions’) in its<BR>place. Cf. Jambudvīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृथ्वी<BR>pṛthvī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृथ्वीलिङ्ग<BR>pṛthvī-liṅga (SII 2), a Śivaliṅga made of earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रुड्<BR>pruḍ, see mṛḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पु<BR>pu (PJS), abbreviation of putra, ‘a son’ (especially in<BR>medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजा<BR>pūjā (CII 1; ML), an honour; the act of honouring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजाहारि<BR>Pūjāhāri (EI 33), same as Pūjāri (Sanskrit pūjādhārin); priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजक|पूजकः<BR>Pūjaka (SITI), one who performs worship; a temple priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजामात्य<BR>Pūj-āmātya (IA 11), official designation; cf. ‘the Pūj-āmātya<BR>of the province of Timbāṇaka’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुजारि<BR>Pujāri (EI 5, 15), a priest; a temple priest; called Pūjārī<BR>or Pūjāhārī (Sanskrit Pūjādhārin) in the early medieval records<BR>of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजाशिला<BR>pūjā-śilā (EI 16, 22), same as śālagrāma-śilā (the stone<BR>emblem of Viṣṇu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजावृत्ति<BR>pūjā-vṛtti (SITI), tax-free land endowed to a temple for<BR>conducting worship. Cf. tala-vṛtti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुक्कोलि<BR>pukkoli, pukkolli, pukkūli (IE 8-8), cf. pukkoli-kṣetra, explain-<BR>ed as ‘an arecanut palm plantation’. An inscription of Kadamba<BR>Mṛgeśvarman seems to suggest that it really means ‘land in-<BR>undated by floods’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 152). See khajjana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुक्कोलिखज्जन<BR>pukkoli-khajjana (EI 33), a type of land; see khajjana and<BR>pukkoli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुक्कोलिक्षेत्र<BR>pukkoli-kṣetra (EI 33), a type of land like khajjana; see<BR>pukkoli or pukkoli-khajjana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूलक|पूलकः<BR>pūlaka (CII 4), a small bundle (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुनर्जन्मन्<BR>Punarjanman (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 290, text line 3),<BR>used in the sense of Dvijanman (i. e. a Brāhmaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्डरीक|पुंडरीक|पुंडरीकं|पुण्डरीकं|पुण्डरीकः<BR>puṇḍarīka (CII 3; BL), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्याहवाचक<BR>puṇyāha-vācaka (EI 11), a priest who officiates in a cere-<BR>mony and proclaims by means of mantras a happy day to the<BR>ceremony and its performer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्याहवाचन|पुण्याहवाचनं<BR>puṇyāha-vācana (IA 14), a ceremony; cf. puṇyāha-vācaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्यवाचन<BR>puṇya-vācana (IA 21), a purificatory rite [in Madras]; cf.<BR>puṇyāha-vācana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुर|पुरं|पुरः<BR>pura, a temple (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 184). See bhavana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूरक|पूरकः<BR>pūraka (CII 3; etc.), used as a termination of the names<BR>of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुराण|पुराणं|पुराणः<BR>purāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 12, 21, 29), name of a coin; a silver<BR>coin also called dharaṇa and kārṣāpaṇa (32 or 24 ratis); cf. kapar-<BR>daka-purāṇa (EI 26), meaning purāṇa calculated in cowrie-<BR>shells; also paṇa-purāṇa (i. e. purāṇa counted in copper paṇas).<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 246), the Purāṇa texts, e. g.<BR>the Āditya Purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुराणलक्षण<BR>purāṇa-lakṣaṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरपालोपरिक<BR>Purapāl-oparika (IE 8-2, 8-3; BL), official designation pro-<BR>bably indicating the governor of a city or chief amongst the<BR>governors of cities; called Mahārāja, Mahāsāmanta, Mahāprati-<BR>hāra, Mahāpīlupati, Pañcakaraṇoparika and Pāṭyuparika addition-<BR>ally (IE 8-3). The expression may also mean two different<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-266" target="_blank">Page-266+ 40</a>]<BR>designations, viz. Purapāla and Uparika. With Purapāla, cf. Pura-<BR>pati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरपति<BR>Purapati (EI 25), mayor of a town; cf. Pura-pradhāna,<BR>Puraśreṭhin, Nagara-śreṣṭhin, Purillaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरप्रधान<BR>Pura-pradhāna (CII 4), mayor of a city; cf. Purapati,<BR>Puraśreṣṭhin, Nagara-śreṣṭhin, Purillaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरश्रेष्ठिन्<BR>Pura-śreṣṭhin (EI 25), official designation; same as Nagara-<BR>śreṣṭhin, Pura-pradhāna, Purapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरतोभद्र<BR>puratobhadra (EI 9), probably, a building with only one<BR>gate in the front side.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरिल्लक<BR>Purillaka (EI 29; CII 4), explained as ‘the mayor of a town.’<BR>Cf. rāja-sāmanta-viṣayapati-grāmabhogika-purillaka-cāṭa-bhaṭa-sevak-<BR>ādin (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, pp. 114-15); also Deśillaka and<BR>Pura-pati, Pura-pradhāna, Pura-śreṣṭhin, Vīthillaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्ण|पूर्णः<BR>pūrṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्णघटकपट्ट<BR>pūrṇaghaṭaka-paṭṭa (LL), slab bearing the representa-<BR>tion of a flower-vase.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्णिमान्त<BR>pūrṇimānta (CII 3, etc.), the technical name for the scheme<BR>of the lunar months in Northern India, according to which<BR>the months end with the full-moon day, and the dark fortnights<BR>precede the bright; Fleet states that in astronomical works, it<BR>is always the amānta arrangement that is actually taken for<BR>calculations though, even in Southern India, the pūrṇimānta<BR>arrangement was used with the Śaka years, for the civil reckoning,<BR>up to between 804 and 866 A. D.; on the other hand, according<BR>to him, even in Northern India, it was not used with the Newar<BR>era in Nepal, though it was adopted there when the Newar<BR>era was followed by the Vikrama era in its northern variety.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोग|पुरोगः<BR>Puroga (EI 23), prominent among a particular class of<BR>people; sometimes wrongly taken to be the same as Purohita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोहित|पुरोहितः<BR>Purohita (CII 4; SII 1; BL; ASLV; HD), a priest; a<BR>family priest; the royal priest; occurs in the list of functionaries<BR>in records like those of the Gāhaḍavālas (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p.<BR>305) and Senas (ibid., Vol. XII, p. 9). See Hist. Dharm., Vol.<BR>III, pp. 111-12, 117.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोनायक<BR>Puro-nāyaka (IE 8-3; EI 28), the chief Nāyaka; probably<BR>the same as Paṭṭa-nāyaka or Puro-Parīkṣaka; cf. Nāyaka. Puro<BR>may really be the modification of a Dravidian word (cf.<BR>Tamil Poṟṟu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोपरीक्ष<BR>Puro-parīkṣa (EI 28, 31), probably, the same as Paṭṭa-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-267" target="_blank">Page-267+ 40</a>]<BR>parīkṣaka, ‘the chief superintendent’; the chief superintendent<BR>of a department. Puro may really be the modification of a<BR>Dravidian word (cf. Tamil Poṟṟu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोप्रतिहस्त<BR>Puro-pratihasta (EI 31), probably, ‘the chief representa-<BR>tive’. Puro may really be the modification of a Dravidian word<BR>(cf. Tamil Poṟṟu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोश्रीकरण<BR>Puro-śrīkaraṇa (EI 31), probably, ‘the chief secretary’.<BR>Puro may really be the modification of a Dravidian word (cf.<BR>Tamil Poṟṟu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुष|पुरुषः<BR>Puruṣa (IE 8-3), same as Rāja-puruṣa, ‘royal officer or agent.’<BR>(HD) an inferior servant (Arthaśāstra, II. 5) or a bailiff<BR>attached to a court of justice (as in Bṛhaspati). See Hist.<BR>Dharm., Vol. III, p. 278.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषच्छाय<BR>puruṣa-cchāya (EI 14), name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषाकार<BR>puruṣ-ākāra (SITI), human form.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषारिक<BR>puruṣārika, cf. ardha-puruṣārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषार्थ|पुरुषार्थः<BR>puruṣ-ārtha (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषोत्तमपुत्र<BR>Puruṣottama-putra (EI 33), epithet of one devoted to the god<BR>Puruṣottama-Jagannātha of Purī. See Rudra-putra, Durgā putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषयुग<BR>puruṣa-yuga, cf. Prakrit purisa-yuga (EI 20); a generation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषायुस्<BR>puruṣ-āyus (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्व|पूर्व्व|पूर्व्वः<BR>pūrva (IE 7-1-2), sometimes used to indicate ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वा|पूर्व्वा<BR>pūrvā (IE 8-8; CII 4; ML), ‘the above’; ‘the aforesaid<BR>(tithi or praśasti)’; used with reference to a tithi and a praśasti;<BR>sometimes wrongly used as a synonym of a tithi or praśasti.<BR>Cf. anupūrvī used with reference to a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वाचार<BR>pūrv-ācāra (SII 3; SITI), an old usage or ancient<BR>custom. Cf. pūrva-rīti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वाग्रहारिक<BR>Pūrv-āgrahārika (EI 23), the former holder of an agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वमर्यादा<BR>pūrva-maryādā (ASLV), ancient constitutional usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वराज<BR>pūrva-rāja (EI 17), a king of eastern countries or of early<BR>times.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वरीति<BR>pūrva-rīti (LP), old custom. Cf. pūrv-ācāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वसिद्धायतन<BR>pūrva-siddh-āyatana (EI 33), epithet of a Buddhist temple;<BR>see siddh-āyatana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्कल|पुष्कलं|पुष्कलः<BR>puṣkala (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity usually regarded<BR>as equal to sixtyfour handfuls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्कर|पुष्करं|पुष्करः<BR>puṣkara (ML), a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्प|पुष्पं<BR>puṣpa (IE 8-8), a coin having the shape or sign of flower.<BR>Cf. a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa (IE 8-5), flowers which<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-268" target="_blank">Page-268+ 40</a>]<BR>the villagers (probably, the florists) were obliged to supply to<BR>the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्पक|पुष्पकं<BR>puṣpaka (CII 4), a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्त|पुस्तं<BR>pusta (CII 4), painting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तक|पुस्तकं|पुस्तकः<BR>pustaka, cf. Tamil pottagam (SITI); register, as of land and<BR>revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तकभाण्डार<BR>Pustaka-bhāṇḍāra (EI 25), a library.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तकपाल<BR>Pustakapāla (IE 8-3; EI 6, 29), record-keeper; same as<BR>Pustapāla; cf. Peṭapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तपाल|पुस्तपालः<BR>Pustapāla (IE 8-3; EI 28; CII 4; HD), record-keeper;<BR>occurs in epigraphs like the Damodarpur plates of the Gupta<BR>age (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 13; cf. Vol. XX, p. 61).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्यराग|पुष्यरागः<BR>puṣya-rāga (SITI), same as puṣpa-rāga; a kind of gem.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्यरथ|पुष्यरथः<BR>puṣya-ratha (EI 3), a car. Cf. puṣpa-ratha or puṣpaka-ratha,<BR>the celestial car.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुटि<BR>puṭi (EI 33), same as puṭṭi or puṭṭidosillu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूति|पूतिः<BR>pūti (EI 12, 14), also read as yūti; cf. tṛṇa-pūti (or yūti)-<BR>go-cara-paryanta, epithet of a gift village. The expression tṛṇa-<BR>pūti or tṛṇa-yūti may mean ‘grass-land’. The word is some-<BR>times written as yutī and yuthī also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्र|पुत्त्रः|पुत्रः<BR>putra, cf. Nigama-putra (LL), ‘the inhabitant of a nigama<BR>(township).’<BR>Cf. Durgā-putra, Puruṣottama-putra, etc.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), probably confused with pāṇḍu-putra and used<BR>to indicate ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रसूनु<BR>putra-sūnu (SII 2), used in the sense of pautra, ‘son's son’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुट्टि<BR>puṭṭi (CITD), Telugu; a measure equal to twenty tūmus;<BR>also called khaṇḍi (spelt candy in English and found as khaṇḍikā<BR>in Sanskrit inscriptions) and regarded as equal to between 800<BR>and 1000 seers. Khaṇḍi at Masulipatam has 3 weights, viz.<BR>488 pounds for tobacco, 500 pounds for metals, hardware, etc.,<BR>and 560 pounds for sugar, dates and other soft articles. The<BR>puṭṭi and its fractions also denote the area of the land that is<BR>supposed by some to produce the particular quantities of<BR>grain. According to some, it is a land measure equal to 8<BR>acres being presumably the area which can be sown with a<BR>puṭṭi of grain. There were different kinds of puṭṭis, e. g. gāl-<BR>puṭṭi. Cf. also pelle-puṭṭi regarded as equal to 80 kuñcas and<BR>Malaca-puṭṭi or Malacca ton as equal to 300 to 240 kuñcas.<BR>(EI 4, 27), a land and grain measure.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-269" target="_blank">Page-269+ 38</a>]<BR>(IE 8-5), same as Telugu puṭṭi-dosillu, ‘a fee of two hand-<BR>fuls from each puṭṭi of grain paid to the village-servants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुट्टिदोसिल्लु<BR>puṭṭi-dosillu (EI 33), a levy; see puṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्योडा<BR>pyoḍā (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piṭha, piḍā,<BR>peḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रा<BR>Rā (LP), abbreviation of Rājaputra, Rāuta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राभस्य|राभस्यं<BR>rābhasya (CII 1), a crime.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राच्छपोच्छ<BR>rāccha-poccha (LP), Gujarātī; household furniture.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रचित|रचितः<BR>racita (CII 3; etc.), composed; a technical term used in<BR>connection with the composition of a record, as opposed to the<BR>writing on the plate or slab for facilitating the work of engrav-<BR>ing and also to engraving. Cf. cintita in Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 59.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रद|रदः<BR>rada (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राधा<BR>rādhā (EI 8), a posture of standing with the feet a span<BR>apart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राधान्त<BR>rādhānta (EI 3), same as siddhānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राग|रागः<BR>rāga (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहापयति<BR>rahāpayati (LP), ‘he keeps’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राहसिक<BR>Rāhasika (IE 8-3; EI 27, 30), same as Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.;<BR>a privy councillor; a private secretary or adviser.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहसिनियुक्त<BR>Rahasi-niyukta (IE 8-3), a private secretary; same as<BR>Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहस्य|रहस्यं<BR>Rahasya (IE 8-3; EI 3-6, 23, 27, 30), a private secre-<BR>tary; same as Rāhasika, Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहस्याधिकृत<BR>Rahasy-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 6, 27, 30; SITI; HD), a<BR>privy councillor or private secretary; same as Rahasya, Rāhasika,<BR>Rahasi-niyuka, etc.; cf. also Vaiśvāsika, Paramaviśvāsin Mahāpara-<BR>maviśvāsin, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 7; Vol. VI, p. 13;<BR>Vol. XXII, p. 298.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राहुत<BR>Rāhuta, Rāhutta (IE 8-2), same as Rāvata = Sanskrit Rāja-<BR>putra; a title of nobility.<BR>(IA 20), also called Rāuta; explained as ‘a horseman.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राहुत्तरायन्<BR>Rāhutta-rāyan (SITI), Sanskrit Rājaputra-rājan; title of<BR>nobility; explained as ‘a cavalry officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रैक्वाल<BR>Raikvāla (Chamba), the king's personal servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज|राजः<BR>Rāja (LP), abbreviation of Rājaputra (Rājpūt); explained<BR>as a cavalry-soldier or a Rājpūt. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-270" target="_blank">Page-270+ 40</a>]<BR>143-44, where it is probably an abbreviation of Rājakula (Rāval).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभाग<BR>rāja-bhāga (LP), government revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभण्डार<BR>rāja-bhaṇḍāra (SITI, ASLV), Sanskrit rāja-bhāṇḍāra;<BR>royal treasury or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभोग|राजभोगः<BR>rāja-bhoga (EI 12), also rāja-sambhoga; dues enjoyed by<BR>the king or land belonging to the king's Khās Mahāls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजदण्ड|राजदण्डः<BR>rāja-daṇḍa (SII 1), punishment imposed by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजदत्ति<BR>rāja-datti (EI 23), a royal gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजदौवारिक|राजदौवारिकः<BR>Rāja-dauvārika (EI 2; BL), door-keeper of the royal<BR>palace (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 115). See Dauvārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजधानी<BR>rājadhānī (EI 23), the capital; sometimes used to indicate<BR>the headquarters of a chief or governor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाधिराज|राजाधिराजः<BR>Rājādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 21, 22, 30; CII 3, 4), title of<BR>paramount sovereignty; an imperial title meaning ‘the king of<BR>kings’; used in the Gupta period in some metrical passages,<BR>both alone and along with Rājarājādhirāja. Cf. Adhirājarāja<BR>(EI 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाध्यक्ष<BR>Rājādhyakṣa (IA 12; SII 11-2), official designation;<BR>probably the same as Rājasthānīya, literally, ‘an officer acting<BR>for the king.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजद्रोह|राजद्रोहः<BR>rāja-droha (SITI), treason against the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजद्वार<BR>rāja-dvāra (EI 32), king's court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजग्रह<BR>rāja-graha (IE 8-8); apprehension or recruitment in the<BR>king's name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजगृह<BR>rāja-gṛha, cf. Tamil rāja-karam (SITI); palace (cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107) or government; officers or autho-<BR>rities; also the taxes due to the same. Cf. rājakaraṅ-kāṇikkai,<BR>‘customary presents to be made to the palace’; rājakara-upādi,<BR>‘tax payable to the palace or to the government officers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजगुरु|राजगुरुः<BR>Rājaguru (EI 21, 27, 30; CII 4; BL; ASLV; HD),<BR>king's preceptor. Cf. Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354; Ind. Ant.,<BR>Vol. XII, p. 120.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजहुण्डिका<BR>rāja-huṇḍikā (LP), the royal bill of exchange.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाज्ञाप्रद<BR>Rājājñāprada (EI 27), probably, the same as Ājñapti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकदैवक<BR>rājaka-daivaka (LP), calamities owing to the king or the<BR>gods; cf. rājaka-daivaka-vaśāt (LP).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकर|राजकरः<BR>rāja-kara, cf. rāja-garam (ASLV), taxes in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकार्य|राजकार्य्य<BR>rāja-kārya (SITI), duties of the state; official work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकार्यभाण्डार<BR>rājakārya-bhāṇḍāra (SITI; ASLV), a treasury related to<BR>state business; an official committee of management.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकीय|राजकीयः<BR>rājakīya (LP), government tax.<BR>Cf. samasta-rājakīyānām = apraveśya (IE 8-5); same as<BR>Rāja-puruṣa or Rāja-sevaka; also Rāja-satka; an officer of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकीयमान<BR>rājakīya-māna (EI 23), same as rāja-māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकुल<BR>Rājakula (IE 8-5; CII 3; IA 20; BL; HD), royal house-<BR>hold; the king, royal officers and members of the royal family.<BR>Originally, ‘the royal family’; then ‘a member of the royal<BR>family’; and then ‘a royal officer’; later, a title of nobility, same<BR>as modern Rāval or Rāul. See Bhandarkar's List, No. 324.<BR>Cf. rājakulaṅ-kāṇi-ppaṟṟu (SITI), ‘land or village in the<BR>enjoyment of the members of the royal family’. The expres-<BR>sion occurs along with devadāna, brahmadeya, paḻḻiccandam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकुमार|राजकुमारः<BR>Rājakumāra (IE 8-3; LL; HD), same as Rājaputra; desig-<BR>nation of a prince. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजलिपिकर<BR>Rāja-lipikara (IE 8-3; EI 2; LL), king's scribe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजमान<BR>rāja-māna (IE 8-6; EI 12, 23, 28; SII 11-1), royal<BR>measure; the standard measure fixed or accepted by the king<BR>or government; same as rājakīya-māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजमाङ्गलीयक<BR>rāja-māṅgalīyaka (LP), auspicious occasions for the royal<BR>family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजामात्य<BR>Rāj-āmātya (EI 26; CII 3; HD), Prakrit Rāy-āmaca; the<BR>king's minister. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 91; CII, Vol.<BR>III, pp. 213, 216.<BR>(IE 8-3), sometimes used to indicate the ministers of the<BR>feudatory rulers; see Amātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजमुद्राधिकारिन्<BR>Rājamudr-ādhikārin (BL), official designation indicating<BR>the keeper of the royal seal or a governor. Cf. Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजन्<BR>Rājan (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HD), royal title;<BR>originally used by imperial rulers; later, when emperors assumed<BR>more dignified titles, a title of feudatories and smaller rulers.<BR>Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 121; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 297.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजनक<BR>Rājanaka (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 23, 29), same as Rājānaka,<BR>Rājanyaka, Rājānika; a feudatory; in some cases, smaller than<BR>the feudatory called Rājan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजानक|राजानकः<BR>Rājānaka (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; BL; HD), same as Rājanaka,<BR>Rājanyaka, Rājānika or Rāṇaka; title of feudatory rulers or of<BR>the nobility; often a feudatory smaller than a Rājan. Cf. Rāja-<BR>taraṅgiṇī, VI. 117, 261 (title given for services to the king and<BR>surviving in the form Rāzdān as a family name of Kashmir Brāh-<BR>maṇas); Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, pp. 394, 306.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजानिक<BR>Rājānika (EI 1), same as Rājanaka, Rājānaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाङ्क<BR>rāj-āṅka (EI 22), brand of royal animals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजन्य|राजन्यः<BR>Rājanya (ASLV; SITI), officers of the king.<BR>(IA 22), same as Kṣatriya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजन्यक|राजन्यकं<BR>Rājanyaka (IE 8-2; EI 15, 23, 29; HD), same as Rājanaka,<BR>Rājānaka, Rājānika or Rāṇaka, title of subordinate rulers. Cf.<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपं<BR>Rāja-paṃ (BL), abbreviation of Rāja-paṇḍita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपण्डित<BR>Rāja-paṇḍita (EI 32), a court Pandit; a scholar patronised<BR>by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपरमेश्वर<BR>Rāja-parameśvara (EI 4, 20), imperial title. Cf. Rāja-<BR>rājaparameśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपातिका<BR>rāja-pātikā (EI 1), royal procession.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपट्ट|राजपट्टः<BR>rāja-paṭṭa, cf. rāja-paṭṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपट्टी<BR>rāja-paṭṭī (EI 4; BL), royal fillet or tiara; status of a<BR>ruler or a feudatory indicated by turban. Same as rāja-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपुरुष|राजपुरुषः<BR>Rājapuruṣa (IE 8-5), a royal agent or officer; same as<BR>Rāja-sevaka or Rājakīya; cf. also Rāja-satka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपुत्र|राजपुत्त्रः|राजपुत्रः<BR>Rāja-putra (EI 30; CII 3; 4; HD), originally ‘a prince’;<BR>title of princes and subordinate rulers; but later a title of nobi-<BR>lity especially in the modified forms Rāvata, Rāuta, etc.; some-<BR>times also used in the sense of ‘a Rājpūt’ often explained as ‘a<BR>horse-man’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321. See Rāja-<BR>putraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपुत्रक<BR>Rāja-putraka (EI 17), same as Rāja-putra; mentioned in<BR>the list of subordinates and officials addressed by the king in<BR>respect of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजप्रदेय<BR>rāja-pradeya (SII 3), taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजप्रासादचैत्यक<BR>rājaprāsāda-caityaka (LL), a small caitya in the royal palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराज|राजराजः<BR>Rājarāja (IE 8-2; LL), imperial title; cf. Greek Basileos<BR>Besileon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजपरमेश्वर<BR>Rājarāja-parameśvara (EI 4), imperial title. Cf. Rājapara-<BR>meśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजार्घिका<BR>rāj-ārghikā (IE 8-8; EI 30), name of a levy; probably,<BR>periodical offerings to the king or the king's share of articles<BR>sold in the markets.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजर्षि|राजर्षिः<BR>Rājarṣi (EI 22), a sage-like king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसामन्त<BR>Rājasāmanta (EI 25), a Rājan and a Sāmanta, or one feuda-<BR>tory enjoying both the designations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसम्भोग<BR>rāja-sambhoga (EI 12), same as rāja-bhoga (q. v.); land<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-273" target="_blank">Page-273+ 40</a>]<BR>belonging to the king's Khās Mahāls (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p.<BR>46). Cf. ratnatraya-sambhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसत्क<BR>Rāja-satka (IE 8-3; EI 29), literally, ‘one belonging to<BR>the king’, i. e. ‘a servant of the king’; same as Rāja-puruṣa or<BR>Rāja-sevaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसेवक<BR>Rāja-sevaka (IE 8-5), same as Rāja-puruṣa, Rājakīya or<BR>Rāja-satka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसिद्धान्त<BR>rāja-siddhānta (EI 24), science of polity; same as rājanīti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजश्रावित<BR>rāja-śrāvita (EI 6; IA 19), a royal decree or proclamation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाश्रय<BR>rāj-āśraya (IA 8), the capital; same as rājadhānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजश्रेष्ठिन्<BR>Rāja-śreṣṭhin (HD), king's banker or the chief of the<BR>bankers. See Commentary on the Yaśastilaka, I, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थान<BR>Rājasthāna, same as Rājasthānīya and Rājasthān-ādhikāra<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 292).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानाधिकार|राजस्थानाधिकारः<BR>Rājasthān-ādhikāra (IE 8-3), probably, the chief justice;<BR>cf. Rājasthānīya (a viceroy), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानी<BR>Rājasthānī, dialect of Hindī prevalent in Rajasthan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानीय|राजस्थानीयः<BR>Rājasthānīya (IE 8-3; EI 24, 26, 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD),<BR>‘an officer acting for the king’; generally a viceroy; probably<BR>also a subordinate ruler; but cf. Rājasthān-ādhikāra who was<BR>also a judge; an official title indicating a viceroy in some areas<BR>and a judge in others; an officer who carried out the object<BR>of protecting subjects, according to some (Ind. Ant., Vol. V,<BR>p. 207). Cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 157; Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p.<BR>112; Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 176 (probably, a chief justice),<BR>explained wrongly as ‘an officer connected with other kings,<BR>i. e. a foreign secretary’ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 122, note 76).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानोपरिक<BR>Rājasthān-oparika (EI 29), probably a viceroy; cf. Rājas-<BR>thānīya and Uparika. See Rājasthān-ādhikāra and Rājas-<BR>thānīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसूय|राजसूयः<BR>rājasūya (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्व|राजस्वं<BR>rājasva (SITI), property belonging to the king or state<BR>[by confiscation, etc.].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजातिराज<BR>Rājātirāja (IE 8-2; EI 21, 26, 30; ML), imperial title of<BR>certain foreign rulers; cf. Basileos Basileon Megalou.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवैद्य<BR>Rāja-vaidya (IE 8-3; LL), physician to the king; the royal<BR>physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजावली<BR>rāj-āvalī (EI 9; IA 30), genealogy of rulers; a list of<BR>lineal succession of kings.<BR>(EI 10), royal titles; cf. rājāvalī pūrvavat (IE 8-2), ‘the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-274" target="_blank">Page-274+ 40</a>]<BR>royal titles as above’, often used when a repetition of the string<BR>of royal titles was avoided. Cf. Paramabhaṭṭārak-ety-ādi-rāj-āvalī-<BR>tray-opeta referring to the imperial titles Paramabhaṭṭāraka,<BR>Mahārājādhirāja and Parameśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवल्लभ|राजवल्लभः<BR>Rāja-vallabha (EI 6, 9, 24; CII 4), explained as ‘a court-<BR>favourite’; a courtier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजावर्त|राजावर्तः|राजावर्त्त|राजावर्त्तः<BR>rājāvarta (SII 2; SITI), a kind of gem; lapis lazuli; same<BR>as vaiḍūrya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवर्त्मन्<BR>rāja-vartman (EI 22), a public road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवेश्याभुजङ्ग<BR>Rāja-veśyā-bhujaṅga (SITI), ‘the lover of the courtesans<BR>of the [enemy] kings’; a title assumed by some kings after cap-<BR>turing the enemies’ countries, probably describing rājya-śrī as<BR>a prostitute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजविलासिनी<BR>rāja-vilāsinī, king's courtesan (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजविषय<BR>rāja-viṣaya (CII 1), a king's dominions. Cf. Rājaviṣayādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजविषयाध्यक्ष<BR>Rājaviṣay-ādhyakṣa, explained as ‘the royal superintendent<BR>of a district’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 234); but rāja-viṣaya<BR>in this case may be the king's Khās Mahāls so that the designa-<BR>tion means ‘the superintendent of the king's Khās Mahāls.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजयोग|राजयोगः<BR>rāja-yoga (EI 12), a particular auspicious moment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जू<BR>rajjū (HRS), used in the Arthaśāstra probably in the sense<BR>of the cost realised by the government in connection with the<BR>expenses of land-measurement or survey.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जुग्राहकामात्य<BR>Rajjugrāhak-āmātya (IE 8-3), same as Rajjuka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जुक|रज्जुकः<BR>Rajjuka (IE 8-3; HD), Prakrit Rajuka or Lajūka (EI 2);<BR>an officer of the land survey and revenue department, accord-<BR>ing to some; but seems to be the governor of a district, one of<BR>whose functions was probably the survey of land with a measur-<BR>ing rope for the fixation of the amount of the king's share of<BR>the produce; probably the same as Greek Agronomoi mentioned<BR>by Megasthenes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जुप्रतिहार<BR>Rajju-pratihāra (EI 24), ‘rope-jugglers or dancers’; cf.<BR>rajju-pratihār-āpaṇa, ‘booths of rope-jugglers and dancers’; but<BR>rajju-pratihār-āpaṇājīvika may be a tax for maintaining surveyors<BR>and gate-keepers (toll-collectors) and from shop-keepers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्ञी<BR>Rājñī (IE 8-2; EI 26; CII 3; HD), a queen; a title of the<BR>wives of paramount sovereigns and subordinate rulers; cf. Mahā-<BR>rājñī, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रजोहरण<BR>rajo-haraṇa (HA), same as ogho (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्य|राज्यं<BR>rājya (IE 8-4; EI 19), district or province of a kingdom;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-275" target="_blank">Page-275+ 40</a>]<BR>(SITI; ASLV), the biggest administrative unit of the Vijaya-<BR>nagara empire; same as pīṭhika; also means ‘sovereignty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्याभिषेक|राज्याभिषेकः<BR>rājy-ābhiṣeka (IA 10), coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्यचिन्तक<BR>Rājya-cintaka (EI 11; BL), a minister or the chief admi-<BR>nistrator; same as Rājyacintākārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्यचिन्ताकारिन्<BR>Rājyacintākārin (EI 1), a minister or the chief adminis-<BR>trator; same as Rājya-cintaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्याधिकृत<BR>Rājy-ādhikṛta (EI 22, 23), chief minister; cf. Rājyādhikārin;<BR>also cf. rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राकाशशाङ्क<BR>rākā-śaśāṅka (SII 1), same as rākā-viṭa; the full-moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रकतपटा<BR>rakata-paṭā (JBORS, Vol. XVIII, pp. 219-20), Oḏiyā;<BR>Sanskrit rakta-paṭṭaka, same as rakta-mānya; also called sira-<BR>kaṭā tambā-paṭā in Oḏiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राकाविट<BR>rākā-viṭa (SII 1), same as rākā-śaśāṅka; the full moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षा<BR>rakṣā (EI 17), confirmation of a former grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षाभोग<BR>rakṣā-bhoga (EI 9), same as rāja-bhoga, the king's share.<BR>(SITI), a fee or a share in the produce given to the village<BR>watchman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षामणि|रक्षामणिः<BR>rakṣā-maṇi (EI 15), protecting jewel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षण|रक्षणं<BR>rakṣaṇa, cf. doṣa-vināś-āvaṣṭabdhi-rakṣaṇāya (LP), ‘for keeping<BR>it safe from the three faults, viz. doṣa, vināśa and avaṣṭabdhi’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षणीय<BR>rakṣaṇīya (LP), ‘to be [prepared and] maintained.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तबिन्दु|रक्तबिन्दुः<BR>rakta-bindu (SII 2), a flaw in diamonds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तमान्य<BR>rakta-mānya, cf. Tamil iratta-mānya, iratta-kkāṇikkai (SITI);<BR>‘blood-present’; endowment of rent-free land for the support<BR>of the descendants of warriors killed in battle; same as<BR>mṛtyuka-vṛtti. See rudhira, rakatapaṭā, vīra-śeṣā, etc. See Ind. Arch.<BR>Rev., 1960-61, Section III, No. 42.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तपट्टक<BR>rakta-paṭṭaka, see rakata-paṭā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तिका<BR>raktikā (IA 27), same as ratī or guñjā (q. v.); a unit of<BR>measurment; about 1-825 grains or 119 grammes in weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राम|रामं|रामः<BR>rāma (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रामनन्दन<BR>rāma-nandana (EI 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रामानुजकूट<BR>rāmānuja-kūṭa (SITI), a rest house for Vaiṣṇava tra-<BR>vellers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्घ्|रंघ्<BR>raṅgh (CII 1), ‘to be eager’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राण|राणं<BR>Rāṇa (EI 16, 23), same as Rāṇaka; see Rāṇa-putra, rāṇa-kula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणा<BR>Rāṇā (IE 8-2; EI 23, 30), derived from Rāṇaka; title of<BR>ruling chiefs; same as Rāṇa, Rāṇaka.<BR>Cf. Rannā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणक<BR>Rāṇaka (IE 8-2; EI 23, 30; CII 4; BL; HD), derived<BR>from Rājanaka, Rājānaka or Rājanyaka; a feudatory title; title<BR>of feudatory rulers and, later, of the nobility. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XVII, p. 321.<BR>(EI 9), explained as ‘the chief counsellor’.<BR>(EI 1), title of the great artist Śūlapāṇi described as<BR>Vārendraka-śilpi-goṣṭhī-cūḍāmaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणकचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Rāṇaka-cakravartin (EI 33), feudatory title; cf. Mahā-<BR>sāmantādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणकुल<BR>rāṇa-kula (LP), same as rāja-kula (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रणरणक|रणरणकः<BR>raṇaraṇaka (LP), anxiety.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रणस्तम्भ|रणस्तंभ|रणस्तम्भः<BR>raṇa-stambha (CII 3, 4), a victory-pillar; a column in<BR>memory of the victory in a battle; same as jaya-stambha.<BR>(BL), a memorial pillar raised for a person who died<BR>fighting for his master on the battle-field; same as vīra-kkal (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणपुत्र<BR>Rāṇa-putra (BL), also called Rāṇa-utra; literally, ‘the son<BR>of a subordinate king’; a title of nobility. See Rāja-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणौत्र<BR>Rāṇa-utra (BL), see Rāṇa-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्ध्र|रंध्र|रंध्रं<BR>randhra (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘nine’; used in the sense of<BR>‘cypher’ in a few late works.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्ध्रपूरक<BR>Randhrapūraka (CITD), probably, a musician who played<BR>on some kind of wind instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्ग|रंग|रङ्गं|रंगः|रङ्गः<BR>raṅga (E I 15), abbreviation of raṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गभोग<BR>raṅga-bhoga (EI 17), amusement to be arranged for a<BR>deity and land granted for it; also called śṛṅgāra-bhoga (EI 5).<BR>(CITD), enjoyment of splendour other than aṅga-bhoga<BR>or personal decoration; gift land received for raṅga-bhoga. See<BR>aṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गलेख<BR>raṅga-lekha (LP), ‘coloured letter’; probably refers to the<BR>custom of sprinkling saffron water on the letters addressed to a<BR>king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गमण्डप|रंगमंडप|रङ्गमण्डपः<BR>raṅga-maṇḍapa (SITI), inner hall of a temple; same as<BR>Tamil tiruv-araṅgu.<BR>(HA), same as sabhā-maṇḍapa; main hall in a shrine.<BR>(EI 9), hall in front of a shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गाङ्गभोग<BR>raṅg-āṅga-bhoga (EI 3), same as aṅga-raṅga-bhoga (i. e.<BR>raṅga-bhoga and aṅga-bhoga), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गत्<BR>raṅgat (EI 12), ‘rolling’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणी<BR>Rāṇī (EI 23, 33), feminine from of Rāṇa or Rāṇā (i. e.<BR>Rāṇaka); designation of a queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्ना<BR>Rannā, name of the Sun-god's wife in West Indian my-<BR>thology; probably a modification of Rājñī. See Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXII, p. 343. The name is also spelt Raṇṇā or Rāṇā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्नेश<BR>Ranneśa, a name of the Sun-god; cf. Rannā. See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXII, p. 343. The name of the Sun-god worshipped at<BR>Thanwala near Pushkar was Rannāditya (also spelt Raṇṇāditya<BR>and Rāṇāditya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशि|राशिः<BR>rāśi (IA 17), a sign of the zodiac.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR>Cf. rāśi-ppon (SITI), also called rāśi-paṇam; explained as<BR>‘pure gold’; probably, ‘current good coin.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिमित्र<BR>Rāśi-mitra (EI 32), a friend of one, because of the birth<BR>of both under the same rāśi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिपण<BR>rāśi-paṇa, also called rāśi-ppon (SITI); probably ‘current<BR>good coins’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रश्मि|रश्मिः<BR>raśmi (IE 7-1-2), probably confused with śīta-raśmi and<BR>used to indicate ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्र|राष्ट्रं<BR>rāṣṭra (IE 8-3, 8-4; EI 9, 23; CII 4; LL), a district or<BR>its subdivision; often the subdivision of a district; cf. Śātavāha-<BR>nīya-rāṣṭra; also Kona-rāṣṭra (EI 32), variously called deśa, maṇḍala,<BR>sīma, sthala, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रग्रामकूट<BR>Rāṣṭra-grāma-kūṭa (EI 28), i. e. Rāṣṭrakūḷa and Grāmakūṭa;<BR>cf. Rāṣṭra-grāma-mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रग्राममहत्तर<BR>Rāṣṭra-grāma-mahattara (IE 8-3; EI 6, 28), i. e. Rāṣṭra-<BR>mahattara and Grāma-mahattara; cf. Rāṣṭra-grāma-kūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रकूट<BR>Rāṣṭrakūṭa (EI 8-3), same as Rāṣṭra-mahattara; either the<BR>officer in charge of a territorial unit called rāṣṭra or, more pro-<BR>bably, a member of the administrative council of a rāṣṭra; cf.<BR>Grāma-kūṭa; also Deśakūṭa (IA 7).<BR>(EI 9), interpreted as ‘the headman of a village’.<BR>(EI 24), according to some, a land-holder.<BR>(CII 4; HD), interpreted as ‘the head of a district or sub-<BR>division’; cf. JBBRAS, Vol. XVI, p. 117.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रमहत्तर<BR>Rāṣṭra-mahattara (IE 8-3), same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa; either the<BR>head of a territorial unit called rāṣṭra or, more probably, a<BR>member of the administrative council of a rāṣṭra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रमहत्तराधिकारिन्<BR>Rāṣṭramahattar-ādhikārin (EI 25), official designation;<BR>probably, Rāṣṭramahattara and Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रपाल|राष्ट्रपालः<BR>Rāṣṭrapāla (HD), head of a district, province or subdivi-<BR>sion; same as Rāṣṭrapati. See Arthaśāstra, V. 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रपालक<BR>Rāṣṭrapālaka (EI 28), ruler of an administrative unit called<BR>rāṣṭra; same as Rāṣṭrapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रपति|राष्ट्रपतिः<BR>Rāṣṭrapati (EI 12, 25; HD), ruler of a province, district<BR>or subdivision called rāṣṭra; same as Rāṣṭrapāla. Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. IV, pp. 278, 285; Vol. VII, p. 39.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रविषय<BR>rāṣṭra-viṣaya (IE 8-4), originally, a rāṣṭra, but later a<BR>viṣaya; cf. Karma-rāṣṭra-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रिक|राष्ट्रिकः<BR>Rāṣṭrika (IE 8-3; CII 1; HD; LL), Prakrit Raṭhika (EI 2),<BR>Raṭṭhika (EI 7); same as Rāṣṭrin; ruler of a rāṣṭra, i. e. a district<BR>or its subdivision; also the name of a people called ‘hereditary<BR>Rāṣṭrikas’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5; Bhandarkar, Aśoka, p. 30.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 78), mentioned in the list of<BR>officials addressed by the king in respect of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रिन्<BR>Rāṣṭrin (EI 7), ruler of a rāṣṭra; same as Rāṣṭrika. Cf.<BR>Rāṣṭrapati, Mahārāṣṭrin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रिय|राष्ट्रियः<BR>Rāṣṭriya (IE 8-3; LL; HD), same as Rāṣṭrika, ruler of a<BR>district or province; a provincial governor. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>VIII, p. 43; Pāṇini, IV. 2. 93; Mahābhārata, Śānti-parvan, 85. 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रीय|राष्ट्रीयः<BR>Rāṣṭrīya (IE 8-3), same as Rāṣṭriya; a provincial governor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रात<BR>Rāta (BL), modification of or mistake for Rāvata or Rāuta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथ|रथः<BR>ratha, rock-cut temples at Mahābalipuram (Journ. Mad.<BR>Univ., Vol. XXXII, p. 140).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथाध्यक्ष<BR>Rath-ādhyakṣa (EI 18), superintendent of chariots.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथकार|रथकारः<BR>Rathakāra (SITI), artisan classes; also their association.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथसप्तमी<BR>ratha-saptamī (EI 22; CII 4; IA 17), an auspicious tithi;<BR>same as Māgha śu-di 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथाष्टमी<BR>rath-āṣṭamī EI 29; CII 4; IA 17), same as Māgha śu-di 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथयात्रा<BR>ratha-yātrā (EI 11), a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथिक|रथिकः<BR>Rathika, superintendent of chariots (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XVIII, p. 156).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथोत्सव<BR>rath-otsava (EI 16), car-festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथ्या<BR>rathyā (EI 19), a street.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रति|रतिः<BR>rati, ratī (IE 8-8; IA 19), also spelt rattī; a small weight;<BR>see Sanskrit raktikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राटि|राटिः<BR>rāṭi (LP), ‘a cry’; cf. Gujarātī rāḏ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्न|रत्नं<BR>ratna (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’; sometimes also used to indicate<BR>‘nine’, and rarely even ‘fourteen’.<BR>(EI 22; CII 4), same as the Buddhist tri-ratna, i. e. the<BR>Buddha, Dharma and Saṅgha.<BR>(ML), a relic [of the Buddha].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नधेनु|रत्नधेनुः<BR>ratna-dhenu (EI 13, 16, 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नगृह<BR>ratna-gṛha (CII 3), ‘the jewel-house’; the house enshrining<BR>the three ratṅas, regarded by some as denoting a great Buddhist<BR>stūpa.<BR>(EI 19; LL), Buddhist; a sanctuary; the sanctuary of<BR>a Buddha image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नाश्व<BR>ratn-āśva (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नत्रय<BR>ratna-traya (EI 8), Jain; samyag-darśana, samyag-jñāna and<BR>samyak-cāritra.<BR>(EI 27, 30, 31), Buddhist; the tri-ratna or trinity; a<BR>Buddhist religious establishment enshrining the three ratnas;<BR>rent-free land in its possession (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 46).<BR>Cf. ratnatraya-sambhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नत्रयसम्भोग<BR>ratnatraya-sambhoga (HRS), traced in Bengal records; rent-<BR>free holding in the possession of Buddhist religious establishments<BR>where the Buddha, Dharma and Saṅgha were worshipped;<BR>same as ratna-traya. Cf. rāja-sambhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रट्टगुडि<BR>Raṭṭaguḍi (EI 30), same as Raṭṭoḍī; official designation;<BR>probably the same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रट्टगुल्लु<BR>Raṭṭaguḻḻu (EI 27), probably, the same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्ती<BR>rattī, see rati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रट्टोडि<BR>Raṭṭoḍi (EI 30), official designation; same as Raṭṭaguḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउ<BR>Rāu (IA 18), same as Rāva (Sanskrit Rājan) or abbrevia-<BR>tion of Rāuta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रौक्यद्र<BR>raukya-dra (LP), abbreviation of raukya-dramma; ‘drammas<BR>in cash’; cf. raukya with Gujarātī rokaḏā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउल<BR>Rāula (EI 24, 28), derived from Sanskrit Rājakula; title of<BR>nobility; same as Rāvata, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रौप्यटङ्क<BR>raupya-ṭaṅka, ‘silver ṭaṅka (q.v.)’. See JNSI, Vol. XXII,<BR>p. 197. According to Nārada, a silver kārṣāpaṇa was called<BR>raupya in South India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउत<BR>Rāuta (IE 8-2; EI 4, 28, 30, 31; CII 4; BL), same as<BR>Rāvata = Sanskrit Rājaputra; a title of feudatory rulers and<BR>noblemen.<BR>(IA 20), also called Rāhutta; explained as ‘a horseman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउत्त<BR>Rāutta (IE 8-2; EI 5, 30, 32), same as Rāuta or Rāvata =<BR>Sanskrit Rājaputra; a title of feudatories and noblemen. See Rāuta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राव|रावः<BR>Rāva (IE 8-2; BL), spelt in English as Rao; title of subor-<BR>dinate rulers and noblemen; derived from Sanskrit Rājan; cf.<BR>Rāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राव|रावः<BR>rāva (LP), a complaint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावल्<BR>Rāval (BL), title of subordinate rulers and noblemen;<BR>derived from Sanskrit Rājakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावल<BR>Rāvala (EI 24; BL), same as Rāval; derived from Sanskrit<BR>Rājakula; title of subordinate rulers and noblemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावणभुज<BR>rāvaṇa-bhuja (IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावणहस्त<BR>rāvaṇa-hasta (ASLV), a musical instrument; may also indi-<BR>cate ‘twenty’ (cf. rāvaṇa-bhuja).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावणशिरस्<BR>rāvaṇa-śiras (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावत्<BR>Rāvat (EI 32), a title of subordinate rulers and noblemen;<BR>same as Rājaputra, Rāuta, etc. See Rāvata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावत<BR>Rāvata (IE 8-2; BL), same as Rāvat; derived from Sanskrit<BR>Rājaputra; a title of feudatories and noblemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रवि|रविः<BR>ravi (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रविबाण<BR>ravi-bāṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रविचन्द्र<BR>ravi-candra (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावुतु<BR>Rāvutu (EI 21), same as Rāuta, Rāvata, etc.; derived<BR>from Sanskrit Rājaputra; a title of feudatories and<BR>noblemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राट<BR>Rāwa (EI 30), variant spelling of Rāva; derived from<BR>Sanskrit Rājan; title of nobility.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राय|रायः<BR>Rāya (IE 8-2; BL), title of nobility; derived from Sans-<BR>krit Rājan; cf. Rāva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायराउत<BR>Rāya-rāuta (EI 31), title of nobility; derived from Sanskrit<BR>Rāja-rājaputra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायराय<BR>Rāyarāya (EI 21), title of nobility; derived from Sanskrit<BR>Rājarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायरेख<BR>rāya-rekha (IA 15), a system of land measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायस<BR>Rāyasa (EI 3, 17; ASLV), Kannaḍa; a secretary; an<BR>officer in the Vijayanagara administration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायस<BR>rāyasa (ASLV), royal order.<BR>(SITI), office of a writer; clerkship; order of the king;<BR>written orders. Cf. Rāyasa-svāmin, head of the rāyasa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायसस्वामिन्<BR>Rāyasa-svāmin (ASLV), ‘the head of the rāyasa’ (SITI);<BR>the chief secretary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋद्धि|ऋद्धिः<BR>ṛddhi (EI 3), supernatural power.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋद्धिपाद<BR>ṛddhi-pāda, cf. iddhi-pāda (EI 5), Buddhist; four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेड्डि<BR>Reḍḍi (ASLV), a village official.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेखा<BR>rekhā (EI 19), a land measure.<BR>Cf. rekai, rekai-ppon (SITI), irekai; regarded as the name<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-281" target="_blank">Page-281+ 40</a>]<BR>of a gold coin (probably bearing signs in straight lines); used<BR>in Vijayanagara inscriptions; probably, revenue income in cash.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेखादण्ड<BR>rekhā-daṇḍa (EI 14), name of a linear measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेष<BR>reṣa (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रिन्तकावड्डि<BR>rintakāvaḍḍi (EI 33), name of a levy; cf. antarābaḍḍi or<BR>āturā-baḍḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रिपु|रिपुः<BR>ripu (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋषिपञ्चमी|ऋषिपंचमी<BR>ṛṣi-pañcamī (EI 23), same as Bhādrapada su-di 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रीतिकार<BR>Rītikāra (EI 32), a brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोचयितव्य<BR>rocayitavya (CII 1), ‘should be liked’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोचीक<BR>rocīka (IE 8-5), a tax or obligation of uncertain<BR>import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोहण|रोहणं|रोहणः<BR>rohaṇa (SITI), function performed at the commence-<BR>ment of a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोही<BR>rohī (IA 11), Pañjābī; uplands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोक|रोकं|रोकः<BR>roka (Chamba), cash. See rūka under rū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋषि|ऋषिः<BR>ṛṣi (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋतु|ऋतुः<BR>ṛtu (EI 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रू<BR>rū (IE 8-1), abbreviation of rūpaka or rūpyaka.<BR>(CITD), abbreviation of Telugu rūka meaning ‘cash’<BR>and probably derived from Sanskrit rūpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूढभारोडि<BR>rūḍhabhāroḍi (HRS), system of forced carriage of loads as<BR>indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. Cf. prayāṇa-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुधिर|रुधिरं|रुधिरः<BR>rudhira, cf. Tamil udira-paṭṭi (SITI), literally, ‘blood-land;’<BR>land given to the descendants of a person who fell fighting<BR>on the king's behalf; see also rakta-mānya, mṛtyuka-vṛtti, rakta-<BR>paṭṭaka and vīra-śeṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्र|रुद्रः<BR>Rudra (SITI), a Śaiva devotee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्र|रुद्रः<BR>rudra (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रदामक<BR>rudradāmaka, ‘silver coin (kārṣāpaṇa) issued by Rudra-<BR>dāman’; name of the silver coins issued by the Śaka rulers of<BR>Western India (JNSI, Vol. XIII, pp. 1 7 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रगण|रुद्रगणः<BR>Rudra-gaṇa (SITI), devotees of Śiva, their managing com-<BR>mittee looking after the affairs of a Śiva temple and being<BR>known as Rudragaṇa-pperumakkaḻ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रगणिका<BR>Rudra-gaṇikā (SITI), a dancing woman attached to a Śiva<BR>temple; a devadāsī serving in a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रमाहेश्वर<BR>Rudra-māheśvara (SITI; ASLV), the two classes of Śaiva<BR>devotees, known as the Rudras and Māheśvaras; designation of<BR>the authorities of a Śaiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रपुत्र<BR>Rudra-putra (EI 33), epithet of one devoted to the god<BR>Śiva. See Durgā-putra, Puruṣottama-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रास्य<BR>rudr-āsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुण्डा<BR>Ruṇḍā, cf. Mahāruṇḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुन्द्र<BR>rundra (IA 6, 10), cf. guṇa-rundra, an epithet of Jinendra;<BR>also cf. Himavad-girīndra-rundra-śikhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप|रूपं<BR>rūpa (HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) a subsidiary<BR>charge in excess of the prescribed fines; (2) a charge upon<BR>mines and upon imported salt. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp.<BR>94, 106.<BR>(IE 8-8; EI 20, 21), currency or coins; name of a<BR>silver coin; same as rūpya or rūpaka.<BR>(EI 1), an animal.<BR>(CII 1), a representation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपदक्ष<BR>Rūpa-dakṣa, cf. Prakrit lupa-dakha (EI 22), a painter or<BR>sculptor. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 30.<BR>(LL), explained by some as ‘a copyist’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपदर्शक<BR>Rūpa-darśaka (EI 20, 21; HD), an examiner of coins. See<BR>Arthaśāstra, II. 5. Cf. Pārikh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपक|रूपकं<BR>rūpaka (IE 8-8; EI 30; CII 4), name of a coin of silver; cf.<BR>kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka (EI 25; CII 4), a silver coin issued by the<BR>Kalacuri king Kṛṣṇarāja; silver coin (1/16) of the value of a gold<BR>dīnāra in the Gupta age (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 5); same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकार|रूपकारः<BR>Rūpakāra (EI 8; BL), a sculptor; epithet of a sculptor.<BR>See Rūpakāraka, Rūpakārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकारक<BR>Rūpakāraka (LL), a sculptor; same as Rūpakāra, Rūpakārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकारिन्<BR>Rūpakārin (EI 5), a sculptor; same as Rūpakāra, Rūpakāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकर्मन्<BR>rūpa-karman (LL), carving.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुपेए<BR>rupee, Anglicised form of rūpīa (q. v.); derived from Sans-<BR>krit rūpyaka. See JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 142.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपीअ<BR>rūpīa (IE 8-8), same as rūpya or rūpyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपिक|रूपिकः<BR>rūpika (HRS), tax on the sale of salt; one of the sources<BR>of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev.<BR>Syst., pp. 25, 92, 106.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप्यक<BR>rūpyaka (IE 8-8), same as rūpaka, rūpīa, rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स|सं|सः<BR>sa (IE 8-1), also written as saṃ; abbreviation of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सा<BR>Sā (EI 32), abbreviation of Sādhanika (q. v.).<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-283" target="_blank">Page-283+ 40</a>]<BR>(PJS), abbreviation of Sāhu or Sādhu, designation of a<BR>member of the mercantile community often used in medieval<BR>inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शब्द|शब्दः<BR>śabda, same as mahā-śabda; cf. pañca-śabda (BL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाब्दिक|शाब्दिकः<BR>śābdika (BL), a grammarian.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभा<BR>sabhā (SII 2; SITI; ASLV), same as mahāsabhā; the body<BR>of the Mahājanas; the assembly of a Brāhmaṇa village of the<BR>Tamil-speaking area, such an assembly of a non-Brāhmaṇa<BR>village being called ūr; local assembly of a Brāhmaṇa village;<BR>same as Tamil kuṟi.<BR>(EI 22), the Buddhist saṅgha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभामध्यम<BR>sabhā-madhyama (SITI), the village common or waste<BR>land in the village belonging to the sabhā; also called sabhai-<BR>ppodu, ūr-ppodu, ūr-mañjikkam, sabhā-mañjikkam, etc., in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभामण्डप|सभामण्डपः<BR>sabhā-maṇḍapa (HA), same as raṅga-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभाविनियोग<BR>sabhā-viniyoga (SITI), individual share payable to make<BR>up the expenses of the sabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सब्रह्मचारिन्<BR>Sabrahmacārin (CII 3), a religious student of a group that<BR>follows the same śākhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साचित्त<BR>sācitta (LP), probably, ‘land attached to government ser-<BR>vants as long as they serve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सचिव|सचिवः<BR>Saciva (EI 33; BL; HD), minister or counsellor. See<BR>Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 105, note 150.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साद|सादः<BR>sāda (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदक<BR>sadaka, cf. upari-sadaka, explained as ‘the upper region’<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI. p. 234).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदासेवा<BR>sadā-sevā, cf. Tamil sadā-servai, sadā-sevai (SII 1; SITI);<BR>constant service; permanent service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षडशीति|षडशीतिः<BR>ṣaḍaśīti (IA 19), same as mithuna-rāśi (Gemini).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षडायतन<BR>ṣaḍ-āyatana, cf. Prakrit ṣaḍ-ayadana (CII 2-1), the six organs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षड्भाग|षड्भागः<BR>ṣaḍ-bhāga, cf. dharma-ṣaḍ-bhāga (Sel. Ins., p. 348, text line<BR>16), one-sixth of the merit for a pious work done by the subjects,<BR>which goes to the king. See ibid., p. 344, text line 3.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधाचार्य<BR>Sādhācārya (IA 12), assistant to the officiating priest at<BR>the Rāmeśvaram temple; also called Adhyayana-bhaṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधन|साधनं<BR>sādhana (IE 8-3; EI 24; LP), an army, cf. sādhana-sahasra-<BR>aikam, an army consisting of one thousand men.<BR>(EI 15), an army, or money.<BR>(SII 12), cf. mūla-sādhana, the original deed; also called<BR>mūla-olai in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधनिक<BR>Sādhanika (CII 4), a general; same as Sāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधनिन्<BR>Sādhanin (EI 23), explained as a ‘a councillor’; but really,<BR>the same as Sādhanika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधार<BR>sādhāra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 177), either a mistake<BR>for sādhāraṇa, ‘common’, or means ‘together with the adjacent<BR>grounds’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधारण|साधारणः<BR>sādhāraṇa (IA 20), used in the sense of laukika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सधर्मिवात्सल्य<BR>sadharmi-vātsalya (HA), attachment to or service of the<BR>followers of one's own faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सध्र्यग्विहारिन्<BR>sadhryagvihārin (LL), doubtful Sanskritisation of Pāli<BR>saddhi-vihārin (Sanskrit sārdhaṃvihārin under the influence of<BR>sādhya), companion of a Buddhist monk. Cf. Jain<BR>Sārdhaṃcara, Sārdhaṃcarī (LL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधु|साधुः<BR>Sādhu (EI 9), a priest.<BR>(HA), a Jain monk.<BR>(LP; HA), same as Sāhu, a merchant.<BR>(CII 1), an adjective meaning ‘good’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साध्वी<BR>Sādhvī (JHA), a Jain nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साध्य|साध्यः<BR>sādhya (IE 8-5; EI 15; SITI), a type of income; income from<BR>land that may be brought under cultivation in future; one of<BR>the eight kinds of enjoyment of property. See aṣṭa-bhoga, siddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साध्यपाल<BR>Sādhyapāla (HD), a bailiff who summoned parties and<BR>witnesses. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 278.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साद्यस्क्र|साद्यस्क्रः<BR>sādyaskra (EI 22; CII 3; etc.), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगर|सगरः<BR>sagara (IE 7-1-2), confused with sāgara and rarely used<BR>to indicate ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सागर|सागरः<BR>sāgara (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; used in the sense of ‘seven’ by<BR>some late writers (IA 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगोत्र|सगोत्रं|सगोत्रः<BR>Sagotra (CII 3, etc.), belonging to the lineage of the person<BR>from whom the gotra name is derived.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहदेश<BR>Sahadeśa (IA 17), also called Sahadeśin, ‘belonging to the<BR>same country’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहगमन<BR>sahagamana (ASLV), self-immolation of a widow on the<BR>funeral pyre of her husband; same as satī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहजकवि<BR>Sahaja-kavi (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 231, note 1), epithet<BR>of a poet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणि<BR>Sāhaṇi (IE 8-3), also called Sāhiṇi, etc.; derived from<BR>Sanskrit Sādhanika; cf. Gaja-sāhiṇi, etc.<BR>(EI 15), see Paṭṭa-sāhaṇi, Peyiya-sāhaṇi, Maleya-sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहानी<BR>Sāhānī (EI 33), same as Sādhanika, Sāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणिअ<BR>Sāhaṇia (IE 8-3), Prakrit form of Sādhanika from sādhana<BR>or army; cf. the modern family name Sāhnī. Same as<BR>Sāhaṇiya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणिकाटि<BR>sāhaṇikāṭi (SII 11-1), supposed to be the name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणिय<BR>Sāhaṇiya (EI 11), Prakrit form of Sādhanika; same as<BR>Sāhaṇia, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहानुषाहि<BR>Sāhānuṣāhi (IE 8-2; EI 19, 22, 30), title of the Kuṣāṇa<BR>kings, derived from Old Persian Kshāyathiyānām Kshāyathiya;<BR>same as modern Persian Shāhān Shāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शहर्<BR>śahar, Persian shahr, a town (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp.<BR>145-46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहस|साहसं|साहसः<BR>sāhasa (CII 4), a violent crime.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहसाधिपति|साहसाधिपतिः<BR>Sāhasādhipati (HD), a judicial or police officer. See Śukra,<BR>I. 120.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहसमल्लाङ्क<BR>sāhasamallāṅka (BL), epithet of a year of the Kalacuri<BR>era probably through confusion, as normally the expression<BR>would mean the Vikrama era.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहस्रांशु|सहस्रांशुः<BR>sahasr-āṃśu (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहस्रायतन<BR>sahasr-āyatana (EI 29), epithet of a temple; literally, ‘having<BR>one thousand rooms or shrines’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहि<BR>Sāhi, Śāhī (IE 8-2; EI 30; LL), same as Persian Shāh,<BR>Old Persian Kshāyathiya; royal title used by some Indian rulers<BR>of foreign origin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहिजादा<BR>Sāhijādā (BL), title of a prince; same as Persian Shāhzādah.<BR>See Sāhiyādā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहीकरी<BR>sahī-karī (Chamba), ‘having approved; having got ap-<BR>proved; having put the signature on’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहिल्य<BR>sāhilya (IA 23), same as bhāṇḍāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहिणि<BR>Sāhiṇi (IE 8-3; EI 32), same as Sanskrit Sādhanika (q. v.),<BR>interpreted as ‘the master of the royal stables’ (BL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहितीविद्या<BR>sāhitī-vidyā (EI 13), same as sāhitya, literature.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहित्य|साहित्यं<BR>sāhitya, cf. sāhitī-vidyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहियादा<BR>Sāhiyādā (BL), title of a prince; same as Persian Shāhzādah.<BR>See Sāhijādā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साह्नी<BR>Sāhnī (IE 8-3), modern family name derived from Sans-<BR>krit Sādhanika = Prakrit Sāhaṇia, Sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहोदर|सहोदरः<BR>sahodara (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’ possibly referring to Kuntī's sons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहु<BR>Sāhu (LP), same as Sanskrit Sādhu; a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैबर<BR>śaibara, cf. sa-śaibaram (EI 17); a levy in kind according<BR>to some; but see saivara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सइका<BR>saïkā (EI 28), Sanskrit śatikā; a levy per one hundred<BR>articles; one payable in a hundred articles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैल|शैलं|शैलः<BR>śaila (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलदेवगृह<BR>śaila-devagṛha (EI 24), a stone temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलगृह<BR>śaila-gṛha (LL), a cave.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलकर्मन्<BR>śaila-karman (LL), stone-work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलालक<BR>Śailālaka (EI 1; LL), same as Śilālin, an actor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलरूपकर्मन्<BR>śaila-rūpakarman (LL), stone-carving.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलवर्धकिन्<BR>Śaila-vardhakin (LL), cf. Prakrit Sela-vaḍhākī (EI 20); a<BR>stone mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैनिकसङ्घमुख्य<BR>Sainika-saṅgha-mukhya (EI 22), official designation; pro-<BR>bably, a general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैन्य|सैन्यं|सैन्यः<BR>sainya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 71), probably, an adminis-<BR>trative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैन्याधिकारिन्<BR>Sainy-ādhikārin (IE 8-3), same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैन्यपति<BR>Sainyapati (IE 8-3), same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवाचार्य<BR>Śaiv-ācārya (CII 4), an ascetic of the Śaiva sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवाचार्यक्षेत्र<BR>śaivācārya-kṣetra (SITI), tax-free land endowed to a Śaiv-<BR>ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवदीक्षा<BR>śaiva-dīkṣā (EI 32), initiation into the Śaiva faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवर<BR>śaivara, a revenue term; cf. śaibara; a levy in kind accord-<BR>ing to Ghoshal (H. Rev. Syst., p. 220); but probably the same as<BR>Marāṭhī śerī, ‘arable land originally excluded from the village<BR>assessment’ (Wilson's Glossary); may also be a tax on farm-<BR>houses (cf. śibara).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक|शकः<BR>Śaka (EI 24), originally, the Seythians; later any foreigners<BR>including Muhammadans; used to indicate the Musalmans<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 44; Bhandatkar's List, No. 926).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक|शकः<BR>śaka, śāka (IA 9, 19), used in the sense of ‘a year’ or ‘an<BR>era’; cf. Vikrama-śaka (IA 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक|शाकं|शाकः<BR>śāka, cf. a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa (EI 8-5); vegetables<BR>which the villagers were obliged to supply to the king or land-<BR>lord on occasions or to the touring officers. Cf. śāka-śaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साका<BR>sākā (IA 29), Rājasthānī; same as jauhar or javhar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाकम्भरीविद्या<BR>śākambharī-vidyā (EI 29; CII 4), name of a science, the<BR>nature of which is uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शकानिका<BR>Śakānikā (CII 4), a Śaka woman. Cf. anikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाकपणिका<BR>śāka-paṇikā, cf. śāka-paṇikā-nyāyena (LP), ‘like vegetables in<BR>a market’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकरुकर<BR>sakarukara, occurs in a Śātavāhana inscription probably for<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-287" target="_blank">Page-287+ 40</a>]<BR>Sanskrit sa-kar-otkara meaning the same thing as s-odraṅga-<BR>s-oparikara, ‘with the udraṅga (kara) and uparikara (utkara)<BR>taxes’; may also be sa-kārukara. See kāru-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाखा<BR>śākhā (CII 3, 4; IA 18, 19), literally, ‘a branch’; a Vedic<BR>school following any particular recension of the Vedas.<BR>(LL), a section of the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्र|शक्रः<BR>śakra (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्रध्वज|शक्रध्वजः<BR>śakra-dhvaja, cf. indra-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्रयज्ञ<BR>śakra-yajña (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्रोत्थान|शक्रोत्थानं<BR>śakr-otthāna (EI 32), a festival, same as śakradhvaj-<BR>otthāna. Cf. śakra-dhvaja, indra-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साक्षिन्<BR>Sākṣin (EI 3, 23; SITI), a witness; an eye-witness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सक्षीणारम्भ<BR>sa-kṣīṇ-ārambha (CII 1), gentle in action.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सक्त|सक्तः<BR>sakta (LP), written for satka, ‘belonging to’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्ति|शक्तिः<BR>Śakti (EI 17), name of the wife of Kāmadeva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्ति|शक्तिः<BR>śakti (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘three’; three in number (EI 6).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्तिमुख<BR>śakti-mukha, (SITI), cf. śatti-mugam; king's order; probably<BR>the same as śrīmukha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्तित्रय<BR>śakti-traya (SII 1), the three [regal] powers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक्य|शाक्यः<BR>Śākya (CII 1), a Buddhist; see Śākya-bhikṣu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक्यभिक्षु|शाक्यभिक्षुः<BR>Śākya-bhikṣu (BL; LL), epithet of a Buddhist monk; same<BR>as Śākya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक्योपासिका<BR>Śāky-opāsikā (LL), a female member of the Buddhist laity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाला<BR>śālā (EI 4; SII 1), a hall.<BR>(EI 4; SITI), a school; same as pāṭha-śālā.<BR>(SII 3), cf. śālai (EI 7; SITI), an alms-house; a feeding<BR>house; cf. śālā-bhoga.<BR>Cf. śālai (EI 24), a hospital; cf. ārogya-śālā, ātura-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शालाभोग<BR>śālā-bhoga (SII 2; SII), same as Tamil arac-cālā-bhogam;<BR>land granted in favour of a feeding house (sattra-śālā). (EI 23),<BR>mentioned along with devadāna and brahmadeya; a rent-free hold-<BR>ing in the possession of a śālā meaning an almshouse or a school.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शलाका<BR>śalākā, cf. śalāgai (SITI), name of a coin also called palañ-<BR>śalāgai (accu) and śrīyakki-palañśalāgai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शालास्थानमुख्य<BR>Śālāsthāna-mukhya (EI 32), probably, officer in charge of<BR>the stables.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलाट<BR>Salāṭa (PJS), Gujarātī; also called Salāvaṭa; a stone-<BR>cutter or mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सालवी<BR>Sālavī (LP), Gujarātī; a weaver.<BR>(PJS), Gujarātī; a carpenter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शालीन|शालीनः<BR>Śālīna (CII 4), a kind of householder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलिलपूर्वक<BR>salila-pūrvaka (IA 9), same as udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सल्लेखना<BR>sallekhanā (EI 3, 6; SITI), Jain; a religious practice of<BR>the Jains; starving oneself to death; starving oneself to death<BR>in fulfilment of a vow; same as samādhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलोहित<BR>Sa-lohita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 295), ‘one having the<BR>same blood’; a relation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शल्यत्रय<BR>śalya-traya (SII 1), the three thorns.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सं|स|सः<BR>saṃ (IE 8-1), abbreviation of saṃbaddha, ‘attached to’,<BR>‘belonging to,’ etc.; possibly also saṃsakta, ‘relating to’ (JAS,<BR>Letters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR>(CII 3, 4), abbreviation of the word saṃvatsara, a year,<BR>or of its declensional cases that can be used in expressing a date.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सं|स|सः<BR>Saṃ (PJS), also written Saṃgha; contraction of Saṃghavī<BR>or Saṃghapati in medieval Jain inscriptions; same as the modern<BR>Jain family name Siṅghī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सां<BR>sāṃ (IE 8-1; LP), abbreviation of sāṃvatsarika, annual.<BR>See sāṃ-hi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शम्<BR>śam (ML) ‘to prevent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम|समः<BR>sama, cf. sam-ālindakam (LP), ‘with a terrace in front<BR>of the door.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाचर्य<BR>samācarya (CII 1), impartiality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाधि|समाधिः<BR>samādhi (CII 4), poetic quality of a composition.<BR>(EI 33), explained as a ‘granary’; probably ‘an agreement’.<BR>Cf. sallekhanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समधिगतपञ्चमहाशब्द<BR>Samadhigata-pañca-mahāśabda (IE 8-2; CII 3), a customary<BR>epithet of feudatory rulers, indicating that they were entitled<BR>to the privilege of the pañca-mahāśabda (five kinds of musical<BR>instruments), or of using five official titles beginning with the<BR>word mahā. There are a few instances in which the epithet<BR>is applied to paramount sovereigns in South India. The title<BR>is sometimes stated to have been conferred on a feudatory by<BR>his overlord. See mahāśabda, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाहर्तृ<BR>Samāhartṛ (EI 27; HD; HRS), official designation; ex-<BR>plained as ‘the collector-general’; officer in charge of the collec-<BR>tion of various branches of revenue; compared by Ghoshal with<BR>the Qānungo of Mughal times (H. Rev. Syst., p. 52). See Artha-<BR>śāstra, I. 12; II. 6; Śabara on Jaimini, XII. 1. 28; Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. VIII, p. 141; Vol. XI, p. 94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाज|समाजः<BR>samāja (EI 20; CII 1), a fair; a festival; a festive gather-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-289" target="_blank">Page-289+ 40</a>]<BR>ing on a particular occasion or for the celebration of an event.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाज्ञप्ति<BR>Samājñapti (EI 27), same as Ājñapti (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामक|सामकं|सामकः<BR>sāmaka (LP), ‘collectively’; cf. Gujarātī sāṃṭuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समकरग्राम<BR>samakara-grāma (LP), a village for which a permanent<BR>revenue is fixed at a particular rate, not to be increased in future.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समकरकुल<BR>samakara-kula (LP), family on which rent is fixed once<BR>for all; farmers that have to pay revenue at a particular rate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाक्रान्त<BR>samākrānta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20), used in some<BR>Orissan records probably in the sense of ‘endowed with boun-<BR>daries’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समम्<BR>samam (LP), ‘in the same way as’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समञ्जस|समंजस|समञ्जसं|समञ्जसः<BR>samañjasa (SITI), conformity; resemblance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समञ्जित<BR>Samañjita (SITI), accountant of a village or a village<BR>assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्त|समंत|समन्तः<BR>samanta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्त|सामंत|सामन्तः<BR>Sāmanta (IE 8-2; 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), title<BR>of feudatory rulers; a feudatory smaller than the Rājan; a sub-<BR>ordinate chief; also explained as ‘a minister’ (SITI). See<BR>Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 297. Cf.<BR>Mahāsāmanta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्त|सामंत|सामन्तः<BR>Sāmanta (CII 1), a neighbour; ‘one who is in possession<BR>of a piece of land in the neighbourhood of the gift land’ (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 220).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्तभद्र|समंतभद्र|समन्तभद्रः<BR>samantabhadra (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 199), prosperous<BR>on all sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्ताधिकारिन्<BR>Sāmant-ādhikārin (ASLV), see Sāmanta and Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्ताधिपति<BR>Sāmant-ādhipati (EI 16), cf. Mahāsāmant-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्तपडिरा<BR>Sāmanta-paḍirā (EI 32), Oḏiyā; Sanskrit Sāmanta-pratirāja;<BR>title of a feudatory or nobleman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्तिक<BR>sāmantika, derived from Sāmanta; chiefship (A.R. Ep.,<BR>1958-59, p. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्थु<BR>samanthu (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामान्य|सामान्यं<BR>sāmānya, cf. traividya-sāmānya (EI 23), cāturvedya-sāmānya;<BR>‘belonging to’; Valabhī-cāturvidya-sāmānya, ‘one of the Catur-<BR>vedins of Valabhī’; used also in the sense of vāstavya, ‘resident<BR>of … ’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 172, 176).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समारचन<BR>samāracana, repairs (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समारण<BR>samāraṇa Prakrit used in Sanskrit for samāracaṇa (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXV, p. 59).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समरापणीय<BR>samarāpaṇīya (LP), to be got repaired; cf. Gujarātī samrā-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-290" target="_blank">Page-290+ 40</a>]<BR>vavuṃ; see samarcāpanīya, samāracana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समराप्य<BR>samarāpya (LP), ‘should be repaired’; cf. Gujarātī samrā-<BR>vatruṃ; also samāracana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समर्चापन<BR>samarcāpana (LP), repairing; cf. samarcāpanīya (LP), ‘to be<BR>got repaired’; cf. samarāpaṇīya; also samāracana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्त|समस्तं<BR>samasta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat especially in<BR>medieval Orissan records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तमहासामन्ताधिपति<BR>Samasta-mahāsāmant-ādhipati (BL), title of a feudatory ruler<BR>of the highest rank. See Mahāsāmant-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तसेनाधिपति<BR>Samasta-sen-ādhipati (EI 29, 30), ‘leader of all the forces’;<BR>commander-in-chief. See Sen-ādhipati, Senāpati, Manĕya-<BR>samasta-sainy-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तसुप्रशस्त्युपेत<BR>samasta-supraśasty-upeta (IE 8-2), a royal epithet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्त्येत्यादि<BR>samasty-ety-ādi (IE 8-2), shortened form of samasta-supra-<BR>śasty-upeta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्यापूरण<BR>samasyā-pūraṇa (CII 4), completion of incomplete verses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्<BR>samat (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत<BR>samata (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समता<BR>samatā (CII 1), impartiality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्त<BR>samatta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवाद|सामवादः<BR>sāma-vāda, cf. Prakrit sama-vāyo (CII 1), found in a rock<BR>edict of Aśoka; ‘restrained speech’; same as saṃyama (i.e.<BR>vāk-saṃyama) found in one version; generally sama-vāyo is<BR>taken as samavāya or concord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवाजिक<BR>Sāmavājika (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 135, note 6), probably,<BR>an officer; cf. Sāmavāyika, Sāmavājin, Sāṃmavājin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवाजीन्<BR>Sāmavājīn (EI 6), probably, an officer; cf. Sāṃmavājin, Sāmavājika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समवसरण<BR>samavasaraṇa (HA), congregation-hall believed to be<BR>built by celestials when a Tīrthaṅkara delivered his sermon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवायिक|सामवायिकः<BR>Sāmavāyika (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 135, note 6), probably,<BR>an officer; cf. Sāmavājika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समवेत|समवेतः<BR>samaveta (IE 8-3), ‘associated’; generally explained as<BR>‘assembled’; but see samupāgata, upeta, upayāta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समय|समयः<BR>samaya (EI 10), a religious system.<BR>(CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a sect; an assemblage, a<BR>company or congregation; established moral or ceremonial<BR>custom; cf. samaiyam (EI 24), a creed.<BR>Cf. samaye (EI 19), used instead of varṣe in the dates after<BR>saṃvat.<BR>(SITI), a religious mendicant; cf. Samay-mudali, religious head.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयाचार|समयाचारः<BR>samay-ācāra (SITI), religious usage; established custom; super-<BR>vision of the religious and social life of the people; censoring of<BR>public morals; also a class of officials called Samayācārya or Dāsari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयाचार्य<BR>Samayācārya (ASLV), also called Samayācāra; same as<BR>Dāśari; a censor of morals; a class of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयधर्म|समयधर्मः<BR>samaya-dharma (SITI), law of the samaya or agreement.<BR>The expression is generally used in relation to the organisation<BR>of merchants and agriculturists known respectively as Nānādeśīn<BR>and Citramel13i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयपत्र<BR>samaya-patra (SII 1; SITI; LP), an agreement; a docu-<BR>ment containing an agreement; a deed of agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामायिक<BR>sāmāyika (HA), remaining steadfast in worship or medi-<BR>tation (at least for 48 minutes), with the mind drawn away<BR>from attachments or ill will and abstaining from committ-<BR>ing sins, which is the daily duty of a Jain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बद्ध|संबद्ध|सम्बद्धः<BR>sambaddha (IA 15), ‘belonging to’ or ‘connected with’.<BR>Cf. Devadroṇī-sambaddha (IE 8-3), probably, superin-<BR>tendent of a temple property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बधना<BR>sambadhanā (LP), strong opposition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शम्बल|शंबल|शंबलं|शंबलः|शम्बलः<BR>śambala (LP), provisions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संभाल<BR>saṃbhāla (LP), care, protection; cf. Gujarātī saṃbal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्भार|संभार|संभारः|सम्भारः<BR>sambhāra (ML), provision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्भोग|संभोग|संभोगः|सम्भोगः<BR>sambhoga, cf. rāja-sambhoga, ratnatraya-sambhoga; same as bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्भोग|संभोग|संभोगः|सम्भोगः<BR>Sambhoga (LL), a section of the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बोधित<BR>sambodhita (LP), advised.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बुद्ध|संबुद्ध|सम्बुद्धः<BR>sambuddha (LP), one who is no longer a minor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संग्रहण|सङ्ग्रहण|संग्रहणं<BR>saṃgrahaṇa, adultery (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्हलातमक<BR>samhalātamaka, cf. samhalātamaka-samanvita (EI 9), mean-<BR>ing uncertain; may be a name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांहि<BR>sāṃ-hi, abbreviation of sāṃvatsarika-hiranya, ‘annual re-<BR>venue income in cash’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 55).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामीप<BR>sāmīpa (CII 1), a neighbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समिति|समितिः<BR>samiti (EI 4), five in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संकाचितक<BR>saṃkācitaka (EI 30), cf. poṭṭalikā-saṃkācitak-ādāna, ‘tax on<BR>bundles suspended from loops at both ends of a pole’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संमत्<BR>saṃmat (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्मत्<BR>sammat (ASLV), same as samuta; an administrative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांमवाजिन्<BR>Sāṃmavājin (EI 33), same as Sāmavājin, Sāmavājika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्मुखवार<BR>sammukha-vāra, probably, Sunday (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV,<BR>p. 115).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संम्वत्<BR>saṃmvat (EI 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्प्राप्ति|संप्राप्ति|संप्राप्तिः|सम्प्राप्तिः<BR>samprāpti, cf. sampirātti (SITI) ‘that which has been ob-<BR>tained’; ‘an acquisition’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्प्रति|संप्रति|सम्प्रतिः<BR>Samprati (SITI), senior accountant; the manager<BR>of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्प्रतिपत्ति|संप्रतिपत्ति|संप्रतिपत्तिः|सम्प्रतिपत्तिः<BR>sampratipatti (CII 1), proper behaviour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्राट्<BR>Samrāṭ (EI 19, 22; CII 3, 4), imperial title; a paramount<BR>sovereign.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संसरण|संसरणं<BR>saṃsaraṇa (CII 1), a house or road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांशयिक|सांशयिकः<BR>sāṃśayika (CII 1), ‘of doubtful value’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्कृत|संस्कृतं|संस्कृतः<BR>Saṃskṛta, see Sanskrit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्तव|संस्तवः<BR>saṃstava (CII 1), cf. dharma-saṃstava, ‘acquaintance<BR>through Dharma’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्था<BR>saṃsthā (HRS), king's dues derived from the market-<BR>place, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्तुत|संस्तुतः<BR>saṃstuta (CII 1), cf. mitra-saṃstuta-jñāti, ‘friends, acquin-<BR>tances and relatives’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्त<BR>samta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat. Mta = mat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदाय|समुदायः<BR>Samudāya (EI 25), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदाय|समुदायः<BR>samudāya (ASLV), same as gaṇa-bhoga; a tenure in which<BR>land is enjoyed by a group of people.<BR>(SITI), a village under the gaṇa-bhoga tenure.<BR>(SITI), village common; managing committee of<BR>a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदयबाह्य<BR>samudaya-bāhya (HRS), occurs in the Damodarpur ins-<BR>criptions; ‘revenue-free’ or ‘yielding no income’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदायप्राप्ति<BR>samudāya-prāpti, cf. samudāya-ppirātti (SITI), any acquisi-<BR>tion from the village to be enjoyed in common by the villagers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुद्र|समुद्रः<BR>Samudra (EI 10), an epithet of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुद्र|समुद्रः<BR>samudra (EI 16), same as sapt-āmbhodhi; name of a mahā-<BR>dāna; also means 4 (rarely 7).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुद्रघोष<BR>samudra-ghoṣa (EI 5), name given to a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समूह|समूहः<BR>samūha (EI 28; CII 4), an assembly; the assembly of a<BR>corporation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुपगत<BR>samupagata (EI 12), explained as ‘assembled at’; really,<BR>‘having connection with’, ‘associated with’; cf. samupagama,<BR>‘contact’; also samaveta, upeta, upayāta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुपागत<BR>samupāgata (IE 8-3), ‘associated’; often explained as<BR>‘assembled’; but cf. samaveta, samupagata, upayāta, upeta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुत<BR>samuta (ASLV), same as sammat; an administrative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुत्क्रीडा<BR>samutkrīḍā (EI 15), same as krīḍā or sport.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्व<BR>samva (IE 8-1), mistake for saṃva which is an abbreviation<BR>of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संव<BR>saṃva (IE 8-1) same as saṃvat; contraction of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवदन|संवदनं<BR>saṃvadana (IE 8-8), submission of information.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवर्तकल्प<BR>saṃvarta-kalpa (CII 1), the aeon of destruction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवास|संवासः<BR>saṃvāsa, cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-saṃvāsa (IE 8-5);<BR>same as āvāsa; shelter or accommodation [which the villagers<BR>were obliged to supply to the touring officers of the king].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्|संवन्त्<BR>saṃvat (IE 8-1), originally an abbreviation of saṃvatsara<BR>(a year) or any of its declensional cases that can be used in ex-<BR>pressing a date; later stereotyped in the sense of ‘a year’ or<BR>‘an era’. It was generally regarded as indeclinable; but we<BR>have some cases of the use of forms with case-endings, e. g.,<BR>saṃvataḥ, saṃvatā, saṃvati and saṃvatām. See also saṃvate (IE<BR>8-1), the seventh case-ending of saṃvata, a corrupt form of<BR>saṃvat. Since the late medieval age, the word specially indi-<BR>cates the Vikrama era, although originally it was used with the<BR>name of any reckoning in quoting the dates of records, especially<BR>the regnal reckoning. The word is used in inscriptions in a<BR>large number of corrupt forms, e. g., samvata, samvatta, samata,<BR>samanta, samatta, saṃmat, samasta, smat, samvatu, samvatū, etc., etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्वत्<BR>samvat (IE 8-1), mistake for saṃvat, originally an abbre-<BR>viation of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सर|संवत्सरः<BR>saṃvatsara (CII 3; 4; IA 17), ‘a year’; ‘an cra’, the<BR>earlier years of the Indian eras being quoted by this term (or<BR>by its abbreviations saṃ, saṃvat, etc.), without any dynastic or<BR>other appellation just as in the case of the year of a regnal<BR>reckoning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांवत्सर|सांवत्सरः<BR>Sāṃvatsara (HD), an astrologer. See Viṣṇu Dh. S., III.<BR>75; Bṛhatasaṃhitā, 2. 9; cf. Sāṃvatsarika (EI 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरप्रतिपदा<BR>saṃvatsara-pratipadā, name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरश्राद्ध<BR>saṃvatsara-śrāddha (CII 4), śrāddha performed on the first<BR>anniversary of a person's death.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरवारिय<BR>saṃvatsara-vāriya (SITI), annual committee appointed<BR>by the sabhā; annual committee for supervising the management<BR>of village affairs; also called āṭṭi-vāriyam (SITI) in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरविमोक्षश्राद्ध<BR>saṃvatsara-vimokṣa-śrāddha (CII 4), same as saṃvatsara-<BR>śrāddha performed on the first anniversary of a person's death.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांवत्सरिक|सांवत्सरिकः<BR>Sāṃvatsarika (HD), an astrologer. See Paiṭhīnasi quoted<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-294" target="_blank">Page-294+ 40</a>]<BR>in Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 193.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांवत्सरिकहिरण्य<BR>sāṃvatsarika-hiraṇya (IE 8-1), annual revenue in cash;<BR>often abbreviated as sāṃ-hi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्वत्त<BR>samvatta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्वतु<BR>samvatu, samvatū (IE 8-1), corrupt forms of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवतुं<BR>saṃvatuṃ (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संविभाग|संविभागः<BR>saṃvibhāga (CII 1), separation of one thing from another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संविद्<BR>saṃvid (EI 32), an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांविनयिक<BR>sāṃvinayika, cf. a-raṭṭha-sāṃvinayika (EI 1), a-rāṣṭra-sāṃ-<BR>vinayika (IE 8-5); administration or control, i. e. administrative<BR>control.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संव्यवहारिन्<BR>Saṃvyavahārin (EI 23), an administrator; same as Vyava-<BR>hārin; cf. Saṃvyavahāry-ādi-kuṭumbinaḥ (EI 24), the agricul-<BR>turist householders led by the village-headman or the collector<BR>of royal dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्य|साम्यं<BR>sāmya (EI 23), often written for svāmya; cf. leja-sāmya<BR>standing for tejaḥ-svāmya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्यक्प्रधान<BR>samyak-pradhāna, cf. sammappadhāna (EI 5), Buddhist;<BR>four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्<BR>san (IA 18), Arabic; a year; an era; sometimes used in<BR>Sanskrit records; in some cases, corrupted to sna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शण|शणं|शणः<BR>śaṇa (LP), linen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाण|शाणं|शाणः<BR>śāṇa, name of a weight or coin; a silver coin which was (1/8)<BR>of a śatamāna in weight and value; generally regarded as 40<BR>ratis in weight, but sometimes also as 32 or 24 or 20 ratis; also<BR>called niṣka, ṭaṅka or dharaṇa or śānaka. See JNSI, Vol. XVI,<BR>pp. 42, 44-45. See śāna-pāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानभोग<BR>Śānabhoga (IE 8-3), village-accountant; same as Senabova,<BR>etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानक<BR>śānaka, see śāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानपाद|शानपादः<BR>śāna-pāda, same as māṣa (JNSI, Vol. p. 47).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनाथ<BR>Sanātha (IA 7), wrongly supposed to mean ‘one whose<BR>father is alive’ or ‘a worthy’; actually, a personal name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चकार<BR>sañcakāra (IA 19), same as satyakāra; an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चरन्तक<BR>Sañcarantaka (HD), Prakrit; ‘a spy’. See Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>I, p. 5. Kauṭilya (Arthaśāstra, I. 12) speaks of Sañcāra (wander-<BR>ing spies like Tīkṣṇa, Rasada, etc.). Cf. Sañcārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चरत्क<BR>Sañcaratka (IE 8-3), a spy; cf. Sañcarantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चारिन्|संचारिन्<BR>Sañcārin (EI 24), cf. Śāsana-sañcārin and Ājñā-sañcārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चरित<BR>sañcarita, cf. ājñāta (IA 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षण्ड|षंड|षंडः|षण्डः<BR>ṣaṇḍa (IA 18), a bull living or wandering at liberty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षण्डगुल<BR>ṣaṇḍa-gula (LP), same as Gujarātī khāṃḍ-gol, i. e. sugar<BR>and molasses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धि|संधि|संधिः|सन्धिः<BR>sandhi (EI 4; SITI), literally, ‘twilight’; but actually,<BR>‘service in the temple in the morning and evening’; daily wor-<BR>ship in temples; special worship offered in the names of persons<BR>who arrange for it by creating endowments, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिपात<BR>sandhi-pāta, emergency (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 213).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकरण<BR>Sandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇa (CII 4), department of peace<BR>and war.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकरणाधिकृत<BR>Sandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇ-ādhikṛta (EI 30; BL), official desig-<BR>nation indicating a person in charge of the office of war and<BR>peace (i. e. foreign affairs); an officer of the ministry or the<BR>minister of foreign affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकरणकायस्थ<BR>Sandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇa-kāyastha, official designation of a<BR>scribe of the office of war and peace (i. e. foreign affairs).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकृत<BR>Sandhivigrah-ādhikṛta (CII 4; BL), an officer in charge of<BR>the department or the minister of war and peace; same as<BR>Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिकरण<BR>sandhi-[vigraha]-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); department of<BR>foreign affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहकारिन्<BR>Sandhivigrahakārin (EI 21), same as Sandhivigrahika. See<BR>Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 320.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहप्पेरु<BR>sandhivigraha-ppeṟu (EI 24; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; a fee<BR>payable to the village Madhyastha; also a fee payable to document-<BR>writers; cf. sandhivigrahi-paṇṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहिक<BR>Sandhivigrahika (HD), minister for peace and war. See<BR>Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 17; Mahābhārata, Śānti-parvan, 85.<BR>30. See Sāndhivigrahika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सान्धिविग्रहिक|सांधिविग्रहिक|सांधिविग्रहिकः<BR>Sāndhivigrahika (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD; LP),<BR>minister for peace and war, i. e. of foreign affairs; sometimes<BR>also called Khādya[kū]ṭapākika, Kumārāmātya, Mahādaṇḍanāyaka,<BR>etc., additionally; same as Sandhivigrahika, etc. See Viṣṇudhar-<BR>mottara, II. 24. 17; Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 320; CII,<BR>Vol. III, p. 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहिन्<BR>Sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3, SITI), minister in charge of peace<BR>and war; officer in charge of the foreign relations department,<BR>who was often the writer of important documents; same as<BR>Sandhivigrahika, etc. Cf. Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin (EI 16), Hĕri-<BR>Lāḻa-sandhivigrahin (EI 12), Hĕri-sandhivigrahin (EI 12), Lāḻa-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-296" target="_blank">Page-296+ 40</a>]<BR>sandhivigrahin (EI 12), Hĕri-Lāṭa-Karṇāta-sandhivigrahin, Hĕri-<BR>Lāṭa-sandhivigrahin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहिपण्णु<BR>Sandhivigrahi-paṇṇu (EI 30), name of a levy; same as<BR>sandhivigraha-ppeṟu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविलक्कु<BR>sandhi-viḻakku (SII 1), a sacred lamp; cf. nandā-viḻakku,<BR>sandhi-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्ध्या|संध्या<BR>sandhyā (CITD), the morning, noon and evening prayers<BR>of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR>(CII 3; IA 17), a period at the commencement of each<BR>of the four Hindu ages; the sandhyā of the Kali-yuga lasts for<BR>36,000 years of men, and is still running; cf. sandhyāṃśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिदीप<BR>sandhi-dīpa, cf. sandi-viḻakku (SITI), a twilight lamp;<BR>generally lighted in the temples in the evening, but sometimes<BR>in the morning; same as sandhyā-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्ध्यांश|संध्यांश|संध्यांशः|सन्ध्यांशः<BR>sandhy-āṃśa (AI 17), a period at the end of each of the<BR>four yugas, the sandhy-āṃśa of the Kali-yuga to last for 36,000<BR>human years.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्दोह|संदोह|संदोहः|सन्दोहः<BR>sandoha, cf. a-puṣpa-kṣīra-sandoha (IE 8-5), realisation or<BR>levy (cf. a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇīya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्गडिरक्षापालक<BR>Saṅgaḍi-rakṣā-pālaka (EI 6), an officer; the meaning of<BR>saṅgaḍi is uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्गम्|संगम्<BR>saṅgam, Tamil; same as Sanskrit saṅgha; an assembly of<BR>ancient Tamil poets; the name given to an assembly of poets<BR>reported in tradition to have functioned in three different pe-<BR>riods. The poets are believed to have been both literary critics<BR>and composers. Literary compositions of the age were later<BR>collected and compiled into anthologies known as Eṭṭuttokai,<BR>Pattuppāṭṭu and Padineṇkīḻkaṇakku according to their contents<BR>and size. The saṅgam is stated to have flourished at Kūḍal<BR>(also called Madurai in later literature) in the first and last<BR>period and at Kavāṭapuram in the middle period. The latest<BR>limit for the first two anthologies may be placed round about<BR>700 A.D. See M. S. Purnalingam Pillai, Tamil Literature,<BR>pp. 14-18; S. Vaiyapuri Pillai, History of Tamil Language and<BR>Literature, p. 38.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घ|संघ|संघः|सङ्घः<BR>saṅgha (ASLV), a social organisation.<BR>(BL), a community of Buddhist monks; the Buddhist Church.<BR>(HA), a Jain congregation; the Jain Church (made up<BR>of four constituents, viz. sādhu, sādhvī, śrāvaka and śrāvikā)<BR>also called Jaina-saṅgha; a group of pilgrims going together on<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-297" target="_blank">Page-297+ 40</a>]<BR>pilgrimage under the leadership of a Saṅghapati (q. v.).<BR>(EI 22), a tribe.<BR>Cf. Tamil saṅgam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घपति<BR>Saṅgha-pati (EI 8; BL), title of the leader of a group of<BR>Jain pilgrims to a holy place, who bears all the expenses of the<BR>whole group; same as Saṅghaprabhu, Saṅghavī, etc. Cf. the<BR>modern Jain family name Siṅghī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घप्रभु<BR>Saṅgha-prabhu (EI 8), Jain; same as Saṅghapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घप्रकृत<BR>Saṅgha-prakṛta (LL), Buddhist; probably, a supporter of<BR>the saṅgha; translated as ‘commissioners of the community’<BR>(Lüders, Mathurā Inscriptions., pp. 84 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घराज<BR>Saṅgharāja (EI 8), Buddhist; title of the principal ec-<BR>clesiastical functionary in Burma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घाराम|संघारामः<BR>saṅghārāma (EI 4; ML; LL), a Buddhist monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घस्थविर<BR>Saṅgha-sthavira (LL), an Elder of the Buddhist congrega-<BR>tion. Cf. Sthavira.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घाट|संघाटः<BR>saṅghāṭa, saṅghāṭā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248), cf.<BR>pāda-saṅghāṭa or pāda-saṅghāṭā, ‘a pair of feet (i. e. foot-marks)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घाटी<BR>saṅghāṭī (EI 25), robe of a Buddhist monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घवी<BR>Saṅghavī (BL; HA; PJS), derived from Sanskrit Saṅgha-<BR>pati (q. v.); designation of the leader of a saṅgha or group of<BR>Jains; the leader of a group of Jain pilgrims, who bears expenses<BR>of all the pilgrims going with him (cf. the Jain family name<BR>Siṅghī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्ग्रहण|संग्रहण|संग्रहणं<BR>saṅgrahaṇa (IE 8-5), adultery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्ग्रहीतृ|संग्रहीतृ<BR>Saṅgrahītṛ (HD), explained by some as ‘a treasurer or<BR>charioteer’ (Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 111); probably, col-<BR>lector of the king's grain share. Cf. Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानि<BR>śāni (SITI), Dravidian; wife; a term by which a<BR>Brāhmaṇa woman was referred to.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शनिवारमण्डप<BR>śanivāra-maṇḍapa (A.R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 13), name of a build-<BR>ing attached to a temple apparently meant for some function<BR>held there on Saturdays; cf. vaikkāṇikku-maṇḍapa under maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्जाति<BR>sañjāti (LP), cf. rāja-sañjātyāṃ kartavyaḥ, ‘may be made a<BR>government property.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्जीवराज<BR>Sañjīva-rāja, cf. Sañjīvarāyar (SITI), name of Hanumān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्काचितक<BR>saṅkācitaka (IE 8-8), a loop; same as Sanskrit kāca.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्कल्प|संकल्प|संकल्पः|सङ्कल्पः<BR>saṅkalpa (Chamba), also called saṅkalpa-hast-odaka; liba-<BR>tion of water; donation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्कर|संकर|संकरः|सङ्करः<BR>saṅkara (EI 9), also called saṅkuru; a double sack.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्कराक्षि<BR>śaṅkar-ākṣi (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्केत|संकेत|संकेतः|सङ्केतः<BR>saṅketa, cf. sva-saṅketa (LP), ‘one's own special arrange-<BR>ment’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्ख|शंख|शंखं|शंखः|शङ्खः<BR>śaṅkha (CII 3, etc.), conch-shell as an emblem on seals;<BR>cf. śaṅghu (ASLV), the use of which was sometimes granted<BR>by kings to their favourites as a privilege.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खधारा<BR>śaṅkhadhārā, cf. śaṃkudhāra (CITD); Telugu; continuous<BR>blowing of the conch-shell. See Śaṅkhadhārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खधारिन्<BR>Śaṅkhadhārin (IE 8-3), blower of the conch-shell;<BR>sometimes mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खकार|शंखकार|शङ्खकारः<BR>Śaṅkhakāra (EI 28), also called Śāṅkhika (q. v.); maker<BR>of conch-shell bangles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खिक<BR>Śaṅkhika, Śāṅkhika (EI 24, 28), same as Śaṅkhakāra (q. v.),<BR>worker on conch-shells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्क्रमण|संक्रमण|संक्रमणं|सङ्क्रमणं<BR>saṅkramaṇa (CII 3; IA 17), also called saṅkrānti; the<BR>entrance of the sun into a sign of the zodiac; regarded as an<BR>auspicious time for performing religious duties.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्क्रान्ति|संक्रान्ति|संक्रांति|संक्रांतिः|संक्रान्तिः|सङ्क्रान्तिः<BR>saṅkrānti (CII 3; IA 17), same as saṅkramaṇa (q. v.).<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षण्मुखबाहु<BR>ṣaṇmukha-bāhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्नाह|संनाह|संनाहः|सन्नाहः<BR>sannāha (LP), armour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्निधातृ|संनिधातृ<BR>Sannidhātṛ (EI 27), official in charge of the receipt of<BR>various articles into the king's treasury, according to some<BR>(HRS); superintendent of the construction of the royal<BR>treasury, store houses, etc., according to others. See Artha-<BR>śāstra, II. 5; cf. I. 10 and 12; Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, pp. 138,<BR>141; Vol. XI, pp. 93-94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्निधि|संनिधि|संनिधिः|सन्निधिः<BR>sannidhi, cf. sannadi (SII 1), presence of a deity; the<BR>front of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्नियुक्तक<BR>Sanniyuktaka (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 11, text line 14),<BR>same as Tanniyuktaka or a mistake for it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्स्क्रित्<BR>Sanskrit, Anglicised form of Saṃskṛta, the name of the<BR>sacred language of the Indians.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्त|संत|संतः|सन्तः<BR>santa (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a fair or market day.<BR>(EI 14), name of a measure or a coin; probably, a small<BR>coin (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तै<BR>santai (ASLV), a weekly fair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तक<BR>santaka (EI 27; CII 3), Prakrit; ‘belonging to’; some-<BR>times Sanskritised as satka. Sometimes santaka (also santika<BR>apparently used in the same sense) has been regarded as<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-299" target="_blank">Page-299+ 40</a>]<BR>meaning ‘a territorial unit’; supposed similarly to mean ‘a ser-<BR>vant’ (EI 23) or ‘an officer’ (EI 24).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सान्तकिक<BR>Sāntakika (IE 8-3), official designation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तान|संतान|संतानं|संतानः|सन्तानः<BR>santāna (SITI), lineage.<BR>(BL), cf. a Jain religious teacher described as belonging to<BR>the paṭṭa of another teacher and the santāna of a third teacher.<BR>(IA 20), used in the sense of āmnāya or kula-krama.<BR>(EI 6), same as santānaka, santati; seven in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तानशाप<BR>santāna-śāpa (SITI), curse that prevents progeny.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तानिकशैव<BR>Santānika-śaiva (SITI), Śaivas who belong to the line<BR>of ācāryas of the santāna-kuravar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तति|संतति|संततिः|सन्ततिः<BR>santati (SITI), lineage. Cf. also sapta-santati (EI 14) and<BR>santānaka (under santāna).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्ततिप्रवेशम्<BR>santati-praveśam (SITI), ‘from generation to generation’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्ति|शांति|शांतिः|शान्तिः<BR>Śānti, a priest in a temple; cf. Tamil-Sanskrit Mel-śānti;<BR>also cf. Śāntikāra, of which Śānti seems to be an abbreviation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्ति|शांति|शांतिः|शान्तिः<BR>śānti (EI 33), a propitiatory rite; cf. śānty-āgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तिक<BR>santika (EI 25), proximity, presence.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्तिकार<BR>Śāntikāra (SITI), a temple priest; also known as Śāntiy-<BR>aḍigal and Śānti-śeyyān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तीरणा<BR>santīraṇā, cf. artha-santīraṇā (CII 1), despatch of business.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्तिवारिक<BR>Śānti-vārika (EI 12, 30, 33), priest in charge of the<BR>performance of propitiatory rites or the priest who provides for<BR>śānti-vāri, ‘propitiatory water’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्त्यागार<BR>śānty-āgāra (EI 12, 30), room wherein a bath is taken<BR>with the propitiatory water after a sacrifice; the room for<BR>performing propitiatory rites. See Śāntyāgārika, Śāntyāgār-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्त्यागाराधिकृत<BR>Śāntyāgār-ādhikṛta (EI 30), priest in charge of the room<BR>for the performance of propitiatory rites. Cf. śānty-āgāra, Śānty-<BR>āgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्त्यागारिक<BR>Śāntyāgārika (EI 30), same as Śāntyāgār-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्हओननोस्हओ<BR>Shaonano Shao (EI 30), known from the legend of Kuṣāṇa<BR>coins; same as Sāhānuṣāhī (q. v.), Persian Shāhān Shāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपादलक्ष<BR>Sapādalakṣa (IE 8-4), name of two territories so called with<BR>reference to the theoretical number of villages in each of them.<BR>Cf. Pādonalakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपिण्डीकरणश्राद्ध<BR>sapiṇḍīkaraṇa-śrāddha (CII 4), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तक्षेत्र<BR>sapta-kṣetra (IA 19), Jain; seven spheres of action.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तमचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Saptama-cakravartin (LP), ‘the seventh emperor’, i. e. the<BR>ruling monarch; according to the Abhidhānacintāmaṇi, the six<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-300" target="_blank">Page-300+ 40</a>]<BR>older Cakravartins are: Māndhātā Dhundhumāraś = ca Hariścan-<BR>draḥ Purūravāḥ | Bharataḥ Kārtavīryaś = ca ṣaḍ = ete cakravartinaḥ ||<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तमातृ<BR>Sapta-mātṛ (EI 23), the seven Divine Mothers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तामात्य<BR>Sapt-āmātya (EI 27), an officer in charge of seven depart-<BR>ments. Cf. Pañca-karaṇ-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्ताम्भोधि<BR>sapt-āmbhodhi (EI 16), name of a mahādāna; same as sapta-<BR>sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्ताङ्ग<BR>sapt-āṅga (CII CITD), the seven constituent parts of<BR>a kingdom, viz., king, ministers, allies, treasury, territory, forts<BR>and forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तसागर|सप्तसागरः<BR>sapta-sāgara (EI 24), name of a mahādāna; same as sapt-<BR>āmbhodhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तसन्तान<BR>sapta-santāna (SITI), also called sapta-santati; merit equal<BR>to that obtainable through progeny from their performance of<BR>seven kinds of great deeds, viz. digging of tanks, hoarding of<BR>treasure, founding of agrahāras, erection of temples, creation<BR>of flower gardens, getting literary works written by poets, and<BR>the establishment of Choultries. An inscription (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. III, pp. 88 ff.) mentions the following seven meritorious<BR>acts a man ought to perform during his lifetime; viz. procrea-<BR>tion of sons, accumulation of wealth, planting of groves, help-<BR>ing people (Brāhmaṇas) to marry, getting poems composed,<BR>erection of temples and excavation of tanks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तसन्तति<BR>sapta-santati (SITI), same as sapta-santāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तविधि<BR>sapta-vidhi (LP), probably, seven kinds of defects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शर|शरं|शरः<BR>śara (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारा<BR>sārā (EI 9; LP), care; cf. etair = aṣṭabhir = goṣṭhikaiḥ … sārā<BR>karaṇīyā, ‘[this place of worship] has to be taken care of by the<BR>following eight trustees’. Cf. also Gujarātī sāravār.<BR>(EI 8, 11), supervision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरभङ्ग|शरभङ्गः<BR>Śarabhaṅga (IE 8-3; 8-8; EI 23), a leader of forces; an<BR>officer of the military department; possibly, a military governor;<BR>same as Persian Sarhang and Hindī Serāṅg; also spelt Sarabhaṅga<BR>and Sarobhaṅga; Wilson's Glossary explains Sarhang as ‘a com-<BR>mander’ and says, “but [it is] generally applied in India to<BR>the headman of a native crew, whether on board a ship or a<BR>boat; also to the headman of a gang of natives attached to artill-<BR>ery, dragging guns, or to the army in general, as tent-pitchers,<BR>and the like, or to the head of gangs of a superior order of labour-<BR>ers employed in public or private works, in docks, buildings,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-301" target="_blank">Page-301+ 40</a>]<BR>etc.’ Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 123, 166 (spelt Sarobhaṅga),<BR>Ind. Cult., Vol. VII, p. 309. Kane (Hist. Dharm., Vol. III,<BR>p. 1005) is certainly wrong when he thinks that it may be con-<BR>nected with śarayantra and Śarayantrin (a title bestowed in Mithilā<BR>upon a very learned man who faced the ordeal of answering<BR>satisfactorily all questions on any śāstra put to him by learned<BR>Ācāryas and also the questions put by common people). See Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 95. ff. See Sarāṅgha, Sarāhang, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारदा<BR>Sāradā, name of the alphabet which developed out of late<BR>Brāhmī and was prevalent in the Kashmir region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सराहन्ग्<BR>Sarāhang (IA 20), also called Sarang, Sarhang, etc. See<BR>Sarāṅgha, Śarabhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरणागतवज्रपञ्जर<BR>Śaraṇāgata-vajrapañjara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 317),<BR>‘the impregnable shelter for one who seeks for it’; a subordinate<BR>title of the Kannaḍa-speaking area; used by the Sena kings of<BR>Bengal because they hailed from the same region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरन्ग्<BR>Sarang (IA 20), also called Sarhang, Sarāhang, etc.; see<BR>Sarāṅgha, Śarabhaṅga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सराङ्घ<BR>Sarāṅgha (IE 8-3), Persian Sarhang and Indian Śarabhaṅga,<BR>Serāṅg, etc. cf. Giligittā-sarāṅgha, ‘the chief of the army at Gilgit’,<BR>in the Hatun inscription of Paṭoladeva (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX,<BR>p. 228).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरस्वतीभाण्डार<BR>Sarasvatī-bhāṇḍāra (EI 25; SITI), a library. Cf. Saras-<BR>vatī-bhāṇḍārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरस्वतीभाण्डारिक<BR>Sarasvatī-bhāṇḍārika (EI 25), librarian. Cf. Sarasvatī-<BR>bhāṇḍāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरयन्त्र<BR>śarayantra, Maithilī; test [prevalent in Mithilā] of the<BR>scholarship of one who is prepared to answer any question on<BR>any śāstra put to him by any other scholar or by the common<BR>people. See Proc. AIOC, Benares, 1943; Kane, Hist. Dharm.,<BR>Vol. III, p. 1005.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरयन्त्रक<BR>śarayantraka (IE 3-1), same as sūtra; the string passing<BR>through the hole in the leaves of manuscripts for holding them<BR>together (Vāsavadatta, Hall's ed., p. 250).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरयन्त्रिन्<BR>Śarayantrin (EI 35), one who has been successful in the<BR>śarayantra test of Mithilā. See śarayantra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारयित्वा<BR>sārayitvā (LP), ‘having finished’; cf. Gujarātī sārvuṃ,<BR>‘to accomplish’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्धञ्चर<BR>Sārdhañcara, Sārdhañcarī (LL), companion of a Jain monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्धंविहारिन्<BR>Sārdhaṃvihārin, cf. Sādhyavihāri (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-302" target="_blank">Page-302+ 40</a>]<BR>p. 10), Pāli saddhivihāri; one's fellow-priest living at the same<BR>monastery; a fellow-student. Cf. F. Edgerton, Bud. Hyb.<BR>Sans. Gram. Dict., Vol. II, p. 593. See Sadhryagvihārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्हन्ग्<BR>Sarhang (IE 8-3; IA 20), Persian; see Śarabhaṅga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरीर|शरीरं<BR>śarīra (SITI), person; individual.<BR>(EI 24; ML), corporeal relies of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरोभङ्ग<BR>Sarobhaṅga (IE 8-3), same as Śarabhaṅga or Sarabhaṅga<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्प|सर्पः<BR>sarpa (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्पबलि<BR>sarpa-bali (IA 19), an offering in snake-worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्षप|सर्षपः<BR>sarṣapa, a small unit of measurement; sometimes specified<BR>as ‘red’ (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्थवाह|सार्थवाहः<BR>Sārthavāha (IE 8-3; EI 24, 31; BL; LL), a trader, a mer-<BR>chant; designation of a member of the mercantile community<BR>represented on an administrative board like the Pañcāyat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्थवाहिनी<BR>Sārthavāhinī (EI 1, 24), wife of a merchant (Sārthavāha) or<BR>a female merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्थवहित्र<BR>sārtha-vahitra (IE 8-3), probably, a cart-load of articles<BR>for sale.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारूप्य|सारूप्यं<BR>sārūpya (CITD), assimilation in the deity, one of the four<BR>states of mukti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्वभौम|सार्व्वभौम|सार्व्वभौमः<BR>Sārvabhauma (EI 7, 27, 30, 32), title of imperial rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाभ्यन्तरसिद्धि<BR>sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi (IA 19; SII 11-1), a fiscal term denot-<BR>ing full and complete right of enjoyment of agricultural income<BR>or internal revenue or taxes to be paid to the village authorities;<BR>cf. sarv-ābhyantara-siddhyā (IA 18), also abhyantara-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदण्डनायक<BR>Sarva-daṇḍa-nāyaka (CII 3; IA 9; IA BL), official desig-<BR>nation; ‘lord of all the forces’; cf. Samasta-sainy-ādhipati. See<BR>Daṇḍa-nāyaka, Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, Sarva-mahā-daṇḍanāyaka. Cf.<BR>Ind. Ant., Vol. VIII, p. 19; Vol. IX, p. 167.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदेशाधिकारिन्<BR>Sarva-deś-ādhikārin (AI 7), chief minister; see Deśādhikṛta,<BR>Sarv-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकाराधिकृत<BR>Sarv-ādhikār-ādhikṛta (EI 31), chief minister or adminis-<BR>trator; same as Sarv-ādhikārin, Sarv-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकारकरण<BR>Sarv-ādhikāra-karaṇa (EI 30), probably, the office of the<BR>chief secretary, administrator or minister.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकारनियुक्त<BR>Sarv-ādhikāra-niyukta (EI 32), official designation; same<BR>as Sarv-ādhikārin, Sarv-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकारिन्|सर्व्वाधिकारिन्<BR>Sarv-ādhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 19; CII 4; HD), prime<BR>minister (cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 568); minister plenipoten-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-303" target="_blank">Page-303+ 39</a>]<BR>tiary or viceroy; sometimes also called Senāpati, Mahāpradhāna,<BR>Hiriya-bhaṇḍāgārin, Mahāsāmanta, Sen-ādi-bāhattara-niyog-<BR>ādhipati, Daṇḍanāyaka, Mahāpasāyita, Amātya, Paramaviśvāsin or<BR>Mahāpramaviśvāsin, etc., additionally.<BR>(IE 8-3), a governor or chief administrator (cf. ‘the Sarv-<BR>ādhikārin of Hagaraṭage-300’).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाध्यक्ष<BR>Sarv-ādhyakṣa (EI 24, 27; CII 3), literally, a general superin-<BR>tendent; probably, the chief minister or administrator; same<BR>as Sarv-ādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकृत<BR>Sarv-ādhikṛta (HD), same as Sarv-ādhikārin, etc. Cf. Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XIV, pp. 360, 362. See Mahāsarvādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाग्रहार<BR>sarv-āgrahāra (EI 21), same as sarva-mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजात<BR>sarva-jāta, cf. sarva-jātaa-bhoga-nirastyā (EI 8-5), ‘with all<BR>kinds of the [king’s] rights renounced’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वमान्य<BR>sarva-mānya (IE 8-5, SITI; CITD), a free tenure; a<BR>rent-free holding; land exempted from taxes; lands and villages<BR>fully exempt from all taxes. This corresponds to the<BR>iṟaiyili class of land mentioned in the Col13a inscriptions. Often<BR>this is associated with aṣṭa-bhoga, i. e. the eight forms of enjoy-<BR>ing the land. For a discussion of this form of land tenure, see<BR>JAHRS, Vol. X, pp. 123-32. It is noteworthy that even the<BR>so-called tax-free (iṟaiyili) lands paid to the king certain dues<BR>of the nature of taxes. See K. A. Nilakanta Sastri, The<BR>Col13as, 2nd ed., pp. 534-35. See sarva-namasya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वमेध|सर्वमेधः<BR>sarva-medha (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वनमस्कृत<BR>sarva-namaskṛta (IA 8), same as sarva-namasya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वनमस्य<BR>sarva-namasya (IE 8-5; EI 23; CITD), a rent-free holding;<BR>same as sarva-mānya, sarva-namaskṛta, namasya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वनियोग<BR>sarva-niyoga (EI 7), exclusive property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वसैन्याधिकारिन्<BR>Sarva-sainy-ādhikārin (IE 8-3), commander-in-chief; cf.<BR>Maneya-samasta-sainy-ādhipati, commander of all the soldiers in<BR>the royal household; also cf. Sarva-daṇḍa-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वस्वहरण|सर्व्वस्वहरण<BR>sarvasva-haraṇa (SITI), forfeiture of one's entire property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वतन्त्राधिकृत<BR>Sarva-tantr-ādhikṛta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV pp. 144-45),<BR>a superintendent of all departments; but tantra is used in South<BR>Indian records in the sense of ‘the army’. See tantra, Tantr-<BR>ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वतोभद्र|सर्वतोभद्रः|सर्व्वतोभद्र|सर्व्वतोभद्रं|सर्व्वतोभद्रः<BR>sarvatobhadra (EI 9), a building having doors on all the<BR>four sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वतोभद्रिका<BR>sarvatobhadrikā (LL; HA), quadruple image showing a<BR>Jina (or several Jinas) on each of the four faces; same as<BR>caumukha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्ववादिनायक<BR>Sarvavādināyaka (EI 10), explained as ‘superintendent of<BR>the intelligence department’; probably, ‘the chief court Pandit.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाय<BR>sarv-āya (EI 15), all the usual dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वीय|सर्व्वीय|सर्व्वीयः<BR>sarvīya (EI 13), ‘good to all’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासन|शासनं<BR>śāsana (EI 19; IA 20), order, a royal edict; any royal<BR>record (cf. vijaya-śāsana).<BR>(IE 8-4; EI 13, 23; CII 3; BL), a charter; land or<BR>village granted by a charter; rent-free land or village; some-<BR>times suffixed to the names of localities which were once rent-<BR>free holdings. See also tāmra-śāsana, a technical term for a deed<BR>of conveyance on copper-plates.<BR>(EI 9, 10), a doctrine; religion or religious faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनबद्ध<BR>Śāsana-baddha (SITI), people bound by a royal charter;<BR>original grantees of a charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनभाण्डारिन्<BR>Śāsana-bhāṇḍārin (EI 25), official designation; cf. Śāsan-<BR>ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनदेवी<BR>Śāsanadevī (IA 18), divine female messenger of a Jain<BR>Arhat; same as Śāsana-sundarī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनाधिकारिक<BR>Śāsan-ādhikārika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 155, text line 85),<BR>same as Śāsan-ādhikārin, etc.; officer in charge of grants (or their<BR>writing or issue), mentioned along with Dān-ādhikārin, ‘officer<BR>in charge of gifts’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनाधिकारिन्<BR>Śāsan-ādhikārin (EI 28, 31), officer in charge of royal grants<BR>or their issue, who was often the writer of documents; same as<BR>Śāsan-ādhikārika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनपटा<BR>śāsana-paṭā (Chamba, etc.), charter; same as Sanskrit<BR>śāsana-paṭṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनमर्यादा<BR>śāsana-maryādā (EI 15), specification of privileges by a<BR>charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनार्धिक<BR>śāsan-ārdhika (IE 8-5; 12, 28), name of a levy; probably,<BR>the half of the cultivator's share of the produce of the land in<BR>the gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासयितृ<BR>Śāsayitṛ (EI 12; BL), one who is responsible for getting<BR>a royal grant executed; cf. Dūtaka, Lekhayitṛ, Ājñāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनसञ्चारिन्<BR>Śāsana-sañcārin (EI 8, 24), same as Ājñā-sañcārin; an official<BR>messenger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनसुन्दरी<BR>Śāsana-sundarī (IA 30), Jain; same as Śāsandevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनिककायस्थ<BR>Śāsanika-kāyastha (EI 11), writer of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शशाङ्क|शशांक|शशाङ्कः<BR>śaśāṅka (IE 7-71-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सष्घानी<BR>Şaṣghānī, coins issued by the Tughlaq Sulṯtāns, 4 jitals in<BR>weight (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 44); same as chagānī, equal to (3/4) of<BR>a ṭaṅka (ibid., Vol. XXII, p. 198). See śāśukāni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शशिन्<BR>śaśin (EI 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षष्ठाधिकृत<BR>Ṣaṣṭh-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; HD), a collector of the king's grain<BR>share which was originally one-sixth of the produce according<BR>to many authorities; cf. Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇika. See Gho-<BR>shal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 246.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षष्ठतप<BR>ṣaṣṭhatapa (IA 19), Jain; a kind of penance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षष्ठीअमावास्या<BR>ṣaṣṭhī-amāvāsyā, cf. caṭṭī-amavāse (EI 5), new-moon follow-<BR>ing the campā-ṣaṣṭhī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सष्टिरात्र<BR>Saṣṭirātra (BL), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शास्त्र|शास्त्रं<BR>śāstra (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाशुकानि<BR>śāśukāni, Indianised form of Şaṣghānī; also called śāśukāni-<BR>ṭaṅka. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, ‘The Śāṇa’, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाश्वतीय<BR>śāśvatīya (SITI), perpetuity, eternity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शत|शतं<BR>śata, cf. ekādaśa-śata (ML), ‘one hundred and eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सात|सातं<BR>Sāta (EI 32), abbreviation of the name Śātavāhana or<BR>Śātakarṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतघ्नी<BR>śataghnī (IA 7, 12), a gun or canon according to late works;<BR>a mechanical weapon placed at the gate of forts according to the<BR>Vasudevahiṇḍī (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1, p. 15). Seekālacakra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतमान|शतमानः<BR>śatamāna, name of a coin; a silver coin weighing 320 ratis<BR>(rarely also 160 ratis); also called pala, niṣka, śukti, aṣṭamikā and<BR>nalā; wrongly regarded as 100 ratis in weight. See JNSI,<BR>Vol. XVI, pp. 41, 46-47. For śatamāna as a gold coin, see ibid.,<BR>Vol. XV, p. 140.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शताङ्ग|शतांग|शताङ्गः<BR>śatāṅga (EI 3), a car.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्चतुष्किका<BR>ṣaṭ-catuṣkikā, cf. cha-cokī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतेर|सतेरः<BR>satera, sateraka, same as Greek stater; regarded as equal to<BR>two dīnāras (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 153).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सती<BR>satī (EI 6, 30; CII 3, 4; BL; CITD), literally, ‘a chaste<BR>woman’; really ‘a woman burning herself with her husband’.<BR>(EI 6, 30), self-immolation of a widow usually on the<BR>funeral pyre of her husband; usually spelt suttee in English.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतिका<BR>śatikā (EI 28), cf. saikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतिलोदक<BR>sa-til-odaka (IA 19), cf. sa-til-odakena vidhinā; same as<BR>udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्क<BR>satka (EI, 1, 13; IA 17), Sanskritised from Prakrit santaka;<BR>‘the holding of … ’, ‘belonging to … ’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्कर्मन्|षट्कर्म्मन्<BR>ṣaṭ-karman (SII 1), the six duties of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्पञ्चाशत्|षट्पंचाशत्<BR>ṣaṭpañcāśat, ‘all’; cf. ṣaṭpañcāśad-deśa = chappanna-deśa (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. V, p. 217, note 7), literally, ‘fiftysix countries’; but<BR>really, ‘all the world’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्पण<BR>ṣaṭ-paṇa, cf. aṟuvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्पुरुष|सत्पुरुषः<BR>Satpuruṣa (LL), a Buddhist saint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्र|सत्त्रं|सत्रं<BR>satra (EI 10, 19, 23, 26), same as sattra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्त्र<BR>sattra (SII 1; CII 3, 4), ‘a charitable feeding house’; an<BR>alms-house; sometimes used to indicate one of the five mahā-<BR>yajñas, usually called atithi. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46,<BR>note 8.<BR>(EI 10, 19, 23), also spelt satra; hospitality to guests; one<BR>of the five mahāyajñas.<BR>(IA 15), a hall for the charitable distribution of food,<BR>etc. Cf. satra-śālā (SII 11-1), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्रागार<BR>satr-āgāra (LP), a house where alms are distributed. Cf.<BR>satra-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्रागारकरण<BR>satr-āgāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); department of Dharmaśālās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्रप्<BR>Satrap (IA 20), Greek; same as Khshathrapāvan, Kṣatrapa,<BR>Sertīp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्त्रपति<BR>Sattrapati (BL), priest in charge of a sacrificial session.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्त्रिंशत्<BR>ṣaṭtriṃśat, literally, ‘thirtysix’, but actually ‘all’ (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXX, p. 115). See aṣṭādaśa, ṣaṭapañcāśat, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्त्रिंशद्दण्डायुध<BR>ṣaṭtriṃśad-daṇḍ-āyudha (LP), thirtysix (really, all),<BR>kinds of weapons; sometimes enumerated as:<BR>Cakra pāsa mogaru gadā ghana tomara tīraha |<BR>sakati sūla trisūla vajra kātara karaḍaṃḍha ||<BR>Paṭukaṭārī kaṃta sarasī ghaḍu avājī |<BR>kaṇīu churī khaḍga nāli golā nārājī ||<BR>ṣaṃḍuṃ ṣapnu muṃsala hala sīṃgani pharasī gupati gaṇi |<BR>niṣaṃga śāṃgi aṃkuśa guruja kuhaka bāṇa batrīsa bhaṇi ||<BR>Cf. Prācīnagurjarakāvyasaṃgraha, G.O.S., pp. 106-07.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शात्त्विकदान<BR>śāttvika-dāna (SITI), gift without the pouring of water<BR>and therefore not expecting any merit in return for the donation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्यधर्मस्थित<BR>Satyadharma-sthita (IE 8-2), ‘adherent of the true religion’;<BR>same as Dharma-sthita; epithet of a Kuṣāṇa king probably point-<BR>ing to his Buddhist faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्यज्ञानदरिशनिगल्<BR>Satya-jñāna-dariśanigaḻ (SITI), followers of a sect of Śaivism;<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-307" target="_blank">Page-307+ 40</a>]<BR>evidently those belonging to the lineage of Mĕykaṇḍār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौ<BR>Śau, abbreviation of Śaulkika or Śauṇḍika (A. R. Ep., 1953-<BR>54, No. B 117).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौध|सौधः<BR>saudha (IA 15), used in the sense of brahmapurī, ‘a<BR>Brāhmaṇa settlement’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौगन्धिक|सौगंधिक|सौगन्धिकं|सौगन्धिकः<BR>Saugandhika, cf. Prakrit Sagandhaka (EI 18); a dealer in<BR>scents or superintendent of the perfumery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौगतपरिव्राजक<BR>Saugata-parivrājaka (BL), a Buddhist mendicant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौल्किक|शौल्किकः<BR>Śaulkika (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; EI 30; HD), toll-collector<BR>or customs officer; officer in charge of collecting customs<BR>duties; superintendent of tolls or customs duties. See<BR>Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 173; CII, Vol. III, pp. 50, 52; Ghoshal,<BR>H. Rev. Syst., p. 246.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौम्य|सौम्यः<BR>saumya (EI 27), lunar or auspicious.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौनिक|शौनिकः<BR>Śaunika (IE 8-3), superintendent of slaughter-houses and<BR>the sale of meat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौण्डिक|शौंडिक|शौंडिकः|शौण्डिकः<BR>Śauṇḍika (IE 8-5), vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौत्रिक|सौत्रिकः<BR>Sautrika (LL), weaver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्ण|सौवर्णं<BR>sauvarṇa (EI 19), name of a coin; cf. suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्णिक<BR>Sauvarṇika (HD), cf. Prakrit Sovaṇika (EI 10), a gold-<BR>smith; the State goldsmith. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, pp.<BR>144-45. See Hairaṇyika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्णिक<BR>sauvarṇika (HRS), profits of the royal monopoly of manu-<BR>facture of gold and silver articles, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सव|सवं|सवः<BR>sava (IE 8-1), contraction of Prakrit savachara = Sanskrit<BR>saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शावडि<BR>śāvaḍi (IE 8-4), a subdivision; same as uśāvaḍi or cāvaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवर्णवृत्ति<BR>savarṇa-vṛtti (SITI), profession of writing documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सावु<BR>Sāvu (EI 9; CII 4), a title; same as Sāhu (Sanskrit Sādhu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शय|शयः<BR>śaya (IE 3-4), derived from a Chinese word; paper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सायक|सायकः<BR>sāyaka (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सायन|सायनं<BR>sāyana (CII 3), ‘inclusive of precession of the equinoxes’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शयनपूजा<BR>śayana-pūjā (IE 8-8), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शयनीय|शयनीयं<BR>śayanīya, a cot; cf. śayanīy-āsana-siddānnaṃ na dāpayet (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 171).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सायर<BR>sāyara (PJS), Arabic shāher; a tax on palm-tree juice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शय्याग्राहक<BR>Śayyāgrāhaka (HD), explained as ‘the guardian of the bed-<BR>chamber.’ See A. S. Gadre, Imp. Ins. Bar. St., p. 72. Cf.<BR>Śayyāpāla, Vāsāgārika, Vitān-ādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शय्यापाल|शय्यापालः<BR>Śayyāpāla (EI 25; HD), officer in charge of the king's bed<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-308" target="_blank">Page-308+ 40</a>]<BR>(i. e. bed-chamber); guardian of the bed-chamber. See<BR>Śayyāgrāhaka, Vāsāgārika, Vitān-ādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेइआ<BR>seiā (IE 8-8), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit selikā (q. v.); cf.<BR>seigā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेइगा<BR>seigā (IE 8-8), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit setikā (q. v.); cf.<BR>seiā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेगाण<BR>Segāṇa (BL), official designation of uncertain import,<BR>found in the Chamba inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक<BR>śeka (EI 11), same as Sanskrit śikya, a loop or swing made<BR>of rope and suspended from the ends of a pole placed on one's<BR>shoulder for carrying loads, or the load itself. Cf. saṃkācitaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेक्यकार<BR>Sekyakāra (EI 12; BL), a brazier; secondarily, an engraver;<BR>cf. Bengali seṅkrā, a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेलहस्त<BR>Selahasta (EI 11), probably, the collector of the king's<BR>grain share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाभक्त<BR>senā-bhakta (HRS), contribution of oil, rice, etc., which<BR>the villagers had to pay to the royal army on march, as suggest-<BR>ed by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनभोग<BR>Sena-bhoga, cf. Śeṇai-bhogam (SITI), an accountant. See<BR>Śāṇa-bhoga, Senabova.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनभोगिक<BR>Senabhogika (EI 18; HD), same as Senabova, etc.; a clerk<BR>or an accountant-clerk. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 285.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनबोव<BR>Senabova (EI 5, 10; IA 18; SII 11-1), a clerk; an account-<BR>ant; a village accountant; modern Śānabhoga or Kuḻkarṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाधिकारिक<BR>Sen-ādhikārika (EI 23), same as Senāpati, Sen-ādhipati, etc.;<BR>a general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाधिप<BR>Sen-ādhipa (BL), ‘leader of forces’. See Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाधिपति<BR>Sen-ādhipati (IE 8-3; EI 23; SII 11-1), same as Sen-<BR>ādhikārika, etc.; sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Hĕri-<BR>sandhivigrahin, Kaḍita-vĕrgaḍĕ, etc., additionally. Cf. Mahā-<BR>senādhipati, Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनादिबाहत्तरनियोगाधिष्ठायक<BR>Sen-ādi-bāhattara-niyog-ādhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-2; EI 5), sup-<BR>perintendent of all appointments including those in the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनगण<BR>Sena-gaṇa (SITI), a division of the Jain community; also<BR>known as Sen-ānvaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनागोप|सेनागोपः<BR>Senāgopa (LL), a general; same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाङ्ग|सेनांग|सेनाङ्गं<BR>sen-āṅga (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनैमुदलियार्<BR>Senai-mudaliyār (SITI), Tamil; same as Sanskrit-Tamil<BR>Senāpatiy-āl13vār; name of the god Viṣvaksenai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनैयळ्ङ्गाडिक<BR>Senaiy-al13ṅgāḍika (SITI), a class of merchants who follow<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-309" target="_blank">Page-309+ 40</a>]<BR>the army with their merchandise; a class of cloth merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनानीनेत्र<BR>senānī-netra (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनापति|सेनापतिः<BR>Senāpati (IE 8-3), leader of forces; mentioned separately<BR>along with Bal-ādhyakṣa; probably, a subordinate of the latter;<BR>the military governor of a district, according to some<BR>(HD); commander-in-chief (ASLV), also called Sarva-sainy-<BR>ādhikārin and Dalavāya, i. e. the chief officer in charge of the<BR>military department. See Bṛhaspati quoted by Viśvarūpa on<BR>Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 307; Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 187. Puṣya-<BR>mitra, the founder of the Śuṅga dynasty, was called Senāpati<BR>even after his accession to the Maurya throne. See Sen-ādhipa,<BR>etc.; cf. also Anusenāpati (EI 18).<BR>(IE 8-3), sometimes called Mahāpradhāna, Bāhattara-<BR>niyogādhiṣṭhāyaka, Paṭṭa-sāhan-ādhipati, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनापतिप्पेरुविलै<BR>senāpati-pperuvilai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; the sale of<BR>lands of a Viṣṇu temple executed in the name of Senai-<BR>mudaliyār, i. e. the god Viṣvaksenai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनापतिया<BR>Senāpatiy-āl13vār (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; same as Senai-<BR>mudaliyār, i. e. the god Viṣvaksenai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेर्<BR>ser (Chamba), also called seri; crown land; state demesne.<BR>(Chamba, etc.), a weight equal to 80 tolās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेराङ्ग्<BR>Serāṅg (IE), see Śarabhaṅga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेरि<BR>seri (Chamba), same as ser; crown-land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेर्तीप्<BR>Sertīp (IA 20), Persian; same as Old Persian Khshthrapā-<BR>van and Indian Kṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेर्वै<BR>śervai (ASLV), Tamil; derived from Sanskrit sevā (q. v.); a<BR>service inām.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेषशीर्ष<BR>śeṣa-śīrṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेसिबिय्यमु<BR>sesi-biyyamu (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; sesi means the<BR>remains of flowers, raw rice and other offerings made to an idol<BR>or used in a śubha-kārya and afterwards distributed among the<BR>worshippers and attendants. The expression probably means<BR>raw rice over which incantations have been pronounced and<BR>which is thrown on the heads of the bride and bridegroom dur-<BR>ing the marriage ceremony and in connection with similar other<BR>rites.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेतिका<BR>setikā (IE 8-5; EI 25), Prakrit seiā, seigā; a measure of<BR>weight equal to two handfuls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टि<BR>Śeṭṭi (ASLV), Sanskrit Śreṣṭhin; the leading member of<BR>a guild. Cf. Nagar-seṭh, Nagara-śreṣṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टिपत्तणस्वामिन्<BR>Śeṭṭi-Pattaṇasvāmin (ASLV), designation of the president<BR>of a merchants' guild. Cf. Nagar-seṭh, Nagara-śreṣṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेतु|सेतुः<BR>setu, embankment; income or taxes resulting from it<BR>(Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 108-09).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेवा<BR>sevā, cf. Tamil sevai, śervai (SITI); service; inām for services;<BR>tax-free land given to servants for enjoyment in lieu of salary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेवक|सेवकः<BR>Sevaka (SITI), a soldier; cf. sevaka-ttevai (SITI), expenses<BR>in connection with the supply and maintenance of retainers of<BR>chiefs and officers during their visit to a place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेविडु<BR>śeviḍu (SITI), Tamil; a small grain measure; (1/5) of an<BR>āl13ākku.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाह्<BR>Śāh (IE 8-2; EI 30), Persian; royal title; same as Old<BR>Persian Khshāyathiya. See Sāhī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिबर<BR>śibara, sibara (CII 4), a farm-house. But cf. śaibara, śaivara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्ध|सिद्धं|सिद्धः<BR>Siddha (CII 4), a person possessing miraculous powers;<BR>an emancipated person.<BR>(CII 3), ‘a perfect one’; the epithet of a class of Jain<BR>saints who are invoked in the plural.<BR>(LL), a Jain saint.<BR>(CII 4), cf. siddham (q. v.), used at the beginning of ins-<BR>criptions to ensure the success of the undertaking and meaning<BR>siddhir = astu, ‘let there be success’. Cf. siddhi.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty-four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्ध|सिद्धं|सिद्धः<BR>siddha, (IE 8-5), income from land under cultivation. See<BR>siddh-āya, etc.<BR>(SITI), also called siddhi; the right of cultivating land;<BR>one of the eight kinds of enjoying landed property; may be the<BR>same as abbyantara-siddhi. See siddha, siddh-āya, ūrdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धचक्र<BR>siddha-cakra (EI 2), a yantra for worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धम्<BR>siddham (EI30; CII 3), literally, ‘success has been attained’;<BR>an invocation found in early inscriptions at the commencement<BR>of the text; used in the sense of siddhir = astu, ‘let there be success’;<BR>sometimes confused with the praṇava; generally indicated in<BR>later records by a symbol having several varieties; sometimes<BR>indicated by the letter cha. Cf. siddhi<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धमातृका<BR>Siddhamātṛkā, name of the Indian alphabet which is deri-<BR>ved from Late Brāhmī and from which are derived North Indian<BR>alphabets like Nāgarī; wrongly called Kuṭila, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धान्न<BR>siddh-ānna (IE 8-8), cooked rice or uncooked food (cf.<BR>Hindī sīdhā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धान्त|सिद्धांत|सिद्धान्तः<BR>siddhānta (CII 4), ‘an established doctrine’; sometimes<BR>used to indicate the Śaiva doctrine or religion (SITI).<BR>Cf. Lākula-siddhānta (EI 32), doctrine of the Śaiva<BR>teacher Lakula (Lakulīśa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धान्तदर्शन<BR>siddhānta-darśana (EI 32), philosophy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धपीठ|सिद्धपीठः<BR>siddha-pīṭha, see yoga-pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धसाध्य|सिद्धसाध्यः<BR>siddha-sādhya (EI 13), present income and the income that<BR>may accrue in future.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धस्थान<BR>siddha-sthāna (EI 22), the place sanctified by a holy man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धाय<BR>siddh-āya (EI 23; SII 11-2; ASLV), fixed income;<BR>regular income; same as Tamil sidd-āyam, sometimes explained<BR>as ‘a tax’ (EI 27); probably, agricultural income.<BR>(SITI), a fixed assessment; minor taxes; minor taxes<BR>payable in cash in the days of the Vijayanagara kings; also<BR>written in Tamil as sidd-āyam, sitt-āyam. See pratiṣiddh-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धायतन<BR>siddh-āyatana (EI 33), cf. pūrva-siddh-āyatana (Buddhist);<BR>temple associated with a Siddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धि|सिद्धिः<BR>siddhi (CII 4), emancipation; sometimes used at the<BR>beginning of documents to ensure the success of the undertaking,<BR>as siddham in early inscriptions, and meaning siddhir = astu.<BR>(SITI), same as siddham, the right of cultivating land.<BR>Cf. ūrdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi-yutā (IA 18), together with income<BR>from horticulture and agriculture; cf. sa-bāhy-ābhyantara-siddhi,<BR>siddhi meaning ‘income’. (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीघ्रलिखित<BR>śīghra-likhita, a document written in a quick hand or<BR>cursive characters (SII, Vol. XI, Part i, p. 29, No. 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिग्लोस्<BR>siglos (IE 8-8), name of the old silver coin of the Persians<BR>(86. 45 grains or 5.6 grammes).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिकावण<BR>sikāvaṇa (EI 27), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिखर|शिखरं|शिखरः<BR>śikhara (SITI; CITD), top portion of the turret built<BR>over the main shrine and the gateway of a temple; the top of<BR>the gopura or vimāna of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिखिन्<BR>śikhin (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिला<BR>śilā (IA 23), [an inscription on] stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलागृह<BR>śilā-gṛha (EI 22), a stone mansion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलागुण्ठ<BR>śilā-guṇṭha (EI 12), Sanskrit-Telugu; a pond with a<BR>demarcation stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाकर्मान्त<BR>śilā-karmānta (LL), stone-work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाकूट<BR>Śilā-kūṭa (EI 1), a stone-cutter; cf. Śilā-kuṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाकुट्ट<BR>Śilā-kuṭṭa (IA 15), a stone-cutter; cf. Śilā-kūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलालष्टि<BR>śilā-laṣṭi (CII 4), Sanskrit śilā-yaṣṭi; memorial pillar<BR>of stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलालेख<BR>śilā-lekha (IA 30; SITI), writing on a stone; an ins-<BR>cription on stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीलन|शीलनं<BR>śīlana (CII 1), same as anuśīlana; practice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीलपत्र<BR>śīla-patra (LP), certificate of good character.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाप्रावेश<BR>śilā-prāveśa (IA 9), laying the corner-stone of a building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाशासन<BR>śilā-śāsana (IA 30), a stone-charter; a document engraved<BR>on stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्पिन्<BR>Śilpin (EI 4, 8; BL), epithet of an artist or artisan;<BR>generally, applied to engravers of inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्पकार|शिल्पकारः<BR>Śilpakāra (EI 32), same as Śilpin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोतर<BR>śilotara (EI 32), also called śilotarī, śilotra, śilotrī, śilot-<BR>tara; name of a tax or income; cf. śrotaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोतरी<BR>śilotarī (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोत्र<BR>śilotra (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोत्री<BR>śilotrī (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोत्तर<BR>śilottara (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्वरि<BR>śilvari (EI 23), Tamil; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीम<BR>sīma (IA 18), used for ‘country’ in the areas on the banks<BR>of the Kṛṣṇā and the Godāvarī.<BR>Cf. Kona-sīma (EI 32), also called a deśa, maṇḍala, sthala, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमा<BR>sīmā (EI 11), five types enumerated by Nārada: Dhvajinī<BR>matsyinī c = aiva naidhānī bhaya-varjitā | rājaśāsana-nītā ca sīmā pañca-<BR>vidhā smṛtā (i. e. big trees or hills, rivers or tanks, under-<BR>ground signs and artificial marks made by men and by the king's<BR>order).<BR>Cf. Tamil śīrmai, śīmai (SITI), a territorial division; also<BR>called sīman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमकर्मकर<BR>Sīmakarmakara (HD), officer in charge of boundaries or<BR>of boundary disputes. See CII, Vol. III, pp. 213, 216.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमन्<BR>sīman (IE 8-4; ASLV), Kannaḍa sīmĕ; a small terri-<BR>torial unit like a Parganā; the sub-division of a district; some-<BR>times used to indicate ‘a province’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमाविवाद|सीमाविवादः<BR>sīmā-vivāda, cf. Tamil śīmai-vivādam (SITI), a boundary<BR>dispute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीमेहब्बरुव<BR>Śīmĕhabbaruva (ASLV), an officer associated with the ad-<BR>ministrative unit called sīmai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहनिका<BR>siṃhanikā, service rendered in lieu of taxes (Ghoshal, H.<BR>Rev. Syst., p. 28).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहपाद<BR>siṃha-pāda, cf. Tamil śiṅga-pādam (SITI), legs of a vessel<BR>or vessel-stand in the shape of lion's feet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहासन|सिंहासनं|सिंहासनः<BR>siṃh-āsana (EI 29), literally, ‘the lion-seat’; the throne<BR>which was one of the royal insignia. Cf. siṃha-sthāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहासनाधिपति<BR>Siṃhāsan-ādhipati (EI 25), officer in charge of the king's<BR>throne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहस्तम्भ<BR>siṃha-stambha (LL), lion-pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहस्थान<BR>siṃha-sthāna (LL), a lion-seat; same as siṃh-āsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिन्धु|सिंधु|सिंधुः|सिन्धुः<BR>sindhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिन्दूर|सिंदूर|सिन्दूरं|सिंदूरः|सिन्दूरः<BR>sindūra (IA 19), corruption of sindhura, an elephant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीरा<BR>sīrā (IA 18), a land measure equal to four halas. See hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरःप्रधानिन्<BR>Śiraḥ-pradhānin (ASLV), cf. Tamil Śirappradāni (SITI),<BR>a senior minister; cf. Pradhāni, Mahāpradhāni, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरःस्थायिन्<BR>śiraḥ-sthāyin (IA 17), used in the description of a trial by<BR>ordeal with reference to the bearing of some sacred symbol or<BR>image on the head of the accused while undergoing it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिरकटा<BR>sira-kaṭā, cf. sira-kaṭā tambā-paṭā (JBORS, Vol. XVIII,<BR>pp. 219-20), Oḏiyā; same as rakata-paṭā, Sanskrit rakta-paṭṭaka.<BR>See also rakta-mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिरिडिक<BR>siriḍika, siriḍikā (EI 32), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरोरक्षिक<BR>Śiro-rakṣika (IE 8-3), body-guard of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरोवर्त्तना<BR>śiro-varttanā (SII 2), top part of a Śiva-liṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीर्षक|शीर्षकं|शीर्षकः<BR>Śīrṣaka (EI 28), village headman; same as Mutuḍa or<BR>Muḻuḍa of South Indian inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरुपाडु<BR>śirupāḍu (EI 30), Tamil; an endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिष्षिन्ति<BR>śiṣṣinti (IA 18), modification of śiṣya-paṅkti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिष्य|शिष्यः<BR>Śiṣya (SII 1), a pupil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीता<BR>sītā (EI 31), cultivated land. Cf. hala.<BR>(HRS), produce of the royal farms, as suggested by the<BR>Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सितचामर<BR>sita-cāmara (EI 29), ‘white chowrie’; one of the royal<BR>insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीताधयक्ष<BR>Sīt-ādhayakṣa (CII 4), officer in charge of the king's Khās<BR>Mahāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीतालेख्य<BR>sītālekhya (IA 12), chilly-powder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीतांशु|शीतांशुः<BR>śītāṃśu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सितपिञ्छ<BR>sitapiñcha (SII 2), a swan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीतरश्मि|शीतरश्मिः<BR>śītaraśmi (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीतारि<BR>śītāri (SITI), Tamil; burning of incenses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिथिलाचार्य<BR>Śithil-ācārya (IA 19), Jain; an Ācārya permitting laxity<BR>of observances.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीत्क<BR>sītka (EI 11), a well.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिव|शिवं|शिवः<BR>śiva (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR>(SITI), title applied to a Śaiva devotee; often śiva, śambhu<BR>etc., are used as the ending of the names of Śaiva ascetics.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिव|शिवं|शिवः<BR>śiva, cf. śrīvijaya-śiva-Mṛgeśavarman; used as an honorific.<BR>Cf. śrī, vijaya, vijayaśiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवभाण्डारिन्<BR>Śiva-bhāṇḍārin (SITI), treasury officer of a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवब्राह्मण<BR>Śiva-Brāhmaṇa (EI 25; SITI), a Śaiva Brāhmaṇa; the<BR>priest of a Śiva temple; also called Ādi-śaiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवदीक्षा<BR>śiva-dīkṣā (EI 32), same as śaiva-dīkṣā, śiva-maṇḍala-dīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवद्रोहिन्<BR>Śiva-drohin (ASLV), a sinner against the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवमान<BR>śiva-māna (EI 33), a measure approved by a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवमण्डलदीक्षा<BR>śivamaṇḍala-dīkṣā (EI 32), same as śaiva-dīkṣā, śiva-dīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवपञ्चायतन<BR>Śiva-pañcāyatana (EI 27), a Śiva temple consisting of five<BR>shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवस्थल<BR>śiva-sthala (CII 2-1), probably, the same as dharma-sthāna,<BR>or a Śiva shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवतिथि<BR>Śiva-tithi (EI 5), same as Śiva-rātri or Śiva-caturdaśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवयोगिन्<BR>Śiva-yogin (SITI), a Śaiva ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कम्भ|स्कंभ|स्कंभः|स्कम्भः<BR>skambha (LL), a post or pillar; cf. dīpa-skambha (LL), a<BR>lamp post. Same as Kannaḍa kamba, kamma. Cf. stambha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्दक|स्कंदक|स्कंदकः|स्कन्दकः<BR>Skandaka (HD), a petty officer; probably the head of the<BR>village administration. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 175.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्दक|स्कंदक|स्कंदकः|स्कन्दकः<BR>skandaka (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIII, p. 69), an instalment;<BR>cf. skandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्ध|स्कंध|स्कंधः|स्कन्धः<BR>skandha (LP), an instalment; cf. skandaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्धक<BR>skandhaka (EI 3; HRS), known from Gujara-Pratīhāra<BR>records; name of a tax; probably, a cess at a certain rate per<BR>shoulder-load.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्धावार|स्कंधावार|स्कन्धावारः<BR>skandhāvāra (EI 29; CII 3; BL), camp; usually called<BR>jaya-skandhāvāra (i. e. the victorious camp) which indicates the<BR>capital of a king in some cases. Cf. Kannaḍa neleviḍu = Sans-<BR>krit sthira-śibira.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्लो<BR>ślo (IE 8-1), abbreviation of śloka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्लोत्र<BR>ślotra (EI 32), same as śilotara, etc.; cf. śrotaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्मत्<BR>smat (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्मृत्युपस्थान<BR>smṛty-upasthāna, cf. satipaṭṭhāna (EI 5), Buddhist; four<BR>in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्नानयात्रा<BR>snāna-yātrā (IA 9), festival of bathing the image of<BR>Kṛṣṇa on Jyaiṣṭha su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्नानमहोत्सव<BR>snāna-mahotsava (HA), bathing ceremony (i. e. birth-<BR>bath) of a Jina performed by Indra and other gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सो<BR>So (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Soma-vāra, Monday.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोडशी<BR>śoḍaśī, śoḍaśikā (SII 4), name of a coin which may have<BR>been (1/16) of the standard coin in weight or value; cf. paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षोडशिन्<BR>ṣoḍaśin (EI4, 22; CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोद्रङ्गीकृत्य<BR>sodraṅgīkṛtya (IE 8-3), same as udraṅgīkṛitya; used in res-<BR>pect of a gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोलग<BR>śoḻaga (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोम|सोमं|सोमः<BR>soma (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमग्रहण<BR>soma-grahaṇa (SII 1), lunar eclipse; same as soma-parvan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमपर्वन्<BR>soma-parvan (LP), lunar eclipse; same as soma-grahaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमस्कन्द<BR>Somaskanda, South Indian representation of Śiva along<BR>with Umā and Skanda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमवती<BR>somavatī (IA 26), same as ba-di 15 falling on a Monday.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमयाग|सोमयागः<BR>soma-yāga (CII 4), name of a Vedic sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमयाजिन्<BR>Somayājin (SITI), one who has performed the soma-yāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपान|सोपानं<BR>sopāna (SITI), steps; stairs; a sloping roof; the base of<BR>the garbha-gṛha of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोतेर्<BR>Soter (IE 8-2), Greek; ‘saviour’; royal title; translated<BR>into Prakrit as Tratara = Trātara (Sanskrit Trātṛ).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोटी<BR>śoṭī (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, pot for measuring liquids<BR>like wine; a ladleful; name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्पार्हविहारता<BR>spārha-vihāratā, cf. Prakrit phāsu-vihālatā (CII 1), comfort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्पष्ट|स्पष्टं<BR>spaṣṭa (CII 3), an astronomical term meaning ‘apparent’;<BR>cf. spaṣṭa-tithi, ‘an apparent tithi’, from which the mean tithi<BR>has to be determined.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्फोटन|स्फोटनं<BR>sphoṭana (IE 8-5), cf. śira-sphoṭana, ‘breaking somebody's head.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्फुरम्<BR>sphuram, quickly (Select Inscriptions, p. 240).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रा<BR>Śrā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Śrāvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्ध|श्राद्धं<BR>śrāddha (CII 4), funeral rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रद्धादान<BR>śraddhā-dāna (ML), a pious gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्धाङ्ग<BR>śrāddh-āṅga (EI 28), gift for the merit of a deceased person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्धकर<BR>śrāddha-kara, tax for performing śrāddha at Gayā (Rājatar.,<BR>VI. 254; VII. 1008).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्धतिथि<BR>śrāddha-tithi (CII 4), date on which the śrāddha is to be<BR>performed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राहे<BR>śrāhe, also spelt śrāhi, srāhi, śrāhī, srāhī, ‘the year’ (pro-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-316" target="_blank">Page-316+ 40</a>]<BR>bably derived from Prakrit sarahi, Sanskrit śaradi, ‘in the year’);<BR>the period of 12 months. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 80, note<BR>2; Vol. XXIX, p. 106; Vol. XXX, p. 161, note 12; XXXII,<BR>p. 233 and note 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राहि<BR>śrāhi, śrāhī (IE 8-1; EI 6, 23), probably, derived from<BR>Sanskrit śaradi = Prakrit sarahi; ‘in the year’; ‘the year’; used<BR>sometimes in place of saṃvat, but sometimes side by side with<BR>it. See srāhe, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्राहि<BR>srāhi, srāhī, same as srāhe, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमण|श्रमणः<BR>Śramaṇa (EI 8; CII 3; LL; BL), a Buddhist or Jain monk;<BR>an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणश्राविका<BR>Śramaṇa-śrāvikā (LL), female disciple of Jain ascetics.<BR>Cf. Śramaṇ-opāsaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रामणेर|श्रामणेरः<BR>Śrāmaṇera (EI 25), cf. Sāmanera (EI 2); Buddhist; a<BR>novice monk; cf. the feminine form Śrāmaṇerī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणिका<BR>Śramaṇikā (LL), cf. Samaṇikā (EI 25), a Buddhist nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणोद्देश<BR>Śramaṇoddeśa (LL), Buddhist; a novice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणोपासक<BR>Śramaṇ-opāsaka (LL), lay follower of Buddhist Śramaṇas.<BR>Cf. Śramaṇa-śrāvikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावक|श्रावकः<BR>Śrāvaka (EI 7, 8, 24; ML; LL; HA), a lay follower of<BR>Jainism or Buddhism; cf. the feminine form Śrāvikā, sometimes<BR>called Śrāvikā bhaginī in Jain records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावक|श्रावकः<BR>śrāvaka (CII 1), ‘a matter relating to a declaration’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावण|श्रावणः<BR>śrāvaṇa (SITI), also called śrāvaṇa-patra (q. v.), sale deed;<BR>a document; cf. śālāvaṇam (SITI), a sale deed (āvaṇa-śālāvaṇam).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावणपत्र<BR>śrāvaṇa-patra (EI 30), a deed of declaration; a sale-deed.<BR>Cf. śrāvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राविका<BR>Śrāvikā (HA), cf. Sāvikā (EI 7), Jain; a female lay wor-<BR>shipper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावित<BR>śrāvita, cf. rāja-śrāvita (EI 6; IA 19), decree; a procla-<BR>mation.<BR>(EI 28), religious instruction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रे<BR>śre (PJS; LP), contraction of Śreṣṭhin, ‘a banker’ or<BR>śreyase, ‘for the merit of … ’ (especially in medieval Jain ins-<BR>criptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेणि|श्रेणिः<BR>śreṇi, śreṇī (CII 3, 4; LL), Prakrit seni (EI 25); a cor-<BR>poration or guild; cf. śreṇī-bala, the army maintained by a<BR>guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेणिकरण<BR>śreṇi-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of guilds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेष्ठिजीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय<BR>śreṣṭhi-jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya, wrongly read as śreṣṭha (LP),<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-317" target="_blank">Page-317+ 40</a>]<BR>probably a mistake for jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya; name of a<BR>coin struck by Śreṣṭhin Viśvamalla. See jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla<BR>(or śrīmalla) -priya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेष्ठिन्<BR>Śreṣṭhin (IE 8-3; CII 4; LL), a banker or merchant or<BR>the foreman of a guild; sometimes mentioned in the list of the<BR>king's officials and subordinates addressed by him while making<BR>a grant (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR>(BL), representative of the banker class in the council of<BR>the local administrators of a town. Cf. Śeṭṭi, Nagara-śreṣṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्री<BR>śrī (CII 3, etc.), honorific prefix to names often rendered<BR>variously in English; e. g., in the case of paramount sovereigns<BR>and their wives by ‘glorious’; of feudatories and other ordinary<BR>persons by ‘illustrious’; of priests, teachers, etc., by ‘saintly’;<BR>of gods by ‘holy’; sometimes śrī is used before consonants and<BR>śrīmat before vowels. The honorific śrī is sometimes used in<BR>South Indian records along with the words vijaya or vijaya-śiva<BR>(q. v.). Cf. śrī-ni, Śrīcaraṇa, etc.<BR>(IA 17), cf. śrī-pūrva used for śrī-yuta; śrī is sometimes<BR>repeated for emphasis, e. g., ‘śrī 108’ is written to indicate the<BR>repetition of the word for 108 times.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीबलि<BR>śrī-bali (SITI), daily offering of the bali service in temples;<BR>also havir-bali. Cf. Tamil śrī-bali-koṭṭuvār, a musical troupe<BR>playing on the instruments at the time of the śrī-bali in temples.<BR>(SITI), image of the deity taken round the temple<BR>when the bali is offered; the procession circumambulating the<BR>temple at the time of the bali service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीबलिभोग<BR>śrī-bali-bhoga (SITI), land set apart to meet the expenses<BR>of the śrī-bali service in a temple; also called śrī-bali-ppaṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीभाण्डार<BR>śrī-bhāṇḍāra (EI 33; SITI), the treasury of a temple.<BR>(ASLV), collective name for the trustees of a temple; same<BR>as śrībhaṇḍāra-vāriyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीभण्डारवारियम्<BR>śrībhaṇḍāra-vāriyam (EI 33), executive body in charge of<BR>the administration of a temple. Cf. śrī-bhāṇdāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीचन्दन<BR>Śrīcandana, a title of nobility in medieval Orissa (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXVIII, p. 310, text lines 8-9). Cf. Haricandana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीचरण<BR>Śrī-caraṇa (IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28), literally, ‘the honourable<BR>feet [of the king]’; the king; cf. Śrī-hasta, Śrī-pāda, śrī-ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीद्वार<BR>śrī-dvāra (EI 6), a special type of gateway like the makara-<BR>toraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीघन|श्रीघनं|श्रीघनः<BR>śrīghana (SII 1), glorious.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीगोशाला<BR>śrī-gośālā, cf. Tamil tiru-kkośālai (SITI), cow-stall of<BR>a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीहस्त<BR>Śrī-hasta (IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28), literally, ‘the honourable<BR>hands [of the king]’; the king; see Śrī-caraṇa, Śrī-pāda, śrī-ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीज्ञान<BR>śrī-jñāna, cf. Tamil tiru-ñānam (SITI), sacred hymns sung<BR>to the deity in a temple during worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकण्ठमणि<BR>śrī-kaṇṭhamaṇi, cf. tiru-kkaṇṭamaṇi (SITI), a kind of<BR>necklace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकार|श्रीकारः<BR>śrīkāra (LP), recognition by writing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरण|श्रीकरणं<BR>śrīkaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 11, 21, 31; HD), the drafting of docu-<BR>ments; a scribe or scribe-accountant or secretary; the minister<BR>Hemādri was styled Sarva-śrīkaraṇa-prabhu (Hist. Dharm., Vol. I,<BR>p. 356, note 849). Cf. Karaṇa, Śrī-karaṇ-ādhipa, śrīsrīkaraṇa.<BR>(EI 23, 29, 30), record office; the record department;<BR>the department responsible for drawing up documents.<BR>(EI 30; CII 4), record officer; the officer in charge of<BR>drawing documents.<BR>Cf. Puravuvari-śrīkaraṇa-nāyaka (EI 21), official designation.<BR>Cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the income department.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणाधिप<BR>Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa (IE 8-3; HD), superintendent of the<BR>department of records; head of all the scribes or of all the depart-<BR>ments. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 17. Hemādri was styled<BR>Samasta-karaṇ-ādhīśvara or Samasta-karaṇ-ādhipati (Hist. Dharm.,<BR>Vol. I, pp. 356-57, notes 850-51). See śrīkaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणाग्रणी<BR>Śrīkaraṇ-āgraṇī (HD), same as Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकारमुद्राङ्कित<BR>śrīkāra-mudr-āṅkita (LP), sealed with the syllable śrī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणप्रभु<BR>Śrīkaraṇa-prabhu (IE 8-3), same as Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणविदितम्<BR>śrīkaraṇa-viditam (LP), ‘having informed the records office<BR>or officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणिन्<BR>Śrīkaraṇin (EI 26), same as Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकार्य<BR>śrī-kārya (SII 2), management of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकटक<BR>śrī-kaṭaka (LP), royal camp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीखण्ड|श्रीखंड|श्रीखण्डः<BR>śrīkhaṇḍa (LP), also spelt śrīṣaṇḍa; sandal wood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीखण्डघोडु<BR>śrīkhaṇḍa-ghoḍu (LP), a kind of horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमाड<BR>śrīmāḍa (EI 10), palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमदादिवराहद्रम्म<BR>śrīmad-ādivarāha-dramma (EI 1), name of a coin, issued<BR>by king Ādivarāha (Bhoja I Pratīhāra, c. 835-85 A.D.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमाहेश्वर<BR>Śrī-māheśvara (ASLV), a Śaiva ascetic who is one among<BR>the authorities of a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमलय<BR>śrī-malaya, cf. Tamil tiru-malai (SITI), literally, ‘the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-319" target="_blank">Page-319+ 40</a>]<BR>sacred hill;’ but really, the central shrine, generally of a Śiva<BR>temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमालिका<BR>śrī-mālikā, cf. Tamil tiru-māḻigai-ppatti (SITI), small shrines<BR>or niches in the prākāra of a temple on the inner side of the com-<BR>pound wall. Cf. tiru-māḻigai-ppiḻḷai, the temple executive.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमन्दिर<BR>śrī-mandira, cf. Tamil tiru-mandiram (SITI), a temple;<BR>also tiru-mandira-kkoḍi, cloth threaded round the flag-staff of a<BR>temple during festivals. See also Tiru-mandirav-olai, a secre-<BR>tary of the government; an officer entrusted with the duty of<BR>communicating the decisions of the king in writing; also Tiru-<BR>mandirav-olai-nāyakam, the chief secretary to the government;<BR>chief of the tiru-mandirav-olai department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमल्<BR>śrīmal (CII 3; IA 13), prefixed, like śrī, to names of per-<BR>sons and also of places; often used before names beginning with<BR>a vowel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमुख|श्रीमुखः<BR>śrī-mukha (SII 12; SITI), royal order or charter; a<BR>letter from the king or a chief. Cf. Tamil tiru-muga-kkāṇam,<BR>expenses as wages, etc., paid to the person who brings the<BR>tiru-mugam (royal order) to the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनक्षत्र<BR>śrī-nakṣatra, cf. Tamil tiru-nakṣatra (SITI), natal star;<BR>annual birthday; a year.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनामन्<BR>śrī-nāman, cf. Tamil tiru-nāma-kkāṇi, tiru-nāmattu-kkāṇi<BR>(SITI), literally, ‘the hereditary right of enjoyment in the<BR>sacred name’; actually, land or village, generally tax-free,<BR>endowed to a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनयन<BR>śrī-nayana, cf. Tamil tiru-nayanam (SITI), an ornament<BR>made of gold or silver resembling the eye and put on the eyes<BR>of the idol; same as Tamil kaṇ-malar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनि<BR>śrī-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Śrīhasta-nirīkṣita, ‘examined<BR>by the king’. See ni and Śrī-hasta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपाद<BR>Śrīpāda (IE 8-8), used to indicate ‘the king’; cf. Śrī-caraṇa,<BR>etc.; also Tamil Śrīpādaṅgal (SITI), an exalted personage; used<BR>as an expression of respect.<BR>Cf. Tamil śrīpadatāṅgikaḻ (SITI), vehicle-bearers attached<BR>to a temple, as supporting the feet of the god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपश्चिममन्दिर<BR>śrī-paścima-mandira, cf. Tamil tiru-meṟ-koyil (SITI), sacred<BR>temple in the west; a Viṣṇu temple which is situated to the<BR>west of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपट्ट<BR>śrī-paṭṭa (EI 15), royal charter or seal.<BR>(EI 2), diadem bestowed [upon a favourite] by the king.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-320" target="_blank">Page-320+ 39</a>]<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 344), same as rāja-paṭṭa or paṭṭī (EI 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपट्टिका<BR>śrī-paṭṭikā, cf. Tamil tiru-ppaṭṭigai (SITI), girdle worn<BR>by the image of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीफल|श्रीफलः<BR>śrīphala (EI 9), the bilva fruit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपृथिवीवल्लभ<BR>Śrī-pṛthivī-vallabha (IE 8-2), literally, ‘the husband of<BR>[the goddesses] Śrī and Pṛthivī (i. e. the god Viṣṇu)’; title<BR>assumed by some kings of the Deccan probably claiming to be<BR>incarnations of the god Viṣṇu; often abbreviated as Śrīvallabha<BR>or Vallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीराम|श्रीरामः<BR>Śrī-Rāma (ASLV), sign manual of some kings of Vijaya-<BR>nagara who often wrote Śrī-Virūpākṣa for the purpose.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीरङ्ग|श्रीरंग|श्रीरङ्गः<BR>śrī-raṅga, cf. Tamil tiru-araṅgu (SITI), same as raṅga-<BR>maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीरुद्र<BR>Śrī-rudra (SITI; ASLV), also called Śrī-rudra-māheśvara;<BR>a Śaiva devotee; same as Śrī-māheśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीसामन्त<BR>Śrīsāmanta (EI 21, 26), sometimes a personal name (e. g.<BR>Sandhivigrahin Śrīsāmanta who was the writer of a royal<BR>charter) and sometimes a designation (as in Kaṃsāra-kulapu-<BR>traka-śreṣṭhin Śrīsāmanta-Svayambhū who was the engraver of the<BR>same charter). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 240.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीश्रीकरणादिसमस्तमुद्राव्यापार<BR>śrīśrīkaraṇ-ādi-samasta-mudrā-vyāpāra, cf. mudrā-vyāpāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवल्लभ|श्रीवल्लभः<BR>Śrīvallabha (IE 8-2), cf. Śrī-pṛthivī-vallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवत्स|श्रीवत्सः<BR>śrīvatsa (SII 2), mole on Viṣṇu's chest; sometimes<BR>represented in the shape of a crown as found in the Hathingumpha<BR>inscription of Khāravela.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीविजय<BR>śrī-vijaya, cf. śrī-vijaya-Nandivarman, śrī-vijaya-Veṅgīpura,<BR>etc. See The Successors of the Sātavāhanas, p. 63. Cf. śrī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीविजयशिव<BR>śrī-vijaya-śiva, honorific prefixed to the names of a few<BR>South Indian kings; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 152, text<BR>line 4; The Successors of the Sālavāhanas, p. 63. Cf. śrī, vijaya-<BR>śiva, śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीविमान<BR>śrī-vimāna (SII 2, 13), same as vimāna; central shrine<BR>in the temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवीरूपाक्ष<BR>Śrī-Vīrūpākṣa (ASLV), sign manual of the Vijayanagara<BR>kings, Virūpākṣa being their tutelary deity. Cf. Śrī-Rāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवीथिनायक<BR>Śrī-vīthi-nāyaka, cf. Tamil Tiru-vidi-nāyakar (SITI), a metal-<BR>lic image of the deity for being taken in procession along the<BR>streets round the temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शृङ्ग|शृंग|शृंगं|शृङ्गं|शृङ्गः<BR>śṛṅga (EI 14), mentioned in relation to a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शृङ्गारभोग<BR>śṛṅgāra-bhoga (EI 5), same as raṅga-bhoga (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रोतक<BR>śrotaka (IE 8-5; EI 32), a kind of rent; cf. śrotra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रोत्र|श्रोत्रं<BR>śrotra (IE 8-5; EI 32), probably, a tax in kind collected<BR>from farmers by a lessee of State lands; same as Marāṭhī<BR>śilotara, śilotarī or śilotrī; cf. śrotaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रोत्रिय|श्रोत्रियः<BR>śrotriya (SITI), land or a village granted to a Śrotriya or<BR>Brāhmaṇa learned in the Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रुतदेवता<BR>śruta-devatā (EI 2), the goddess of eloquence.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रुति|श्रुतिः<BR>śruti (SII 1), a Vedic text.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रुतिमान्<BR>Śrutimān (SITI), elders of a community looking after<BR>its affairs; perhaps adapted from Tamil Keḻvi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्र्याज्ञा<BR>śry-ājñā, cf. Tamil śrīy-ājñai (SITI), royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्र्यमृत<BR>śry-amṛta, cf. Tamil tiruv-amudu (SITI), food offering<BR>(mainly, rice) to a deity in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्तम्भ|स्तंभ|स्तंभः|स्तम्भः<BR>stambha (BL), a tower.<BR>(LL), a pillar. Cf. skambha.<BR>(IE 8-6; EI 3), same as Kannaḍa kamma, kamba, kambha;<BR>a land measure equal to one-hundredth of a mattaru or nivartana.<BR>(SITI), lamp-stand or lamp-post.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्था<BR>sthā, cf. paratra sthāpayitvā (LP), ‘by laying it out at in-<BR>terest’; yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāpanaṃ sthāpayitvā, ‘besides raising the<BR>pillar’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 136). See sthāpayitvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थल्<BR>sthaḻ (IA 15), a standard for measuring gardens.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थल|स्थलं<BR>sthala (IE 8-4), shortened form of deva-sthala; sometimes<BR>suffixed to names of localities; also the subdivision of a district.<BR>(IE 8-4; EI 12, 18, 24; ASLV), a small territorial unit<BR>like a Parganā; a district or its subdivision. Cf. Kona-sthala<BR>(EI 32), also called a deśa, maṇḍala, rāṣṭra, sīma, etc.<BR>(CITD), a place, habitation; a holy place; a district.<BR>Cf. sa-jala-sthala (IE 8-5); the land [of a village].<BR>Cf. Tamil sthala-kkāval (SITI), village watch.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलदुर्ग<BR>sthala-durga (ASLV), fort built on the plains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलगौड<BR>Sthala-gauḍa (ASLV), officer associated with the admi-<BR>nistration of the unit called sthala; cf. Sthala-karṇam, Gauḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थालक|स्थालकः<BR>sthālaka (EI 19), explained as ‘a back-bone.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलकरण<BR>Sthala-karaṇa, cf. Sthala-karṇam (q. v.)., a village official<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 261).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलकर्णम्<BR>Sthala-karṇam (ASLV), an accountant-clerk associated<BR>with the administration of the unit called sthala. Cf. Sthala-karaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलपथकरण<BR>[sthala]-patha-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of<BR>roadways.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलपुराण<BR>sthala-purāṇa (IA 30), a eulogistic work on a holy place,<BR>river, etc. Cf. māhātmya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलवृत्ति<BR>sthala-vṛtti (EI 13), explained as ‘a tenure in which pay-<BR>ment of tax was made in kind from the produce’; cf. tala-vṛtti<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 273).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थली<BR>sthalī (IE 8-4), shortened form of deva-sthalī; sometimes<BR>suffixed to names of localities; also the subdivision of a district<BR>(EI 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थाम्य<BR>Sthāmya (EI 24), wrong reading of Sthāyin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थान|स्थानं<BR>sthāna (EI 8), residence.<BR>(IE 8-4; SITI), literally, ‘a place’; abbreviation of deva-<BR>sthāna or a temple; sometimes suffixed to names of localities.<BR>Cf. bhagavato … sthāne (Lüders, Mathurā Ins., p. 62, text lines<BR>2-3).<BR>(LL), also sthānaka, a temple; cf. Sthānika, Sthānattār.<BR>(SII 1), a shrine; cf. mahāsthāna, a great temple.<BR>(IA 3), a Bhūta temple.<BR>Cf. tāna-mānam (SITI), dignity or honour attached to<BR>a status or office.<BR>Cf. siṃha-sthāna (LL), same as siṃh-āsana.<BR>(SII 11-1), cf. Kannaḍa thāna; name of a geographical<BR>unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थान|स्थानं<BR>Sthāna (CII 4), a superintendent cf. Sthānapāla, etc.<BR>(EI 9), cf. ‘officer in charge of the sthānas.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानभूमि<BR>sthāna-bhūmi (EI 24), land belonging to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाचार्य<BR>Sthān-ācārya (EI 5, 6, 16, 28), priest of a temple; the<BR>chief priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानदान<BR>sthāna-dāna (LP), allowing one to stand somewhere, i. e.<BR>allotting some land to one.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिकार|स्थानाधिकारः<BR>sthān-ādhikāra (IA 18), office of the superintendent of<BR>a shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिकरणिक<BR>Sthān-ādhikaraṇika (EI 3, 6, 24), officer in the administra-<BR>tion of an outpost; see Sthān-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिकृत<BR>Sthān-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 24), modern Thānādār; officer<BR>in charge of a police or military outpost; cf. Gaulmika. See<BR>Sthān-ādhipati, Sthānapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिपति<BR>SThān-ādhipati (CITD), same as Sthān-ādhyakṣa, Sthānapati,<BR>etc.; a local governor; superintendent of a place; a watch-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-323" target="_blank">Page-323+ 39</a>]<BR>man; a police officer; often also called Sthānika-dharma-kartṛ.<BR>(EI 24), officer in charge of an outpost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानक|स्थानकं<BR>sthānaka (LL), same as sthāna, a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानकरण<BR>sthāna-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the public<BR>works department’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानलक<BR>Sthānalaka (CII 4), a local officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानमहाजन<BR>Sthāna-mahājana (EI 31), same as Tamil Sthānattār (Sanskrit<BR>Sthānastha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानमान्य<BR>sthāna-mānya (CITD), probably, land granted by the<BR>ruler to his officers for their maintenance in lieu of salary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानान्तरिक<BR>Sthānāntarika (IE 8-3; EI 23, 28, 29), probably, superin-<BR>tendent of encampment or transfer of the king's residence from<BR>one camp to another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानपाल|स्थानपालः<BR>Sthānapāla (EI 15; HD), officer in charge of a police out-<BR>post. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 149.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानपति<BR>Sthānapati (IE 18), a civil agent kept by the Nāyakas at the<BR>imperial court at Vijayanagara.<BR>(EI 18, 28), officer in charge of an outpost.<BR>(IA 18), designation associated with a religious office;<BR>cf. Sthān-ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानत्तार्<BR>Sthānattār (SITI; ASLV), Sanskrit Sthānastha; managers<BR>of a temple; the temple executive.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानिक|स्थानिकः<BR>Sthānika (IA 12; ASLV), superintendent or manager<BR>of a temple; cf. Tamil Tānigar (SITI), temple executive; also<BR>Tānika-rāyar, director of the temple ceremonies.<BR>(EI 8), title of priests in Jain temples.<BR>(EI 28), an officer belonging to an outpost probably serving<BR>under the Sthānapati, or the same as the Sthānapati.<BR>(HD), an officer in charge of a ward of a city or a district.<BR>See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, pp. 143 and 149.<BR>(HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) officer in charge<BR>of one-fourth of the kingdom; (2) officer in charge of one-<BR>fourth of a city.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थापनाचार्य<BR>Sthāpan-ācārya (HA), same as Thavaṇī (q. v.). Cf. Sthān-<BR>ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थपति|स्थपतिः<BR>Sthapati (EI 4; BL; HD), a mason or architect. See<BR>Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 39.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थपतिसम्राज्<BR>Sthapati-samrāj (CII 3; HD), ‘the chief of architects’;<BR>the chief architect. See CH, Vol. III, p. 119.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थापयित्वा<BR>sthāpayitvā, cf. Prakrit ṭhapaīchaṃ (CII 2-1), literally,<BR>‘having kept’; relly, ‘besides’, ‘in addition to … ’; cf. yaṣṭi-<BR>pratiṭhanaṃ ṭhapaīchaṃ (Sanskrit yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāpanaṃ sthāpayit-<BR>vā), ‘in addition to the erection of the memorial pillar’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थावर|स्थावरं|स्थावरः<BR>sthāvara, cf. sa-sthāvara-jaṅgama (IE 8-5); the immovable<BR>belongings of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविर|स्थविरं|स्थविरः<BR>Sthavira (CII 3, etc.), a Buddhist priestly title; same as<BR>Pāli Thera; an Elder in the community of Buddhist monks; a<BR>senior monk. Cf. Thaira (EI 3), an Elder among Buddhist<BR>monks; also Saṅgha-sthavira (Lüders, Mathurā Ins., p. 190),<BR>‘the senior of the order’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविरकल्पिन्<BR>Sthavira-kalpin (HA), a Jain Sādhu whose practices are not<BR>so rigorous as that of a Jina-kalpin and are easier to practise.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविरी<BR>Sthavirī (LL), Buddhist; a senior nun; Pāli Therī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविरीय<BR>Sthavirīya, cf. Prakrit Therīya (EI 33), community of the<BR>Buddhist monks called Sthaviravādin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थायिन्<BR>Sthāyin (wrongly read as Sthāmin in Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV,<BR>p. 145, text line 2), possibly, the permanent tenants of a village.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 234. Cf. Āsthāyika-puruṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थिरा<BR>sthirā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 181), a permanent<BR>endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थिरशिबिर<BR>sthira-śibira (IA 12), same as Kannaḍa nele-vīḍu; ‘a stand-<BR>ing camp’; capital; cf. jaya-skandhāvāra of the Pāla inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थित|स्थितः<BR>sthita (CII 1), same as upasthita, present.<BR>(BEFEO, Vol. XLIII, p. 6, text lien 15), same as pratiṣṭhita,<BR>installed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितक<BR>sthitaka (EI 11), perpetual grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थिति|स्थितिः<BR>sthiti (EI 32), decree.<BR>(IE 8-5), regulation; see ācāra-sthiti.<BR>(EI 12), usage; practice [in respect of calculation of<BR>dates]; Mālava-gaṇa-sthiti-vāśāt=kāla-jñānāya likhiteṣu, ‘[in the<BR>years … ] written for the knowledge of time (i. e. the<BR>date of some event) according to the practice [of calculation]<BR>of the Mālava republic’; Mālavānāṃ gaṇa-sthityā yāte śata-catuṣ-<BR>ṭaye, ‘four hundred years … having elapsed according to<BR>the practice [of calculation] of the Mālavas.”<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिपात्र<BR>sthiti-pātra (IE 8-5), same as ācāra-sthiti-pātra (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXX, p. 169); a document containing regulations; see<BR>sthiti-vyavasthā, etc. Pātra seems to be used for patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिपत्रक<BR>sthiti-patraka (EI 32), a record of decision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिपात्रव्यवस्था<BR>sthitipātra-vyavasthā (IE 8-5), same as sthiti-pātra or ācāra-<BR>sthithi-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिव्यवस्था<BR>sthiti-vyavasthā (IE 8-5), same as sthiti-pātra or ācāra-sthiti-<BR>pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थूणा<BR>sthūṇā (ML), a pilaster.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्रतेग<BR>Stratega (IE 8-2, 8-3), Greek Strategos (q. v.), com-<BR>mander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्रतेगोस्<BR>Strategos (IE 8-2, 8-3), Greek; commander of forces,<BR>transliterated as Stratega (q. v.) in Indian records; a feudatory<BR>or gubernatorial title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्रीधन|स्त्रीधनं<BR>strī-dhana (SITI; ASLV), dowry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्र्यध्यक्ष|स्त्र्यध्यक्षः<BR>Stry-adhyakṣa (IE 8-3; CII 1), superintendent of matters<BR>concerning the ladies of the royal household; cf. Antaḥpur-<BR>ādhyakṣa, Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्र्यध्यक्षमहामात्र<BR>Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra (HD), Prakrit Ithijhakha-mahā-<BR>māta, etc.; superintendent of the harem. See CII, Vol. I, p. 20.<BR>Cf. Antaḥpura-mahāmātra in the Masulipatam plates of<BR>Amma II (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्तूप|स्तूपः<BR>stūpa (CII 3; BL; LL), technical name of a type of<BR>Buddhist monument; a Buddhist structure enshrining relics.<BR>Sometimes the term ratna-gṛha (i. e. the house enshrining the<BR>three ratnas or the best amongst the three) seems to be used to<BR>denote a stūpa.<BR>(EI 2), a Jain religious establishment.<BR>(SITI), pinnacle of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्तुपी<BR>stupī, same as vimāna (IA 9), q. v.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शु<BR>śu (IE 8-1; CII 3; LP), abbreviation of śukla-pakṣa or<BR>śuddha-pakṣa or the bright fortnight; a day of the bright half of<BR>the month; used in connection with di (e. g. śu-di), but some-<BR>times by itself; often written as su. Cf. ba-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सु<BR>su, cf. śu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुभाषित|सुभाषितः<BR>subhāṣita (CII 4), a pithy saying in a stanza.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुभ्र|शुभ्रं|शुभ्रः<BR>śubhra (IA 17), used to indicate the bright fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूचि|सूचिः<BR>sūci (LL), sūcī (EI 15), a rail bar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुदि<BR>śu-di (IE 8-1), abbreviation of śukla (or śuddha) -pakṣa-dina<BR>(or divasa), often written as su-di. See śu-ti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुदि<BR>su-di (IE 8-1), mistake for śu-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुद्धावास<BR>śuddh-āvāsa (IA 10), Buddhist; ‘pure abode’ being five<BR>in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुधाकर्मन्<BR>sudhā-karman (EI 23), white-washing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुधांशु|सुधांशुः<BR>sudhāṃśu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुदिवसा<BR>su-divasā (IA 18; CII 1), an auspicious day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुकनास|शुकनासः<BR>śuka-nāsa, cf. śukanāsi (Arch. Rev., 1960-61, Section III)<BR>literally, ‘a parrot's nose’ explained as ‘a gargoyle or<BR>the water spout in a building’ (Acharya, Ind. Arch., p. 169)<BR>and ‘a vestibule’ (R. Narasiṃhachar, The Keśava Temple of<BR>Somanāthapur, p. 3); but also as ‘the projection of the main<BR>body of the śikhara of a temple originally at the front-<BR>side’ (Kramrisch, Hindu Temple, p. 241); also called śuk-<BR>āṅghri. The Dīpārṇava (ed. Prabhāśaṅkar O. Sompurā, p. 116)<BR>has the following stanzas on the subject:<BR>agre kolī kapolas = tu śuka-nāsas = tu nāsikā |<BR>sāndhāre stambha-rekhā ca kartavyā madhya-koṣṭhake ||<BR>prāsādasya puro-bhāge nirvāṇa-mūla-śṛṅgakam |<BR>tad-agre śuka-nāśaṃ ca ek-ādi saptam = udgamam ||<BR>tasy = opari siṃhaḥ sthāpyo maṇḍapa-kalaśa-samaḥ |<BR>dvi-stambhaḥ śuka-nās-āgre vijñeyaḥ pāda-maṇḍapaḥ ||<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुकरकवि<BR>Sukara-kavi (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 231, note 1), epithet of<BR>a poet; cf. Āśu-kavi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखा<BR>sukhā (IA 26), same as su-di 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखडि<BR>sukhaḍi, sukhaḍī (LP), Gujarātī; also spelt suṣaḍī; a kind<BR>of sweetmeat; a reward.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखन<BR>sukhana, sukhanā (CII 1), ‘causing happiness’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखासन<BR>sukh-āsana (Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 95), translated as ‘a<BR>palanquin’; enumerated as one of the five prasādas granted by<BR>a king to a subordinate. Cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखसङ्कथाविनोद<BR>sukha-saṅkathā-vinoda (IA 8), ‘the delight of pleasing<BR>conversation’; cf. ‘while he was ruling, with the delight of<BR>pleasing conversation, at the capital of Kalyāṇa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुक्रनेत्र<BR>śukra-netra (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुकृत|सुकृतं<BR>sukṛta (CII 1), a good deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुक्ति|शुक्तिः<BR>śukti, same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूल|शूलं|शूलः<BR>śūla (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’; cf. triśūla, a trident.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुलपाल<BR>Śulapāla (EI 11), probably, an associate of the courtesans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुलतान<BR>Sulatāna (BL), Indian modification of a title of the<BR>Muhammadan kings; same as Arabic Sulṯān. Cf. Sulitāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूलवरि<BR>śūlavari (EI 25), Tamil; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूलिन्<BR>śūlin (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुलितान<BR>Sulitāna (BL), Indian modification of a title of the<BR>Muhammadan kings; same as Arabic Sulṯān. Cf. Sulatāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्क|शुल्कं|शुल्कः<BR>śulka (IE 8-5; EI 12, 23, 25, 30; CII 4; CITD), tolls;<BR>customs duties; octroi duties; taxes particularly levied at ferries<BR>and passes and on roads, etc.; cf. krīḍara-śulka (EI 5), name of<BR>a tax; also śuṅgam, śuṅkam (SITI), customs, tolls.<BR>(HRS), tax, probably identical with bali according to<BR>early authorities; ferry dues, tolls and transit duties according<BR>to the Smṛtis and lexicons; according to the Arthaśāstra, (1)<BR>duties levied upon articles imported into a city, (2) port-dues,<BR>(3) duty upon the sale of liquors, (4) customs collected by<BR>the ferrymen and boundary-officers, (5) duty upon mining<BR>products, (6) duty upon imported salt, and (7) duty upon<BR>animals intended for slaughter; according to Śukra, tolls and<BR>duties upon building-sites, etc. The Amarakoṣa explains śulka<BR>as ghaṭṭ-ādi-deya and Kṣīrasvāmin enumerates the dues as ferry<BR>duties, tolls paid at military stations or police outposts and<BR>transit duties paid by merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्काधिकार<BR>śulk-ādhikāra, cf. suṅk-ādhikāra (EI 5), ‘office for the collec-<BR>tion of tolls [of the Banavāsi District]’. Same as Śulk-ā-dhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कग्राह<BR>Śulkagrāha (HD), an official who collected tolls or cus-<BR>toms duties. See Śukra, II. 128.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कमण्डपिका<BR>śulka-maṇḍapikā (EI 3, 9), customs house. See śulka-śālā.<BR>(CII 4), explained by some as ‘a market-pavilion’.<BR>(Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 329 and note 31), translated as ‘the<BR>rent office’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कशाला<BR>śulka-śālā, cf. śuṅga-śālai (SITI), place where tolls are<BR>collected; a customs house. See śulka-maṇḍapikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कातियात्रिक<BR>śulk-ātiyātrika (IE 8-8; EI 30), boundary-crossing fee;<BR>exit tax; cf. atiyātrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुमन्त्र|सुमन्त्रः<BR>Sumantra (HD), king's counsellor on matters relating<BR>to income and expenditure. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 114,<BR>note 150.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूना<BR>sūnā (HRS), royal dues collected by the superintendent of<BR>the slaughter-house, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुण्डक<BR>suṇḍaka (IA 19), meaning doubtful; probably, a bundle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्क<BR>suṅka (EI 12), a corrupt form of śulka often found in<BR>South Indian inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्कपन्नायदधिष्ठायक<BR>Suṅkapannāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit;<BR>superintendent of the income from tolls. See Suṅka-vĕrgaḍĕ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्कवेर्गडे<BR>Suṅka-vĕrgaḍĕ (EI 19), Kannaḍa; official designation;<BR>Sanskrit Śulk-ādhyakṣa. See Suṅkapannāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शून्य|शून्यं|शून्यः<BR>śūnya (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शून्यग्राम<BR>śūnya-grāma, cf. ‘she made a further grant of five śūnya-<BR>grāmas’ (Arch. Rev.,) 1960-61, Section III, No. 44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुण्यारा<BR>Suṇyārā, Sunyārā (Chamba), a goldsmith; from Sanskrit<BR>Suvarṇakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूपकारपति<BR>Sūpakārapati (EI 13; HD), the chief cook. See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XIII, pp. 109, 115. Cf. Bhānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ, Mahānas-ādhyakṣa,<BR>Ma(Mā)hānasika, Khādya(kū*)ḷapākika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुपर्ण|सुपर्णः<BR>Suparṇa (EI 2), a class of demi-gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुप्रभात|सुप्रभातं<BR>suprabhāta (IA 12), name of the morning worship at the<BR>Rāmeśvara temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुप्रदार्य<BR>supradārya (CII 1), ‘easy to enter’, ‘easy to do’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुर|सुरः<BR>sura (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरभि|सुरभिः<BR>surabhi, see surahī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरही<BR>surahī (HA), Sanskrit surabhi; inscribed stone with the<BR>representation of a cow with her calf and the sun and the moon<BR>in the upper part, the inscriptions usually recording gifts or<BR>donations or exemptions from obligations or taxes declared<BR>by kings. This indicated permanence and inviolability.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुराकरण<BR>surā-karaṇa (EI 30), distillation of liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरताण<BR>Suratāṇa (IE 8-2; EI 12), same as Arabic Sulṯān; see<BR>Suratrāṇa, Sulatāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरत्राण<BR>Suratrāṇa (IE 8-2; EI 4, 1, 13, 32; BL), variously spelt<BR>as Suritrāṇa, Suratāṇa, etc.; Hindu adaptation of the Muslim<BR>royal title Sulṯān; often adopted as a personal name. Cf.<BR>Hammīra. See Sulatāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरवाल<BR>Suravāla (EI 33), one who sets songs or musical instru-<BR>ments to tune.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूरि|सूरिः<BR>Sūri (EI 9), title of Jain religious teachers; often used as<BR>their name-ending.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरित्राण<BR>Suritrāṇa (BL), same as Suratrāṇa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्य|सूर्यः|सूर्य्य|सूर्य्यः<BR>sūrya (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्यभ<BR>sūrya-bha (JAHRS, Vol. II, p. 287, text line 64), literally,<BR>‘the sun's asterism’, the Hastā-nakṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्यग्रह|सूर्यग्रहः|सूर्य्यग्रह|सूर्य्यग्रहः<BR>sūrya-graha (EI 24), solar eclipse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्यपर्वन्|सूर्य्यपर्वन्<BR>sūrya-parvan (IA 19; LP), solar eclipse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुश्रूषा<BR>śuśrūṣā (CII 1), obedience; cf. dharma-śuśrūṣāṃ śuśrūṣatu,<BR>‘one should practise obedience to morality.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुत|सुतः<BR>suta (IE 7-1-2), confused with Pāṇḍu-suta and used to<BR>indicate ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत|सूतः<BR>Sūta, one of the king's high functionaries (ratna or ratnin);<BR>cf. Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 111.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुतचेला<BR>Suta-celā (BL), a pupil or disciple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुति<BR>śu-ti (IE 8-1), contraction of śukla (or śuddha) -pakṣa-tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्र|सूत्रं<BR>sūtra (IA 20), a manual of religious rituals, etc.<BR>(HRS), royal receipts collected by the superintendent of<BR>weaving, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR>(IE 3-1), same as śarayantraka; the string holding the<BR>leaves of a manuscript together (Vāsavadatta, Hall's ed., p. 250).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्र|सूत्रं<BR>Sūtra (PJS), abbreviation of Sūtradhāra, a mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रभृत्<BR>Sūtrabhṛt (EI 33), same as Sūtradhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधार|सूत्रधारः<BR>Sūtradhāra (EI 24; CII 4; BL), a mason; an artisan; an<BR>epithet generally applied to the engravers of stone inscriptions<BR>of the medieval period. See Sūtrabhṛt, Sūtradhṛt, Sūtradhārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधारपितामह<BR>Sūtradhāra-pitāmaha, cf. pitāmaha (IA 19); ‘the very<BR>Brahman among the masons’; title of a mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधारिन्<BR>Sūtradhārin (EI 15), same as Sūtradhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधृत्<BR>Sūtradhṛt (EI 31), same as Sūtradhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रान्तिक<BR>Sūtrāntika (LL), a Buddhist monk versed in the sūtra<BR>works. See Sūtrāntikinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रान्तिकिनी<BR>Sūtrāntikinī (LL), a Buddhist nun versed in the sūtra works.<BR>See Sūtrāntika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुत्तेए<BR>suttee (CII 3, etc.), see satī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्ण|सुवर्णं|सुवर्णः|सुवर्ण्ण<BR>suvarṇa (IE 8-8; EI 28; CII 3), name of a gold coin and<BR>also of a weight of gold; equal to 16 māṣas or 80 ratis; also<BR>called akṣa, picu, pāṇi, kroḍa, binduka, viḍālapadaka, haṃsapada,<BR>grāsagraha and tola. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46.<BR>(SII 13), same as Tamil kaḻañju.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णदण्ड<BR>suvarṇa-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28), tax on goldsmiths;<BR>same as Tamil taṭṭar pāṭṭam, etc., noticed in Appendix II.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णादाय<BR>suvarṇ-ādāya (CITD), same as suvarṇ-āya. Cf. hiraṇya,<BR>etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णाध्यक्ष<BR>Suvarṇ-ādhyakṣa (EI 24), official designation; probably<BR>the same as Suvarṇavthy-adhikṛta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णकार|सुवर्णकारः<BR>Suvarṇakāra (EI 24, BL), a goldsmith; often the epithet<BR>of the engravers of copper-plate grants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णवीथ्यधिक्त<BR>Suvarṇavīthy-adhikta (EI 18), superintendent of the gold-<BR>smith's business. Suvaṇa-vīthī literally means ‘the quarters of<BR>the goldsmiths’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णाय<BR>suvarṇ-āya (also called suvarṇ-ādāya); land revenue paid in<BR>cash. Cf. hiraṇya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुवास्तियम्<BR>śuvāstiyam (SITI), Tamil; right of hereditary enjoyment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वभ्र|श्वभ्रं<BR>śvabhra, cf. sa-vana-śvabhra-nidhāna; a pit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वदेशिन्<BR>Svadeśin (CITD), often used with the word Para-deśin or<BR>Nānādeśin with reference to the two main communities of<BR>traders and merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वहस्त|स्वहस्तः<BR>sva-hasta (EI 23; CII 3; IA 8), signature or sign-manual.<BR>Cf. sva-hast-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a receipt.<BR>(Ind. Ep., p. 187, verse 77), used to indicate a grant of<BR>land because the donor's signature was required to be put on a<BR>deed of grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वःश्वः|श्वःश्व<BR>śvaḥ-śvaḥ (CII 1), daily; same as ahar-ahaḥ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वल्प|स्वल्पः<BR>svalpa (EI 24), small; sometimes prefixed to the name of<BR>a locality (e. g. Svalpa-Vallūra), etc., to distinguish it from<BR>others of the same name but styled ‘big’ or ‘medium’. Cf.<BR>Kṣudra-Dharmagiri and Mahā-Dharmagiri; Vaḍa-Hosa and Maṃjhi-<BR>Hosa (EI 35).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वामिन्<BR>Svāmin (IE 8-3; EI 24; CII 3; LL), royal title probably<BR>of foreign origin, assumed by the kings of Śaka-Kuṣāṇa ex-<BR>traction; adopted by indigenous rulers like the Śātavāhanas.<BR>Cf. Śāmi (SITI), the king.<BR>Cf. Vihāra-svāmin (founder or master of a monastery), etc.<BR>(EI 7), same as Svāmi-Mahāsena, i. e. Kārttikeya.<BR>(EI 23), designation of the member of a guild.<BR>(EI 5), cf. ‘the 500 Svāmins of Aiholĕ’; probably meaning<BR>the Māheśvaras.<BR>Cf. svāmi-vāram (SITI), land-lord's share; same as<BR>Tamil mel-vāram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वामिभोग<BR>svāmi-bhoga (EI 8; SII 3), ‘the master's share’; the land-<BR>lord's share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वामिनी<BR>Svāminī (CII 3), a noble lady or mistress. Cf. also<BR>Vihāra-svāminī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वमुखाज्ञा<BR>sva-mukh-ājñā (CII 3), ‘the order or command from one's<BR>own mouth’; used with reference to the king's verbal order for<BR>the preparation and issue of charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वाम्य|स्वाम्यं<BR>svāmya (SITI), ownership; right to property; cf. ubhaya-<BR>svāmya (EI 5), tejaḥ-svāmya; also mameya-svāmya (SII 11-1),<BR>tenure held by a Manneya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर|स्वरः<BR>svara (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वरत्राण<BR>Svaratrāṇa (BL), same as Suratrāṇa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्ग|स्वर्गः<BR>svarga (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyone’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्ण|स्वर्णं<BR>svarṇa, cf. śoṇa-vari (SITI), svarṇa-vari, explained as ‘tax<BR>payable in gold'; same as Tamil pŏn-vari; but cf. also suvarṇa-<BR>daṇḍa, profession-tax payable by the goldsmiths.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णभाण्डारिन्<BR>Svarṇa-bhāṇḍārin, cf. Poṉ-paṇḍārigal (EI 33), members of<BR>the administrative council of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णादाय<BR>svarṇ-ādāya (SII 1; SITI), ‘revenue in gold’; taxes pay-<BR>able in coin. Cf. hiraṇya, suvarṇ-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णदण्ड<BR>svarṇa-daṇḍa, see suvarṇa-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णकार|स्वर्णकारः<BR>Svarṇakāra (EI 24), a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णक्ष्मा<BR>svarṇa-kṣmā (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णमेरु<BR>svarṇa-meru (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वरूप|स्वरूपं|स्वरूपः<BR>svarūpa (SITI), an estate of the Nambūdris, royal per-<BR>sonages, etc., of Malai-nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसमय<BR>sva-samaya (EI 24), explained as a Jain doctrine; the doc-<BR>trines of one's own religion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्ति<BR>svasti (CII 3, 4), welfare; auspicious word used at the<BR>beginning of some inscriptions to ensure success of the under-<BR>taking; an exclamation used at the commencement of inscrip-<BR>tions. Sometimes used as a neuter noun, with astu in the<BR>maṅgala at the end of documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्तिकपट्ट<BR>svastika-paṭṭa (LL), slab with the representation of a<BR>svastika symbol.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्त्ययन<BR>svastyayana (EI 31), rite for averting evil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वतल<BR>sva-tala (EI 11), surface of the ground [of the gift land].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वतन्त्र|स्वतंत्र|स्वतन्त्रः<BR>svatantra (SITI), a share; a customary fee; emoluments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वयंवर|स्वयंवरः<BR>svayaṃvara (EI 8), the bride's selection of her husband.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतच्छत्र<BR>śveta-cchatra (EI 29), ‘the white umbrella’; one of the<BR>royal insignia; same as śvet-ātapatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतगरुत्<BR>śveta-garut (SII 2), swan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेताम्बर|श्वेतांबर|श्वेताम्बरः<BR>śvetāmbara (IA 7), a Jain sect; same as Śvetapaṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतपट<BR>Śvetapaṭa (IA 7), same as Śvetāmbara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतातपत्र<BR>śvet-ātapatra (EI 29), ‘the white umbrella’, one of the<BR>royal insignia; same as śveta-cchatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वोलिकापात<BR>svolikā-pāta, svolī-pāta (EI 1), meaning doubtful. Svo = kho?<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्याद्वाद|स्याद्वादः<BR>syādvāda (EI 3; SII 1), Jain; also called syādvāda-mata,<BR>syādvāda-vidyā; scepticism.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्यारमल्लिक<BR>Syāramallika (EI 33), probably Persian Sair Malik (i. e.<BR>Malik-us-Sai), collector or taxes, Sair meaning ‘tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तबु<BR>tabu (IA 20, 29), a taboo.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तदानियुक्तक<BR>Tad-āniyuktaka (IE 8-3; EI 23), official designation; same as<BR>Tad-āyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तदात्व|तदात्वं<BR>tadātva (CII 1), the present time; the time being.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तदायुक्तक<BR>Tad-āyuktaka (IE 8-3; EI 6, 23), an officer who was a<BR>subordinate to the Āyuktaka; mentioned along with Viniyuktaka;<BR>cf. Tad-āniyuktaka, Tan-niyuktaka, Tad-viniyuktaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तादायुक्तक<BR>Tādāyuktaka (EI 15), same as Tad-āyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तद्भव<BR>tad-bhava (IA 7), a word in Prakrit or the regional languages,<BR>which is modified from a Sanskrit word.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तद्विनियुक्तक<BR>Tad-viniyuktaka (IE 8-3), same as Tad-āyuktaka or Tan-<BR>niyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तगरपति<BR>Tagarapati (EI 13), mistake for Nagarapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैल|तैलं<BR>taila, oils; a branch of revenue according to the Artha-<BR>śāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 90.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलाभ्यङ्ग|तैलाभ्यंग|तैलाभ्यङ्गः<BR>tail-ābhyaṅga (IA 22), cf. abhyaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलघाणक<BR>taila-ghāṇaka (EI 19), oil mill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलपर्णिका<BR>taila-parṇikā (EI 24), explained as ‘leaves producing oil’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलिकराज<BR>Tailika-rāja (EI 23), ‘chief of a guild of oilmen’; desig-<BR>nation of the chairman of the oilmen's guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैर्थिक<BR>Tairthika (EI 32), same as Tīrthika, a priest [of the non-<BR>Buddhists].<BR>(IE 8-3), cf. Tūthika (EI 1; LL), ferry-officer or officer<BR>in charge of the places of pilgrimage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताजिक|ताजिकः<BR>Tājika Tajjika (EI 23, 32), Tājiya, Tāyika; an Arab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाका<BR>ṭākā, Bengali form of ṭaṅka, meaning a silver coin (rupee)<BR>and also money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठाकोर्खाना<BR>ṭhākorkhānā (HA), same as balānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तक्षाचार्य<BR>takṣ-ācārya, cf. Tamil tacc-ācāriyam (SITI), the status of<BR>the master carpenter; chief of the carpenters. Cf. tacc-ācāriya-<BR>kkāṇi, the right of officiating as the chief carpenter, as also the<BR>stone-mason of a temple; the land set apart for the enjoyment<BR>of the holder of that office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तक्षन्<BR>takṣan (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तल|तलं|तलः<BR>tala, cf. sa-tala (IE 8-5); surface of the ground.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताल|तालं|तालः<BR>tāla (IE 8-5), a palmyra palm; cf. sa-tālaka as an epithet<BR>of a gift village referring to the right of enjoying the trees by<BR>privileged tenants in some areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताल|तालं|तालः<BR>tāla (SII 2), Tamil; a dish.<BR>(EI 21; SITI), Tamil; the treasury<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभेद्या<BR>tala-bhedyā (IA 18), word of uncertain implication; men-<BR>tioned with ghāṇaka, mallaka, vundhaka etc. (IA 18); cf. talabhedyā-<BR>ghāṇaka-mallaka-vundhaka-daṇḍadoṣa-prāpt-ādāya (Ind. Ant., Vol.<BR>XVIII, p. 83, text lines 19-20), epithet of gift village. See<BR>tala-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभोग<BR>tala-bhoga (IA 7; SII 11-1), explained as ‘the enjoyment<BR>of sites of land’; really, ‘land granted for the maintenance of a<BR>temple at the time of its consecration’; same as tala-vāṭaka,<BR>tala-vṛtti, and probably also tala-bhedyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालध्वज|तालध्वजः<BR>Tāladhvaja (BL), official designation of the governor of a<BR>territory; same as Gujarātī Tāḻājā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैवन्<BR>Talaivan (SII 1), Tamil; a chief.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैयारि<BR>Talaiyāri (SII 1), Tamil; same as Kannaḍa Talāri; a<BR>watchman. See Talavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलक|तलकं<BR>talaka (LP), ‘on the spot’.<BR>(EI 23), a territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलाक<BR>taḻāka (EI 14), same as taṭāka, taḍāga; a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलपद<BR>tala-pada (HRS), known from Caulukya records; lands<BR>fully assessed for revenue, as distinguished from estates which<BR>were held on condition of service or for a reduced lump assess-<BR>ment; explained as Gujarātī talpat, ‘land paying rent to the<BR>government’ (IA 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलपाट<BR>tala-pāṭa (SITI), Tamil; an army; armaments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालपत्र|तालपत्रं<BR>tāla-patra, Tamil olai (SITI); literally, ‘palmyra-leaf’;<BR>an order from the king or a person in authority. Cf. olai-ccāda-<BR>nam, ‘a document written on palm-leaf’; olai-ccampaḍam, ‘wages<BR>paid to the messenger who brings the olai to meet his expenses<BR>on the way’; also written as olai-ccambaḻam, olai-ccammāḍam, etc.;<BR>same as nirūpa-ccambaḍam; cf. olai-nāyaka, ‘the chief secretary<BR>or the senior officer looking after correspondence.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालपट्ट<BR>tāla-paṭṭa (IA 15), probably the same as tāla-patra, mean-<BR>ing ‘an ear-ornament’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलप्रहारिन्<BR>Talaprahārin (EI 6), official designation; probably the<BR>same as Talārī or Kotwāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलार<BR>Talāra (IE 8-2; EI 22; LP; BL; HD), administrator of<BR>a city or prefect of the city police; same as Talavara, Talārī or<BR>Kotwāl. Talavara of early South Indian inscriptions means<BR>a Rājasthānīya (a Duke or a viceroy) according to some<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-334" target="_blank">Page-334+ 40</a>]<BR>commentators and the Kotwāl or a city magistrate according to<BR>others. A subdivision of high class Khatris of the Punjab is<BR>called Tālwār. Cf. Tala-rakṣa or Tal-ārakṣa; also called Ārakṣika<BR>and Daṇḍapāśika. See Bhandarkar's List, No. 579; IHQ, 1960,<BR>p. 266.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलाराभाव्य<BR>talār-ābhāvya (EI 11), tax for payment to the Talāra; ac-<BR>cording to some, Talāra is the Kotwāl and bhāvya or ābhāvya is<BR>what is called saṃbhāvanā, i. e. pāghḍī, and talār-ābhāvya is the<BR>pāghḍī money given to the Kotwāl (LP).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलारी<BR>Talārī (IE 8-2), Telugu-Kannaḍa; ‘a village watchman’;<BR>same as Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलारिक<BR>talārika (ASLV), the office of the Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलारक्ष<BR>Tal-ārakṣa (EI 22), same as Talavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलाटी<BR>Talāṭī (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 165, noted 38), a<BR>stipendiary (i. e. not hereditary) village accountant in the<BR>Kannaḍa-and Marāṭhī-speaking areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवर<BR>Talavara (IE 8-2; EI 20, 28), a title of the nobility or of<BR>subordinate rulers in some cases (a Rājasthānīya according<BR>to Vinayavijaya's Subodhikā commentary on the Jain Kalpa-<BR>sūtra); but the designation of the administrator of a city or of<BR>the police officer in charge of a city, according to some sour-<BR>ces (Hemacandra explaining Talāra as Nagara-rakṣaka); cf.<BR>Talāra, Talārī, etc.; also Mahātalavara.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 78), cf. Talavara mentioned in<BR>the list of royal officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवर्गिक<BR>Talavargika (EI 3), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवारिका<BR>talavārikā, cf. Kannaḍa taḻavārikā (EI 1), the village-<BR>watchman's quit-rent; cf. Taḻavāra or Talāri (Tamil Talaiyāri),<BR>‘a village-watchman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालावारिक<BR>Tālāvārika (IA 12), official designation; same as either<BR>Talārī or Talāṭī (a stipendiary village-accountant in the<BR>Marāṭhī-and Kannaḍa-speaking areas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवाटक<BR>tala-vāṭaka (EI 31), same as tala-pāṭaka or tala-vṛtti. But<BR>cf. tala-vāṭaka in tala-vāṭaka-vāstunā saha kṣetram, ‘a piece of<BR>land together with suburbs, gardens and homestead land’<BR>(Select Inscriptions, p. 349, text line 18). The meaning here<BR>may also be ‘adjoining land’ which was probably the original<BR>implication of the expression.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलावाटक<BR>Talāvāṭaka (CII, Vol. III, p. 216; also p. 217 and note),<BR>possibly the superintendent of temple property (cf. tala-vāṭaka);<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-335" target="_blank">Page-335+ 40</a>]<BR>same as Gujarātī Talāṭī (a petty revenue officer), accord-<BR>ing to some (HD).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवृत्ति<BR>tala-vṛtti (EI 13, 15, 21, 33; IA 7; SII 11-1; SITI),<BR>‘endowment of the adjoining land’; land granted for the main-<BR>tenance of a temple or deity at the time of its consecration;<BR>same as tala-bhoga, tala-vāṭaka, tala-pāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालि|तालिः<BR>tāli, tālī (EI 1), a measure of liquor.<BR>(SII 3), the marriage badge; cf. māṅgalya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तल्लज|तल्लजः<BR>tallaja (SII 1), excellent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टं|ट|टः<BR>ṭaṃ (Chamba, etc.), abbreviation of ṭaṃkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्बूलदानाधिकृत<BR>Tāmbūladān-ādhikṛta (EI 19), officer supplying betel<BR>bīḍās to the king. Cf. Vārgulika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्बूलकवाहक<BR>Tāmbūlaka-vāhaka (EI 28), bearer of the king's betel-<BR>box; same as Oḏiyā Vāguli. See Tāmbūladān-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्बुलिक<BR>Tāmbulika (EI 28), producer and seller of betel leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तम्बूरु<BR>tambūru (ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तमिल्<BR>Tamil, name of an alphabet and language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तम्मडि<BR>Tammaḍi (CITD), Telugu; also called Tammaḻa, Tāṃbaḻi,<BR>Taṃbala-vāḍu and Taṃbiga; a Śaiva priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्र|ताम्रं|ताम्रः<BR>tāmra (IE; EI 8, 23), same as tāmra-śāsana; a copper-plate<BR>grant; also land granted by means of such charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रहार<BR>Tāmrahāra, cf. Tāmerā (EI 16), a coppersmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रक|ताम्रकं<BR>tāmraka (IE; EI 1, 4), same as tāmra-paṭṭa; a copper-plate<BR>grant; also gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रपत्र|ताम्रपत्रः<BR>tāmra-patra (EI 23), also called tāmra-paṭṭa, tāmra-<BR>paṭṭaka; same as tāmra-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रपट्ट|ताम्रपट्टं|ताम्रपट्टः<BR>tāmra-paṭṭa (EI 19, 23, 24; CII 4; Chamba), a copper-<BR>plate charter; gift land. Cf. tāmra-patra, tāmra-paṭṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रपट्टक<BR>tāmra-paṭṭaka (EI 4, 23), same as tāmra-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रफली<BR>tāmra-phalī (EI 22), a copper plate. Cf. triphalī-tāmra-<BR>śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रप्रशस्ति<BR>tāmra-praśasti (CII 4), culogy written on copper plates;<BR>a copper-plate charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रशासन<BR>tāmra-śāsana (IE; EI 23; CII 3), a copper-charter; a techni-<BR>cal term for a deed of conveyance written on copper plates; also<BR>gift land. See śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तान|तानं|तानः<BR>tāna (IE 7-1-2), ‘fortynine’; but sometimes used to<BR>indicate ‘thirtyfour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तनयप्राप्त<BR>tanaya-prāpta (CII 3), ‘an adopted son’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताण्डव|तांडव|तांडवं|ताण्डवं|तांडवः|ताण्डवः<BR>tāṇḍava (CII 4), name of the dance of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डुल|तंडुल|तंडुलः|तण्डुलः<BR>taṇḍula, unit of measurement; half of a dhānya-māṣa (JNSI,<BR>Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डुलपर्वत<BR>taṇḍula-parvata (IA 9), name of a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाङ्क्<BR>ṭāṅk (IA 26), also called tāṅkī, etc.; same as ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्क|टंक|टंकं|टंकः|टङ्कः<BR>ṭaṅka (EI 9, 20; CII 4; ML), name of a coin; cf. Vijayarāja-<BR>ṭaṅka, ṭaṅka issued by Vijayarāja; spelt often as ṭaṅkā and in old<BR>Bengali as taṅkā; same as śāna also called dharaṇa; a coin in<BR>general; regarded as equal to 4 silver fanams; name applied to<BR>both gold and silver issues 80 ratis in weight (JNSI, Vol.<BR>XXII, pp. 197-98); silver coins of the Delhi Sulṯāns--96 or 100<BR>ratis in weight. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 42-49. Cf. śāśukāni-<BR>ṭaṅka, hema-ṭaṅka, raupya-ṭṅka; also ṭaṅka (LP), a copper coin<BR>equal to half of a pice.<BR>(Chamba), a copper coin equal to (1/20) of a Rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कक|टंकक|टंककः|टङ्ककः<BR>ṭaṅkaka (EI 19; CII 4; BL), name of a coin; a silver<BR>coin. Cf. ‘ṭaṅkakas stamped with the figure of the Bhagavat’<BR>(Bhandarkar's List, No. 2033).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कशाला<BR>ṭaṅka-śālā, cf. Tamil iṭaṅka-śālai (SITI), a mint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कशालाकरण<BR>ṭaṅka-śālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of minting<BR>coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्मात्र|तन्मात्रं<BR>tanmātra (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्नियुक्तक<BR>Tan-niyuktaka (IE 8-3); an officer probably under the Āyukta;<BR>same as Tad-āyuktaka or Tad-viniyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्तलि<BR>tantali (IE 8-5), a tamarind tree; cf. sa-tantalika,<BR>epithet of a gift village referring to the right to enjoy such<BR>trees by privileged tenants in some areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्र|तंत्र|तंत्रं|तन्त्रं<BR>tantra (ASLV), army, government; cf. Tantrin in South<BR>Indian inscriptions.<BR>(SITI), army, mainly the infantry; cf. Tantrin in<BR>South Indian inscriptions.<BR>(CII 4), explained as ‘Home Affairs’.<BR>(LP), cf. tantre nirūpita, ‘officially sent’.<BR>(HIQ, Vol. XXXIV, p. 277), cf. Tantr-ādhikārin, ‘officer<BR>in charge of administration’, in the Bhāturiyā inscription of<BR>Rājyapāla. In this case, a person was at first a Mantrin, then<BR>a Saciva and finally a Tantr-ādhikārin.<BR>Cf. Sarva-tantr-ādhikṛta (EI 24), superintendent of all<BR>departments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्राधिकारिन्<BR>Tantr-ādhikārin (EI 33), also called Tantr-ādhyakṣa, Tan-<BR>trapāla, etc.; probably, officer in charge of administration. See<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-337" target="_blank">Page-337+ 40</a>]<BR>Sarvatantr-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्राधिप<BR>Tantr-ādhipa (EI 25, 29; CII 4), same as Tantr-ādhikārin, etc.;<BR>minister for home affairs, according to some. See Sarvatantr-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्राध्यक्ष<BR>Tantr-ādhyakṣa (EI 33), same as Tantr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR>See Sarvatantr-ādhikṛta, Tantrapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रकरण<BR>tantra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the political<BR>department’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रनायक<BR>Tantra-nāyaka (ASLV), official designation associated<BR>with tantra meaning the army or government. See Tantr-ādhi-<BR>kārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रपाल<BR>Tantrapāla (SITI), chief of the army.<BR>(IE 8-3; EI 33), probably, officer in charge of adminis-<BR>tration; cf. Mahātantr-ādhyakṣa, Sarva-tantr-ādhikṛta, Tantra-<BR>pati and Mahātantr-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR>(HD), an officer like the Chargé-d' Affaires, according to<BR>some; cf. Tantrapāla-Mahāsāmanta-Mahādaṇḍanāyaka (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XIV, p. 185; cf. Vol. V, p. 77).<BR>(Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34), explained<BR>as ‘an officer of the king's bodyguard or royal retinue.’<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 77), explained as ‘a councillor.’<BR>(SII 11-2), cf. Tantrapālaradhiṣṭhāyaka; also Tantra-<BR>pāladadhiṣṭhāyaka (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रपति<BR>Tantrapati (IE 8-3); HD), occurs in the Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>VIII. 2322; explained as Dharm-ādhikārin, ‘officer in charge of<BR>the department of justice and charity’; see Bṛhattantrapati. Cf.<BR>the Muslim official designations Sadrus-Sudūr, etc., explained as<BR>‘the chief judge and officer in charge of the king's charities’<BR>(Journ. As. Soc. Pak., Vol. IV, pp. 53-54).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रवाय|तंत्रवाय|तन्त्रवायः<BR>Tantravāya (EI 24), a weaver. Cf. lunnavāya = a tailor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रिन्|तंत्रिन्<BR>Tantrin (SITI; ASLV), a soldier; a trooper; a leader<BR>of the army; a temple priest; a weaver. It has been sup-<BR>posed that the Tamil words Kaikkoḻar and Aṭavi came to signify<BR>both a soldier and a weaver on the analogy of the word Tantrin<BR>used in both the senses. Cf. Tantrimār, members of the army<BR>corps; a class of persons who perform worship in temples; a priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तनु|तनुः<BR>tanu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; rarely used to indicate ‘eight’.<BR>(Select Inscriptions, pp. 241, 245); one's own; see tanuvaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तनुवक<BR>tanuvaka (CII 2-1), Prakrit; used in the sense of svakiya;<BR>see tanu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तपन|तपनः<BR>tapana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’ with reference to Agni; but<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-338" target="_blank">Page-338+ 40</a>]<BR>‘twelve’ with reference to ‘the sun’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तपस्विन्<BR>tapasvin (SITI), an ascetic; a recluse; a religious mendicant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तापत्रय<BR>tāpa-traya (SII 1), the three kinds of pain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तापित<BR>tāpita (EI 23, 24), ‘heated’ [for affixing the seal to a cop-<BR>per-plate grant].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तपोधन|तपोधनः<BR>Tapodhana (CITD), in Telugu-Kannaḍa records, often<BR>used to indicate Jain monks; in Orissan records, a Śaiva ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तार्<BR>tār (SII 1), name of a silver coin, equal to (1/6) of a gold<BR>fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तर|तरः<BR>tara (EI 9), same as nilaya; the family aggregate of dwel-<BR>lings with some of them meant for servants and artisans; also a<BR>street or a hamlet.<BR>(HRS), same as tara-deya, ferry dues, as indicated by the<BR>Arthaśāstra. See tārya.<BR>Cf. taram (EI 7), revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरदेय<BR>tara-deya, ferry dues. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 78, 227.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरपणी<BR>tarapaṇī (HA), a wooden water-vessel used by Jain<BR>monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरपति|तरपतिः<BR>Tarapati (IE 8-3; CII 4; HD), officer in charge of the<BR>ferries; superintendent of the ferries; cf. Tarika and Tairthika;<BR>but see Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321, where Tarika and Tara-<BR>patika are separately mentioned, and Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p.<BR>306, text line 35 where Tarapati is likewise mentioned sepa-<BR>rately from Tarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवर<BR>Taravara (EI 20, 25), same as Talavara (q. v.); official<BR>designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवुशात्तु<BR>Taravu-śāttu (SITI), an officer of the Col13a kings, possibly<BR>associated with taravu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक|तरिकः<BR>Tarika (IE 8-3; HD), a ferry officer or one in charge of<BR>a ferry service. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक|तरिकः<BR>tarika (HRS), same as tara; ferry dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तर्क|तर्कः<BR>tarka (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘six’.<BR>(CII 4), logic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तर्कुक|तर्कुकः<BR>Tarkuka (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 34, note 7), a supplicant;<BR>a beggar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तार्य|तार्य्य<BR>tārya (HRS), same as tara; ferry dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत|ततं|ततः<BR>tata (IE 7-1-2), probably confused with tattva and used<BR>to indicate ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तटाकमातृक<BR>taṭāka-mātṛka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 98), ‘tank-nourished<BR>[land].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताताम्बा<BR>tāt-āmbā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 261), the mother,<BR>step-mother or aunt of one's father.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताटङ्क|ताटंक|ताटंकः|ताटङ्कः<BR>tāṭaṅka (EI 16), an ear-ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तथाज्ञातीय<BR>tathā-jñātīya (EI 8), used for taj-jñātīya (taj-jātīya; cf.<BR>jñātīya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत्पादपरिगृहीत<BR>tat-pāda-parigṛhīta (IE 8-2), see parigṛhīta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत्सम<BR>tatsama (IA 7), a Sanskrit word used in the regional<BR>languages without change or with slight change.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टार्<BR>Taṭṭār (SII 1), goldsmith; cf. Taṭṭhakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्ठकार<BR>Taṭṭhakāra (EI 15, 28; BL), a brazier, cf. Ṭhaṭhara, Ṭhaṭherā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत्त्व|तत्त्वं<BR>tattva (IE 7-1-2; EI 8), ‘twentyfive’; rarely also used<BR>to indicate ‘five.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तौण्डिक<BR>tauṇḍika (IE 8-8), ‘biting of crops with the mouth’; cf.<BR>gavāṃ tauṇḍike.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजः|तेज<BR>tejaḥ (EI 12), abbreviation of tejaḥ-svāmya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजःस्वाम्य<BR>tejaḥ-svāmya (IE 8-5; EI 16), cf. aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya;<BR>tejaḥsvāmya is tejo-yukta-svāmya, ‘ownership endowed with full<BR>authority’, which resulted from the eight (i. e. all or various)<BR>kinds of enjoyment. See tejo-mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजस्कर|तेजस्करं<BR>tejaskara (EI 24), polisher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजि<BR>teji (LP), fine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजोलिङ्ग<BR>tejo-liṅga (SII 2), the Śivaliṅga of light.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजोमान्य<BR>tejo-mānya, cf. teja-mānyam (SITI), the ownership of<BR>landed property with the aṣṭa-bhoga or eight (various or all)<BR>kinds of enjoyment; also called tejaḥ-svāmyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेलुगु<BR>Tĕlugu, also spelt Tĕnugu, name of a language and al-<BR>phabet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेलुगुकन्नड<BR>Tĕlugu-Kannaḍa, also called Kannaḍa-Tĕlugu; name of<BR>the medieval alphabet prevalent in the Telugu-and Kannaḍa-<BR>speaking areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठ|ठः<BR>Ṭha (IE 8-1; LP; PJS), abbreviation of Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठा<BR>Ṭhā (PJS), contraction of Ṭhākura, a modification of<BR>Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थड<BR>thaḍa (LP), stem or trunk of a tree; a tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठक<BR>ṭhaka, cf. ṭhakka (IA 6); ṭhaka-purisa is explained as ‘a<BR>trader’, and associated with ṭhag, ‘a cheat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थाकमान<BR>thākamāna (LP), remainder; what remains to be paid up; cf.<BR>thakalelī bākī in Marāṭhī. See also apūryamāṇa-thākamāna-drammāḥ,<BR>i. e. drammas (coins) which are not completely paid off and are<BR>still to be paid.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठक्कुर|ठक्कुरः<BR>Ṭhakkura (IE 8-3; EI 23, 30; CII 4; HD), supposed<BR>to be a title derived from a Turkish word (Tegin); occurs as a<BR>title in the Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 290, 706, 738; probably, a<BR>fief-holder; sometimes mentioned in the list of subordinates;<BR>generally used as a title of particular persons indicating their<BR>rank or office. The significance of the word possibly varied<BR>in different localities and ages. Its foreign origin is sup-<BR>ported by its unpopularity in the South. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XIII, p. 297; Vol. XIX, p. 243.<BR>(IE 8-3), probably a fief-holder; mentioned as Pātra.<BR>(EI 9), explained as ‘the lord-in-waiting’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठक्कुराज्ञी<BR>Ṭhakkurājñī (EI 8; CII 4; IA 16), title of the wife of<BR>a Ṭhakkura; same as Ṭhākurāṇī in some dialects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठाक्रि<BR>Ṭhākri (CII 4), same as Ṭhākur.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठकुर<BR>Ṭhakura, Ṭhākura (EI 23, 33; CII 4), same as Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठाकुर<BR>Ṭhākura (LP), Gujarātī; often a member of the Koli<BR>caste of Gujarat, who generally tries to detect thieves, etc.<BR>(LP), Gujarātī Ṭhākor, the chief among certain tribes<BR>of Rajputs; a small chieftain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठामि<BR>ṭhāmi (LP), a kind of earthern pot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थानापति<BR>Thānāpati (EI 30), same as Sthānapati; officer in charge<BR>of an outpost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थठर<BR>Thaṭhara, Thaṭhāra (Chamba), a brazier or copper-<BR>smith; same as Taṭṭhakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थवणी<BR>thavaṇī (HA), a wooden stand used as a symbol for the<BR>teacher or the Tīrthaṅkara, a religious text or certain pres-<BR>cribed small objects being placed on it and worshipped by<BR>Jain monks; same as sthāpan-ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठेक<BR>ṭheka (LP), special restraint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ति|तिः<BR>ti (IE 8-1), abbreviation of tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टि<BR>ṭi (IE 8-1), abbreviation of ṭikar or ṭikkara, ‘a mound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिगुलदण्ड<BR>tiguḻa-daṇḍa (IE 8-5), name of a tax; see turuṣka-daṇḍa<BR>and āndhra-daṇḍa. Tiguḻa is the same as Tamil13. Tiguḻa-daṇḍa<BR>may also be ‘the Tamilian measuring rod’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टीकर<BR>ṭīkara (IE 8-1), same as ṭikkara; a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिखरा<BR>tikharā (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टिक्कर<BR>ṭikkara (EI 28), same as ṭīkara; a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिलमक<BR>tilamaka (CII 3; IA 9), a water-course; probably, a<BR>channel leading the waters from the hillside over the terraced<BR>fields.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिलपिषक<BR>Tila-piṣaka (CII 4; LL), an oil-miller.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीम्मिर<BR>tīmmira (EI 11), a land measure; cf. timpira, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिम्पीर<BR>timpīra (IE 8-6; EI 23, 24, 29), also spelt timpira, ṭim-<BR>pira, etc.; a land measure mentioned in Orissan records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टिप्पनक<BR>ṭippanaka (LP), a certificate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरम<BR>tirama (EI 24), Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्णदण्ड<BR>Tīrṇa-daṇḍa (CII 1), ‘one who has been convicted’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थ|तीर्थं<BR>tīrtha (IE 8-3, 8-4; EI 3; SII 1; CII 4; LL), a place<BR>of pilgrimage; a holy place or holy waters; a bathing place; a<BR>flight of steps for descent into a river; a ferry; sometimes<BR>suffixed to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थकर|तीर्थकरः<BR>Tīrthakara (BL), epithet of the Jinas; same as Tīrthaṅ-<BR>kara (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थङ्कर|तीर्थङ्करः<BR>Tīrthaṅkara (CII 3; EI 9); epithet of the 24 great leaders<BR>of the Jain faith; propagator of the Jain faith or tīrtha;<BR>creator of the four sections, viz. monk, nun, layman and<BR>laywoman (sādhu, sādhvī, śrāvaka and śrāvikā); same as Jina;<BR>sometimes spelt Tīrthakara; also called Ādikartṛ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थिक|तीर्थिकः<BR>Tīrthika (EI 9), Buddhist; teacher of a religion other<BR>than one's own; a non-Buddhist (especially, Śaiva) teacher.<BR>(EI 32), same as Tairthika, ‘a priest’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थोपाध्याय<BR>Tīrth-opādhyāya (BL), title of a family priest at Jagan-<BR>nātha-kṣetra (Purī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरुमेनिकावल्<BR>Tirumeni-kāval (ASLV), watchman in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरुविडैयाट्टम्<BR>tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam (EI 30), Tamil; a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथि|तिथिः<BR>tithi (CII 3; IA 17), a lunar day; one mean tithi is equal<BR>to 0.9843529572 of a mean solar day and night; the mean<BR>tithis in a solar year are 371, and 3 ghaṭīs and 53.4 palas; gener-<BR>ally the term tithi means the end of a tithi, not its beginning<BR>or duration, and the week-day of a tithi is the week-day on<BR>which that tithi ends; the tithis given in the Pañcāṅga are<BR>apparent, not mean, and they are intended to be given from<BR>apparent sunrise.<BR>Cf. Tamil tiyadi, tedi (SITI), a date.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘fifteen’.<BR>(EI 16), same as mahā-tithi, an auspicious tithi; cf. saptamī<BR>called the tithi of the sun-god and aṣṭamī that of the god Śiva<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 168, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिभोग<BR>tithi-bhoga (CII 3; IA 16), duration of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिध्रुव<BR>tithi-dhruva (CII 3; IA 16), constant of a tithi; a term<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-342" target="_blank">Page-342+ 40</a>]<BR>denoting the number of complete tithis that elapse from the<BR>commencement of Caitra upto the tithi during which the Meṣa-<BR>saṃkrānti occurs. See tithi-śudhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिकेन्द्र<BR>tithi-kendra (CII 3), anomaly of a tithi, expressed in<BR>tithis; an annual variation in the tithi-kendra is 7 tithis, 9 ghaṭīs<BR>and 42 palas. See kendra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिस्पष्टकेन्द्र<BR>tithi-spaṣṭa-kendra (IA 16), the apparent anomaly of a<BR>tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिशुद्धि<BR>tithi-śuddhi (CII 3), the subtraction of tithis; a term de-<BR>noting the number of tithis that elapse from the commence-<BR>ment of Caitra up to the time of the Meṣa-saṃkrānti. See<BR>tithi-dhruva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोल|तोलं|तोलः<BR>tola, tolā, cf. Telugu-Kannaḍa tulā (CITD), weight of<BR>a rupee, taken as the unit of the system of weights; fixed at<BR>180 grains troy by the British; also called suvarṇa (JNSI,<BR>Vol. XVI, p. 46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोलक|तोलकं<BR>tolaka, same as tola; equal to 2 śānas or 80 ratis; also<BR>called kola, draṅkṣaṇa, badara, kṣudraka, vaṭaka, etc. (JNSI,<BR>Vol. XVI, pp. 41, 44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोरै<BR>torai (SITI), Tamil; a standard linear measure of four<BR>fingers' breadth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोरण|तोरणं|तोरणः<BR>toraṇa (CII 4; LL; CITD), an arch; a gateway; an<BR>arched doorway; a portal; a temporary ornamental arch;<BR>also a garland in Telugu-Kannaḍa.<BR>Cf. toraṇa-kkāṇikkai (SITI), tax on gates or presents<BR>for decorating the village with arches.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैपिटक<BR>Traipiṭaka, cf. Trepiṭaka (EI 9), one versed in the three<BR>piṭakas, i. e. the three classes of Buddhist religious literature.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैपिटकोपाध्याय<BR>Traipiṭak-opādhyāya (LL), Buddhist; teacher of the three<BR>piṭakas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैपुरुष|त्रैपुरुषः<BR>Traipuruṣa (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, pp.<BR>34-35), same as the composite god Tripuruṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैराज्य<BR>trairājya (EI 19), a group of three realms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैराज्यस्थिति<BR>trairājya-sthiti (EI 27), cf. trairājya-sthitim = ātmasāt = kṛtavataḥ,<BR>‘of one who has obtained steadiness in the three realms.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैविद्य|त्रैविद्यं|त्रैविद्यः<BR>Traividya (LL), Buddhist; teacher of the three piṭakas.<BR>(EI 16), cf. Trivedin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैविद्यसामान्य<BR>Traividya-sāmānya (EIZ23), same as Trivedin; cf. Cāturvidya-<BR>sāmānya = Caturvedin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रास|त्रासः<BR>trāsa (SII 2), flaw in a ruby.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रातृ<BR>Trātṛ (IE 8-2; LL), same as Prakrit Trātara, ‘the savi-<BR>our’; royal title of foreign origin; Greek Soter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रयी<BR>trayī (SII 1), the three Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रयोदशम<BR>trayodaśama (EI 15), same as trayodaśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रि|त्रिः<BR>Tri (EI 32), abbreviation of Trivedin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रि|त्रिः<BR>tri (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभागाभ्यन्तरसिद्धि<BR>tribhāg-ābhyantara-siddhi (IE 8-5), generally spelt tribhog-<BR>ābhyantara-siddhi; the right to enjoy one-third of the revenue,<BR>the other two parts going in equal shares to gods and Brāh-<BR>maṇas. Cf. abhyantara-siddhi, bāhy-ābhyantara-siddhi, tribhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभङ्ग<BR>tri-bhaṅga (EI 17), pose in standing images with bends<BR>in three limbs, viz. the neck, the wrists and the knees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभङ्गि<BR>tri-bhaṅgi, cf. tri-bhaṅga; see Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 65.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभोग<BR>tri-bhoga (EI 16; IA 19), a joint tenure enjoyed by a<BR>private person, a god (or gods) and the Brāhmaṇas (cf.<BR>Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 271). See tribhāg-ābhyantara-<BR>siddhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभोगाभ्यन्तर<BR>tribhog-ābhyantara (EI 15), same as tribhog-ābhyantara-siddhi,<BR>tribhāg-ābhyantara-siddhi, tribhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभोग्य<BR>tribhogya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 313), cf. gaṇa-bhogya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभुवनविजयस्तम्भ<BR>tribhuvana-vijaya-stambha (SII 1), a pillar commemo-<BR>rating the conquest of ‘the three worlds’, the conventional claim<BR>of a hero.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिचीवर<BR>tri-cīvara (EI 25), complete robe of a Buddhist monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिदण्ड|त्रिदंड|त्रिदण्डः<BR>tri-daṇḍa, cf. Tridaṇḍin (IA 10); tree staves tied to-<BR>gether as borne by Brāhmaṇa mendicants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिदश|त्रिदशः<BR>tridaśa (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिदीनारिक्य<BR>tridīnārikya (EI 15), same as traidīnārikya, ‘priced at three<BR>dīnāras.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिगत<BR>tri-gata (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिगुण|त्रिगुणं<BR>tri-guṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिजगत्<BR>tri-jagat (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’; but jagat sometimes also<BR>means ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिक|त्रिकं<BR>trika (HA), a group of three figures of the Tīrthaṅkaras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिकाल<BR>tri-kāla (SII 1; SITI), the three parts of the day, viz.<BR>morning, noon and evening [when worship is offered in temples].<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिकूट|त्रिकूटं|त्रिकूटः<BR>trikūṭa (EI 3), a junction of three villages (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XIII, p. 34, note 3); same as trikuṭa or trikuṭṭa. Cf. tri-sandhi;<BR>also Telugu muggaḍa, ‘a junction of three or more villages’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिलक्षण<BR>tri-lakṣaṇa (EI 3), three qualities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृण|तृणं<BR>tṛṇa, cf. a-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); grass which the<BR>villagers were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on<BR>occasions or to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणयूति<BR>tṛṇa-yūti, cf. yūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणयूति<BR>tṛṇa-yūti (or puti) -gocara (EI 17), grass-fields and pasturelands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणोदक<BR>tṛṇ-odaka (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28), name of a tax or cess;<BR>the grazing tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिनेत्र|त्रिनेत्रः<BR>trinetra (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपद<BR>tripada (LP), the three chief account books, viz. rojmol,<BR>khātā-vahī and pāvtī-vahī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपदलेख्यक<BR>tripada-lekhyaka (LP), accounts book and receipt book.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपाठिन्<BR>Tripāṭhin (EI 4, 31), same as Trivedin; epithet or family-<BR>name of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिफलीताम्रशासन<BR>triphalī-tāmraśāsana (EI 3), a grant engraved on three<BR>copper plates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपीडिदान<BR>tri-pīḍi-dāna (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 271), a grant to be<BR>enjoyed by three generations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपुरुष<BR>Tripuruṣa (EI 33), a composite deity (tri-mūrti); a com-<BR>bined image of Brahman, Viṣṇu (represented as Sūryanārāyaṇa<BR>in Gujarat) and Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिसहस्र<BR>trisahasra (EI 31), also called trisahasra-vidyā; certain<BR>sciences.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिसन्धि|त्रिसन्धिः<BR>tri-sandhi (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 34, note 3), a junction<BR>of three villages; cf. trikūṭa or trikuṭṭa; also Telugu muggaḍa,<BR>‘the junction of three or more villages’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिशर<BR>triśara (SII 2), name of an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिस्पर्शा<BR>trisparśā (IA 26), the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिस्थली<BR>tri-sthalī (EI 21), the three holy places, viz. Gayā, Pra-<BR>yāga and Kāśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिष्टुभ्<BR>triṣṭubh (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिशूल|त्रिशूलं<BR>triśūla, cf. tiriśūlam (SITI), trident; same as śūla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रितीर्थी<BR>tri-tīrthī (HA), an image showing figures of three Jinas,<BR>usually one Jina standing or sitting in the centre as the main<BR>deity of the group and two others sitting or standing on the<BR>two sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिवर्ग|त्रिवर्गः<BR>tri-varga (SII 1), the three objects of human life.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिवेदिन्<BR>Trivedin (EI 4), same as Tripāṭhin; epithet of Brāhmaṇas<BR>later stereotyped as family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिविधक्षितीशचूडामणि<BR>Trividha-kṣitīśa-cūḍāmaṇi (IE 8-2), epithet of a king pro-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-345" target="_blank">Page-345+ 40</a>]<BR>bably referring to the Aśvapati, Gajapati and Narapati types of<BR>rulers, i. e. those who were strong in elephants, cavalry and<BR>infantry respectively.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रोडनिका<BR>troḍanikā (IE 8-5), same as troṭana; cf. karṇa-troḍanikā,<BR>‘cutting somebody's ears.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रोटन<BR>troṭana (IE 8-5), cf. karṇa-troṭana, same as karṇa-troḍanikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्र्यक्षमुख<BR>tryakṣa-mukha (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुडवु<BR>tuḍavu (SITI), Tamil; a liquid measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुक्खार|तुक्खारः<BR>tukkhāra (CII 4), a Tokharian horse; cf. Tuḥkhāra people<BR>of the Purāṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुला<BR>tulā (IA 26), a weight [of silver].<BR>(CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit tola or<BR>tolaka; the weight of one rupee or 30 canteroy fanams; (1/3) of<BR>a navaṭāku; a measure or weight of gold and silver, being 100<BR>palas or about 145 ounces troy. The tulā varied a great deal<BR>according to the age and locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलाभार|तुलाभारः<BR>tulā-bhāra (EI 4, 17, 26; SITI), name of a mahādāna;<BR>same as tulāpuruṣa; weighing a king or an exalted personage<BR>against gold or other precious metals and stones and distributing<BR>the same to temples, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलाधिरोह<BR>tul-ādhiroha (EI 3), same as tulā-puruṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलापुरुष|तुलापुरुषः<BR>tulā-puruṣa (EI 29; CII 4), name of a mahādāna; same<BR>as tulā-bhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलसीविवाह|तुलसीविवाहः<BR>tulasī-vivāha (EI 32), name of a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलु<BR>Tulu, name of a language which is written in Malayāḻam<BR>characters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुल्य|तुल्यः<BR>tulya (SITI), literally, ‘equal’; a true copy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुल्यमेय<BR>tulya-meya (EI 7, 10; HRS), ‘what is to be weighed and<BR>measured’; same as meya in deya-meya; known from records<BR>like those of Harṣavardhana, in which it may be epithet of bhāga-<BR>bhoga or a separate item (Ind. Ep., p. 394).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तूम्बु<BR>tūmbu (SITI), Tamil, a measure of capacity; cf. tūmu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तूमु<BR>tūmu (EI 27), a grain measure; cf. tūmbu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तून्क्<BR>tūnk (HA), Jain; top of a mountain or hill on which<BR>there is a shrine or several shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरग|तुरगः<BR>turaga (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरगसाधनिक<BR>Turaga-sādhanika (EI 25), the leader of cavalry. Cf.<BR>Sādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरक<BR>Turaka (EI 32), same as Turuka and Turuṣka; a Turk or<BR>Turkish Muhammadan; a Muhammadan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरङ्गम|तुरंगम|तुरंगमः|तुरङ्गमः<BR>turaṅgama (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरीयजन्मन्<BR>Turīya-janman (EI 24; CII 4), same as Śūdra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरुक<BR>Turuka (EI 32), cf. Turaka and Turuṣka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरुष्क|तुरुष्कः<BR>Turuṣka (EI 5, 17, 32), originally, a Turk or a Turkish<BR>Muhammadan; later, Muhammadans in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरुष्कदण्ड<BR>turuṣka-daṇḍa (HRS; Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 196, Vol.<BR>XI, p. 21), name of a tax collected by the Gāhaḍavāla kings<BR>from their Muhammadan subjects or for defending their king-<BR>dom from Muhammadan attacks; cf. the danegeld in early<BR>English history. See andhra-daṇḍa, tiguḻa-daṇḍa, bhoṭṭa-viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुर्य|तुर्य्य|तुर्य्यः<BR>turya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्यागीआचार्य<BR>Tyāgī-ācārya (IA 19), Jain; an Ācārya who does not permit<BR>laxity of observances.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उ|उः<BR>u (IE 8-1), abbreviation of the land measure called<BR>udāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभय|उभयं|उभयः<BR>ubhaya, cf. ubhaiyam (SII 1), an offering.<BR>Cf. ubhaya-paliśai (SITI), interest in two ways, i. e.<BR>in money and in kind.<BR>(SITI), a tax payable in gold; probably the same as<BR>ubhaya-mārga or the tolls collected on the highways in both the<BR>directions, i. e. inward and outward.<BR>(SII, Vol. III, p. 209), a gift to a temple or monastery<BR>in Tamil records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयमुखी<BR>ubhaya-mukhī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 15, note 4),<BR>a cow in the act of giving birth to a calf; sometimes explained<BR>as ‘a pregnant cow’ (EI 6).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयमुखीदक्षिणा<BR>ubhayamukhī-dakṣiṇā (CITD), some special kind of re-<BR>ligious present or fee; the gift of a cow at the point of giving<BR>birth to a calf (cf. ubhayamukhī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयनानादेशि<BR>Ubhaya-nānā-deśi (SITI), the two divisions of the Nānā-<BR>deśi organisation, e. g., the Nānādeśi and the Citramel13i.<BR>(CITD), explained as the entire merchant commu-<BR>nity, i. e. including both the Sva-deśi and Para-deśi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयस्वाम्य<BR>ubhaya-svāmya, cf. ubhaya-sāmya (EI 5), probably, two kinds<BR>of ownership.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उचट<BR>ucaṭa (LP), impatience, anxiety; cf. Gujarātī uchāṭ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्चावच|उच्चावचः<BR>ucc-āvaca (CII 1), ‘more or less’, ‘of various kinds’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छन्न|उच्छन्नं<BR>ucchanna (CII 3), corruption of utsanna; found in Sanskrit<BR>inscriptions. See JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, 1954, p. 204.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छीर्ण<BR>ucchīrṇa (IA 19), a loan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छ्रय|उच्छ्रयः<BR>ucchraya (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 46, note 3), a shelter;<BR>same as pratiśraya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छृङ्खल|उच्छृंखल|उच्छृङ्खलं<BR>ucchṛṅkhala (LP), free from a burden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उछालकभृत<BR>uchālaka-bhṛta (LP), loaded with uchālaka (Gujarātī ucāḻo),<BR>i. e. household furniture that can be easily moved about.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उड<BR>uḍa (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyseven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदगयन|उदगयनं<BR>udag-ayana (EI2 3), the winter solstice; same as uttarāyaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदगयनपर्वन्<BR>udagayana-parvan (EI 20), cf. udag-ayana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उडैयार्<BR>Uḍaiyār (SITI), Tamil; literally, a possessor; a king or<BR>lord; the chief deity of a temple. Cf. uḍaiyār-śālai, the feeding<BR>house attached to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकबन्ध<BR>udaka-bandha (EI 3), a sluice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकधारा<BR>udaka-dhārā, cf. udaka-dārai (SITI), [a gift given] with<BR>the libation of water; also referred to in Tamil as udakañśeydu<BR>and udakaṃ paṇṇi. See udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकपूर्वम्<BR>udaka-pūrvam (IA 7), also expressed as udak-ātisargeṇa,<BR>‘with libations of water’; refers to the custom of pouring water<BR>in the hand of the donee while making the ceremonial gift of an<BR>object which cannot be placed in the latter's hands. Cf. Dra-<BR>vyasya nāma gṛhnīyād=dadān=īti tathā vadet | toyaṃ dadyāt=tato<BR>haste dāne vidhir=ayaṃ smṛtaḥ || (Agni Purāṇa, Ch. 209,<BR>verses 49-50).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकसर्ग<BR>udaka-sarga (IA 8), same as udak-ātisarga (cf. udaka-<BR>pūrvam).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकासीहारकुल्लक<BR>udak-āsīhāra-kullaka, cf. sa-vanaspaty-udak-āsīhāra-kullaka-<BR>pānīya-sametā (IE 8-5), translated as ‘together with the fruit-<BR>trees and with the water-courses and channels’ (with the<BR>omission of the doubtful words).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदमान|उदमानः<BR>udamāna (IE 8-6; EI 29), a small land measure; pro-<BR>bably the same as unmāna and udāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदान|उदानः<BR>udāna, see udamāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदपान|उदपानं|उदपानः<BR>udapāna (CII 1; LL), a well or reservoir.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदार|उदारः<BR>udāra (CII 1), a person of high rank; a rich man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदरबन्धन<BR>udara-bandhana (SII) 2), a waist-band; name of an or-<BR>nament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदरम्भरीण<BR>udaram-bharīṇa (IA 17), same as udaram-bharin, ‘filling<BR>the belly.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदर्चिस्|उदर्च्चिस्<BR>udarcis (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदासीन|उदासीनः<BR>udāsīna, cf. udāsina-vāriyam (SITI), a committee which<BR>is neutral to both the parties; same as madhyastha or the arbi-<BR>tration committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदय|उदयः<BR>udaya (EI 24), ‘the produce’ [of a field]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदयगिरि|उदयगिरिः<BR>Udaya-giri (IA 22), the mythical Sun-rise mountain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्बलि<BR>udbali, cf. umbaḻi (EI 13), umbaḻam, umbaḻikkai, umbaḻika<BR>(SITI), rent-free gift of land; land granted rent-free for the<BR>performance of service; same as mānya. See udbalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्बलिक<BR>udbalika (IE 8-5; CII 1), free from taxes; free from the<BR>obligation of paying bali probably meaning land tax payable in<BR>addition to the king's share of grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्दामन्<BR>uddāman (EI 9), same as uddāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्दातव्य<BR>uddātavya, ‘to be repaid’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 239); ‘to be<BR>handed over’ (ibid., p. 246).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्देश|उद्देशः<BR>uddeśa (CII 4), a territorial division.<BR>(EI 14), cf. s-oddeśa (IE 8-5); space above the ground;<BR>same as ūrdhva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्ध<BR>uddha (IA 19), explained as ‘deserted’. Cf. uddha-grāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धग्राम<BR>uddha-grāma (LP), the village of which the revenue is<BR>fixed in a lump sum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धखिलभूमि<BR>uddha-khila-bhūmi (LP), table land which is uncultivated<BR>(khila). But cf. uddha-grāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धार|उद्धारं|उद्धारः<BR>uddhāra (LP), borrowed on trust or credit; cf. udhār.<BR>(IE 8-5), same as udraṅga; cf. Tamil uttāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धारप्रोद्धार<BR>uddhāra-proddhāra (LP), taking on credit; cf. Marāṭhī<BR>udhār-pādhār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धार्य<BR>uddhārya (LP), ‘may be debited’; cf. Gujarātī udhāra-<BR>vuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धार्यव्यवहार<BR>uddhārya-vyavahāra (LP), the business of lending money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्द्योतित<BR>uddyotita (EI 13), literally, ‘caused to shine’; actually<BR>‘with repairs effected.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्गणक<BR>udgaṇaka (LP), a revenue chart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्गणनीय<BR>udgaṇanīya (LP), cf. Gujarātī gaṇī āpavuṃ, ‘the charge<BR>should be handed over.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्घाटित|उद्घाटितः<BR>udghāṭita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20), same as<BR>utkīrṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्ग्राह्<BR>udgrāh, cf. udgrāhayiṣyāmi (LP), ‘I shall get the revenue<BR>collected [from the country in this way]’; also udgrāhita<BR>(LP), ‘taxed’; udgrāhyamāṇa (LP), cf. Gujarātī ughrāvayuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्ग्रन्थ|उद्ग्रंथ<BR>udgrantha (IE 8-5), same as udraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उधरित<BR>udharita (IA 18), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदीचीपति<BR>Udīcīpati (BL), literally, ‘the ruler of the north (i. e.<BR>the northern province of an empire)’; title of a viceroy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्रङ्ग|उद्रंगः|उद्रङ्गः<BR>udraṅga (IE 8-3; 8-5; EI 22; CII 3, 4; HRS), explained<BR>as ‘the fixed tax’, ‘the land tax’, ‘the principal tax’ or ‘the<BR>tax on the permanent tenants’; generally mentioned along<BR>with uparikara, i. e. minor taxes or the tax on temporary<BR>tenants; same as kḻpta. Udraṅga may have been paid in grains<BR>at least in soem regions since the Audraṅgika (collector of ud-<BR>raṅga) is sometimes separately mentioned together with the<BR>Hiraṇyasāmudāyika (collector of revenue in cash). In one<BR>case, the land is said to have been granted after making it<BR>udraṅga, i. e. s-odraṅga. See s-odraṅga (IA 10), draṅga, uttāra.<BR>Cf. mah-odraṅga in pravartita-mahodraṅg-ādi-dāna-vyasan-ānupajāta-<BR>santoṣa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 118, text line 40).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्रङ्गीकृत्य<BR>udraṅgīkṛtya (IE 8-3), same as s-odraṅgīkṛtya; used in<BR>respect of a gift land. Cf. udraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्रव<BR>udrava (EI 27), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदुम्बर|उदुंबर|उदुम्बरं|उदुंबरः|उदुम्बरः<BR>udumbara (LP), ‘threshold’; cf. gṛh-odumbara-madhye,<BR>‘into the house’; cf. umbara-bheda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्वस<BR>udvasa, cf. udvasa-kuṭumbika (LP), cultivators who have<BR>come from outside and settled.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्वात<BR>udvāta (EI 13), tempest; cf. bhūta-vāla-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्याम|उद्यामः<BR>udyāma (CII 1), used in the sense of udyama or exertion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्यान|उद्यानं|उद्यानः<BR>udyāna (CII 1), march; a garden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्क<BR>ukka, ukkā (Chamba), the total sum; a lump sum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्कोड<BR>ukkoḍa, a kind of levy; probably, periodical presents; same<BR>as utkoṭa. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्कोटभङ्ग<BR>ukkoṭa-bhaṅga, same as khoṭa-bhaṅga (q. v.) according to the<BR>Abhidhānarājendra, s. v. parihāra; cf. utkoṭa and ukkoḍa, periodi-<BR>cal presents (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्कुट्ठी<BR>ukkuṭṭhī (IE 8-8), Prakrit; see utkṛṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्तनियोग<BR>ukta-niyoga (EI 33), doubtful expression probably indi-<BR>cating an official designation. Cf. uttara-niyoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्थ्य<BR>ukthya, (EI 22; CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लन्बन<BR>ullanbana (IE 8-8), a crime, the real nature of which is<BR>uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लेख|उल्लेखः<BR>ullekha, ‘high-flashing’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 36).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लेखक<BR>Ullekhaka, engraver (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 203 and<BR>note 11). See Vilekhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लुञ्चन|उल्लुंचन|उल्लुंचनं<BR>ulluñcana (LP), cleaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उमराव<BR>Umarāva (EI 26; BL), title of a feudatory ruler; same<BR>as the Muhammadan title Umrah.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बलि<BR>umbaḻi (ASLV), Tamil; same as Sanskrit udbali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बर|उंबर|उंबरः|उम्बरः<BR>umbara (IE 8-8), same as Prakrit ummara; threshold or<BR>door; cf. umbara-bheda, also udumbara and unmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बरभेद|उम्बरभेदः<BR>umbara-bheda (IE 8-5; EI 25), ‘violation of the closed<BR>door’; the right of royal officers to enter into a house with doors<BR>closed for realising taxes. This probably related to the houses<BR>of merchants who were away from their home-towns in the<BR>course of their business; cf. unmara or umbara; also prātibhedikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उमुरभेद<BR>umura-bheda (CII 4), mistake for umbara-bheda (q. v.);<BR>forcible entry into a house. Cf. unmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊनाब्दिकश्राद्ध<BR>ūnābdika-śrāddha (CII 4), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छ|उञ्छं|उंछः|उञ्छः<BR>uñcha, cf. uñcha-kara-bhar-ādi-vivarjita; tolls (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXXIII, p. 89); may be collection of small quantities of crops<BR>(cf. prastha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उण्बलि<BR>uṇbaḻi (SII 11-1), same as Sanskrit udbali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छमन्न<BR>uñchamanna (EI 26), used along with maṟumanna; a privi-<BR>lege of the donee of rent-free land; see uñcha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छवृत्ति<BR>uñcha-vṛtti (EI 24), a gleaner of corn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्मान|उन्मानं|उन्मानः<BR>unmāna (IE 8-6; EI 15, 21, 29), name of a small land<BR>measure; same as udāna or udamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्मर<BR>unmara (EI 30), Sanskritised form of Prakrit ummara (cf.<BR>umbara); threshold. Merchants, who were often absent from<BR>home for a long time, were sometimes made free from unmara-<BR>bheda (entry into their house) by royal officers probably be-<BR>cause they paid their dues on their return from business tours.<BR>Cf. prātibhedikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्नत|उन्नतः<BR>unnata (IE 8-5), high land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्नीति<BR>unnīti, ‘adopted daughter’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपधा<BR>upa-dhā (CII 1), cf. hīta-sukham=upadadhyuḥ; to bring<BR>[welfare and happiness to the people].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाधि|उपाधिः<BR>upādhi (SII 1), probably, a condition.<BR>Cf. opādi (SII 2), dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाध्याय|उपाध्यायः<BR>Upādhyāya (CII 4), a teacher; epithet of Brāhmaṇas.<BR>(IA 19), Jain; an Ācārya who has the right of reading the<BR>sacred text, but not of explaining it.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-351" target="_blank">Page-351+ 40</a>]<BR>(IE 8-3; EI 7), epithet of teachers; mentioned as a Pātra.<BR>(CII 3), a sub-teacher who is the instructor in only a part<BR>of the Veda, or in grammar and the other Vedāṅgas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाध्यायिनी<BR>Upādhyāyinī (LL), a female teacher; the wife of an<BR>Upādhyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपग<BR>upaga (CII 1), suitable; cf. manuṣy-opaga, ‘beneficial<BR>to men’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपगत|उपगतः<BR>upagata (CII 1), same as saṅgata, intimately associated;<BR>see upeta, etc. See Ind. Ep., pp. 161 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपगता<BR>upagatā (LP), a receipt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपहन्<BR>upa-han (CII 1), to harm; cf. upaghāta, injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपकर<BR>upakara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 106, note 5),<BR>cf. nikara and upaskara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपकारिका<BR>upakārikā, probably, a territorial unit around the<BR>headquarters of an administrative unit (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XV, p. 286).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपखिल<BR>upakhila, cf. sa-khil-opakhila (Chamba), ‘together<BR>with fallow (khila) and partially fallow (upakhila) land’.<BR>See pakhila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपकॢप्त<BR>upakḷpta (EI 15; CII 3, 4), a levy; probably, the<BR>tax on temporary tenants or the unfixed taxes or minor in-<BR>come; cf. sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta (IE 8-5), also kḷpta, kḷpta-kara,<BR>udraṅga and uparikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपक्रमकरण<BR>upakrama-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of<BR>new undertakings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपक्षय<BR>upakṣaya (LP), expense; ‘other expenses’; cf. s-opak-<BR>ṣaya, sañjāt-opakṣaya, ‘expenses incurred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपक्षिति<BR>upakṣiti (IE 8-5; EI 33), probably, tax on inferior land;<BR>may also be the same as upakṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपलक्षित<BR>upalakṣita (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), ‘examined’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपान<BR>upāna (SITI), the first moulding above the plinth, in<BR>the construction of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपनिधि|उपनिधिः<BR>upanidhi (IE 8-5; EI 12), same as nikṣepa; cf. nidhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपनिपातक<BR>upanipātaka (CII 3), same as upapātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपपातक|उपपातकं<BR>upapātaka (CII 3), sins of the second degree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपपीठ<BR>upapīṭha (SII 2), a lower pedestal; cf. pīṭha; also upa-<BR>pīṭhattukaṇḍappaḍai, the lower tier of the basement of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपप्रधानिन्<BR>Upapradhānin (ASLV), an executive officer lower in rank<BR>than the Pradhānīn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरहिण्डीय<BR>Uparahiṇḍīya (LP), a tax-inspector.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरक्षित<BR>uparakṣita (LL), explained as ‘kept in custody’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिक<BR>Uparika (IE 8-3; CII 3; BL; HD), a viceroy; the<BR>governor of a province. An Uparika was appointed by the<BR>emperor and he himself appointed the governor of the district<BR>(cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 130). He is sometimes styled<BR>Mahārāja and Rājaputra. Viśvarūpa on the Yājñavalkyasmṛti,<BR>I. 307, quotes a prose passage from Bṛhaspati where the re-<BR>quisite qualities of an Uparika are set out. See Vogel, Ant. Ch.<BR>St., p. 123. The word literally means ‘one placed at the top’.<BR>(IE 8-3), cf. Auparika, a viceroy.<BR>Cf. Bṛhad-uparika (IE 8-3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिकमहाराज<BR>Uparika-mahārāja (IE 8-3), an Uparika enjoying the<BR>title Mahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिकर|उपरिकरः<BR>uparikara (IE 8-5; CII 3, 4; HRS), explained as ‘ad-<BR>ditional taxes’, ‘unfixed taxes’, ‘minor taxes’, or ‘tax paid<BR>by the temporary tenants’; cf. s-oparikara (IA 10), sometimes<BR>called parikara (cf. sa-parikara in place of s-opakriara). See<BR>upri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिङ्ख्<BR>upa-riṅkh (EI 12), to spread.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपासक|उपासकः<BR>Upāsaka (EI 3, 8, 27; CII 3), a Buddhist lay worshipper;<BR>a lay follower of the Buddha; cf. Upāsikā.<BR>(SII 13), a temple servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपसम्पदा<BR>upasampadā (EI 9; IA 22), the initiation of a Buddhist<BR>monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपसन्धि<BR>upasandhi (SITI), intermediary service of worship in<BR>a temple, between the morning and the midday service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपासनिन्<BR>Upāsanin (EI 32), title or family name of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपसन्न|उपसन्नः<BR>upasanna, cf. kṛt-opasannā (EI 30); word of doubtful<BR>import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपासिका<BR>Upāsikā (CII 3, 4), feminine form of Upāsaka (q. v.);<BR>a female lay-follower of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपस्कर|उपस्करः<BR>upaskara (HRS), known from the Kamauli plate of<BR>Vaidyadeva; probably meaning upakara (q. v.) or the appur-<BR>tenance to a tax (kara).<BR>Cf. nikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाश्रय|उपाश्रयः<BR>upāśraya (LL), a shelter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपस्थान|उपस्थानं<BR>upasthāna (LL), reception room.<BR>(HRS), a group of royal receipts arising from underhand<BR>methods of collection of the contributions in kind, as suggested<BR>by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपस्थानशाला<BR>upasthāna-śālā (LL), hall of reception.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपतल्प|उपतल्पः<BR>upatalpa (EI 8), the upper story [of a house].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाति<BR>upāti (SITI), Tamil; also spelt opādi; Sanskrit upādhi;<BR>literally, obstruction; dues; anything payable as a debt or<BR>obligation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपात्त|उपात्तं|उपात्तः<BR>upātta, cf. sa-bhūt-opātta-pratyāya (EI 23), ‘together with<BR>the income derived on account of changes in the natural<BR>phenomena.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाय|उपायः<BR>upāya (EI 6, 25), four in number; ‘four’. Cf. catur-upāya<BR>(SII 1).<BR>(SITI), probably, minor taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयात<BR>upayāta (EI 33), same as opeta, upagata, ‘closely asso-<BR>ciated’. See samupagata, samaveta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयुक्त|उपयुक्तः<BR>Upayukta (HD), same as Upayuktaka, ‘a subordinate<BR>officer’. See Arthaśāstra, II. 5; Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 285.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयुक्तक<BR>Upayuktaka (IE 8-3; HD), probably the same as Niyuk-<BR>taka, Viniyuktaka, Tad-viniyuktaka, etc. See Upayukta; cf.<BR>Yuktak-Opayukta (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 40).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयुक्तिक<BR>Upayuktika (EI 23), official designation; probably the<BR>same as Upayuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपेक्षा<BR>upekṣā (CII 4), Buddhist; indifference; one of the bhā-<BR>vanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपेत<BR>upeta (CII 1), same as saṅgata; ‘intimately associated’; cf.<BR>upagata, upayāta, samupagata, samaveta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपोद<BR>upoda (Chamba), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपोसथागार<BR>uposath-āgāra (EI 23), ‘the uposatha hall’. See poṣadha,<BR>pauṣadha<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उप्रि<BR>upri (IE 8-5), Marāṭhī; same as uparikara (q. v.), tax<BR>on temporary tenants, according to some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्<BR>ūr (ASLV), the assembly of a non-Brāhmaṇa village, that<BR>of a Brāhmaṇa village being called sabhā or mahāsabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरन्दर<BR>urandara (LP), delay.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्व|ऊर्द्ध्वः<BR>ūrdhva, cf. s-ādha-ūrdhva (IE 8-5), ‘[what is] above the<BR>surface of the ground’; same as uddeśa.<BR>Cf. ūrdhva-dina-pāṭikāyām (LP), ‘for the series of days<BR>afterwards.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वाधः<BR>ūrdhv-ādhaḥ (IA 16), explained as ‘what is above and<BR>below [in the gift land]’; cf. ūrdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi-yutā (IA 18),<BR>‘with income from the produce above and below the surface of<BR>the ground’; same as s-ādha-ūrdhva, epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वपट्ट<BR>ūrdhva-paṭṭa (LL), an upright slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वयित<BR>ūrdhvayita, cf. Prakrit ubhayita (EI 20), raised. See<BR>ūrdhvita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वित<BR>ūrdhvita, Prakrit ubhayita (Sel. Ins., p. 222), raised,<BR>contributed. See ūrdhvayita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उर्गामुण्ड<BR>Ur-gāmuṇḍa (IA 12), Kannaḍa; official designation; cf.<BR>Gāmuṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ण|ऊर्णं|ऊर्ण्ण<BR>ūrṇa (EI 8), a mark between the brows of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्णस्थान<BR>ūrṇa-sthāna (IE 8-3), a wool factory. Cf. Aurṇasthānika,<BR>officer in charge of the ūrṇā-sthānas (Select Inscriptions, p. 360,<BR>text line 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरोडे<BR>Uroḍĕ (IA 8), Kannaḍa; the village headman; cf. Uroḍĕya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरोडेय<BR>Uroḍĕya (IA 12), Kannaḍa; official designation; cf. Uroḍĕ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्पद्दिन्काडि<BR>ūr-paddinkāḍi (EI 28), name of a rural tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उर्वरा|उर्व्वरा<BR>urvarā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उषर<BR>uṣara, cf. sa-gartt-oṣara (IE 8-5); a saline spot or barren land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उशावडि<BR>uśāvaḍi (IE 8-4; SITI), a subdivision of the district; same<BR>as śāvaḍi or cāvaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊष्मल<BR>ūṣmala (EI 12), glowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उष्णिष<BR>uṣṇiṣa, cf. Prakrit uṃnisa (EI 20; LL), a coping stone.<BR>(EI 8), protuberance of the Buddha's skull.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कलित|उत्कलितः<BR>utkalita, cf. kaṭakam=utkalitam (IA 14, 30), ‘the camp was<BR>pitched’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कर|उत्करः<BR>utkara (IE 8-5), probably, minor taxes; but see kāru-kara.<BR>Cf. upakara, nikara, etc. But see also Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 47.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कर्णित<BR>utkarṇita (LP), frightened.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कर्ष|उत्कर्षः<BR>utkarṣa (CII 1), used in the sense of utkṛṣṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्खातकार्मण<BR>Utkhātakārmaṇa (EI 15), epithet of a donee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्खेटन<BR>utkheṭana (EI 32; HRS), known from certain records<BR>from Assam; explained as an impost levied upon the villagers<BR>on specified occasions; probably, the trouble of free labour.<BR>Cf. Utkheṭayitā, Autkheṭika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्खेटयिता<BR>Utkheṭayitā (EI 12; BL; HRS), known from certain<BR>Assam records; explained as a tax-collector; officer in charge<BR>of utkheṭana (q. v.); same as Autkheṭika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कीर्ण|उत्कीर्ण्ण<BR>utkīrṇa (CII 3), ‘engraved’; a technical expression for<BR>the actual engraving of an inscription on copper or stone; some-<BR>times indicated by the word udghāṭita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p.<BR>20) and ghaṭita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 121). See Ullekhaka,<BR>likhita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कोट<BR>utkoṭa (IE 8-5, 8-8; EI 33), Prakrit ukkoḍa; a levy; cus-<BR>tomary presents to be made on occasions to the king or land-<BR>lord and others. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कॄ<BR>ut-kṝ, ‘to engrave’; cf. Prakrit kaṇḍāra, used in some<BR>Kannaḍa inscriptions (Bul. Dec. Col. Res. Inst., Vol. XI, 1950,<BR>pp. 170-71). Cf. utkīrṇa, udghāṭita, Ullekhaka, Vilekhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कृष्टि<BR>utkṛṣṭi (IE 8-8; EI 30), same as Prakrit ukkuṭṭhī (q. v.),<BR>Sanskrit utkrośa; wailing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्क्रोश|उत्क्रोशः<BR>utkrośa (IE 8-8), see utkṛṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कृति|उत्कृतिः<BR>utkṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentysix’; rarely ‘twentyone’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पद्यमानविष्टिक<BR>utpadyamāna-viṣṭika (CII 4), ‘with the right to unpaid<BR>labour as occasion may arise’; a privilege attached to gift<BR>lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पन्न|उत्पन्नः<BR>utpanna, decided or ascertained (Select Inscriptions, pp.<BR>284, 286); same as pratipanna; cf. pratipad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पाट्<BR>ut-pāṭ (LP), Gujarātī upāḍavuṃ; cf. Vaidyanātha-patram=<BR>utpāṭayati, ‘takes a bilva-patra of the god Vaidyanātha (Śiva)’,<BR>i. e. swears.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पात|उत्पातः<BR>utpāta (EI 33), unusual phenomenon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पट्ट<BR>utpaṭṭa, cf. upaṭṭa (EI 13), abundance; exuberance or<BR>overflowing [especially of rich dishes at a feast].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पत्ति|उत्पत्तिः<BR>utpatti (EI 12), cf. samast-otpatti-sahita, ‘together with all<BR>the produce (or income)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्साह|उत्साहः<BR>utsāha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 189), generous gift, bounty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्साहशक्ति|उत्साहशक्तिः<BR>utsāha-śakti (CII 4), personal energy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सङ्ग|उत्संग|उत्संगः|उत्सङ्गः<BR>utsaṅga (HRS), extra cess levied upon villagers and<BR>citizens on occasions of festival events, such as the birth of a<BR>prince, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सर्पण|उत्सर्पणं|उत्सर्प्पण<BR>utsarpaṇa, cf. pañca-mahāyajña-kriy-otsarpaṇ-ārtham (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXV, p. 279, text lines 64-65).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सर्पित|उत्सर्प्पित<BR>utsarpita (CII 1), erected.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सृत<BR>utsṛta (CII 1) = ucchrita, man of a high position; a rich man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्त|उत्तं<BR>utta (LP), modification of Sanskrit putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमदानि<BR>uttama-dāni (SITI), a gift made without expecting any<BR>merit for the same; a superior kind of gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमगोसास<BR>uttama-gosāsa (IA 11), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमोत्तम<BR>uttam-ottama (EI 25), a type of temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तानद्वादशि<BR>uttāna-dvādaśi (SITI), twelfth day of the bright fortnight<BR>in the month of Kārttigai when the god Viṣṇu is believed to<BR>wake up from his sleep; see utthāna-dvādaśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तर|उत्तरं|उत्तरः<BR>uttara, cf. uttarāṇi (LP), same as uttar-ākṣarāṇi. See akṣara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तार|उत्तारः<BR>uttāra (SITI), a regular fixed payment; same as uddhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरकुलिक<BR>Uttarakulika (EI 30), a class of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरकुलिकवारिक<BR>Uttarakulika-vārika (IE 8-8), an official designation of<BR>uncertain import. See Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरमन्त्रिन्<BR>Uttara-mantrin (EI 8; SITI), the chief minister.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरनियोग<BR>uttara-niyoga (EI 32), ‘subsequent assignment’; cf. ukta-<BR>niyoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरसभा<BR>uttara-sabhā (EI 19), the supreme assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरवाद<BR>uttara-vāda (SITI), a guarantee; responsibility.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरायण|उत्तरायणं<BR>uttar-āyaṇa (IA 17; SII 1), the winter solstice; the<BR>period during which the sun gradually moves from south to<BR>north; cf. dakṣiṇ-āyana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थान|उत्थानं<BR>utthāna (CII 1), exerting oneself.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थानद्वादशी<BR>utthāna-dvādaśī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 163, 167,<BR>169), name of a tithi (EI 9); twelfth day of the bright fort-<BR>night in the month of Kārttigai when the god Viṣṇu is believ-<BR>ed to wake up from his sleep (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थाय<BR>utthāya, ‘of one's own accord’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 248).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थितासनिन्<BR>Utthit-āsanin (IE 8-3); see Autthilāsanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तिरम्<BR>uttiram (SII 2), the projecting part of a wall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उवटक<BR>uvaṭaka (EI 1), probably, a verandah, porch or vesti-<BR>bule; cf. Marāṭhī oṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः<BR>va (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vaḍḍavāra (Saturday or<BR>Thursday).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः<BR>va (CII 3; IA 8-1), an abbreviation of vadya or ‘the dark<BR>fortnight’ or else a substitute for ba (abbreviation of bahula)<BR>used in connection with di; see ba-di, va-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः<BR>va, vā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Prakrit vassa or vāsa-<BR>Sanskrit varṣā, the rainy season.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वा<BR>vā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vāra.<BR>Cf. vā-bhū, vā-ṭī.<BR>(LP), abbreviation of Vāṇija, a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाभू<BR>vā-bhū (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vāstu-bhūmi, ‘home-<BR>stead land.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाचक|वाचकः<BR>Vācaka (LL), a Jain preacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वचन|वचनं<BR>vacana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वचनकार<BR>Vacanakāra (EI 23), an author of vacanas or sayings; cf.<BR>subhāṣita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाचनिक<BR>vācanika, cf. rāja-vāchanika (CII 1), a royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वचोगुप्ति<BR>vaco-gupti (CII 1), restraint in the matter of speech.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाड|वाडः<BR>vāḍa (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a street, a range of houses.<BR>(EI 11), a ward.<BR>(IA 7), also vāḍi; often suffixed to geographical names.<BR>(CII 4), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाड|वाडः<BR>vāḍa, vāḍā (IE 8-4), corrupt forms of pāṭaka, ‘part<BR>of a village’; in soem dialects, also ‘a village’; often suffixed<BR>to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वडहरक<BR>Vaḍaharaka (EI 11), same as Marvāḏī (Marwari)<BR>Baḍero; an old man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डाचार्य<BR>Vaḍḍ-ācārya (SII 11-1), Sanskrit Vṛddh-ācārya or<BR>Bṛhad-ācārya; designation of a Jain teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डवार<BR>vaḍḍa-vāra (EI 13; CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa;' Satur-<BR>day or Thursday (A. Venkatasubbiah, Some Śaka Dates in<BR>Inscriptions, pp. 57. ff.); same as bṛha-vāra. The word in the<BR>Telugu part of an inscription is explained as śanaiścara-vāra in<BR>the Sanskrit portion of the said record; sometimes wrongly<BR>supposed to stand for some other day, e. g. Friday (IA 23)<BR>or Sunday (Venkatasubbiah, op. cit., p. 58). Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XII, p. 147; XIII, p. 16; Vol. XXXI, p. 100, note 1; Vol.<BR>XXXIII, p. 1, note 2; Ind. Ant., Vol. XXII, pp. 111, 251-52;<BR>XXIII, p. 168. Vaḍḍa=vṛddha or bṛhat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डव्यवहारि<BR>Vaḍḍa-vyavahāri (SITI; ASLV), the leader of a merchant<BR>guild; a banker; the principal money-changer; chief of the<BR>Nānādeśi (non-local) merchants. Cf. Mahāvaḍḍavyavahāri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वडवा<BR>Vaḍavā (EI 22, 27), Marāṭhil; record-keeper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाध|वाधः<BR>vādha (EI 16), land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाधा<BR>vādhā, cf. bādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाढढा<BR>vāḍhaḍhā (IA 15), a doubtful word probably meaning ‘a<BR>drum’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वध्रिकुक्कुट<BR>vadhri-kukkuṭa (IA 18, CII 1), Prakrit vadhi-kukuṭa; a<BR>capon; also Sanskritised as vṛddhi-kukkuṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वधू<BR>vadhū, one's own wife; one's son's wife. (putra-vadhū)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वदि<BR>va-di (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vadya-pakṣa-dina or a<BR>mistake for ba-di (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाडि<BR>vāḍi (IA 7), same as vāḍa; often suffixed to geographical<BR>names.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाद्य|वाद्यं<BR>vādya (SITI), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाद्यमहाराज<BR>Vādya-mahārāja, cf. Tamil Vācciya-mārāyaṉ (SITI), the<BR>head musician or the chief Meḻakāraṉ of a temple or palace; title<BR>conferred by the king on an expert in instrumental music.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वगैर<BR>vagaira (IA 20), Persian; ‘and so forth’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वागुली<BR>Vāgulī (EI 28), Oḏiyā; also written Bāgulī; the king's<BR>betel-bearer; same as Vārgulika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वागुलिक<BR>Vāgulika, Vāgūlika (CII 4; BL), explained by some as ‘a<BR>seller of betel-leaves’; the bearer of the betel-box of an Orissan<BR>ruler; same as Vārgulika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वागुणि<BR>Vāguṇi (EI 24), mistake for Vāguli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वह|वहः<BR>vaha, cf. a-vaha (IE 8-5); [free] carrying of loads [which<BR>the villagers had to provide for the touring officers of the<BR>king or land-lord]; may also be a horse for the use of the officers.<BR>(EI 31; IA 18; CII 4), a streamlet; a water-channel.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 177), a common highway.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाह|वाहः<BR>vāha, cf. Vāha-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहक|वाहकः<BR>Vāhaka (EI 3), probably, a driver or attendant of cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहला<BR>vāhalā (EI 3), a water course.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहलि<BR>Vāhali (BL), official designation explained as ‘the lord of<BR>horses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहमान<BR>vahamāna (LP), cf. vahamāna-hala-balīvarda, ‘bullocks used<BR>in ploughing land’; vahamāna-samakara-bhūmi in which vahamāna<BR>means ‘[the land that is] being ploughed’.<BR>(LP), travelling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहन|वाहनं<BR>vāhana (LP), a load-carrier; a cart, ship, etc. See<BR>vahitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहनायक<BR>Vāha-nāyaka (EI 23), official designation; probably, ‘the<BR>officer in charge of the king's Khās Mahāls’ (from vāha, a<BR>plough); may also be the superintendent of transport. See<BR>vāhoṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहिका<BR>vahikā (LP), an account book.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहिनीपति|वाहिनीपतिः<BR>Vāhinīpati (EI 28; IA 10), leader of forces; a general; cf.<BR>Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहणि<BR>vahaṇi (IA 18), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहित्र|वहित्रं<BR>vahitra (IE 8-5, 8-8; EI 30), boat or any large carrier<BR>like a cart; see vāhana. Cf. sārtha-vahitreṣu praveśe nirgame ca<BR>pratyekaṃ rūpakaḥ devasya yātr-otsave dātavyaḥ (Ep. Ind., Vol.<BR>XXV, p. 232).<BR>(IE 8-8), cf. bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra, ‘a wagon full of pots or jars’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वह्नि|वह्निः<BR>vahni (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहोटक<BR>vāhoṭaka (LP), either Gujarātī vighoṭi, an assessment<BR>of land collected per vighā (bīghā), or the plough tax (i. e. land<BR>tax) from vāha, a plough.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाह्यालि<BR>vāhyāli (BL), explained as ‘stables’; cf. bāhy-āli.<BR>(EI 6), explained as ‘a camp’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वह्नि|वह्निः<BR>vahni (EI 33), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैभोग<BR>vaibhoga, cf. aṅga-raṅga-vaibhoga (EI 3; SII 1; SITI);<BR>same as bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैदर्वेयक<BR>vaidarveyaka, cf. vedaveyaka (IA 18; CII 1), an eel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैधरण<BR>vaidharaṇa (HRS), a compensation fee levied upon<BR>the sale of liquors, royal merchandise, mining products and<BR>imported salt, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैदिल<BR>vaidila (CII 3), a word of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्य|वैद्यः<BR>Vaidya (EI 9, 30; BL), a physician; member of the physician<BR>community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यभाग<BR>vaidya-bhāga (SII 2), same as vaidya-bhoga, vaidya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यभोग<BR>vaidya-bhoga (SITI), also called vaidya-bhāga, vaidya-<BR>vṛtti; land set apart for the maintenance of the physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यपरिचारक<BR>Vaidya-paricāraka, cf. Tamil Vaijya-paricārakar (EI 24),<BR>medical attendants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यवृत्ति<BR>vaidya-vṛtti (SII 1), land enjoyed by the Vaidyas for<BR>their maintenance; cf. vaidya-bhāga, vaidya-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैजक<BR>Vaijaka (EI 26), official designation; probably Vaidyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैजयिक|वैजयिकं<BR>vaijayika, carrying victory; cf. Ep. Ind., XXXII, p. 88.<BR>See vijaya-vaijayika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैजयिकधर्मस्थान<BR>vaijayika-dharmasthāna (EI 22), ‘the victorious office<BR>of justice’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैक्षेपिक<BR>Vaikṣepika (EI 8-3; EI 26), probably, the dispatcher of<BR>messengers; same as Preṣaṇika. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVI,<BR>p. 206. See also vikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैलब्धिक<BR>Vailabdhika (EI 8-3; EI 30), officer in charge of vilabdhi<BR>(q. v.); probably, the custodian of recovered stolen property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैदान्तिक<BR>Vaidāntika (BL), an exponent of the Vedānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैर|वैरं<BR>vaira (IA 18), blood-money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैरागि<BR>Vairāgi (SITI), an ascetic serving in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैशारद्य|वैशारद्यं<BR>vaiśāradya cf. vesārajja (EI 5), Buddhist; four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैषयिक|वैषयिकः<BR>Vaiṣayika (EI 7), probably, the ruler of a viṣaya or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्वदेव|वैश्वदेवः<BR>vaiśvadeva (EI 10, 14, 23; CII 3, 4), offerings to gods;<BR>one of the five mahāyajñas; sometimes called vaiśvānara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्वानर|वैश्वानरः<BR>vaiśvānara (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR>Cf. vaiśvadeva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्वासिक<BR>Vaiśvāsika (IE 8-3; EI 9, 28, 29), probably the same as<BR>Rahasyādhikṛta, etc.; cf. Paramaviśvāsin, Viśvāsa, Viśvāsika; the<BR>privy councillor or private secretary.<BR>(EI 3), mentioned along with Antaraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्याग्रहार<BR>vaiśy-āgrahāra (IE 8-5; EI 30, 33), a privileged holding<BR>created in favour of members of the mercantile community;<BR>see agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्यवाणियनगरत्तार्<BR>vaiśya-vāṇiya-nagarattār (SITI), ASLV), Sanskrit vaiśya-<BR>vāṇija-nagarastha; a corporation of the merchants; the guild of<BR>a class of merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाजपेय|वाजपेयं|वाजपेयः<BR>vājapeya (EI 22; CII 4; BL), name of a Vedic sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाजिन्<BR>vājin (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाजिवैद्य<BR>Vāji-vaidya (BL), explained as ‘a veterinary physician’;<BR>literally, ‘a physician for horses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वज्र|वज्रं|वज्रः<BR>vajra (HA), thunderbolt.<BR>Cf. vaccira-ppaḍai (SITI), the lower or foundation tier<BR>of the wall of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वज्रासन<BR>vajrāsana (LL), name of the seat on which the Buddha<BR>sat for meditation for the attainment of supreme knowledge<BR>(bodhi).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाक्पारुष्य|वाक्पारुष्यं<BR>vāk-pāruṣya (EI 30), use of abusive language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाक्ष<BR>vākṣa (Chamba), tax in cash; same as bācha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलदी<BR>valadī (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 17, text line 21), correctly<BR>baladī derived from balīvarda; same as vara-balīvarda, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालगिरि<BR>vāḻa-giri (SITI), abbreviation of the name of the mythical<BR>mountain called cakravāla-giri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलनाडु<BR>vaḻanāḍu (IE 8-4; EI 25), Tamil; a province; a district<BR>consisting of sub-divisions called kuṟṟam or nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलक्ष|वलक्षः<BR>valakṣa (IA 17), used to indicate the bright fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालनीय<BR>vālanīya (LP), see valiṣyati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलत्कौषन्<BR>Valatkauṣan (CII 3), official designation of uncertain<BR>import; probably, a mistake for Bala-kauṣṭhika, officer-in-charge<BR>of the treasury of the military department. Cf. Mahavalākoṣṭhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलाकोष्ठिक<BR>Valākoṣṭhika, probably, a mistake for Balakoṣṭhika; cf. Valat-<BR>kauṣan, Mahāvalākoṣṭhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलय|वलयं|वलयः<BR>valaya (CITD), a ring; a bracelet; in Telugu-Kannaḍa,<BR>also an enclosure, a boundary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलयष्टि<BR>vala-yaṣṭi (CII 4), mistake for bala-yaṣṭi, memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलययष्टि<BR>valaya-yaṣṭi (EI 33; CII 3), wrong emendation of bala-<BR>yaṣṭi and supposed to mean ‘a boundary-pillar’. See bala-yaṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालयित्वा<BR>vālayitvā (LP), Gujarātī vāḻīne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्होडीय<BR>valhoḍīya (LP), rams.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालि|वालिः<BR>vāḻi (SII 2), ear-ring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलिस्यति<BR>valisyati (LP), cf. Gujarātī vāḷi levāmāṃ āvaśe; see vālanīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलित<BR>valita, vaḻita (E 12; SITI), same as vaṇita; a small terri-<BR>torial unit; a district or its subdivision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलितपत्रविधि<BR>valita-patra-vidhi (LP), cf. Gujarātī vaḻat-dān-khat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलीवर्द|वलीवर्दः|वलीवर्द्द|वलीवर्द्दः<BR>valīvarda, variant spelling of balīvarda (q. v.); cf. a-param-<BR>parā-valivarda, etc. (IE 8-5); a pair of bullocks [which the<BR>villagers were obliged to provide for the cart of the royal officers<BR>when they were camping or touring in the village].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्ल|वल्लः<BR>valla (IE 8-8), name of a weight equal to 3 ratis; see dvi-<BR>vallakya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्लभ|वल्लभः<BR>Vallabha (IE 8-3; EI 12, 26), the king's favourite or a<BR>courtier; same as Rājavallabha.<BR>(IE 8-2), same as Vallabharāja; a shortened form of the<BR>title Śrī-pṛthivī-vallabha assumed by certain imperial rulers of the<BR>Kannaḍa-speaking area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्लक्य<BR>vallakya, cf. dvi-vallakya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्लव|वल्लवः<BR>Vallava (IE 8-3; 27; LL), official designation; officer in<BR>charge of the king's cattle; same as Sanskrit Vallabha, a herdsman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वामनमुद्रा<BR>vāmana-mudrā (SITI), figures of śaṅkha and cakra marked<BR>on the boundary stones set up to demarcate the lands of a Viṣṇu<BR>temple. Cf. Vāmana-kkal, boundary stone of land granted for<BR>religious purposes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वांफय<BR>vāṃphaya, cf. niddhi-vāṃphaya-sahita (EI 12), wrong reading<BR>of nidhi-nikṣepa-sahita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंशधर<BR>vaṃśadhara (EI 24), a palanquin-bearer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंशकर<BR>Vaṃśakara (LL), a bamboo-worker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंशावली<BR>Vaṃś-āvalī (IA 30), a genealogical list; called kula-pañjī or<BR>kula-pañjikā in Bengal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वांशिक|वांशिकः<BR>Vāṃśika (EI 33), a flute-player.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंश्य|वंश्यः<BR>vaṃśya, same as dhvaṃśī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वन|वनं<BR>vana, a source of income. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp.<BR>109-10. Cf. nāga-vana (IE 8-4), an elephant-forest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनचर<BR>vanacara (EI 12), an animal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनधि<BR>vanadhi (IE 7-1-2), used in the sense of vāridhi to indicate<BR>‘four.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनदुर्ग<BR>vana-durga (ASLV), fort built in the midst of forests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणजारक<BR>Vaṇajāraka, also spelt Vaṇijāraka (EI 11), same as the<BR>Vanjārī of Rājasthān, whose hereditary calling is to carry grains<BR>on pack-bullocks; cf. Vaṇijjāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वन्दापना<BR>vandāpanā (IE 8-5; EI 12, 33), Oḏiyā; presents to be made<BR>on meeting the king or landlord; same as Persian nazrāna; cf.<BR>vijaya-vandāpanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वङ्गाली<BR>Vaṅgālī, see Bengali which is its Anglicised spelling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाणिज|वाणिजः<BR>Vāṇija, Vāṇijaka (EI 15; LL), a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिज्जारक<BR>Vaṇijjāraka (BL), probably, merchants or traders of cara-<BR>vans; cf. Vaṇajāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्<BR>Vaṇik (IE 8-3; BL), merchant or a member of the<BR>merchantile community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्पथ|वणिक्पथः<BR>vaṇik-patha, ‘trade-route’; a revenue term. See Ghoshal, H.<BR>Rev. Syst., pp. 79-80.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्स्थान<BR>vaṇik-sthāna (EI 23), an association of merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्सुवर्णकार<BR>Vaṇik-suvarṇakāra (BL), probably, ‘one who is a banker<BR>and a goldsmith’; cf. the Suvarṇa-vaṇik community of Bengal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिङ्कोट्ट<BR>vaṇiṅ-koṭṭa (CII 4), ‘the traders’ fortress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिङ्नगर<BR>Vaṇiṅ-nagara (CII 4), ‘a town of merchants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणित<BR>vaṇita (IE 8-4; SITI), Kannaḍa; same as vaḻita; a small<BR>territorial unit like a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वञ्जुली<BR>vañjulī (IA 26), the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वन्निआ<BR>vanniā (IE 8-8), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit varṇikā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वण्टक|वंटक|वंटकः|वण्टकः<BR>vaṇṭaka (EI 9, 13), a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वण्ट्य<BR>vaṇṭya (EI 12), a district; cf. vĕṇṭhĕ, vĕṇṭhĕya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाप|वापः<BR>vāpa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 310, note 4), explained as a<BR>handcast or handful; but really, the same as vapa, sowing [seed<BR>grains appa ently by handcast].<BR>(EI 15), cf. kulyavāpa (area requiring one kulya measure<BR>of seeds to be sown by handcast); see vāpa-gatyā, etc.<BR>(EI 3), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वापगत्या<BR>vāpa-gatyā, cf. vauge (EI 10), grain sown broadcast.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वापी<BR>vāpī (EI 13), step-well; an irrigation well; same as vāpikā.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), a well with a flight of<BR>stairs; cf. kūpa which is an ordinary well.<BR>(EI 22), a reservoir of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वापिका<BR>vāpikā (CCI 3), a step-well, an irrigation well; same as vāpī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वप्पक<BR>vappaka (EI 23), a land measure. Same as vapyaka, vāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वप्यक<BR>vapyaka (EI 3), a land measure; same as vappaka, vāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार|वारं|वारः<BR>vāra (BL), a board of administrators [formed by the<BR>śreṣṭhins, sārthavāhas and others].<BR>(IA 16), the solar day.<BR>(SITI), method of reciting the Vedas.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 17, note 1), probably, a week.<BR>(EI 30; SITI), a share of the produce.<BR>(EI 24), a multitude. Cf. also vāra-Nāka-Lokta-Gāñīk-<BR>ādīnāṃ, ‘belonging to Nāka, Lokta and Gāñīka collectively’<BR>(JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, pp. 202, 204).<BR>(CII 1) cf. vārataḥ, ‘in consequence of an occasion.’<BR>(EI 23), same as vāra-goṣṭhī; a committee; cf. vāra-pra-<BR>mukha. Vāra is the same as Tamil vāriyam.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR>Cf. bāre (Chamba), ‘during or in the time of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरबलीवर्द<BR>vara-balīvarda (EI 12, 33), tax on choice bullocks for<BR>bull-fights; cf. valadī, yamalikambali, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरदमुद्रा<BR>varada-mudrā (HA), the gift-bestowing attitude of the<BR>right hand with palm outwards and fingers pointing downwards.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारगोष्ठी<BR>vāra-goṣṭhī (EI 5, 23), a committee's assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरग्राम<BR>vara-grāma (SITI), village given as a gift to a temple<BR>or maṭha or a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारगृह<BR>vāra-gṛha (EI 19), outside houses; cf. Sanskrit bahir-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराह|वराहः<BR>varāha (IE 8-8; EI 25; SITI; SII 1), also called hūn or<BR>hon; name of a gold coin called pagoda or ‘star pagoda’ in English;<BR>Cf. doḍḍa-varāha (EI 20), varāha-paṇam (SITI), varāhanpuḻḻi-<BR>kuḻigai (SITI), parumuḻai-varāhan (SITI); etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहगद्याण<BR>varāha-gadyāṇa (EI 8, 27), same as varāha or gadyāṇa; i. e.<BR>a pagoda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहकीयविंशोपक<BR>varāhakīya-viṃśopaka (EI 1), name of a coin which was one-<BR>twentieth of a varāha in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहमुद्रा<BR>varāha-mudrā, cf. varāha-muddirai (SITI), the seal or<BR>emblem bearing the figure of a boar, being the crest of certain<BR>kings like those of Vijayanagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराक|वराकः<BR>varāka (CII 1), distressed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारकृत<BR>Vārakṛta (EI 23), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरण|वरणं|वरणः<BR>varaṇa (SITI), the selection or election of a person to a<BR>committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरण्डिकावृत<BR>varaṇḍikā-vṛta (LP), ‘surrounded by a verandah’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारप्रमुख<BR>Vāra-pramukha (EI 5), the head of a committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारसिद्धि<BR>vāra-siddhi, cf. a-vāra-siddhika (EI 8-5); probably refers<BR>to the supply of unpaid labour by the villagers in turn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरटका<BR>varaṭakā (EI 1), ‘cowrie-shell used as a coin’; same as<BR>varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराटिका<BR>varāṭikā, ‘a cowrie-shell used as a coin’; money. See<BR>Gaurī-varāṭikā, varaṭakā, barāḍ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरवझे<BR>varavajhe (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIV, p. 103, text line 12),<BR>doubtful name of a tax; same as vara-balīvarda, baladī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरयात्रा<BR>vara-yātrā (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, the procession of a<BR>bride-groom to the bride's place for marriage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्धकि|वर्द्धकिः|वर्धकिः<BR>Vardhaki (LL), a carpenter; cf. Śaila-vardhaki, a mason<BR>or sculptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्धमान|वर्द्धमानः<BR>vardhamāna (LP), ‘when cut down.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्धि|वार्द्धिः|वार्धिः<BR>vārdhi (EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्ग|वर्गः|वर्ग्ग<BR>varga (CII 1), a group or cadre of officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्गुलिक<BR>Vārgulika (IE 8-3; EI 28; BL), same as Oḏiyā Bāguli,<BR>Vāguli; the bearer of the king's betel-box. Cf. Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरि<BR>vari (SITI), Tamil; tax; revenue register; order of<BR>the king and his officers fixing the revenue. Cf. vari-ppotta-<BR>gam, tax register; an officer maintaining the same; also Vari-<BR>ppottaga-nāyakam, the head office of the revenue accounts;<BR>the chief officer of the same office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिधि|वारिधिः<BR>vāridhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिग<BR>Vāriga (EI 33), corruption of Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिगृहकरण<BR>vāri-gṛha-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the<BR>department of water works’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिक<BR>Vārika (IE 8-8; EI 30, 32), a class of officials; the priest<BR>or superintendent of a temple like a Pāṇḍā of modern times;<BR>cf. Deva-vārika (EI 27), superintendent of a temple; also cf.<BR>Tamil Vāriyan (SITI), a supervisor.<BR>Cf. Mahāgandhakuṭī-vārika (LL), ‘superintendent of the<BR>great gandhakūṭī (q. v.).’ The official designation Pāṭvāri seems<BR>to be derived from Paṭṭavārika.<BR>Cf. Tamil vāriyaṃ (SITI), an executive committee;<BR>appointment as a member of that body; an office of supervision;<BR>cf. śrībhaṇḍāra-vāriyam (EI 33). See SII, Vol. III, p. 151, note.<BR>Cf. bārika (EI 5, 19), a village official; one entrusted<BR>with putting an official seal or stamp to a document; cf.<BR>bārika-jana-hasta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिनिधि|वारिनिधिः<BR>vārinidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्कर|वर्करः<BR>varkara (IA 19), a goat; cf. botkaṭa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्ण|वर्णं|वर्णः|वर्ण्ण<BR>varṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR>(Select Inscriptions, p. 187, text line 6), same as varṇanā, a<BR>description or list.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्णन|वर्णनं<BR>varṇana (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), a written order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्णिका<BR>varṇikā (IE 8-8; EI 30), same a Prakrit vanniā, a sample;<BR>sometimes, a small measure of capacity (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p.<BR>302, verse 69).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्ष|वर्षं|वर्षः<BR>varṣa (CII 3, 4; IA 17), a year; used for saṃvatsara or its<BR>abbreviations.<BR>(EI 23), the rainy season.<BR>Cf. varṣe (IA 19), used in the dates after the quotation<BR>of saṃvat; sometimes abbreviated to va. Cf. samaye used in the<BR>same sense.<BR>Cf. Tamil varuṣa-kāṇikkai (SITI), annual presents.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’; cf. the nine divisions of Jambu-dvīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षग्रन्थि<BR>varṣa-granthi (EI 8), an anniversary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षपर्युषित<BR>varṣa-paryuṣita (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, ‘camping for<BR>the rainy season only’; used in connection with merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षवर्तमानी<BR>varṣa-vartamānī, the annual Durbar (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol.<BR>X, p. 15).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षवृद्धि|वर्षवृद्धिः<BR>varṣa-vṛddhi, probably ‘birthday anniversary’ (JAS, Letters,<BR>Vol. XX, p. 206).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्त|वार्त्त|वार्त्तं|वार्त्तः<BR>Vārta, Vartta (CII 4; IA 14), same as Vṛtti-bhuj, ‘one who<BR>enjoys a grant or the share of a grant’; a person in possession of<BR>a vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तमान|वर्त्तमान|वर्त्तमानः<BR>vartamāna (HRS), ‘running revenue’, as suggested by<BR>the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तमानभविष्यत्<BR>vartamāna-bhaviṣyat (IE 8-3), ‘of the present and future’;<BR>used with reference to the officers associated with a gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तना<BR>vartanā (SITI), perquisites due to an office; periodical<BR>presents to be offered to an officer of rank by his subordinates<BR>and the people. Cf. vartanī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तनी|वर्त्तनी<BR>vartanī (HRS), transit duties collected by the ferrymen, the<BR>superintendent of tolls and the boundary officer, as suggested<BR>by the Arthaśāstra. Cf. vartanā.<BR>(IA 18), a district; often found suffixed to the names of<BR>districts in the Kaliṅga region.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 174), a road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्तानुकर्षक|वार्त्तानुकर्षक|वार्त्तानुकर्षकः<BR>Vārt-ānukarṣaka (IA 6), official designation of doubtful<BR>meaning; probably, a spy; mentioned in the Mahābhārata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्त्मदण्ड<BR>vartma-daṇḍa (IE 8-5), tolls collected on the roads for<BR>the passage of articles of merchandise through a village. Cf.<BR>Tamil vaḻiy-āyam (SITI), ‘tolls on the roadway’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्त्मपाल<BR>Vartmapāla (IE 8-3), superintendent of roads or the<BR>collector of the vartma-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारुघोटक<BR>vāru-ghoṭaka (LP), a riding horse; cf. Marāṭhī vāru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारुणी<BR>vāruṇī, cf. mahāmahāvāruṇī, mahāvāruṇī (EI 25); name of a<BR>tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसा<BR>Va-sā (PJS), probably, an abbreviation of Vaṇik-sādhu, ‘a<BR>merchant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसद्भोगमर्यादा<BR>vasad-bhoga-maryādā (IA 5), explained as ‘the condition<BR>that the gift villages should be enjoyed only by those residing<BR>therein’; the custom relating to the enjoyment of the gift land<BR>by the donee by residing therein; but see vasad-bhogya-maryādā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसद्भोग्यमर्यादा<BR>vasad-bhogya-maryādā (EI 24), interpreted as ‘with the<BR>tenants’ occupancy rights assured’; same as vasad-bhoga-maryādā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसदि<BR>vasadi (EI 10), Sanskrit vasati; a Jain temple; cf. vasahī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासागारिक<BR>Vāsāgārika (IE 8-3; EI 30), officer in charge of the king's<BR>bed-chamber. See Vitān-ādhipa, Śayyāpāla, Śayyāgrāhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसही<BR>vasahī (HA), Sanskrit vasati; a Jain temple; cf. vasadi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासक|वासकः<BR>vāsaka (EI 3, 14, 23, 30; IA 13), royal residence whence the<BR>copper-plate grants were often issued; the camp or capital of<BR>a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासक्षेप<BR>vāsa-kṣepa (HA), scattering of powder; also the powder itself.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्<BR>Vāśal (ASLV), same as Vāśal-kāriyam; chief guard of the<BR>palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्कारियम्<BR>Vāśal-kāriyam (ASLV), also called Vāśal; chief guard of<BR>the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्पणम्<BR>vāśal-paṇam (SII 1), the door-money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासनिका<BR>vāsanikā (EI 23), a dwelling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसन्तगरुवु<BR>vasantagaruvu (ASLV), a rest house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसन्तमण्डप<BR>vasanta-maṇḍapa (SITI), maṇḍapa in the midst of a plea-<BR>sure garden where the spring-festival of a deity is celebrated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसन्तोत्सव|वसंतोत्सव|वसन्तोत्सवः<BR>vasant-otsava (BL), spring festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासापक<BR>Vāsāpaka (EI 6, 12; CII 4; IA 12, 13), explained as<BR>‘officials whose duty was to assign places of residence to strang-<BR>ers’; also spelt Vāsāvaka; cf. also the tax called vāsāvakī (EI 33).<BR>Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XIII, p. 69, note 11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासावक<BR>Vāsāvaka (CII 4), same as Vāsāpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसावकी<BR>vasāvakī (EI 33), name of a tax; cf. the official designation<BR>Vāsāpaka or Vāsāvaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसति|वसतिः<BR>vasati, modified to basadi (EI 10), basahi (HA), pasti,<BR>basti (SITI), etc.; a Jain temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसतिदण्ड<BR>vasati-daṇḍa (EI 25), obligation of the villagers to supply<BR>food to the royal officers camping in their village; explained by<BR>some as ‘the tax for the lodging of touring royal officers’ (CII<BR>4); but probably refers to an obligation and not a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासेलकुटुंबिक<BR>Vāsela-kuṭuṃbika (LP), resident farmers; cf. Gujarātī<BR>Vasṇārā-kaṇbī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तव्य|वास्तव्यः<BR>Vāstavya (EI 16), a community of the Kāyasthas.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 172, note 3), rarely also<BR>called sāmānya; ‘resident’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तु<BR>vāstu (EI 15, 32), homestead land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुभूमि<BR>vāstu-bhūmi (IE 8-1), homestead land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुक|वास्तुकं<BR>vāstuka, a building site. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst.,<BR>pp. 97-98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुकृत्य<BR>vāstu-kṛtya (SITI), building work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुपरिवार<BR>vāstu-parivāra (SITI), vacant site attached to a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वस्तुप्राभृतक<BR>vastu-prābhṛtaka, cf. vastu-prābhṛtakena (LP), ‘in exchange<BR>for a present’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसु|वसुः<BR>vasu (IE 7-1-2; EI 15), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासु|वासुः<BR>vāsu (Ep 11), a ward.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसुधा<BR>vasudhā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसुन्धरा|वसुंधरा<BR>vasundharā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसुपत्रपद्म<BR>vasu-patra-padma (IA 9), eight-petalled lotus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाल|वालः<BR>vāla (IE 8-5; EI 15; CII 3), cf. sa-bhūta-vāta-pratyāya,<BR>etc.; probably, storms (cf. udvāta; also called āvāta.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातादेय<BR>vāt-ādeya (EI 32), ‘income resulting from storms’; same<BR>as vāta-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटक|वाटकः<BR>vāṭaka (LL), a garden.<BR>(IE 8-4; EI 15; IA 7), corrupt form of pāṭaka; ‘part<BR>of a village’; often suffixed to names of localities.<BR>Cf. the second component in Talla-vāṭaka, meaning modern<BR>vāḍa, spelt in English as wara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वटक|वटकः<BR>vaṭaka, same as tolaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातप्रत्याय<BR>vāta-pratyāya (EI 32; CII 4), explained by some as ‘octroi<BR>duty’, but actually, ‘income resulting from storms’; same as<BR>vāt-ādeya. See bhūta-vāta-pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वति|वतिः<BR>va-ti (IE 8-1), contraction of vadya-pakṣa-tithi, though va<BR>may be a mistake for ba (bahula).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटि<BR>vāṭi, vāṭī (IE 8-6; EI 28, 30), also called vāṭikā (q. v.);<BR>land measure equal to twenty māṇas in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटी<BR>vā-ṭī, abbreviation of vāstu-ṭīkara, ‘a mound containing<BR>land suitable for building houses.’ See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX,<BR>p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटिका<BR>vāṭikā (EI 15; SITI), same as nilam or veḻi, defined in<BR>the Mayamata as 5120 square daṇḍas, the length of the daṇḍa<BR>being 4 cubits; 4. 48 acres.<BR>(EI 30), a land measure equal to twenty māṇas in<BR>Orissa; same as vāṭi, vāṭī; equal to 20 acres.<BR>(EI 27), a hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातोत्तर<BR>vāt-ottara (IE 8-5), ‘resulting from storms’; cf. vāt-ādeya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टग्राम<BR>vaṭṭa-grāma (EI 24), subsidiary village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टम्<BR>vaṭṭam (SITI), money-changer's commission; trade discount.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टे<BR>Vaṭṭel13uttu, name of a alphabet prevalent in medieval<BR>times in the southern part of the Tamil-speaking area and the<BR>land to its west.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाव<BR>vāva (IE 8-2), one's uncle or a relation of one's father's<BR>generation; cf. vāva-pād-ānudhyāta, ‘meditating on (or,<BR>favoured by) the feet of the uncle (or a relation of one's father's<BR>generation).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाय्क्केल्वि<BR>Vāy-kkeḻvi, Vāy-kkeḻviyār (SITI), an officer who received<BR>the king's oral orders; an officer in attendance on the king,<BR>acting as the intermediary between the king and his subjects;<BR>the king's order. Cf. Ājñapti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वायु|वायुः<BR>vāyu (IE 7-1-2), ‘fortynine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेद|वेदः<BR>veda (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’ (the four Vedas being Ṛk, Yajus,<BR>Sāman and Atharvan); rarely used to indicate ‘three’ (cf. trayī)<BR>in late records (IE 7-1-2; IA 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदमठ<BR>veda-maṭha (ASLV), school for teaching the Vedas. There<BR>was such a school at Kāñcīpuram. Cf. śālā, khaṇḍikā, Ṛgveda-<BR>khaṇḍikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदपारायण<BR>Veda-pārāyaṇa (IA 12), priest who repeats the Veda at<BR>the Rāmeśvaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदवेयक<BR>vedaveyaka (CII 1), Prakrit; see vaidarveyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदवृत्ति<BR>veda-vṛtti (SITI), tax-free land set apart for meeting the<BR>expenses of reciting, the Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदि|वेदिः<BR>vedi (EI 32), a seat; also a raised platform (cf. vedikā).<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-369" target="_blank">Page-369+ 40</a>]<BR>See JBRS, Vol. XXXIX, Parts 1-2, pp. 43-44, 47; Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXXV, p. 192.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदिका<BR>vedikā (LL), a rail; also, a raised platform (cf. vedi).<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 192.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेग्गडे<BR>Vĕggaḍĕ (IE 8-3), same as Vĕrgaḍĕ, Pĕggaḍĕ, Pĕrgaḍĕ,<BR>Hĕggaḍĕ, etc. (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलादुर्गपाल<BR>Velā-durga-pāla (SITI), a port officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलैक्कारर्<BR>Veḻai-kkārar (SITI), Tamil; trusted warriors even pre-<BR>pared to lay down their lives in the service of their master.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलाकुल<BR>velākula, velākūla (IE 8-4; EI 31; LP), a harbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलाकुलकरण<BR>velākula-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the harbour department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलापुर<BR>velāpura, cf. velāura (IA 10, 14), a harbour; same as<BR>velākūla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलावित्त|वेलावित्तः<BR>Velāvitta (HD), meaning uncertain. See Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>V. 226; VI. 73, 106, 126. Cf. Pīṭhikāvitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलि<BR>veḻi (IE 8-6; EI 25), Tamil; a big land measure. See<BR>vāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिचेनु<BR>veli-cenu (CITD), Telugu; usually, a field on a high level<BR>depending on rain water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिपोलमु<BR>veli-polamu (CITD), Telugu; see veli-volamu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिवोलमु<BR>veli-volamu (CITD), Telugu; also called veli-polamu;<BR>similar to veli-cenu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेल्लि|वेल्लिः<BR>veḻḻi (EI 15), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेना<BR>venā (EI 31), a kind of grass.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेणी<BR>veṇī (IA 17), a stream or river.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेङ्कटविलासमण्टप<BR>veṅkaṭa-vilāsa-maṇṭapa (ASLV), hall in which the royal<BR>council met at Vijayanagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेण्ठे<BR>vĕṇṭhĕ (EI 16; ASLV), same as viṣaya, nirvṛtti, koṭṭam,<BR>etc.; an administrative division; also called vĕṇṭhĕya, vaṇtya,<BR>vĕṭha, vĕṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेण्ठेय<BR>vĕṇṭhĕya (EI 16), a sub-division or district; same as vĕṇṭhĕ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेर्गडे<BR>Vĕrgaḍĕ (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; same as Vĕggaḍĕ, Pĕrgaḍĕ,<BR>Hĕggaḍĕ, etc.; also Sanskrit Adhyakṣa, Adhikārin (a superin-<BR>tendent or governor).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेश्य|वेश्यं<BR>veśya (CII 4), explained as ‘situated in … ’ Cf. prāveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेट<BR>vĕṭa (IE 8-4), same as vĕṇṭhĕ, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेटकिल<BR>Veṭakila (IE 8-3); HD), probably ‘the bearer of vīṭikā<BR>(betel bīḏā)’. See Vogel. Ant. Ch. St., p. 128. Cf. Vārgulika;<BR>also Paṭṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेतन|वेतनं<BR>vetana, vetanā (SITI), wages (used along with veṭṭi, i. e.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-370" target="_blank">Page-370+ 40</a>]<BR>Sanskrit viṣṭi or unpaid labour); probably wages for the<BR>labourers in the public works of the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेठ<BR>vĕṭha (IE 8-4), Kannaḍa; same as vĕṇṭhĕ, vĕṭa, etc.; a<BR>small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेत्रिक<BR>Vetrika (EI 9; CII 4), explained by some as ‘the chamber-<BR>lain’; cf. Yāṣṭika, Piśuna-vetrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वि|विः<BR>vi (CITD), abbreviation of Telugu vinnapamulu, represen-<BR>tation or saying. It may stand for visālu (visā or vīsa) also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभाग|विभागः<BR>vibhāga (HRS), king's share of the output of mines; as<BR>suggested by the Arthaśāstra, rent from mines and from the<BR>private manufacturers of salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभव|विभवः<BR>vibhava (IA 14), used in the sense of nirvāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभेद|विभेदः<BR>vibheda (IE 8-4), subdivision of a khaṇḍa of Bhārata or<BR>Bhārata-varsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभोग<BR>vibhoga (EI 16), holy ashes; same as vibhūti (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभूति|विभूतिः<BR>vibhūti (IA 12), holy ashes; same as vibhoga.<BR>(SITI), also called vibhūti-kāṇikkai in Tamil inscriptions;<BR>originally, voluntary contribution to a temple by the devotees<BR>while receiving the sacred ashes; later, it was collected as a<BR>tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विचारकर्तृ|विचारकर्त्तृ<BR>Vicārakartṛ, (EI 8), a supervisor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विचित्रकवित्व<BR>vicitra-kavitva (CITD), probably, a class of poetry like<BR>citra-kavitva, abounding in all kinds of highly artificial verses<BR>displaying the pedantry and verbal jugglery of the composer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडालपदक|विडालपदकं<BR>viḍālapadaka, same as vivarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विध|विधः<BR>vidha (SITI), variety, kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विधारणा<BR>vidhāraṇā (EI 1), same as paripanthanā, ‘creating obs-<BR>tacles’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विधिपत्र<BR>vidhi-patra (LP), a judgement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विधु|विधुः<BR>vidhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडूरसार<BR>viḍūra-sāra (EI 3), same as vaiḍūrya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्वज्जन<BR>vidvaj-jana (SITI), a body of learned men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्या<BR>vidyā (CII 4), the right knowledge.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याभोग<BR>vidyā-bhoga (EI 18), same as vidy-ānubhoga and vidyā-dhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याचारण<BR>vidyā-cāraṇa, see cāraṇa (EI 3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याधन|विद्याधनं<BR>vidyā-dhana (HRS), explained as land assigned as a re-<BR>ward for learning; same as vidyā-bhoga and vidy-ānubhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याधरतोरण<BR>vidyādhara-toraṇa (SII 2), an ornamental arch probably<BR>depicting Vidyādharas; cf. makara-toraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याधिकारिन्<BR>Vidy-ādhikārin (EI 11, 25; HD), officer in charge of<BR>a school or of schools; the director of education. Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XI, p. 314.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्यानुभोग<BR>vidy-ānubhoga (SITI), an endowment of land to a school<BR>for the encouragement of learning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्यार्थिन्<BR>Vidyārthin (SITI), a student.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्यास्थान<BR>vidyā-sthāna (EI 2; SII 2; SITI), an educational insti-<BR>tution for higher studies; a college.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहद्रम्मविसोवक<BR>vigrahadramma-visovaka (EI 1), name of a coin; the latter<BR>part of the name (i. e. visovaka = viṃśopaka) suggests that it was<BR>one-twentieth of the vigraha-dramma in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालद्रम्म<BR>vigrahapāla-dramma (EI 1), name of a coin; same as<BR>vigrahapāla-satka-dramma, vigrahapālīya-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालसत्कद्रम्म<BR>vigrahapāla-satka-dramma (EI 1), see vigrahapālīya-dramma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालीयद्रम्म<BR>vigrahapālīya-dramma (EI 1; CII 4), name of a coin<BR>apparently so called after a king named Vigrahapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहतुङ्गीयद्रम्म<BR>vigrahatuṅgīya-dramma (EI 1; CII 4), name of a coin<BR>apparently so called after a king named Vigrahatuṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहार|विहारः<BR>vihāra (EI 22, 25; CII 3, 4; BL), a Buddhist or Jain<BR>monastery or temple or convent (EI 35).<BR>(HA), wandering of a Jain monk; also a Jain<BR>temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारकारक<BR>Vihārakāraka, cf. Prakrit Viharakarahvaa (CII 2-1), ‘one<BR>who builds a monastery’; same as Vihārasvāmin; explained by<BR>some as ‘the superintendent of monastery’ (ML).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहरमाणजिन<BR>Viharamāṇa-Jina (HA), a Jina at present living in other<BR>kṣetras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारपाल<BR>Vihārapāla, ‘the manager of a monastery’ (Select Inscrip-<BR>tions, p. 345).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारस्वामिन्<BR>Vihārasvāmin (EI 8, 33; CII 3; BL; LL), ‘the master of a<BR>monastery’; the builder or owner of a monastery. Cf. Vihāra-<BR>kāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारस्वामिनी<BR>Vihārasvāminī (CII 3; IA 11), the feminine form of<BR>Vihārasvāmin; wife of a Vihārasvāmin or the female owner<BR>of a vihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारयात्रा<BR>vihāra-yātrā (CII 1), a pleasure-tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारिका<BR>vihārikā (EI 23, 27), derived from vihāra, vihāraka; a<BR>small vihāra or monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहिंसा<BR>vihiṃsā (CII 1), hurting, injuring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहित|विहितः<BR>vihita (CII 1), established; settled.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहृतयति<BR>vihṛtayati, ‘[he] wastes’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 245).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजालयितव्य<BR>vijālayitavya, to be untied (Select Inscriptions, p. 238).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजाटिन्<BR>Vijāṭin (IA 11), cf. Vijāṭi-vidyādhara, ‘a Vidyādhara unwind-<BR>ing his head-dress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजय|विजयः<BR>vijaya, used in Kannaḍa inscriptions in the sense of<BR>‘going in state, going in a triumpal procession, making a state<BR>procession, making a state progress through one's dominions’<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 223, note 6; Vol. VI, p. 51, note 5).<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 18), Oḏiyā, etc.; used in<BR>Oḏiyā inscriptions in the sense of ‘stay’.<BR>(IA 7), cf. vijaya-rājya-saṃvalsara, vijaya-saṃvatsara,<BR>vijaya-kaṭaka, vijaya-skandhāvāra, etc. Cf. śrī-vijaya and<BR>śrī-vijaya-śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजया<BR>vijayā (IA 26), same as su-di 11 or the eleventh tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयाभिषेक<BR>vijay-ābhiṣeka (SITI), being crowned as a victor; same as<BR>vīr-ābhiṣeka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयचन्द्र<BR>vijaya-candra (SII 2), name of an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयादशमी<BR>vijayā-daśamī (EI 31), Āśvina-sudi 10.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयक<BR>vijayaka (LP), same as vijaya, victory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयकटक<BR>vijaya-kaṭaka (EI 2; LP), ‘the victorious camp’; the royal<BR>camp or capital.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयलेख<BR>vijaya-lekha (EI 9), a royal record.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयराजटङ्क<BR>vijayarāja-ṭaṅka (CII 4), name of a coin apparently<BR>so called after a ruler named Vijayarāja who was its issuer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयसप्तमी<BR>vijaya-saptamī (EI 3), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयशासन<BR>vijaya-śāsana (EI 33), any royal record (cf. śāsana);<BR>sometimes the same as dharma-vijaya-śāsana (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयशिव<BR>vijaya-śiva, cf. śrī-vijaya-śiva-Mṛgeśavarman, etc. (The<BR>Successors of the Sātavāhanas, pp. 261 ff.); an honorific prefixed<BR>to royal names. See śrī, vijaya, śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयस्तम्भ<BR>vijaya-stambha (SITI), pillar of victory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयवैजयिक<BR>vijaya-vaijayika, victory; sometimes used as an adjective<BR>qualifying the regnal date (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 152, text<BR>line 5; cf. ibid., Vol. XXXII, p. 88).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयवन्दापना<BR>vijaya-vandāpanā (IE 8-5; EI 12), Oḏiyā; a levy; pre-<BR>sents to be offered to the king or landlord on the occasion of<BR>his victorious return from a campaign or for the preparation of<BR>a campaign; cf. vandāpanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयविक्षेप<BR>vijaya-vikṣepa (IA 13), epithet of a place where a king<BR>was staying. See vikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजित|विजितः<BR>vijita (CII 1), dominions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञानिन्<BR>Vijñānin (EI 20, 32), an artisan; same as Śilpin; epithet of<BR>an artisan who is usually the engraver of an inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञापना<BR>vijñāpanā (IA 10), also called vijñapti; an application; a<BR>request; cf. Kannaḍa binna-vattaḷĕ = Sanskrit vijñāpana-patra<BR>(SII 11-1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञप्ति|विज्ञप्तिः<BR>Vijñapti (EI 29), official designation. Cf. Ājñapti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञप्ति|विज्ञप्तिः<BR>vijñapti (SITI), sometimes also spelt vijñāpti; peti-<BR>tioning to the king (cf. vijñāpanā); an officer who brings the<BR>petition of the subjects to the king's notice.<BR>(EI 23; SII 2), also called vijñāpya, an application or<BR>petition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञापि<BR>vi-jñāpi (CII 3, etc.), verb used in connection with the<BR>making of a grant by the king at the request, or on the advice,<BR>of someone who was the real donor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञाप्य|विज्ञाप्यं<BR>vijñāpya (EI 23), cf. Tamil viṇṇappam (SII 1), a peti-<BR>tion; also called vijñapti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विकर|विकरः<BR>vikara, cf. vikara-padāni (LP), a small present, a bonus;<BR>cf. Gujarātī pān-sopārī.<BR>(LP), cf. vikara-pada explained as ‘miscellancous expenses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विकरणपट्टक<BR>vikaraṇa-paṭṭaka (LP), a merket-tax contract.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विक्रमादित्य|विक्रमादित्यः<BR>Vikramāditya (IE 8-2), see āditya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विकृति|विकृतिः<BR>vikṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विक्षेप|विक्षेपः<BR>vikṣepa (IA 7, 13), cf. vijaya-vikṣepa used as an epithet of the<BR>place whence a royal charter was issued; cf. vijaya-vikṣepāt Bha-<BR>rukaccha-vāsakāt; wrongly interpreted as ‘a camp or cantonment’<BR>(IA 17). See also Vaikṣepika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलब्धि<BR>vilabdhi (IE 8-3; EI 30), used in the Rājataraṅgiṇī,<BR>probably in the sense of presents offered to the king or the stolen<BR>property recovered; explained as ‘an assignment’. See<BR>Vailabdhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलहणा<BR>vilahaṇā (LP), probably, an escort; suite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलासिनी<BR>Vilāsinī (EI 33), same as Devadāsī; also called Gaṇikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलेखक<BR>Vilekhaka (EI 22), an engraver. Cf. Ullekhaka, utkṛ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलोक्<BR>vi-lok, cf. vilokyante (LP), ‘are being searched for’, used<BR>in respect of one who is in search of money in times of difficulty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विमान|विमानं|विमानः<BR>vimāna (SITI), the pinnacle or upper structure over the<BR>sanctum of a temple; the central shrine of a temple (SII 3);<BR>also called śrī-vimāna (SII 13); same as garbha-gṛha.<BR>(EI 3, 23), a shrine.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-374" target="_blank">Page-374+ 40</a>]<BR>(IA 9), the steeple tower over a shrine; also called stupī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशतिक|विंशतिकः<BR>viṃśatika, regarded as equal to 20 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI,<BR>p. 52); cf. viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंसतिम<BR>viṃsatima (CII 3), used for viṃśatitama, twentieth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंसोपक<BR>viṃsopaka (EI 1), corrupt form of viṃśopaka, a copper coin<BR>which was (1/20) of the standard silver coin in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशोपक<BR>viṃśopaka (IE 8-6, 8-8; EI 29, 30; CII 4), a copper coin<BR>which was one-twentieth of the standard silver coin in value; cf.<BR>Viśālapriya-viṃśopaka (IE 8-8); Varāhakīya-viṃśopaka (EI 1); Vṛṣa-<BR>viṃśopaka (q. v.); a land measure equal to one twentieth of the<BR>standard land measure. See vīsa, viṃsopaka, vīsovā, visovaka.<BR>Cf. viśopaka (LP), supposed to be the same as vighā, a<BR>measure of land equal to 20 vasas [in Gujarat].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीणा<BR>vīṇā (ASLV), a musical instrument. Cf. vīṇai-kkāṇi (SITI),<BR>right of playing on the vīṇā before the god in a temple during<BR>worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनमु<BR>vinamu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown weight greater<BR>than a cinna or cinnamu, otherwise called sinna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनाश|विनाशः<BR>vināśa (LP), ‘not doing anything at all’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनाशिन्<BR>vināśin, cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-vāsa (IE 8-5), an<BR>attendant, or fuel. The villagers were obliged to supply it to the<BR>touring officers of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनष्टराज्य<BR>vinaṣṭa-rājya (IE), same as gata-rājya or atīta-rājya, someone's<BR>sovereignty that was a thing of the past.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनय|विनयः<BR>vinaya (IE 8-8; EI 30), fines.<BR>(EI 13), same as indriya-jaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनयधर<BR>Vinayadhara (LL), Buddhist; one who has learnt the<BR>Vinaya texts by heart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनायक|विनायकः<BR>Vināyaka (LL), a teacher of the vinaya texts; a name of<BR>the god Gaṇeśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनायकहोम<BR>Vināyaka-homa (EI 26), a rite; same as Gaṇeśa-homa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विन्दु|विंदु|विन्दुः<BR>vindu (EI 7-1-2), also spelt bindu; ‘cypher’.<BR>(SII 2), a flaw in diamonds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनिबद्धकार<BR>Vinibaddhakāra, see Vinibandhakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनिबन्धकार<BR>Vinibandhakāra (EI 8), same as Vinibaddhakāra; explained<BR>as ‘one who registers [a document]’; really, ‘one who cancels<BR>the registration [of a document]’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनिर्गत<BR>vinirgata (EI 7), cf. Pāṭaliputra-bhaṭṭāgrahāra-vinirgata<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 122, text line 16); ‘hailing from’,<BR>or more suitably ‘one whose family hails from’. When a<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-375" target="_blank">Page-375+ 39</a>]<BR>locality called Aṭṭamūla is described as vinirgata from Bṛhad-<BR>dhaṭṭa, it seems to mean that the former was originally a part<BR>of the latter (ibid., Vol. XXXIII, p. 151).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनियोग|विनियोगः<BR>viniyoga (SITI), an employment; use; expenditure.<BR>(EI 24), a tax; cf. Tamil vāśal-viniyogam (SITI), same<BR>as vāśal-paṇam; also sabhā-viniyoga (SII 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनियुक्त<BR>Viniyukta (HD), an officer probably under the Āyuktaka;<BR>same as Viniyuktaka (q. v.), etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV,<BR>p. 256.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनियुक्तक<BR>Viniyuktaka (CII 3, 4), an official title meaning a smaller<BR>administrative officer serving under a higher officer; an official<BR>probably under the Āyuktaka; same as Viniyukta. Cf. Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XI, pp. 80, 83.<BR>(IE 8-3), mentioned along with Tadāyuktaka. Cf. Tad-<BR>viniyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विप्रविनोदिन्<BR>Vipra-vinodin (SITI), a class of Brāhmaṇas who were<BR>adepts in jugglery and magical practices.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीर|वीरं|वीरः<BR>vīra (IE 8-2), sometimes prefixed to the names of kings<BR>and even treated as almost an integral part of the name; cf.<BR>pratāpa, vīra-pratāpa, etc.<BR>(EI 3), Jain; same as Mahāvīra.<BR>Cf. vīra-kaḻ (SITI), also written vīra-kkaḻ, vīra-gaḻ; a hero-<BR>stone; an inscribed or uninscribed stone pillar raised in honour<BR>of a person who died in fighting for a good cause.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरभद्र|वीरभद्रः<BR>Vīrabhadra (SITI), also called Vīramuṣṭi; member of<BR>a militant class of temple servants who diligently protected<BR>the properties and rights of the temples. Cf. Vīrakośa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीराभिषेक<BR>vīr-ābhiṣeka (EI 18; SITI), ‘anointment as a hero’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरभोग<BR>vīra-bhoga (SITI), land assigned for the maintenance of<BR>a warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरगल्<BR>vīra-gaḻ (CII 4), also written vīra-kkaḻ. See vīra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरक्कल्<BR>vīra-kkaḻ (CII 4), also written vīra-gaḻ, a stone pillar raised<BR>in memory of heroes. See vīra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरकोश<BR>Vīrakośa, official designation (The Successor of the Sāta-<BR>vāhanas, p. 110, note 2); mentioned along with Hastikośa as an<BR>officer related to a district; probably, an officer in charge of<BR>the local soldiers or infantry men. Cf. Vīrabhadra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरक्त|विरक्तः<BR>Virakta (SITI), an ascetic; a man free from worldly<BR>attachment; a recluse of the Śaiva order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरलरिशि<BR>viral-ariśi (ASLV), rice provided for goldsmiths for am-<BR>putating the last two fingers of the wives of farmers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरमाला<BR>vīra-mālā, cf. vīra-mālai (SITI), a poem in praise of a<BR>warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरमुष्टि<BR>Vīramuṣṭi (SITI), same as Vīrabhadra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरपट्ट|वीरपट्टः<BR>vīra-paṭṭa (SII 2; SITI), an ornament; a front plate, pro-<BR>bably a plate worn on the forehead by distinguished warriors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरपट्टण<BR>vīra-paṭṭaṇa (SITI), also called eṟi-vīra-paṭṭaṇam; a mer-<BR>cantile town inhabited by the eṟi-vīrar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरप्रताप<BR>Vīra-pratāpa (IE 8-2), cf. Vīra and Pratāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरशासन<BR>vīra-śāsana (SITI), CITD) explained by some as the same<BR>as vīrakaḻ, ‘a hero stone’, established for commemorating the<BR>death of soldiers on the battle-field; a grant made by the king<BR>in recognition of the heroic activity of a person; a charter<BR>recording the grant of land or other property to a warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरशेष<BR>vīra-śeṣa, cf. vīra-śeṣai (SITI); probably, the provision<BR>made for the descendants of dead warriors; sometimes explained<BR>as a tax (EI 22). Cf. mṛtyuka-vṛtti, rakta-mānya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरसिंहासन<BR>vīra-siṃhāsana (SII 1), the throne of heroes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरयात्रिक<BR>Vīra-yātrika (IA 17; HD), an official designation; probably,<BR>the leader of an expedition; a person taking part in a military<BR>expedition. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 129.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरूपाक्षपति<BR>Virūpākṣa-pati, cf. Prakrit Virūpakha-pati (EI 20), epithet<BR>of the god Mahāsena or Kārttikeya, Virūpākṣa probably being<BR>the name of a host of which the god was conceived as the leader.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीस<BR>vīsa (IE 8-8; EI 5), name of a coin (JNSI, Vol. XXVI,<BR>pp. 127ff.); cf. lokkiya-vīsa, probably meaning ‘a vīsa minted<BR>at Lokkiguṇḍi’; Sanskrit viṃśa, viṃśaka, viṃśatika, or viṃśopaka.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 232, note 6), Telugu-Kannaḍa;<BR>(1/16) of a haṇa (paṇa); but (1/20) of the standard coin in value<BR>essentially.<BR>(CITD), also called visā, visya, visāmu; Telugu-Kannaḍa;<BR>the fraction (1/10); gold equal in weight to one grain of rice;<BR>(1/256) of a Hun or Pagoda; 40 palas; a measure of land<BR>equal nearly to 2 acres.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसा<BR>visā, also spelt visāmu (CITD), see vīsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषहरभोग<BR>viṣahara-bhoga (SITI), also called viṣa-vṛtti; land set apart<BR>for the support of a poison-doctor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसलप्रियद्रम्म<BR>vīsala-priya-dramma, also called vīsala-prī-dramma; cf. jīrṇa-<BR>viśvamalla-priya, etc. (A. R. Ep., 1957-58, Nos. B 490-92).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसंस्थुल<BR>visaṃsthula (LP), agitated, unsteady.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसतिअठूप्रस्थ<BR>visatiaṭhū-prastha (IA 18), a levy; probably viṃśatisatka-<BR>prastha, ‘one out of 20 prasthas.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषवृत्ति<BR>viṣa-vṛtti (SITI), same as viṣahara-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषय|विषयः<BR>viṣaya (EI 8-4), a district; often a kingdom or terri-<BR>tory; sometimes a viṣaya was included in a maṇḍala; but, in<BR>some cases, a maṇḍala was included in a viṣaya; at times maṇḍala<BR>and viṣaya were synonymous.<BR>(IE 8-5; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; SITI), a district; cf.<BR>viṣaya-suṅka (EI 24), the tax of a district; Viṣaya-vyavahārin,<BR>officer in the service of a district.<BR>(ASLV), same as nirvṛtti or koṭṭam; an administrative<BR>division.<BR>(IE 8-4; CII 4), sometimes used in a wider sense to indi-<BR>cate ‘a country’.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसय<BR>visaya (CITD), same as Telugu visā, visāmu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयभोगिक<BR>Viṣaya-bhogika (EI 28), probably, the ināmdār or ināmdārs<BR>of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयभूभुज्<BR>Viṣaya-bhūbhuj (IA 15), explained as ‘a native ruler’ as<BR>opposed to a ‘foreign conqueror.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयदान<BR>viṣaya-dāna (HRS), name of a tax (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI,<BR>p. 21; Vol. XIV, p. 196), probably, a regional tax or<BR>taxes realisable from a particular district; known from Gāha-<BR>ḍavāla records; cf. viṣayālī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयदानिक<BR>Viṣaya-dānika (EI 7; CII 4), collector of the levy called<BR>viṣaya-dāna; or a district officer in charge of gifts or an officer in<BR>charge of gift lands in a district; or the collector of the revenue<BR>of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयाधिकरण<BR>Viṣay-ādhikaraṇa (EI 23, 31), administrative officer<BR>of a district; the district administrator's office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयाधिपति|विषयाधिपतिः<BR>Viṣay-ādhipati, same as Viṣayapati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV,<BR>p. 219).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयकरण<BR>Viṣaya-karaṇa (EI 32), probably, the chief scribe at the<BR>office of the administrators of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयाली<BR>viṣayālī (EI 33), name of a tax; probably the same as<BR>viṣaya-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयामात्य<BR>Viṣay-āmātya (EI 27, 30), governor of a district; an<BR>Amātya in charge of a viṣaya or an Amātya under the Viṣayapati.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 64.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयण<BR>viṣayaṇa (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयपाल<BR>Viṣayapāla (EI 28), same as Viṣayapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयपति|विषयपतिः<BR>Viṣayapati (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), governor of a<BR>district called viṣaya; distinguished from Viṣaya-vyāpṛtaka; same<BR>as Viṣay-ādhipati. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. V, p. 114. See Viṣa-<BR>yeśa, Viṣayeśvara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयव्यापृतक<BR>Viṣaya-vyāpṛtaka (IE 8-3), sometimes distinguished from<BR>the Viṣayapati; an officer associated with the administration<BR>of a district (cf. Viṣaya-vyavahārin).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयव्यवहारिन्<BR>Viṣaya-vyavahārin (IE 8-3), an administrative officer in<BR>a district or a member of the district council. Cf. Viṣaya-vya-<BR>vahārin, Viṣayika, Viṣayin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयेश<BR>Viṣayeśa (HD), same as Viṣayapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयेश्वर<BR>Viṣayeśvara (EI 26), same as Viṣayapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयिक<BR>Viṣayika (EI 24), same as Viṣaya-vyavahārin; cf. Viṣayin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयिकाधिकारिक<BR>Viṣayik-ādhikārika (EI 32), taken to be a single official<BR>designation; probably Viṣayika and Ādhikārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयिन्<BR>Viṣayin (EI 24, 32), possibly, the same as Viṣaya-vyava-<BR>hārin; cf. Viṣayika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसेणिम<BR>viseṇima, viseṇimā (CII 4), a tax, also called viseṇim-<BR>ādāya (EI 21).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशेषादाय<BR>viśeṣ-ādāya (SITI), also called viśeṣ-āya; a special group<BR>of taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशेषाय<BR>viśeṣ-āya (SITI), same as viśeṣ-ādāya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशिख|विशिखः<BR>viśikha (BL), name of a kind of building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशीर्ण|विशीर्णः<BR>viśīrṇa, wearing out, worn out part of a building; cf. bhagna-<BR>viśīrṇa-samāracana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशिष<BR>Viśiṣa (IE 8-3; EI 1, 30), probably, the governor or<BR>commander of a fort; a word of uncertain derivation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुबाहु<BR>viṣṇu-bāhu, see hari-bāhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुगृह|विष्णुगृहं<BR>viṣṇu-gṛha (SITI), a Viṣṇu temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुपद|विष्णुपदं<BR>viṣṇu-pada (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुतिथि|विष्णुतिथिः<BR>viṣṇu-tithi (IA 19), same as Jyaiṣṭha-sudi 11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुश्राध<BR>viṣṇu-śrādha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 37), an expres-<BR>sion of doubtful meaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसोवा<BR>vīsovā (CII 4), name of a coin; a land measure; same as<BR>viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसोवक<BR>visovaka (EI 1), corrupt form of viṃśopaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्टप|विष्टपं|विष्टपः<BR>viṣṭapa (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विस्तरण<BR>vistaraṇa (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्टि|विष्टिः<BR>viṣṭi (IE 8-5; CII 4; HRS), labour which the villa-<BR>gers were obliged to provide to the king or landlord on occa-<BR>sions; unpaid labour; forced labour.<BR>Cf. veṭṭi (SITI), unpaid labour for public works in the vil-<BR>lage without time or other limits; usually mentioned along with<BR>vetana as veṭṭi-vetanai. Cf. veṭṭi-ccoṟu, the obligation of feed-<BR>ing veṭṭi labourers free of cost; also cf. Tamil veṭṭi-pāṭṭam (EI<BR>24), explained as ‘a kind of tax’; tax in lieu of viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशुद्धि|विशुद्धिः<BR>viśuddhi, cf. viśuddhiṃ yāvat (LP), ‘till the account<BR>is clear’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषुव|विषुवं<BR>viṣuva (CII 4; SII 1), the autumnal or vernal equinox;<BR>also called viṣuvat (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषुवत्|विषुवन्त्<BR>viṣuvat (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR>Cf. viṣuva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्व|विश्वं|विश्वः<BR>viśva (IE 7-1-2), same as viśvedevāḥ, ‘thirteen.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वचक्र|विश्वचक्रं<BR>viśvacakra (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वेदेवाः<BR>viśvedevāḥ (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’; same as viśva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्वग्देवा<BR>viṣvag-devā (LL), Jain; a quadruple image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वकर्मन्|विश्वकर्म्मन्<BR>Viśvakarman (LL), an architect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वाल<BR>Viśvāla (EI 31), Oḏiyā; a village watchman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वास|विश्वासः<BR>Viśvāsa (EI 24), official designation; same as Vaiśvāsika;<BR>cf. the titles Viśvāsa-Khāna, Viśvāsa-rāya, etc., conferred by the<BR>Muslim rulers especially in the Bengal region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वासन|विश्वासनं<BR>viśvāsana (CII 1), ‘being inspired with faith’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वसत्ता<BR>viśva-sattā (IA 14), wrong Sanskritisation of Prakrit vasa-<BR>sata (Sanskrit varṣa-śata); translated as ‘universal rule’. See<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 241, note 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वासिक<BR>Viśvāsika (EI 24), same as Vaiśvāsika (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वविश्वोपक<BR>Viśvaviśvopaka (IA 19), Jain; explained as ‘one whose<BR>body and soul exhibit marks of an ācārya’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वितान|वितानं|वितानः<BR>vitāna (SII 13), probably, a canopy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वितानाधिप<BR>Vitān-ādhipa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 325, note 3),<BR>supposed to be ‘an officer in charge of the king's bed-chamber’.<BR>Cf. Vāsāgārika, Śayyāpāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विटप|विटपः<BR>viṭapa (IE 8-5), a bush; used in sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa; a branch.<BR>Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 183.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विठविगार<BR>viṭha-vigāra (Chamba), unpaid labour; from Sanskrit<BR>viṣṭi and Persian begār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीथि|वीथिः<BR>vīthi, vīthī (SII 1), a street.<BR>(EI 24, 30; CII 4), a shop; a stall or shop in a market.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-380" target="_blank">Page-380+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 21, 23, 29, 30), a territorial unit; the subdivision<BR>of a district.<BR>(IE 8-4), sometimes a subdivision forming part of a<BR>maṇḍala, but sometimes a district forming part of a bhukti or<BR>province.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीथीमहत्तर<BR>Vīthī-mahattara (HD), headman of the territorial unit<BR>called vīthī. Cf. IHQ, Vol. XIX, pp. 16, 21.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीथ्यधिकरण<BR>vīthy-adhikaraṇa (EI 31), administrative office of a sub-<BR>division called vīthī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वित्तबन्ध<BR>vitta-bandha (CII 4), mortgage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विट्टोल्लकर<BR>viṭṭolla-kara (HRS), known from Maitraka records; ex-<BR>plained as the contribution in forced labour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाह|विवाहः<BR>Vivāha (EI 12), ‘one whose vehicle is the bird’; i. e. Viṣṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाह|विवाहः<BR>vivāha (CII 1), marriage of a daughter; cf. āvāha which<BR>means the marriage of a son.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाहकर<BR>vivāha-kara, cf. Tamil kaṇṇāla-kkāṇan (EI 28), the marriage<BR>fee; cf. vivāha-ppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाहपण<BR>vivāha-paṇa, cf. vivāha-ppaṇam (SITI), same as kaṇṇāla-<BR>kkāṇam; a tax on marriage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवीत|विवीतः<BR>vivīta (HRS), royal dues collected by the superintendent<BR>of pastures, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवीताध्यक्ष|विवीताध्यक्षः<BR>Vivīt-ādhyakṣa (EI 28), known from the Arthaśāstra; officer<BR>in charge of the pasture land. Cf. Vrajabhūmika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वियत्|वियन्त्<BR>viyat (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोदा<BR>vodā (IE 8-5; EI 29), a kind of levy in Oḏiyā records;<BR>same as Oḏiyā vadāi, ‘the obligation of offering uncooked food.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोडी<BR>voḍī, voḍrī (EI 23), (1/4) paṇa; 20 cowrie-shells; cf. kapardaka-<BR>voḍī, ‘voḍī counted in cowrie-shells’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोलापन<BR>volāpana, see volāpika, vulāvi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोलापिक<BR>Volāpika (LP), an officer in charge of collecting the tax<BR>called volāpana or vulāvī. It is supposed that a Volāpaka or the<BR>men under him accompanied the merchants in their journey<BR>for the safety of their goods and the volāpana tax was collected<BR>from the merchants for safeguarding their goods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोट<BR>voṭa, cf. boṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रज|व्रजं|व्रजः<BR>vraja, see Vraja-bhūmika. Cf. Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 110.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रजभूमि<BR>vraja-bhūmi (IE 8-4), grazing land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रजभूमिक<BR>Vrajabhūmika (CII 1; EI 2; HD), Prakrit Vacabhūmika;<BR>superintendent of cowpens; officer in charge of the royal cattle<BR>and pasture lands. Cf. Vivīt-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रत|व्रतं|व्रतः<BR>vrata (CITD), religious vow; a self-imposed task; a<BR>religious act of devotion or austerity; vowed observance; a vow in<BR>general. There are many vratas mentioned in the different Purāṇas.<BR>But new vratas crop up in different parts of the country.<BR>(EI 4), five in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रीहिकर<BR>vrīhi-kara, cf. Tamil arisi-kkāṇam (SITI), a levy for<BR>husking paddy into rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्ध|वृद्धं|वृद्धः<BR>vṛddha (LP), participle of vṛdh, ‘to cut’.<BR>Cf. Vṛddha-Gaṇeśa (IA 19), ‘the senior Gaṇeśa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धधानुष्क<BR>Vṛddha-dhānuṣka (IE 8-3), senior archer; the chief archer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धराज|वृद्धराजः<BR>Vṛddharāja (EI 3; LL), ‘prosperous king’; title of a pious<BR>king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धि|वृद्धिः<BR>vṛddhi (EI 28), a super tax or the interest on arrears of<BR>taxes; also interest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धिकुक्कुट<BR>vṛddhi-kukkuṭa (CII 1), Prakrit vadhi-kukuṭa; a cock that<BR>has been caponed; also Sanskritised as vadhri-kukkuṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृषतापशासन<BR>vṛṣatāpa-śāsana (EI 13), same as tāmra-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृषविंशोपक<BR>vṛṣa-viṃśopaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 39), name of a<BR>coin (probably bearing the figure of a bull); cf. viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृत्ति|वृत्तिः<BR>vṛtti (SITI), means; livelihood, occupation; grant of<BR>land for one's livelihood.<BR>(SII 3), land granted for service.<BR>(EI 17, 31; CITD), share; share in a village granted to a<BR>Brāhmaṇa as a free gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुढालेङ्का<BR>Vuḏhā-leṅkā (EI 28), Oḏiyā; official designation; cf. Leṅkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुलापिका<BR>vulāpikā (LP), tax for the maintenance of the camp-<BR>followers; cf. Gujarātī vaḻāmaṇ vulāyiyā; also volāpika, vulā-<BR>viyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुलावी<BR>vulāvī (LP), same as volāpana; a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुलाविया<BR>Vulāviyā (LP), a camp-follower; cf. Gujarātī Vuḻāviyā.<BR>See vulāpikā and Volāpika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुंवक<BR>vuṃvaka (EI 14), name of a measure.<BR>Cf. ‘rūpakas to be levied on each vuṃvaka of the distillers’<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्य|व्यः<BR>Vya (PJS), abbreviation of Vyavahārin, especially in<BR>medieval Jain inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्या<BR>Vyā (PJS), abbreviation of Vyāpārin (merchant) or Vyāsa<BR>(exponent or reciter of epic and Puranic texts) especially in<BR>medieval Jain inscriptions. Cf. vyā-bhū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याभू<BR>vyā-bhū (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vyāmiśra-bhūmi; ‘mixed<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-382" target="_blank">Page-382+ 40</a>]<BR>land’; land containing different categories such as cultivable,<BR>fallow, homestead, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याचरण<BR>vyācaraṇa (EI 15), meaning uncertain; probably, com-<BR>merce.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याघ्रचर्मन्|व्याघ्रचर्म्मन्<BR>vyāghra-carman (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28), tiger's skin [which<BR>was the king's monopoly]; tax probably payable by hunters<BR>in tiger's skin; refers to the right to keep tiger's skins without<BR>surrendering them to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याज|व्याजः<BR>vyāja, vyājaka (LP), interest; cf. dvika-śata-vyājena, ‘at<BR>2 per cent interest’. See vyājī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याजी<BR>vyājī (HRS), as suggested by the Arthaśāstra, (1) com-<BR>pensation fee levied upon the sale of liquors, royal merchan-<BR>dise, mining products, salt and sugar; (2) charge paid for<BR>minting coins; (3) subsidiary charge over and above the regular<BR>fines. See vyāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याकरणदानमण्डप<BR>vyākaraṇa-dāna-maṇḍapa (SITI), hall in the Śiva temple<BR>at Tiruvoṟṟiyūr, where Sanskrit grammar is taught with<BR>the belief that the Māheśvara-sūtras, on which Sanskrit grammar<BR>is founded, were composed by the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याख्यावृत्ति<BR>vyākhyā-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart to meet the expenses<BR>of expounding the Purāṇas and other śāstras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यक्त|व्यक्तः<BR>vyakta (CII 1), experienced.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यामिश्रभूमि<BR>vyāmiśra-bhūmi (IE 8-1), an area consisting of different<BR>kinds of land such as cultivated land, homestead land, fallow<BR>land, etc. See vyā-bhū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यञ्जन|व्यंजन|व्यंजनं|व्यञ्जनं<BR>vyañjana, cf. vĕñjanam, viñjanam (SITI), condiment;<BR>vegetable relish; condiments and curry in food offerings; cf.<BR>vĕñjana-bhaṇḍāram.<BR>(CII 1), a letter or an implication.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापादित|व्यापादितः<BR>vyāpādita (LP), ‘much harassed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापार|व्यापारः<BR>vyāpāra (SII 1), a trade.<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 20), administration. Cf.<BR>mudrā-vyāpāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापारकरण<BR>vyāpāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), the department of com-<BR>merce.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापारिन्<BR>Vyāpārin (EI 22; SII 1), a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापृत|व्यापृतः<BR>Vyāpṛta (IE 8-3; EI 6), cf. Vāpata (EI 9), a governor; a<BR>superintendent; cf. also official designations like Hasty-aśva-<BR>naubala-vyāpṛta or °vyāpṛtaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यास|व्यासः<BR>Vyāsa (EI 11; PJS), a reciter or exponent; a Brāhmaṇa<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-383" target="_blank">Page-383+ 40</a>]<BR>who recites or expounds the epics and Purāṇas in public. Cf.<BR>Paurāṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यसन|व्यसनं<BR>vyasana (CII 1), misfortune.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याषेध<BR>vyāṣedha (LP), vyāṣedhaḥ kāritaḥ or niṣedhaḥ kāritaḥ, ‘prov-<BR>ed the contrary [in the court that it was his own land and not<BR>ḍohalikā land’]; vahamāna-bhūmi-vyāṣedha, ‘no one should stop him<BR>when he is ploughing his own piece of land’.<BR>(LP), seizure; confiscation as government property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यतिकर|व्यतिकरः<BR>vyatikara (LP), ‘in connection with’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यतीपात|व्यतीपातः<BR>vyatīpāta (IA 19), used in relation to eclipses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यव<BR>Vyava (LP), abbreviation of Vyavahārika in the sense of a<BR>dealer, a money-lender, a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवच्छिन्न|व्यवच्छिन्नं|व्यवछिन्न<BR>vyavacchinna, fixed (Select Inscriptions, p. 237); demarcated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहार|व्यवहारः<BR>vyavahāra, cf. vyavahāra-pade (LP), ‘as a tax from mer-<BR>chants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहाराभिलेखितक<BR>Vyavahār-ābhilekhitaka (EI 30), the clerk who writes down<BR>the statements of cases in a court of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहरमाण<BR>vyavaharamāṇa (LP), current.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहरण<BR>vyavaharaṇa (EI 11), administration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारपत्र<BR>vyavahāra-patra (LP), a deed relating to a loan or debt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारसमता<BR>vyavahāra-samatā (CII 1), impartiality in judicial proceed-<BR>ings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारिक|व्यवहारिकः<BR>Vyavahārika (EI 7, 32), an administrator; same as Vyava-<BR>hārin (q. v.) or Vyavahartṛ; see also Vyava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारिन्<BR>Vyavahārin (EI 19, 24, 28, 29; BL; LL; HD), an ad-<BR>ministrator; sometimes explained as ‘a controlling officer’;<BR>same as Vyavahārika. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 60, 63.<BR>(LL), a merchant. See also Vyava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवस्था<BR>vyavasthā, cf. vyavasthai (EI 24; SITI), regulations;<BR>rules of proper conduct; a settlement or arrangement; a deed<BR>of agreement.<BR>(EI 22; SII 2), a resolution; a declaration.<BR>(EI 32), an agreement.<BR>(SII 3), conditions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यय|व्ययं|व्ययः<BR>vyaya (HRS), government expenditure; cf. Tamil viyā-<BR>yam (SITI), expenditure, as opposed to āyam or income.<BR>(IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्ययकरण|व्ययकरणः<BR>vyaya-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), the department of expen-<BR>diture.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्योमन्<BR>vyoman (IE 7-1-2; EI 33), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यूह|व्यूहः<BR>vyūha (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्युषित<BR>Vyuṣita (Prakrit Vivutha), sometimes taken to be Vyuṣṭa<BR>(CII 1); ‘one who is away from his residence’. See IHQ, 1962,<BR>pp. 222 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

याग|यागः<BR>yāga (EI 31), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यक्ष|यक्षः<BR>Yakṣa (CII 4; HA), a semi-divine being; a demi-god<BR>belonging to the class of vyantara-devatās according to Jain<BR>mythology.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यज्ञविद्या<BR>yajña-vidyā (EI 8), knowledge regarding the perfor-<BR>mance of sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यदा<BR>yadā tad=āpi (LP), ‘only’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यादवचक्रवर्तिन्<BR>Yādava-cakravartin (IE 8-2), title assumed by kings of the<BR>Yādava dynasty; see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यागमण्डप<BR>yāga-maṇḍapa (SITI), sacrificial hall in a temple; same<BR>as yāga-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यागशाला<BR>yāga-śālā (SITI), same as yāga-maṇḍapa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यक्षद्वार<BR>yakṣa-dvāra, gateway adorned with Yakṣa figures (Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यम|यमः<BR>yama (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

याम|यामः<BR>yāma (EI 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमल|यमलं<BR>yamala (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलपत्र|यमलपत्रः<BR>yamala-patra (LP), treaty of alliance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलिकामलि<BR>yamalikāmali (EI 24), a tax probably on a pair of prize<BR>bullocks (yamala-kambalin; cf. varabalīvarda); also spelt<BR>yamalikambali, yamalikāmbali. See valadī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलिकम्बलि<BR>yamalikambali (IE 8-5), name of a tax; also spelt yama-<BR>likāmbali, yamalikāmali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलिकाम्बलि<BR>yamalikāmbali (HRS), a tax known from the Gāhaḍavāla<BR>records; also spelt yamalikamabali, yamalikāmali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यानक|यानकं<BR>yānaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253, note 4), probably a<BR>cart-road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यानिका<BR>yānikā, same as yānaka, probably, a cart road (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. IV. p. 253, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यन्त्र|यंत्र|यंत्रं|यन्त्रं<BR>yantra (SITI), a mechanical contrivance, as for diverting<BR>water.<BR>(HA), a mystic diagram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यन्त्रकुटी<BR>yantra-kuṭī (IE 8-8; EI 30), an oil mill or manufactory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यशस्<BR>yaśas (CII 1), glory in this life; cf. yaśo vā kīrtir = vā. See<BR>kīrti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यष्टि|यष्टिः<BR>yaṣṭi (EI 33; CII 4; ML), a memorial pillar; a relic<BR>pillar raised in memory of the dead.<BR>Cf. jaṣṭi (EI 19), a land measure.<BR>Cf. laṣṭi (EI 16), a memorial pillar.<BR>Cf. śilā-yaṣṭi (LL), a stone pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

याष्टिक<BR>Yāṣṭika (HD), staff bearer; an attendant on the king. See<BR>Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI 203; Pāṇini, IV. 4. 59. See Vetrika, Piśuna-<BR>vetrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यष्टिप्रातिष्ठानक<BR>Yaṣṭi-prātiṣṭhānaka (ML), the erection of a pillar; same<BR>as Sanskrit yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथाकालभाविन्<BR>yathākāla-bhāvin (IE 8-3), same as vartamāna-bhaviṣyat,<BR>yathāsambadhyamānaka; also written as yathā-kāl-ādhyāsin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथाकालाध्यासिन्<BR>yathākāl-ādhyāsin (EI 4, 23), ‘one who may be employed<BR>[in the area including the gift land] from time to time’; one<BR>who may be associated with the area about the gift land in differ-<BR>ent periods of time; same as yathākāla-bhāvin, vartamāna-bhaviṣyat,<BR>yathā-sambadhyamānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथासम्बध्यमानक<BR>yathā-sambadhyamānaka (IA 9), same as yathākāla-bhāvin,<BR>vartamāna-bhaviṣyat, yathākāl-ādhyāsin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यठि<BR>yaṭhi (CII 4), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit yaṣṭi (q. v.); a<BR>memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यति|यतिः<BR>Yati (BL), a monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यात्रा<BR>yātrā (EI 11; CII 4), festival; the festival of a deity; same<BR>as yātr-otsava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यात्रादान<BR>yātrā-dāna (EI 27), gift or levy for running a festival.<BR>(SITI), propitiatory gift made before starting on an<BR>expedition of conquest by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यात्रोत्सव|यात्रोत्सवः<BR>yātr-otsava (IE 8-5; EI 3, 9), same as yātrā (q. v.); the<BR>festival of a deity; festival in honour of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यौत<BR>yauta (CII 1), a respite; cf. yautaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यव|यवः<BR>yava, one-fifteenth of a māṣa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 45);<BR>equal to 2 dhānyamāṣas (ibid., p. 48); (1/3) of a rati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यावदेकपात्र<BR>Yāvadeka-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 122, text lines<BR>4-5), official designation. See Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यवन|यवनः<BR>Yavana (EI 26; CII 1), originally, an Ionian Greek; then,<BR>people of Greek nationality; ultimately, any foreigner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यवुग<BR>Yavuga (EI 14), royal title of foreign origin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योग|योगः<BR>yoga (CII 4), meditation; a philosophical system.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-386" target="_blank">Page-386+ 40</a>]<BR>(EI 18), a council or corporation.<BR>(CII 3; IA 17), addition of the longitudes of the sun and<BR>moon; an astrological element.<BR>Cf. yogaṃ yuñjantām, ‘let them obtain the association [of<BR>the gods]’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 208. Cf. yuj.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगक्षेम|योगक्षेमं|योगक्षेमः<BR>yoga-kṣema (IA 7; LP), death; cf. jāta-yoga-kṣema, dead.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगपट्ट|योगपट्टं<BR>yoga-paṭṭa (EI 14), band used by the ascetics to keep their<BR>limbs in a position of rigidity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगपट्टक<BR>yoga-paṭṭaka, cf. joga-vaṭṭigĕ (IA 14), explained as ‘a<BR>garment worn during contemplation’; same as yoga-paṭṭa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगपीठ|योगपीठं<BR>yoga-pīṭha (IA 10), a holy place where an ascetic obtained<BR>perfection (siddhi) by his austerities; also called siddha-pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगिन्<BR>yogin, cf. yogīndra (SII 1) a [Jain] ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योजन|योजनं<BR>yojana (CII 1, 4), name of a measure of distance; a dis-<BR>tance of about nine miles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योनिपट्ट<BR>yoni-paṭṭa, same as gaurī-paṭṭa; see pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युद्धित<BR>yuddhita, ‘onewho died fighting’ (Ep. Ind., XXXI, p. 324).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युध्य<BR>yudhya (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग|युगं|युगः<BR>yuga (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; rarely, 2 or 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग|युगं|युगः<BR>yuga, yugā (EI 1), meaning doubtful; cf. yugā in the sense<BR>of ‘a voucher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगा<BR>yugā (CII 4), a voucher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगादि<BR>yug-ādi (CII 4; IA 18), name applied to certain tithis; day<BR>of the commencement of a yuga; e. g. Vaiśākha-sudi 3, regarded<BR>as the commencement of the Kṛta-yuga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगादितिथि<BR>yugādi-tithi (EI 13), see yug-ādi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगादिपर्वन्<BR>Yugādi-parvan (EI 14), name of an auspicious time; same<BR>as yugādi-tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगल|युगलं<BR>yugala (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगन्धरी<BR>yugandharī (EI 11), same as javār (jawār), millet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग्म|युग्मं<BR>yugma (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग्यचर्य<BR>Yugyacarya (CII 1), a charioteer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युज्<BR>yuj (CII 1), cf. vṛddhir=yujyatām, ‘should devote them-<BR>selves for an increase’; śāśvataṃ samayam=[etad]=yuñjyuḥ, ‘they<BR>may strive for this at all times’. Cf. yoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युक्त|युक्तं|युक्तः<BR>Yukta (EI 8-3; HD), an officer in general; also an offi-<BR>cial designation (CII, Vol. 1, p. 4); the word used in Rock<BR>Edict III of Aśoka is explained by some scholars as the designa-<BR>tion of a class of officers, although there also the word may be<BR>understood in the sense of ‘an officer’; but it is an official desig-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-387" target="_blank">Page-387+ 22</a>]<BR>nation in passages like yukta-niyukta-vāsāvak-ādhikārika (Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXI, p. 144) where it may be the same as Āyuktaka.<BR>Cf. Yuktaka, Āyukta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युक्तक<BR>Yuktaka (IE 8-3; HD), same as Yukta, Āyukta or Āyuktaka.<BR>See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, pp. 26, 39-40.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यूप|यूपः<BR>yūpa (EI 2, 24, 33), sacrificial pillar; it was sometimes<BR>made of stone and inscribed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यूथी<BR>yūthī, also spelt yūtī (IA 17), generally written as yūti<BR>or pūti; cf. tṛṇa-yūti (or pūti) -gocara-paryanta, ‘as far as grass<BR>land and pasture land’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यूति|यूतिः<BR>yūti, cf. sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-yūti-gocara-paryanta (IE 8-5); also<BR>written as pūti; a word of uncertain import; probably, ‘[land]<BR>reserved [for growing grass, etc.]’ Cf. go-yūti, tṛṇa-yūti, kāṣṭha<BR>-yūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युवमहाराज<BR>Yuvamahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 3, 20, 24), modification of<BR>Yuvarāja; designation of the heir-apparent or crown-prince;<BR>same as Mahāyuvarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युवराज|युवराजः<BR>Yuvarāja (IE 8-2, CII 3, 4; HD; ASLV), designation of<BR>the heir-apparent or crown-prince. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12 (men-<BR>tioned among the 18 tīrthas); cf. CII, Vol. II, Part i, p. 40.<BR>Cf. Tamil Tuvarāśaṉ (EI 4), also Duvarāja.<BR>Cf. Mahāyuvarāja (EI 32), same as Yuvamahārāja (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभटच्छात्रप्रावेश्य<BR>a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya (EI 26, 27; CII 3), same as a-cāṭa-<BR>bhaṭa-prāveśya, Chātra (literally, ‘the umbrella-bearer’) being used<BR>for Cāṭa probably meaning ‘the leader of a group of Bhaṭas (i. e.<BR>Pāiks or Piādas)’; same as a-prāveśya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभटप्रावेश्य<BR>a-bhaṭa-prāveśya, same as a-prāveśya, etc. Cf. Prakrit a-bhaḍa-<BR>papesa (Select Inscriptions, p. 435).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभृतप्रवेश्य<BR>a-bhṛta-praveśya (EI 24), same as a-bhaṭa-prāveśya; cf. a-<BR>prāveśya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धि<BR>abhyantara-siddhi (EI 22), same as abhyantara-siddhyā, abhyan-<BR>tara-siddhika; refers to internal revenue income or taxes to be<BR>paid to local authorities; cf. sa-bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धिक<BR>abhyantara-siddhika, (EI 20) same as abhyantara-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धिसहित<BR>abhyantara-siddhi-sahita (EI 27), same as abhyantara-siddhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्ध्या<BR>abhyantara-siddhyā, ‘together with the internal income or<BR>taxes to be paid to the local authorities’; cf. abhyantara-siddhika<BR>and sa-bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 398.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रादित्यकालीय<BR>ā-candr-āditya-kālīya (IE), ‘to be enjoyed as long as the moon<BR>and sun endure’ (i. e. permanently); epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्कक्षितिसमकालम्<BR>ā-candr-ārka-kṣiti-sama-kālam, ‘as long as the moon, the sun<BR>and the earth exist’ (i. e. permanently).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्क<BR>ā-candr-ārka (IE; SITI), ‘in perpetuity.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्कार्णवक्षितिस्थितिसमकालीन<BR>ā-candr-ārk-ārṇava-kṣiti-sthiti-sama-kālīna (EI), ‘to last as<BR>long as the moon, the sun, the seas and the earth endure’<BR>(i. e. permanently); cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 134.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्कार्णवक्षितिसरित्पर्वतसमकालीन<BR>ā-candr-ārk-ārṇava-kṣiti-sarit-parvata-sama-kālīna, ‘to be en-<BR>joyed as long as the moon, the sun, the seas, the earth, the rivers<BR>and hills exist (i. e. permanently)’; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII,<BR>p. 134.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रतारकम्<BR>ā-candra-tārakam, ‘as long as the moon and stars endure’<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 149, text line 12), i. e. permanently.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचारासनचर्माङ्गार<BR>a-cār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE; EI 27), refers to the freedom of<BR>the gift village from the obligation to supply conveyance, accom-<BR>modation, hide (i. e. hide-seats) and charcoal free of charges<BR>to the touring officers on their visit. The word cāra meaning<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-389" target="_blank">Page-389+ 40</a>]<BR>‘passage or conveyance’ is sometimes substituted by pāra meaning<BR>‘ferrying’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचारसिद्धिक<BR>a-cāra-siddhika (EI 26), explained by some as ‘without<BR>grazing right for the royal cattle’. Cf. a-vāra-siddhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचर्माङ्गारक<BR>a-carm-āṅgāraka, refers to the freedom of the gift village<BR>from the obligation to supply hide-seats and charcoal to the king<BR>or landlord on occasions or to the touring royal officers on their<BR>visit. Cf. Prakrit a-camm-aṅgālaka (Select Inscriptions, p. 409).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचाटभटगोचर<BR>a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-gocara (EI 22), same as a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचाटभटप्रवेश<BR>a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa (EI 27, 29; CII 3), refers to the free-<BR>dom of the gift village from the entry of the Cāṭas (leaders of<BR>groups of Pāiks and Piādas) and the Bhaṭas (Pāiks and Piādas);<BR>cf. a-bhaṭa-praveśa, a-bhaṭa-chātra-prāveśya, a-bhṛta-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचाटभटप्रावेश्य<BR>a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya (CII 3, 4), same as a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-pra-<BR>veśa; refers to the freedom of the gift land from being entered<BR>by the Bhaṭas (the king's Pāiks and Piādas) and the Cāḷa (the<BR>leader of a group of Pāiks and Piādas); cf. Chātra in place of Cāṭa<BR>in a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya; also Bhṛta for Bhaṭa in a-bhṛta-praveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचट्टभट्टप्रवेश<BR>a-caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-praveśa (EI 27), same as a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचुल्लककूरखट्वाग्रहण<BR>a-cullaka-kūra-khaṭvā-grahaṇa, similar to a-kūra-chullaka-<BR>vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अदुग्धदधिग्रहण<BR>a-dugdha-dadhi-grahaṇa, refers to the freedom of the gift<BR>village from the obligation of supplying milk and curs to the<BR>king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officials on their<BR>visit. Cf. Prakrit a-dudha-dadhi-gahaṇa (Select Inscriptions, p. 439).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहरीतकशाकपुष्पग्रहण<BR>a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa, refers to the freedom of the<BR>gift land from the supply of myrobalan, vegetables and flowers<BR>to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers<BR>on their visit. Cf. Prakrit a-haritaka-sāka-pupha-gahaṇa (Select<BR>Inscriptions, p. 439).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहरीतपर्णशाकपुष्पफलदुग्धदधिघृततक्रग्रहण<BR>a-harīta-parṇa-śāka-puṣpa-phala-dugdha-dadhi-ghṛta-takra-grahaṇa,<BR>similar to a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa and a-dugdha-dadhi-<BR>grahaṇa, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहस्तप्रक्षेपणीय<BR>a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīya (EI 11, 23), same as a a-bhaṭa-praveśa,<BR>etc. Cf. samasta-rājakīyānām=a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहिरण्यधान्यप्रणयप्रदेय<BR>a-hiraṇya-dhānya-praṇaya-pradeya (EI 26), refers to the<BR>freedom of the gift land from the payment of revenue in cash,<BR>the king's grain share and the benevolence or emergency<BR>imposts. Cf. Prakrit a-hiraṇṇa-dhaṇṇa-ppaṇaya-ppadeya (Select-<BR>Inscriptions, pp. 408-09).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरद<BR>a-karada (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the donee of<BR>the gift land from paying taxes in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरदायिन्<BR>a-karadāyin (EI 26, 27), same as a-karada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरवातोत्तर<BR>a-kara-vāt-ottara (IE; EI 32), sometimes with āvāta, vāt-ādeya,<BR>bhūt-opātta-pratyāya, etc., in place of vāt-ottara; cf. sa-bhūta-vāta-<BR>(or pāta) -pratyāya, etc; ‘free from the collections resulting from<BR>storms (e. g. uprooted trees, fruits, etc.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरविष्टिकोञ्जल्ल<BR>a-kara-viṣṭi-koñjalla (IE), refers to the freedom of the donee<BR>of the gift land from the payment of taxes and the obligation to<BR>supply free labour and koñjalla (kāñji) to the king's labourers.<BR>Cf. Select Inscriptions, p. 439.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अखट्वाचुल्लकवैनाशिक<BR>a-khaṭvā-cullaka-vaināśika, cf. Prakrit a-khaṭṭa-collaka-veṇe-<BR>sika (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the gift village from the<BR>obligation to supply cots, food and attendant or fuel to the<BR>touring royal officers on their visit or to the king or landlord<BR>on occasions. Cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्कर<BR>a-kiñcit-kara, ‘not to pay even a small amount as rent or<BR>tax’; epithet of gift land; same as a-kiñcit-pragrāhya. It has to<BR>be noted that sometimes a small amount of tax was fixed for<BR>the gift lands. Cf. kara-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्करग्राह्य<BR>a-kiñcit-kara-grāhya (EI 27), same as a-kiñcit-kara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्प्रग्राह्य<BR>a-kiñcit-pragrāhya (EI 29), refers to the freedom of the gift<BR>land from the payment of taxes and the obligation of supplying<BR>articles to the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring<BR>officers on their visit; same as a-kiñcit-kara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्प्रतिकर<BR>a-kiñcit-pratikara (EI 23), ‘[land] free from any yield<BR>of revenue’; cf. utpratikara. But pratikara also means<BR>‘compensation’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकूरचुल्लकवैनाशिखट्वावास<BR>a-kūra-cullaka-vaināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (or °saṃvāsa), cf. a-kūra-<BR>yollaka-venesi-khaṭṭ-āvāsa (EI 26); refers to the freedom of the<BR>gift village from the obligation of supplying boiled or unboiled<BR>rice, pots or fire-places for cooking, attendant or fuel, cot and<BR>shelter to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring<BR>officers on their visit; same as a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-saṃvāsa,<BR>etc. See sāmant-āmātya-dūtānām=anyeṣām c=ābhyupāgame śayanīy-<BR>āsana-siddh-ānnaṃ na dāpayet (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 171).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणगुडक्षोभ<BR>a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (EI 26), same as a-lavaṇa-khātaka,<BR>guḍa or sugar being added to lavaṇa or salt; cf. a-lavaṇa-klinna-<BR>khātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणखातक<BR>a-lavaṇa-khātaka, cf. Prakrit a-loṇa-khādaka (EI 7), refers<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-391" target="_blank">Page-391+ 40</a>]<BR>to the freedom of the gift land from being dug out or its trees<BR>being pierced for salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्लिन्नखनक<BR>a-lavaṇa-klinna-khanaka (EI 26), same as a-lavaṇa-klinna-<BR>kreṇi-khanaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्लिन्नखातक<BR>a-lavaṇa-klinna-khātaka, same as a-lavaṇa-khātaka, klinna,<BR>sometimes wrongly spelt kliṇva, probably, ‘toddy, sugar, etc.’<BR>being added to lavaṇa or salt. Cf. a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha, a-lavaṇa-<BR>klinna-kreṇi-khanaka, etc. Cf. Select Inscriptions, p. 408.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्लिण्वक्रेणिखनक<BR>a-lavaṇa-kliṇva(nna)-kreṇi-khanaka (EI 26, 27), same as a-<BR>lavaṇa-klinna-khātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्रेणिखनक<BR>a-lavaṇa-kreṇi-khanaka (EI 23), same as a-lavaṇa-klinna-<BR>khātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलेखनीप्रवेशतया<BR>a-lekhanī-praveśatayā (EI 29), probably refers to the absence<BR>of the right to re-grant the gift land to any other party on the<BR>part of the king and to alienate the gift land on the part of the<BR>donee; lekhanī-praveśa may mean that the gift land should not<BR>be made the subject of another document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाच्छेद्य|अनाछेद्य<BR>anācchedya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 267, note), ‘unresum-<BR>able’; but since anāhāra, ‘unresumable’, is sometimes used in the<BR>same context, probably, ‘uncurtailable’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनादेश्य<BR>anādeśya (EI 12), same as anirdeśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाहार|अनाहारः<BR>anāhāra, ‘unresumable’ (Ind. Ep., p. 395), cf. anācchedya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनङ्गुलिप्रक्षेपणीय<BR>anaṅguli-prakṣepaṇīya (EI 23), also called anaṅguli-prekṣaṇīya<BR>same as a-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनङ्गुलिप्रेक्षणीय<BR>anaṅguli-prekṣaṇīya (EI 23), same as anaṅguli-prakṣepaṇīya,<BR>a-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनासेध्य<BR>anāsedhya (Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 267, note 4), refers to<BR>the freedom of the people associated with the gift land from<BR>legal restraints.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनवमर्श्य<BR>anavamarśya, refers to the freedom of the gift land from<BR>troubles associated with the visit of royal agents. Cf. Prakrit<BR>anomasa (Select Inscriptions, pp. 192, 194).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपारम्पर<BR>a-pārampara, same as a-paramparā-balīvarda or a-paraṃ-<BR>parā-balīvarda-grahaṇa, a privilege of the donee of rent-free land<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरम्पराबलीवर्द<BR>a-paramparā-balīvarda (SITI), refers to the freedom of the<BR>gift village from the supply of bullocks primarily for the con-<BR>veyance of royal officers on tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरम्पराबलीवर्दग्रहण<BR>a-paramparā-balīvarda-grahaṇa (EI 26), same as a-pāram-<BR>para, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरम्परागोबलीवर्द<BR>a-paramparā-go-balīvarda (EI 22, 26, 27), same as a-pāram-<BR>para, etc., in which go (cow) has been added to balīvarda (bullock).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरिपन्थ्य<BR>a-paripanthya, ‘without opposition’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपशुमेध्य<BR>a-paśu-medhya (Select Inscriptions, p. 414), refers to the<BR>freedom from the supply of animals for sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रावेश्य<BR>a-prāveśya, refers to the freedom of the gift land from the<BR>entry of royal agents; same as a-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc. Cf. Prakrit<BR>a-pāvesa (Select Inscriptions, pp. 192, 194).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुष्पक्षीरग्रहण<BR>a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇa (EI 26), same as a-puṣpa-kṣīra-san-<BR>doha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुष्पक्षीरग्रहणीय<BR>a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇīya, refers to the freedom of the gift<BR>land from the supply, of flowers and milk to the king or land-<BR>lord on occasions or to the touring officers on their visit; same<BR>as a-puṣpa-kṣīra-sandoha, etc. Cf. Prakrit a-puppha-kkhīra-gahaṇi<BR>(Select Inscriptions, p. 409).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुष्पक्षीरसन्दोह<BR>a-puṣpa-kṣīra-sandoha (EI 26, 27), same as a-puṣpa-kṣīra-<BR>grahaṇīya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रधनं|अपुत्रधन<BR>aputra-dhanaṃ nāsti, ‘there is no confiscation, by the king,<BR>of the property of persons dying without a son’; cf. aputrā-sahita,<BR>etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रासहित<BR>aputrā-sahita (IE), ‘together with the right to confiscate<BR>the property of persons dying without leaving any son’; epithet<BR>of gift village. Cf. aputra-dhanaṃ nāsti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अराष्ट्रसांविनयिक<BR>a-rāṣṭra-sāṃvinayika (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the<BR>gift land from the administrative control to which the district<BR>in which it was situated was subject. Cf. Prakrit a-raṭha-saṃ-<BR>vinayika (Select Inscriptions, pp. 92, 94). See bhoga-sambandha-<BR>nirvacanīya, grāma-nilaya-nāḍa-sarva-bādhā-parithāreṇa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असन्नरप्रवृत्तिविनिवृत्ताचार<BR>asan-nara-pravṛtti-vinivṛtt-ācāra (Ind., Ant., Vol. XI p. 113,<BR>text lines 36-37), translated as ‘the established customs [of the<BR>gift land] are withheld from [injury by] the enterprise of<BR>wicked men.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभागिक<BR>aṣṭa-bhāgika, ‘paying one-eighth of the produce [in place<BR>of the usual one-sixth]’. Cf. Prakrit aṭha-bhāgiya (Select Ins-<BR>criptions, p. 70).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभोगतेजःस्वाम्यदण्डशुल्कयुक्त<BR>aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya-daṇḍaśulka-yukta (Ind. Ant., Vol XIX,<BR>p. 247, text line 102), mentioned along with nidhi-nikṣepa<BR>pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣprakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikh-āya-sahita. See aṣṭa-<BR>bhoga, tejaḥ-svāmya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशजातिपरिहार<BR>aṣṭādaśa-jāti-parihāra, the eighteen (i. e. all or various) kinds<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-393" target="_blank">Page-393+ 40</a>]<BR>of exemptions [usually enjoyed by rent-free holdings]. Cf.<BR>Prakrit aṭṭhārasa-jāti-parihāra (Select Inscriptions., pp. 439-40).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतृणकाष्ठग्रहण<BR>a-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-grahaṇa (EI 26), refers to the freedom of<BR>the donee of the gift village from the supply of grass and fuel<BR>to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers<BR>on their visit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवह<BR>a-vaha (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the gift village<BR>from the obligation of carrying loads of the touring officers,<BR>etc., or of supplying a horse to them free of charges.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवारसिद्धिक<BR>a-vāra-siddhika (IE), refers to the freedom of the gift<BR>village from the obligation to supply unpaid labour in turn.<BR>Cf. a-cāra-siddhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागभोगपशुहिरण्यकरशुल्क<BR>bhāga-bhoga-paśu-hiraṇya-kara-śulka (EI 20), ‘together with<BR>[the right to] the share of the produce, periodical offerings,<BR>cattle or animals [for sacrificial purposes], tax in cash, tax in<BR>kind and tolls’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाविष्यत्कररहित<BR>bhāviṣyat-kara-rahita (EI 24), ‘without all the taxes to be<BR>levied in future.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगसम्बन्धनिर्वचनीय<BR>bhogasambandha-nirvacanīya (EI 12), ‘the relations [of<BR>the gift land] with the administrative unit (i. e. bhoga, to<BR>which it belonged) should not be reckoned [since the land is<BR>granted after separating it from the district] (bhogād=uddhṛtya)’.<BR>Cf. a-rāṣṭra-sāṃvinayika, grāma-nilaya-nā ḍa-sarva-bādhā-parihāreṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रनायेन<BR>bhūmi-cchidra-nāyena or °cchidra-pidhāna-vyāyena, ‘in accor-<BR>dance with the principle of cultivating the land for the first<BR>time and enjoying it free of taxes as a result’. The word chidra<BR>in the first means ‘cultivation’ and chidra-pidhāna in the second<BR>‘reclamation of uncultivable land for the first time.’ Some-<BR>times vidhāna is wrongly used for pidhāna. See Ind. Ep., pp. 397-98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतभविष्यद्वर्तमाननिःशेषादात्यसहित<BR>bhūta-bhaviṣyad-vartamāna-niḥśeṣ-ādātya-sahita, ‘together with<BR>the arrears of taxes and with the present and future taxes in<BR>their entirety’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रार्ककालिकं<BR>candr-ārka-kālikaṃ śulkam=ādeyaṃ samasta-rājye n=āsti,<BR>‘there is no collection of tolls in the whole kingdom as long as the<BR>moon and the sun exist’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रार्कस्थितिकालं<BR>candr-ārka-sthiti-kālaṃ yāvat, ‘as long as the moon and sun<BR>endure (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135, text lines 21-22); some-<BR>times candr-ārka-ksiti°, candr-ārk-ārṇāva-kṣīti-sarit-parvata°, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चलुःसीमावच्छिन्न<BR>caluḥ-sīm-āvacchinna, same as sva-sīm-āvachinna, catur-aghāṭa-<BR>viśuddha, etc. Cf. Majumdar, Ins. Beng., Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुःसीमा<BR>catuḥ-sīmā yāvat, same as catuḥ-sīmā-paryanta, etc. Cf. Ind.<BR>Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुराघाटविशुद्ध<BR>catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha, ‘with the boundaries well demarca-<BR>ted’; same as catuḥ-sīm-āvacchina, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 396.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुराघाटान्तर्वर्तिजलपाषाणनिधिनिक्षेपशुल्कादिसर्वतेजःस्वाम्यसहित<BR>catur-āghāṭ-āntarvarti-jala-pāṣāṇa-nidhi-nikṣepa-śulk-ādi-sarva-tejaḥsvāmya-sahita<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 40, text lines<BR>37-38). See tejaḥ-svāmya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुष्कण्टकविशुद्ध<BR>catuṣ-kaṇṭaka-viśuddha (EI 23), cf. catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha;<BR>probably refers to the custom of demarcating a plot of land by<BR>planting thorny shrubs on the borders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरवर्जम्<BR>caura-varjam, also quoted as cora-varjam, cora-daṇḍa-varjam,<BR>cora-rājāpathyakāri-varjam, etc.; according to some ‘with immu-<BR>nity from the police tax’, while others take it to be related to<BR>a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa and think that the policemen were prohi-<BR>bited from entering a gift village except in connection with the<BR>apprehension of criminals; may also mean ‘without any right<BR>to inflict punishment of thieves, etc., or to levy fines from<BR>thieves, etc.’ See CII, Vol. III, p. 109.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरदण्डवर्ज<BR>cora-daṇḍa-varja (EI 27), same as caura-varja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्ज<BR>cora-varja (IE), ‘without the right to punish the thieves and to<BR>realise stolen articles’; cf. sa-caur-oddharaṇa. But see also cauravarjam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशमर्यादारुवणान्विल<BR>deśa-maryād-āruvaṇ-ānvila (Ind. Ant. Vol. XIX, p. 247, text<BR>line 103), refers to the right to levy the tax called āruvaṇa<BR>(Sanskrit ṣaṭ-paṇa) according to the local custom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवब्राह्मणभुक्तिवर्ज<BR>deva-Brāhmaṇa-bhukti-varja (EI 23, 30), ‘excluding the<BR>property of the gods (i. e. temples) and Brāhmaṇas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलपुष्करिण्याधिकं<BR>devakula-puṣkariṇy-ādhikaṃ kārayitvā, refers to the right of<BR>the donee to build temples and excavate tanks in the gift land<BR>without the permission of the king or landlord as was necessary<BR>in the case of ordinary tenants. Cf. Majumdar, Ins. Beng.,<BR>Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोगौडसमेत<BR>go-gauḍa-sameta, ‘together with the cattle and herdsmen<BR>[of state farms] or with the grazing tax’; epithet of gift village.<BR>Go-gauḍa may be the same as go-kara. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामनिलयनाडसर्वबाधापरिहारेण<BR>grāma-nilaya-nāḍa-sarva-bādhā-parihāreṇa (EI 9), ‘with the<BR>exemption of all troubles connected with [the administration<BR>of] the village, subdivision (literally, habitation) and district [in<BR>which the gift land is situated]’. Cf. a-rāṣṭra-sāṃvinayika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहावतरणहरितपक्वसस्येक्षुचारणलवनोपमर्दनरोचिकाचिटोलाग्रहणपीठकपीठिकाखट्वापहरणकाष्ठेन्धन<BR>gṛh-āvataraṇa-harita-pakva-sasy-ekṣu-cāraṇa-lavan-opamardana-rocikā-ciṭolā-grahaṇa-pīṭhaka-pīṭhikā-khaṭv-āpaharaṇa-kāṣṭh-endhana-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-395" target="_blank">Page-395+ 40</a>]<BR>ghāsa-bus-ādikaṃ na kenacit = [kartavyaṃ] pragrāhyaṃ [ca],<BR>‘no one should enter into the donce's house, should graze one's<BR>cattle on the green crops in his fields, should harvest the ripe<BR>crops in his fields, should crush his sugar-cane, should accept<BR>rocikā and ciṭolā from him, should take stools, seats and cots<BR>from him and should take wood, fuel, grass, chaff, etc., from<BR>him’. For gṛh-āvataraṇa, see umbara-bheda. Words like rocikā,<BR>ciṭolā, etc., are not intelligible, although they certainly refer<BR>to certain obligations or levies. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुवाकनारिकेलादिकं<BR>guvāka-nārikel-ādikaṃ laggāvayitvā, refers to the right of<BR>planting arecanut and coconut palms in the gift land without<BR>the permission of the king or landlord as was necessary in the<BR>case of ordinary tenants; cf. sa-guvāka-nārikela. Cf. Majum-<BR>dar, Ins. Beng., Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिदण्डवरबलीवर्द<BR>hastidaṇḍa-varabalīvarda-coṭāla-andhā(rthā?)ruvā-pratyandhā-<BR>(rthā?)ruvā-adattā-padātijīva-ahidaṇḍa-ānta(tu?)rāvaḍḍi-bandha-<BR>daṇḍa-vijayavandāpanā-mārgaṇika-prabhṛti-bhaviṣyat-kara-sahita, refers<BR>to the donee's right to enjoy various taxes the nature of some of<BR>which is doubtful. These include the tax for keeping elephants<BR>and prize bullocks, tax for the maintenance of the king's Padātis<BR>(footmen or Pāiks), tax on the professional snake-charmers,<BR>ransom in lieu of imprisonment, presents to be made to the<BR>king on his return from a victorious campaign and tax to be paid<BR>for using the road in the gift village for the transit of articles of<BR>merchandise. See the expressions separately as noticed above.<BR>See also suvarṇa-daṇḍa-ahidaṇḍa … below. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनधनसहित<BR>jana-dhana-sahita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘to-<BR>gether with the tenants and revenue income [of the village]’;<BR>some as sa-jana-dhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशलतापूतहस्तोदकेन<BR>kuśa-latā-pūta-hast-odakena, cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc. See Ind.<BR>Ep., p. 395<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादोषविवर्जित<BR>mahādoṣa-vivarjita (EI 23), ‘excluding fines for great<BR>crimes’; cf. doṣa and daṇḍa-doṣa (fines) noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुक्तोपरिकर<BR>mukt-oparikara (EI 29), free from minor taxes or without<BR>freedom from them. Cf. s-oparikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नानावृक्षसमेत<BR>nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta, ‘together with the various trees’; epithet<BR>of gift village. Some of the trees not to be enjoyed by unpri-<BR>vileged tenants were mango, madhūka, jack, coconut, arecanut,<BR>palmyra palm, sīsu, tamarind tree, etc. But the group was<BR>different in different parts of the country. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवनिधानसहित<BR>nava-nidhāna-sahita (IA 11), probably, ‘with the taxes fixed<BR>afresh’, though nidhāna is often the same as nikṣepa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधिनिक्षेपपाषाणारामादिचतुष्प्रकारबीरवणपारिखायसहित<BR>nidhi-nikṣepa-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣprakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikh-āya-sahita<BR> (Ind. Int., Vol. XIX, p. 247), mentioned along with<BR>aṣṭabhoga-tejassvāmy-daṇḍaśulka-yukta. See the expressions as sepa-<BR>rately noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधिनिक्षेपापुत्रकधनदण्डोपजातकसहित<BR>nidhi-nikṣep-āputrakadhana-daṇḍ-opajātaka-sahita, ‘together<BR>with the right to enjoy treasure-trove and the occasional finds<BR>and accumulations on the land and to confiscate the property<BR>of persons dying without leaving any son, and to enjoy the right<BR>to appropriate the income derived from fines’; epithet of gift<BR>village. Cf. Ind. Ep., 406.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधिनिक्षेपसहित<BR>nidhi-nikṣepa-sahita, see sa-vṛkṣamālā-nīdhi-nikṣepa-sahita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निध्युपनिधिहस्तिदन्तव्याघ्रचर्मनानावनचरसमेत<BR>nidhy-upanidhi-hastidanta-vyāghracarma-nānāvanacara-sameta,<BR>refers to the right of the donee to treasure-troves, occasional<BR>finds or accumulations on the ground, elephants’ tusks, tiger's<BR>skin and certain prized animals without surrendering them<BR>to the king as ordinary tenants had to do; epithet of the gift<BR>village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषिद्धचाटभटप्रवेश<BR>niṣiddha-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa (EI 22), same as a-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिहृतपङ्गोत्कोट<BR>parihṛta-paṅg-otkoṭa (EI 33), ‘exempted from the levies<BR>called paṅga and utkoṭa’. See the words as separately noticed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिहृतसर्वपीड<BR>parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa (EI 27, 29), ‘free from all troubles’;<BR>same as sarva-pīḍā-varjita, sarva-bādhā-vivarjita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलरतिक<BR>phalaratika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), refers pro-<BR>bably to the right to enjoy all kinds of fruits in the gift land with-<BR>out special permission that was necessary for ordinary tenants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसिद्धचतुःसीमावच्छिन्न<BR>prasiddha-catuḥ-sīm-āvacchinna, ‘demarcated by the well-<BR>known boundaries on all the sides’; epithet of the gift land.<BR>Cf. catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषिद्धचाटभटप्रवेश<BR>pratiṣiddha-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa (EI 23, 27), same as a-<BR>praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषिद्धचाटादिप्रवेश<BR>pratiṣiddha-cāṭ-ādi-praveśa (I. E., p. 395), same as a-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वभुज्यमानदेवब्राह्मणक्षेत्रखण्डलकं<BR>pūrva-bhujyamāna-deva-brāhmaṇa-kṣetra-khaṇḍalakaṃ varjayitvā<BR>(or vihāya), see Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135; same as deva-<BR>brāhmaṇa-bhukti-varja, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 398.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वभुक्तकभुज्यमानदेवब्रह्मदायवर्जित<BR>pūrva-bhuktaka-bhujyamāna-deva-brahma-dāya-varjita (EI 23),<BR>same as deva-brāhmaṇa-bhukti-varja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वप्रत्तदेवब्रह्मदेयरहित<BR>pūrva-pratta-deva-brahma-deya-rahita, sometimes with dāya in<BR>place of deya; refers to the absence of the donee's right to have<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-397" target="_blank">Page-397+ 40</a>]<BR>any control over that land in the gift village which was already<BR>a rent-free holding in the possession of gods or Brāhmaṇas;<BR>same as deva-brahmaṇa-bhukti-varja, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 398.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्रादिसन्ततिक्रमेण<BR>putra-pautrādi-santati-krameṇa, same as putra-pautr-ānvaya-kram-<BR>opabhogya, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 399.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्राद्यन्वयोपभोगा<BR>putra-pautr-ādy-anvay-opabhogā, °ānugaminī, etc.; same as<BR>putra-pautr-ānugamaka. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 394-95.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्रानुगमक<BR>putra-pautr-ānugamaka, ‘the donce's right of enjoying the gift<BR>land should pass on to his sons and grandsons’; epithet of gift land;<BR>same as putra-pautr-ānvaya-kram-opabhogya, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 392.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्रान्वयक्रमोपभोग्य<BR>putra-pautr-ānvaya-kram-opabhogya, refers to the permanent<BR>nature of a gift of land to be enjoyed by the donee as well as<BR>his descendants; same as putra-putr-ānugamaka (I.E., p. 398).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभाव्यसर्वप्रत्यायसमेत<BR>rāja-bhāvya-sarva-pratyāya-sameta (EI 23), bhāvya being<BR>often changed to ābhāvya; same as a-kiñcit-pragrāhya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजग्राह्यसमस्तप्रत्यायसमन्वित<BR>rāja-grāhya-samasta-pratyāya-samanvita (EI 22), same as<BR>a-kiñcit-pragrāhya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजपुरुषैर्<BR>rāja-rājapuruṣair=apy=anaṅguli-nirdeśyam, same as srava-<BR>rāja-kīyānām=a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīyaḥ, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 400.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसेवकानां<BR>rājasevakānāṃ vasatidaṇḍa-prayāṇadaṇḍau na staḥ, refers to<BR>the freedom of the gift village from the obligation to provide<BR>accommodation and conveyance, etc., to the royal officers on<BR>tour; cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, a-paraṃparā-balīvarda,<BR>etc. See CII, Vol. III, p. 98, note 2.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्ञाराजपुरुषैर्<BR>rājñā rājapuruṣair=apy=anaṅguli-prakṣepaṇīya (Ind., Ant., Vol.<BR>XIX, p. 247, text lines 103-04), same as sarva-rājakīyānām=<BR>a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīyaḥ, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रम्य|रम्यः<BR>ramya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), refers to the fact<BR>that the gift land had nothing unpleasant about it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋणादायादिसम्बन्धवर्जित<BR>ṛṇ-ādāy-ādi-sambandha-varjita (EI 23), refers to the free-<BR>dom of the gift land from confiscation for the realisation of debts<BR>incurred by the donee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सबाह्याभ्यन्तरादाय<BR>sa-bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya, ‘together with the external and<BR>internal income or taxes to be paid to the state and to the<BR>village authorities’; epithet of the gift village; cf. abhyantara-<BR>siddhyā, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभोग<BR>sa-bhoga (EI 27; IA 9), ‘together with the aṣṭa-bhoga’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभूतपातप्रत्याय<BR>sa-bhūta-pāta-pratyāya (CII 3), refers to the income from<BR>the gift land as a result of some action of nature's agencies.<BR>Sometimes vāta and āvāta are found for pāta probably in the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-398" target="_blank">Page-398+ 40</a>]<BR>sense of ‘a storm’ (cf. udvāta) and also upātta, ‘realised’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभूतवातप्रत्याय<BR>sa-bhūta-vāta-pratyāya (EI 23), with pāta sometimes in<BR>place of vāta; ‘together with the income arising out of a change<BR>of the natural phenomena (such as due to earthquakes, storms,<BR>etc.)’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभूतोपात्तप्रत्याय<BR>sa-bhūt-opātta-pratyāya (EI 23), same as sa-bhūta-vāta-pra-<BR>tyāya, etc. The word upātta means ‘realised’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सचौरोद्धरण<BR>sa-caur-oddharaṇa (EI 12, 23, 29), ‘together with the right<BR>to punish thieves and recover stolen property or fines’; epithet<BR>of gift villages. Cf. caura-varja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदण्डदोष<BR>sa-daṇḍa-doṣa (EI 23), ‘together with [the right to] levy fines<BR>for crimes’; the meaning of doṣa is really doubtful in the context.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदण्डनिग्रह<BR>sa-daṇḍa-nigraha (EI 24), refers to the king's power to<BR>punish [culprits] by fines or corporal punishment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदशापचार<BR>sa-daś-āpacāra, same as sa-daś-āparādha; cf. Ind. Ep.,<BR>p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदशापराध<BR>sa-daś-āparādha (EI 27), also quoted as sa-daś-āpacāra;<BR>‘together with the right to punish and realise fines for the ten<BR>offences (murder, theft, etc.)’; epithet of gift village; cf.<BR>sahya-daś-āparādha probably meaning that the crimes committed<BR>in the gift village should not be punished by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदेयमेय<BR>sa-deya-meya (EI 7), same as sa-dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सधान्यहिरण्यादेय<BR>sa-dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya (EI 11, 12, 23; IA 9), ‘together<BR>with the king's grain share and taxes in cash’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधऊर्ध्व<BR>s-ādha-ūrdhva, ‘together with what is [produced or found]<BR>below and above the ground’; epithet of gift land. Cf. Ind.<BR>Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सागमनिरमप्रवेश<BR>s-āgama-nirama-praveśa, ‘together with approaches, ingress<BR>and egress’; epithet of gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगर्तावस्कर<BR>sa-gart-āvaskara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), mentioned<BR>along with s-oṣara. The word avaskara (also avakara) probably<BR>means ‘a mound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगर्तोषर<BR>sa-gart-oṣara (EI 27, 29), ‘together with pits and saline<BR>spots or barren lands’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगिरिगहननिधान<BR>sa-giri-gahana-nidhāna (EI 24), ‘together with hills, forests<BR>and deposits’. See also nidhāna noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगोकुल<BR>sa-gokula, ‘together with the cowpens’; epithet of gift<BR>village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगोप्रचार<BR>sa-gopracāra (EI 12), ‘together with the pasture lands’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगुल्मलता<BR>sa-gulma-latā (EI 12), same as sa-gulma-latāka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगुल्मलताक<BR>sa-gulma-latāka, ‘together with shrubs and creepers’; epithet<BR>of the gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगुवाकनारिकेर<BR>sa-guvāka-nārikera (EI 12), sometimes with nālikela in<BR>place of nārikera; ‘together with the arecanut and coconut<BR>palms’; epithet of gift land; see guvāka-nārikel-ādikaṃ laggāvayitvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहट्टघट्टसतर<BR>sa-haṭṭa-ghaṭṭa-sa-tara (EI 22), ‘together with market-<BR>places and ferries (or passes) and with ferry-dues’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहिरण्यभागभोग<BR>sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga (EI 23), same as sa-deya-meya, etc.<BR>See the words as separately noticed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहिरण्यभागभोगोपरिकरसर्वादायसमेत<BR>sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhog-oparikara-sarv-ādāya-sameta (EI 23),<BR>‘together with all levies such as hiraṇya, bhāga, bhoga and upa-<BR>rikara’. See the various words as noticed separately.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहिरण्यादान<BR>sa-hiraṇy-ādāna (EI 26), ‘together with levies in cash’;<BR>privilege of the donee of rent-free and.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सह्यदशापराध<BR>sahya-daś-āparādha (IE), see sa-daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजलस्थल<BR>sa-jala-sthala (EI 12, 27, 29), ‘together with land and<BR>waters [of the gift village]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजलस्थलारण्य<BR>sa-jala-sthal-āraṇya (EI 23), ‘together with the land,<BR>waters and jungles [of the gift village]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजलस्थलसहित<BR>sa-jala-sthala-sahita (EI 23), same as sa-jala-sthala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजनधन<BR>sa-jana-dhana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139), same as<BR>jana-dhana-sahita. Cf. sa-jana (ibid., Vol. V, p. 185).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजाङ्गलानूप<BR>sa-jāṅgal-ānūpa (EI 12), ‘together with arid and marshy<BR>lands’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सझाटविटप<BR>sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa, ‘together with bushes and shrubs (or<BR>branches)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकरोत्कर<BR>sa-kar-otkara = Prakrit sa-kar-ukara (EI 7); refers to a piece<BR>of land granted with the donee's right to enjoy major and minor<BR>taxes; cf. s-odraṅga-s-oparikara and sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta, etc. See<BR>kar-otkara as noticed separately above; also cf. kāru-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखल्लौन्नत<BR>sa-khalla-unnata=sa-khall-onnata (EI 12), ‘together with<BR>low and high lands’; epithet of gift land. Khalla is Oḏiyā<BR>khāl ‘low land’. Cf. sa-nimn-onnata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखण्डपालीय<BR>sa-khaṇḍapālīya, ‘together with the tax for the maintenance<BR>of the swordsmen’; epithet of gift village; cf. padāti-jivya,<BR>tax for the maintenance of Pāiks or footmen. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखटविटप<BR>sa-khaṭa-viṭapa (EI 12), mistake for sa-jhāṭa-vitapa or sa-<BR>kheṭa-viṭapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखेटघट्टनदीतरस्थानादिगुल्मक<BR>sa-kheṭa-ghaṭṭa-nadītara-sthān-ādi-gulmaka (EI 29), ‘to-<BR>gether with the military, police or customs outposts in the ham-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-400" target="_blank">Page-400+ 40</a>]<BR>lets, landing places on the banks of rivers (or passes in the<BR>hilly tracts) and ferrying stations’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखेटविटप<BR>sa-kheṭa-viṭapa, ‘together with outposts and bushes’;<BR>epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखिलनाल<BR>sa-khila-nāla, ‘together with the fallow and cultivated<BR>lands’; epithet of gift village; same as sa-khila-polācya. See<BR>Majumdar, Ins. Beng., Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखिलपोलाच्य<BR>sa-khila-polācya, ‘together with fallow and cultivated land’;<BR>same as sa-khila-nāla. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखिलोपखिल<BR>sa-khil-opakhila, ‘together with land which is fallow and<BR>partially fallow’. Pakhila in the same context is a mistake for<BR>upakhila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकॢप्त<BR>sa-kḷpta (EI 24), ‘together with the tax on permanent<BR>tenants or the fixed revenue’; same as s-odraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकॢप्तोपकॢप्तक<BR>sa-kḷpt-opakḷptaka (EI 24, 27), refers to the freedom of the<BR>gift land from the payment of fixed taxes on permanent<BR>tenants as well as occasional taxes or taxes on temporary tenants;<BR>same as s-odraṅga-s-oparikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकृतप्रान्त<BR>sa-kṛta-prānta, cf. Prakrit sa-kutu-ppanta (EI 26), ‘together<BR>with the demarcated boundaries’; epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलवण<BR>sa-lavaṇa (EI 12), ‘together with salt (i. e. the right to<BR>enjoy salt produced in the land). Cf. a-lavaṇa-khātaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलवणाकर<BR>sa-lavaṇ-ākara (EI 12), ‘together with the salt pits’. Cf.<BR>a-lavaṇa-khātaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलोहाद्याकर<BR>sa-loh-ādy-ākara, together with the mines of metals, etc.’;<BR>epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलोहलवणाकर<BR>sa-loha-lavaṇ-ākara (EI 23, 26), ‘together with the mines<BR>and salt-pits’, epithet of gift land. Cf. sa-loh-ādy-ākara, a-<BR>lavaṇa-khātaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समधूकचूतवनवाटिकाविटपतृनयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त<BR>sa-madhūka-cūta-vana-vāṭikā-viṭapa-tṛna-yūti-gocara-paryanta,<BR>‘together with the madhūka and mango trees, forests, gardens,<BR>bushes (or, branches), grass yūti (grass land) and including the<BR>pasture land’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 396. It is better to take sa-madhūka-<BR>cūṭa-vana-vāṭikā-viṭapa and tṛnayūti-gocara-paryanta separately.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समधूकाम्रवनवाटिकाविटपतृणयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त<BR>sa-madhūk-āmra-vana-vāṭikā-viṭapa-tṛṇa-yūti-gocara-paryanta<BR>(EI 24), ‘together with the madhuka and mango trees, forests,<BR>gardens, shrubs and as far as and the grass yuli (grass land) and<BR>pasture lands’. See sa-madhūka-cūta … , above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्दिरप्राकार<BR>sa-mandira-prākāra, ‘together with temples and walls’;<BR>epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-401" target="_blank">Page-401+ 40</a>]<BR>trees and areas covered by jungles (or areas covered with mango<BR>and madhūka plantations)’; see Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समञ्चमहाकरण<BR>sa-mañca-mahākaraṇa (EI 26), ‘together with mañca (pro-<BR>bably, platforms for the collection of tolls) and mahākaraṇa<BR>(official documents)’; epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्तामात्यदूतानाम्<BR>sāmant-āmātya-dūtānām = anyeṣām = c = ābhyupāgame śayanīy-<BR>āsana-siddhānnaṃ na dāpayet, refers to the obligation of the people<BR>to supply beds, seats and boiled or unboiled rice to feudatory<BR>rulers, ministers, messengers and others encamped in a<BR>village; see a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, etc. See Ep. Ind.,<BR>Vol. XXX, p. 171.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तभागभोगकरहिरण्यादिप्रत्यायसमेत<BR>samasta-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇy-ādi-pratyāya-sameta, ‘together<BR>with all incomes including the king's grain share, the periodical<BR>offerings to be made to the king or landlord and to the touring<BR>officers, taxes in grains, taxes in cash, etc.’; epithet of gift<BR>land; same as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc. See Ind. Ep., p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तभागभोगकरहिरण्यादायसमेत<BR>samasta-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇy-ādāya-sameta (EI 23), same<BR>as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तराजकीयानाम्<BR>samasta-rājakīyānām = apraveśya, same as a-bhaṭa-praveśa, a-<BR>cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśya, a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya, etc. (Ind. Ep., p. 398).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तराजकीयानम्<BR>samasta-rājakīyānam = ahasta-prakṣepaṇīya (CII 3), same as<BR>ā-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तराजप्रत्यादायसमेत<BR>samasta-rājapratyādāya-sameta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV,<BR>p. 129), same as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तोत्पत्तिसहित<BR>samast-otpatti-sahita (EI 12), ‘together with all the pro-<BR>duce or income’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तोत्पत्तिशुल्कोत्पत्तिसहित<BR>samast-otpatti-śulk-otpatti-sahita (EI 23), ‘together with<BR>all the produce of the land and the income arising from tolls’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्स्यकच्छप<BR>sa-matsya-kacchapa (EI 12), ‘together with the right to<BR>catch fish and tortoises’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्स्याकर<BR>sa-matsy-ākara (EI 24), 26), ‘together with the sources of<BR>fish (e. g., rivers, tanks, etc)’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्हलालमकसमन्वित<BR>samhalālamaka-samanvita (EI 9), the reading is apparently<BR>wrong; meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समीनतोय<BR>sa-mīna-toya (EI 24), ‘together with fish and the waters’<BR>or ‘together with the waters containing fish.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रमधूक<BR>s-āmra-madhūka (IE; EI 12, 27, 29), ‘together with the<BR>mango and madhūka trees’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रमधुवन<BR>s-āmra-madhu-vana (EI 12), same as s-āmra-madhū-van-ākīrṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रमधुवनाकीर्ण<BR>s-āmra-madhu-van-ākīrṇa, see Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रपनस<BR>s-āmra-panasa (EI 12), ‘together with mango and jack trees’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुछितदेयभागभोगकरहिरण्यादि<BR>samuchita-deya-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇy-ādi (EI 23), same<BR>as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदयबाह्याद्यस्तम्ब<BR>samudayabāhy-ādyastamba (EI 23), ‘[land] covered with<BR>original shrubs (i.e. never cultivated) and not yielding any<BR>revenue [to the State].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समूल|समूलं<BR>sa-mūla (EI 13), ‘together with the root crops’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधानालीपक<BR>nidhān-ālīpaka-kumārīsāhas-āputrādhana-pradhān-āpradhāna-doṣa-<BR>samanvita (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 274), see the words as noticed<BR>separately above. The word doṣa here means ‘fines’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिधि<BR>sa-nidhi (EI 27), refers to the freedom of the donee of the<BR>gift land from the obligation of surrendering to the king under-<BR>ground treasures in the land on their discovery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिधिनिधान<BR>sa-nidhi-nidhāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139), same as<BR>sa-nidhi-nikṣepa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिधिनिक्षेप<BR>sa-nidhi-nikṣepa, see nidhi, nikṣepa, nidhāna, ālipaka, etc.,<BR>as noticed separately. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 396.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिध्युपनिधि<BR>sa-nidhy-upanidhi (EI 26), same as sa-nidhi-nikṣepa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिम्नोन्नत<BR>sa-nimn-onnata (IA 16), same as sa-khall-onnata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिर्गमप्रवेश<BR>sa-nirgama-praveśa (EI 12), ‘together with ingress and egress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सानूपजाङ्गल<BR>s-ānūpa-jāṅgala (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 34, text line<BR>5), same as sa-jāṅgal-ānūpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपद्रारण्य<BR>sa-padr-āraṇya (EI 23, 24), same as sa-padr-āraṇyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपद्रारण्यक<BR>sa-padr-āraṇyaka (EI 12), ‘together with habitations and<BR>jungles’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपल्लिक<BR>sa-pallika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘together<BR>with its hamlets’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपरिकर<BR>sa-parikara (EI 23), same as or a mistake for s-oparikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपर्णाकर<BR>sa-parṇ-ākara (EI 26), ‘together with the fields growing<BR>betel leaves’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्रतीहार<BR>sa-pratīhāra, ‘together with the tax for the maintenance<BR>of the watchmen of the city gates’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वबाधापरिहार<BR>sarva-bādhā-parihāra (EI 23, 24), same as parihṛta-sarva-<BR>pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वबाधाविवर्जित<BR>sarva-bādhā-vivarjita (EI 24), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाभ्यन्तरसिद्धि<BR>sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi (EI 20; IA 19), ‘together with<BR>the entire internal revenue income or all the taxes to be paid<BR>to local authorities’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाभ्यन्तरसिद्ध्या<BR>sarv-ābhyantara-siddhyā (IA 18), same as sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादानदित्यविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहीन<BR>sarv-ādāna-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna (CII 4), ‘free<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-403" target="_blank">Page-403+ 40</a>]<BR>from all levies, ditya, forced labour and prātibhedikā’. See<BR>ditya and prātibhedikā as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादानसङ्ग्राह्य<BR>sarv-ādāna-saṅgrāhya (6II 4), ‘with the right to levy all<BR>the dues’; same as sarv-ādāya-sameta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादानविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहीन<BR>sarv-ādāna-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna (CII 4), ‘free from<BR>the payment of all imposts and the obligation regarding unpaid<BR>labour and prātibhedikā’; epithet of gift village. See prāti-<BR>bhedikā as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादायसमेत<BR>sarv-ādāya-sameta (EI 23), same as sarv-ādāna-saṅgrāhya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादेयविशुद्ध<BR>sarv-ādeya-viśuddha (CII 4), ‘with all kinds of taxes<BR>fixed’; same as sarv-ādāya-sameta (cf. sarv-āya-viśuddha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदित्यविष्टिजेमककरभरपरिहीन<BR>sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-jemaka-kara-bhara-parihīna (CII 4), ‘free<BR>from the burden of all the ditya, forced labour, jemaka and<BR>taxes’. See ditya and jemaka as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदित्यविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहीन<BR>sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna (EI 9; CII 4), ‘free<BR>from all kinds of ditya, forced labour and prātibhedikā’. See the<BR>words as noticed separately.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदित्यविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहृत<BR>sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihṛta (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI,<BR>p. 298, text lines 201-21), same as sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-<BR>parihīna. See the words as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजातभोगनिरस्त<BR>sarva-jāta-bhoga-nirasta, refers to a grant of land with all<BR>kinds of royal rights abrogated. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 390.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजातभोग<BR>sarva-jāta-bhoga (EI 24), ‘together with all kinds of<BR>privileges to be enjoyed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजातपारिहारिक<BR>sarva-jāta-pārihārika, cf. Prakrit sava-jāta-pārihārika (Select<BR>Inscriptions, pp. 92, 94), ‘endowed with all kinds of exemptions.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वकरपरिहार<BR>sarva-kara-parihāra (EI 23, 27), ‘exemption from all<BR>taxes.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वकरसमेत<BR>sarva-kara-sameta (EI EI 23, 27), ‘together with all<BR>taxes.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपङ्गपरिहृत<BR>sarva-paṅga-parihṛta (EI 33), ‘free from all levies falling<BR>in the category of paṅga’. See paṅga noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपरिहारकारुदेय<BR>sarva-parihāra-kārudeya (EI 24), refers to all kinds of<BR>exemptions including the dues from artisans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपिडापरिहृत<BR>sarva-piḍā-parihṛta (EI 23), same as sarva-pīḍā-varjita,<BR>sarva-pīḍā-vivarjita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपीडावर्जित<BR>sarva-pīḍā-varjita (EI 23), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa,<BR>sarva-bādhā-vivarjita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपीडाविवर्जित<BR>sarva-pīḍā-vivarjita (EI 27), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वराजकीयानाम्<BR>sarva-rājakīyānām = a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīyaḥ (CII 3), same as<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-404" target="_blank">Page-404+ 40</a>]<BR>a-bhaṭa-praveśa, a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya, a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्ववाधाविवर्जित<BR>sarva-vādhā-vivarjita, with vādhā in the place of bādhā; same<BR>as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, sarva-pīḍā-varjita, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वविष्टिपरिहारपरिहृत<BR>sarva-viṣṭi-parihāra-parihṛta (EI 23, 24, 26), ‘endowed with<BR>the exemptions from all kinds of unpaid labour’; epithet of<BR>the gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वायसहित<BR>sarv-āya-sahita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247, text line 203),<BR>‘together with the entire income.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वायविशुद्ध<BR>sarv-āya-viśuddha (EI 23), ‘having fixed and regular income.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोपद्रववर्जित<BR>sarv-opadrava-varjita (EI 24), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोपरिकरादानसहित<BR>sarv-oparikar-ādāna-sahita, ‘together with the right to levy<BR>all minor taxes or taxes on temporary tenants’; epithet of gift<BR>village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोपरिकरकरादानसमेत<BR>sarv-oparikara-kar-ādāna-sameta (EI 23), ‘together with<BR>all the levies falling in the categories of uparikara and kara’.<BR>See kara and uparikara as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोत्पत्तिसहित<BR>sarv-otpatti-sahita (EI 23), ‘together with whatever is<BR>produced (i. e. crops or income).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वेष्टिपरिहारपरिहृत<BR>sarv-eṣṭi-parihāra-parihṛta (EI 27), sarv-eṣṭi may be a<BR>mistake for sarva-viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससैबर<BR>sa-saibara (EI 17), also written sa-śaivara; ‘together with<BR>unassessed arable lands or the tax on farm-houses’; cf. śaivara<BR>and saibara noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससर्वपल्लिक<BR>sa-sarva-pallika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 129), ‘together<BR>with all the hamlets’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससर्वाशनेक्षुकर्पासशणाम्रमधूकादिभूरुह<BR>sa-sarv-āśan-ekṣu-karpāsa-śaṇ-āmra-madhūk-ādi-bhūruha, ‘to-<BR>gether with aśana (pītaśāla), sugarcane, cotton-plants, hemp-<BR>plants, mango, madhūka and other trees’; epithet of gift land.<BR>Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससाटविटप<BR>sa-sāṭa-viṭapa (EI 12), mistake or wrong reading of sa-<BR>jhāṭa-viṭapa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साष्टादशप्रकृत्य्<BR>s-āṣṭādaśa-prakṛty = opeta (EI 2), ‘together with the<BR>eighteen (i. e. all) kinds of tenants (i. e. tenants belonging<BR>to all the communities)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सस्थावरजङ्गम<BR>sa-sthāvara-jaṅgama, ‘together with the immovable and<BR>movable belongings [of the gift village]’. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतल<BR>sa-tala (EI 12, 29), ‘together with the surface of the<BR>ground’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतालक<BR>sa-tālaka (EI 12), ‘together with palmyra palms’; epi-<BR>thet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतन्तलिक<BR>sa-tantalika (EI 12), ‘together with tamarind trees’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतन्तुवायगोकुटशौण्डिकादिप्रकृतिक<BR>sa-tantuvāya-gokuṭa-śauṇḍik-ādi-prakṛtika, ‘together with such<BR>tenants as the weavers, cowherds or milkmen and vintners’;<BR>epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 393.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतर<BR>sa-tara (EI 22), see sa-haṭṭa-ghaṭṭa-sa-tara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साटविविटपसमन्वित<BR>s-āṭavi-viṭapa-samanvita (EI 23), ‘together with forests<BR>and shrubs’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतृणकाष्ठोदकोपेत<BR>sa-tṛṇa-kāṣṭh-odak-opeta (EI 24), ‘together with the grass,<BR>fuel and waters [of the gift village]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवनस्पत्युदकासीहारकुल्लकपानीयसमेत<BR>sa-vanaspaty-udak-āsīhāra-kullaka-pānīya-sameta ‘together with<BR>the fruit-trees and various kinds of water courses’; epithet of<BR>gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवनश्वभ्रनिधान<BR>sa-vana-śvabhra-nidhāna, ‘together with forests, pits and<BR>mines’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवातभूतप्रत्याय<BR>sa-vāta-bhūta-pratyāya (EI 11; IA 9), same as sa-bhūta-vāta-<BR>pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सविटपलता<BR>sa-viṭapa-latā (EI 24), ‘together with shrubs and creep-<BR>ers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सविटपारण्य<BR>sa-viṭap-āraṇya, ‘together with bushes and jungles’;<BR>epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवृक्षमालाकुल<BR>sa-vṛkṣamālā-kula (EI 23; IA 11), ‘together with vari-<BR>ous gardens or plantations’. See nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवृक्षमालानिधिनिक्षेपसहित<BR>sa-vṛkṣamālā-nidhi-nikṣepa-sahita (EI 23), see sa-vṛkṣamālā-<BR>kula and sa-nidhi-nikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमान्तर्गतवस्तुसहित<BR>sīm-āntargata-vastu-sahita, ‘together with [all] things with-<BR>in the boundaries’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीसूमधूकतालप्रभृतिनानावृक्षसमेत<BR>sīsū-madhūka-tāla-prabhṛti-nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta, refers to the<BR>right to use various trees in the gift village without the king's<BR>permission which was necessary for the ordinary tenants. See<BR>nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep. p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोद्देश<BR>s-oddeśa (EI 12, 29), ‘together with the space above the<BR>surface of the ground’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोद्रङ्ग<BR>s-odraṅga (EI 12, 27, 29), ‘together with the tax called<BR>udraṅga’. Udraṅga is = uddhāra, Tamil uttāra, fixed taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपजातान्यवस्तुक<BR>s-opajāt-ānya-vastuka (EI 26), ‘together with all the<BR>articles that may be produced [in the gift land] other than<BR>those mentioned.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपनिधि<BR>s-opanidhi (EI 12, 27), refers to the freedom of the donee<BR>of the gift land from the obligation of surrendering to the king<BR>any valuables found on it; cf. niṣepa in sa-nidhi-nikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपरिकर<BR>s-oparikara (EI 12, 27, 29), sometimes quoted as sa-pari-<BR>kara; ‘together with minor taxes or taxes realisable from tem-<BR>porary tenants’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपरिकरदण्ड<BR>s-oparikara-daṇḍa (EI 27), ‘together with minor taxes<BR>(or the tax on temporary tenants) and fines.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोर्ध्वाधः<BR>s-ordhv-ādhaḥ (EI 23), same as s-ādha-ūrdhva (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोर्ध्वाधश्<BR>s-ordhv-ādhaś = catur-āghāṭa viśuddha (EI 24), see s-ordhv-<BR>ādhaḥ and catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha. Āghāṭa is often written āghāṭana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोषर<BR>s-oṣara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘together with<BR>barren lands (or saline spots)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोषरावस्करस्थाननिवातलवणाकर<BR>s-oṣar-āvaskara-sthāna-nivāta-lavaṇ-ākara (EI 22), see the<BR>various words as noticed above. Nivāta = āvāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोत्पध्यमानविष्टि<BR>s-otpadhyamāna-viṣṭi (EI 11), same as s-otpadyamāna-<BR>viṣṭika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोत्पध्यमानविष्टिक<BR>s-otpadhyamāna-viṣṭika (EI 23, IA 11), ‘together with the<BR>right to get unpaid labour whenever that may be due from the<BR>tenants’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुकृष्ट<BR>su-kṛṣṭa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘well-cultivated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कदण्डदाण<BR>śulka-daṇḍa-dāṇa-kāruka-maulika-śrotra-nidhi-nikṣepa-jala-<BR>paṣāṇa-tejaḥ-svāmyam = ity-ādy-aṣṭa-bhoga-sahitam, ‘together with<BR>right to the enjoyment of the gift land in eight ways such as<BR>the rights to tolls, fines (or obligations), customs duties, taxes<BR>on artisans, fixed revenue, rent of public buildings, treasure-<BR>trove, occasional finds or deposits, fishing, quarrying and tejaḥ-<BR>svāmya (full authority arising out of ownership).’ See the various<BR>words as noticed above. Cf. Ind. Ep., Vol. XXXII, p. 42.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुपल्लिकापेत<BR>su-pallik-āpeta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139), same as<BR>sa-pallika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णदण्डअहिदण्ड<BR>suvarṇadaṇḍa-ahidaṇḍa-vartmadaṇḍa-vandāpanā-vijayandāpanā-<BR>tṛṇodaka-śāsanārdhika-cara(vara ?)balīvarad-ārthāruvā-pratyarthāruvā-<BR>padātijīvya-ādattā-āturāvaḍḍi-bhaviṣyat-kar-ādi-sahita, refers to the<BR>right of the donee to levy various taxes, the nature of some of<BR>which is uncertain (see the different expressions as noticed above).<BR>These include tax on the goldsmiths and snake-charmers, tolls to<BR>be collected for using the road passing through the gift village for<BR>the transit of articles of merchandise, presents to be made to<BR>the king or landlord on occasions, especially on his return from<BR>a victorious campaign, etc. See hastidaṇḍa-varabalīvarda …<BR>above. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वच्छन्दोपभोगेन्<BR>svacchand-opabhogen = opabhoktum, refers to the right of the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-407" target="_blank">Page-407+ 40</a>]<BR>donee to enjoy the gift land according to his own free will.<BR>Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 399.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमापर्यन्त<BR>sva-sīmā-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as its boundaries’; epi-<BR>thet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणगोचरगोयूतिपर्यन्त<BR>sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-gocara-goyūti-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as the<BR>grass land on the boundaries as well as the pasture lands and<BR>goyūti’. Goyūti may be an enclosure for cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणकाष्ठयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त<BR>sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-yūti-gocara-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as<BR>the yūti (preserve) of grass and wood as well as the pasture<BR>lands on the boundaries’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त<BR>sva-sīmā-tṛṇayūti-gocara-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as the<BR>preserve of grass as well as the pasture lands on the boun-<BR>daries’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणगोयूथीगोचरपर्यन्त<BR>sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-goyūthī-gocara-paryanta, same as sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-<BR>yūti-gocara-paryanta, yūthī being a synonym of yūti (also spelt<BR>pūti), probably meaning ‘a preserve’. See sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-gocara-<BR>goyūti-paryanta, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त<BR>sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-yūti-gocara-paryanta, ‘as far as its boundaries,<BR>the yūti of grass and pasture land’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमावच्छिन्न<BR>sva-sīm-āvacchinna, ‘with its boundaries demarcated’; epi-<BR>thet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभेद्याघाणकमल्लकवुन्दकदण्डदोषप्राप्तादाय<BR>talabhedyā-ghāṇaka-mallaka-vundaka-daṇḍadoṣa-prāpt-ādāya (Ind.<BR>Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 83, text lines 19-20), see the words as<BR>noticed separately above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभेद्यागोवाटिका<BR>talabhedyā-govāṭikā-śākamuṣṭi-tailapalikā-kumbhapūrak-ākāśot-<BR>pati-pātāla-nidhi-nikṣhpa-devāyatan-odyāṅa-taḍāga-vāpī-kup-ādi-sahita<BR>(Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 155).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिलदर्भोदकपवित्रपाणिना<BR>tila-darbh-odaka-pavitra-pāṇinā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p.<BR>135, text line 23), cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणकाष्ठोदकोपेत<BR>tṛṇa-kāṣṭh-odak-opeta (EI 23), ‘together with grass and<BR>fuel and the waters’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणपूति<BR>tṛṇa-pūti (or yūti) gocara-paryanta (EI 12), epithet of<BR>gift land; see sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-yūti (or pūti)-gocara-paryanta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकपूर्वम्<BR>udaka-pūrvam, cf. udak-ātisargeṇa, udakena, tila-darbh-odaka-<BR>pavitra-pāṇinā, kuśa-lalā-pūta-hast-odakena, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकेन<BR>udakena, cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 136-37.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्बलिक<BR>udbalika, ‘free from land tax’; cf. utpratikara. Cf. Prakrit<BR>ubalika (Select Inscriptions, p. 70).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बरभेदः|उम्बरभेद<BR>umbara-bhedaḥ rājapuruṣāṇām = āvāsako jemakaś = ca n =<BR>āsti, ‘there is no entry of royal officers into a house with its door<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-408" target="_blank">Page-408+ 37</a>]<BR>closed (referring especially to the houses of merchants away<BR>from home on business tours abroad) nor should there be<BR>any provision for their accommodation and meals’. See Ep.<BR>Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 232-33.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छकरभरादिविवर्जित<BR>uñcha-kara-bhar-ādi-vivarjita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 89);<BR>see uñcha, etc., as noticed separately above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उर्ध्वाधःसिद्धियुत<BR>urdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi-yuta (IA 18), ‘together with the income<BR>from fruits and roots.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्प्रतिकर<BR>utpratikara (EI 23), same as a-kiñcit-pratikara; cf. udbalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनवाटिकातृणजन्तुगोचरपर्यन्त<BR>vana-vāṭikā-tṛṇa-jantu-gocara-paryanta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIII<BR>p. 229), ‘including forests, gardens, grass fields and pasture<BR>lands for cattle and animals.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुक्षेत्रजलाधारगर्तामार्गसमन्वित<BR>vāstu-kṣetra-jalādhāra-gartā-mārga-samanvita (EI 22), ‘to-<BR>gether with homestead lands, tanks, pits, pathways and roads’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातोडरीय<BR>vātoḍarīya (EI 22), epithet of gift land; probably a cor-<BR>ruption of vāt-ottarīya; cf. sa-bhūta-vāt-ādeya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथादीयमान<BR>yathādīyamāna-bhāgabhogakara-paravaṇikara-kūṭaka-prabhṛti-sa-<BR>mast-ādāya, sometimes with turuṣka-daṇḍa and kumāra-gady-<BR>āṇaka in place of kūṭaka, and hiraṇya, jalakara, gokara, nidhi-<BR>nikṣepa, yamali-kambali, etc., added to the list. Bhāga-bhoga-<BR>kara means ‘taxes in general together with the king's share<BR>of grains and the periodical offerings payable to him.’ For pravaṇi-<BR>kara, kūṭaka and yamalikambali, see the words as noticed above.<BR>Turuṣkadaṇḍa was a tax levied from the Muhammadan sub-<BR>jects or for the defence of the kingdom from Muhammadan<BR>attacks and Kumāra-gadyāṇa may be a tax of one gaḍyāṇa levied<BR>on the occasion of a prince's birth. Hiraṇya is ‘tax in cash’,<BR>jala-kara fishing tax, go-kara grazing tax, nidhi treasure-trove<BR>and nikṣepa valuables found or accumulated on the land. Cf.<BR>Ind. Ep., p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथाप्रदीयमानभागभोगहिरण्यादिक<BR>yathā-pradīyamāna-bhāga-bhoga-hiraṇy-ādika (EI 23), ‘what-<BR>ever is payable as bhāga-bhoga, hiraṇya, etc.’ See the words<BR>as noticed separately; also yathā-samucita-bhāga-bhoga-kara-<BR>hiraṇy-ādi-sarva-rāja-bhāvya-pratyāya (Ind. Ep., p. 394).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथोत्पद्यमानभागभोगादिक<BR>yath-otpadyamāna-bhāga-bhog-ādika (EI 23), ‘with the power<BR>to realise bhāga, bhoga, etc., whenever they become due.’ See<BR>the words as noticed separately above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेकक्काणिक्कै<BR>abhiṣeka-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; presents offered<BR>to a king at the time of his coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यपूजनै<BR>ācārya-pūjanai (SITI), honorarium payable to priests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुतरि<BR>accu-taṟi, accu-ttaṟi (SITI), Tamil; a variety of loom; tax<BR>payable on looms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुवरि<BR>accu-vari (SITI), Tamil; probably, the same as pŏn-vari; duty<BR>payable for minting gold or metal into coins; cf. akkaśālai-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारप्पेरु<BR>adhikāra-ppeṟu (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; probably, presents<BR>offered to an officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारवर्त्तनै<BR>adhikāra-varttanai (SITI), customary payments made to<BR>an officer at stipulated periods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिमैक्काशु<BR>aḍimai-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; fee collected from temple<BR>servants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिक्काशु<BR>aḍi-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax collected from stall-keepers<BR>in markets.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आडिप्पच्चै<BR>āḍi-ppaccai (SITI), Tamil; probably, prerequisites payable<BR>in grain in the month of Āḍi after the harvest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिरैप्पाट्टम्<BR>ādirai-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on cattle; cf. attiṟai-<BR>pāṭṭam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आडुक्कलैप्पुरम्<BR>āḍukkalai-ppuṟam (SITI), Tamil; an endowment for the<BR>kitchen expenses of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कशालैवरि<BR>akkaśālai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax payable to the mint<BR>for minting coins; cf. accu-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलमञ्जि<BR>āḻ-amañji (SII 12), a levy; explained as ‘workmen pressed<BR>into service without wages’ (SITI); Sanskrit viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्लायमान्यम्<BR>aḻḻāya-mānyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; probably, the<BR>right to receive a handful of grain or a prescribed quantity of<BR>an article sold in the market as wages for measuring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आल्नेल्<BR>āḻ-nĕl, āṇĕl (SITI), Tamil; a tax payable in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्पमिरै<BR>alpamirai (SITI), Tamil; a minor tax payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलु|अलुः<BR>aḻu (SITI), Tamil; a variety of market dues; probably, the<BR>same as aḻḻu and aḻḻāya-mānyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलुगल्शरक्कु<BR>aḻugal-śarakku (SITI), Tamil; the right of collecting the<BR>refuse and waste thrown in the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आल्वरि<BR>āḻ-vari (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; poll-tax. See per-kkaḍamai,<BR>per-vāśi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आ<BR>āṉai-ccālai (SITI), Tamil; ‘an elephant stable’; tax<BR>payable for the maintenance of the elephant stable.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आण्डे<BR>āṇḍ-el13uttu-ttevai (SITI), Tamil, a tax of uncertain im-<BR>port.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गाडिक्कूलि<BR>aṅgāḍi-kkūli, aṅgāḍi-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on<BR>bazars, shops, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्नियायवावदण्डइरै<BR>anniyāya-vāva-daṇḍa-iṟai (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; penal tax<BR>imposed on some unauthorised item of occupation or enjoy-<BR>ment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरविनियोगम्<BR>antara-viniyogam (SITI), Sanskrit; individual share to<BR>make up the shortage in the total revenue occasioned by the<BR>grant of exemptions of antar-āyam or uḻ-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरायम्<BR>antar-āyam (SITI), Sanskrit; internal revenue; taxes<BR>levied by a local body; also called uḻ-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरायक्काशु<BR>antarāya-kkāśu; antarāya-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil;<BR>internal taxes; minor taxes like the profession tax, etc., payable<BR>to the village assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवर्त्तनै<BR>anuvarttanai (SITI), a class of contingent dues which come<BR>under the head varttanai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरक्कल्<BR>arakkal (SITI), Tamil; an instalment of land-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरन्दै<BR>arandai (EI 18), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरशुप्पेरु<BR>araśu-ppeṟu (SITI), Tamil; same as mahārāja-prayojana;<BR>probably, fees collected for payment for the performance of<BR>police duties in the rural areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराय्च्चि<BR>ārāycci, kāriyav-ārāycci (SITI), Tamil; cess paid for<BR>the superintendence of transactions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनाभोग<BR>arcanā-bhoga, arcanā-vṛtti (SITI), Sanskrit; land set apart<BR>for meeting the expenses of worship (arcanā) in the village<BR>temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिको<BR>arikol13i, ariśi-ttuṇḍam (SITI), taxes of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिकूलि<BR>arikūli (SITI), Tamil; dues payable in handfuls of the<BR>stalks harvested.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिमुक्कै<BR>arimukkai (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिप्पदिक्कावल्<BR>arippadikkāval (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिशिक्काणम्<BR>ariśi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax for husking paddy into<BR>rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्रङ्करैत्तेवै<BR>āṟṟaṅkarai-ttevai (SITI), Tamil; tax for keeping the river-<BR>bund in repair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्रुक्कुलै<BR>āṟṟu-kkulai (SITI), Tamil; ‘river-bund’; tax to repair<BR>breaches in the river-bund.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्रुक्कालमञ्जि<BR>āṟṟukkāl-amañji (SITI), Tamil; unpaid labour to keep the<BR>channel from the river in good repair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरुन्तोडु<BR>aruntoḍu (SITI), Tamil; ‘eating-plate’; a tax payable<BR>according to the number of eating plates in feeding houses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुविकल्कासु<BR>āśuvikaḻ-kāsu, āśuva-kkāśu, āśuva-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil;<BR>tax payable by the Ājīvakas or for maintaining Ājīvaka monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आट्चिप्पाट्टम्<BR>āṭci-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; probably, a succession tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतीरै<BR>ātīrai (SITI), Tamil; probably, the expenses for the ārdrā<BR>festival in the month of Mārgal13i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अटियुरै<BR>aṭiyuṟai (SITI), Tamil; offerings made at the feet of a<BR>high personage; written differently as aḍiyiṟai, aḍiyaṟai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आट्टैक्कानिक्कै<BR>āṭṭai-kkānikkai (SITI), Tamil; annual contribution or<BR>presents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्तिरैप्पाट्टम्<BR>attiṟai-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on cattle; cf.<BR>ādiraipāṭṭam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टणैक्काल्<BR>aṭṭaṇaikkāl (SITI), Tamil; a kind of stand or pedestal<BR>(probably of eight legs).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आट्टुक्कीरै<BR>āṭṭukk-īṟai, āṭṭiṟai (SITI) Tamil; tax on sheep; also<BR>called āṭṭu-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टुक्किरै<BR>aṭṭukkiṟai (SITI), Tamil; tax on charities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवणम्<BR>āvaṇam (SITI), Tamil a document; generally, a sale-<BR>deed; also called villaiy-āvaṇam; cf. āvaṇa-kkaḻari (SITI),<BR>place where documents like the sale-deeds, etc., are registered; a<BR>registration office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसरवर्त्तनै<BR>avasara-varttanai (SITI), presents payable to an Avasara,<BR>an officer of the royal household having the duty of bringing to<BR>the notice of the king anything that demanded his immediate<BR>attention.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयम्<BR>āyam (SITI); ‘income’; tax in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बण्णिगितेरे<BR>baṇṇigitĕre, Kannaḍa; a kind of levy (A. R. Ep., 1958-59,<BR>p. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिल्कोडे<BR>bilkoḍĕ (EI 28), Kannaḍa; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिराड<BR>birāḍa (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बण्णिगे<BR>baṇṇigĕ (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भत्ताय<BR>bhatt-āya (SII 11-1), same as Sanskrit bhakt-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिट्टि<BR>biṭṭi (SII 11-1), same as Sanskrit viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बित्तुकट्टे<BR>bittu-kaṭṭĕ, Kannaḍa; same as bittu-vaṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बित्तुवट्ट<BR>bittu-vaṭṭa, a portion of the produce from the land irriga-<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-412" target="_blank">Page-412+ 40</a>]<BR>ted by a tank, granted to a person who excavated or repaired<BR>the tank (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 10).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मणराशक्काणम्<BR>brāhmaṇa-rāśa(rāja)-kkāṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax<BR>payable by the Brāhmaṇa (purohita) to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रकाणिक्कै<BR>cakra-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; profession-tax<BR>paid by the potters; also called tirigai-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डकाणम्<BR>daṇḍa-kāṇam (SII 13), fines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशबन्ध|दशबन्धः<BR>daśabandha (SITI), Sanskrit; tax or cess levied to keep<BR>the sources of water supply, like the tank, etc., in good repair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यादाय<BR>dhāny-ādāya (SITI), Sanskrit; tax payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यवर्ग<BR>dhānya-varga, cf. tāniya-varakkam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरडु<BR>eraḍu dogarāca-ppaṇṇu (EI 30), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एच्चोरु<BR>eccoṟu (SII 13), a tax or the obligation of free feeding.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडैवरि<BR>eḍai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on weights.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडुत्तुक्कोट्टै<BR>eḍuttu-kkoṭṭai (SITI), Tamil; a tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडुत्तुक्कोट्टि<BR>eḍuttukkoṭṭi (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एलवै<BR>elavai (SITI), also spelt ĕlavai; Tamil; death-duty; fee for<BR>crematorium.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ए<BR>ĕl13uttu-viniyogam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; dues payable as<BR>ĕl13uttu for the village-accountant to be apportioned among the<BR>villagers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एणिक्काणम्<BR>eṇi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; ladder tax evidently levied<BR>on toddy-drawers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एण्णेय्<BR>ĕṇṇĕy (SITI), Tamil; tax levied on the oil-trade; obligation<BR>for the supply of oil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरडुबिल्कोदे<BR>eraḍu-bilkodĕ (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिआयम्<BR>eri-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; income from fishing in<BR>the tank, etc.; amount payable by the owners of the fields<BR>irrigated by the tank for its upkeep.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिईवु<BR>eri-īvu (SITI), Tamil; share in the expenses of the main-<BR>tenance of the tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एर्क्कडमै<BR>er-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax on ploughs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एर्प्पोन्<BR>er-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax to be paid in cash for each<BR>plough; also called er-kkaṇikkai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरुमैप्पोन्<BR>erumai-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax payable on buffaloes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिक्काडि<BR>erikkāḍi (SII 12), tank cess of one kāḍi of paddy per field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिमीन्पाट्टम्<BR>eri-mīṉ-pāṭṭam (SII 12), a tax; income from fish in the tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेज्जुङ्क<BR>hĕjjuṅka, same as pĕrjuṅka, Kannaḍa; name of tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडङ्गैवरि<BR>iḍaṅgai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax paid by the members of<BR>the iḍaṅgai community or the left-hand classes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडैप्पाट्टम्<BR>iḍai-ppāṭṭam, also called iḍai-ppūṭci (SITI), Tanmil; tax<BR>on herdsmen or cattle-breeders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडैत्तुरै<BR>iḍaittuṟai, also spelt iḍatoṟai (SITI), Tamil; a tax of un-<BR>certain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडैयर्वरि<BR>iḍaiyar-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on shepherds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इलैवाणियप्पाट्टम्<BR>ilaivāṇiya-ppāṭṭam (SITI), tax on the sellers of betel-leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडतोरै<BR>iḍatoṟai, see iḍaittuṟai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इलक्कुलम्<BR>ilakkulam (SII 13), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इळम्पुञ्जै<BR>iḻam-puñjai, īḻam-puṭci (SITI), Tamil; tax for toddy-<BR>drawing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इलाञ्जनैप्पेरु<BR>ilāñjanai-ppeṟu, also called lāñjinai-ppeṟu, lāñjanai-ppeṟu<BR>(SITI), Tamil; fee for affixing the royal seal; ilāñjanai = Sans-<BR>krit lāñchana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इल्वरि<BR>ilvari (SITI), Tamil; house-tax; cf. manai-ppaṇam, manav-iṟai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इनवरि<BR>inavari (SII 12), inavari-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; communal tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरै<BR>iṟai (SII 13; SITI), Tamil; a general term denoting<BR>revenue income and the taxes to be paid to government; land tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैद्रव्यम्<BR>iṟai-dravyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; explained as a<BR>lump sum paid in lieu of land tax; amount payable in com-<BR>mutation of the taxes payable on landed property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैकावल्<BR>iṟai-kāval (SITI), Tamil; amount of deposit which yielded<BR>interest per annum equal to the tax due on the land; sometimes<BR>regarded as a tax for police duties.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैयिलिमुदल्<BR>iṟaiyili-mudal (SII 13), same as iṟai-dravyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैयिलिक्काशु<BR>iṟaiyili-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; amount paid for compound-<BR>ing taxes in order to make the land tax-free; also regarded as<BR>the amount payable to meet the shortage in the revenue occa-<BR>sioned by the grant of exemption from tax on certain lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईरङ्कोल्लि<BR>īraṅkolli, īraṅkoḻḻi (SITI), Tamil; ‘a washerman’; tax<BR>payable by washermen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरवु<BR>iravu (EI 30), Tamil; royal dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरुप्पुक्कट्टि<BR>iruppu-kkaṭṭi (SITI), Tamil; probably, the cake of the<BR>Mahua seeds after the extraction of oil, largely used as soap;<BR>tax for the manufacture and sale of such cakes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इशैक्किडाय्<BR>iśai-kkiḍāy (SITI), Tamil; ‘beautiful ram’; dues to be<BR>paid for the ram kept for show; cf. al13ag-erudu-kkāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोडि<BR>joḍi, also spelt śoḍi (SITI), Tamil; name of a small quit-<BR>rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडैवडैक्काय्<BR>koḍai-vaḍaikkāy (SITI), Tamil; tax on arecanuts brought<BR>for sale.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडमै<BR>kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; revenue, tax to be paid to the<BR>government in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कदिर्क्काणम्<BR>kadir-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax paid in sheaves of corn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काडुकावल्<BR>kāḍu-kāval (SITI), Tamil; tax for the preservation and<BR>maintenance of forests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक्कमिकुदि<BR>kaṇakka-mikudi (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्लवलिक<BR>kaḻḻavalika (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानिक<BR>kānika, Kannaḍa; also called kāṇika-kanĕ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनिकेकप्प<BR>kanikĕ-kappa, kappa-kānikĕ, etc.; customary presents;<BR>presents from inferior to superior (EI 33).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिक्कै<BR>kāṇikkai (EI 17, 21; SITI), Tamil; presents or customary<BR>payment as offerings to the king and other high officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्णालक्काणम्<BR>kaṇṇāla-kkāṇam (SII 13; EI 28), marriage fee; collected<BR>by the village assembly; same as vivāha-ppaṇam; cf. ugappār-pŏn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः<BR>kaṉṉār-iṟai (SITI), Tamil; profession tax payable by a<BR>brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानुक<BR>kānuka (CITD), same as kāṇika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कप्प<BR>kappa (EI 33), Kannaḍa; tolls;<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिक्कजोडि<BR>karaṇikka-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), quit-rent of the Karaṇam<BR>or Karṇam (village-accountant or Paṭvārī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काराण्मै<BR>kārāṇmai (SITI), Tamil; a tenure with the hereditary<BR>right of enjoyment; cultivation right; tax for the same; also<BR>known as kārāṇkiḻamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारियप्पेरु<BR>kāriya-ppeṟu (SITI), Tamil; probably, the same as<BR>kāriya-vārāycci, ārāycci.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारियवाराय्च्चि<BR>kāriya-vārāycci (SITI), Tamil; cess paid for the superin-<BR>tendence of transactions; same as ārāycci.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्कडमै<BR>kāṟ-kaḍamai (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्प्पूरविलै<BR>karppūra-vilai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; sale-price paid<BR>for temple lands; price paid for cultivation rights of temple<BR>lands and in commutation of the taxes thereon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिगैक्काशु<BR>kārttigai-kkāśu, kārttigai-kkāṇi, kārttigai-ppaccai, kārttigaiy-ariśi<BR> (SITI), Tamil; payments in kind in the month of Kārtti-<BR>gai, i. e. during the harvest; cf. āḍi-ppaccai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुविपणम्<BR>karuvi-paṇam, karivi-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on the<BR>implements in cash, probably paid by the barbers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुवूलवरि<BR>karuvūla-vari (SITI), Tamil; fee for the safe-custody of<BR>precious articles in the treasury; or fee for the watch of<BR>the treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशायम्<BR>kāś-āyam (SITI), kāśu-āyam; Tamil-Sanskrit; tax and<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-415" target="_blank">Page-415+ 40</a>]<BR>dues payable in coin; also called kāśāya-vargam, kāśu-vargam and<BR>kāśu-kaḍamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशुकडमै<BR>kāśu-kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काट्चि<BR>kāṭci (SITI), Tamil; presents offered to a highly superior<BR>person at the time of meeting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काट्चियेरदुक्काशु<BR>kāṭciy-eradu-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on bulls<BR>kept for show.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काट्टाल्काशु<BR>kāṭṭāḻ-kāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टणम्<BR>kaṭṭaṇam (SITI), Tamil; periodical presents made to<BR>superiors by their subordinates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टायम्<BR>kaṭṭ-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; consolidated amount<BR>payable for the minor taxes; also written as kaṇḍ-āyam; some-<BR>times taken as the compulsory payment of certain dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कत्तिगैप्पच्चै<BR>kattigai-ppaccai (SII 12), see kārtigai-kkāśu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कत्तिक्काणम्<BR>katti-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on weapons like sword,<BR>etc., or tax on the manufacture of swords or arms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टुक्कुत्तगै<BR>kaṭṭu-kkuttagai (SITI), Tamil; rent fixed at the time of<BR>farming out the land; payment of consolidated rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टुमुक्कै<BR>kaṭṭumukkai (SITI), Tamil; ‘three handfuls in the bundle’;<BR>a contribution of three handfuls for every bundle of paddy stalks<BR>harvested, which were payable to the temples; cf. arimukkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कावल्पेरु<BR>kāval-peṟu (SII 12), name of a tax; cf. kāval-kāni, the right<BR>to guard temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कि<BR>kil13-iṟai (SITI; SII 12), Tamil; minor taxes, or tax<BR>fixed at a lower rate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

की<BR>kīl13-iṟai-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; small cesses and taxes like<BR>mīn-pāṭṭam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्रुवरि<BR>kīṟṟu-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on thatched sheds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किरुकुल<BR>kirukula (SITI), Tamil; commercial tax or tolls on retail<BR>articles; also called kirukūla-viśeṣam; cf. kūlam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडिक्कडमि<BR>kŏḍi-kkaḍami (SITI), Tamil; explained as a tax for the<BR>cultivation of the medicinal plant kŏḍi-veli, otherwise known as<BR>citra-mūlam; probably, the same as kodi-kkaḍamai, tax on new<BR>cloth; cf. tiru-ppudiyidu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्कूलि<BR>kol-kūli (SITI), Tamil; tax for measuring or weighing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्निरैकूलि<BR>kol-niṟai-kūli (SITI), Tamil; tax on articles measured<BR>by weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्मुरैप्पाडु<BR>kŏḻmuṟai-ppāḍu (SITI), Tamil; customary dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलु<BR>kŏḻu (SITI), Tamil; tax on ploughshares.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्वरि<BR>kŏḻvari (SITI), Tamil; tax in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोमुरै<BR>ko-muṟai (SITI), Tamil; revenue due to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोपदवारम्<BR>ko-pada-vāram (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax due to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टैक्कूलि<BR>koṭṭai-kkūli (SITI); ‘wages on nuts’; probably, charges<BR>for the upkeep of forts; cf. koṭṭai-magamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टैमगमै<BR>koṭṭai-magamai (SITI), Tamil; tax for the maintenance of<BR>forts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोयिल्वाशि<BR>koyil-vāśi (SITI), Tamil; minor taxes payable to the<BR>palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुडिक्काणम्<BR>kuḍi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; fee paid by the tenants; pro-<BR>bably, the same as kuḍi-kkāśu and kuḍi-ppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुडिमै<BR>kuḍimai (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; taxes in general (with the<BR>exception of land revenue) payable to the state for the protec-<BR>tion of the civil rights it offers; tenancy tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैमार्रु<BR>kudirai-māṟṟu (SITI), Tamil; tax on horses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैप्पन्दि<BR>kudirai-ppandi (SITI), Tamil; ‘a stable’; tax for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैवरि<BR>kudirai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on horses; also known<BR>as kudirai-māṟṟu, kudiraiv-ilāḍam; probably the same as kudirai-<BR>ppandi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैविलाडम्<BR>kudiraiv-ilāḍam (SITI), Tamil; ‘horse-shoe’; fee for<BR>shoeing horses; probably connected with kudirai-ppandi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवडै<BR>kuḻavaḍai (EI 17), tax for the enjoyment of the tank<BR>and its income.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूलम्<BR>kūlam (SITI), Tamil; tax on grains and pulses; cf.<BR>kirukulam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमरकच्चाणम्<BR>kumara-kaccāṇam (SITI), Tamil; explained as a tax pay-<BR>able in coin for the maintenance of the temple of Kumāra or<BR>Subrahamaṇya; but same as kumāra-gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूर्ररिशि<BR>kūṟṟariśi (SITI), Tamil; obligation of husking paddy be-<BR>longing to the temple into rice and the charges to be met for the<BR>same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुर्रुनेल्<BR>kuṟṟu-nĕl, kūṟṟu-nĕllu (SITI), Tamil; tax for husking<BR>paddy payable to king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशक्काणम्<BR>kuśa-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on potters; also known<BR>as tirigaiāyam, śakkara-kkāṇikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लञ्जनैप्पेरु<BR>lañjanai-pperu, lañjinai-ppeṟu, see ilañjanai-ppeṟu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडैक्कूलि<BR>māḍai-kkūli (SITI), Tamil; tax for minting gold into coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मादाप्पडि<BR>mādā-ppaḍi (SITI), Tamil; allowances payable monthly;<BR>also called mādārikka, mādan and mādārikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडुकाणिक्कै<BR>māḍu-kāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; obligation of supplying<BR>draught cattle to the visiting nobles by the tenants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मगमै<BR>magamai, maganmai, magaṇamai (SITI), Tamil; small<BR>portion of the income or of the value of articles of merchandise<BR>collected as voluntary contribution by the merchants from among<BR>themselves for the maintenance of temples, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मगन्मै<BR>maganmai (SITI), Tamil; poll-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मक्कल्पेरु<BR>makkaḻ-peṟu (SITI), Tamil; one's obligations as a citizen;<BR>probably, dues payable to a temple, or poll-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लायिमघमै<BR>mallāyi-maghamai (SITI), Tamil; probably a customary<BR>collection in the market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मामगम्<BR>māmagam (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in cash probably<BR>for the great Māgha (Mahāmāgha) festival; or, a mistake for<BR>mārgam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनैमेय्प्पान्कोल्लुमिरै<BR>manai-meyppān-koḻḻum-iṟai, tax for the supervisor of houses<BR>or the building-supervisor; cf. meyppān (SITI), Tamil; ‘shep-<BR>herd; grazier;’ a supervisor; probably related to kaṇkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनैप्पणम्<BR>manai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; house tax; also called manai-<BR>vari. Cf. ilvari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः<BR>maṉaiy-iṟai (SITI), Tamil; house-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्दैप्पणम्<BR>mandai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on cattle grazing in<BR>the village common.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलमुदन्मैप्पेरु<BR>maṇḍala-mudanmai-ppeṟu (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; fee for<BR>presents offered to the rulers of the maṇḍala or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्मदिल्<BR>maṇ-madil (SITI), Tamil; ‘high wall or rampart made<BR>of mud’; tax for the erection and upkeep of such a wall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पदक्कु<BR>māppadakku (SITI), Tamil; payment at the rate of one<BR>padakku or two kuruṇi for every mā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पणम्<BR>māppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; a tax payable at the rate of<BR>one paṇam for every mā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पट्टडै<BR>māppaṭṭaḍai (SITI), Tamil; tax probably for the penning<BR>of cattle; may also be mara-ppaṭṭaḍai, ‘a timber depot’; tax<BR>payable for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरक्कडमै<BR>mara-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable for trees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरमञ्जाडि<BR>mara-mañjāḍi (SITI), Tamil; tax of one mañjāḍi for every<BR>tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गादायम्<BR>mārg-ādāyam (SITI), Sanskrit; tolls on the articles in transit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरियादि<BR>mariyādi (SITI), Tamil; customary dues; also spelt mar-<BR>jādi, mariśādi, maruśādi, etc., and used in the sense of manner,<BR>way, extent, limit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माट्टुक्करै<BR>māṭṭukkaṟai (SITI), Tamil; probably, a tax on cattle<BR>(cows and buffaloes).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माविन्दक्कडमै<BR>māvinda-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेलडि<BR>melaḍi (SITI), Tamil; taxes paid in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्विट्टियवड्दारवुल<BR>melviṭṭiya-vaḍdāravuḻa, cf. vaḍḍāravuḻa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्वेट्टप्पेरु<BR>mel-vĕṭṭa-pperu (SITI), land set apart for meeting expenses<BR>of public works (vĕṭṭi).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मे<BR>meṉi-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; poll-tax; tax on individuals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरै<BR>merai (SITI), Tamil; portion of the crop given at the<BR>threshing floor to certain village officers and servants as per-<BR>quisite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेर्पाडिकावल्<BR>mer-pāḍi-kāval (SITI), Tamil; policing duty over the nāḍu.<BR>See nāḍu-kāval.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेट्टुनिलम्<BR>meṭṭu-nilam (SITI), Tamil; ‘high land’; tax payable for<BR>the cultivation of such land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिलगुतरगु<BR>miḻagu-taragu (SITI), Tamil; brokerage on pepper trade.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोनम्पाट्टम्<BR>monampāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; a tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदर्रिरमन्<BR>mudaṟṟiraman, mudal-tiramam (SITI), Tamil; tax (payable<BR>in cash) of uncertain import; tiramam is the coin called dramma<BR>(from Greek drachma).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुल्लडिशिन्नम्<BR>muḻḻaḍiśinnam (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a tax of uncertain<BR>import; probably, payment for clue in detection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूङ्गिल्वरि<BR>mūṅgil-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on bamboos.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुत्तावणम्<BR>muttāvaṇam (SITI), Tamil; a tax probably on the sale<BR>of pearls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुकावल्<BR>nāḍu-kāval (SITI), Tamil; ‘policing duty of the nāḍu’;<BR>tax payable by the residents in the division for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुतलैयारिक्कम्<BR>nāḍu-talaiyārikkam (SITI), Tamil; police-tax of the nāḍu;<BR>same as nāḍu-kāval.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्किडा<BR>nal-kiḍā, naṟ-kiḍā (SITI), Tamil; cess for the upkeep of<BR>the show-ram; or, tax for show-rams.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्लेरुदु<BR>nall-ĕrudu (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; cess for the maintenance<BR>of a model bull, which was probably also used for breeding pur-<BR>poses; cf. al13agerudu-kkāśu, kāṭci-ĕrudu-kkāśu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्लेरुमै<BR>nall-erumai (SITI), tax for the maintenance of specimen<BR>buffaloes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नर्किडा<BR>naṟ-kiḍā (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टुक्कणक्कुवरि<BR>nāṭṭu-kkaṇakku-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax payable for the<BR>maintenance of the revenue accounts of the nāḍu or the country<BR>as a whole.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाटुक्काणिक्कै<BR>nāṭu-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; presents payable to or by<BR>the assembly of the nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टुपाति<BR>nāṭṭupāti (SITI), Tamil; nāḍu-upādi; the obligations to<BR>be met and taxes payable to the local assembly of the nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टुविनियोगम्<BR>nāṭṭu-viniyogam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; individual share<BR>payable to make up the shortage in the total revenue by the<BR>grant of exemptions by the assembly of the nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेल्लायम्<BR>nĕll-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax payable in paddy;<BR>also known as nĕṟ-kaḍamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेय्<BR>nĕy (SITI), Tamil; tax on the traders in ghee; same as<BR>nĕy-vilai; cf. also eṇṇĕy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निलत्तिरप्पुकडमै<BR>nilattiṟappu-kaḍamai (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीराणिक्कवरि<BR>nīrāṇikka-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax for the supervision of<BR>the regulation of water supply in a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीर्क्काणम्<BR>nīr-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; water-cess; also known as<BR>nīr-vilai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीर्निलैक्काशु<BR>nīr-nilai-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tank-cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरुणिसुङ्क<BR>niruṇi-suṅka (SII 11-1), water tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीर्विलै<BR>nīr-vilai (SITI), Tamil; water-cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नूलायम्<BR>nūl-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on cotton thread<BR>for weaving cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओलिवण्णार्पारै<BR>oḻi-vaṇṇāṟ-pāṟai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable by the washer-<BR>man calculated on the number of washing stones.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पच्चैप्पणम्<BR>paccai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; payment in cash towards<BR>the obligation of paccai payable in kind; also referred to as<BR>paccai-ppāṭṭam. Cf. Kārttigai-paccai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडैप्पणम्<BR>paḍai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax for the main-<BR>tenance of an army unit or fee from the army; also known as<BR>paḍai-kkāṇikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडन्क<BR>paḍan-kal13i (SITI), Tamil; an obligation of uncertain<BR>import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडवरि<BR>pāḍavari (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on metallic mir-<BR>rors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदवारम्<BR>padavāram, also spelt paduvāram (SITI), Tamil; fee pay-<BR>able for exchanging landed property; transfer fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडिक्कावल्<BR>pāḍikkāval (SITI), Tamil; ‘watch or the police duties<BR>of the village’; contribution for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुवारम्<BR>paduvāram, cf. padavāram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प|पं|पः<BR>paḻanel (SII 13), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिक्कप्पाट्टम्<BR>pālikka-ppāṭṭam (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणवर्गम्<BR>paṇa-vargam (SITI), Sanskrit; class of taxes payable in<BR>cash; same as kāśāya-vargam; cf. paṇam, coin, money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणवाशि<BR>paṇa-vāśi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; discount payable for<BR>the exchange of coins; amount payable to make up the wear<BR>in the coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवारवूरिडुवरि<BR>pañca-vārav-ūr-iḍu-vari (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; levied by<BR>the pañca-vāriyam (the five committees) of the local assembly (ūr).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चुप्पीलि<BR>pañcu-ppīli (SITI EI 24), Tamil; tax on cotton; also<BR>referred to as pāñjupili.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्डवेट्टि<BR>paṇḍa-vĕṭṭi (SITI), Tamil; a variety of vĕṭṭi, probably<BR>for the temple lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डिवरि<BR>pāṇḍivari (SITI), Tamil; probably tax on carts drawn<BR>by bulls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणिक्कोत्तु<BR>paṇi-kkŏttu (SITI), Tamil; ‘village servants’; cess collec-<BR>ted for their maintenance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्कुरुणि<BR>paṇ-kuṟuṇi (SITI), Tamil; cess payable at the rate of one<BR>kuṟuṇi of the produce for each field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नाय<BR>pannāya (IE 8-5; EI 27), Kannaḍa; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारैक्काणम्<BR>pāṟai-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on washing stone pay-<BR>able by washermen; sometimes explained as the tax on quarries.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परैत्तरि<BR>paṟai-ttaṟi (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a variety of hand-<BR>loom; the tax for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परैयिरै<BR>paṟaiy-iṟai (SITI), Tamil; a tax [payable in cash] pro-<BR>bably for tomtoms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशानम्<BR>paśānam (EI 23), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशिप्पाट्टम्<BR>pāśi-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on fishing; same as<BR>mīn-pāṭṭam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टाडैआयम्<BR>paṭṭāḍai-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on silk cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टाडैनूलायम्<BR>paṭṭāḍai-nūl-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on silk<BR>thread used for weaving cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टडैवरि<BR>paṭṭaḍai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax probably for the use<BR>of the threshing floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टम्<BR>pāṭṭam (SITI EI 21), Tamil; tax or rent; payable pro-<BR>bably for an industry or a profession.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टनेल्<BR>pāṭṭa-nĕl (SITI), Tamil; paddy to be paid by the tenant<BR>to the landlord as per terms of lease.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टयक्काणिक्कै<BR>paṭṭaya-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; fee for the issue of royal<BR>charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिक्काडि<BR>paṭṭi-kkāḍi (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in grain at the<BR>rate of one kāḍi for each paṭṭi of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिक्काल्<BR>paṭṭi-kkāl (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in cash at the<BR>rate of one fourth (probably of paṇam) for each paṭṭi of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिगैक्काणम्<BR>paṭṭigai-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; obligation to pay at the<BR>rate of one kāṇam for each paṭṭi of land; probably, the same as<BR>paṭṭaya-kkāṇikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिप्पोन्<BR>paṭṭi-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टित्तण्डम्<BR>paṭṭi-ttaṇḍam (SITI), Tamil; probably, punitive tax of a<BR>village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावै<BR>pāvai (EI 8-5), similar to Persian nazarāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेज्जुङ्क<BR>pĕjjuṅka (EI 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of tax; also spelt<BR>pĕrjuṅka, pĕrujuṇka, hĕjjuṅka; probably derived from piriya-<BR>suṅka = Sanskrit bṛhac-chulka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्जुङ्क<BR>pĕrjuṅka, cf. pĕjjuñka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्क्कडमै<BR>pĕr-kkaḍamai (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; explained as<BR>poll tax, the same as āḻvari; (also called pervāśi); but may be a<BR>payment to be made on the occasion of the naming ceremony<BR>of a child.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुजुङ्क<BR>pĕrujuṅka, cf. pĕjjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुम्पाडिकावल्<BR>perum-pāḍi-kāval (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; police duties of<BR>a larger area, as distinct from the śiṟu-pāḍi-kāval for the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिदाना<BR>pidā-nāl13i (EI 28), Tamil; same as pudā-nāl13i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो<BR>pŏṉ-vari (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रचण्डकाणिक्कै<BR>pracaṇḍa-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; a variety of<BR>military cess; this is found mentioned along with other military<BR>cessess like paḍai-ppaṇam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानिजोडि<BR>pradhāni-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), the chief minister's quit-rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुडान<BR>puḍā-nal13i (SITI), Tamil; probably, a local cess on each<BR>door or gate or house; also, mentioned as pidā-nāl13i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुलवरि<BR>pulavari (SITI), Tamil; ‘tax on a pulam (piece of land)’;<BR>probably to be corrected as pulvari meaning ‘tax on grass.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुल्लवरि<BR>pullavari (SITI), tax payable for grazing cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुल्लन्दि<BR>pullandi (SITI), Tamil; an obligation probably con-<BR>nected with the pasture land in the form of fine on stray cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पु<BR>pul13ugu-kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; fee for meeting the ex-<BR>penses of coating the image of gods with civet; also known as<BR>pul13uguvari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरक्कडमै<BR>puṟa-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; external taxes, i. e., taxes<BR>and fees payable to the state.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवायम्<BR>puṟav-āyam (SITI), Tamil; revenue from external sour-<BR>ces, collected mainly in cash.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवेट्टि<BR>puṟavĕṭṭi (SITI), Tamil; a variety of vĕṭṭi for public<BR>work, probably outside the area in question.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवु<BR>puravu (SITI), Tamil; land revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवुनेल्<BR>puravu-nĕl (SITI), Tamil; revenue paid in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवुपोन्<BR>puravu-pŏn (SITI), Tamil; revenue paid in gold.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्करक्काणिक्कै<BR>śakkara-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; tax on potters; also<BR>known as tirigai-āyam; cf. kuśa-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शण्डालप्पेरु<BR>śaṇḍāla-ppeṟu (SITI), Tamil; a local cess or tax collec-<BR>ted from or for the Caṇḍālas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहप्पेरु<BR>sandhivigraha-ppeṟu (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; fee payable<BR>to the village madhyastha; also a fee payable to the document<BR>writers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शट्टुवरि<BR>śaṭṭu-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax for the grazing ground in<BR>the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शवैक्कडमै<BR>śavai-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; taxes payable to the<BR>sabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक्कायम्<BR>śekk-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on oil-presses;<BR>also called śekk-iṟai and śekku-kkaḍamai (SII 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक्कुकडमै<BR>śekku-kaḍamai (SII 12), same as śekk-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक्कुम<BR>śekku-maṉṟāḍi (SITI), Tamil; a tax or cess; probably.<BR>related to śekku.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेङ्कोडिक्काणम्<BR>seṅkŏḍi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; explained as ‘the tax on<BR>the cultivation of the medicinal plant known variously as<BR>śeṅgŏḍi, kŏḍiveli and citramūlam’; see also kŏḍi-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टियार्मगमै<BR>śeṭṭiyār-magamai (SITI), Tamil; voluntary contribution<BR>(magamai) of the merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टियिरै<BR>śeṭṭiy-iṟai (SITI), Tamil; tax on merchants; also known<BR>as śeṭṭ-iṟai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेवकक्काशु<BR>śevaka-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; fee for the maintenance of<BR>the soldiers; or, tax levied on the soldier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्कुडिमै<BR>śil-kuḍimai (SITI), minor taxes and cesses payable to<BR>the local authority.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्लन्तरायम्<BR>śill-antar-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; minor taxes which<BR>fall in the group of antar-āyam or uḻ-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलायम्<BR>śil-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; same as śill-irai, śil-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्लिरै<BR>śill-iṟai (SITI), Tamil; same as sil-āyam, śil-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्वरि<BR>śil-vari (SITI; EI 27), Tamil; minor taxes; same as<BR>śil-āyam, śil-iṟai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिर्रायम्<BR>śiṟṟ-āyam (SITI), Tamil; minor taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरुप्पाडिकावल्<BR>śiṟu-ppāḍi-kāval (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरुशुङ्गम्<BR>śiru-śuṅgam (SITI), Tamil; minor tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोडि<BR>śoḍi, see joḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शो<BR>śŏṉa-vari (SITI), Tamil; same as pŏn-vari; explained as<BR>‘tax payable in gold’; but may be professional tax payable by<BR>the goldsmiths; cf. suvarṇa-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुडुकाट्टुप्पाट्टम्<BR>śuḍu-kāṭṭu-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; fee payable by a<BR>prostitute, especially those accompanying the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूलवरि<BR>śūla-vari (EI 25; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; a tax payable<BR>for the unkeep probably of a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्क<BR>suṅka (EI 12), same as Sanskrit śulka, tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुर्रायक्काशु<BR>śuṟṟ-āya-kkāśu (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णादायम्<BR>svarṇ-ādāyam (SITI), Sanskrit; revenue in gold; taxes<BR>payable in coin; or, profession tax payable by the goldsmiths.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शडक्कडमै<BR>śaḍa-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax on shepherds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैक्काणम्<BR>taḻai-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; fee or tax on the taḻai or<BR>foot-binding used by toddy-tappers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैयारिक्कम्<BR>talaiyārikkam (SITI), Tamil; tax payable for the main-<BR>tenance of the village watchman; same as talaiyāri-kkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डलिर्कडमै<BR>taṇḍaliṟ-kaḍamai, taṇḍaṟ-kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; fee pay-<BR>able for the maintenance of tax-collectors; or, tax on bill-<BR>collectors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डक्काणम्<BR>taṇḍa-kkāṇam, laṇḍa-kkuṟam, etc. (SITI), in which taṇḍa<BR>is punitive tax and kuṟṟam fines for crimes committed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त|तं|तः<BR>taṉiyāḻ (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तानियवरक्कम्<BR>tāniya-varakkam, dhānya-varga (SITI), Sanskrit; ‘the grain<BR>group’; class of taxes payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्णीर्क्काणम्<BR>taṇṇīr-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; water-cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरगिपाट्टम्<BR>taragi-pāṭṭam (SII 12), brokerage fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरविडुनेल्<BR>tarav-iḍu-nĕl (SITI), Tamil; paddy given in lieu of wages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवु<BR>taravu (SITI), Tamil; ‘that which has been given’; collec-<BR>tion of debt or tax on pressure; also a dun; also used in the<BR>sense of ‘order or instruction’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवुकोल्लुदल्<BR>taravu-kŏḻḻudal (SITI), Tamil; ‘to obtain a receipt for<BR>anything given’; collection of tax exercising pressure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिअक्कवे<BR>taṟi-akkave (SII 13), same as taṟi-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिइरै<BR>taṟi-irai (SII 12, 13), same as taṟi-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक्कडमै<BR>taṟi-kkaḍamai (SII 12), same as taṟi-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक्कुरै<BR>taṟi-kkuṟai (SITI), same as taṟi-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिप्पुडवै<BR>taṟi-ppuḍavai (SITI), Tamil; tax on looms payable in the<BR>shape of cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरितलै<BR>taṟi-taḻai (SITI), Tamil; tax on looms; probably, the<BR>same as taṟi-kkaḍamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टार्पाट्टम्<BR>taṭṭār-pāṭṭam, taṭṭāra-ppāṭṭam (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; tax<BR>on goldsmiths. Cf. suvarṇa-daṇḍa noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टोलि<BR>taṭṭ-ŏli (SITI), Tamil; mentioned along with taṭṭār-<BR>pāṭṭam; probably, tax on the smiths or the workshop of the<BR>artisans like the blacksmiths.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टुक्काणम्<BR>taṭṭu-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; same as taṭṭār-pāṭṭam; ‘fee<BR>for hammering’; probably also the same as taṭṭukk-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेवै<BR>tevai (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिङ्गल्काशु<BR>tiṅgaḻ-kāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax payable every month; cf.<BR>tiṅgaṭ-coṟu, tiṅgaḻ-nĕy, tiṅgaḻ-mogam, etc. Cf. also māda-ppaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरिगैआयम्<BR>tirigai-āyam (SITI), tax payable by the potter for his trade;<BR>cf. tirigai, a potter's wheel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरुमुगक्काणम्<BR>tiru-muga-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; expenses as wages, etc.,<BR>payable to the person who brings the tiru-mugam (royal order)<BR>to a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिवु<BR>tivul13-desa (EI 30), Tamil; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीयेरिशोरु<BR>tīyeṟi-śoṟu (SII 13), Tamil; literally, ‘offering in fire’;<BR>supposed to be the name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोलोट्टु<BR>tol-ŏṭṭu (SITI), Tamil; a fee probably connected with<BR>hides and skins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोनिक्कडमै<BR>loni-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax on boats.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोरणक्काणिक्कै<BR>toraṇa-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; presents for decorating<BR>the village with arches, etc.; or tax on gates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोट्टप्पुरवु<BR>toṭṭa-ppuravu (SITI), Tamil; tax on garden lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलाक्कूलि<BR>tulā-kkūli (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; fee for weighing in<BR>balance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तूशकत्तरि<BR>tūśaka-ttaṟi (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on looms<BR>weaving tent-materials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उगप्पार्पोन्<BR>ugappār-pŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in gold on joyous<BR>occasions like marriage; probably the same as kaṇṇāla-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उलवुकाट्चि<BR>ulavu-kāṭci (SITI), Tamil; probably, presents offered to<BR>the king or other exalted persons when going in procession<BR>round the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्गु<BR>ulgu (SITI), Tamil; customs duties; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लियक्कूलि<BR>ulliya-kkūli (SITI), Tamil; probably, water-fee for irri-<BR>gation from wells; tax or wages for well-digging.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उलुप्पै<BR>uluppai (SITI), Tamil; presents of fruits, articles of food,<BR>etc., offered to great personages; free supplies made by the<BR>people or subordinates to officials on tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्वरि<BR>uḻ-vari (SITI), Tamil; internal revenue; taxes levied<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-425" target="_blank">Page-425+ 40</a>]<BR>by the local body; same as antar-āyam; orders issued by the<BR>government fixing the amount of such taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उप्पुक्काशु<BR>uppu-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; salt-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरल्वरि<BR>ural-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax or fee for the maintenance<BR>of the mortar for husking paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊरेट्टु<BR>ūr-ĕṭṭu (SITI), Tamil; ‘committee of eight members of<BR>the village assembly (ūr)’; taxes payable for the expenses of<BR>the committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊरिडुवरिप्पाडु<BR>ūr-iḍu-varippāḍu (SII 13; SITI), Tamil; tax levied by<BR>the village assembly (ūr).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्क्कडमै<BR>ūr-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; obligations and taxes pay-<BR>able to the village assembly (ūr).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्त्तनिशु<BR>ūr-ttaniśu (SII 13), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊशिवाशि<BR>ūśi-vāśi (SITI), Tamil; tax probably connected with<BR>tailoring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उवच्चवरि<BR>uvacca-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax payable by or for the main-<BR>tenance of the uvaccar (drummers in temple service).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उवच्चक्काणि<BR>uvacca-kkāṇi (SITI), Tamil; rent-free land given to the<BR>uvaccaṉ for serving as drummer in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डरावुल<BR>vaḍḍarāvuḻa, vaḍḍāravuḻa (EI 19, 28; IE 8-8), Kannaḍa;<BR>name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वगैन्दकाशु<BR>vagainda-kāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in cash for<BR>marking the details, as of land; fees for subdivision of land;<BR>also the fee for settlement, as of a dispute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालमञ्जाडि<BR>vāla-mañjāḍi (SITI), Tamil; probably the same as vāla-<BR>vari and vāla-kkāṇam; tax of a mañjāḍi on the units of measure-<BR>ment in the length of a house-site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलङ्गैइडङ्गैमगन्मै<BR>valaṅgai-iḍaṅgai-maganmai (SITI), Tamil; tax on the right-<BR>hand and left-hand castes, to be paid by all able-bodied men<BR>capable of bearing arms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः<BR>val13inaḍaikk-iḍum-paṇam (SITI), Tamil; road cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः<BR>val13iy-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tolls on the roadways.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः<BR>val13udiy-accu-vargam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; group of<BR>taxes payable in Pāṇḍya coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वण्णार्वरि<BR>vaṇṇār-vari, vaṇṇāra-ppāṟai (SITI), Tamil; tax on washer-<BR>men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः<BR>vaṉ-pāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; fixed rent in kind due under<BR>a lease-deed which does not provide for any relief against loss<BR>due to drought.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरि<BR>vari (SITI), Tamil; tax, revenue register, order of the<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-426" target="_blank">Page-426+ 40</a>]<BR>king and his officer fixing the revenue; cf. vari-ppŏttagam, tax<BR>register; officer maintaining the same; also Vari-kkūṟu-śeyvār,<BR>Varrikkukkūṟu-śeyvār (SITI), Tamil; officers grading the culti-<BR>vable land and fixing the tax payable thereon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरिशै<BR>variśai (SITI), Tamil; village dues; cess payable by or<BR>to the local authority.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशलिल्पोन्दकुडिमै<BR>vāśalil-ponda-kuḍimai (SITI), Tamil; ‘burden of citizen-<BR>ship dues at the gate’; taxes, probably other than the land<BR>revenue, payable to the state.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्काणिक्कै<BR>vāśal-kāṇikkai, (SITI), Tamil; presents offered to the palace,<BR>probably annually.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्कु<BR>vāśal-kul13i-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; probably, door-<BR>tax, i. e., house-tax based on the main doorways.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्पणम्<BR>vāśal-paṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; periodical payment<BR>due to the palace; door-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्तिरमम्<BR>vāśal-tiramam (SITI), Tamil; door-tax; tiramam is the<BR>same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्विनियोगम्<BR>vāśal-viniyogam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; same as vāśal-<BR>paṇam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टम्<BR>vaṭṭam (SITI), money-changers’ commission; trade dis-<BR>count.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टिना<BR>vaṭṭi-nāl13i (SITI), Tamil; probably, a tax payable at the<BR>rate of one nāl13i for each vaṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाय्क्काल्पाट्टम्<BR>vāykkāl-pāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; channel cess; fee for keep-<BR>ing the channels in good repairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिक्काशु<BR>veli-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax (payable in cash) of<BR>uncertain import; cf. veli-kkul13i-ppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिप्पयरु<BR>veli-ppayaru (SII 12; SITI), same as veli-kkāśu<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेल्लानिरै<BR>veḻḻān-iṟai (SITI), Tamil; cultivation tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेण्डुगोल्<BR>veṇḍugoḻ, veṇḍukoḻ (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; supplication;<BR>petition; fee for the same; also known as veṇḍukoḻ-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेट्टि<BR>vĕṭṭi (SII 12, 13), same as Sanskrit viṣṭi, ‘unpaid<BR>labour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेट्टिवेदिनै<BR>vĕṭṭi-vedinai (SII 13), explained as a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेयदिकाणम्<BR>veyadi-kāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in grains, pro-<BR>bably on thatched sheds; or, may be related to veynĕl (collection<BR>of bamboo-grain from forests).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभूतिकाणिक्कै<BR>vibhūti-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; contribution paid<BR>voluntarily to a temple by its devotees while receiving the<BR>sacred ashes, later collected as compulsory dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडैप्पेर्<BR>viḍai-pper, viḍai-ppeṟu (SITI), Tamil; perquisites payable<BR>on the receipt of a reply to a petition to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विल्पणम्<BR>vil-paṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; sale-tax; also explain-<BR>ed as a tax on bows or on archery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विप्रविनोदिवरि<BR>vipravinodi-vari (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax from or for the<BR>maintenance of the Vipravinodins (Brāhmaṇa magicians).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरशेषै<BR>vīra-śeṣai (SITI); EI 22), sometimes supposed to be the<BR>name of a tax; but see vīra-śeṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विर्पणम्<BR>viṟ-paṇam (SITI), vil-paṇam; Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on bows<BR>and arrows; may also be a tax on sales.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरुत्तुप्पट्टिगै<BR>viruttu-ppaṭṭigai (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on profits<BR>and the income from interest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशक्काणम्<BR>viśa-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax or share in the produce<BR>as remuneration due to a Viyavaṉ or village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशेषायम्<BR>viśeṣ-āyam, viśeṣ-ādāyam (SITI), Sanskrit; a special group<BR>of taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाहप्पणम्<BR>vivāha-ppaṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; marriage fee; cf.<BR>kaṇṇāla-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चु<BR>accu, Tamil; name of a coin; money; tax or income.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आछु<BR>āchu, same as āsu; cf. accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आड<BR>āḍa, also spelt aḍḍa; name of a coin; half of a fanam; cf.<BR>aḍḍaga and aḍḍuga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडतालीसगानी<BR>aḍatālīsa-gānī, 6 aṭha-gānīs or ṭaṅkas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्ड<BR>aḍḍa, same as aḍa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डचिन्न<BR>aḍḍa-cinna, cf. āḍa or aḍḍa and cinna or sinna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डग<BR>aḍḍaga, also spelt aḍḍuga; same as āḍa, aḍḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डुग<BR>aḍḍuga, same as aḍḍaga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिक्काशु<BR>aḍi-kkāśu, ‘tax collected from the stall-keepers in the<BR>market’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिमैक्काशु<BR>aḍimai-kkāśu, ‘fee collected from the temple servants (or<BR>for their maintenance)’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिवराहद्रम्म<BR>ādivarāha-dramma, ‘a dramma issued by Ādivarāha (Patīhāra<BR>Bhoja I, c. 836-85 A. D.)’; same as śrīmad-ādivarāha-dramma;<BR>see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आद्यमाष<BR>ādya-māṣa, the original māṣa of 5 ratis as opposed to the<BR>later māṣa of various weights upto 10 ratis. Cf. māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आजीवककाशु<BR>ājīvaka-kāśu, same as Tamil āśuva-kkāśu; ‘tax collected from<BR>the Ājivakas (or for the maintenance of the Ājīvaka monks)’; see<BR>kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कम्<BR>akkam, one-twelfth of a kāśu (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्ष|अक्षं|अक्षः<BR>akṣa, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलगच्चु<BR>aḻag-accu, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बिलिगद्याण<BR>ambili-gadyāṇa, see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमुदनच्चु<BR>amudan-accu, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनैअच्चु<BR>anai-accu, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आणक|आणकः<BR>āṇaka, Sanskritized form of Muhammadan āna = English anna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अण्दिक<BR>aṇdika, aṇḍikā, (1/4) of a māṣa; also regarded as the same as<BR>paṇa which was (1/12) or (1/16) of a dīnāra or suvarṇa in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्कगद्याण<BR>aṅka-gadyāṇa, see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्न|अन्नं|अन्नः<BR>anna, Anglicised form of Muhammadan āna; (1/16) of rupee,<BR>property, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धककिनी<BR>ardha-kakinī, half of a kākinī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्णिका<BR>arṇikā, equal to 2 māṣas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टमिका<BR>aṣṭamikā, same as śatamāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसु<BR>āsu, cf. accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुवक्काशु<BR>āśuva-kkāśu, same as ājīvaka-kāśu (q. v.); see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अठगानी<BR>aṭha-gānī, same as ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औरेउस्<BR>aureus, Roman gold coin (124 grains); same as the gold<BR>denareus (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदर|बदरं|बदरः<BR>badara, same as tola or tolaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बडिमाडुवुलु<BR>baḍi-māḍuvulu, see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलोत्र<BR>balotra, name applied to an Indian silver coin by the<BR>Muslim chroniclers of the early medieval period.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बराड्<BR>barāḍ, modified form of varāṭaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बारह्गानी<BR>bārah-gānī, 1(1/2) aṭha-gānīs or ṭaṅkas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेल्लियद्रम्म<BR>beḻḻiya-dramma, Kannaḍa; ‘silver dramma’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाग|भागः<BR>bhāga, see hāga, pāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भैरवगद्याण<BR>bhairava-gadyāṇa ‘a gadyāṇa minted by a goldsmith<BR>named Bhairava’; cf. bṛhat-bhairava-gadyāṇa; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीमप्रियद्रम्म<BR>bhīmapriya-dramma, ‘a dramma minted by a goldsmith named<BR>Bhīma’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलमाडै<BR>bhujabala-māḍai, ‘a māḍai issued by a ruler named or enti-<BR>tled Bhujabala’; see māḍa, māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिन्दुक<BR>binduka, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्भैरवगद्याण<BR>bṛhat-bhairava-gadyāṇa, ‘the bigger bhairava-gadyāṇa (q. v.)’;<BR>see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुडी<BR>buḏī, Bengali name for a unit equal to 5 gaṇḍās; cf. voḍī,<BR>voḍrī, kapardaka-voḍī; also kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामर|चामरं|चामरः<BR>cāmara, also called cāmara-māḍa; probably ‘a māḍa bearing<BR>the figure of a fly-whisk’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामरमाड<BR>cāmara-māḍa, see cāmara and māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्सम्<BR>carsam (karṣa ?), equal to 4 māḍas; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चस्ह्<BR>cash, Anglicised spelling of kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चस्त्<BR>‘cast’, see ‘die-struck’ and ‘punch-marked’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौबीसगानी<BR>caubīsa-gānī, 3 aṭha-gānīs or ṭaṅkas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौगानी<BR>cau-gānī, (1/2) of an aṭha-gānī or ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवल<BR>cavala, also spelt cavela; (1/8) of a pagoda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवेल<BR>cavela, same as cavala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छगानी<BR>cha-gānī, (3/4) of an aṭha-gānī or ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीनक्कनक्कम्<BR>cīna-kkanakkam, Tamil; ‘Chinese gold coin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिन्न|चिन्नः<BR>cinna, also spelt sinna; same as fanam (q. v.); (1/8) of a<BR>pagoda (q. v.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरविद<BR>ciravida, Telugu; supposed to be a kind of gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाम्<BR>dām, derivative of dramma (q. v.); copper coin, (1/40) of a<BR>Mughal rupee (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम|दमः<BR>dama, same as dāma or dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाम<BR>dāma, same as dām or dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्म<BR>damma, same as dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डाङ्ग्<BR>ḍāṅg, corrupt form of ṭanka (q. v.); cf. dāṅk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाङ्क्<BR>dāṅk, corrupt form of ṭaṅka (q. v.); cf. ḍāṅg.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दरिच्<BR>daric, gold coin of ancient Iran (about 133 grains); double<BR>daric = Greek stater or tetradrachma, four times the drachma in weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दायद्रम्म<BR>dāya-dramma, ‘tax or money to be paid’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देह्लीटाल्<BR>dehlīwāl, see jītal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देनरिउस्<BR>denarius, name of the Roman silver (also gold) coin; equal<BR>to Greek drachma; origin of the Indian coin name dīnāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानक|धानकं|धानकः<BR>dhānaka, same as māṣa; cf. hemadhānyaka; same as dhānika<BR>(q. v.); also called aṇḍika and regarded as equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas<BR>or (1/12) of suvarṇa (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानिक<BR>dhānika, equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or 64 paṇas according to the<BR>Kṛtyakalpataru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यमाष<BR>dhānya-māṣa, (1/2) of yava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरण|धरणं|धरणः<BR>dharaṇa, old silver coin of 32 ratis (about 58 grains); also<BR>called kārṣāpaṇa and purāṇa; 24 (actually about 20) ratis in<BR>weight and half of gadyāṇa in value according to medieval autho-<BR>rities; otherwise called dramma, śāna or ṭaṅka; sometimes regarded<BR>as a gold coin or weight equal to ten palas or 40 suvarṇas or niṣkas<BR>(3200 ratis); cf. śalamāna (silver) = 10 dharaṇas (320 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वंशि<BR>dhvaṃśi, same as vaṃśya; a minute unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिद्रछ्म<BR>didrachma, ‘two-drachma’, ‘double drachma’; see drachma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिएस्त्रुच्क्<BR>‘die-struck’, coins on which the symbols and legends were<BR>impressed by means of an anvil and a single punch, both bear-<BR>ing negative representations, by placing a blank on the socket<BR>in the anvil and striking the punch placed on it by a hammer;<BR>see punch-marked.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनार<BR>dināra, also spelt dinnāra; generally spelt dīnāra (q. v.);<BR>a cowrie-shell according to the Kashmir chronicle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीनार|दीनारः<BR>dīnāra, derived from Roman denarius (124 grains); name of<BR>a gold coin equal to 16 silver coins called rūpaka, etc. (about 20<BR>ratis); a silver coin according to the Kṛtyakalpataru; sometimes<BR>called kāśu in Tamil, etc.; sometimes regarded as half of satera<BR>or sateraka (Greek stater); see dināra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारि<BR>dināri, generally spelt as dīnāra; local modification of<BR>the Roman denarius prevalent in the Ikṣvāku kingdom in the<BR>Krishna-Guntur region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारिमाषक<BR>dināri-māṣaka, same as dināri, or one-sixteenth of a dināri<BR>or dīnāra in weight or value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिन्नार<BR>dinnāra, see dināra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिरमम्<BR>diramam, Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोड्डवराह<BR>doḍḍa-varāha, see varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोगानी<BR>do-gānī, (1/4) of an aṭha-gānī or ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्र<BR>dra, abbreviation of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रछ्म<BR>drachma, Greek silver coin; equal to 6 obols; Attic standard<BR>67 grains, but the Indo-Greek standard was soon modified, their<BR>coins of 37 or 38 grains being called drachma or hemi-drachma by<BR>different scholars; origin of the Indian coin name dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षण|द्रक्षणं<BR>drakṣaṇa, same as draṃkṣana or tola; equal to 8 māṣas (80<BR>ratis); cf. drakṣuṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षुण<BR>drakṣuṇa, same as drakṣaṇa or tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रंक्षण|द्रङ्क्षण|द्रङ्क्षणं<BR>draṃkṣaṇa, same as tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम<BR>drama, same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्म|द्रम्मं<BR>dramma, Indian form of Greek drachma; a silver coin (1/16) of<BR>a gold niṣka according to the Līlāvatī; name applied to the<BR>Śaka-type silver purāṇa, dharaṇa or kārṣāpaṇa (about 20 ratis,<BR>also called rūpaka); copper coin (dām) regarded as (1/40) of a<BR>Mughal rupee; money in general; the name first occurs on the<BR>Yaudheya coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मार्ध<BR>dramm-ārdha, half of dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मत्रिभाग<BR>dramma-tribhāga, one-third of dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रङ्ग|द्रङ्गः<BR>draṅga, variant of dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुगानी<BR>du-gānī, same as do-gānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुक्र<BR>dukra, (1/5) of a phadiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुकानी<BR>dukānī, (1/2) of a phadiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअदिया<BR>fadiyā, see phadiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअनम्<BR>fanam, Anglicised form of Tamil paṇam (q. v.); Sanskrit<BR>paṇa (q. v.); a gold coin equal to (1/20) of a varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग|गं|गः<BR>ga, abbreviation of gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधैया<BR>gadhaiyā, same as gadhiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधैयापैसा<BR>gadhaiyā-paisā, same as ghadhiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदिआणक<BR>gadiāṇaka, cf. kumāra-gadiāṇaka, name of a tax; same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधिया<BR>gadhiyā, also spelt gadhaiyā; copper coin imitated from old<BR>Sasanian issues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधियापैसा<BR>gadhiyā-paisā, same as gadhiyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदियाण<BR>gadiyāṇa, same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्या<BR>gadyā, abbreviation of gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यान<BR>gadyāna, same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याण<BR>gadyāṇa, a gold coin or weight; generally regarded as 48<BR>ratis (about 88 grains) in weight; sometimes called ‘the gold<BR>gadyāṇa’; sometimes regarded as a coin like a farthing, equal<BR>to (1/4) or (1/5) of the paikamu (q. v.); regarded in some places as<BR>equal to 20 vals, 8 māṣas or (1/2) tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यानक|गद्यानकं|गद्यानकः<BR>gadyānaka, same as gadyāṇaka or gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याणक|गद्याणकः<BR>gadyāṇaka, same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याणपोन्नु<BR>gadyāṇa-ponnu, ‘gadyāṇa of gold’; same as pon-gadyāṇa; see<BR>gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डा<BR>gaṇḍā, equal to 4 cowrie-shells; (1/20) of a paṇa; cf. gaṇḍaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डगोपालन्माडै<BR>gaṇḍagopālaṉ-māḍai, ‘māḍa issued or minted by<BR>Gaṇḍagopāla’; see māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डक|गंडक|गंडकः|गण्डकः<BR>gaṇḍaka, same as gaṇḍā. Cf. kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डमाड<BR>gaṇḍa-māḍa, probably ‘māḍa bearing the figure of a rhi-<BR>noceros’ or an abbreviation of Gaṇḍagopālan-māḍai (q. v.);<BR>sometimes characterised by the epithet ‘small’; sometimes<BR>also called kārṣāpaṇa, niṣka and gaṇḍa-niṣka; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डनिष्क<BR>gaṇḍa-niṣka, same as gaṇḍa; see māḍa and niṣka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्धहस्तिमाड<BR>gandhahasti-māḍa, same as gandhavāraṇa-māḍa; probably,<BR>‘māḍa bearing the figure of an elephant in rut’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गानी<BR>gānī, cf. aṭha-gānī, equal to a ṭaṅka and weighing a tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गरद्रम्म<BR>gara-dramma, see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गावगद्याण<BR>gāva-gadyāṇa, see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटितहीनद्रम्माः<BR>ghaṭita-hīna-drammāḥ, ‘drammas (money) that are want-<BR>ing’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोलका<BR>golakā, same as gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोलक्कै<BR>goḻakkai, Tamil; same as golakā (gulikā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रासग्रह<BR>grāsagraha, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुलिका<BR>gulikā, same as golakā, etc.; a small coin apparently<BR>globular or circular in shape; supposed to be a coin issued by<BR>the Śambhuvarāya chiefs and also by the Pāṇḍyas; cf. vīra-<BR>champan-kuḻigai and vaḻḻāl-val13i-tiṟantāṉ-guḻikai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुञ्जा|गुंजा<BR>guñjā, same as rati or raktikā (1-83 or about 1(3/4) grains).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाग<BR>hāga, Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit bhāga; probably (1/4) of<BR>the standard coin; see pāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंसपद|हंसपदः<BR>haṃsapada, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेम|हेमं|हेमः<BR>hema, same as māṣa; cf. hema-dhānyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमधान्यक|हेमधान्यकः<BR>hema-dhānyaka, same as māṣa; see hema and dhānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमटङ्क<BR>hema-ṭaṅka, ‘a gold ṭaṅka (q. v.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमिद्रछ्म<BR>hemi-drachma, Greek; same as Sanskrit dramm-ārdha (q. v.);<BR>see drachma, dramma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होन्<BR>hon, variant spelling of hūn; same as varāha, gadyāṇa (gold<BR>gadyāṇa) and pagoda (star pagoda); cf. suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हून्<BR>hūn, same as hon or varāha (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईलक्करुङ्काशु<BR>īḻa-kkaruṅ-kāśu, ‘Ceylonese coin’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईलक्काशु<BR>īḻa-kkāśu, ‘Ceylonese coin’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इनवरिक्काशु<BR>inavari-kkāśu, ‘communual tax in cash’; see kāśu<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगदलंगद्याण<BR>jagadaḻaṃ-gadyāṇa, see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जैथल<BR>jaithala, same as jītal (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णश्रेष्ठिश्रीमल्लप्रिय<BR>jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-śrīmalla-priya, possibly, ‘an old coin of the mint<BR>of Śreṣṭhin Śrīmalla’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णश्रेष्ठिविश्वमल्लप्रिय<BR>jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya, same as jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya;<BR>possibly, ‘an old coin of the mint of Śreṣṭhin Viśvamalla’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीतल्<BR>jītal, a copper coin, (1/48) of a silver ṭanka of the Delhi<BR>Sulṯāns; also called delhīwāl; (1/3) of a silver tār which was<BR>itself (1/6) of a fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय<BR>jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya, same as jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya,<BR>possibly, ‘an old coin of the mint of Viśvamalla’; cf. vīsala-<BR>priya-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडा<BR>kaḏā, Bengali, etc; cowrie-shell regarded as coin; (1/4)<BR>of gaṇḍā and (1/80) of paṇa in some areas. Cf. kapardaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहण<BR>kāhaṇa, Bengali, etc; also spelt kahāṇa and kāhāṇa; same<BR>as kāhāpaṇa = kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कहाण<BR>kahāṇa, same as kāhaṇa = kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहाण<BR>kāhāṇa, same as kāhaṇa = kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहापण<BR>kāhāpaṇa, same as Sanskrit kārṣāpaṇa and modern kāhaṇ,<BR>etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काक|काकं|काकः<BR>kāka, same as kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकनिका<BR>kākanikā, same as kakanī, kakinī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककिनी<BR>kakinī, equal to 20 cowrie-shells according to the Līlāvatī;<BR>(1/4) of a paṇa; same as buḏī. Cf. gaṇḍā<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः<BR>kal13añju, Tamil; name of a weight or coin weighing 10<BR>mañjāḍis (32 ratis theoretically); sometimes called suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणम्<BR>kāṇam, Tamil; name of a coin; a gold coin or weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिके<BR>kāṇikĕ, also spelt kāṇiki; (1/64) part of a coin; money or tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिकि<BR>kāṇiki, same as kāṇikĕ (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्द|कपर्दः|कपर्द्द|कपर्द्दः<BR>kaparda, same as kapardaka, etc.; cowrie-shell used as<BR>coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दक|कपर्दकः|कपर्द्दक|कपर्द्दकः<BR>kapardaka, also called kaparda, kapardikā, kapardī, etc.; cowrie-<BR>shell used as coin. Cf. kaḏā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकपुराण<BR>kapardaka-purāṇa, ‘a purāṇa (q. v.) counted in kapardakas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकवोडी<BR>kapardaka-voḍī, ‘a voḍī counted in kapardakas’; cf. buḏī and<BR>voḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दी|कपर्द्दी<BR>kapardī, same as kapardikā, kapardaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दिका<BR>kapardikā, same as kapardī, kapardaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्ष|कर्षः<BR>karṣa, name of a weight equal to 80 ratis or about 146<BR>grains; sometimes regarded 100 ratis or about 183 grains;<BR>sometimes also regarded as 120 ratis in weight; a coin (cf.<BR>kārṣāpaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्षापण|कार्षापणं|कार्षापणः<BR>kārṣāpaṇa, silver coin weighing 32 ratis (about 58 grains),<BR>also called purāṇa or dharaṇa; copper coin of 80 ratis or about<BR>146 grains (sometimes 100 ratis or about 183 grains), also<BR>called paṇa; Śaka-type silver coin of about 20 ratis, also called<BR>rūpaka, dramma, etc.; gold coin of 80 ratis (cf. suvarṇa); name<BR>applied to gaṇḍa māḍa (probably (1/2) tola in weight), also called<BR>niṣka (q. v.); same as kāhaṇa, etc.; cf. karṣa of 120 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्षार्ध<BR>karṣ-ārdha, ‘half of a karṣa (q. v.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुङ्काशु<BR>karuṅ-kāśu, ‘Ceylonese coin’; see kāśu, īl13a-kkāśu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशु<BR>kāśu, Tamil; spelt in English as cash; name of a copper<BR>coin, (1/100) of a fanam; sometimes called dīnāra; money; tax; cf.<BR>kāśu-kaḍamai, ‘tax in coins’; also Sanskrit karṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कठारिअङ्कुशगद्याण<BR>kaṭhāri-aṅkuśa-gadyāṇa, probably, ‘a gadyāṇa bearing the<BR>representation of a dagger and a goad’; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल|कोलं|कोलः<BR>kola, same as tola; equal to 2 śāṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलक्कै<BR>koḻakkai, Tamil; same as golakā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोमरिनगद्याण<BR>komarina-gadyāṇa, same as kumāra-gadyāṇa; name of a tax;<BR>see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोवै<BR>kovai, Tamil; name of a gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रोड|क्रोडं|क्रोडः<BR>kroḍa, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णल|कृष्णलः<BR>kṛṣṇala, same as rati or guñjā (about 1(3/4) grains); re-<BR>garded as equal to 3 ratis by the Kṛtyalalpataru which seems to<BR>confuse rati with yava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णराजरूपक<BR>kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka, ‘rūpaka issued by Kṛṣṇarāja (Kalacuri<BR>Kṛṣṇa, sixth century A. D.)’; see rūpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रक|क्षुद्रकः<BR>kṣudraka, same as draṃkṣaṇa or tola (q. v.); cf. kṣudrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रम<BR>kṣudrama, variant of kṣudraka; same as tola (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगद्याणक<BR>kumāra-gadyāṇaka, name of a tax; see gadyāṇa; cf. koma-<BR>rina-gadyāṇa and kumara-kaccāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमरकच्चाणम्<BR>kumara-kaccāṇam, Tamil; same as kumāra-gadyāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलिगै<BR>kuḻigai, same as gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलोत्तुङ्गमाड<BR>kulottuṅga-māḍa, ‘māḍa issued by Kulottuṅga (i. e. Col13a-<BR>Cālukya Kulottuṅga I, 1070-1120 A. D.)’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लागिद्रम्माः<BR>lāgi-drammāḥ, ‘expenses incurred’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहडिया<BR>lohaḍiyā, equal to 20 pāvīsās or 100 cowrie-shells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहितक|लोहितकं|लोहितकः<BR>lohitaka, equal to 3 māṣas (30 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोक्किगद्याण<BR>lokki-gadyāṇa, ‘gadyāṇa minted at Lokki (modern Lak-<BR>kundi in the Dharwar District, Mysore State)’; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माड|माडः<BR>māḍa, Telugu; gold or silver coin, 40 ratis (about 73<BR>grains) in weight; half of a dīnāra; half of a pagoda, or tenth<BR>of a paṇa (fanam) in value; same as māḍha, māḍhā, māḍai;<BR>50 per cent; cf. gaṇḍa-māḍa also called kārṣāpaṇa and gaṇḍa-<BR>niṣka; Tamil modification of Sanskrit māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडबदिपातुक<BR>māḍa-badipātuka, fraction of a māḍa; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडै<BR>māḍai, Tamil; same as māḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माढ<BR>māḍha, Oḏiyā; also spelt māḍhā; same as māḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापण<BR>mahāpaṇa, cf. māppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लनन्दिमाड<BR>malla-nandi-māḍa, probably, ‘māḍa bearing the figure of<BR>a wrestler and a bull’, or ‘māḍa minted by Mallanandin’; see<BR>māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लमाड<BR>malla-māḍa, possibly, ‘māḍa bearing the figure of a wrest-<BR>ler’, or an abbreviation of malla-nandi-māḍa; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मंक्षुण|मङ्क्षुण|मङ्क्षुणं<BR>maṃkṣuṇa, equal to 7 māṣas (70 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्ड|मंडं|मण्डं|मंडः|मण्डः<BR>maṇḍa, equal to 5 māṣas (50 ratis); cf. māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जाडि<BR>mañjāḍi, (1/10) of a kaḻañju, (1/100) of a śatamāna; sometimes<BR>regarded as 5(1/2) grains in weight, but may be about 4 grains also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पणम्<BR>māppaṇam, same as Sanskrit mahāpaṇa; may be also ‘tax of<BR>one paṇa per mā measure of grains’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरीचि|मरीचिः<BR>marīci, a minute unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माष|माषः<BR>māṣa, name of a weight or a coin weighing 5 ratis originally;<BR>later regarded as 10 ratis in weight; (1/4) of a śāna and (1/8) of a<BR>śatamāna; sometimes regarded as (1/20) of a paṇa of 100 ratis<BR>(i. e. 5 ratis); a gold coin (as opposed to the silver māṣaka)<BR>according to the Kṛtyakalpataru; cf. ādya-māṣa, māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माषक|माषकः<BR>māṣaka, same as māṣa; according to the Kṛtyakalpataru,<BR>a silver coin as opposed to the gold māṣa<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृड|मृडः<BR>mṛḍa, name of a weight like māñjāḍi (q. v.). Cf. pṛḍa, pruḍ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल्तिरमम्<BR>mudal-tiramam, mudaṟṟiramam, Tamil; ‘tax payable in<BR>cash’; cf. tiramam = dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नला<BR>nalā, same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्काशु<BR>nal-kāśu, see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्लानैअच्चु<BR>nall-ānai-accu, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाना<BR>nānā, same as nāṇaka; cf. Kuṣāṇa coins bearing the repre-<BR>sentation of the West Asian mother-goddess Nana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणै<BR>nāṇai, same as nāṇaka, nānā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणक|नाणकं<BR>nāṇaka, a coin; see nāṇai, nānā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नत्काशु<BR>nat-kāśu, see kāsu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेल्लूर्माडै<BR>nellūr-māḍai, ‘the Nellore māḍai’; see māḍa, māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्क|निष्कं|निष्कः<BR>niṣka, gold coin or weight equal to one karṣa (80 ratis or<BR>about 146 grains) of 16 māṣas or to 4 or 108 or 150 suvarṇas<BR>(q. v.); silver coin equal to one śatamāna (320 ratis); some-<BR>times identified with māḍa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओबोल्<BR>obol, Greek coin; (1/6) of drachma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादविंशोपक<BR>pāda-viṃśopaka, ‘one-fourth of a viṃśopaka (q. v.)’; cf. pāvīsā<BR>which is the same as paisā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मनिधिमल्लमाड<BR>padmanidhi-malla-māḍa, probably, ‘maḍa bearing the<BR>figure of a wrestler meant for depositing in a temple treasury’;<BR>but cf. malla-māḍa, etc.; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुच्चलागैअच्चु<BR>paduccalāgai-accu, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाग<BR>pāga, same as Kannaḍa hāga; (1/4) of the standard coin;<BR>probably the same as Sanskrit bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पगोद<BR>pagoda, also called ‘star pagoda’; Anglicised form of the name<BR>of the gold coin called gadyāṇa, hūn (hon) or varāha; since the<BR>word pagoda also meant ‘a temple’, the coin seems to have been<BR>so named owing to the representation of a temple or a deity on<BR>it; pagoda may be a corruption of bhagavatī meaning ‘the mother-<BR>goddess’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैकमु<BR>paikamu, Telugu; supposed to be a small coin equal to<BR>(1/4) or (1/5) of a gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैसा<BR>paisā, (1/64) or (1/100) of a rupee; same as pāvīsā = Sanskrit<BR>pāda-viṃśaka (°viṃśatika or °viṃśopaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल|पलं|पलः<BR>pala, weight of 320 ratis (cf. śatamāna); equal to 4 or 5<BR>suvarṇas according to the Yājñavalkyasmṛti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलमुदलानैअच्चु<BR>paḻamudal-ānai-accu, same as palañśalāgai; see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलम्पुल्लिमाडै<BR>paḻam-puḻḻi-māḍai, see māḍa, māḍai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलञ्जलागैअच्चु<BR>paḻañjalāgai-accu, same as palañśalāgai; see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलङ्काशु<BR>palaṅ-kāśu, see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलञ्शलागै<BR>paḻañ-śalāgai, Tamil; a kind of coin (accu) probably of the<BR>shape of a śalākā. Cf. śrī-yakki-paḻañ-śalāgai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलार्ध<BR>pal-ārdha, (1/2) of a pala (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण|पणः<BR>paṇa, same as the copper kārṣāpaṇa, 80 ratis in weight<BR>according to Manu, etc.; equal to 80 cowrie-shells according<BR>to the Līlāvatī; regarded in East India during the late medieval<BR>period as equal to 80 cowrie-shells and (1/16) of a kāhaṇ =<BR>kārṣāpaṇa (q. v.); (1/16) of a suvarṇa according to some; (1/48) of a<BR>kārṣāpaṇa according to the Kṛtyakalpataru; same as Tamil paṇam<BR>(q. v.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणम्<BR>paṇam, Tamil; spelt fanam in English; same as Sans-<BR>krit paṇa (q. v.); but in Tamil, a small gold coin or money<BR>in general; cf. paṇa-vargam, ‘taxes in cash’, also called kāś-<BR>āya-vargam (literally, ‘taxes payable in kāśu, i. e. cash or money’).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणपुराण<BR>paṇa-purāṇa, ‘purāṇa (q. v.) counted in paṇas (q. v.)’; cf.<BR>kapardaka-purāṇa and kapardaka-voḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणवाशि<BR>paṇa-vāśi, Tamil; ‘discount for the exchange of coins’;<BR>see paṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्चालवच्चु<BR>paṇcālav-accu, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चियकद्रम<BR>pañciyaka-drama, probably, ‘dramma minted by the pañca or<BR>pañcakula i. e. the Pañcāyat Board’; or ‘dramma equal to five<BR>copper coins’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणि|पाणिः<BR>pāṇi, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेष्ठिगद्याण<BR>parameṣṭhi-gadyāṇa, see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्ताब्<BR>partāb, name of a gold coin; a half pagoda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परुमुलैवराहन्<BR>parumuḻai-varāhan, see varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारुत्थ<BR>pāruttha, a silver coin equal to 8 drammas of copper or<BR>billon; cf. poruttha-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौर|पौरं<BR>paura, cf. purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावीसा<BR>pāvīsā, (1/20) of a lohaḍiyā; same as Sanskrit pāda-viṃśaka<BR>(°viṃśatika or °viṃśopaka) and modern paisā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फदिया<BR>phadiyā, same as phadyaka; a copper coin about two annas<BR>in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फद्यक<BR>phadyaka, same as phadiyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचु|पिचुः<BR>picu, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचुल|पिचुलः<BR>picula, equal to 6 maṣas (60 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्<BR>pon, also spelt poṉ in Tamil; same as hon (i. e. hūn or<BR>varāha); same as ‘gold’ māḍai, gadyāṇa, etc.; money. Cf.<BR>Tamil pon-bhaṇḍāram, pon-paṇḍāra-vāśal; also pon-vargam, pon-<BR>vari, etc., meaning ‘taxes payable in gold or coins’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो<BR>poṉ, Tamil; see pon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्गद्याण<BR>pon-gadyāṇa, ‘gold gadyāṇa’; same as gadyāṇa-ponnu; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोरुत्थद्रम्म<BR>poruttha-dramma, see dramma; cf. pāruttha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रताप|प्रतापः<BR>pratāpa, same as partāb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृड<BR>pṛḍa, a variant of mṛḍa (q. v.). Cf. pruḍ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रियश्राहगजमल्लगद्याण<BR>priyaśrāha-gajamalla-gadyāṇa, probably, gadyāṇa minted by<BR>Priyaśrāha and Gajamalla (or Gajamalla of Priyaśrāha); see<BR>gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रुड्<BR>pruḍ, a variant of mṛḍa (q. v.). Cf. pṛḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुल्लिगुलिकैवराहन्<BR>puḻḻi-guḻikai-varāhan, see gulikā and varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुन्छ्मर्केद्<BR>‘punch-marked’, name applied to old Indian coins of<BR>copper and silver, on which the symbols were punched by<BR>different punches as was not the case with the die-struck and<BR>cast coins. Similar coins were sometimes cast from dies also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुराण|पुराणं|पुराणः<BR>purāṇa, a silver coin also called dharaṇa and kārṣāpaṇa, 32<BR>ratis (about 58 grains) in weight; name applied to the silver<BR>punch-marked coins and also to the Śaka-type silver coins<BR>weighing about 20 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजमाड<BR>rājarāja-māḍa, Telugu; ‘māḍa or māḍai issued by king<BR>Rājarāja (Col13a Rājarāja I, 985-1016 A. D.)’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजन्माडै<BR>rājarājan-māḍai, Tamil; same as rājarāja-māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रजेन्द्रचो<BR>rajendracol13a-māḍa, ‘māḍa issued by king Rājendra-col13a<BR>(Rājendra I, 1016-43 A.D.)’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तिका<BR>raktikā, modern rati; a little above 1(3/4) grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिपणम्<BR>rāśi-paṇam, ‘current good coins’; also called rāśi-ppon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिप्पोन्<BR>rāśi-ppon, same as rāśi-paṇam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रति|रतिः<BR>rati, same as raktikā; a little above 1(3/4) grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रौप्यटङ्क<BR>raupya-ṭaṅka, ‘a silver ṭaṅka (q. v.)’; a silver kārṣāpaṇa so<BR>called in South India according to Nārada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेकैप्पोन्<BR>rekai-ppon, regarded as the name of a gold coin of the<BR>Vijayanagara times so called probably for bearing linear marks<BR>(rekhā); may be ‘revenue income in cash’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेखा<BR>rekhā, cf. rekai-ppon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रदामक<BR>rudradāmaka, ‘kārṣāpaṇa issued by Rudradāman’; name<BR>applied to the silver coins issued by the Śaka rulers of Western<BR>India; its later imitations were called rūpaka, dramma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप|रूपं<BR>rūpa, same as rūpaka or rūpyaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपक|रूपकं<BR>rūpaka, silver coin; silver coin (1/16) (about 20 ratis) of a<BR>gold dīnāra, etc.; also called dramma, purāṇa, kārṣāpaṇa, etc.;<BR>same as modern rupee; cf. kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुपेए<BR>rupee, English form of rūpīya (q. v.); silver coin equal to<BR>16 annas and 64 paisās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपीय<BR>rūpīya (rūpīah), Muhammadan name of rūpya, rūpaka or<BR>rūpyaka (q. v.); same as modern rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप्य|रूप्यं<BR>rūpya, same as rūpaka or rūpyaka (q. v.); same as modern<BR>rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाहणिकाटि<BR>śāhaṇikāṭi, supposed to be the name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शलागै<BR>śalāgai, Tamil; name of a coin also called paḻañśalāgai<BR>(accu); probably had the shape of a śalākā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शलाका<BR>śalākā, same as Tamil śalāgai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बिरणिप्पलङ्गाशु<BR>sambiraṇippalaṅ-gāśu, see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाण|शाणं|शाणः<BR>śāṇa, name of a weight or a coin 40 ratis in weight; equal<BR>to 4 māṣas; sometimes regarded as 32 ratis and called niṣka and<BR>ṭaṅka; rarely also regarded as equal to 24 or 20 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानपाद|शानपादः<BR>śāna-pāda, same as māṣa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानक<BR>śānaka, same as śāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्षप|सर्षपः<BR>sarṣapa, sometimes called ‘red sarṣapa’; a small unit of<BR>measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाशुकानि<BR>śāśukāni, also called śāśukāni-ṭaṅka; same as ŞaŞghānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाशुकानिटङ्क<BR>śāśukāni-ṭaṅka, same as śāśukāni or ŞaŞghāṇī.<BR>ŞaŞghānī, Tughluk coin, 4 jītals in weight and value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतमान|शतमानः<BR>śatamāna, the weight of 320 ratis; literally, ‘a hundred<BR>units of measurement’, the unit probably being the mañjāḍi (q. v.);<BR>also called pala and niṣka (320 ratis of gold or silver);<BR>during the medieval period, sometimes regarded as 160 ratis;<BR>name sometimes applied to an ancient gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतेर|सतेरः<BR>satera, also spelt sateraka; probably the same as Greek<BR>stater; regarded as equal to 2 dīnāras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतेरक<BR>sateraka, same as satera (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्ण|सौवर्णं<BR>sauvarṇa, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेनपकक्कुलिगै<BR>śenapaka-kkuḻigai, see kuḻigai, gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिग्लोस्<BR>siglos, name of the silver coin (86.45 grains) of ancient<BR>Irān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिन्न<BR>sinna, same as cinna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षोडशी<BR>ṣoḍaśī, also called ṣoḍaśikā; probably, one-sixteenth of<BR>the standard silver coin in weight or value; cf. paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोडशिका<BR>soḍaśikā, same as ṣoḍaśī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शो<BR>śol13iya-kkāśu, ‘the Col13a kāśu (copper coin)’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेष्ठिजीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय<BR>śreṣṭhi-jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya, probably a mistake for jīrṇa-<BR>śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya, ‘old coin minted by Śreṣṭhin Viśvamalla’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमदादिवराहद्रम्म<BR>śrīmad-ādivarāha-dramma, ‘dramma issued by śrīmad-Ādivarāha’;<BR>cf. ādivarāha-dramma; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीयक्किपलञ्शलागै<BR>śrī-yakki-paḻañ-śalāgai, cf. yakki-accu, paḻañ-śalāgai, śalākā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्ततेर्<BR>stater, Greek silver and gold coin; silver stater was<BR>also called tetradrachma; gold stater had the same weight as Persian<BR>double daric (265 grains).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुक्ति|शुक्तिः<BR>śukti, same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरभिमाड<BR>surabhi-māḍa, probably, ‘māḍa bearing the figure of a<BR>cow’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्ण|सुवर्णं|सुवर्णः|सुवर्ण्ण<BR>suvarṇa, weight of 16 māṣas or 80 ratis (about 146 grains);<BR>16 kārṣāpaṇas or rūpakas or 48 paṇas according to different<BR>authorities; called picu, pāṇi, kroḍa, binduka, viḍālapadaka,<BR>haṃsapada, grāsagraha and tola; also called niṣka; (1/4) of pala; gold<BR>coin weighing 80 ratis; name applied to Tamil kal13añju (about<BR>32 ratis or 58 grains theoretically).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णगद्याण<BR>suvarṇa-gadyāṇa, ‘gold gadyāṇa’; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाका<BR>ṭākā, modern Bengali form of ṭaṇkā (from ṭaṅkaka); silver<BR>coin; money; written in old Bengali as taṅkā; see ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टं|ट|टः<BR>ṭaṃ, abbreviation of ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डुल|तंडुल|तंडुलः|तण्डुलः<BR>taṇḍula, (1/2) of a dhānya-māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताङ्क्<BR>tāṅk, also called tāṅkī; same as ṭanka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्क|टंक|टंकं|टंकः|टङ्कः<BR>ṭaṅka, a coin in general; a silver coin (often one tola in<BR>weight); same as śāna; equal to 4 silver fanams, silver coin<BR>of the Delhi Suḻtāns, 96 or 100 ratis in weight; same as aṭha-<BR>gānī (q. v.); a small copper coin; (1/2) of a rupee. There were<BR>gold and copper taṅkas; see hema-ṭaṅka and raupya-ṭaṅka. Cf.<BR>ṭāṅk, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कक|टंकक|टंककः|टङ्ककः<BR>ṭaṅkaka, same as ṭaṅka (q. v.); name of a silver coin; some-<BR>times mentioned as bearing the figure of the Bhagavat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाङ्की<BR>ṭāṅkī, same as ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तार्<BR>tār, name of a silver coin, equal to (1/6) of a gold fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेत्रद्रछ्म<BR>tetradrachma, ‘four-drachma’; quadruple drachma; see drachma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरम<BR>tirama, Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोल|तोलं|तोलः<BR>tola, also spelt tolaka; 80 ratis in weight; same as suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोलक|तोलकं<BR>tolaka, same as kola or tola; 80 ratis in weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिशूलकाशु<BR>triśūla-kāśu, probably, ‘kāśu bearing the representation<BR>of a trident’; possibly issued by the authorities of a Śiva temple;<BR>see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलैप्पोन्<BR>tuḻai-ppon, Tamil; ‘correct weight’ or ‘good current coin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरैमि<BR>turai-miṉṉar-pon, a kind of pon (i. e. hon, gadyāṇa or varāha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उण्डिअच्चु<BR>uṇḍi-accu, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उप्पुक्काशु<BR>uppu-kkāśu, ‘salt money’; name of a tax; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्कलञ्जू<BR>ūr-kaḻañjū, see kal13añju.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्काशु<BR>ūr-kāśu, see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमगण्डमाड<BR>uttama-gaṇḍa-māḍa, probably ‘good (i. e. new) gaṇḍamāḍa’<BR>or ‘gaṇḍa-māḍa issued by king Uttama (i. e. Uttama-col13a,<BR>980-85 A. D.); see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वगैन्दकाशु<BR>vagainda-kāśu, name of a tax; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्<BR>val, sometimes regarded as (1/20) of a gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्ल|वल्लः<BR>valla, equal to 3 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलाल्व<BR>vaḻāl-val13i-tiṟantāṉ-guḻikai, Pāṇḍya coin supposed to be<BR>issued by Jaṭāvarman Sundara-pāṇḍya I; see gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलुदियच्चुवर्गम्<BR>vaḻudiy-accu-vargam, see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराह|वराहः<BR>varāha, a gold coin; same as hūn or hon (q. v.); also called<BR>pagoda (q. v.) or ‘star pagoda’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहगद्याण<BR>varāha-gadyāṇa, same as varāha (q. v.), gadyāṇa or pagoda<BR>(q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहपणम्<BR>varāha-paṇam, probably ‘money calculated in varāha (q. v.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहविंशोपक<BR>varāha-viṃśopaka, (1/20) of a varāha; see varāha and viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहन्पुल्लिकुलिगै<BR>varāhan-puḻḻi-kuḻigai, see varāha and gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराटका<BR>varāṭakā, same as varāṭaka or varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराटिका<BR>varāṭikā, cowrie-shell used as a coin; money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्पणम्<BR>vāśal-paṇam, ‘door-tax’; periodical payment due to the<BR>palace; same as vāśal-tiramam; see paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्तिरमम्<BR>vāśal-tiramam, ‘door-tax’; same as vāśal-paṇam; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वटक|वटकः<BR>vaṭaka, same as draṃkṣaṇa or tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेल्लि|वेल्लिः<BR>veḻḻi, name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिक्काशु<BR>veli-kkāśu, same as veli-ppayaṟu; name of a tax; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिप्पयरु<BR>veli-ppayaṟu, same as veli-kkāśu (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडालपदक|विडालपदकं<BR>viḍālapadaka, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहद्रम्म<BR>vigraha-dramma, ‘dramma issued or minted by Vigraha’;<BR>same as vigrahapāla-dramma, etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहद्रम्मविस्वोवक<BR>vigraha-dramma-visvovaka, ‘(1/20) of the vigraha-dramma’; see<BR>dramma and viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालद्रम्म<BR>vigrahapāla-dramma, ‘dramma issued or minted by Vigraha-<BR>pāla’; same as vigraha-dramma (q. v.), etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालसत्कद्रम्म<BR>vigrahapāla-satka-dramma, same as vigrahapāla-dramma (q. v.),<BR>etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालीयद्रम्म<BR>vigrahapālīya-dramma, ‘dramma issued or minted by Vigra-<BR>hapāla’; same as vigraha-dramma (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहतुङ्गीयद्रम्म<BR>vigrahatuṅgīya-dramma, ‘dramma issued or minted by<BR>Vigrahatuṅga’; cf. vigraha-dramma, etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयराजटङ्क<BR>vijayarāja-ṭaṅka, ‘ṭaṅka issued by Vijayarāja’; see ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विल्पणम्<BR>vil-paṇam, ‘sales tax’, or ‘tax on bows or archery’; see<BR>paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशतिक|विंशतिकः<BR>viṃśatika, regarded as equal to 20 māṣas; cf. viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंसोपक<BR>viṃsopaka, corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशोपक<BR>viṃśopaka, (1/20) of the standard silver coin of about 20 ratis;<BR>same as visvovaka, visopaka, vīsovā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरचम्पन्गुलिगै<BR>vīracampan-guḻigai, gulikā of the Śambhuvarāya king<BR>Vīracampa; see gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरपञ्चालन्काशु<BR>vīrapañcālan-kāśu, see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसलप्रियद्रम्म<BR>vīsala-priya-dramma, also called vīsala-prī-dramma; cf. jīrṇa-<BR>viśvamalla-priya, Vīsala being the same as Viśvamalla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसोपक<BR>visopaka, corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसोवा<BR>vīsovā, corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विस्वोवक<BR>visvovaka, corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोडी<BR>voḍī, also called voḍikā and voḍrī; sometimes regarded as a<BR>cowrie-shell used as coin; but really, the unit equal to 5 gaṇḍās<BR>= 20 cowries. Cf. buḏī, kapardaka-voḍī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोडिका<BR>voḍikā, same as voḍī. Cf. buḏī and kapardaka-voḍī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोड्री<BR>voḍrī, same as voḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृषविंशोपक<BR>vṛṣa-viṃśopaka, ‘a viṃśopaka bearing the figure of a bull’;<BR>see viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यादवरायन्पणम्<BR>yādavarāyan-paṇam, ‘coin issued by the Yādavarāyas’; see<BR>paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यक्किअच्चु<BR>yakki-accu, ‘accu bearing the figure of a Yakṣī (a village<BR>goddess)’; see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यव|यवः<BR>yava, (1/15) of māṣa; (1/3) of rati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

